WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:19.320
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:25.679
Book 11, The Lost Continent, read by

00:00:25.679 --> 00:00:27.000
Shannon McManus.

00:00:45.060 --> 00:00:51.060
The Lost Continent Prophecy.

00:00:51.119 --> 00:00:57.060
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, to

00:00:57.060 --> 00:01:00.420
the land across the sea, where dragons

00:01:00.420 --> 00:01:03.780
are poisoned and dragons are dying, and

00:01:03.780 --> 00:01:05.400
no one can ever be free.

00:01:05.459 --> 00:01:09.179
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:01:09.239 --> 00:01:11.400
A secret hides within their book.

00:01:11.459 --> 00:01:16.560
A secret buried far below may save those

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:17.579
brave enough to look.

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:22.379
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

00:01:22.379 --> 00:01:25.079
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:29.459
Face a great evil with talons united.

00:01:29.519 --> 00:01:32.579
Or none of the tribes will survive.

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:49.739
Prologue.

00:01:49.859 --> 00:01:52.799
About 2,000 years ago.

00:01:52.859 --> 00:01:56.519
If you are flying directly into a

00:01:56.519 --> 00:01:59.340
hurricane, it is probably useful to be a

00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:00.480
dragon who can see the future.

00:02:00.599 --> 00:02:04.920
Then again, if you are a dragon who can

00:02:04.920 --> 00:02:07.560
see the future, you are most likely far

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:09.300
too smart to fly directly into a

00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:09.960
hurricane.

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:13.560
And yet, according to clear site's

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:15.780
visions, that was exactly what she needed

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:16.259
to do.

00:02:16.319 --> 00:02:20.699
She shook out her black wings, which were

00:02:20.699 --> 00:02:22.800
already tired from how far she'd flown

00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:24.840
all morning and the day before.

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:28.199
Her talons clung to the slippery, wet

00:02:28.199 --> 00:02:28.979
rock below her.

00:02:29.039 --> 00:02:32.759
Her scales felt itchy with salt from the

00:02:32.759 --> 00:02:33.719
ocean spray.

00:02:33.780 --> 00:02:37.080
Above her, the sun peeked wearily through

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:39.000
cracks in the dull gray clouds.

00:02:39.120 --> 00:02:42.780
She closed her eyes, tracing the future

00:02:42.780 --> 00:02:43.919
paths ahead of her.

00:02:43.979 --> 00:02:48.000
In one direction, south, and a little

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.699
east, there was a small island with a

00:02:50.699 --> 00:02:51.960
warm, sandy beach.

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:55.199
Two coconut palms nodded toward each

00:02:55.199 --> 00:02:57.780
other, and there were lazy tiger sharks

00:02:57.780 --> 00:02:58.139
to eat.

00:02:58.199 --> 00:03:00.539
The hurricane would pass it by

00:03:00.539 --> 00:03:00.960
completely.

00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:04.860
If she went there, Clearsight could rest

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:06.900
eat, and sleep in safety.

00:03:06.960 --> 00:03:10.319
Then she could continue on in 2 days

00:03:10.319 --> 00:03:12.120
after the storm was over.

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:14.639
But in the other direction.

00:03:14.699 --> 00:03:19.259
A long flight west and slightly north, the

00:03:19.259 --> 00:03:20.879
lost continent was waiting for her.

00:03:20.939 --> 00:03:23.819
She knew it was real now.

00:03:23.879 --> 00:03:26.939
When she'd left Pyria to find it.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.340
She'd half expected to fly all the way

00:03:29.340 --> 00:03:32.039
around the world, and end up back on

00:03:32.039 --> 00:03:33.300
Pyria's other post.

00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:36.599
No one was sure another continent even

00:03:36.599 --> 00:03:37.139
existed.

00:03:37.199 --> 00:03:40.680
And if it did, everyone knew it was too

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:41.759
far away to fly to.

00:03:41.819 --> 00:03:45.599
Any dragon would tire, fall into the sea

00:03:45.599 --> 00:03:47.039
and drown before reaching it.

00:03:47.099 --> 00:03:50.639
But clear sight wasn't any dragon.

00:03:50.699 --> 00:03:53.340
She had something no one else did.

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:56.939
The ability to carefully trace the paths

00:03:56.939 --> 00:03:58.620
of multiple possible futures.

00:03:58.680 --> 00:04:01.979
Standing on the edge of Pyria.

00:04:02.039 --> 00:04:03.840
She could see which direction would take

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:05.819
her to an island where she could rest.

00:04:05.879 --> 00:04:08.340
And then the next day, to another

00:04:08.340 --> 00:04:08.639
island.

00:04:08.699 --> 00:04:11.819
Shifting her course slightly each day

00:04:11.819 --> 00:04:15.060
guided by her visions, she had found a

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:17.459
trail of small islands to take her safely

00:04:17.459 --> 00:04:18.120
across the ocean.

00:04:18.180 --> 00:04:21.360
A gust of wind roared over her

00:04:21.360 --> 00:04:23.759
splattering a handful of raindrops onto

00:04:23.759 --> 00:04:24.180
her head.

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:27.000
The hurricane was almost upon her.

00:04:27.120 --> 00:04:30.720
If she didn't leave right now, dragons on

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:31.980
the lost continent would die.

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.459
Dragons who might one day be her friends

00:04:35.459 --> 00:04:36.839
if she saved them.

00:04:36.899 --> 00:04:40.139
Dragons who had no idea what was bearing

00:04:40.139 --> 00:04:42.480
down on them, because there was no one

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:43.259
there to warn them.

00:04:43.379 --> 00:04:44.639
Yet.

00:04:44.759 --> 00:04:48.660
Clearsight took a deep breath, vaulted

00:04:48.660 --> 00:04:50.939
into the sky, and pointed herself west.

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.480
Her mind immediately started flashing

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:56.279
through all the ways she could die in the

00:04:56.279 --> 00:04:56.939
next 2 days.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.480
This was why she hated flying in storms.

00:05:00.540 --> 00:05:02.339
They were too unpredictable.

00:05:02.399 --> 00:05:05.459
The smallest twitch of the wind in the

00:05:05.459 --> 00:05:07.379
wrong direction, could send her

00:05:07.379 --> 00:05:10.139
plummeting to the rocks below, or drive a

00:05:10.139 --> 00:05:11.759
stray palm branch into her heart.

00:05:11.819 --> 00:05:13.920
Don't think about that.

00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:16.500
Think about the dragons who need you.

00:05:16.560 --> 00:05:19.199
The other vision was fading.

00:05:19.259 --> 00:05:21.899
The one where she flew southeast and

00:05:21.899 --> 00:05:22.620
hid.

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.560
In that one, she'd arrived on the lost

00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:27.600
continent in the hurricane's aftermath.

00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:30.480
The images of the devastation and dead

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:32.879
bodies would be hard to shake off, even

00:05:32.879 --> 00:05:34.379
if she prevented them in reality.

00:05:34.439 --> 00:05:36.300
Will they believe me?

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:38.339
Will they listen to me?

00:05:38.399 --> 00:05:41.160
In some of her visions, they did.

00:05:41.220 --> 00:05:43.860
In some, they didn't.

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:47.100
All she could do was fly her hardest and

00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:47.519
hope.

00:05:47.579 --> 00:05:50.819
The hurricane fought her at every wing

00:05:50.819 --> 00:05:53.579
beat, as if it knew she was trying to

00:05:53.579 --> 00:05:55.319
snatch victims from its claws.

00:05:55.379 --> 00:05:58.319
Rain battered her ferociously.

00:05:58.379 --> 00:06:01.019
She felt like she'd be driven into the

00:06:01.019 --> 00:06:02.220
endless sea at any moment.

00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:06.360
Or maybe she'd drown up here in the water

00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:07.139
logged sky.

00:06:07.259 --> 00:06:10.860
But this was only the outer edge of the

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:11.160
storm.

00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:13.980
There was far worse still to come.

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:16.920
Clear sight was trying to reach land

00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:19.920
before the really terrible fury behind

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:20.459
her did.

00:06:20.519 --> 00:06:23.639
She couldn't stop, couldn't slow down for

00:06:23.639 --> 00:06:24.120
a moment.

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:28.439
At one point, she glanced back and saw a

00:06:28.439 --> 00:06:30.060
spout of water sucked into the air.

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:33.600
In the middle of it, an orca flailed

00:06:33.600 --> 00:06:36.180
desperately, before the storm flung it

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:36.420
away.

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:38.459
A while later.

00:06:38.579 --> 00:06:41.040
After the sun had apparently been

00:06:41.040 --> 00:06:43.980
swallowed for good, Clearsight saw an

00:06:43.980 --> 00:06:46.620
entire hut fly by her, then splinter

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:47.100
apart.

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:49.980
She had to duck quickly to a lower air

00:06:49.980 --> 00:06:51.420
current to avoid the debris.

00:06:51.480 --> 00:06:53.220
Where had it come from?

00:06:53.279 --> 00:06:54.899
Who had lived in it?

00:06:54.959 --> 00:06:57.959
She would never know, her visions told

00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:58.199
her.

00:06:58.259 --> 00:07:02.100
And then, when Clearside was beginning to

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:04.980
lose all feeling in her wings, she saw a

00:07:04.980 --> 00:07:07.860
shape loom out of the clouds ahead, a

00:07:07.860 --> 00:07:08.279
cliff.

00:07:08.339 --> 00:07:09.420
Land.

00:07:09.480 --> 00:07:10.920
A lot of land.

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:15.420
A whole continent, in fact, She canted

00:07:15.420 --> 00:07:17.519
her wings and soared toward the top of it

00:07:17.579 --> 00:07:19.920
where she could see a never ending line

00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:22.199
of trees tossing violently in the wind.

00:07:22.259 --> 00:07:25.079
The hurricane made one more effort to

00:07:25.079 --> 00:07:27.420
throw her back into the sea, but she

00:07:27.420 --> 00:07:30.180
fought with her last reserves until she

00:07:30.180 --> 00:07:31.620
felt earth beneath her talons.

00:07:31.680 --> 00:07:35.339
She collapsed forward, clutching the wet

00:07:35.339 --> 00:07:36.240
soil for a moment.

00:07:36.300 --> 00:07:38.100
Grateful to be alive.

00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:40.439
Keep going.

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:42.240
They're not safe yet.

00:07:42.300 --> 00:07:45.360
Clearsight pushed herself up and faced

00:07:45.360 --> 00:07:45.779
the trees.

00:07:45.899 --> 00:07:47.399
They were coming.

00:07:47.459 --> 00:07:50.819
The 1st 2 dragons she would meet in this

00:07:50.819 --> 00:07:51.839
strange new world.

00:07:51.899 --> 00:07:55.560
What would it be like to face unfamiliar

00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:57.959
tribes, completely different from the

00:07:57.959 --> 00:07:58.620
ones she knew.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:01.740
There wouldn't be any night wings like

00:08:01.740 --> 00:08:02.160
her here.

00:08:02.220 --> 00:08:06.839
No sand dragons, no sea dragons, no ice

00:08:06.839 --> 00:08:07.740
dragons.

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:10.620
She'd glimpsed what these new dragons

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:11.519
would look like.

00:08:11.639 --> 00:08:13.620
But she didn't know anything yet about

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:14.339
their tribes.

00:08:14.399 --> 00:08:16.620
Or whether they would trust her.

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:20.639
They stepped out of the trees, eyeing her

00:08:20.639 --> 00:08:21.779
with wary curiosity.

00:08:21.899 --> 00:08:26.100
Oh, they're beautiful, she thought.

00:08:26.160 --> 00:08:29.100
One was dark forest green.

00:08:29.220 --> 00:08:31.500
The color of the trees all around them.

00:08:31.560 --> 00:08:34.980
His wings curved gracefully, like long

00:08:34.980 --> 00:08:37.379
leaves on either side of him, and

00:08:37.379 --> 00:08:39.779
mahogany brown underscales glinted from

00:08:39.779 --> 00:08:40.200
his chest.

00:08:40.259 --> 00:08:43.080
But it was the other who took clear

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:44.039
sight's breath away.

00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:48.000
His scales were iridescent gold, layered

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:50.879
over metallic rose and blue, shimmering

00:08:50.879 --> 00:08:51.299
through the rain.

00:08:51.360 --> 00:08:54.840
He outshone even the rain wings she'd

00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:57.299
occasionally seen in the marketplace, and

00:08:57.299 --> 00:08:59.159
those were the most beautiful dragons in

00:08:59.159 --> 00:08:59.639
Pyria.

00:08:59.759 --> 00:09:03.419
Not only that, but his wings were

00:09:03.419 --> 00:09:04.320
startlingly weird.

00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:06.899
There were 4 of them instead of two.

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:10.019
A 2nd pair at the back overlapped the

00:09:10.019 --> 00:09:12.600
front ones, tilting and dipping at

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.279
slightly different angles from the 1st

00:09:14.279 --> 00:09:17.159
pair to give the dragon extra agility in

00:09:17.159 --> 00:09:17.399
the air.

00:09:17.460 --> 00:09:21.240
Like dragonflies, she realized.

00:09:21.299 --> 00:09:24.299
Remembering the delicate insects darting

00:09:24.299 --> 00:09:25.620
across the ponds in the mountain

00:09:25.620 --> 00:09:26.100
meadows.

00:09:26.159 --> 00:09:29.279
Well, butterflies, or beetles.

00:09:29.399 --> 00:09:32.580
She sat up and spread her front talons to

00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:33.419
show that she was harmless.

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:35.159
Hello?

00:09:35.220 --> 00:09:38.100
She said, in her very least threatening

00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:38.340
voice.

00:09:38.399 --> 00:09:41.399
The green one circled her slowly.

00:09:41.460 --> 00:09:45.000
The iridescent one sat down and gave her

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:45.600
a small smile.

00:09:45.720 --> 00:09:49.200
She smiled back, although her heart was

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:49.620
pounding.

00:09:49.679 --> 00:09:52.620
She knew she had to wait for them to make

00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:57.840
the 1st move. said the green dragon

00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:01.080
finally, in a deep, calm voice, way

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:01.559
root.

00:10:01.679 --> 00:10:03.360
Take a breath.

00:10:03.419 --> 00:10:05.759
You knew it would be like this at first.

00:10:05.820 --> 00:10:10.440
My name is Clearsight, she said, touching

00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:10.919
her forehead.

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:13.620
I am from far over the sea.

00:10:13.679 --> 00:10:16.440
She pointed at the turning ocean

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:18.120
stretching way off to the east behind

00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:18.419
her.

00:10:18.480 --> 00:10:21.000
Anyone speak dragon?

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:24.419
The 2 strangers exchanged surprised

00:10:24.419 --> 00:10:24.960
glances.

00:10:25.019 --> 00:10:29.580
The old language, said the shimmering

00:10:29.580 --> 00:10:32.639
dragon, awkwardly and slowly, as if

00:10:32.639 --> 00:10:34.620
pulling the words from his memory bit by

00:10:34.620 --> 00:10:34.860
bit.

00:10:34.919 --> 00:10:39.179
You do know it, Clearsight said, hope

00:10:39.179 --> 00:10:40.259
darting through her veins.

00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:43.500
Some little, he said.

00:10:43.559 --> 00:10:46.919
Much old, he smiled again.

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:49.980
The green dragon said something in their

00:10:49.980 --> 00:10:52.259
own language and nodded at the ocean.

00:10:52.320 --> 00:10:54.659
The other answered, and they spoke for a

00:10:54.659 --> 00:10:55.019
few moments.

00:10:55.139 --> 00:10:58.139
If they had been a pair of night wings

00:10:58.139 --> 00:10:59.940
Clearsight would have guessed they were

00:10:59.940 --> 00:11:02.460
arguing, but their tone was so peaceful

00:11:02.460 --> 00:11:03.659
that she couldn't really tell.

00:11:03.659 --> 00:11:06.179
The old language.

00:11:06.240 --> 00:11:09.000
I wonder if their continent in ours had

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:10.019
more contact in the past.

00:11:10.139 --> 00:11:12.720
Maybe we will again in the future.

00:11:12.779 --> 00:11:16.679
I could teach them all dragon. especially

00:11:16.679 --> 00:11:17.820
if some of them already know it.

00:11:17.940 --> 00:11:20.879
That way, if any more Pyreans ever come

00:11:20.879 --> 00:11:22.980
this way, they could communicate.

00:11:23.039 --> 00:11:26.460
It was hard to imagine other dragons

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:28.440
making the journey she'd just made

00:11:28.440 --> 00:11:28.620
though.

00:11:28.740 --> 00:11:32.940
It was so far, and depended on finding

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:35.340
those small islands in such a vast sea.

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:38.100
But maybe she could help with that.

00:11:38.159 --> 00:11:39.960
Not soon, though.

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:43.259
Not while I feel any temptation to wake

00:11:43.259 --> 00:11:44.039
dark stalker.

00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:47.039
I can't go back to Pyria until I have

00:11:47.039 --> 00:11:47.460
forgotten him.

00:11:47.519 --> 00:11:50.519
So, probably never.

00:11:50.580 --> 00:11:54.179
Why are you here down?

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:56.340
The gold pink Dragon asked her.

00:11:56.399 --> 00:12:00.419
There's a really bad storm coming, she

00:12:00.419 --> 00:12:02.279
said, as clearly as she could.

00:12:02.340 --> 00:12:03.840
Very bad.

00:12:03.960 --> 00:12:07.860
He spread his wings and looked up, smiling

00:12:07.860 --> 00:12:09.000
into the raindrops.

00:12:09.059 --> 00:12:12.779
See that, he said with a shrug.

00:12:12.899 --> 00:12:15.600
No, she shook her head.

00:12:15.659 --> 00:12:18.059
I see.

00:12:18.179 --> 00:12:19.860
She pointed to her head.

00:12:19.919 --> 00:12:21.960
I see the future.

00:12:22.019 --> 00:12:24.899
Tomorrow and tomorrow and the next day.

00:12:25.019 --> 00:12:26.279
I see all the days.

00:12:26.399 --> 00:12:29.159
This storm kills many dragons.

00:12:29.220 --> 00:12:31.919
She waved her talons at the dripping

00:12:31.919 --> 00:12:35.820
forest around them, rips up many, many

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:36.539
trees.

00:12:36.659 --> 00:12:39.360
Both dragons were frowning now.

00:12:39.419 --> 00:12:43.980
Tree harm, growled the green dragon.

00:12:44.039 --> 00:12:46.500
Twig Hard Lot Splinter Fall.

00:12:46.559 --> 00:12:50.279
But you can save them, Clear sight

00:12:50.279 --> 00:12:50.820
pressed on.

00:12:50.879 --> 00:12:53.639
The visions were crowding into her head.

00:12:53.700 --> 00:12:55.740
She was running out of time.

00:12:55.799 --> 00:12:58.200
She couldn't be diplomatic and patient

00:12:58.200 --> 00:12:58.799
any longer.

00:12:58.860 --> 00:13:01.500
We have to move everyone.

00:13:01.559 --> 00:13:05.580
All dragons, far, far, far inland, as far

00:13:05.580 --> 00:13:08.399
as they can fly right now, and wait there

00:13:08.399 --> 00:13:09.419
until the storm is over.

00:13:09.480 --> 00:13:12.659
She turned to the metallic dragon.

00:13:12.720 --> 00:13:15.120
Her talons clasped together.

00:13:15.179 --> 00:13:17.940
Please, save them.

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.580
The moment teetered.

00:13:20.639 --> 00:13:23.399
Two paths waveringly possible.

00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:27.179
Finally, the shimmering dragon nodded.

00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:28.919
Move all.

00:13:28.980 --> 00:13:30.539
We will do.

00:13:30.659 --> 00:13:33.299
He said something in their language to

00:13:33.299 --> 00:13:35.340
the green dragon, who nodded as well.

00:13:35.399 --> 00:13:38.639
The relief hit clear sight so hard.

00:13:38.700 --> 00:13:40.740
She nearly had to lie down again.

00:13:40.799 --> 00:13:43.620
But the dragons beckoned her to follow

00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:46.500
them, and they all took off, flying

00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:48.179
cautiously through the storm tossed

00:13:48.179 --> 00:13:48.840
treetops.

00:13:48.899 --> 00:13:52.379
Dragons appeared between the leaves as

00:13:52.379 --> 00:13:54.059
she swept through the forest with her 2

00:13:54.059 --> 00:13:56.820
companions, all of them watching her with

00:13:56.820 --> 00:13:57.779
startled curiosity.

00:13:57.840 --> 00:14:01.500
Most of them were dark green and brown

00:14:01.500 --> 00:14:02.759
with leaf shaped wings.

00:14:02.820 --> 00:14:06.299
That's their name and dragon, she

00:14:06.299 --> 00:14:08.940
realized from a new cascade of visions.

00:14:09.059 --> 00:14:10.500
Leaf wings.

00:14:10.559 --> 00:14:13.379
But about a quarter of them were the

00:14:13.379 --> 00:14:14.039
other tribe.

00:14:14.100 --> 00:14:16.559
The one clear site didn't have a name for

00:14:16.559 --> 00:14:19.799
yet, and those glittered like jewels on

00:14:19.799 --> 00:14:20.460
the branches.

00:14:20.519 --> 00:14:24.480
Gold and blue and purple and orange, and

00:14:24.480 --> 00:14:25.919
every color of the rainbow.

00:14:25.980 --> 00:14:29.580
She saw a tiny lavender dragonette

00:14:29.580 --> 00:14:32.100
clinging to a branch, and for a moment

00:14:32.100 --> 00:14:34.679
Clearsight was alarmed to see that she

00:14:34.679 --> 00:14:35.759
didn't have any wings.

00:14:35.820 --> 00:14:38.940
And she spotted little wing buds on the

00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:41.340
dragonette's back and remembered, or

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:45.000
foresaw, or remembered foreseeing, that

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:46.860
the glittering tribe grew their wings a

00:14:46.860 --> 00:14:47.940
few years after hatching.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.159
Growing up wingless.

00:14:50.220 --> 00:14:52.019
That must be so strange.

00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:55.500
Clearside's mind flashed to that other

00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:57.360
vision, the horrible one.

00:14:57.419 --> 00:14:59.879
Where this dragonette had been one of the

00:14:59.879 --> 00:15:01.620
many bodies left in the hurricane

00:15:01.620 --> 00:15:02.220
wreckage.

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:05.700
But instead, Tomorrow the little dragon

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:07.620
would wake up and chase butterflies in

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:09.899
the sunlight, complaining that she wanted

00:15:09.899 --> 00:15:11.159
blackberries for breakfast.

00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:13.259
I saved her.

00:15:13.320 --> 00:15:15.120
I did something right.

00:15:15.179 --> 00:15:18.840
The green dragon called out in a booming

00:15:18.840 --> 00:15:20.399
voice like a bell tolling.

00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:23.700
Whatever he said, the dragons around them

00:15:23.700 --> 00:15:25.559
repeated it, passing it along.

00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:28.500
Clearsight could hear the echoes of other

00:15:28.500 --> 00:15:30.120
dragon voices rolling through the

00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:30.419
forest.

00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:33.360
She felt the drumming wing beats behind

00:15:33.360 --> 00:15:36.299
her as both tribes rose into the air, and

00:15:36.299 --> 00:15:37.259
followed them to safety.

00:15:37.320 --> 00:15:39.779
You save us.

00:15:39.899 --> 00:15:42.960
Said the shimmering dragon, moving around

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:44.580
to fly beside Clearside.

00:15:44.700 --> 00:15:46.080
He smiled at her again.

00:15:46.139 --> 00:15:48.659
You safe now too.

00:15:48.779 --> 00:15:51.659
Maybe I am, she thought.

00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:54.000
I stopped Dark Stalker.

00:15:54.059 --> 00:15:57.600
I saved fathom, and the night wings, and

00:15:57.600 --> 00:15:58.200
my parents.

00:15:58.320 --> 00:16:01.559
And now I found a new home, with new

00:16:01.559 --> 00:16:02.340
dragons to save.

00:16:02.399 --> 00:16:04.860
I can help them with my visions.

00:16:04.919 --> 00:16:07.620
I can do everything right this time.

00:16:07.740 --> 00:16:10.620
New futures exploded in her mind.

00:16:10.679 --> 00:16:14.159
She might marry this kind, funny dragon

00:16:14.159 --> 00:16:16.019
whose name would turn out to be sun

00:16:16.019 --> 00:16:16.559
streak.

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:19.440
Or she could end up with a dragon she'd

00:16:19.440 --> 00:16:21.600
meet in 3 days while helping to clean up

00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:24.480
the forest. whose gentle green eyes were

00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:25.980
nothing like dark stalkers.

00:16:26.039 --> 00:16:29.159
She could move in with an affable, very

00:16:29.159 --> 00:16:32.340
old leaf wing named Maple, who spoke the

00:16:32.340 --> 00:16:34.860
old language, or she could find her own

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:37.139
tree hollow to live in, or she could

00:16:37.139 --> 00:16:39.419
explore the new continent first, then

00:16:39.419 --> 00:16:40.799
come back here to build a home.

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:44.340
And there would be dragonettes, if she

00:16:44.340 --> 00:16:44.759
wanted them.

00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:48.659
Clearsight felt a sudden, dizzying rush

00:16:48.659 --> 00:16:50.879
of love for dragons who weren't even eggs

00:16:50.879 --> 00:16:54.120
yet, little Jewel, and whip smart

00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:56.580
tortoiseshell, and cuddly orange.

00:16:56.639 --> 00:16:59.100
Who names their dragonette orange?

00:16:59.220 --> 00:17:01.379
Sunstreak apparently.

00:17:01.440 --> 00:17:03.299
They might have to have some

00:17:03.299 --> 00:17:04.680
conversations about that plan.

00:17:04.799 --> 00:17:08.279
And Commodore, the king of giggles.

00:17:08.339 --> 00:17:11.759
She would always miss the dragonette she

00:17:11.759 --> 00:17:13.379
should have had with Dark Stalker.

00:17:13.440 --> 00:17:15.660
But she would love the ones that were

00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:18.240
coming with all her heart, and nothing

00:17:18.240 --> 00:17:21.359
bad would ever, ever. happened to them.

00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:24.660
They would all live the longest happiest

00:17:24.660 --> 00:17:27.960
lives because she would be here, tracking

00:17:27.960 --> 00:17:29.759
their paths, keeping them safe.

00:17:29.819 --> 00:17:32.339
She would get it right this time.

00:17:32.400 --> 00:17:35.099
Your root place.

00:17:35.160 --> 00:17:38.339
Sunstreak said, gently interrupting her

00:17:38.339 --> 00:17:38.640
thoughts.

00:17:38.700 --> 00:17:40.200
Where?

00:17:40.259 --> 00:17:42.720
She pointed back out to sea.

00:17:42.779 --> 00:17:44.880
Pyria.

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:47.339
She waved her claws at the continent

00:17:47.339 --> 00:17:47.819
around them.

00:17:47.880 --> 00:17:49.259
This?

00:17:49.259 --> 00:17:50.400
Where?

00:17:50.460 --> 00:17:51.299
She asked.

00:17:51.420 --> 00:17:53.099
He smiled again.

00:17:53.160 --> 00:17:58.799
Pantala, he said slowly and clearly, and

00:17:58.799 --> 00:17:59.759
with evident pride.

00:17:59.819 --> 00:18:03.480
Pantala, she echoed back.

00:18:03.539 --> 00:18:06.180
The lost continent is real.

00:18:06.240 --> 00:18:09.839
And it has a name, and it's my home now.

00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:13.740
Pantala, here I am.

00:18:13.799 --> 00:18:18.299
Part one.

00:18:18.359 --> 00:18:23.039
In the cocoon. 2000 years later.

00:18:23.099 --> 00:18:24.900
Chapter one.

00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:28.559
Blue was a dragon who liked things the

00:18:28.559 --> 00:18:29.099
way they were.

00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:32.640
That is, if he didn't exactly like

00:18:32.640 --> 00:18:35.700
everything about live as a silk wing, he

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:37.619
had to admit that at least he was safe.

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:41.460
And you know, things were fine, really, it

00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:42.180
wasn't perfect.

00:18:42.240 --> 00:18:45.180
But at least his tribe and the hive wings

00:18:45.180 --> 00:18:46.559
coexisted peacefully.

00:18:46.619 --> 00:18:49.319
The hive wings protected them from

00:18:49.319 --> 00:18:52.319
outside threats, and everyone followed

00:18:52.319 --> 00:18:54.359
the rules, and the hives were beautiful

00:18:54.359 --> 00:18:56.940
and spotless, and there were always

00:18:56.940 --> 00:18:58.859
enough yams and okra to eat.

00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:01.680
So wasn't that the kind of world everyone

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:02.519
wanted to live in?

00:19:02.579 --> 00:19:05.640
Blue wasn't sure how everyone else felt.

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:08.220
But he wondered about it all the time.

00:19:08.279 --> 00:19:10.920
He often tried to imagine himself as

00:19:10.920 --> 00:19:12.059
other dragons.

00:19:12.119 --> 00:19:14.519
Were they all as content as he was?

00:19:14.579 --> 00:19:16.740
Or was he luckier than most?

00:19:16.799 --> 00:19:19.740
Did they want the same things he did?

00:19:19.799 --> 00:19:21.599
What did they worry about?

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:23.700
What did they hope for?

00:19:23.759 --> 00:19:25.859
If they seemed unhappy?

00:19:25.920 --> 00:19:27.420
Why was that?

00:19:27.480 --> 00:19:31.619
His guesses were probably mostly wrong, he

00:19:31.619 --> 00:19:31.980
was sure.

00:19:32.039 --> 00:19:34.140
But Blue couldn't stop thinking about

00:19:34.140 --> 00:19:34.319
it.

00:19:34.380 --> 00:19:37.380
It felt like a constant tugging on his

00:19:37.380 --> 00:19:37.980
imagination.

00:19:38.039 --> 00:19:41.940
What was the fidgety dragonette next to

00:19:41.940 --> 00:19:44.339
him in math class thinking, while she

00:19:44.339 --> 00:19:46.259
drew hexagons in the margins of her

00:19:46.259 --> 00:19:46.680
test?

00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:49.500
What did their rose pink neighbor worry

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:49.740
about?

00:19:49.799 --> 00:19:52.140
While he cleaned the dead bugs from his

00:19:52.140 --> 00:19:52.500
webs.

00:19:52.619 --> 00:19:54.900
What about the hive wings?

00:19:54.960 --> 00:19:58.259
How were their lives and hopes, and

00:19:58.259 --> 00:20:00.059
lunches, and morning aches, and

00:20:00.059 --> 00:20:01.980
nightmares different from his?

00:20:02.039 --> 00:20:05.160
The other lives drew him like a flame?

00:20:05.220 --> 00:20:07.680
Or the scent of nectarines?

00:20:07.740 --> 00:20:10.619
He spent the night before his sister's

00:20:10.619 --> 00:20:13.500
metamorphosis as her, winding himself

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.480
deep into the dream of being Luna.

00:20:15.539 --> 00:20:18.359
Perhaps her wing buds had started to

00:20:18.359 --> 00:20:19.799
flutter open as she fell asleep.

00:20:19.859 --> 00:20:23.819
Perhaps she lay awake for a while, gazing

00:20:23.819 --> 00:20:26.640
up at the shrouded stars, thinking of the

00:20:26.640 --> 00:20:28.500
moment she could leap from the top of the

00:20:28.500 --> 00:20:31.079
hive and race the skylarks to the sea.

00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:34.019
He thought she might also be looking

00:20:34.019 --> 00:20:36.299
forward to the moon silk dark she would

00:20:36.299 --> 00:20:38.940
spin herself, and the days of emerald

00:20:38.940 --> 00:20:40.920
tinted sleep inside the cocoon.

00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:44.460
No one could yell at her, or sign her

00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:46.980
extra work while she was in there, growing

00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:47.519
her wings.

00:20:47.519 --> 00:20:51.720
He knew Luna wasn't scared, like he would

00:20:51.720 --> 00:20:54.480
be in 6 days when his own metamorphosis

00:20:54.480 --> 00:20:54.960
time came.

00:20:55.079 --> 00:20:58.500
Luna had always felt ready for life with

00:20:58.500 --> 00:20:59.220
wings.

00:20:59.279 --> 00:21:04.019
Blue was not, and most of all, he was not

00:21:04.019 --> 00:21:06.660
ready for life with her wings, which

00:21:06.660 --> 00:21:07.920
meant everything changing.

00:21:07.980 --> 00:21:11.579
Once she had wings, Luna would be

00:21:11.579 --> 00:21:12.660
assigned to a work order.

00:21:12.720 --> 00:21:15.839
Soon she'd be paired up with whichever

00:21:15.839 --> 00:21:18.059
partner the queen chose for her, and

00:21:18.059 --> 00:21:19.559
given another cell to live in.

00:21:19.619 --> 00:21:22.920
She might even be moved to another hive.

00:21:22.980 --> 00:21:25.019
It was normal.

00:21:25.079 --> 00:21:28.259
It was the way life always was for silk

00:21:28.259 --> 00:21:28.619
wings.

00:21:28.680 --> 00:21:31.140
Everyone had a metamorphosis.

00:21:31.200 --> 00:21:34.140
Everyone had a new life chosen for them.

00:21:34.200 --> 00:21:36.119
Everyone moved on.

00:21:36.180 --> 00:21:39.180
But now that it was happening to his

00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:42.720
family, Blue founded extremely nerve

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:42.720
racking.

00:21:42.779 --> 00:21:46.500
He was already awake when Luna bounded

00:21:46.500 --> 00:21:48.180
across the web and started shaking him

00:21:48.180 --> 00:21:49.799
shortly before dawn.

00:21:49.920 --> 00:21:51.960
He wasn't sure he'd slept at all.

00:21:52.019 --> 00:21:54.779
For a while, he'd been watching the glow

00:21:54.779 --> 00:21:57.420
of tiny lights moving far below them in

00:21:57.420 --> 00:22:00.299
Cicada Hive, imagining himself as one of

00:22:00.299 --> 00:22:02.519
those early rising dragons on their way

00:22:02.519 --> 00:22:04.920
to work, awake before the sun.

00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:08.519
In the distance, he could see hornet hive

00:22:08.519 --> 00:22:11.099
in one direction, and mantas hive in the

00:22:11.099 --> 00:22:11.220
other.

00:22:11.279 --> 00:22:13.619
Although the webs that connected them

00:22:13.619 --> 00:22:15.299
were mostly invisible in the dark.

00:22:15.420 --> 00:22:18.180
He'd never been to any of the other

00:22:18.180 --> 00:22:18.720
hives.

00:22:18.779 --> 00:22:21.180
But he knew they were spread out in a

00:22:21.180 --> 00:22:22.740
wide circle around the plains of

00:22:22.740 --> 00:22:23.400
Pentala.

00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:26.519
The enormous dragon cities rose from the

00:22:26.519 --> 00:22:29.279
grassland and reached for the sky, like

00:22:29.279 --> 00:22:31.859
towering dragon made echoes of the trees

00:22:31.859 --> 00:22:33.299
that used to dominate the land.

00:22:33.359 --> 00:22:37.619
Their roofs arched out like branches, and

00:22:37.619 --> 00:22:40.019
the dense silvery threads of silk wing

00:22:40.019 --> 00:22:42.779
webs created a canopy, tying those

00:22:42.779 --> 00:22:43.559
branches together.

00:22:43.619 --> 00:22:46.859
So even wingless silkwing dragonettes

00:22:46.859 --> 00:22:48.900
could travel between hives far above the

00:22:48.900 --> 00:22:52.319
ground, if they wanted to. and were

00:22:52.319 --> 00:22:52.920
allowed to.

00:22:52.980 --> 00:22:57.119
He yawned and batted Luna's talons away

00:22:57.119 --> 00:22:59.279
pretending he'd been in a deep sleep.

00:22:59.339 --> 00:23:02.759
Dewdrops glittered all across the web

00:23:02.759 --> 00:23:05.220
around and above them, as if it had

00:23:05.220 --> 00:23:06.960
rained tiny diamonds in the night.

00:23:07.019 --> 00:23:10.319
He could see the silk bundled shape of

00:23:10.319 --> 00:23:12.000
Luna's mother on the outer edge of their

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:14.220
cell, still fast asleep.

00:23:14.279 --> 00:23:17.460
His own mother was on a night crew these

00:23:17.460 --> 00:23:19.680
days, and had been gone since midnight.

00:23:19.740 --> 00:23:22.019
It's today.

00:23:22.079 --> 00:23:24.480
It's today, Luna whispered.

00:23:24.539 --> 00:23:27.180
Her pale green tail flipped back and

00:23:27.180 --> 00:23:29.819
forth, sending tremors through the silken

00:23:29.819 --> 00:23:30.240
threads.

00:23:30.299 --> 00:23:33.480
She bounced closer to blue to poke his

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:35.579
shoulder again, and sent his hammock

00:23:35.579 --> 00:23:36.839
rocking perilously.

00:23:37.019 --> 00:23:41.039
Hey, watch it, he teased, nudging her

00:23:41.039 --> 00:23:41.220
away.

00:23:41.279 --> 00:23:43.980
Some of us won't have wings for another 6

00:23:43.980 --> 00:23:44.640
days.

00:23:44.759 --> 00:23:47.759
There were layers and layers of other

00:23:47.759 --> 00:23:50.279
strong webs crisscrossing below his

00:23:50.279 --> 00:23:53.339
family's web, ready to catch any falling

00:23:53.339 --> 00:23:54.119
dragonettes.

00:23:54.180 --> 00:23:57.359
But even so, it was hard to forget how

00:23:57.359 --> 00:23:58.680
far down the ground was.

00:23:58.740 --> 00:24:01.859
He always felt safer in the hives than he

00:24:01.859 --> 00:24:04.680
did out on the webs, which he worried was

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:06.720
not a very normal silk wing attitude.

00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:11.339
And some of us, she's saying, we'll have

00:24:11.339 --> 00:24:12.180
them today.

00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:15.720
She sat up and flexed the tiny wing buds

00:24:15.720 --> 00:24:16.500
on her shoulder blades.

00:24:16.619 --> 00:24:20.579
Well, not exactly, he pointed out.

00:24:20.640 --> 00:24:23.400
Today is only your cocoon spinning day.

00:24:23.460 --> 00:24:25.859
It'll take another 5 days for your wings

00:24:25.859 --> 00:24:27.359
to actually, ah!

00:24:27.420 --> 00:24:30.539
He yelped as she abended his hammock and

00:24:30.539 --> 00:24:31.440
dumped him onto the web.

00:24:31.500 --> 00:24:34.980
Don't you actually me, Luna said

00:24:34.980 --> 00:24:35.460
sternly.

00:24:35.579 --> 00:24:38.099
I'm your older sister, and I've been to

00:24:38.099 --> 00:24:40.380
like 12 metamorphosis days.

00:24:40.440 --> 00:24:42.539
Plus, I have the highest grade in our

00:24:42.539 --> 00:24:43.680
class in silk studies.

00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:46.500
I can actually you under the table.

00:24:46.619 --> 00:24:49.140
Yes, all right.

00:24:49.200 --> 00:24:52.259
Blue said, stretching his legs one by

00:24:52.259 --> 00:24:52.559
one.

00:24:52.619 --> 00:24:55.500
You're the smartest dragon in the

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:55.859
family.

00:24:55.920 --> 00:24:56.519
I know.

00:24:56.579 --> 00:24:57.839
I admit it.

00:24:57.900 --> 00:25:00.359
He snuck a glance over his shoulder at

00:25:00.359 --> 00:25:01.500
his own wing buds.

00:25:01.559 --> 00:25:03.599
They looked the same as yesterday.

00:25:03.660 --> 00:25:07.019
Small, tightly curled, and iridescent

00:25:07.019 --> 00:25:09.779
violet, a brighter, more purple shade

00:25:09.779 --> 00:25:11.759
than the gem like azure of the rest of

00:25:11.759 --> 00:25:12.299
his scales.

00:25:12.359 --> 00:25:15.480
Luna's wing buds were starting to unfurl

00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:18.660
so he could see whorls of cobalt and gold

00:25:18.660 --> 00:25:20.759
inside the pale green exterior.

00:25:20.819 --> 00:25:23.519
There were also signs of her silk coming

00:25:23.519 --> 00:25:23.880
in.

00:25:23.940 --> 00:25:27.119
Already her palms and wrists were glowing

00:25:27.119 --> 00:25:29.819
a little, as though tiny fireflies were

00:25:29.819 --> 00:25:30.960
waking up under her scales.

00:25:31.079 --> 00:25:34.859
That'll be me soon, he thought.

00:25:34.980 --> 00:25:37.200
Tamping down a wave of panic.

00:25:37.259 --> 00:25:40.799
After my own metamorphosis, I'll have

00:25:40.799 --> 00:25:41.940
wings and silk too.

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:45.599
Maybe the changes would be small.

00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:48.420
Maybe he'd be assigned to live right here

00:25:48.420 --> 00:25:50.880
to help his mother strengthen the bridges

00:25:50.880 --> 00:25:51.720
between hives.

00:25:51.779 --> 00:25:55.559
Maybe Luna would stay too, and be a hive

00:25:55.559 --> 00:25:57.960
drone like her mother, working for one of

00:25:57.960 --> 00:25:59.819
the upper class hive wing families.

00:25:59.880 --> 00:26:02.220
She wouldn't like that, though.

00:26:02.339 --> 00:26:04.680
Luna wanted to be a spinner.

00:26:04.740 --> 00:26:07.559
She was hoping to be paired with sword

00:26:07.559 --> 00:26:09.900
tail in an artist's cell near the sunny

00:26:09.900 --> 00:26:10.799
heights of the web.

00:26:10.859 --> 00:26:13.440
She wanted to make a weaving so

00:26:13.440 --> 00:26:14.039
beautiful.

00:26:14.099 --> 00:26:16.259
It would have to be given to the queen of

00:26:16.259 --> 00:26:20.160
the hive wings, who ruled both tribes, or

00:26:20.160 --> 00:26:22.200
at least to one of the queen's sisters.

00:26:22.259 --> 00:26:26.220
Blue had seen the queen only once when

00:26:26.220 --> 00:26:27.660
she visited Cicada Hive.

00:26:27.720 --> 00:26:30.900
Queen Wasp had come through to inspect

00:26:30.900 --> 00:26:33.660
their school with 20 hive wing soldiers

00:26:33.660 --> 00:26:36.119
marching in impressive exact unison

00:26:36.119 --> 00:26:36.660
behind her.

00:26:36.720 --> 00:26:40.200
Her scales glittered in perfect black and

00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:42.779
yellow stripes, and her eyes were large

00:26:42.779 --> 00:26:46.319
and completely black, surrounded by an

00:26:46.319 --> 00:26:47.579
oval of yellow scales.

00:26:47.640 --> 00:26:51.420
Imagining himself into her was almost

00:26:51.420 --> 00:26:52.259
impossible.

00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:55.140
It was like trying to imagine life as the

00:26:55.140 --> 00:26:55.440
sun.

00:26:55.500 --> 00:26:57.599
But he couldn't help trying.

00:26:57.660 --> 00:27:00.779
He thought about how she must wake up in

00:27:00.779 --> 00:27:02.579
the morning and eat breakfast, like

00:27:02.579 --> 00:27:05.940
anyone else, although, if the rumors were

00:27:05.940 --> 00:27:09.299
true, She ate as rarely as possible, and

00:27:09.299 --> 00:27:10.319
only predators.

00:27:10.380 --> 00:27:13.140
The head of a lioness for lunch one day

00:27:13.140 --> 00:27:16.799
slices a black mamba in squid ink soup

00:27:16.799 --> 00:27:18.059
for dinner 12 days later.

00:27:18.180 --> 00:27:21.660
He wondered if her wings felt strong or

00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:24.539
heavy as she flew from hive to hive to

00:27:24.539 --> 00:27:25.500
check on her subjects.

00:27:25.559 --> 00:27:28.920
Was she relieved to have sisters to share

00:27:28.920 --> 00:27:30.119
her responsibilities with?

00:27:30.180 --> 00:27:33.000
Or did she worry that they might covet

00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:33.480
her throne?

00:27:33.599 --> 00:27:37.019
How often did she check the book of Clear

00:27:37.019 --> 00:27:37.440
Sight?

00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:40.980
If he were queen, with 2 tribes full of

00:27:40.980 --> 00:27:43.859
1000s of dragons depending on him, Blue

00:27:43.859 --> 00:27:46.440
guessed he'd read it every day, until he

00:27:46.440 --> 00:27:47.279
had it memorized.

00:27:47.339 --> 00:27:50.940
At one point during her visit, she had

00:27:50.940 --> 00:27:53.700
spotted Blue and Luna, and stared at them

00:27:53.700 --> 00:27:56.339
for approximately a century and a half by

00:27:56.339 --> 00:27:57.359
his internal clock.

00:27:57.480 --> 00:28:01.019
He'd gotten the distinct feeling that she

00:28:01.019 --> 00:28:03.000
was trying to decide between adopting

00:28:03.000 --> 00:28:04.380
them or eating them.

00:28:04.500 --> 00:28:08.039
Queen Wasp was as breathtaking and

00:28:08.039 --> 00:28:10.019
superior as all the stories said.

00:28:10.079 --> 00:28:14.700
After that, her sister, Lady Cicada, the

00:28:14.700 --> 00:28:16.799
ruler of their hive, had never seemed

00:28:16.799 --> 00:28:18.480
quite so terrifying to him again.

00:28:18.539 --> 00:28:21.539
And maybe that was the point of the

00:28:21.539 --> 00:28:24.480
queen's visits, to remind everyone whose

00:28:24.480 --> 00:28:25.740
claws held the real power.

00:28:25.799 --> 00:28:30.900
So, Luna said, taking one of his talons

00:28:30.900 --> 00:28:34.019
in hers, my last day as a dragonette.

00:28:34.079 --> 00:28:35.039
What are we going to do?

00:28:35.099 --> 00:28:38.279
Lie around on the web in the sunlight?

00:28:38.339 --> 00:28:40.259
He suggested, hopefully.

00:28:40.319 --> 00:28:43.980
No, you lazy banana slug, she said.

00:28:44.039 --> 00:28:45.960
All my favorite things.

00:28:46.079 --> 00:28:47.700
That's the correct answer.

00:28:47.759 --> 00:28:51.119
This isn't fair, he pointed out.

00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:54.299
By the time it's my metamorphosis day

00:28:54.299 --> 00:28:56.819
nobody will be left to do all my favorite

00:28:56.819 --> 00:28:57.599
things with me.

00:28:57.660 --> 00:29:00.720
You'll all be too busy flying around with

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:03.960
your big, flappy wings, doing fancy, busy

00:29:03.960 --> 00:29:04.680
wingish things.

00:29:04.740 --> 00:29:09.059
Luna managed not to make a face, but Blue

00:29:09.059 --> 00:29:11.099
instantly felt guilty anyway.

00:29:11.160 --> 00:29:13.859
He knew she wished Swordtail could spend

00:29:13.859 --> 00:29:14.640
the day with them too.

00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:17.640
But Sortell was on construction duty on

00:29:17.640 --> 00:29:19.920
the west side of Cicada Hive all day

00:29:19.920 --> 00:29:23.640
probably getting dusty and frustrated, and

00:29:23.640 --> 00:29:24.960
missing Luna like crazy.

00:29:25.019 --> 00:29:28.140
Sorry, Blue said.

00:29:28.200 --> 00:29:30.720
Don't be, Luna said.

00:29:30.779 --> 00:29:32.220
Once I have my wings.

00:29:32.279 --> 00:29:35.220
Sortel and I can be partnered, and then

00:29:35.220 --> 00:29:36.539
I'll see quite enough of him.

00:29:36.660 --> 00:29:40.019
She grinned, as though applying for the

00:29:40.019 --> 00:29:42.059
partnership actually meant they'd get it

00:29:42.059 --> 00:29:44.759
which Blue thought was far from certain.

00:29:44.819 --> 00:29:48.240
He didn't know any adult silk wings who'd

00:29:48.240 --> 00:29:49.680
been given the partner of their choice.

00:29:49.740 --> 00:29:53.099
His mother and Luna's mother, hadn't even

00:29:53.099 --> 00:29:55.559
known their father, who had been whisked

00:29:55.559 --> 00:29:57.359
away to another hive once there were

00:29:57.359 --> 00:29:57.599
eggs.

00:29:57.660 --> 00:30:01.740
Blue knew his name, Admiral, and nothing

00:30:01.740 --> 00:30:02.039
else.

00:30:02.099 --> 00:30:05.819
Better this way, though, he thought.

00:30:05.880 --> 00:30:09.000
Burnett and Silverspot ended up loving

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:10.740
each other much more than they could ever

00:30:10.740 --> 00:30:11.819
have loved Admiral.

00:30:11.940 --> 00:30:14.700
They were a good family, the 4 of them.

00:30:14.759 --> 00:30:16.980
It had all worked out for the best.

00:30:17.039 --> 00:30:20.519
Queen WAS and her sisters knew what they

00:30:20.519 --> 00:30:22.140
were doing with the partner assignments.

00:30:22.200 --> 00:30:25.319
If Luna and Swordtail weren't matched up

00:30:25.319 --> 00:30:26.880
it would be for a good reason.

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:29.460
So where do we start?

00:30:29.579 --> 00:30:30.539
He asked.

00:30:30.599 --> 00:30:32.640
No wait, let me guess.

00:30:32.700 --> 00:30:34.680
Honey drops.

00:30:34.740 --> 00:30:38.819
Honey drops, Luna sang, bouncing the web

00:30:38.819 --> 00:30:40.619
again and fluttering her wing buds.

00:30:40.740 --> 00:30:43.079
Move your tail and maybe we'll beat the

00:30:43.079 --> 00:30:43.980
line at the checkpoint.

00:30:44.039 --> 00:30:47.099
He dipped his snout into their due

00:30:47.099 --> 00:30:47.519
collector.

00:30:47.579 --> 00:30:51.000
Washing his antennae and the dry scales

00:30:51.000 --> 00:30:51.480
under his eyes.

00:30:51.539 --> 00:30:54.119
As Luna darted across the web to her

00:30:54.119 --> 00:30:54.359
mother.

00:30:54.420 --> 00:30:57.839
Silverspot sat up and wrapped her wings

00:30:57.839 --> 00:30:58.799
around Luna.

00:30:58.859 --> 00:31:01.259
Quickly enough that Blue wondered whether

00:31:01.259 --> 00:31:02.880
she had been awake all night too.

00:31:02.940 --> 00:31:06.000
Have a wonderful day, my darling.

00:31:06.059 --> 00:31:08.160
I'll try to make it to the cocoon.

00:31:08.279 --> 00:31:10.200
Silverspot promised.

00:31:10.259 --> 00:31:13.500
But I know, Luna said.

00:31:13.559 --> 00:31:14.579
It's all right.

00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:18.119
Silverspot's mistress was bad tempered

00:31:18.119 --> 00:31:20.400
and frantically insecure about her place

00:31:20.400 --> 00:31:23.160
in the hive hierarchy, and she tended to

00:31:23.160 --> 00:31:25.680
take out her rage on silver spot, with

00:31:25.680 --> 00:31:27.359
1000s of small cruelties.

00:31:27.480 --> 00:31:30.000
Keeping silver spot from her only

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:32.339
daughter's metamorphosis would probably

00:31:32.339 --> 00:31:33.660
be the highlight of her year.

00:31:33.720 --> 00:31:37.319
Just think, Luna said brightly.

00:31:37.380 --> 00:31:39.960
Next time I see you, I'll have wings.

00:31:40.019 --> 00:31:41.339
We can go flying together.

00:31:41.400 --> 00:31:43.619
I can't wait.

00:31:43.680 --> 00:31:45.660
Silverspot agreed.

00:31:45.720 --> 00:31:48.359
But when she hugged Luna again.

00:31:48.420 --> 00:31:50.759
Blue caught a strange expression crossing

00:31:50.759 --> 00:31:51.059
her face.

00:31:51.119 --> 00:31:52.980
Anxiety?

00:31:53.039 --> 00:31:54.299
Fear?

00:31:54.359 --> 00:31:57.299
He felt a weird chill run through his

00:31:57.299 --> 00:31:57.660
scales.

00:31:57.779 --> 00:32:00.720
Silverspot looked as though she knew

00:32:00.720 --> 00:32:01.799
something they didn't.

00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:06.480
As if, for some reason, Silverspot

00:32:06.480 --> 00:32:08.160
suspected she would never see her

00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:08.759
daughter again.

00:32:08.819 --> 00:32:13.200
Chapter 2.

00:32:13.440 --> 00:32:17.579
The creeping sense of foreboding followed

00:32:17.579 --> 00:32:19.799
Blue, as he clambered along the webs

00:32:19.799 --> 00:32:23.400
after Luna, the sun was rising, sending

00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:25.680
shafts of filmy gray light through the

00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:27.059
silken strands around them.

00:32:27.119 --> 00:32:30.960
The soft hum of insect wings rose from

00:32:30.960 --> 00:32:33.240
the tall, waving grasses of the savannah

00:32:33.240 --> 00:32:33.660
below.

00:32:33.720 --> 00:32:37.619
Luna was a reckless climber, weeping from

00:32:37.619 --> 00:32:40.380
one level to the next like a monkey, or

00:32:40.380 --> 00:32:42.720
like a dragon who already had her wings.

00:32:42.779 --> 00:32:46.380
Blue was more sensible, relying on the

00:32:46.380 --> 00:32:48.480
slight stickiness of the silk to keep him

00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:52.140
anchored as he ascended, even so, today

00:32:52.140 --> 00:32:54.059
he felt more airsick than he normally

00:32:54.059 --> 00:32:54.240
did.

00:32:54.299 --> 00:32:57.539
Each tremor along the silk seemed to

00:32:57.539 --> 00:33:00.599
vibrate right into his bones, making his

00:33:00.599 --> 00:33:02.880
antennae twitch nervously, and his teeth

00:33:02.880 --> 00:33:03.299
ache.

00:33:03.359 --> 00:33:06.119
He was relieved when they reached the

00:33:06.119 --> 00:33:08.519
hive entrance, where the webs connected

00:33:08.519 --> 00:33:10.019
to the uppermost tier of the city.

00:33:10.079 --> 00:33:13.140
There was already aligned 20 dragons

00:33:13.140 --> 00:33:13.440
long.

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:15.599
But at least here they could wait on the

00:33:15.599 --> 00:33:17.339
solid ground of the entrance tunnel.

00:33:17.400 --> 00:33:20.339
He stepped off the web onto the papery

00:33:20.339 --> 00:33:22.559
dry surface and flexed his talons.

00:33:22.619 --> 00:33:25.920
The walls of the tunnel were painted with

00:33:25.920 --> 00:33:28.380
a mural of silk wings and hive wings

00:33:28.380 --> 00:33:31.619
flying together in a bright blue sky, all

00:33:31.619 --> 00:33:33.599
of them looking as happy as Luna on a

00:33:33.599 --> 00:33:34.500
honey drop spree.

00:33:34.619 --> 00:33:37.019
Much of the mural was covered up, though

00:33:37.019 --> 00:33:39.900
by the posters that lined the walls.

00:33:39.960 --> 00:33:41.339
Be vigilant.

00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:43.740
We are always in danger.

00:33:43.799 --> 00:33:45.660
Beware of leaf wings.

00:33:45.720 --> 00:33:49.259
Report disloyal silk wings to a hive wing

00:33:49.259 --> 00:33:50.339
authority immediately.

00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:53.640
Queen Wasp sees everything.

00:33:53.700 --> 00:33:56.099
Queen Wasp protects us all.

00:33:56.099 --> 00:33:58.380
All hail Queen Wasp.

00:33:58.500 --> 00:34:03.359
Leave wings, gone, or lying in wait.

00:34:03.420 --> 00:34:06.480
Report any sightings of possible leaf

00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:07.799
wings to a high wing authority

00:34:07.799 --> 00:34:08.400
immediately.

00:34:08.460 --> 00:34:12.599
That last one had a drawing of a snarling

00:34:12.599 --> 00:34:15.239
dark green dragon on it, complete with

00:34:15.239 --> 00:34:16.860
blood stained claws and teeth.

00:34:16.920 --> 00:34:20.219
It seemed as if a new poster appeared on

00:34:20.219 --> 00:34:21.420
the walls every other day.

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:23.940
And half of them were about the threat of

00:34:23.940 --> 00:34:24.659
leaf wings.

00:34:24.719 --> 00:34:27.779
Luna caught him studying the picture and

00:34:27.779 --> 00:34:28.319
snorted.

00:34:28.380 --> 00:34:30.059
What?

00:34:30.059 --> 00:34:30.719
he said.

00:34:30.780 --> 00:34:33.960
Come on, she said, you're not really

00:34:33.960 --> 00:34:35.460
afraid of leaf wings, are you?

00:34:35.519 --> 00:34:37.500
Why not?

00:34:37.500 --> 00:34:38.280
he asked.

00:34:38.340 --> 00:34:41.039
They nearly wiped us out half a century

00:34:41.039 --> 00:34:41.460
ago.

00:34:41.519 --> 00:34:44.460
Or has my genius sister forgotten all our

00:34:44.460 --> 00:34:45.599
history lessons already?

00:34:45.659 --> 00:34:47.819
But they failed.

00:34:47.880 --> 00:34:49.320
She pointed out.

00:34:49.380 --> 00:34:52.320
And now they're extinct, so there's

00:34:52.320 --> 00:34:53.039
nothing to worry about.

00:34:53.099 --> 00:34:55.500
It's not like they can attack us if

00:34:55.500 --> 00:34:56.219
they're all dead.

00:34:56.280 --> 00:34:59.699
We don't know that they are, he argued.

00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:03.000
Tusig said his uncle saw one flying

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:04.380
overhead a couple of years ago.

00:35:04.440 --> 00:35:07.380
And what about that section of mantis

00:35:07.380 --> 00:35:08.880
hive that collapsed last year?

00:35:08.940 --> 00:35:11.639
Everyone said that was leaf wing

00:35:11.639 --> 00:35:12.300
sabotage.

00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:15.480
Luna said scornfully.

00:35:15.539 --> 00:35:18.119
What Tussock's uncle saw was a green

00:35:18.119 --> 00:35:18.840
silkwing.

00:35:18.900 --> 00:35:21.780
He's just hysterical, and that collapse

00:35:21.780 --> 00:35:23.760
was caused by shoddy workmanship.

00:35:23.820 --> 00:35:26.340
The sabotage story was so obviously a

00:35:26.340 --> 00:35:26.820
cover up.

00:35:26.940 --> 00:35:31.320
Blue said, glancing at the hive wing

00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:32.099
soldiers up ahead.

00:35:32.159 --> 00:35:35.699
They looked busy checking IDs, but they

00:35:35.699 --> 00:35:37.860
might still overhear Luna's treacherous

00:35:37.860 --> 00:35:38.099
talk.

00:35:38.159 --> 00:35:43.139
Look, Luna said, lowering her voice and

00:35:43.139 --> 00:35:43.800
rolling her eyes.

00:35:43.860 --> 00:35:47.519
No one has really seen a leaf wing in

00:35:47.519 --> 00:35:50.519
over 50 years, and we cut down all their

00:35:50.519 --> 00:35:50.880
trees.

00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:53.820
So where would they even be living if

00:35:53.820 --> 00:35:54.659
they were still alive?

00:35:54.719 --> 00:35:57.420
Slithering through the tall grass of the

00:35:57.420 --> 00:35:58.139
Savannah?

00:35:58.199 --> 00:36:01.980
No, they're gone, thanks to Queen Wasp.

00:36:02.039 --> 00:36:04.260
So all of this is totally unnecessary.

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:07.320
She waved her claws at the warning

00:36:07.320 --> 00:36:07.800
posters.

00:36:07.860 --> 00:36:11.460
The hives don't cover the whole continent

00:36:11.460 --> 00:36:14.159
he suggested, but she was already talking

00:36:14.159 --> 00:36:14.639
over him.

00:36:14.760 --> 00:36:18.659
The queen just needs us to have a, what's

00:36:18.659 --> 00:36:21.360
it called, a common enemy, you know?

00:36:21.420 --> 00:36:23.940
So the silk wings don't start complaining

00:36:23.940 --> 00:36:26.039
or asking for their own queen or anything

00:36:26.039 --> 00:36:26.460
like that.

00:36:26.519 --> 00:36:29.099
Our own queen?

00:36:29.159 --> 00:36:31.019
Lou was startled.

00:36:31.079 --> 00:36:33.480
He never even thought about the silk

00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:35.159
wings asking for a separate queen

00:36:35.159 --> 00:36:35.460
before.

00:36:35.519 --> 00:36:38.880
It was kind of alarming that Luna had.

00:36:38.940 --> 00:36:41.820
That seemed like the kind of dangerous

00:36:41.820 --> 00:36:43.860
idea sore tail might have put in her

00:36:43.860 --> 00:36:44.280
head.

00:36:44.340 --> 00:36:47.400
I mean, not that I think we should.

00:36:47.519 --> 00:36:49.380
Luna said hurriedly.

00:36:49.440 --> 00:36:52.380
And this time, she was the one to glance

00:36:52.380 --> 00:36:53.280
over at the soldiers.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:57.059
But you know, someone might, if they were

00:36:57.059 --> 00:36:58.380
unhappy with the way things are.

00:36:58.500 --> 00:37:00.659
Blue shook his head.

00:37:00.719 --> 00:37:02.760
I don't think so.

00:37:02.820 --> 00:37:05.639
I don't know any unhappy silk wings.

00:37:05.699 --> 00:37:09.840
The poster behind Luna read, Loyalty

00:37:09.840 --> 00:37:12.780
above all, with a giant drawing of Queen

00:37:12.780 --> 00:37:14.639
Wasp's huge dark eyes.

00:37:14.639 --> 00:37:17.460
Sometimes they were a comforting sight

00:37:17.460 --> 00:37:19.679
but in the middle of this conversation

00:37:19.679 --> 00:37:21.780
they were making him uneasy.

00:37:21.840 --> 00:37:25.139
Everything is great in the hives.

00:37:25.199 --> 00:37:27.719
We're safe, and we all work together.

00:37:27.780 --> 00:37:30.059
So I don't see what anyone would have to

00:37:30.059 --> 00:37:30.599
complain about.

00:37:30.659 --> 00:37:34.320
The line moved them within earshot of the

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:36.480
soldiers, and they both stopped talking

00:37:36.480 --> 00:37:37.320
instinctively.

00:37:37.380 --> 00:37:40.920
Blue gazed at the long, pale blue wings

00:37:40.920 --> 00:37:42.179
of the dragon in front of him.

00:37:42.239 --> 00:37:45.659
Imagining where she might be going, until

00:37:45.659 --> 00:37:46.679
finally it was their turn.

00:37:46.739 --> 00:37:50.699
Names, said one of the soldiers in a

00:37:50.699 --> 00:37:51.119
bored voice.

00:37:51.239 --> 00:37:54.719
Every hive wing had at least a few black

00:37:54.719 --> 00:37:57.239
scales, inherited from their common

00:37:57.239 --> 00:37:58.920
ancestor, Clearsight.

00:37:58.980 --> 00:38:02.159
But this dragon was almost entirely black

00:38:02.159 --> 00:38:05.039
with only a few orange flecks here and

00:38:05.039 --> 00:38:05.219
there.

00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:08.219
Blue and Luna had seen him here at the

00:38:08.219 --> 00:38:10.500
checkpoint nearly every day for 3 years.

00:38:10.559 --> 00:38:13.139
And yet the soldier never gave any

00:38:13.139 --> 00:38:16.079
indication of recognizing them, or caring

00:38:16.079 --> 00:38:17.699
that they existed beyond their IDs.

00:38:17.820 --> 00:38:21.239
His name was Hawker, not that he'd ever

00:38:21.239 --> 00:38:21.780
told them that.

00:38:21.840 --> 00:38:24.420
Blue had picked it up from listening to

00:38:24.420 --> 00:38:25.920
the guards grumbling at one another.

00:38:25.980 --> 00:38:29.880
Blue, he said, holding out his right

00:38:29.880 --> 00:38:30.239
arm.

00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:33.719
The soldier studied the letters that had

00:38:33.719 --> 00:38:36.239
been carved into Blue's palm when he was

00:38:36.239 --> 00:38:37.920
a newly hatched dragonette.

00:38:37.980 --> 00:38:42.000
B for his name, forming a triangle with a

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:44.760
smaller B and A for his parents' names.

00:38:44.820 --> 00:38:48.239
Luna always said she was glad the marking

00:38:48.239 --> 00:38:49.739
happened while they were too young to

00:38:49.739 --> 00:38:50.099
remember.

00:38:50.159 --> 00:38:52.920
But Blue was pretty sure he did have

00:38:52.920 --> 00:38:53.940
memories of that day.

00:38:54.000 --> 00:38:58.800
A bright light, a searing pain, and most

00:38:58.800 --> 00:39:00.960
clearly, a sense of betrayal.

00:39:01.019 --> 00:39:04.739
Hawker grunted, and moved on to examining

00:39:04.739 --> 00:39:06.539
the wrist cough on Blue's other arm.

00:39:06.659 --> 00:39:10.380
It was a dull bronze color and annoyingly

00:39:10.380 --> 00:39:12.659
heavy, although Blue was mostly used to

00:39:12.659 --> 00:39:13.199
it by now.

00:39:13.260 --> 00:39:16.320
It indicated that he was a student at one

00:39:16.320 --> 00:39:17.820
of the schools in the hive.

00:39:17.880 --> 00:39:20.039
So he was permitted to go in and out

00:39:20.039 --> 00:39:21.239
through this checkpoint.

00:39:21.239 --> 00:39:24.000
The name of the school was inscribed in

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:24.360
the metal.

00:39:24.420 --> 00:39:26.159
Silkworm Hall.

00:39:26.219 --> 00:39:29.699
And I'm Luna, said his sister.

00:39:29.760 --> 00:39:32.699
Ah, said the soldier.

00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:35.099
Turning to consult a list on a small

00:39:35.099 --> 00:39:36.360
rectangle of paper.

00:39:36.420 --> 00:39:38.400
Metamorphosis today.

00:39:38.460 --> 00:39:40.019
That's right.

00:39:40.079 --> 00:39:41.519
Luna said.

00:39:41.579 --> 00:39:43.920
Blue could tell she was trying so hard

00:39:43.920 --> 00:39:44.880
not to smile.

00:39:44.940 --> 00:39:47.579
Smiling at soldiers was always risky.

00:39:47.639 --> 00:39:50.460
You never knew if you'd get a rare smile

00:39:50.460 --> 00:39:52.920
back, or if you'd end up spending an

00:39:52.920 --> 00:39:55.380
afternoon on misbehavior's way, for

00:39:55.380 --> 00:39:57.539
taunting a figure of authority.

00:39:57.599 --> 00:40:01.199
Blue imagined that the soldiers had to be

00:40:01.199 --> 00:40:02.519
that alert and suspicious.

00:40:02.579 --> 00:40:05.880
If dragons didn't respect them, how could

00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:07.860
they keep the peas and control the hive?

00:40:07.920 --> 00:40:11.760
But he also believed that Soratel hadn't

00:40:11.760 --> 00:40:14.099
deserved it any of the 3 times he'd wound

00:40:14.099 --> 00:40:15.599
up on misbehaviors way.

00:40:15.659 --> 00:40:19.500
Sortell had wild ideas, and talked a

00:40:19.500 --> 00:40:21.539
little too freely, but he wasn't a danger

00:40:21.539 --> 00:40:22.260
to the hive.

00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:25.440
You'll have a new one of these next time

00:40:25.440 --> 00:40:26.099
you come through here.

00:40:26.159 --> 00:40:29.760
Hawker said, tapping Luna's wrist cuff

00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:31.019
which matched blues.

00:40:31.139 --> 00:40:35.400
I know, she said, as Blue's heart sank.

00:40:35.519 --> 00:40:37.199
One more change.

00:40:37.260 --> 00:40:39.659
Luna was done with school now.

00:40:39.719 --> 00:40:41.579
He'd have to go without her.

00:40:41.639 --> 00:40:44.039
Not for very long, though.

00:40:44.099 --> 00:40:46.679
I'll be needing a new wristband soon

00:40:46.679 --> 00:40:46.980
too.

00:40:47.039 --> 00:40:50.460
How would it feel to have this one cut

00:40:50.460 --> 00:40:52.679
off and exchanged for something else?

00:40:52.739 --> 00:40:55.980
Surely it would be a bit like having one

00:40:55.980 --> 00:40:57.900
of his toes casually replaced.

00:40:57.960 --> 00:41:01.139
Well, said the soldier.

00:41:01.199 --> 00:41:04.079
He looked at his list, and then back at

00:41:04.079 --> 00:41:04.739
Luna again.

00:41:04.800 --> 00:41:06.239
You may go.

00:41:06.360 --> 00:41:09.719
Hawker cleared his throat gruffly as they

00:41:09.719 --> 00:41:10.199
started forward.

00:41:10.260 --> 00:41:12.599
Good luck.

00:41:12.659 --> 00:41:16.500
Oh, thank you, Luna said.

00:41:16.559 --> 00:41:17.460
Startled.

00:41:17.519 --> 00:41:20.760
She dragged Blue Ford, managing to hold

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:22.500
on until they were far down the tunnel

00:41:22.500 --> 00:41:24.659
before she burst into giggles.

00:41:24.719 --> 00:41:27.480
He said so many words to us all of a

00:41:27.480 --> 00:41:28.920
sudden, she cried.

00:41:28.980 --> 00:41:30.960
I didn't know he knew so many words.

00:41:31.019 --> 00:41:33.360
Maybe he likes you.

00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:35.820
Blue suggested with a grin.

00:41:35.880 --> 00:41:37.079
It was a joke.

00:41:37.139 --> 00:41:39.900
But then, what if he did?

00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:42.900
Blue felt himself slipping into visions

00:41:42.900 --> 00:41:44.579
of the hive wing's possible life.

00:41:44.639 --> 00:41:48.239
Did Hawker go home and dream of the silk

00:41:48.239 --> 00:41:50.699
wing he saw every day, but couldn't ever

00:41:50.699 --> 00:41:51.119
be with?

00:41:51.179 --> 00:41:53.760
Did his friends tease him about his

00:41:53.760 --> 00:41:54.900
dedication to his work?

00:41:54.960 --> 00:41:57.059
Did he like being a soldier?

00:41:57.119 --> 00:41:59.340
Following orders all day long?

00:41:59.400 --> 00:42:01.679
Or did he ever wish the rules were

00:42:01.679 --> 00:42:01.980
different?

00:42:02.099 --> 00:42:06.900
Ooh, maybe we'll have a forbidden love.

00:42:07.019 --> 00:42:10.079
Luna gasped, falling into blue and

00:42:10.079 --> 00:42:11.280
knocking him back into reality.

00:42:11.400 --> 00:42:15.420
Well, I am not going to be the one to

00:42:15.420 --> 00:42:17.099
tell sword tail, he said.

00:42:17.159 --> 00:42:20.039
Luna laughed and started telling a story

00:42:20.039 --> 00:42:22.380
about something funny, Soratell had said

00:42:22.380 --> 00:42:22.920
the night before.

00:42:22.980 --> 00:42:25.320
Blue padded beside her.

00:42:25.380 --> 00:42:28.199
Glad to be off the topic of silk wing

00:42:28.199 --> 00:42:29.820
hive wing relationships.

00:42:29.880 --> 00:42:32.280
Forbidden was putting it mildly.

00:42:32.340 --> 00:42:35.820
Whatever the strongest word for illegal

00:42:35.820 --> 00:42:37.739
was, that was the right word.

00:42:37.800 --> 00:42:41.940
Prohibited, outlawed, punishable by death

00:42:41.940 --> 00:42:44.940
all of those times a 1000000.

00:42:45.179 --> 00:42:48.179
They reached the end of the tunnel, where

00:42:48.179 --> 00:42:49.980
it widened and forked into several other

00:42:49.980 --> 00:42:50.519
tunnels.

00:42:50.639 --> 00:42:54.239
The path to the right led to the mosaic

00:42:54.239 --> 00:42:56.699
garden, but they'd go there later.

00:42:56.760 --> 00:42:57.599
Blue was sure.

00:42:57.659 --> 00:42:59.820
It was Luna's favorite place in the

00:42:59.820 --> 00:43:00.360
hive.

00:43:00.420 --> 00:43:03.539
First, though, they made their way down 3

00:43:03.539 --> 00:43:05.639
levels. through 2 more checkpoints.

00:43:05.699 --> 00:43:10.019
It was warm, as always in the hive, with

00:43:10.019 --> 00:43:11.880
sunlight filtering through the walls to

00:43:11.880 --> 00:43:13.800
cast an amber glow over everything.

00:43:13.860 --> 00:43:17.159
All the hives were made of tree stuff

00:43:17.159 --> 00:43:20.219
which was a particular mix of wood pulp

00:43:20.219 --> 00:43:23.039
and silk and clay, and other things blue

00:43:23.039 --> 00:43:24.900
would learn about if he was assigned to a

00:43:24.900 --> 00:43:25.739
construction crew.

00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:29.159
It looked paper thin, and allowed light

00:43:29.159 --> 00:43:31.559
to filter through, but it was solid as

00:43:31.559 --> 00:43:31.860
rock.

00:43:31.920 --> 00:43:33.719
Under his talons.

00:43:33.780 --> 00:43:36.780
The tree stuff floor was dry and mostly

00:43:36.780 --> 00:43:37.199
smooth.

00:43:37.260 --> 00:43:39.840
Apart from a few lumps where workers

00:43:39.840 --> 00:43:40.860
hadn't been careful enough.

00:43:40.920 --> 00:43:45.000
The problem was, the hives had been built

00:43:45.000 --> 00:43:46.920
back when there were plenty of trees all

00:43:46.920 --> 00:43:47.880
over Pentala.

00:43:47.940 --> 00:43:51.119
Now that the trees were all gone, or

00:43:51.119 --> 00:43:53.940
mostly gone, the only wood pulp came from

00:43:53.940 --> 00:43:55.739
the shrubby little bushes that fought

00:43:55.739 --> 00:43:57.780
their way out of the dry soil of the

00:43:57.780 --> 00:43:58.380
savannah.

00:43:58.440 --> 00:44:02.219
So the only way to expand a hive, was to

00:44:02.219 --> 00:44:03.780
take the tree stuff from somewhere else

00:44:03.780 --> 00:44:06.239
in the hive, and reshape it where you

00:44:06.239 --> 00:44:06.599
wanted it.

00:44:06.659 --> 00:44:09.780
It was hard back breaking work.

00:44:09.840 --> 00:44:12.719
Usually given to the silk wings who

00:44:12.719 --> 00:44:15.480
caused the most trouble in school, such

00:44:15.480 --> 00:44:17.880
as, for instance, sword tail.

00:44:18.000 --> 00:44:22.079
Blue was really, really hoping he didn't

00:44:22.079 --> 00:44:23.760
get assigned to a construction crew.

00:44:23.820 --> 00:44:26.579
A silk work detail would be different.

00:44:26.639 --> 00:44:29.699
What his mom did in the sky between hives

00:44:29.699 --> 00:44:32.460
was half architecture, half art.

00:44:32.760 --> 00:44:34.320
He wouldn't mind a job like that.

00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:38.400
Blue had been a good, quiet, obedient

00:44:38.400 --> 00:44:40.679
student at Silkworm Hall his whole life.

00:44:40.739 --> 00:44:43.500
Surely he'd earned a better assignment

00:44:43.500 --> 00:44:44.880
than tree stuff construction.

00:44:44.940 --> 00:44:49.079
Finally, Luna took a path to the right

00:44:49.079 --> 00:44:51.599
instead of the left, and they came to the

00:44:51.599 --> 00:44:53.219
open market of Cicada Hive.

00:44:53.340 --> 00:44:56.940
This was a huge vaulted space that hummed

00:44:56.940 --> 00:44:57.420
with activity.

00:44:57.480 --> 00:45:01.260
The best shops had permanent 6 sided

00:45:01.260 --> 00:45:02.760
cells around the outer wall.

00:45:02.880 --> 00:45:06.300
Everyone else had to scramble for stalls

00:45:06.300 --> 00:45:07.559
in the Labyrinthian middle.

00:45:07.619 --> 00:45:11.460
Overhead, yellow and orange lanterns hung

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:14.039
along silk filaments, crisscrossing the

00:45:14.039 --> 00:45:16.320
ceiling like necklaces of tiny suns.

00:45:16.440 --> 00:45:20.880
And, as always, soldiers perched on

00:45:20.880 --> 00:45:23.519
balconies above the market, keeping a

00:45:23.519 --> 00:45:25.559
sharp eye on the hustle and bustle of the

00:45:25.559 --> 00:45:26.460
dragons below.

00:45:26.519 --> 00:45:29.820
Some of them held long, needle like

00:45:29.820 --> 00:45:32.519
lances that looked like bigger versions

00:45:32.519 --> 00:45:34.559
of the stingers that could spring from

00:45:34.559 --> 00:45:36.840
the tips of Queen Wasp's claws.

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:39.599
Not that Blue had ever seen her use them

00:45:39.599 --> 00:45:42.000
but they were featured in several of the

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:42.360
posters.

00:45:42.420 --> 00:45:46.800
Some of those in here, in fact, Her face

00:45:46.800 --> 00:45:49.500
loomed over the market in murals and

00:45:49.500 --> 00:45:52.079
posters, until he almost felt as though

00:45:52.079 --> 00:45:55.139
he had a 100 lenses in his eyes, each of

00:45:55.139 --> 00:45:56.760
them reflecting her back at him.

00:45:56.760 --> 00:46:00.059
Luna led the way confidently through the

00:46:00.059 --> 00:46:03.179
maze, until Blue realized she was aiming

00:46:03.179 --> 00:46:06.179
for the best nectar store in the hive, a

00:46:06.179 --> 00:46:09.119
tall, imposing cell front, with delicate

00:46:09.119 --> 00:46:11.039
sugar confections arrayed in the window.

00:46:11.099 --> 00:46:14.099
He jumped forward and stepped on her tail

00:46:14.099 --> 00:46:15.179
yanking her back.

00:46:15.300 --> 00:46:17.579
Ow, she yelped.

00:46:17.639 --> 00:46:18.719
What was that for?

00:46:18.780 --> 00:46:22.199
Three haughty looking hive wings nearly

00:46:22.199 --> 00:46:24.780
ran into them, and he tugged Luna out of

00:46:24.780 --> 00:46:26.760
their way, mumbling apologies.

00:46:26.820 --> 00:46:29.400
They wrinkled their noses and spread

00:46:29.400 --> 00:46:31.980
their wings, making a few other silk

00:46:31.980 --> 00:46:33.900
wings duck to the side of the path to

00:46:33.900 --> 00:46:36.119
give them space, and then they swept

00:46:36.119 --> 00:46:36.360
away.

00:46:36.420 --> 00:46:40.679
Luna, silk wings don't go into the sugar

00:46:40.679 --> 00:46:42.360
dream, he said.

00:46:42.480 --> 00:46:45.059
Let's go to droplets, like we always do.

00:46:45.119 --> 00:46:49.079
It's my metamorphosis day, she objected.

00:46:49.139 --> 00:46:51.599
We've only never been there because we

00:46:51.599 --> 00:46:54.059
usually can't afford it, but today is

00:46:54.059 --> 00:46:54.539
different.

00:46:54.599 --> 00:46:56.699
Mother gave me enough scales for it.

00:46:56.760 --> 00:47:00.420
She said to have the best last day ever.

00:47:00.480 --> 00:47:03.480
Blue shivered involuntarily.

00:47:03.539 --> 00:47:07.559
The phrase, last day, really wasn't

00:47:07.559 --> 00:47:09.780
helping his anxiety about silver spots

00:47:09.780 --> 00:47:10.500
face this morning.

00:47:10.619 --> 00:47:15.000
Stop worrying, Luna said, nudging his

00:47:15.000 --> 00:47:15.300
shoulder.

00:47:15.360 --> 00:47:17.880
They'll take our scales no matter who we

00:47:17.880 --> 00:47:20.280
are, and these might be the best honey

00:47:20.280 --> 00:47:21.659
drops we ever get.

00:47:21.719 --> 00:47:25.500
She bounded off again, and he followed

00:47:25.500 --> 00:47:28.079
unconvinced, but aware that arguing with

00:47:28.079 --> 00:47:29.519
his sister would get him exactly

00:47:29.519 --> 00:47:30.000
nowhere.

00:47:30.119 --> 00:47:35.159
There was only one other customer in The

00:47:35.159 --> 00:47:36.659
Sugar Dream when they entered.

00:47:36.719 --> 00:47:40.079
An older lemon yellow hive wing, with

00:47:40.079 --> 00:47:42.539
black stripes on her wings, and ruby

00:47:42.539 --> 00:47:44.460
scales freckling her nose and tail.

00:47:44.460 --> 00:47:47.760
She peered over a pair of spectacles at

00:47:47.760 --> 00:47:48.179
them.

00:47:48.239 --> 00:47:50.400
Then went back to squinting at the

00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:52.380
shelves of pale pink and lavender

00:47:52.380 --> 00:47:52.860
candies.

00:47:52.920 --> 00:47:55.619
But the hive wing behind the counter

00:47:55.619 --> 00:47:57.960
stiffened and flicked his long red tail

00:47:57.960 --> 00:47:58.860
disapprovingly.

00:47:58.920 --> 00:48:01.679
His brows arching as high as they could

00:48:01.679 --> 00:48:02.219
possibly go.

00:48:02.280 --> 00:48:06.960
Hello, Luna said cheerfully, ignoring his

00:48:06.960 --> 00:48:07.559
expression.

00:48:07.619 --> 00:48:10.079
We'd like 2 honey drops, please.

00:48:10.139 --> 00:48:13.679
She touched the soft gray silk pouch

00:48:13.679 --> 00:48:16.139
around her neck as she spoke. so that the

00:48:16.139 --> 00:48:17.699
scales inside jingled.

00:48:17.760 --> 00:48:20.159
Who's your mistress?

00:48:20.219 --> 00:48:21.599
The clerk asked.

00:48:21.659 --> 00:48:23.280
Is she new to this hive?

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:25.920
She should know that shopping for luxury

00:48:25.920 --> 00:48:28.679
items is not a task traditionally

00:48:28.679 --> 00:48:30.119
entrusted to servants.

00:48:30.179 --> 00:48:34.260
We are nobody's servants, Luna said

00:48:34.260 --> 00:48:35.039
indignantly.

00:48:35.099 --> 00:48:36.599
We want them for ourselves.

00:48:36.659 --> 00:48:40.619
Nobody's servants yet, Blue added

00:48:40.619 --> 00:48:41.159
quickly.

00:48:41.219 --> 00:48:42.900
We're still in school.

00:48:42.960 --> 00:48:45.599
He pointed to their wing buds.

00:48:45.659 --> 00:48:49.199
It's her metamorphosis day today, actually

00:48:49.199 --> 00:48:52.019
so we'll know our assignment soon.

00:48:52.079 --> 00:48:56.460
And then I'm sure our, uh, the dragons we

00:48:56.460 --> 00:49:00.599
work for will, uh, He made himself stop

00:49:00.599 --> 00:49:01.320
talking.

00:49:01.500 --> 00:49:03.840
Judging by the frown on the shopkeeper's

00:49:03.840 --> 00:49:05.760
face. was clearly not helping.

00:49:05.820 --> 00:49:09.840
Indeed, said the sales dragon.

00:49:09.900 --> 00:49:12.840
Well, as you can see, I am currently

00:49:12.840 --> 00:49:14.159
assisting another customer.

00:49:14.219 --> 00:49:16.380
I'm afraid you will have to wait.

00:49:16.500 --> 00:49:20.760
He narrowed his eyes, and tipped his chin

00:49:20.760 --> 00:49:21.840
at the spectacled dragon.

00:49:21.900 --> 00:49:24.659
Blue and Luna glanced over at her.

00:49:24.719 --> 00:49:27.539
The elderly dragon had her snout down

00:49:27.539 --> 00:49:29.280
close to a box of honey sticks.

00:49:29.340 --> 00:49:30.599
As they watched.

00:49:30.719 --> 00:49:33.599
She nudged a bag of sugar cubes closer to

00:49:33.599 --> 00:49:35.340
her, and tapped it with a claw.

00:49:35.400 --> 00:49:37.980
Mumbling as though she was counting each

00:49:37.980 --> 00:49:38.519
cube.

00:49:38.579 --> 00:49:42.119
Luna shot the clerk in, are you kidding

00:49:42.119 --> 00:49:42.420
me?

00:49:42.480 --> 00:49:43.260
Look.

00:49:43.320 --> 00:49:45.239
He pretended not to see it.

00:49:45.300 --> 00:49:47.579
We can wait.

00:49:47.639 --> 00:49:49.440
Blue whispered to her.

00:49:49.500 --> 00:49:51.900
Causing trouble would only get them

00:49:51.900 --> 00:49:53.699
kicked out with no honey drops.

00:49:53.820 --> 00:49:56.940
Several long moments passed.

00:49:57.000 --> 00:50:00.059
Blue studied the beautiful spun sugar

00:50:00.059 --> 00:50:03.480
artwork behind the clerk, an elegant pale

00:50:03.480 --> 00:50:06.300
green praying mantis, a glittering blue

00:50:06.300 --> 00:50:09.119
and white dragonfly, an array of

00:50:09.119 --> 00:50:11.519
different jewel colored beetles, and

00:50:11.519 --> 00:50:12.960
several miniature wasps.

00:50:13.019 --> 00:50:16.380
He wondered if it felt disrespectful to

00:50:16.380 --> 00:50:18.659
any of the hive wings to eat something

00:50:18.659 --> 00:50:20.099
their queen was named after.

00:50:20.159 --> 00:50:23.699
Was this Clerk the one who had made the

00:50:23.699 --> 00:50:25.079
delicate sugar insects?

00:50:25.139 --> 00:50:28.019
Did he spend his early mornings in the

00:50:28.019 --> 00:50:30.719
back room of the shop, carefully pouring

00:50:30.719 --> 00:50:33.480
honey into frozen teardrops, and lacing

00:50:33.480 --> 00:50:35.519
chocolate stars with speckles of orange

00:50:35.519 --> 00:50:36.000
peel?

00:50:36.119 --> 00:50:38.699
Did he love coming here every day?

00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:42.300
Or was he so sick of sweetness that all

00:50:42.300 --> 00:50:44.460
he could stomach anymore was the saltiest

00:50:44.460 --> 00:50:45.480
gazelle jerky?

00:50:45.539 --> 00:50:48.719
Blue guessed that the shopkeeper had

00:50:48.719 --> 00:50:50.280
hoped his rudeness would drive them

00:50:50.280 --> 00:50:50.519
away.

00:50:50.579 --> 00:50:53.400
And now he was regretting his choice

00:50:53.400 --> 00:50:56.159
because it meant 2 silk wings were

00:50:56.159 --> 00:50:58.739
lingering in his precious store, right

00:50:58.739 --> 00:51:00.659
where anyone might wander by and see

00:51:00.659 --> 00:51:00.840
them.

00:51:00.900 --> 00:51:03.599
He probably wished he had taken their

00:51:03.599 --> 00:51:05.039
money and gotten rid of them quickly.

00:51:05.099 --> 00:51:07.739
But now he was stuck waiting for his

00:51:07.739 --> 00:51:10.440
other customer to make up her mind, just

00:51:10.440 --> 00:51:10.920
as they were.

00:51:10.980 --> 00:51:14.880
The door swung open, letting in a burst

00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:17.280
of noise from outside as 2 hive wings

00:51:17.280 --> 00:51:17.579
entered.

00:51:17.699 --> 00:51:20.820
Their giddy chatter dropped away abruptly

00:51:20.820 --> 00:51:23.340
when they saw Blue and Luna standing by

00:51:23.340 --> 00:51:23.760
the counter.

00:51:23.880 --> 00:51:26.760
Oh, said one of them.

00:51:26.820 --> 00:51:28.320
Schaefer.

00:51:28.380 --> 00:51:29.099
What?

00:51:29.099 --> 00:51:31.739
Interesting new customers you have.

00:51:31.800 --> 00:51:35.519
The other one giggled, and edged past

00:51:35.519 --> 00:51:38.340
blue, keeping her wings canted away from

00:51:38.340 --> 00:51:38.940
him.

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:41.880
Don't worry, weevil, sir.

00:51:41.940 --> 00:51:45.840
I'm sure they'll be leaving soon, Chafer

00:51:45.840 --> 00:51:46.139
said.

00:51:46.199 --> 00:51:49.500
Somehow managing to be oily and tense at

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:50.280
the same time.

00:51:50.460 --> 00:51:54.599
Yes, we will, Luna piped up, as soon as

00:51:54.599 --> 00:51:55.500
we get our honey drops.

00:51:55.559 --> 00:51:59.579
Chafer twitched to snout at her, as if

00:51:59.579 --> 00:52:01.440
she were an actual moth he'd found

00:52:01.440 --> 00:52:02.820
nibbling on one of his rugs.

00:52:02.880 --> 00:52:05.460
By the hive.

00:52:05.519 --> 00:52:08.820
What a bore it must be to be wingless.

00:52:08.940 --> 00:52:12.900
Weevil said, pacing around the 2 silkwing

00:52:12.900 --> 00:52:13.679
dragonettes.

00:52:13.739 --> 00:52:16.500
I bet you feel like half a dragon.

00:52:16.559 --> 00:52:18.719
Hardly a dragon at all.

00:52:18.780 --> 00:52:22.139
Such cute little wing buds, though.

00:52:22.199 --> 00:52:23.400
Can I touch one?

00:52:23.519 --> 00:52:26.219
He reached out toward Luna's back.

00:52:26.280 --> 00:52:28.679
No, Luna cried.

00:52:28.739 --> 00:52:29.940
Jerking away from him.

00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:33.239
Blue wasn't sure which dragon was the

00:52:33.239 --> 00:52:36.659
most horrified, himself, chafer or the

00:52:36.659 --> 00:52:37.559
rude hive wing.

00:52:37.619 --> 00:52:39.360
You can touch mine.

00:52:39.420 --> 00:52:40.980
He said quickly.

00:52:41.039 --> 00:52:44.039
It's her metamorphosis day, so she's

00:52:44.039 --> 00:52:45.480
there.

00:52:45.480 --> 00:52:48.539
It's um, better not to touch them right

00:52:48.539 --> 00:52:49.260
before the change.

00:52:49.320 --> 00:52:51.480
That wasn't true at all.

00:52:51.539 --> 00:52:54.000
Luna was just being difficult and

00:52:54.000 --> 00:52:56.099
impertinent to dragons who could really

00:52:56.099 --> 00:52:58.139
get them in a lot of trouble if they

00:52:58.139 --> 00:52:58.559
wanted to.

00:52:58.619 --> 00:53:02.219
Those soldiers outside could be summoned

00:53:02.219 --> 00:53:04.440
at a moment's notice by any hive wing.

00:53:04.500 --> 00:53:06.360
Oh.

00:53:06.480 --> 00:53:07.980
Said Weevil.

00:53:08.039 --> 00:53:12.179
Right, of course, he added, as though he

00:53:12.179 --> 00:53:13.440
obviously knew everything about

00:53:13.440 --> 00:53:14.579
metamorphosis.

00:53:14.579 --> 00:53:18.000
How exciting for you, little silk wing.

00:53:18.059 --> 00:53:20.940
He reached out his talons and poked

00:53:20.940 --> 00:53:23.280
Blue's wing buds roughly. as though

00:53:23.280 --> 00:53:25.199
Weevil was trying to unfurl them by

00:53:25.199 --> 00:53:25.619
force.

00:53:25.679 --> 00:53:27.900
Blue tried not to wince.

00:53:28.019 --> 00:53:31.320
He tried to make it better by imagining

00:53:31.320 --> 00:53:32.219
Weevil's life.

00:53:32.340 --> 00:53:35.280
A family who loved him, perhaps, who

00:53:35.280 --> 00:53:36.539
hugged him goodbye in the morning.

00:53:36.599 --> 00:53:39.780
Maybe he'd desperately wanted to be a

00:53:39.780 --> 00:53:42.239
soldier, but hadn't qualified for the

00:53:42.239 --> 00:53:42.900
academies.

00:53:42.960 --> 00:53:45.719
Maybe he'd been reassigned to a

00:53:45.719 --> 00:53:48.539
management or gathering job instead, which

00:53:48.539 --> 00:53:50.820
made him bitter and imperious with anyone

00:53:50.820 --> 00:53:52.260
he could safely push around.

00:53:52.320 --> 00:53:56.099
It was difficult, though, to slide into

00:53:56.099 --> 00:53:57.900
sympathy with this particular dragon.

00:53:57.960 --> 00:54:01.800
Possibly, he was just a jerk, and had

00:54:01.800 --> 00:54:02.760
always been that way.

00:54:02.820 --> 00:54:06.300
The old hive wing with the spectacles

00:54:06.300 --> 00:54:08.699
suddenly appeared at Weevil's side.

00:54:08.760 --> 00:54:11.699
There's no need to be a brute weevil.

00:54:11.760 --> 00:54:13.079
She said to him.

00:54:13.139 --> 00:54:16.199
Could you help me with these nectar vials

00:54:16.199 --> 00:54:16.619
over here?

00:54:16.679 --> 00:54:20.340
I'm always afraid my old claws will drop

00:54:20.340 --> 00:54:20.579
one.

00:54:20.639 --> 00:54:23.460
Of course, Lady Scarab.

00:54:23.579 --> 00:54:25.619
Weevil said deferentially.

00:54:25.679 --> 00:54:28.500
He let go of blue and followed her to the

00:54:28.500 --> 00:54:29.400
other side of the shop.

00:54:29.460 --> 00:54:33.539
Waity scarab, Blue thought.

00:54:33.599 --> 00:54:36.719
If she had a title, she must be related

00:54:36.719 --> 00:54:37.320
to the queen.

00:54:37.440 --> 00:54:40.380
A sister, or an aunt perhaps?

00:54:40.440 --> 00:54:42.840
But not one with her own hive.

00:54:42.840 --> 00:54:46.679
Still, she would be way up the hierarchy

00:54:46.679 --> 00:54:48.840
of the hive wings, which explained

00:54:48.840 --> 00:54:50.280
Weevil's behavior toward her.

00:54:50.340 --> 00:54:55.320
Hmm, someone said honey drops, and now I

00:54:55.320 --> 00:54:58.739
must have them, said Weevil's friend, who

00:54:58.739 --> 00:55:00.659
had been blissfully pretending not to see

00:55:00.659 --> 00:55:01.739
Luna or Blue.

00:55:01.860 --> 00:55:03.719
We'll take 8 of those.

00:55:03.780 --> 00:55:06.780
Six of the little sugar wasps and a box

00:55:06.780 --> 00:55:07.980
of apricot taffy.

00:55:08.039 --> 00:55:09.000
Make it pretty.

00:55:09.059 --> 00:55:13.139
Of course, said the sales dragon.

00:55:13.199 --> 00:55:15.900
He took a pale pink box out from under

00:55:15.900 --> 00:55:18.119
the counter and started packing her order

00:55:18.119 --> 00:55:18.539
into it.

00:55:18.599 --> 00:55:20.579
Don't say anything.

00:55:20.699 --> 00:55:24.119
Blue whispered to Luna, who was giving

00:55:24.119 --> 00:55:26.280
Chafer her best murderous glare.

00:55:26.340 --> 00:55:28.380
It's just the way it is.

00:55:28.440 --> 00:55:32.400
To her credit, and Blue's surprise.

00:55:32.460 --> 00:55:34.860
Luna bit her tongue until the 2 hive

00:55:34.860 --> 00:55:37.380
wings were gone, sailing out of the shop

00:55:37.380 --> 00:55:40.019
with their candy, and a few loud whispers

00:55:40.019 --> 00:55:42.239
about poor wingless street urchins

00:55:42.239 --> 00:55:43.320
cluttering up the place.

00:55:43.380 --> 00:55:48.179
So, Luna said to Chafer, with strained

00:55:48.179 --> 00:55:51.360
politeness, may we please have our honey

00:55:51.360 --> 00:55:52.380
drops now?

00:55:52.440 --> 00:55:55.440
After I serve the lady scarab.

00:55:55.500 --> 00:55:57.239
He said sniffly.

00:55:57.300 --> 00:56:02.280
But, those, you just, Luna protested.

00:56:02.340 --> 00:56:05.219
I beg your pardon.

00:56:05.340 --> 00:56:09.179
Blue turned and saw Lady Scarab, eyeing

00:56:09.179 --> 00:56:11.699
Chafer like a bone she'd already chewed

00:56:11.699 --> 00:56:11.820
on.

00:56:11.880 --> 00:56:14.400
She had moved on from counting sugar

00:56:14.400 --> 00:56:16.860
cubes to checking nectar vials under one

00:56:16.860 --> 00:56:17.400
of the lamps.

00:56:17.519 --> 00:56:20.760
But her talons were suddenly still, and

00:56:20.760 --> 00:56:23.099
her tail was coiled up like a snake.

00:56:23.159 --> 00:56:26.460
Am I to understand that you are delaying

00:56:26.460 --> 00:56:28.619
these little no wings on my account?

00:56:28.679 --> 00:56:33.000
It's no trouble, lady scarab.

00:56:33.059 --> 00:56:34.980
Chafer oozed.

00:56:35.039 --> 00:56:36.119
They can wait.

00:56:36.179 --> 00:56:38.820
You are my 1st priority.

00:56:38.880 --> 00:56:43.440
Well, I don't want to be, she snapped.

00:56:43.559 --> 00:56:45.780
Serve them right now.

00:56:45.840 --> 00:56:49.559
Blue poked Luna with his tail to try to

00:56:49.559 --> 00:56:50.940
get the smug look off her face.

00:56:51.000 --> 00:56:54.900
My lady, said Shafer.

00:56:54.960 --> 00:56:56.519
I quite insist.

00:56:56.579 --> 00:56:59.940
We do not serve 2nd class dragons before

00:56:59.940 --> 00:57:01.980
royalty in this establishment.

00:57:02.099 --> 00:57:07.440
Even if I insist, she said coldly.

00:57:07.559 --> 00:57:10.199
They stared at each other for a long

00:57:10.199 --> 00:57:13.079
moment, and Blue suddenly got the feeling

00:57:13.079 --> 00:57:15.239
that there was something more complicated

00:57:15.239 --> 00:57:17.519
about Lady Scarab's place in the hive

00:57:17.519 --> 00:57:20.280
than he'd realized. something that made

00:57:20.280 --> 00:57:22.440
this sales clerk willing to test the

00:57:22.440 --> 00:57:23.639
edges of her dominance.

00:57:23.699 --> 00:57:25.980
And then the air shifted.

00:57:26.039 --> 00:57:29.099
Blue's nose twitched. and twitched

00:57:29.099 --> 00:57:29.340
again.

00:57:29.400 --> 00:57:33.420
It was some kind of smell.

00:57:33.539 --> 00:57:38.099
It started small, a faint hint of

00:57:38.099 --> 00:57:41.820
rottenness, but slowly grew stronger and

00:57:41.820 --> 00:57:43.860
sharper and more horrible.

00:57:43.920 --> 00:57:46.860
Luna covered her snout with a gagging

00:57:46.860 --> 00:57:47.460
sound.

00:57:47.579 --> 00:57:50.820
My lady, chafer cried.

00:57:50.880 --> 00:57:53.280
Stumbling back as though the odor had

00:57:53.280 --> 00:57:54.119
punched him in the face.

00:57:54.179 --> 00:57:56.699
Please, don't.

00:57:56.760 --> 00:57:58.679
I'll have to close my shop for the rest

00:57:58.679 --> 00:57:59.219
of the day.

00:57:59.280 --> 00:58:00.659
This isn't necessary.

00:58:00.780 --> 00:58:04.980
I said, she hissed.

00:58:05.099 --> 00:58:07.980
Serve them right now.

00:58:08.039 --> 00:58:12.119
He scrabbled frantically behind the

00:58:12.119 --> 00:58:15.000
counter, grabbed a small white box and

00:58:15.000 --> 00:58:16.679
dumped 2 honey drops into it.

00:58:16.739 --> 00:58:20.400
Here, he gasped at Luna.

00:58:20.460 --> 00:58:21.179
Take it.

00:58:21.239 --> 00:58:22.860
How much?

00:58:22.860 --> 00:58:25.260
she asked through her talons.

00:58:25.320 --> 00:58:28.440
Just get out of here, he begged.

00:58:28.500 --> 00:58:31.980
Blue took the box, but Luna stopped to

00:58:31.980 --> 00:58:33.840
pull a pair of scales out of her pouch.

00:58:33.900 --> 00:58:35.880
She dropped them on the counter and

00:58:35.880 --> 00:58:36.840
darted toward the door.

00:58:36.900 --> 00:58:41.340
Thank you, I think, Lou said to Lady

00:58:41.340 --> 00:58:43.559
Scarab, trying not to breathe through his

00:58:43.559 --> 00:58:43.800
nose.

00:58:43.920 --> 00:58:46.980
She looked serene and supremely

00:58:46.980 --> 00:58:48.239
unbothered by the smell.

00:58:48.300 --> 00:58:51.960
Choose an establishment friendlier to

00:58:51.960 --> 00:58:54.599
silk wings next time, she suggested.

00:58:54.659 --> 00:58:57.960
He nodded. and escaped out into the

00:58:57.960 --> 00:58:59.219
market behind Luna.

00:58:59.280 --> 00:59:02.460
Was that her?

00:59:02.519 --> 00:59:05.039
Luna asked as they hurried between

00:59:05.039 --> 00:59:05.639
stalls.

00:59:05.699 --> 00:59:09.300
Did she make that awful smell?

00:59:09.360 --> 00:59:12.780
I've heard some hive wings have that

00:59:12.780 --> 00:59:15.960
power, he said, but I didn't think anyone

00:59:15.960 --> 00:59:17.280
would ever actually use it.

00:59:17.340 --> 00:59:20.099
I mean, why would they?

00:59:20.159 --> 00:59:23.280
To terrorize their enemies.

00:59:23.340 --> 00:59:24.599
Luna answered.

00:59:24.719 --> 00:59:26.039
Moons.

00:59:26.099 --> 00:59:27.239
I sure would.

00:59:27.300 --> 00:59:30.000
If I had super stink powers.

00:59:30.059 --> 00:59:32.699
I'd have blasted that weevil guy right in

00:59:32.699 --> 00:59:33.360
a snout.

00:59:33.420 --> 00:59:35.699
The moment he got anywhere near our wing

00:59:35.699 --> 00:59:36.179
buds.

00:59:36.239 --> 00:59:37.500
Ooh.

00:59:37.559 --> 00:59:39.179
That would have been awesome.

00:59:39.239 --> 00:59:42.360
For about too heartbeat.

00:59:42.480 --> 00:59:45.480
Blue pointed out, and then it would have

00:59:45.480 --> 00:59:47.639
been the opposite of awesome, because you

00:59:47.639 --> 00:59:48.659
would be in jail forever.

00:59:48.719 --> 00:59:51.360
Blue, she said.

00:59:51.420 --> 00:59:54.059
Don't you think it's unfair that hive

00:59:54.059 --> 00:59:56.280
wings can use their weapons on us anytime

00:59:56.280 --> 00:59:58.679
they want, but we can't do anything to

00:59:58.679 --> 00:59:59.099
fight back?

00:59:59.159 --> 01:00:01.079
No.

01:00:01.139 --> 01:00:04.380
He looked around quickly, but none of the

01:00:04.380 --> 01:00:06.659
nearby dragons reacted as if they'd just

01:00:06.659 --> 01:00:07.320
heard treason.

01:00:07.440 --> 01:00:10.440
It was loud enough in the market, and

01:00:10.440 --> 01:00:11.760
they were moving so quickly between

01:00:11.760 --> 01:00:14.400
stalls, that he could hope no one would

01:00:14.400 --> 01:00:14.940
overhear them.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:18.420
The hive wings saved us, remember?

01:00:18.480 --> 01:00:21.599
Our tribe agreed to accept their queen.

01:00:21.659 --> 01:00:24.840
Besides, there's a reason why the

01:00:24.840 --> 01:00:26.880
universe gave them weapons and not us.

01:00:26.940 --> 01:00:29.099
That's why they're in charge.

01:00:29.159 --> 01:00:33.059
But maybe, if we fought back, They

01:00:33.059 --> 01:00:35.579
wouldn't be in charge, she pointed out.

01:00:35.699 --> 01:00:37.679
Muna.

01:00:37.739 --> 01:00:40.440
He herded her into the tunnels that led

01:00:40.440 --> 01:00:41.820
to the other levels of the hive.

01:00:41.880 --> 01:00:44.400
His voice dropped to a whisper.

01:00:44.460 --> 01:00:46.500
For the love of silk.

01:00:46.559 --> 01:00:48.300
What's gotten into you today?

01:00:48.360 --> 01:00:51.900
I know sore tail is full of crazy ideas.

01:00:51.960 --> 01:00:54.000
But please don't let him drag you into

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:55.320
prison along with him.

01:00:55.320 --> 01:00:59.880
Those are my ideas, she said crossly.

01:00:59.940 --> 01:01:01.500
He got them from me.

01:01:01.559 --> 01:01:05.159
Well, then leave me out of it.

01:01:05.219 --> 01:01:07.019
He covered his ears.

01:01:07.079 --> 01:01:08.880
La, la, la.

01:01:08.940 --> 01:01:11.099
Everyone's a good hive citizen here.

01:01:11.219 --> 01:01:13.380
His sister rolled her eyes.

01:01:13.440 --> 01:01:15.239
Oh, Blue.

01:01:15.300 --> 01:01:19.320
She hesitated, studying his face, and

01:01:19.320 --> 01:01:21.599
then shook her head, as though she hadn't

01:01:21.599 --> 01:01:22.920
found the answer she wanted there.

01:01:22.980 --> 01:01:25.800
All right, I'm sorry.

01:01:25.860 --> 01:01:29.159
She flexed her claws and looked down at

01:01:29.159 --> 01:01:29.699
her wrists.

01:01:29.760 --> 01:01:32.699
It's probably because of my silk coming

01:01:32.699 --> 01:01:33.000
in.

01:01:33.059 --> 01:01:35.820
It hurts a lot more than I expected it

01:01:35.820 --> 01:01:36.000
to.

01:01:36.059 --> 01:01:40.500
Her palms and wrists were glowing even

01:01:40.500 --> 01:01:41.699
brighter than before.

01:01:41.820 --> 01:01:44.400
Blue hadn't noticed in the well lit

01:01:44.400 --> 01:01:44.820
market.

01:01:44.880 --> 01:01:47.760
But here in the dim tunnels, it was

01:01:47.760 --> 01:01:48.780
impossible to ignore.

01:01:48.840 --> 01:01:52.019
She seemed to have little balls of fire

01:01:52.019 --> 01:01:55.380
clustered under her scales, bubbles of

01:01:55.380 --> 01:01:57.239
molten orange and gold.

01:01:57.300 --> 01:01:59.820
That doesn't look normal.

01:01:59.940 --> 01:02:01.739
He said anxiously.

01:02:01.800 --> 01:02:05.280
I've never seen anyone's silk glands do

01:02:05.280 --> 01:02:06.719
that before metamorphosis.

01:02:06.780 --> 01:02:07.800
Have you?

01:02:07.860 --> 01:02:12.599
Sortail and his sister, Io, had gotten

01:02:12.599 --> 01:02:13.860
their wings not too long ago.

01:02:13.920 --> 01:02:17.039
He remembered their palms glowing a

01:02:17.039 --> 01:02:19.019
little bit, but not like this.

01:02:19.139 --> 01:02:21.900
And they hadn't mentioned anything about

01:02:21.900 --> 01:02:22.559
it hurting.

01:02:22.619 --> 01:02:25.619
Does metamorphosis hurt?

01:02:25.679 --> 01:02:28.260
Why wouldn't someone warn us about that?

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:30.840
I'm sure it's nothing.

01:02:30.900 --> 01:02:33.059
Luna said with a shrug.

01:02:33.119 --> 01:02:36.179
Everyone metamorphosis a little

01:02:36.179 --> 01:02:36.599
differently.

01:02:36.659 --> 01:02:39.599
Should we take you to a doctor?

01:02:39.659 --> 01:02:42.780
No way, she said.

01:02:42.840 --> 01:02:45.780
She swiped the box of honey drops out of

01:02:45.780 --> 01:02:46.500
his talons.

01:02:46.559 --> 01:02:49.440
I'm not spending my perfect last day

01:02:49.440 --> 01:02:52.260
getting prodded by some hive wing who

01:02:52.260 --> 01:02:53.820
thinks we're all weird and revolting.

01:02:53.880 --> 01:02:55.260
I'm totally fine.

01:02:55.320 --> 01:02:57.300
To the mosaic garden.

01:02:57.360 --> 01:02:58.139
Let's go.

01:02:58.199 --> 01:03:01.139
Luna darted away up the tunnel.

01:03:01.199 --> 01:03:05.460
Blue rubbed his own wrists worriedly, and

01:03:05.460 --> 01:03:06.300
then followed her.

01:03:06.360 --> 01:03:08.880
He could see the glow from her scales

01:03:08.880 --> 01:03:10.679
reflecting off the tunnel walls.

01:03:10.739 --> 01:03:13.260
Is she going to be all right?

01:03:13.380 --> 01:03:17.219
If everything has to change, Could it at

01:03:17.219 --> 01:03:19.320
least be ordinary predictable change?

01:03:19.380 --> 01:03:22.380
Spirit of clear sight.

01:03:22.440 --> 01:03:23.519
If you're listening.

01:03:23.579 --> 01:03:25.679
Please take care of my sister.

01:03:25.739 --> 01:03:28.559
Please let her metamorphosis be normal.

01:03:28.619 --> 01:03:32.579
And if you have time, please could you

01:03:32.579 --> 01:03:34.559
also make sure she's not arrested for

01:03:34.559 --> 01:03:34.980
treason?

01:03:35.039 --> 01:03:36.539
That would be great.

01:03:36.599 --> 01:03:37.559
Thanks.

01:03:37.619 --> 01:03:41.940
Chapter 3.

01:03:42.239 --> 01:03:46.199
The mosaic garden glimmered in droplets

01:03:46.199 --> 01:03:49.320
of amber and gold, cobalt and jade

01:03:49.320 --> 01:03:51.000
obsidian and pearl.

01:03:51.119 --> 01:03:54.599
Fragments of dragons prowled along the

01:03:54.599 --> 01:03:57.239
walkways under claw and coiled around the

01:03:57.239 --> 01:03:57.719
columns.

01:03:57.780 --> 01:04:01.800
In the pavilions, claws and teeth roared

01:04:01.800 --> 01:04:02.820
across the ceilings.

01:04:02.880 --> 01:04:05.880
Ancient battles captured in bits of glass

01:04:05.880 --> 01:04:06.840
forever.

01:04:06.900 --> 01:04:10.980
Here at the top of the hive, the sky was

01:04:10.980 --> 01:04:11.820
allowed to run free.

01:04:11.880 --> 01:04:15.480
It was the only space where hive wings

01:04:15.480 --> 01:04:18.119
could look up and see no roof, unless

01:04:18.119 --> 01:04:19.980
they wanted to climb to the top layers of

01:04:19.980 --> 01:04:23.639
the webs, which hive wings never did, or

01:04:23.639 --> 01:04:25.619
venture into the dry savannah below.

01:04:25.679 --> 01:04:30.000
Across the garden, sunlight drenched the

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:33.000
grassy slopes and hedgerows, soaking into

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:35.760
the obedient faces of the flowers that

01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:39.059
marched rose carnation, marigold, violet

01:04:39.059 --> 01:04:41.219
and orderly lines beside the path.

01:04:41.280 --> 01:04:45.659
The scents were heavy and warm, like the

01:04:45.659 --> 01:04:48.179
drowsy buzzing insects that browsed the

01:04:48.179 --> 01:04:48.960
floral options.

01:04:49.019 --> 01:04:52.380
The path itself seemed winding and random

01:04:52.380 --> 01:04:55.800
branching and wandering back, but it

01:04:55.800 --> 01:04:57.659
eventually spiraled everyone into the

01:04:57.659 --> 01:04:58.139
central feature.

01:04:58.199 --> 01:05:00.119
The Salvation Wall.

01:05:00.179 --> 01:05:03.480
This morning, the garden was busy with

01:05:03.480 --> 01:05:06.300
dragons, but Blue and Luna found a spot

01:05:06.300 --> 01:05:08.280
on the grassy slope, where they could

01:05:08.280 --> 01:05:10.199
sprawl with a view of the Salvation

01:05:10.199 --> 01:05:10.860
Mosaic.

01:05:10.920 --> 01:05:14.219
I'm not sure why you like this scene so

01:05:14.219 --> 01:05:17.579
much, Blue said, as Luna passed him his

01:05:17.579 --> 01:05:18.059
honey drop.

01:05:18.119 --> 01:05:21.719
It has a few too many dead silk wings in

01:05:21.719 --> 01:05:22.079
it for me.

01:05:22.139 --> 01:05:25.559
His wing buds twitched, and he glanced

01:05:25.559 --> 01:05:27.960
around, double checking that there were

01:05:27.960 --> 01:05:29.400
no hive wings and earshot.

01:05:29.460 --> 01:05:32.519
He didn't think, it was treason to

01:05:32.519 --> 01:05:35.280
criticize the Salvation Mosaic, but it

01:05:35.280 --> 01:05:35.880
certainly might be.

01:05:35.940 --> 01:05:39.119
But even more dead leaf wings.

01:05:39.179 --> 01:05:41.039
Luna pointed out.

01:05:41.159 --> 01:05:42.840
Isn't that reassuring?

01:05:42.900 --> 01:05:44.880
Blue didn't argue with her.

01:05:44.940 --> 01:05:47.760
But he'd always found the mosaic sad

01:05:47.760 --> 01:05:49.019
instead of triumphant.

01:05:49.079 --> 01:05:51.659
He knew it showed the end of the war.

01:05:51.719 --> 01:05:54.059
So it made sense that there were dead

01:05:54.059 --> 01:05:55.019
dragons in it.

01:05:55.139 --> 01:05:57.719
It should make him glad that these were

01:05:57.719 --> 01:05:59.880
supposed to be the last dragons ever

01:05:59.880 --> 01:06:01.739
killed in the war with the leaf wings.

01:06:01.800 --> 01:06:04.980
He also knew they should all be grateful

01:06:04.980 --> 01:06:07.320
to the hive wings for saving the silk

01:06:07.320 --> 01:06:09.000
wings from the vicious green tribe.

01:06:09.059 --> 01:06:12.900
But it just made him wonder why there had

01:06:12.900 --> 01:06:13.739
to be a war at all.

01:06:13.860 --> 01:06:16.800
Why didn't the leaf wings give up and go

01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:17.159
away?

01:06:17.219 --> 01:06:20.219
Or agree to be ruled by Queen Wasp.

01:06:20.280 --> 01:06:22.860
Why did they fight so hard instead?

01:06:22.920 --> 01:06:25.980
They must have known they couldn't win?

01:06:26.039 --> 01:06:28.800
There were so many more hive wings.

01:06:28.920 --> 01:06:32.039
And of course, there was the book, which

01:06:32.039 --> 01:06:34.079
was guaranteed to guide the hive wings to

01:06:34.079 --> 01:06:34.380
victory.

01:06:34.440 --> 01:06:37.500
So why do the leaf wings bother

01:06:37.500 --> 01:06:37.860
fighting?

01:06:37.980 --> 01:06:40.920
Knowing so many dragons would die for no

01:06:40.920 --> 01:06:41.400
good reason?

01:06:41.460 --> 01:06:45.360
It was their own fault their tribe was

01:06:45.360 --> 01:06:48.059
wiped out, if Luna was right, and they

01:06:48.059 --> 01:06:49.019
were really gone.

01:06:49.079 --> 01:06:51.719
Queen Sequoia should have given up her

01:06:51.719 --> 01:06:54.300
throne and accepted Queen Wasp's

01:06:54.300 --> 01:06:56.880
protection, like Queen Monarch did.

01:06:56.940 --> 01:06:59.280
Then the leaf wings could have lived

01:06:59.280 --> 01:07:00.840
alongside the silk wings.

01:07:00.900 --> 01:07:04.380
All 3 tribes under one queen, working

01:07:04.380 --> 01:07:04.800
together.

01:07:04.860 --> 01:07:08.400
Maybe Queen Wasp would have left them

01:07:08.400 --> 01:07:10.320
some trees to live in, between the

01:07:10.320 --> 01:07:10.679
hives.

01:07:10.739 --> 01:07:13.380
So what made them fight instead of

01:07:13.380 --> 01:07:13.980
accepting that?

01:07:14.039 --> 01:07:17.099
Had their queen really thought her tribe

01:07:17.099 --> 01:07:18.360
had any chance of winning?

01:07:18.480 --> 01:07:22.260
Blue studied the blocky, dark green shape

01:07:22.260 --> 01:07:23.940
that was meant to be the queen of the

01:07:23.940 --> 01:07:24.480
leaf wings.

01:07:24.599 --> 01:07:27.659
It was so hard to imagine being Queen

01:07:27.659 --> 01:07:31.260
Sequoia, leading an entire tribe into a

01:07:31.260 --> 01:07:31.679
doomed war.

01:07:31.739 --> 01:07:34.619
He didn't even like arguing with other

01:07:34.619 --> 01:07:35.280
dragons.

01:07:35.340 --> 01:07:38.099
If someone offered blue, peace and

01:07:38.099 --> 01:07:38.639
stability.

01:07:38.699 --> 01:07:40.860
And all he had to give up was a little

01:07:40.860 --> 01:07:43.320
independence, he would say yes in a

01:07:43.320 --> 01:07:43.800
heartbeat.

01:07:43.860 --> 01:07:48.119
I hope I get to see it one day, Luna said

01:07:48.119 --> 01:07:50.159
licking honey off her claws.

01:07:50.219 --> 01:07:51.719
What?

01:07:51.719 --> 01:07:54.480
he said, startled out of his reverie.

01:07:54.539 --> 01:07:58.019
She pointed at the mosaic, at the central

01:07:58.019 --> 01:08:00.599
yellow and black striped figure, holding

01:08:00.599 --> 01:08:02.400
a rectangular shape over her head.

01:08:02.460 --> 01:08:05.940
The only object in the mosaic made

01:08:05.940 --> 01:08:08.820
entirely of gold tiles, so it caught the

01:08:08.820 --> 01:08:10.320
sun like a fragment of fire.

01:08:10.380 --> 01:08:12.780
The book of clear sight.

01:08:12.840 --> 01:08:14.579
Luna said softly.

01:08:14.639 --> 01:08:17.340
Don't you ever wonder what it says?

01:08:17.399 --> 01:08:20.399
What the next big disaster will be?

01:08:20.460 --> 01:08:22.739
Or what's going to happen to all of us

01:08:22.739 --> 01:08:23.039
next?

01:08:23.100 --> 01:08:26.640
Of course, Blue said.

01:08:26.699 --> 01:08:29.399
But nobody gets to read it except the

01:08:29.399 --> 01:08:30.479
queen and the librarian.

01:08:30.539 --> 01:08:34.079
I could see it though, Luna said.

01:08:34.140 --> 01:08:35.579
From a distance.

01:08:35.640 --> 01:08:37.859
If I get to visit the temple one day.

01:08:37.920 --> 01:08:43.140
Whoa, wasp hive's not that far away, Blue

01:08:43.140 --> 01:08:43.560
said.

01:08:43.619 --> 01:08:46.079
It'll be easy to visit the Temple of

01:08:46.079 --> 01:08:48.060
Clearsight once you have wings.

01:08:48.119 --> 01:08:51.420
If you're assigned a job with travel

01:08:51.420 --> 01:08:54.239
permission and time off, he thought.

01:08:54.300 --> 01:08:56.399
But didn't say out loud.

01:08:56.460 --> 01:08:59.220
Luna had enough to worry about.

01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:02.699
He stole a glance at her wrists, which

01:09:02.699 --> 01:09:04.619
she kept rubbing and then resting in the

01:09:04.619 --> 01:09:05.159
cool grass.

01:09:05.220 --> 01:09:08.640
With the quiet lavender scales on his

01:09:08.640 --> 01:09:11.100
arms glow like that in 6 days.

01:09:11.159 --> 01:09:14.279
Was metamorphosis really more painful

01:09:14.279 --> 01:09:15.659
than anyone had warned them?

01:09:15.720 --> 01:09:19.199
He'd expected his wings to hurt a little

01:09:19.199 --> 01:09:21.539
as they came in, but he hadn't even

01:09:21.539 --> 01:09:22.920
thought to worry about his silk.

01:09:22.979 --> 01:09:25.799
They heard the chatter of approaching

01:09:25.799 --> 01:09:26.699
Dragonettes.

01:09:26.760 --> 01:09:29.039
Enough voices that it was probably a

01:09:29.039 --> 01:09:31.079
field trip from one of the fancy hive

01:09:31.079 --> 01:09:31.680
wing schools.

01:09:31.739 --> 01:09:35.279
Blue scooped up the empty sugar dream box

01:09:35.279 --> 01:09:37.439
and they retreated to a less crowded

01:09:37.439 --> 01:09:39.479
section of the garden, where they played

01:09:39.479 --> 01:09:42.060
hide and seek, until the sun reached its

01:09:42.060 --> 01:09:44.760
highest and began to slant back down the

01:09:44.760 --> 01:09:45.180
sky.

01:09:45.239 --> 01:09:48.539
They ate lunch at Luna's favorite cafe

01:09:48.600 --> 01:09:51.479
and then wandered through the lady cicada

01:09:51.479 --> 01:09:53.699
art gallery on one of the lower floors of

01:09:53.699 --> 01:09:54.119
the hive.

01:09:54.180 --> 01:09:57.180
Blue found all the different portraits of

01:09:57.180 --> 01:10:00.239
Lady Zicada, little intense, but Luna

01:10:00.239 --> 01:10:01.560
liked the tapestry rooms.

01:10:01.619 --> 01:10:04.380
Weavings were the one kind of art that

01:10:04.380 --> 01:10:06.300
was left entirely to silk wings.

01:10:06.359 --> 01:10:09.840
A hive wing could probably buy dyed silk

01:10:09.840 --> 01:10:12.659
threads from one of the market stalls, and

01:10:12.659 --> 01:10:15.060
a loom, like the ones silk wing

01:10:15.060 --> 01:10:16.560
dragonettes used for practice.

01:10:16.619 --> 01:10:18.720
But none of them would bother with

01:10:18.720 --> 01:10:20.819
learning to make a low silk wing art.

01:10:20.880 --> 01:10:22.979
Which Blue thought was a bit silly.

01:10:23.039 --> 01:10:25.439
They certainly didn't mind buying the

01:10:25.439 --> 01:10:27.359
results, and hanging them all over their

01:10:27.359 --> 01:10:27.960
walls.

01:10:28.020 --> 01:10:30.899
He left Luna gazing at her favorite

01:10:30.899 --> 01:10:34.260
tapestry, the one where Lady Cicada is

01:10:34.260 --> 01:10:36.659
flying with a long trail of radiant silk

01:10:36.659 --> 01:10:37.800
wings behind her in the sky.

01:10:37.859 --> 01:10:40.500
While he checked out the sculpture

01:10:40.500 --> 01:10:40.800
rooms.

01:10:40.920 --> 01:10:44.039
Lady Cicada was old enough to have been

01:10:44.039 --> 01:10:45.659
alive when there were still trees to

01:10:45.659 --> 01:10:46.020
spare.

01:10:46.079 --> 01:10:49.020
So there was one small wooden carving of

01:10:49.020 --> 01:10:51.060
her in the middle of the clay and metal

01:10:51.060 --> 01:10:52.020
and marble statues.

01:10:52.140 --> 01:10:55.199
The wood was a shade of brown close to

01:10:55.199 --> 01:10:56.279
her actual red color.

01:10:56.340 --> 01:10:59.579
And Blue liked to look at it, and wonder

01:10:59.579 --> 01:11:00.300
about the artist.

01:11:00.359 --> 01:11:03.300
What did wood carvers do when there were

01:11:03.300 --> 01:11:04.500
no more trees to carve?

01:11:04.619 --> 01:11:06.840
Did they still get to make art?

01:11:06.899 --> 01:11:09.300
And did they have to learn all new

01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:10.140
techniques?

01:11:10.199 --> 01:11:12.300
Or did the queen give them new jobs?

01:11:12.420 --> 01:11:15.779
Did they ever wish all the trees weren't

01:11:15.779 --> 01:11:15.960
gone?

01:11:16.020 --> 01:11:20.279
Let's get to the cocoon, Luna said

01:11:20.279 --> 01:11:21.779
appearing behind him.

01:11:21.840 --> 01:11:25.020
Her pale green scales looked white in the

01:11:25.020 --> 01:11:27.539
dim light of the gallery, and it was hard

01:11:27.539 --> 01:11:29.579
to see the gold flecks along her back and

01:11:29.579 --> 01:11:29.819
tail.

01:11:29.880 --> 01:11:33.060
Her wing beds were definitely more

01:11:33.060 --> 01:11:34.859
unfurled than they had been this morning

01:11:34.859 --> 01:11:37.619
though, and her wrists were glowing as

01:11:37.619 --> 01:11:38.640
brightly as the lamps.

01:11:38.760 --> 01:11:42.899
We have a little more time, Blue said

01:11:42.899 --> 01:11:44.880
seized with a sudden panic.

01:11:44.939 --> 01:11:49.020
We could get another honey drop, or no

01:11:49.020 --> 01:11:50.460
Luna said.

01:11:50.520 --> 01:11:54.000
Her expression was strange, as though she

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:55.319
was already drifting into the

01:11:55.319 --> 01:11:56.579
metamorphosis trance.

01:11:56.640 --> 01:12:01.079
I think I need to get to the cocoon as as

01:12:01.079 --> 01:12:01.800
quick as we can.

01:12:01.859 --> 01:12:05.460
All right, Blue said.

01:12:05.520 --> 01:12:07.979
Should he have made her see a doctor

01:12:07.979 --> 01:12:08.399
after all?

01:12:08.460 --> 01:12:11.699
But someone at the cocoon would know what

01:12:11.699 --> 01:12:13.199
to do if there was anything wrong

01:12:13.199 --> 01:12:14.279
surely.

01:12:14.340 --> 01:12:18.180
They hurried to the outer spiral and down

01:12:18.180 --> 01:12:23.159
level after level getting darker, as they

01:12:23.159 --> 01:12:24.779
descended in strange silence.

01:12:24.840 --> 01:12:28.619
For Luna, Blue couldn't remember a time

01:12:28.619 --> 01:12:30.300
when she'd stopped talking for this

01:12:30.300 --> 01:12:30.779
long.

01:12:30.840 --> 01:12:33.779
Blue wasn't sure if he was imagining that

01:12:33.779 --> 01:12:36.899
the hum seemed louder down here, as if

01:12:36.899 --> 01:12:38.939
the insects outside were closer to the

01:12:38.939 --> 01:12:41.520
hive, busily swarming around it.

01:12:41.579 --> 01:12:45.180
The cocoon wasn't on quite the lowest

01:12:45.180 --> 01:12:48.180
ground floor level of the hive, but it

01:12:48.180 --> 01:12:48.720
was close to it.

01:12:48.779 --> 01:12:51.659
Here, the streets were dimmer and

01:12:51.659 --> 01:12:52.260
emptier.

01:12:52.319 --> 01:12:54.840
The lamps fewer and farther between.

01:12:54.960 --> 01:12:58.560
A few lower class hive wings lived down

01:12:58.560 --> 01:13:01.319
here, in the small cells near the outer

01:13:01.319 --> 01:13:01.800
spiral.

01:13:01.859 --> 01:13:04.800
There was one hulking building that Blue

01:13:04.800 --> 01:13:06.539
thought might be a training center for

01:13:06.539 --> 01:13:06.899
guards.

01:13:06.960 --> 01:13:10.140
The courtyard around it was open for a

01:13:10.140 --> 01:13:12.600
few levels up, to give them space to fly

01:13:12.600 --> 01:13:13.500
their exercises.

01:13:13.560 --> 01:13:15.960
Blue glanced up as they went by.

01:13:16.020 --> 01:13:18.779
Watching the dragons moving around the

01:13:18.779 --> 01:13:19.560
streets above them.

01:13:19.619 --> 01:13:22.739
Occasionally a flutter of black and red

01:13:22.739 --> 01:13:24.000
wings broke the quiet.

01:13:24.060 --> 01:13:26.699
As a hive wing flew from one side of the

01:13:26.699 --> 01:13:28.979
hive to the other, to save walking time.

01:13:29.039 --> 01:13:31.619
But the main thing on this level.

01:13:31.739 --> 01:13:33.119
Was the cocoon.

01:13:33.180 --> 01:13:38.100
A long oval dome, 2 levels tall, which

01:13:38.100 --> 01:13:40.560
was swathed in so many beautiful weavings

01:13:40.560 --> 01:13:43.079
it almost seemed to be made out of silk

01:13:43.079 --> 01:13:43.739
itself.

01:13:43.800 --> 01:13:47.880
Every silk wing and cicada hive came here

01:13:47.880 --> 01:13:49.800
for his or her metamorphosis.

01:13:49.920 --> 01:13:53.159
And according to tradition, Afterward

01:13:53.159 --> 01:13:55.920
each one made a silk weaving for the dome

01:13:55.920 --> 01:13:57.300
as an offering of thanks.

01:13:57.359 --> 01:14:00.899
Some of the weavings, especially the

01:14:00.899 --> 01:14:02.939
older ones were simple.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:05.939
Shimmery, silver, gray silk, in the shape

01:14:05.939 --> 01:14:09.000
of cobwebs, or sunbursts, or clouds.

01:14:09.119 --> 01:14:12.479
Other dragons had used dyes to add

01:14:12.479 --> 01:14:13.500
brilliant colors.

01:14:13.560 --> 01:14:16.979
Here, a silver dragon spangled with

01:14:16.979 --> 01:14:19.199
emerald green wings and matching green

01:14:19.199 --> 01:14:20.220
eyes all around her.

01:14:20.279 --> 01:14:24.060
Here a swarm of tiny orange butterflies

01:14:24.060 --> 01:14:27.359
someone had even been able to afford 2

01:14:27.359 --> 01:14:30.539
colors, weaving a midnight black shape of

01:14:30.539 --> 01:14:33.659
a hive behind an iridescent blue web.

01:14:33.720 --> 01:14:36.119
There were no trees, of course.

01:14:36.180 --> 01:14:39.300
It was forbidden to include trees and art

01:14:39.300 --> 01:14:41.520
ever since the leaf wings had been driven

01:14:41.520 --> 01:14:41.699
out.

01:14:41.760 --> 01:14:44.880
Even the hive shape was dangerously

01:14:44.880 --> 01:14:45.899
closed to that of a tree.

01:14:45.960 --> 01:14:48.779
And Blue wondered if the weaver had been

01:14:48.779 --> 01:14:49.319
worried about that.

01:14:49.380 --> 01:14:53.460
But for the 1st time, Maybe because

01:14:53.460 --> 01:14:55.560
anxiety was sharpening his attention.

01:14:55.619 --> 01:14:58.439
Blue noticed something on one of the

01:14:58.439 --> 01:15:00.539
tapestries that looked like a leaf.

01:15:00.600 --> 01:15:01.920
No, wait.

01:15:01.979 --> 01:15:03.840
Was it a teardrop?

01:15:03.960 --> 01:15:06.779
A single autumn red shape.

01:15:06.840 --> 01:15:10.079
Somewhere between a leaf and a teardrop

01:15:10.079 --> 01:15:13.859
and no bigger than his claw tip, gleamed

01:15:13.859 --> 01:15:15.899
in the middle of the butterfly swarm.

01:15:15.960 --> 01:15:17.699
Was he seeing that right?

01:15:17.760 --> 01:15:21.180
Why spend the money on a 2nd die color

01:15:21.180 --> 01:15:23.640
and only use it in such a small way?

01:15:23.699 --> 01:15:25.380
Wait.

01:15:25.439 --> 01:15:26.819
There was another one.

01:15:26.880 --> 01:15:29.699
He blinked, startled.

01:15:29.819 --> 01:15:32.460
This one was slightly darker red.

01:15:32.520 --> 01:15:35.520
Hidden against the black backdrop of the

01:15:35.520 --> 01:15:36.300
hive weaving.

01:15:36.359 --> 01:15:39.180
His eyes scanned the dome.

01:15:39.300 --> 01:15:40.920
There was another.

01:15:40.979 --> 01:15:44.220
Veiled among a spray of escaping diamonds

01:15:44.220 --> 01:15:45.060
from a waterfall.

01:15:45.119 --> 01:15:48.840
Blue wrinkled his snout, puzzled.

01:15:48.899 --> 01:15:51.600
Now that he was looking, there were

01:15:51.600 --> 01:15:53.819
little red leaf drops hidden in half the

01:15:53.819 --> 01:15:54.779
weavings he could see.

01:15:54.840 --> 01:15:58.680
Why had so many silk wings decided to

01:15:58.680 --> 01:16:00.659
include that shape and that color?

01:16:00.720 --> 01:16:04.020
If it meant something, why didn't he know

01:16:04.020 --> 01:16:04.319
about it?

01:16:04.380 --> 01:16:08.220
Blue realized that Luna was staring up at

01:16:08.220 --> 01:16:10.800
the dome weavings too, opening and

01:16:10.800 --> 01:16:12.539
closing her talons nervously.

01:16:12.600 --> 01:16:15.720
He thought about asking her if she'd

01:16:15.720 --> 01:16:17.279
noticed the hidden red shapes.

01:16:17.340 --> 01:16:19.800
But it wasn't worth it to start a

01:16:19.800 --> 01:16:21.600
conversation that might stress her out.

01:16:21.659 --> 01:16:24.659
What she needed was distraction and

01:16:24.659 --> 01:16:25.439
calming down.

01:16:25.500 --> 01:16:28.979
What you're weaving going to look like?

01:16:28.979 --> 01:16:29.939
he asked.

01:16:30.000 --> 01:16:31.260
Have you decided?

01:16:31.380 --> 01:16:34.560
She'd been talking about nothing else for

01:16:34.560 --> 01:16:35.100
weeks.

01:16:35.159 --> 01:16:37.380
So Blue had heard all her ideas.

01:16:37.439 --> 01:16:40.020
But he was mostly trying to get her to

01:16:40.020 --> 01:16:43.439
smile, or blink, or do anything to

01:16:43.439 --> 01:16:45.479
reassure him that his bubbly sister was

01:16:45.479 --> 01:16:46.020
still in there.

01:16:46.079 --> 01:16:48.239
Luna winced.

01:16:48.300 --> 01:16:50.880
I don't know, she said.

01:16:50.939 --> 01:16:52.439
I have to.

01:16:52.920 --> 01:16:54.720
Get through this first.

01:16:54.779 --> 01:16:58.739
You'll be fine, Blue said.

01:16:58.800 --> 01:17:01.079
Taking her front talons in his.

01:17:01.199 --> 01:17:04.140
I've never heard of anything going wrong

01:17:04.140 --> 01:17:05.579
during a metamorphosis.

01:17:05.640 --> 01:17:08.159
I'm sure what you're feeling is totally

01:17:08.159 --> 01:17:08.699
normal.

01:17:08.760 --> 01:17:10.739
All of this is normal.

01:17:10.800 --> 01:17:12.600
It's going to be all right.

01:17:12.659 --> 01:17:15.840
Everything is always all right in the end

01:17:15.840 --> 01:17:16.199
you know?

01:17:16.260 --> 01:17:18.779
You're going to wake up with awesome

01:17:18.779 --> 01:17:22.380
wings and cool silk and fly everywhere

01:17:22.500 --> 01:17:24.600
and be the greatest spinner in the

01:17:24.600 --> 01:17:25.439
history of the hives.

01:17:25.560 --> 01:17:29.100
Luna closed her eyes and whispered.

01:17:29.220 --> 01:17:33.779
Everything is always all right, as though

01:17:33.779 --> 01:17:36.899
he'd just said, the sun is always shining

01:17:36.899 --> 01:17:40.319
or, the bees would absolutely love for

01:17:40.319 --> 01:17:41.399
you to take all their honey.

01:17:41.460 --> 01:17:42.479
Instead.

01:17:42.539 --> 01:17:46.140
Blue was relieved to see a cluster of

01:17:46.140 --> 01:17:48.300
dragons gathered near the low arched

01:17:48.300 --> 01:17:49.680
entrance of the cocoon.

01:17:49.739 --> 01:17:51.840
Maybe one of them could get through to

01:17:51.840 --> 01:17:52.319
Luna.

01:17:52.380 --> 01:17:56.279
Look how popular you are, he joked.

01:17:56.340 --> 01:17:59.939
But his smile faded, as they got closer

01:17:59.939 --> 01:18:02.579
and he realized that most of the gathered

01:18:02.579 --> 01:18:04.979
dragons were hive wing guards.

01:18:05.039 --> 01:18:07.619
Why are there so many guards?

01:18:07.739 --> 01:18:10.920
He was sure that normally there were only

01:18:10.920 --> 01:18:11.159
two.

01:18:11.279 --> 01:18:14.460
He remembered the 2 extremely bored

01:18:14.460 --> 01:18:16.439
looking guards who had fallen asleep by

01:18:16.439 --> 01:18:19.199
the exit during Swordell's metamorphosis

01:18:19.199 --> 01:18:21.359
while he and Luna called encouraging

01:18:21.359 --> 01:18:22.199
words to their friend.

01:18:22.260 --> 01:18:25.739
But today, there were at least 5 outside

01:18:25.739 --> 01:18:28.680
and they all looked anything but bored.

01:18:28.800 --> 01:18:32.399
Black and yellow and red scales shifted

01:18:32.399 --> 01:18:35.039
and caught the dim lamplight, as the hive

01:18:35.039 --> 01:18:36.779
wings scowled and stamped their feet.

01:18:36.840 --> 01:18:39.420
Two of them carried weapons.

01:18:39.479 --> 01:18:41.819
But the other 3 looked menacing enough

01:18:41.819 --> 01:18:42.359
without them.

01:18:42.420 --> 01:18:45.899
Most likely they had venom in their claws

01:18:45.899 --> 01:18:48.659
or shot poisonous darts from their tails

01:18:48.659 --> 01:18:50.939
or something along those lines.

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:53.579
Blue shot a worried look at Luna.

01:18:53.640 --> 01:18:57.539
First silverspot, and Luna's weird

01:18:57.539 --> 01:18:58.619
glowing scales.

01:18:58.680 --> 01:19:00.659
Now all these guards.

01:19:00.779 --> 01:19:04.140
What does everyone know that we don't?

01:19:04.199 --> 01:19:08.399
Chapter 4.

01:19:08.640 --> 01:19:11.939
Blue had to keep Luna calm.

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:13.979
Whatever was going on?

01:19:14.039 --> 01:19:15.659
He didn't want her to go into her

01:19:15.659 --> 01:19:18.000
metamorphosis feeling scared or anxious.

01:19:18.060 --> 01:19:21.119
Why are there so many guards today?

01:19:21.180 --> 01:19:23.460
Luna whispered to Blue.

01:19:23.520 --> 01:19:26.399
Weren't there only 2 at SoraTales

01:19:26.399 --> 01:19:27.180
metamorphosis?

01:19:27.239 --> 01:19:31.140
Oh, I don't remember, he said brightly.

01:19:31.199 --> 01:19:34.020
I'm sure there are always this many, and

01:19:34.020 --> 01:19:35.100
we just never noticed them.

01:19:35.159 --> 01:19:38.399
Hmm, she said doubtfully.

01:19:38.460 --> 01:19:40.439
Muna.

01:19:40.500 --> 01:19:43.439
Swartail cried, emerging from the group

01:19:43.439 --> 01:19:44.880
and bounding toward them.

01:19:44.939 --> 01:19:48.180
His scales were dark blue, with a small

01:19:48.180 --> 01:19:50.220
pattern of white triangles along his

01:19:50.220 --> 01:19:53.100
spine and snout, and then dappled all

01:19:53.100 --> 01:19:55.859
over with orange splotches, as though

01:19:55.859 --> 01:19:58.319
someone had melted a sunset in a cauldron

01:19:58.319 --> 01:20:00.119
and flung it at his wings.

01:20:00.180 --> 01:20:03.119
Blue always thought of his friend as one

01:20:03.119 --> 01:20:05.880
of the shiniest silk wings around, bright

01:20:05.880 --> 01:20:08.699
and gleaming, the way Sortell had been

01:20:08.699 --> 01:20:10.859
when they 1st met on the school racetrack

01:20:10.859 --> 01:20:11.640
5 years ago.

01:20:11.699 --> 01:20:14.699
But lately, Sortell was always covered in

01:20:14.699 --> 01:20:15.060
dirt.

01:20:15.180 --> 01:20:17.579
With splinters of tree stuff caught

01:20:17.579 --> 01:20:20.399
between his claws, entangled in his long

01:20:20.399 --> 01:20:21.239
elegant horns.

01:20:21.300 --> 01:20:24.239
And all too often he wore this

01:20:24.239 --> 01:20:25.079
expression.

01:20:25.140 --> 01:20:28.680
This worried, grim look that was really

01:20:28.680 --> 01:20:30.899
the last thing Luna needed today.

01:20:30.960 --> 01:20:34.260
Happy Metamorphosis Day.

01:20:34.319 --> 01:20:37.500
Blue said to him, perhaps a little too

01:20:37.500 --> 01:20:37.859
loud.

01:20:37.920 --> 01:20:40.920
He widened his eyes significantly at

01:20:40.920 --> 01:20:41.640
sword tail.

01:20:41.699 --> 01:20:44.279
Isn't this exciting?

01:20:44.340 --> 01:20:46.319
Are you all right?

01:20:46.439 --> 01:20:49.619
Sortell asked, gathering Luna into his

01:20:49.619 --> 01:20:50.100
wings.

01:20:50.159 --> 01:20:53.039
She leaned into him, as though she'd been

01:20:53.039 --> 01:20:55.260
flying for days, and he was the island

01:20:55.260 --> 01:20:56.520
she'd been searching for.

01:20:56.640 --> 01:20:59.760
He took one of her front talons in his

01:20:59.760 --> 01:21:02.520
and soft gray silk spun out from his

01:21:02.520 --> 01:21:05.340
wrists, gently wrapping around hers to

01:21:05.340 --> 01:21:06.119
wind them together.

01:21:06.180 --> 01:21:08.640
I can't believe you're here.

01:21:08.699 --> 01:21:09.899
Luna said.

01:21:09.960 --> 01:21:12.239
I thought Grasshopper would never let you

01:21:12.239 --> 01:21:12.600
come.

01:21:12.659 --> 01:21:15.060
Sortail made a face.

01:21:15.180 --> 01:21:16.859
He didn't.

01:21:16.920 --> 01:21:19.979
I finished all my work and asked, yes

01:21:19.979 --> 01:21:22.800
very politely, blue, I promise.

01:21:22.859 --> 01:21:24.539
And he still said no.

01:21:24.600 --> 01:21:25.979
He shrugged.

01:21:26.039 --> 01:21:27.960
So I snuck off when he wasn't looking.

01:21:28.020 --> 01:21:32.640
Blue's idea of politely, tended to be

01:21:32.640 --> 01:21:34.199
quite different from sword tails.

01:21:34.260 --> 01:21:38.279
But Blue had met Soretail's boss once, and

01:21:38.279 --> 01:21:40.560
was not at all surprised that Grasshopper

01:21:40.560 --> 01:21:42.359
had tried to keep Soretail from attending

01:21:42.359 --> 01:21:43.920
Luna's metamorphosis.

01:21:43.979 --> 01:21:46.680
Silverspot's mistress would do it out of

01:21:46.680 --> 01:21:47.039
spite.

01:21:47.159 --> 01:21:50.520
Grasshopper most likely said no, because

01:21:50.520 --> 01:21:52.680
he was still trying to teach sword tail

01:21:52.680 --> 01:21:54.119
obedience and good behavior.

01:21:54.180 --> 01:21:57.899
If Sordail would quit picking bites with

01:21:57.899 --> 01:22:00.479
hive wings, and expressing unpopular

01:22:00.479 --> 01:22:03.000
opinions all over the place, Blue

01:22:03.000 --> 01:22:03.359
thought.

01:22:03.420 --> 01:22:06.000
Perhaps figures of authority would be a

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:08.039
little less annoyed with him, and his

01:22:08.039 --> 01:22:09.119
life would be a little bit easier.

01:22:09.180 --> 01:22:14.340
Oh, sword tail, he said ruefully, you're

01:22:14.340 --> 01:22:15.420
going to be in so much trouble.

01:22:15.479 --> 01:22:17.220
Doesn't matter.

01:22:17.279 --> 01:22:18.600
This is more important.

01:22:18.659 --> 01:22:22.380
Soratel turned Luna's palms up. and

01:22:22.380 --> 01:22:24.239
frowned at the glowing embers under her

01:22:24.239 --> 01:22:24.600
scales.

01:22:24.659 --> 01:22:26.579
Whoa.

01:22:26.640 --> 01:22:28.680
Does it look weird to you?

01:22:28.739 --> 01:22:30.720
Luna said anxiously.

01:22:30.779 --> 01:22:33.720
Of course not, Blue said.

01:22:33.779 --> 01:22:34.739
You're totally fine.

01:22:34.800 --> 01:22:38.399
I remember a little bit of light where my

01:22:38.399 --> 01:22:41.340
silk came in, but not this bright

01:22:41.340 --> 01:22:44.340
Soartail said, completely trampling over

01:22:44.340 --> 01:22:46.380
Blue's efforts to calm Luna down.

01:22:46.439 --> 01:22:47.819
I'm not.

01:22:48.479 --> 01:22:49.739
I'm not sure this is normal.

01:22:49.800 --> 01:22:51.479
Io.

01:22:51.539 --> 01:22:53.159
Have you seen anything like this before?

01:22:53.220 --> 01:22:56.699
He turned to his sister as she came up to

01:22:56.699 --> 01:22:57.060
join them.

01:22:57.119 --> 01:23:00.000
Directly behind her was Blue's mother.

01:23:00.060 --> 01:23:03.180
Burnett, who stepped around the others to

01:23:03.180 --> 01:23:04.920
give Blue and Luna quick hugs.

01:23:04.979 --> 01:23:06.300
No.

01:23:06.359 --> 01:23:10.079
Io said, sounding even more alarmed than

01:23:10.079 --> 01:23:10.500
he did.

01:23:10.560 --> 01:23:13.079
Her wings had come in several months

01:23:13.079 --> 01:23:13.439
ago.

01:23:13.500 --> 01:23:16.859
Huge and dark purple, with shimmers of

01:23:16.859 --> 01:23:17.819
aquamarine green.

01:23:17.939 --> 01:23:21.479
She was only a year older than them, but

01:23:21.479 --> 01:23:23.819
she had long aristocratic looking bones

01:23:23.819 --> 01:23:26.520
and horns, and she towered over Luna.

01:23:26.579 --> 01:23:28.500
You don't think?

01:23:28.619 --> 01:23:31.319
They both glanced to burn it for some

01:23:31.319 --> 01:23:32.939
reason, but she wouldn't meet their

01:23:32.939 --> 01:23:33.180
eyes.

01:23:33.239 --> 01:23:36.539
Oh, she said carelessly.

01:23:36.600 --> 01:23:39.359
I've been to so many of these, and

01:23:39.359 --> 01:23:40.739
there's always something surprising.

01:23:40.800 --> 01:23:42.779
Never anything serious, though.

01:23:42.840 --> 01:23:43.619
Nothing to worry about.

01:23:43.680 --> 01:23:47.760
Blue had never heard his mother lie in

01:23:47.760 --> 01:23:48.779
his own stretched.

01:23:48.840 --> 01:23:51.239
Everything is fine here, voice.

01:23:51.300 --> 01:23:54.420
It made him feel as if his nice normal

01:23:54.420 --> 01:23:57.239
world was as thin as paper, and is easy

01:23:57.239 --> 01:23:58.439
to stab holes in.

01:23:58.500 --> 01:24:00.600
Are you Luna?

01:24:00.659 --> 01:24:03.359
One of the hive wing guards said roughly

01:24:03.359 --> 01:24:04.680
slithering up to them.

01:24:04.739 --> 01:24:08.340
He muscled Sortell aside, breaking the

01:24:08.340 --> 01:24:10.260
slender threads that bound him and Luna

01:24:10.260 --> 01:24:10.619
together.

01:24:10.680 --> 01:24:12.420
You're late.

01:24:12.479 --> 01:24:13.680
Time to get inside.

01:24:13.800 --> 01:24:16.500
Sorry Luna said.

01:24:16.560 --> 01:24:18.600
Which was what she was supposed to say

01:24:18.600 --> 01:24:21.779
and yet so unlike Luna to actually say it

01:24:21.779 --> 01:24:23.279
that Blue shivered.

01:24:23.340 --> 01:24:25.979
The ground felt unsteady below him.

01:24:26.039 --> 01:24:30.539
Also, they were not late, not even by a

01:24:30.539 --> 01:24:31.020
heartbeat.

01:24:31.079 --> 01:24:34.199
All hive wings and silk wings had a

01:24:34.199 --> 01:24:36.659
precise internal clock, that always kept

01:24:36.659 --> 01:24:39.000
their days on schedule, and warned them

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:40.500
when the rainy season was coming.

01:24:40.560 --> 01:24:43.619
Blues told him they were right on time.

01:24:43.680 --> 01:24:46.680
But of course, he wasn't about to argue

01:24:46.680 --> 01:24:47.279
with the guard.

01:24:47.399 --> 01:24:49.979
I love you, Luna.

01:24:50.100 --> 01:24:52.380
Swartail said fiercely.

01:24:52.439 --> 01:24:56.520
We do too, said Burnett, and Blue

01:24:56.520 --> 01:24:57.000
nodded.

01:24:57.060 --> 01:24:59.100
Although his sister wasn't looking at

01:24:59.100 --> 01:25:00.899
them and didn't seem to hear them

01:25:00.899 --> 01:25:01.199
either.

01:25:01.260 --> 01:25:05.399
You lot, up to the balcony, if you must

01:25:05.399 --> 01:25:05.760
stay.

01:25:05.880 --> 01:25:09.659
The guard said, waving one of his crimson

01:25:09.659 --> 01:25:11.460
and black dappled wings at the side

01:25:11.460 --> 01:25:11.819
entrance.

01:25:11.939 --> 01:25:14.760
He gave Luna a small shove in the

01:25:14.760 --> 01:25:16.800
direction of the archway, and she went

01:25:16.800 --> 01:25:19.800
with only one last nervous glance back at

01:25:19.800 --> 01:25:21.720
them before she disappeared inside.

01:25:21.779 --> 01:25:24.359
Should we do something?

01:25:24.420 --> 01:25:27.720
Io asked SwordTail, tell someone?

01:25:27.840 --> 01:25:29.520
There's no time.

01:25:29.640 --> 01:25:30.779
He said.

01:25:30.840 --> 01:25:33.600
His long blue antennae unfurled.

01:25:33.659 --> 01:25:36.420
Twitching, and he turned to stride toward

01:25:36.420 --> 01:25:36.779
the dome.

01:25:36.840 --> 01:25:39.000
And it's probably not.

01:25:39.119 --> 01:25:41.460
I mean, it's so rare.

01:25:41.520 --> 01:25:43.439
What?

01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:44.399
Blue asked.

01:25:44.460 --> 01:25:46.140
Tell someone what?

01:25:46.199 --> 01:25:47.939
What are you so worried about?

01:25:48.060 --> 01:25:50.520
Io, what's so rare?

01:25:50.579 --> 01:25:53.819
Io looked as though she might be about to

01:25:53.819 --> 01:25:54.779
tell him, but...

01:25:54.779 --> 01:25:58.800
Nothing, Bernard said, putting one wing

01:25:58.800 --> 01:26:00.000
over Blue's shoulders.

01:26:00.060 --> 01:26:01.979
Don't worry, sweetheart.

01:26:02.039 --> 01:26:03.479
Let's go cheer for Luna.

01:26:03.539 --> 01:26:06.539
He let his mother steer him through the

01:26:06.539 --> 01:26:09.119
side entrance and up the stairs. their

01:26:09.119 --> 01:26:11.340
footsteps muffled on the ancient silver

01:26:11.340 --> 01:26:12.539
silk carpets.

01:26:12.600 --> 01:26:16.079
The gallery was a long open balcony that

01:26:16.079 --> 01:26:19.020
ran around the entire dome, overlooking

01:26:19.020 --> 01:26:20.520
the dim, quiet floor below.

01:26:20.579 --> 01:26:24.239
The only light came from small candles

01:26:24.239 --> 01:26:26.159
floating in the central pool of water.

01:26:26.220 --> 01:26:30.479
Blue started toward their usual spot, on

01:26:30.479 --> 01:26:33.060
the far side of the dome, but Burnett

01:26:33.060 --> 01:26:34.079
gently tugged him back.

01:26:34.140 --> 01:26:37.979
Let's stand here this time, she said

01:26:37.979 --> 01:26:40.560
choosing a spot not far from the stairs.

01:26:40.680 --> 01:26:44.100
Soretail and Io joined them.

01:26:44.159 --> 01:26:46.859
The faint glow of candlelight rippling

01:26:46.859 --> 01:26:48.539
along their iridescent scales.

01:26:48.600 --> 01:26:52.140
Swordtail rested his front talons on the

01:26:52.140 --> 01:26:54.479
thick stone railing so he could lean over

01:26:54.479 --> 01:26:56.880
the edge, as though trying to get as

01:26:56.880 --> 01:26:58.319
close to Luna as he could.

01:26:58.319 --> 01:27:00.899
Blue wouldn't do that until he had

01:27:00.899 --> 01:27:01.260
wings.

01:27:01.319 --> 01:27:04.319
It wasn't far to fall, but it would still

01:27:04.319 --> 01:27:04.979
hurt if he did.

01:27:05.100 --> 01:27:09.000
All around them, silk wings were gathered

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:10.439
in the shadows of the balcony.

01:27:10.500 --> 01:27:13.020
Friends and family to the 3 other

01:27:13.020 --> 01:27:15.180
dragonettes undergoing metamorphosis

01:27:15.180 --> 01:27:15.420
today.

01:27:15.479 --> 01:27:19.619
Blue recognized many of their faces, lit

01:27:19.619 --> 01:27:21.899
from below like eerie moons all around

01:27:21.899 --> 01:27:22.380
the dome.

01:27:22.439 --> 01:27:24.960
Most of them were whispering to one

01:27:24.960 --> 01:27:25.500
another.

01:27:25.560 --> 01:27:28.500
But a hush fell as Luna was escorted onto

01:27:28.500 --> 01:27:28.979
the floor.

01:27:29.039 --> 01:27:30.899
Like the others.

01:27:30.960 --> 01:27:33.420
Her wristband had been cut off by the

01:27:33.420 --> 01:27:33.720
guards.

01:27:33.840 --> 01:27:37.500
Now, in the twilight room next to the

01:27:37.500 --> 01:27:39.840
other dragons, and with her scales more

01:27:39.840 --> 01:27:40.859
visible.

01:27:40.920 --> 01:27:43.560
It was terrifyingly clear that something

01:27:43.560 --> 01:27:45.180
different was happening to Luna.

01:27:45.239 --> 01:27:48.659
Where the others had a pale, silvery

01:27:48.659 --> 01:27:50.100
light coming from their wrists.

01:27:50.159 --> 01:27:53.279
Luna seemed to have fireflies on fire.

01:27:53.340 --> 01:27:56.340
Startling spots of molten gold.

01:27:56.399 --> 01:28:01.199
Blue felt Io grab sore tails' arm, but he

01:28:01.199 --> 01:28:03.359
couldn't look away from his sister, all

01:28:03.359 --> 01:28:04.859
alone on the cocoon floor.

01:28:04.920 --> 01:28:07.920
I'm the one who was with her all day.

01:28:07.979 --> 01:28:10.079
I should have noticed that something was

01:28:10.079 --> 01:28:10.260
wrong.

01:28:10.380 --> 01:28:12.659
I should have made her ask someone for

01:28:12.659 --> 01:28:12.899
help.

01:28:12.960 --> 01:28:15.600
One Silkwing.

01:28:15.659 --> 01:28:18.720
A starved looking turquoise dragonette

01:28:18.720 --> 01:28:20.819
from their class at school, had already

01:28:20.819 --> 01:28:22.859
entered her metamorphosis trance.

01:28:22.859 --> 01:28:26.460
Two long seamless strands of moon colored

01:28:26.460 --> 01:28:28.800
silk spiraled out of her wrists.

01:28:28.859 --> 01:28:32.279
Her eyes were closed, and her talons

01:28:32.279 --> 01:28:35.100
moved automatically, weaving the silk

01:28:35.100 --> 01:28:36.420
into a cocoon around her.

01:28:36.479 --> 01:28:40.920
As Luna glanced around nervously, a 2nd

01:28:40.920 --> 01:28:43.800
dragonette drifted into his trance and

01:28:43.800 --> 01:28:46.859
lifted his talons, silk threads spinning

01:28:46.859 --> 01:28:47.159
out.

01:28:47.220 --> 01:28:50.039
His cocoon looked like the 1st

01:28:50.039 --> 01:28:52.439
dragonettes, like every silk wings.

01:28:52.500 --> 01:28:55.380
It would shelter him for 5 days and

01:28:55.380 --> 01:28:57.659
nights while his wings came in.

01:28:57.720 --> 01:29:00.960
Sortell had promised blue, that he

01:29:00.960 --> 01:29:02.340
wouldn't remember a thing about the trans

01:29:02.340 --> 01:29:02.819
time.

01:29:02.880 --> 01:29:05.880
The blue found that almost scarier.

01:29:05.939 --> 01:29:08.939
The idea that he'd be unconscious to the

01:29:08.939 --> 01:29:11.699
world for that long, and then he'd come

01:29:11.699 --> 01:29:13.140
out looking totally different.

01:29:13.199 --> 01:29:15.539
Not totally different.

01:29:15.600 --> 01:29:19.079
Soritel insisted, I still look like me

01:29:19.079 --> 01:29:19.859
don't I?

01:29:19.920 --> 01:29:23.520
Which he sort of did, except that the

01:29:23.520 --> 01:29:25.560
wings made him look quite a bit bigger

01:29:25.560 --> 01:29:26.340
and more dramatic.

01:29:26.399 --> 01:29:29.819
The 3rd dragonette was eyeing Luna's

01:29:29.819 --> 01:29:32.640
wrists with concern and taking small

01:29:32.640 --> 01:29:34.079
sidling steps away from her.

01:29:34.140 --> 01:29:36.840
Whisperers were gusting through the

01:29:36.840 --> 01:29:39.359
watching silk wings, like the sweeping

01:29:39.359 --> 01:29:41.279
winds that shook their webs before the

01:29:41.279 --> 01:29:42.720
storms of the rainy season.

01:29:42.779 --> 01:29:45.300
There were even more guards now.

01:29:45.359 --> 01:29:48.779
At least 7 of them, most standing

01:29:48.779 --> 01:29:51.539
unsettlingly close to Luna, and

01:29:51.539 --> 01:29:54.300
pretending not to watch her, while their

01:29:54.300 --> 01:29:56.340
eyes darted constantly from her to the

01:29:56.340 --> 01:29:59.699
balcony to the pool, to the others, and

01:29:59.699 --> 01:30:00.180
back to her.

01:30:00.239 --> 01:30:04.560
Luna held out her front talons, and the

01:30:04.560 --> 01:30:06.899
whole world seemed to hold its breath for

01:30:06.899 --> 01:30:07.199
a moment.

01:30:07.260 --> 01:30:09.600
Then suddenly.

01:30:09.720 --> 01:30:13.380
She let out a sharp cry, and silk began

01:30:13.380 --> 01:30:14.880
to spiral out of her wrists.

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:18.539
But it wasn't normal grace silk.

01:30:18.600 --> 01:30:22.800
Luna's silk flared like threads of lava

01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:24.420
erupting from under her scales.

01:30:24.479 --> 01:30:28.319
It hissed as it hit the air, lighting up

01:30:28.319 --> 01:30:30.060
the room with sudden bright star

01:30:30.060 --> 01:30:30.659
brilliance.

01:30:30.720 --> 01:30:33.659
It was like the fire of the sun twisted

01:30:33.659 --> 01:30:36.300
into filaments that snaked back to clutch

01:30:36.300 --> 01:30:39.300
at Luna's talons, her legs, her whole

01:30:39.300 --> 01:30:39.659
body.

01:30:39.720 --> 01:30:43.619
Oh no, Io whispered.

01:30:43.680 --> 01:30:46.920
She looked at Swordtail, whose face was

01:30:46.920 --> 01:30:48.359
transfixed with horror.

01:30:48.420 --> 01:30:52.079
Flame silk, he breathed.

01:30:52.140 --> 01:30:56.340
Chapter 5.

01:30:56.760 --> 01:31:01.380
Wood's flame silk, Blue asked frantically

01:31:01.380 --> 01:31:03.420
as the guards advanced toward his

01:31:03.420 --> 01:31:03.779
sister.

01:31:03.779 --> 01:31:06.300
He shook sore tail with trembling

01:31:06.300 --> 01:31:06.960
talons.

01:31:07.079 --> 01:31:08.520
What's happening?

01:31:08.579 --> 01:31:09.899
What's wrong with Luna?

01:31:09.960 --> 01:31:13.920
The 3rd dragonette down below, bolted for

01:31:13.920 --> 01:31:16.439
the far side of the dome, and tried to

01:31:16.439 --> 01:31:19.140
scramble up one of the side walls, away

01:31:19.140 --> 01:31:20.760
from the guards and the burning light.

01:31:20.819 --> 01:31:24.659
Luna shrieked with fear, and leaped away

01:31:24.659 --> 01:31:26.939
from the fiery silk spilling out of her

01:31:26.939 --> 01:31:28.500
but there was nowhere to go.

01:31:28.560 --> 01:31:31.859
It clung to her like a real cocoon wood

01:31:31.859 --> 01:31:35.340
winding around her talons and legs, even

01:31:35.340 --> 01:31:36.779
as she tried to claw it away.

01:31:36.840 --> 01:31:39.000
Is it burning her?

01:31:39.060 --> 01:31:40.140
Blue cried.

01:31:40.199 --> 01:31:43.560
He turned to Io, his voice high and

01:31:43.560 --> 01:31:43.979
desperate.

01:31:44.039 --> 01:31:46.500
Io, is she all right?

01:31:46.560 --> 01:31:48.060
What is flame silk?

01:31:48.119 --> 01:31:51.960
It won't hurt her, his mother said.

01:31:52.079 --> 01:31:56.159
But her voice was as sad and soft as the

01:31:56.159 --> 01:31:58.500
splash of a silk wrapped corpse slipping

01:31:58.500 --> 01:31:58.920
into the bay.

01:31:59.039 --> 01:32:03.779
Did you know, Io asked Burnett, fiercely

01:32:03.779 --> 01:32:04.500
over Blue's head?

01:32:04.619 --> 01:32:07.500
Silverspot and I suspected.

01:32:07.560 --> 01:32:09.359
Bernard answered.

01:32:09.420 --> 01:32:11.760
Their father didn't say anything.

01:32:11.819 --> 01:32:14.399
And you couldn't tell by looking at him.

01:32:14.460 --> 01:32:17.939
But he was watched so carefully and taken

01:32:17.939 --> 01:32:18.840
away so quickly.

01:32:18.899 --> 01:32:21.239
We knew there had to be something.

01:32:21.300 --> 01:32:23.640
You could have warned us.

01:32:23.699 --> 01:32:25.500
Io hissed.

01:32:25.560 --> 01:32:26.760
We could have hidden her.

01:32:26.880 --> 01:32:29.159
Barnett shook her head.

01:32:29.220 --> 01:32:32.819
Luna let out another fainter cry

01:32:32.819 --> 01:32:35.279
collapsing forward with her eyes closed.

01:32:35.340 --> 01:32:39.239
The flame silk spun on and on, and

01:32:39.239 --> 01:32:41.100
everywhere it touched her she went still

01:32:41.100 --> 01:32:43.619
as though it was tranquilizing her.

01:32:43.680 --> 01:32:46.979
Everybody, please remain calm.

01:32:47.100 --> 01:32:50.100
One of the hive wings said smoothly

01:32:50.100 --> 01:32:52.560
spreading his wings to address the

01:32:52.560 --> 01:32:54.539
horrified audience of silk wings.

01:32:54.600 --> 01:32:57.479
We are well prepared for silkwing

01:32:57.479 --> 01:32:59.880
diseases like this, everything is under

01:32:59.880 --> 01:33:00.300
control.

01:33:00.359 --> 01:33:02.399
Diseases.

01:33:02.460 --> 01:33:05.039
Blue echoed in a choked whisper.

01:33:05.100 --> 01:33:06.600
Io scowled.

01:33:06.720 --> 01:33:09.720
His sister wouldn't be left to transform

01:33:09.720 --> 01:33:12.479
quietly on the floor of the cocoon, like

01:33:12.479 --> 01:33:15.060
the other 2 small silken bundles beside

01:33:15.060 --> 01:33:15.180
her.

01:33:15.239 --> 01:33:17.880
Already she was surrounded by all the

01:33:17.880 --> 01:33:21.840
guards, spears lifted, swords and claws

01:33:21.840 --> 01:33:24.840
and tail spikes all pointed at her, as

01:33:24.840 --> 01:33:27.180
though her flame silk cocoon might sprout

01:33:27.180 --> 01:33:28.920
fiery wings and try to escape.

01:33:28.979 --> 01:33:32.579
And a dark metal cart was rattling

01:33:32.579 --> 01:33:33.060
through the door.

01:33:33.119 --> 01:33:36.180
Yawning mouth ready to swallow her up.

01:33:36.239 --> 01:33:38.279
Luna!

01:33:38.340 --> 01:33:41.159
Swartell shouted, shaken out of his

01:33:41.159 --> 01:33:43.500
horror by the side of the cart, he

01:33:43.500 --> 01:33:45.840
vaulted over the balcony railing, and

01:33:45.840 --> 01:33:48.539
plummeted to the floor below, with barely

01:33:48.539 --> 01:33:50.279
enough time to spread his wings to break

01:33:50.279 --> 01:33:50.699
his fall.

01:33:50.760 --> 01:33:53.760
His legs were already moving as he landed

01:33:53.760 --> 01:33:56.279
galloping across the floor toward the

01:33:56.279 --> 01:33:56.819
guards.

01:33:56.819 --> 01:33:58.800
What do we do?

01:33:58.920 --> 01:34:01.260
Blue asked Io and Burnett.

01:34:01.319 --> 01:34:03.600
Should they all jump down and try to save

01:34:03.600 --> 01:34:04.199
Luna?

01:34:04.260 --> 01:34:06.180
But there were so many guards.

01:34:06.239 --> 01:34:08.760
And maybe they were trying to help her.

01:34:08.819 --> 01:34:12.180
They did say they were prepared, so

01:34:12.180 --> 01:34:13.199
they'd seen this before.

01:34:13.260 --> 01:34:15.960
Maybe they could take her somewhere to

01:34:15.960 --> 01:34:16.500
cure her.

01:34:16.560 --> 01:34:19.260
Maybe they could fix her silk and make it

01:34:19.260 --> 01:34:19.560
normal.

01:34:19.619 --> 01:34:23.460
You, run, Io said.

01:34:23.520 --> 01:34:26.039
She dragged Blue away from the railing

01:34:26.039 --> 01:34:27.899
and shoved him at the stairs.

01:34:27.960 --> 01:34:28.979
Me?

01:34:29.039 --> 01:34:31.020
Blue said, astonished.

01:34:31.079 --> 01:34:33.300
He can't escape.

01:34:33.359 --> 01:34:37.199
Bernard argued tiredly, following Io.

01:34:37.260 --> 01:34:39.420
There's nowhere he can go.

01:34:39.479 --> 01:34:41.579
It would be safer for him to turn himself

01:34:41.579 --> 01:34:41.880
in.

01:34:41.939 --> 01:34:44.880
No way, Io cried.

01:34:45.000 --> 01:34:47.220
We can't just let them take him.

01:34:47.279 --> 01:34:49.800
Why would they take me?

01:34:49.859 --> 01:34:51.960
Blue yelped in alarm.

01:34:52.020 --> 01:34:54.840
His talons scrabbled on the stone floor

01:34:54.840 --> 01:34:56.880
as Io pushed him forward again.

01:34:56.939 --> 01:34:58.979
I didn't do anything.

01:34:59.039 --> 01:35:00.060
I'm not sick.

01:35:00.119 --> 01:35:02.699
Neither is Luna.

01:35:02.819 --> 01:35:04.319
Io pointed out.

01:35:04.380 --> 01:35:06.840
She herded him along in front of her

01:35:06.840 --> 01:35:09.479
talking fast as they stumbled down the

01:35:09.479 --> 01:35:10.140
steps.

01:35:10.199 --> 01:35:12.840
Flame silk is something you hatch with.

01:35:12.899 --> 01:35:15.060
She must have inherited it from your

01:35:15.060 --> 01:35:17.159
father, which means you have it too.

01:35:17.279 --> 01:35:19.260
Which means they'll come for you next.

01:35:19.319 --> 01:35:21.300
But why?

01:35:21.359 --> 01:35:22.260
He said.

01:35:22.380 --> 01:35:25.260
One of his claws snagged painfully on the

01:35:25.260 --> 01:35:25.739
carpet.

01:35:25.800 --> 01:35:28.979
He paused to unhook it, looked back up

01:35:28.979 --> 01:35:31.260
the stairs, and saw his mother watching

01:35:31.260 --> 01:35:33.300
him go with a bleak expression.

01:35:33.359 --> 01:35:36.119
Watching, but not following.

01:35:36.180 --> 01:35:38.399
She'd already given up.

01:35:38.460 --> 01:35:41.340
What are they going to do with Luna?

01:35:41.399 --> 01:35:44.520
We don't know, Io said.

01:35:44.579 --> 01:35:46.380
We've never been able to find out.

01:35:46.500 --> 01:35:49.859
Flame soaks are very rare, and the hive

01:35:49.859 --> 01:35:51.539
wings make them banish immediately.

01:35:51.600 --> 01:35:53.760
Vanish?

01:35:53.819 --> 01:35:54.899
Blue echoed.

01:35:54.960 --> 01:35:57.659
Like, forever?

01:35:57.720 --> 01:36:01.020
His insides felt as if they'd all leaped

01:36:01.020 --> 01:36:02.880
off the top of the hive, and were

01:36:02.880 --> 01:36:04.619
currently plummeting toward the distant

01:36:04.619 --> 01:36:04.920
ground.

01:36:04.979 --> 01:36:07.800
Do you see why you have to run?

01:36:07.859 --> 01:36:10.619
Io pushed open the door at the bottom of

01:36:10.619 --> 01:36:11.760
the stairs and looked out.

01:36:11.819 --> 01:36:13.140
All clear.

01:36:13.199 --> 01:36:15.720
Quick, while they're busy with Luna and

01:36:15.720 --> 01:36:16.199
Sortail.

01:36:16.260 --> 01:36:19.800
Blue dug in his claws as she tried to

01:36:19.800 --> 01:36:20.640
throw him out the door.

01:36:20.699 --> 01:36:22.739
Wait, wait.

01:36:22.800 --> 01:36:24.239
Run where?

01:36:24.359 --> 01:36:25.199
He pleaded.

01:36:25.260 --> 01:36:27.539
Anywhere. she said.

01:36:27.600 --> 01:36:30.779
Run, hide, and don't let them find you.

01:36:30.840 --> 01:36:34.140
But I'll get in trouble, he said.

01:36:34.199 --> 01:36:36.600
I can't hide from the hive wings.

01:36:36.659 --> 01:36:37.859
Mother's right.

01:36:37.920 --> 01:36:40.319
If they want me, I should turn myself

01:36:40.319 --> 01:36:40.619
in.

01:36:40.680 --> 01:36:43.020
They won't hurt me.

01:36:43.079 --> 01:36:46.680
His voice wavered, thinking of flame

01:36:46.680 --> 01:36:47.939
silks vanishing forever.

01:36:48.060 --> 01:36:51.420
Disappeared so thoroughly that he'd never

01:36:51.420 --> 01:36:52.199
even heard of them.

01:36:52.260 --> 01:36:57.359
Maybe they can fix me, so I won't have

01:36:57.359 --> 01:36:58.079
flame silk.

01:36:58.199 --> 01:37:00.479
Io groaned softly.

01:37:00.539 --> 01:37:02.939
Why did it have to be you?

01:37:02.939 --> 01:37:04.079
she said.

01:37:04.140 --> 01:37:07.079
The one silk wing who thinks hive wings

01:37:07.079 --> 01:37:08.039
have any good in them.

01:37:08.100 --> 01:37:11.399
Listen, Blue, stop trusting them right

01:37:11.399 --> 01:37:11.699
now.

01:37:11.760 --> 01:37:14.399
They've let you go about your ordinary

01:37:14.399 --> 01:37:17.520
life so far, but now, you look dangerous

01:37:17.520 --> 01:37:19.619
to them, and they're not going to let you

01:37:19.619 --> 01:37:20.760
have that life back.

01:37:20.819 --> 01:37:21.840
It's gone.

01:37:21.899 --> 01:37:25.079
But it doesn't have to be.

01:37:25.199 --> 01:37:26.880
Blue protested.

01:37:26.939 --> 01:37:30.600
If I'm good, if I do what I'm told, I

01:37:30.600 --> 01:37:32.399
mean, I'm not dangerous.

01:37:32.460 --> 01:37:34.260
I could never be dangerous.

01:37:34.380 --> 01:37:39.779
I know, Io said, rubbing the spot on her

01:37:39.779 --> 01:37:41.039
forehead between her horns.

01:37:41.100 --> 01:37:44.159
Unfortunately, I think that's true.

01:37:44.220 --> 01:37:47.039
She took his shoulders and shook him.

01:37:47.100 --> 01:37:48.960
But they don't care.

01:37:49.020 --> 01:37:52.140
Please, promise me you'll hide from them

01:37:52.140 --> 01:37:52.439
blue.

01:37:52.500 --> 01:37:53.939
Don't let them catch you.

01:37:54.000 --> 01:37:55.859
For how long?

01:37:55.979 --> 01:37:57.000
Blue said.

01:37:57.060 --> 01:37:58.439
Where can I go?

01:37:58.500 --> 01:38:00.720
What about my metamorphosis?

01:38:00.779 --> 01:38:01.920
It's really soon.

01:38:01.979 --> 01:38:03.720
And then I'll have to come back here.

01:38:03.779 --> 01:38:06.060
Io sighed.

01:38:06.119 --> 01:38:09.359
Let's hide you 1st and then figure that

01:38:09.359 --> 01:38:09.600
out.

01:38:09.659 --> 01:38:10.920
She said.

01:38:10.979 --> 01:38:13.800
She shoved open the door, flung him

01:38:13.800 --> 01:38:15.239
outside and bolted after him.

01:38:15.359 --> 01:38:18.960
Blue found himself running, even though

01:38:18.960 --> 01:38:20.880
his brain was shouting at him to go back

01:38:20.880 --> 01:38:24.359
to ask the guards for help, to make sure

01:38:24.359 --> 01:38:25.319
Luna was all right.

01:38:25.439 --> 01:38:27.779
Was she still terrified?

01:38:27.840 --> 01:38:30.359
Or had this silk entranced her?

01:38:30.479 --> 01:38:34.140
Taking her into peaceful darkness even as

01:38:34.140 --> 01:38:36.300
chaos swarmed outside her cocoon.

01:38:36.359 --> 01:38:39.539
What had the guards done to Swordtail?

01:38:39.600 --> 01:38:41.699
He could never fight so many.

01:38:41.760 --> 01:38:44.520
A silk wing didn't stand a chance against

01:38:44.520 --> 01:38:45.899
even one hive wing.

01:38:45.960 --> 01:38:49.380
Was he lying beside Luna on the sand now

01:38:49.380 --> 01:38:52.319
bleeding and swollen with venom?

01:38:52.380 --> 01:38:55.920
Blue shuddered, his claws wobbling

01:38:55.920 --> 01:38:56.699
underneath him.

01:38:56.760 --> 01:38:59.159
They had just reached to the edge of the

01:38:59.159 --> 01:39:01.319
outer courtyard when he heard shouts

01:39:01.319 --> 01:39:01.739
behind them.

01:39:01.800 --> 01:39:03.420
Stop.

01:39:03.479 --> 01:39:04.199
You there.

01:39:04.260 --> 01:39:06.239
Silk Wings, stop at once.

01:39:06.359 --> 01:39:09.359
His feet obeyed instinctively.

01:39:09.420 --> 01:39:11.520
Guards were talking to him.

01:39:11.579 --> 01:39:13.500
Guards were to be listened to.

01:39:13.560 --> 01:39:17.220
You never argued with high wing guards, or

01:39:17.220 --> 01:39:19.380
else you'd get sprayed, or stabbed with

01:39:19.380 --> 01:39:19.800
something.

01:39:19.859 --> 01:39:21.119
Everyone knew that.

01:39:21.180 --> 01:39:23.640
But Io didn't stop.

01:39:23.699 --> 01:39:27.000
Io threw her talons around his chest and

01:39:27.000 --> 01:39:29.760
hurled up into the air, her spectacular

01:39:29.760 --> 01:39:31.500
wings pumping desperately.

01:39:31.560 --> 01:39:33.239
I-O!

01:39:33.300 --> 01:39:36.180
Blue yelped with fear. as his claws left

01:39:36.180 --> 01:39:36.539
the ground.

01:39:36.600 --> 01:39:39.180
Suddenly they were flying along the

01:39:39.180 --> 01:39:39.899
narrow streets.

01:39:39.960 --> 01:39:42.960
Flashes of startled faces peering out of

01:39:42.960 --> 01:39:43.619
windows at them.

01:39:43.680 --> 01:39:47.100
The indigo whirl of Io's wings beat

01:39:47.100 --> 01:39:49.319
around Blue's head, and he covered his

01:39:49.319 --> 01:39:49.500
eyes.

01:39:49.560 --> 01:39:51.600
Stop.

01:39:51.659 --> 01:39:54.300
Queen Wasp orders you to stop at once.

01:39:54.359 --> 01:39:57.000
Where did Io think they were going?

01:39:57.060 --> 01:39:59.579
There was nowhere in the hives where

01:39:59.579 --> 01:40:01.079
Queen Wasp wouldn't find them.

01:40:01.199 --> 01:40:05.579
Nobody ran from the queen's guards, and

01:40:05.579 --> 01:40:07.260
she would surely kill them both for

01:40:07.260 --> 01:40:08.340
disobeying her orders.

01:40:08.460 --> 01:40:12.119
Io let out a small roar of frustration

01:40:12.119 --> 01:40:14.220
and Blue peeked through his claws.

01:40:14.279 --> 01:40:17.159
They were nearly at the exit that led to

01:40:17.159 --> 01:40:18.659
the tunnels spiraling up.

01:40:18.720 --> 01:40:21.420
The guards were closing rank in front of

01:40:21.420 --> 01:40:24.779
it, spears crossed, teeth gleaming.

01:40:24.899 --> 01:40:26.939
That's the only exit.

01:40:27.060 --> 01:40:28.920
Blue thought frantically.

01:40:28.979 --> 01:40:31.739
There weren't even any windows or ledges

01:40:31.739 --> 01:40:33.659
to the open sky on this level of the

01:40:33.659 --> 01:40:34.020
hive.

01:40:34.079 --> 01:40:38.880
Oh, he realized, with a fresh burst of

01:40:38.880 --> 01:40:39.300
terror.

01:40:39.359 --> 01:40:41.640
That's probably intentional.

01:40:41.699 --> 01:40:44.579
So there's no way for a flame silk to

01:40:44.579 --> 01:40:44.819
escape.

01:40:44.880 --> 01:40:49.260
I a whirled in the air. and shot down one

01:40:49.260 --> 01:40:50.579
of the avenues toward the training

01:40:50.579 --> 01:40:51.060
center.

01:40:51.119 --> 01:40:54.359
Which, frankly, seemed like a poorly

01:40:54.359 --> 01:40:55.199
thought out plan.

01:40:55.199 --> 01:40:58.140
Blue could see a small army of eager

01:40:58.140 --> 01:41:00.960
looking hive wing trainees swarming out

01:41:00.960 --> 01:41:01.800
of the front gate.

01:41:01.859 --> 01:41:05.100
Yellow striped wings flicked and buzzed

01:41:05.100 --> 01:41:08.399
sharp white teeth snapped to the air as

01:41:08.399 --> 01:41:10.020
the dragon spread out to search the

01:41:10.020 --> 01:41:10.680
streets.

01:41:10.680 --> 01:41:13.920
For us, they are searching for us.

01:41:13.979 --> 01:41:17.640
But then IO banked suddenly left and up.

01:41:17.699 --> 01:41:20.819
Up through the open courtyard toward the

01:41:20.819 --> 01:41:21.840
higher hive levels.

01:41:21.899 --> 01:41:25.020
Blue yelped again, as the ground dropped

01:41:25.020 --> 01:41:28.140
even farther away, and then really wished

01:41:28.140 --> 01:41:29.399
she hadn't even thought the word

01:41:29.399 --> 01:41:30.539
dropped.

01:41:30.600 --> 01:41:34.500
Shouts of fury rose from below. followed

01:41:34.500 --> 01:41:37.380
by the sound of buzzing, beating wings, as

01:41:37.380 --> 01:41:39.180
all the guards and soldiers took to the

01:41:39.180 --> 01:41:39.420
air.

01:41:39.479 --> 01:41:42.779
We're going to die, Blue thought.

01:41:42.840 --> 01:41:45.840
There's so many of them, and they have

01:41:45.840 --> 01:41:46.859
wait.

01:41:46.920 --> 01:41:48.960
Why aren't they shooting at us?

01:41:49.020 --> 01:41:52.500
He knew some of the hive wings behind

01:41:52.500 --> 01:41:54.300
them had dart weapons and spears.

01:41:54.359 --> 01:41:56.520
So why hadn't they thrown them?

01:41:56.579 --> 01:42:00.479
Dragons on the surrounding levels, rushed

01:42:00.479 --> 01:42:01.979
to the edge of the ledges to watch the

01:42:01.979 --> 01:42:02.340
chase.

01:42:02.399 --> 01:42:05.760
Blue had never had this many eyes on him

01:42:05.760 --> 01:42:06.060
before.

01:42:06.119 --> 01:42:08.340
What do they see?

01:42:08.399 --> 01:42:09.899
What do they think?

01:42:09.960 --> 01:42:12.180
Does anyone want to help?

01:42:12.300 --> 01:42:15.060
Or are they all hoping we'll be caught?

01:42:15.119 --> 01:42:16.800
And it'll be exciting to watch.

01:42:16.859 --> 01:42:21.359
Suddenly, Io was jerked backward, and

01:42:21.359 --> 01:42:23.520
Blue felt himself slip through her talons

01:42:23.520 --> 01:42:26.340
for just a moment until she dug her claws

01:42:26.340 --> 01:42:26.579
in.

01:42:26.640 --> 01:42:29.819
Ouch, and gave a mighty heave of her

01:42:29.819 --> 01:42:32.340
wings, kicking backward at the high wing

01:42:32.340 --> 01:42:33.239
who'd grabbed her tail.

01:42:33.300 --> 01:42:36.600
They struggled in the air, blue dangling

01:42:36.600 --> 01:42:39.539
between them, and then Io swept her wings

01:42:39.539 --> 01:42:42.840
in a huge arc, and threw blue up toward

01:42:42.840 --> 01:42:43.859
the highest open level.

01:42:43.920 --> 01:42:45.960
Yaha!

01:42:46.020 --> 01:42:47.520
Blue screamed.

01:42:47.640 --> 01:42:50.279
He flung out his claws and felt them

01:42:50.279 --> 01:42:52.140
catch in their rough tree stuffed walls.

01:42:52.199 --> 01:42:55.140
His body slammed into the side with a

01:42:55.140 --> 01:42:57.840
bone jarring thump, and he dug in his

01:42:57.840 --> 01:42:59.159
back talons desperately.

01:42:59.220 --> 01:43:03.359
Up. Io shouted to him. as she swung her

01:43:03.359 --> 01:43:06.119
attacker like a club, smashing other hive

01:43:06.119 --> 01:43:06.720
wings away.

01:43:06.779 --> 01:43:08.460
Climb blue.

01:43:08.520 --> 01:43:12.000
Go. He tried to imagine he was out on the

01:43:12.000 --> 01:43:12.420
webs.

01:43:12.479 --> 01:43:15.359
Having a perfectly normal climb, with

01:43:15.359 --> 01:43:18.239
lots and lots and lots of secure webs

01:43:18.239 --> 01:43:19.140
below to catch him.

01:43:19.199 --> 01:43:23.220
He pushed himself up and up again, and in

01:43:23.220 --> 01:43:25.560
a moment, he felt the ledge above.

01:43:25.619 --> 01:43:29.100
He clutched at it, his wing buds churning

01:43:29.100 --> 01:43:29.819
as though they could help.

01:43:29.880 --> 01:43:34.680
Two faces peered down at him, silk wings

01:43:34.680 --> 01:43:35.880
ones he didn't know.

01:43:35.939 --> 01:43:37.859
But he could guess what they were

01:43:37.859 --> 01:43:38.159
thinking.

01:43:38.220 --> 01:43:41.760
Should we help this wingless dragonette?

01:43:41.819 --> 01:43:44.460
Will the hive wings punish us if we do?

01:43:44.520 --> 01:43:47.159
What has he done to make the guards chase

01:43:47.159 --> 01:43:47.399
him?

01:43:47.460 --> 01:43:51.060
He must be a very bad dragon to be

01:43:51.060 --> 01:43:52.020
running from the guards.

01:43:52.079 --> 01:43:55.260
But if we let him fall, he'll die.

01:43:55.319 --> 01:43:58.920
Talons reached down and circled his

01:43:58.920 --> 01:43:59.279
wrists.

01:44:00.060 --> 01:44:01.800
Strong arms pulled him up to safety.

01:44:01.859 --> 01:44:05.460
He sprawled on the tree stuff, gasping

01:44:05.460 --> 01:44:06.960
more from fear than exhaustion.

01:44:07.020 --> 01:44:10.739
This was a residential level, full of

01:44:10.739 --> 01:44:13.319
hive wing homes, a bit smaller than the

01:44:13.319 --> 01:44:16.319
one where Silverspot worked, and he'd

01:44:16.319 --> 01:44:17.819
landed in their school's practice

01:44:17.819 --> 01:44:19.140
vegetable garden.

01:44:19.260 --> 01:44:22.020
All around him were garden boxes full of

01:44:22.020 --> 01:44:25.020
dirt and little tendrils of, maybe one

01:44:25.020 --> 01:44:27.300
day I'll be a plant, labeled with

01:44:27.300 --> 01:44:29.340
optimistic scrawls on flat wooden

01:44:29.340 --> 01:44:29.760
sticks.

01:44:29.819 --> 01:44:32.819
The 2 silk wings, watching him with

01:44:32.819 --> 01:44:35.279
confusion, were the only dragons nearby.

01:44:35.340 --> 01:44:37.800
But he could see hive wings running

01:44:37.800 --> 01:44:40.079
toward him along the streets, and others

01:44:40.079 --> 01:44:42.420
spreading their wings on the far side of

01:44:42.420 --> 01:44:42.659
the city.

01:44:42.779 --> 01:44:47.159
Io, he panted, scrambling up.

01:44:47.220 --> 01:44:48.359
Is she?

01:44:48.659 --> 01:44:50.279
Are you all right?

01:44:50.340 --> 01:44:53.880
Asked the gray blue silkwing, with

01:44:53.880 --> 01:44:55.619
speckles of yellow across her scales.

01:44:55.680 --> 01:44:57.659
What?

01:44:57.659 --> 01:45:00.539
began the other, but he broke off as Io

01:45:00.539 --> 01:45:02.100
landed on the ledge behind Blue.

01:45:02.159 --> 01:45:04.140
The seeds will grow again.

01:45:04.199 --> 01:45:05.939
Io said to them.

01:45:06.060 --> 01:45:08.460
She shoved Blue forward without waiting

01:45:08.460 --> 01:45:09.420
for a response.

01:45:09.479 --> 01:45:12.119
But he saw a look of recognition cross

01:45:12.119 --> 01:45:13.020
their faces.

01:45:13.079 --> 01:45:14.579
What?

01:45:14.640 --> 01:45:17.640
He said to her, as they plunged down the

01:45:17.640 --> 01:45:18.539
nearest empty street.

01:45:18.659 --> 01:45:21.720
He glanced back and saw the silk wings

01:45:21.720 --> 01:45:24.000
casually blocking the road behind them

01:45:24.000 --> 01:45:27.060
their wings spread wide, as they started

01:45:27.060 --> 01:45:28.380
arguing about something.

01:45:28.439 --> 01:45:31.020
There are silkwings who will help you.

01:45:31.079 --> 01:45:34.439
IO said rapidly, if you can find them.

01:45:34.500 --> 01:45:36.600
A group called the Chrysalis.

01:45:36.720 --> 01:45:40.319
The houses they ran past were narrow but

01:45:40.319 --> 01:45:42.960
elegant, made of tree stuff that flowed

01:45:42.960 --> 01:45:45.180
straight into the street below, and into

01:45:45.180 --> 01:45:47.460
the roof above them, as though they had

01:45:47.460 --> 01:45:48.420
grown with the hive.

01:45:48.539 --> 01:45:51.659
Most of them had intricate patterns of

01:45:51.659 --> 01:45:54.420
seashells, or glass tiles embedded in

01:45:54.420 --> 01:45:57.359
their outer walls, spirals of pearl pink

01:45:57.359 --> 01:45:59.939
coral, or zigzagging diamonds of

01:45:59.939 --> 01:46:00.720
aquamarine.

01:46:00.779 --> 01:46:03.300
Street lamps that hung from the ceiling

01:46:03.300 --> 01:46:06.479
above, cast a warm glow over everything

01:46:06.479 --> 01:46:10.140
deceptively calm and cozy, like a shroud

01:46:10.140 --> 01:46:11.939
of silk around a wasp nest.

01:46:12.060 --> 01:46:14.939
The chrysalis?

01:46:15.000 --> 01:46:15.840
What?

01:46:15.840 --> 01:46:17.460
Why don't I know about them?

01:46:17.520 --> 01:46:19.920
Blue asked, breathing hard.

01:46:19.979 --> 01:46:22.619
He'd never run this much for this long in

01:46:22.619 --> 01:46:23.039
his life.

01:46:23.100 --> 01:46:27.119
His sides ached, and his talons hurt, and

01:46:27.119 --> 01:46:29.399
his eyes were blurry, and his heart felt

01:46:29.399 --> 01:46:31.140
like a beehive about to explode.

01:46:31.199 --> 01:46:33.060
Io snorted.

01:46:33.119 --> 01:46:36.840
Because every time someone says to you

01:46:36.840 --> 01:46:39.779
hey, wasn't that mean what that hive wing

01:46:39.779 --> 01:46:43.680
did, you say, oh, maybe she's tired, or

01:46:43.680 --> 01:46:46.020
frustrated with work, or just lost

01:46:46.020 --> 01:46:48.359
something important, or is having a fight

01:46:48.359 --> 01:46:49.199
with her sister.

01:46:49.260 --> 01:46:51.960
And then it's kind of hard to follow up

01:46:51.960 --> 01:46:55.500
with, well, so care to join a movement to

01:46:55.500 --> 01:46:56.220
take her down?

01:46:56.279 --> 01:46:57.899
A movement?

01:46:57.960 --> 01:46:59.279
Blue sputtered.

01:46:59.399 --> 01:47:00.899
To take who down?

01:47:01.020 --> 01:47:04.739
The street abruptly ended, spilling them

01:47:04.739 --> 01:47:06.000
out into a hive wing park.

01:47:06.060 --> 01:47:09.000
Or at least, it looked a bit like a park

01:47:09.000 --> 01:47:11.340
but without any grass or flowers.

01:47:11.340 --> 01:47:14.939
Instead, the vast circle was full of

01:47:14.939 --> 01:47:17.279
playground structures carved from real

01:47:17.279 --> 01:47:20.939
wood, dark and smooth, like the abandoned

01:47:20.939 --> 01:47:22.319
bones of ancient trees.

01:47:22.380 --> 01:47:25.260
Many of them arched all the way to the

01:47:25.260 --> 01:47:28.260
roof, which was probably a lot of fun if

01:47:28.260 --> 01:47:30.720
you are a dragonette with wings, and a

01:47:30.720 --> 01:47:32.279
chance of surviving a fall from that

01:47:32.279 --> 01:47:32.640
height.

01:47:32.760 --> 01:47:36.659
A hive wing school, shinier and much

01:47:36.659 --> 01:47:39.659
bigger than Silkworm Hall, loomed along

01:47:39.659 --> 01:47:42.000
one side of the park, and in the center

01:47:42.000 --> 01:47:44.760
of the circle was a pool of water lined

01:47:44.760 --> 01:47:46.739
with silver bright mirror tiles.

01:47:46.800 --> 01:47:50.520
On the far side of the park, Blue caught

01:47:50.520 --> 01:47:52.260
a glimpse of slanting sunset light

01:47:52.260 --> 01:47:54.720
through one of the openings where dragons

01:47:54.720 --> 01:47:56.460
could fly in and out of the hive.

01:47:56.579 --> 01:48:00.300
Out that window were the savannah and the

01:48:00.300 --> 01:48:01.020
open sky.

01:48:01.079 --> 01:48:03.119
But how could they get there?

01:48:03.180 --> 01:48:06.060
The park was full of hive wings

01:48:06.060 --> 01:48:09.180
dragonettes playing, parents gathering

01:48:09.180 --> 01:48:12.119
water from the pool, guards and families

01:48:12.119 --> 01:48:14.039
and teachers who'd finished school for

01:48:14.039 --> 01:48:17.579
the day, all strolling the paths, filling

01:48:17.579 --> 01:48:19.500
the space between here and escape.

01:48:19.560 --> 01:48:22.619
He'd wondered why the houses they ran

01:48:22.619 --> 01:48:24.060
past seemed to be empty.

01:48:24.119 --> 01:48:27.479
Apparently, this park was the place where

01:48:27.479 --> 01:48:29.279
the entire neighborhood gathered at the

01:48:29.279 --> 01:48:29.699
end of the day.

01:48:29.819 --> 01:48:32.039
Duck your head.

01:48:32.100 --> 01:48:33.180
Io said.

01:48:33.239 --> 01:48:34.680
Pretend to be a servant.

01:48:34.739 --> 01:48:37.020
Walk quickly, but not too fast.

01:48:37.079 --> 01:48:41.340
She folded her wings in close. and darted

01:48:41.340 --> 01:48:44.220
out onto one of the more crowded pathways

01:48:44.220 --> 01:48:45.479
weaving between dragons.

01:48:45.539 --> 01:48:48.180
With her head bowed submissively.

01:48:48.239 --> 01:48:50.520
She blended in with the other silkwing

01:48:50.520 --> 01:48:52.319
servants blue could see here and there

01:48:52.319 --> 01:48:55.979
many of them carrying heavy water jugs, or

01:48:55.979 --> 01:48:58.380
keeping an eye on young dragonettes, while

01:48:58.380 --> 01:49:00.060
hive wing parents chatted with each

01:49:00.060 --> 01:49:00.239
other.

01:49:00.359 --> 01:49:04.619
This is never going to work, Blue thought

01:49:04.619 --> 01:49:06.539
as he ducked his head and followed her.

01:49:06.600 --> 01:49:10.680
And yet, for a moment, it seemed as if it

01:49:10.680 --> 01:49:11.100
might.

01:49:11.159 --> 01:49:14.220
The hive wings barely glanced at 2 more

01:49:14.220 --> 01:49:15.420
lowly silk wings.

01:49:15.479 --> 01:49:17.340
They were so busy with one another.

01:49:17.399 --> 01:49:19.920
It was as though the silk wings didn't

01:49:19.920 --> 01:49:20.159
exist.

01:49:20.220 --> 01:49:23.340
Many of them were watching a group of

01:49:23.340 --> 01:49:25.979
young dragonettes lead from a climbing

01:49:25.979 --> 01:49:28.739
structure, their tiny wings pumping to

01:49:28.739 --> 01:49:30.300
help them drift down.

01:49:30.359 --> 01:49:32.939
One little black and orange dragonette

01:49:32.939 --> 01:49:35.279
crashed into blue as she ran across to

01:49:35.279 --> 01:49:38.340
her friends, but she just yelped, oops

01:49:38.340 --> 01:49:39.899
sorry, and kept going.

01:49:39.960 --> 01:49:42.840
It looked like a nice place to live.

01:49:42.899 --> 01:49:46.920
Perhaps not as huge and impressive as the

01:49:46.920 --> 01:49:49.260
higher level where Silver Spot's mistress

01:49:49.260 --> 01:49:51.659
had her mansion, but a place where

01:49:51.659 --> 01:49:53.399
families were friends with one another.

01:49:53.460 --> 01:49:56.159
These dragons made one another laugh

01:49:56.159 --> 01:49:58.800
worked hard, cared about their

01:49:58.800 --> 01:49:59.579
dragonettes.

01:49:59.640 --> 01:50:01.319
They were happy to be safe.

01:50:01.380 --> 01:50:04.079
They weren't so different from Blue and

01:50:04.079 --> 01:50:04.859
his family.

01:50:04.920 --> 01:50:07.560
Surely they wouldn't let him be dragged

01:50:07.560 --> 01:50:10.979
away by guards to whatever happened to

01:50:10.979 --> 01:50:11.939
flame silks.

01:50:11.939 --> 01:50:14.880
Did they even know about flame silks?

01:50:14.939 --> 01:50:18.239
Behind him, he heard clanking and running

01:50:18.239 --> 01:50:19.380
talon steps.

01:50:19.439 --> 01:50:21.720
He tried to deck his head even farther

01:50:21.720 --> 01:50:25.439
following Io around a tall, fort like

01:50:25.439 --> 01:50:28.500
playhouse, where 3 hive wing dragonettes

01:50:28.500 --> 01:50:30.479
passed pretend honey tea out the

01:50:30.479 --> 01:50:30.960
windows.

01:50:31.079 --> 01:50:34.260
The open air wasn't too far away now.

01:50:34.380 --> 01:50:37.739
In a moment, Io could swoop him off into

01:50:37.739 --> 01:50:38.520
the grassland.

01:50:38.640 --> 01:50:42.239
Hive Wings didn't like going out too far

01:50:42.239 --> 01:50:44.640
into the Savannah, so they should be able

01:50:44.640 --> 01:50:46.260
to find somewhere to hide out there.

01:50:46.319 --> 01:50:49.619
And then Io could explain everything to

01:50:49.619 --> 01:50:52.199
him, and they could figure out a safe way

01:50:52.199 --> 01:50:52.979
to make this right.

01:50:53.039 --> 01:50:56.520
They were passing behind a cluster of

01:50:56.520 --> 01:50:59.520
tiny dragonettes in a sandbox, when the

01:50:59.520 --> 01:51:00.180
silence fell.

01:51:00.239 --> 01:51:04.439
It fell so suddenly, like a wall of

01:51:04.439 --> 01:51:07.199
nothingness, that Blue found himself

01:51:07.199 --> 01:51:09.000
pausing to touch his ears in

01:51:09.000 --> 01:51:10.020
bewilderment.

01:51:10.140 --> 01:51:12.960
Why did everyone stop?

01:51:13.020 --> 01:51:15.359
Talking.

01:51:15.420 --> 01:51:18.720
He glanced around uneasily.

01:51:18.779 --> 01:51:21.779
They hadn't just stopped talking.

01:51:21.840 --> 01:51:24.779
Every hive wing inside was frozen.

01:51:24.899 --> 01:51:27.420
Right in the middle of whatever they'd

01:51:27.420 --> 01:51:27.840
been doing.

01:51:27.899 --> 01:51:31.140
The dragonette halfway up the climbing

01:51:31.140 --> 01:51:33.420
structure had one claw raised.

01:51:33.479 --> 01:51:36.600
The twins in the sandbox were scowling at

01:51:36.600 --> 01:51:39.659
each other, mouths open, but no sound

01:51:39.659 --> 01:51:40.439
coming out.

01:51:40.439 --> 01:51:44.159
Io slowed to a stop in front of him.

01:51:44.220 --> 01:51:46.920
Spreading her wings slightly to keep him

01:51:46.920 --> 01:51:47.100
back.

01:51:47.159 --> 01:51:50.699
Her gaze nervously darted around at the

01:51:50.699 --> 01:51:51.840
silent dragons.

01:51:51.899 --> 01:51:55.260
Blue realized that the other silk wings

01:51:55.260 --> 01:51:57.779
in the park were looking around too, many

01:51:57.779 --> 01:51:59.100
of them just as bewildered.

01:51:59.220 --> 01:52:02.279
And then the hive wings lifted their

01:52:02.279 --> 01:52:02.579
heads.

01:52:02.699 --> 01:52:06.060
All of them at once, and tilted their

01:52:06.060 --> 01:52:07.619
chins toward the east.

01:52:07.739 --> 01:52:10.920
Blue felt a scream building in his

01:52:10.920 --> 01:52:11.340
throat.

01:52:11.399 --> 01:52:15.420
All of their eyes had gone pure white.

01:52:15.479 --> 01:52:18.960
Find the flame soaked dragonette.

01:52:19.020 --> 01:52:21.420
The hive wings said in unison.

01:52:21.479 --> 01:52:25.319
Capture him, and bring him to me.

01:52:25.380 --> 01:52:30.060
Chapter 6.

01:52:30.119 --> 01:52:33.779
A shriek of terror ripped through the

01:52:33.779 --> 01:52:34.319
heavy air.

01:52:34.380 --> 01:52:36.180
But it wasn't coming from blue.

01:52:36.239 --> 01:52:38.640
It came from near the pool.

01:52:38.699 --> 01:52:41.939
From a young silk wing, with pale blue

01:52:41.939 --> 01:52:44.880
and pink wings, holding a baby hive wing

01:52:44.880 --> 01:52:46.140
in his arms.

01:52:46.199 --> 01:52:48.720
The tiny dragonette glared up at him with

01:52:48.720 --> 01:52:50.039
its fathomless eyes.

01:52:50.100 --> 01:52:51.960
Aphid?

01:52:52.020 --> 01:52:53.880
The silk wing cried.

01:52:53.939 --> 01:52:55.140
What's wrong with you?

01:52:55.199 --> 01:52:57.239
Aphid, can you hear me?

01:52:57.300 --> 01:53:01.680
Aphid bared small teeth, and twisted his

01:53:01.680 --> 01:53:03.960
body fiercely, struggling to get free.

01:53:04.079 --> 01:53:08.939
Let him go, said an older silkwing softly

01:53:09.000 --> 01:53:11.100
touching the younger one's shoulder.

01:53:11.159 --> 01:53:13.739
They're not themselves right now.

01:53:13.800 --> 01:53:17.640
The dragonette snapped at his caretaker's

01:53:17.640 --> 01:53:20.399
talons, as the silk wings set him gently

01:53:20.399 --> 01:53:20.880
on the ground.

01:53:20.939 --> 01:53:24.720
Where is the flame silk?

01:53:24.840 --> 01:53:28.560
Avid said, and spine chilling unison with

01:53:28.560 --> 01:53:29.460
the other hive wings.

01:53:29.520 --> 01:53:31.920
Who can see him?

01:53:32.279 --> 01:53:34.979
The hive wings all slowly.

01:53:35.100 --> 01:53:38.340
Eerily began swiveling their heads

01:53:38.340 --> 01:53:41.279
staring in turn at each silk wing in

01:53:41.279 --> 01:53:44.220
their line of sight, like snakes studying

01:53:44.220 --> 01:53:45.600
a herd for the weakest prey.

01:53:45.659 --> 01:53:48.000
Io?

01:53:48.060 --> 01:53:50.279
Blue whispered as softly as he could.

01:53:50.340 --> 01:53:52.260
I think.

01:53:52.500 --> 01:53:55.680
Run, she whispered back.

01:53:55.739 --> 01:53:57.840
They bolted for the exit.

01:53:57.899 --> 01:54:00.659
Blues, legs, screaming in protest.

01:54:00.720 --> 01:54:03.479
Every head snapped toward them.

01:54:03.539 --> 01:54:07.500
A black spotted scarlet dragonette, no

01:54:07.500 --> 01:54:09.899
taller than Blue's wing buds, threw

01:54:09.899 --> 01:54:12.239
herself off a slide at them, hissing.

01:54:12.300 --> 01:54:15.659
She landed on Io's back and sank in her

01:54:15.659 --> 01:54:18.539
claws, but Io dove into a roll and

01:54:18.539 --> 01:54:19.020
knocked her off.

01:54:19.079 --> 01:54:22.619
Blue felt pin pricks of pain stab into

01:54:22.619 --> 01:54:22.979
his ankle.

01:54:23.039 --> 01:54:26.460
He glanced back as he ran, and found an

01:54:26.460 --> 01:54:28.920
orange dragonette with his teeth embedded

01:54:28.920 --> 01:54:31.619
in Blue's back leg, too small to do much

01:54:31.619 --> 01:54:33.960
damage, but hanging on grimly.

01:54:34.020 --> 01:54:36.840
How do I shake him off without hurting

01:54:36.840 --> 01:54:37.079
him?

01:54:37.140 --> 01:54:38.699
Blue thought frantically.

01:54:38.760 --> 01:54:41.340
There was no more time to think.

01:54:41.399 --> 01:54:44.640
Two much larger hive wings blocked their

01:54:44.640 --> 01:54:47.640
path, wings spread and claws gleaming.

01:54:47.760 --> 01:54:52.439
Give up, wingless, they said, you cannot

01:54:52.439 --> 01:54:53.279
escape me.

01:54:53.399 --> 01:54:56.699
Blue skitted to a stop, and the

01:54:56.699 --> 01:54:58.199
dragonette tumbled off his ankle.

01:54:58.260 --> 01:55:00.840
There were hive wings in every direction

01:55:00.840 --> 01:55:02.760
all focused on him.

01:55:02.819 --> 01:55:04.920
The voice was right.

01:55:04.979 --> 01:55:08.819
There was no, Io barreled into the 2

01:55:08.819 --> 01:55:09.840
dragons in front of them.

01:55:09.899 --> 01:55:12.720
Her wings flapped huge and purple in

01:55:12.720 --> 01:55:14.760
their faces, driving them back for a

01:55:14.760 --> 01:55:16.439
moment, clearing a path.

01:55:16.500 --> 01:55:18.659
And there was the sky.

01:55:18.720 --> 01:55:22.979
Blue darted to the opening and ran pell

01:55:22.979 --> 01:55:24.060
mell toward the ledge.

01:55:24.119 --> 01:55:25.260
It was close now.

01:55:25.380 --> 01:55:28.439
He could see 2 of the 3 moons rising.

01:55:28.500 --> 01:55:31.979
He could see small twisted trees, and a

01:55:31.979 --> 01:55:34.260
distant giraffe, and the long yellow

01:55:34.260 --> 01:55:38.939
grass waving far below. too far below.

01:55:39.000 --> 01:55:41.460
He reached the edge and froze.

01:55:41.520 --> 01:55:45.060
The wall of the hive plunged down before

01:55:45.060 --> 01:55:45.479
him.

01:55:45.539 --> 01:55:48.960
Impossibly steep, impossibly terrifying.

01:55:49.020 --> 01:55:52.859
This level was far below the webs, but

01:55:52.859 --> 01:55:54.479
still a long way from the ground.

01:55:54.600 --> 01:55:57.180
Blue couldn't possibly jump from here.

01:55:57.239 --> 01:55:59.279
He would break his neck and die.

01:55:59.399 --> 01:56:02.279
If only I had my wings.

01:56:02.399 --> 01:56:06.239
He turned and saw Io fighting off 3 full

01:56:06.239 --> 01:56:07.319
grown hive wings.

01:56:07.380 --> 01:56:10.979
Their talons slashed at her side, and one

01:56:10.979 --> 01:56:13.500
had his tail raised to stab her with a

01:56:13.500 --> 01:56:14.100
stinger at the end.

01:56:14.159 --> 01:56:15.960
Io!

01:56:16.020 --> 01:56:17.159
Blue cried.

01:56:17.220 --> 01:56:19.920
Go, Blue, she shrieked.

01:56:19.979 --> 01:56:21.180
Get out of here.

01:56:21.239 --> 01:56:22.920
I can't.

01:56:23.039 --> 01:56:26.340
He felt tears finally start to flood his

01:56:26.340 --> 01:56:26.579
eyes.

01:56:26.640 --> 01:56:28.859
I can't go without you.

01:56:28.979 --> 01:56:30.960
In a way, he meant.

01:56:31.079 --> 01:56:32.579
I can't fly from here.

01:56:32.640 --> 01:56:33.840
I need your wings.

01:56:33.899 --> 01:56:36.600
But in another deeper way.

01:56:36.659 --> 01:56:38.699
He really meant that he couldn't leave

01:56:38.699 --> 01:56:40.560
her at the mercy of these zombie

01:56:40.560 --> 01:56:40.979
dragons.

01:56:41.039 --> 01:56:43.560
He couldn't keep running, alone.

01:56:43.619 --> 01:56:46.199
Knowing she would be caught and punished

01:56:46.199 --> 01:56:48.720
and punished worse if he did escape.

01:56:48.779 --> 01:56:50.880
You have to.

01:56:51.000 --> 01:56:52.380
She shouted.

01:56:52.439 --> 01:56:55.079
But she must have realized he couldn't

01:56:55.079 --> 01:56:55.859
take that leap.

01:56:55.920 --> 01:56:58.560
As he took an indecisive step back toward

01:56:58.560 --> 01:56:58.800
her.

01:56:58.859 --> 01:57:01.739
She kicked a hive wing in the face and

01:57:01.739 --> 01:57:04.439
broke free for a moment, just long enough

01:57:04.439 --> 01:57:06.300
for her to grab a twisted ladder

01:57:06.300 --> 01:57:08.579
structure, and knock it over between her

01:57:08.579 --> 01:57:09.659
and her attackers.

01:57:09.720 --> 01:57:11.939
And the breath that gave her.

01:57:12.000 --> 01:57:14.640
She shot a twist of silk from her wrists

01:57:14.640 --> 01:57:17.100
up at the ceiling, and another that

01:57:17.100 --> 01:57:18.960
coiled around Blue's ankle.

01:57:19.020 --> 01:57:21.899
A heartbeat later, he was hurled toward

01:57:21.899 --> 01:57:22.619
the roof.

01:57:22.680 --> 01:57:25.619
His claws caught the webs that Io was

01:57:25.619 --> 01:57:27.180
shooting across the top of the cavern.

01:57:27.300 --> 01:57:30.539
Instinctively, he swung to the next one

01:57:30.539 --> 01:57:31.439
and then the next.

01:57:31.500 --> 01:57:33.300
He jumped swiftly.

01:57:33.359 --> 01:57:35.819
Like they'd learned to do in school

01:57:35.819 --> 01:57:37.439
during emergency drills.

01:57:37.439 --> 01:57:39.479
What if the web is falling?

01:57:39.539 --> 01:57:42.119
What if you have to get to a hive quickly

01:57:42.119 --> 01:57:42.720
for safety?

01:57:42.779 --> 01:57:45.600
What if you only have a few strands of

01:57:45.600 --> 01:57:46.560
silk to escape along?

01:57:46.619 --> 01:57:49.619
But those drills had been about the

01:57:49.619 --> 01:57:51.659
thread of leaf wings attacking the webs.

01:57:51.720 --> 01:57:54.119
They were practiced so that little

01:57:54.119 --> 01:57:56.159
wingless dragonettes would be ready to

01:57:56.159 --> 01:57:58.260
flee to a place where hive wings could

01:57:58.260 --> 01:57:58.739
protect them.

01:57:58.800 --> 01:58:02.399
Never once, despite his overactive

01:58:02.399 --> 01:58:03.119
imagination.

01:58:03.180 --> 01:58:06.420
Had Blue ever imagined using these skills

01:58:06.420 --> 01:58:08.699
to run away from hive wings?

01:58:08.760 --> 01:58:11.159
He shot over the heads of the families on

01:58:11.159 --> 01:58:14.039
the playground so fast that they lost

01:58:14.039 --> 01:58:15.239
track of him for a moment.

01:58:15.300 --> 01:58:17.880
As they whipped their heads around

01:58:17.880 --> 01:58:21.000
buzzing and hissing, he reached the end

01:58:21.000 --> 01:58:24.359
of Io's silk, shielded by a tall slide

01:58:24.359 --> 01:58:26.399
near the walls of the school, and looked

01:58:26.399 --> 01:58:26.640
back.

01:58:26.699 --> 01:58:30.840
Io was almost the ledge, and with the

01:58:30.840 --> 01:58:33.180
hive wings distracted, looking for him.

01:58:33.239 --> 01:58:35.640
She might be able to get out and fly

01:58:35.640 --> 01:58:35.880
away.

01:58:35.939 --> 01:58:37.800
But not with him.

01:58:37.859 --> 01:58:40.619
She'd only be able to escape without

01:58:40.619 --> 01:58:40.979
him.

01:58:41.039 --> 01:58:44.520
He gouged a chunk of tree stuff out of

01:58:44.520 --> 01:58:46.680
the ceiling above him, and threw it as

01:58:46.680 --> 01:58:48.060
far and hard as he could.

01:58:48.119 --> 01:58:51.359
It landed with a scattering thud halfway

01:58:51.359 --> 01:58:53.760
across the playground, and all the hive

01:58:53.760 --> 01:58:55.260
wings spun toward the sound.

01:58:55.380 --> 01:58:59.699
Blue let go of Io's silk, and dropped to

01:58:59.699 --> 01:59:01.979
the top of the school wall, then over it

01:59:01.979 --> 01:59:03.659
and down into the small courtyard

01:59:03.659 --> 01:59:04.020
beyond.

01:59:04.079 --> 01:59:07.979
Triangles of lime colored chalk marked

01:59:07.979 --> 01:59:09.779
out the games young hive wings played

01:59:09.779 --> 01:59:10.739
here during recess.

01:59:10.800 --> 01:59:12.000
For a moment.

01:59:12.060 --> 01:59:14.340
Blue thought about grabbing one of the

01:59:14.340 --> 01:59:16.439
pale blue metal practice spears that

01:59:16.439 --> 01:59:17.819
leaned against the wall.

01:59:17.880 --> 01:59:20.399
But the truth was that he'd be more

01:59:20.399 --> 01:59:22.319
likely to hurt himself than anyone else

01:59:22.319 --> 01:59:24.720
with one of those, and he couldn't even

01:59:24.720 --> 01:59:27.180
begin to imagine stabbing another dragon

01:59:27.180 --> 01:59:27.899
on purpose.

01:59:27.960 --> 01:59:30.119
Where do I go?

01:59:30.239 --> 01:59:33.359
He glanced around the courtyard, trying

01:59:33.359 --> 01:59:34.140
to catch his breath.

01:59:34.199 --> 01:59:37.079
It was surrounded on all sides by the

01:59:37.079 --> 01:59:39.180
school, except for the wall behind him

01:59:39.180 --> 01:59:41.939
which had the neighborhood park and a

01:59:41.939 --> 01:59:44.520
horde of white eyed zombie dragons on the

01:59:44.520 --> 01:59:44.880
other side.

01:59:44.939 --> 01:59:48.840
They'll follow the trail of Ayu silk. and

01:59:48.840 --> 01:59:50.100
figure out where I went in a moment.

01:59:50.159 --> 01:59:52.859
Even if I can get out of this school

01:59:52.859 --> 01:59:53.460
somehow.

01:59:53.579 --> 01:59:55.380
Where would I go after that?

01:59:55.439 --> 01:59:57.600
I can't go back to mother.

01:59:57.659 --> 02:00:00.960
I'm sure Swordtail will be on misbehavors

02:00:00.960 --> 02:00:01.739
way by morning.

02:00:01.859 --> 02:00:03.899
If he's still alive.

02:00:03.960 --> 02:00:06.720
And I have no idea what they've done with

02:00:06.720 --> 02:00:07.199
Luna.

02:00:07.260 --> 02:00:10.260
He pressed his talons to his mouth.

02:00:10.380 --> 02:00:12.180
He didn't have time to cry.

02:00:12.239 --> 02:00:14.880
He didn't have time to be sucked into

02:00:14.880 --> 02:00:17.880
imagining how Luna and sore tail, and

02:00:17.880 --> 02:00:19.739
Burnett and Io must be feeling right

02:00:19.739 --> 02:00:19.920
now.

02:00:20.039 --> 02:00:23.520
He started across the courtyard toward

02:00:23.520 --> 02:00:24.300
one of the school doors.

02:00:24.359 --> 02:00:26.760
Although at this time of day, he was

02:00:26.760 --> 02:00:28.020
afraid they'd all be locked.

02:00:28.079 --> 02:00:29.760
Psst.

02:00:29.880 --> 02:00:31.079
Over here.

02:00:31.140 --> 02:00:33.180
Blue whirled around.

02:00:33.239 --> 02:00:36.239
A small equipment shed was built along

02:00:36.239 --> 02:00:38.880
the side of one of the school walls, the

02:00:38.880 --> 02:00:41.279
door was open a crack, and a pair of

02:00:41.279 --> 02:00:43.199
golden yellow talons was reaching out of

02:00:43.199 --> 02:00:44.880
it, beckoning to him.

02:00:44.939 --> 02:00:47.760
He could hear the hive wing voices

02:00:47.760 --> 02:00:49.859
issuing commands on the other side of the

02:00:49.859 --> 02:00:50.100
wall.

02:00:50.159 --> 02:00:52.500
There wasn't time to be worried and

02:00:52.500 --> 02:00:53.279
indecisive.

02:00:53.340 --> 02:00:56.279
He bolted toward the shed, and let the

02:00:56.279 --> 02:00:57.960
strange talons yank him inside.

02:00:58.020 --> 02:01:01.920
The door snicked shut behind him. leaving

02:01:01.920 --> 02:01:03.119
them in pitch darkness.

02:01:03.180 --> 02:01:06.899
Blue tripped over a ball under his claws

02:01:06.899 --> 02:01:09.659
and the other dragon caught him, strong

02:01:09.659 --> 02:01:10.800
arms holding him up.

02:01:10.859 --> 02:01:13.380
He felt the brush of wings against his

02:01:13.380 --> 02:01:13.560
side.

02:01:13.619 --> 02:01:16.859
This was a silk wing who had already gone

02:01:16.859 --> 02:01:19.199
through metamorphosis then, but it must

02:01:19.199 --> 02:01:19.800
have been recently.

02:01:19.859 --> 02:01:22.500
This dragon was smaller than he was.

02:01:22.560 --> 02:01:24.119
Who?

02:01:24.119 --> 02:01:25.260
He whispered.

02:01:25.319 --> 02:01:27.359
She said.

02:01:27.420 --> 02:01:30.060
She wrapped her front claws softly around

02:01:30.060 --> 02:01:30.659
his snout.

02:01:30.779 --> 02:01:33.659
The shed was small, and packed with

02:01:33.659 --> 02:01:34.619
paraphernalia.

02:01:34.680 --> 02:01:37.020
There was barely room for Blue and the

02:01:37.020 --> 02:01:38.039
other dragon to stand.

02:01:38.100 --> 02:01:41.520
His claws fell clumsily entangled with

02:01:41.520 --> 02:01:41.939
hers.

02:01:42.000 --> 02:01:45.300
His neck kept bumping against cool scales

02:01:45.300 --> 02:01:48.300
and her tail lightly rested over his.

02:01:48.359 --> 02:01:51.960
But she was so perfectly still, that he

02:01:51.960 --> 02:01:52.560
couldn't pull away.

02:01:52.619 --> 02:01:56.699
Or at least, he feared that if he did, he

02:01:56.699 --> 02:01:58.439
might knock over a wall of armor or

02:01:58.439 --> 02:01:58.859
something.

02:01:58.859 --> 02:02:01.739
He wondered if she could feel his heart

02:02:01.739 --> 02:02:03.180
slamming around his chest.

02:02:03.300 --> 02:02:05.399
Did she work at the school?

02:02:05.520 --> 02:02:08.520
cleaning hive wing classrooms, or

02:02:08.520 --> 02:02:09.659
preparing their snacks.

02:02:09.779 --> 02:02:12.720
Had she ever seen the hive wings act like

02:02:12.720 --> 02:02:13.140
this before?

02:02:13.199 --> 02:02:16.079
As though their minds had all melded into

02:02:16.079 --> 02:02:16.380
one?

02:02:16.439 --> 02:02:18.960
Did she know what was happening?

02:02:19.020 --> 02:02:21.779
And how dangerous it was to protect him?

02:02:21.840 --> 02:02:25.560
Don't move, she whispered.

02:02:25.619 --> 02:02:27.899
Apple scented breath in his ear.

02:02:27.960 --> 02:02:31.260
She let go of his face, and in the dark

02:02:31.260 --> 02:02:34.199
he felt her crouch beside him, reaching

02:02:34.199 --> 02:02:35.039
for the inner wall.

02:02:35.100 --> 02:02:37.739
Her wings were like a cloud of

02:02:37.739 --> 02:02:40.560
butterflies against his scales, touching

02:02:40.560 --> 02:02:42.659
down and taking off in a 1000 little

02:02:42.659 --> 02:02:43.140
brushes.

02:02:43.199 --> 02:02:45.779
Maybe she was scared too.

02:02:45.840 --> 02:02:49.260
Or had she rescued other silk wings like

02:02:49.260 --> 02:02:49.560
this before?

02:02:49.619 --> 02:02:53.100
He tried to imagine being that brave

02:02:53.100 --> 02:02:55.800
brave enough to see a dragon in trouble.

02:02:55.859 --> 02:03:00.239
And an entire tribe turned terrifying, and

02:03:00.239 --> 02:03:01.199
still reach out to help.

02:03:01.260 --> 02:03:05.100
Maybe if he imagined it hard enough, he

02:03:05.100 --> 02:03:06.779
could make himself a little braver too.

02:03:06.840 --> 02:03:10.260
She took one of his front talons and

02:03:10.260 --> 02:03:12.960
touched it to the wall, or rather, to a

02:03:12.960 --> 02:03:15.239
spot where the wall disappeared, an

02:03:15.239 --> 02:03:17.699
opening, a trap door into a tunnel.

02:03:17.760 --> 02:03:21.539
Stay close to me, she whispered.

02:03:21.600 --> 02:03:23.699
The tunnels can be confusing.

02:03:23.760 --> 02:03:27.000
Are you with the chrysalis?

02:03:27.060 --> 02:03:30.300
He whispered back, his nose bumping hers

02:03:30.300 --> 02:03:31.500
as he turned toward her.

02:03:31.560 --> 02:03:33.779
She touched his mouth again.

02:03:33.840 --> 02:03:37.199
A hush gesture before ducking into the

02:03:37.199 --> 02:03:37.500
tunnel.

02:03:37.560 --> 02:03:40.979
He followed as close as he dared, trying

02:03:40.979 --> 02:03:42.180
not to step on her tail.

02:03:42.239 --> 02:03:45.479
It was like crawling through an ant farm

02:03:45.479 --> 02:03:48.180
following the tunnels in a winding maze

02:03:48.180 --> 02:03:49.439
through the walls of the school.

02:03:49.500 --> 02:03:52.380
Here and there chinks of light shone

02:03:52.380 --> 02:03:54.600
through the cracks, and blue caught

02:03:54.600 --> 02:03:56.819
glimpses of the buttercup yellow scales

02:03:56.819 --> 02:03:58.199
of the dragon in the dark.

02:03:58.319 --> 02:04:00.840
Through the cracks, he could also see

02:04:00.840 --> 02:04:03.539
fragments of the school, even rows of

02:04:03.539 --> 02:04:06.359
tables, a blackboard covered with neat

02:04:06.359 --> 02:04:09.239
columns of numbers, an easel divided into

02:04:09.239 --> 02:04:11.100
narrow lines of blue and black paint.

02:04:11.159 --> 02:04:15.000
At last, she stopped, and peeked through

02:04:15.000 --> 02:04:17.340
a small hole just at eye level.

02:04:17.399 --> 02:04:21.180
After a moment, she unlatched a trap door

02:04:21.180 --> 02:04:24.119
pushed it open, and climbed out, beckoning

02:04:24.119 --> 02:04:25.020
for him to follow.

02:04:25.079 --> 02:04:27.300
He had to deck his head as he came

02:04:27.300 --> 02:04:27.539
through.

02:04:27.600 --> 02:04:30.300
Since the trap door opened out of the

02:04:30.300 --> 02:04:31.680
wall under a long table.

02:04:31.739 --> 02:04:34.800
Blue's eyes were dazzled for a moment as

02:04:34.800 --> 02:04:35.460
he crawled out.

02:04:35.520 --> 02:04:38.039
Although the room they were in was not

02:04:38.039 --> 02:04:39.060
particularly bright.

02:04:39.119 --> 02:04:42.479
It had no outer windows and was led only

02:04:42.479 --> 02:04:44.039
by a few small lamps.

02:04:44.039 --> 02:04:47.100
The 1st thing he saw, as his eyes

02:04:47.100 --> 02:04:49.020
adjusted, were the books.

02:04:49.079 --> 02:04:52.800
Shelves and shelves of books, reaching

02:04:52.800 --> 02:04:54.600
floor to ceiling all around the room.

02:04:54.720 --> 02:04:57.960
He stretched his aching legs and turned

02:04:57.960 --> 02:05:01.439
in a slow, wondering circle, thinking of

02:05:01.439 --> 02:05:03.060
the students who were lucky enough to

02:05:03.060 --> 02:05:04.800
attend a school with so many books.

02:05:04.920 --> 02:05:07.500
Had anyone read all of them?

02:05:07.560 --> 02:05:10.619
Did the librarian love handing them out?

02:05:10.680 --> 02:05:13.199
Or did she wish she could keep all of

02:05:13.199 --> 02:05:15.000
them safely within the circle of her

02:05:15.000 --> 02:05:15.180
wings?

02:05:15.300 --> 02:05:19.619
This is our library. said his rescuer

02:05:19.619 --> 02:05:22.439
hopping up onto the table and curling her

02:05:22.439 --> 02:05:23.939
tail around her back claws.

02:05:24.000 --> 02:05:27.359
I know, it's pretty small, but it's

02:05:27.359 --> 02:05:28.199
closed most of the time.

02:05:28.260 --> 02:05:31.020
We share our librarian with a bigger

02:05:31.020 --> 02:05:31.739
school up level.

02:05:31.800 --> 02:05:34.199
So it's a good place to hide when the

02:05:34.199 --> 02:05:36.119
rest of the tribe goes all creepy eyes.

02:05:36.180 --> 02:05:40.380
Blue turned slowly toward her, his heart

02:05:40.380 --> 02:05:41.819
thumping like mad.

02:05:41.880 --> 02:05:45.779
Her claws were small and sharp, like a

02:05:45.779 --> 02:05:48.300
leopard's, and her fore wings swooped

02:05:48.300 --> 02:05:50.100
down from her back in beautiful smooth

02:05:50.100 --> 02:05:50.699
folds.

02:05:50.760 --> 02:05:54.600
She had an open, curious face, gold

02:05:54.600 --> 02:05:57.720
rimmed spectacles, and warm, dark brown

02:05:57.720 --> 02:06:00.479
eyes that made him think of owls and tree

02:06:00.479 --> 02:06:01.140
hollows.

02:06:01.199 --> 02:06:03.420
In the glow of the lamplight.

02:06:03.479 --> 02:06:06.060
Her scales were gold and tangerine.

02:06:06.119 --> 02:06:08.819
But speckled here and there with black

02:06:08.819 --> 02:06:11.819
scales that looked like tiny ink blots.

02:06:11.880 --> 02:06:13.979
Black scales.

02:06:14.039 --> 02:06:16.920
The unmistakable sign of a dragon

02:06:16.920 --> 02:06:18.420
descended from clear sight.

02:06:18.479 --> 02:06:21.779
Silkwings never had black scales.

02:06:21.840 --> 02:06:25.380
His rescuer was a hive wing.

02:06:25.439 --> 02:06:29.760
Chapter 7.

02:06:29.819 --> 02:06:32.939
Blue inhaled sharply.

02:06:33.000 --> 02:06:36.539
I I thought, he stammered.

02:06:36.659 --> 02:06:41.760
Wow, you're beautiful, she said

02:06:41.760 --> 02:06:42.420
wonderingly.

02:06:42.539 --> 02:06:45.300
I've never seen a silk wing in those

02:06:45.300 --> 02:06:46.739
shades of blue and purple before.

02:06:46.800 --> 02:06:48.960
Is that what your parents look like too?

02:06:49.020 --> 02:06:54.300
Um, he said, looking down at his Azure

02:06:54.300 --> 02:06:55.020
talons.

02:06:55.079 --> 02:06:56.220
Not exactly.

02:06:56.279 --> 02:06:58.619
Or I mean, I'm not sure.

02:06:58.680 --> 02:07:00.300
I've never met my father.

02:07:00.359 --> 02:07:01.680
Shouldn't you?

02:07:02.460 --> 02:07:02.699
Really?

02:07:02.760 --> 02:07:03.600
She said.

02:07:03.659 --> 02:07:06.119
She tipped her head at him.

02:07:06.180 --> 02:07:08.399
Catching sparkles from the lamps and her

02:07:08.399 --> 02:07:08.819
glasses.

02:07:08.880 --> 02:07:11.340
Why don't you know your father?

02:07:11.399 --> 02:07:13.500
Is that normal for Silk Wings?

02:07:13.560 --> 02:07:15.239
Don't you live with your parents?

02:07:15.300 --> 02:07:17.039
Or, I'm sorry.

02:07:17.100 --> 02:07:19.079
Is that a question I'm not supposed to

02:07:19.079 --> 02:07:19.319
ask?

02:07:19.380 --> 02:07:21.300
I ask a lot of questions.

02:07:21.359 --> 02:07:22.319
I'm not supposed to ask.

02:07:22.380 --> 02:07:25.020
Apparently, according to most of my

02:07:25.020 --> 02:07:25.500
teachers.

02:07:25.619 --> 02:07:27.060
Also my parents.

02:07:27.119 --> 02:07:29.640
Actually, according to pretty much every

02:07:29.640 --> 02:07:30.899
grown up hive wing.

02:07:30.960 --> 02:07:33.899
Too many questions, cricket, don't you

02:07:33.899 --> 02:07:35.579
know what happens to nosy little hive

02:07:35.579 --> 02:07:37.560
wings, they lose those noses.

02:07:37.680 --> 02:07:39.479
Which is silly.

02:07:39.539 --> 02:07:41.520
I've never seen a dragonette without a

02:07:41.520 --> 02:07:45.000
nose, and I'm sure I can't be the 1st one

02:07:45.000 --> 02:07:45.840
with this many questions.

02:07:45.960 --> 02:07:47.399
What's your name?

02:07:47.460 --> 02:07:49.739
Oh, that's another question.

02:07:49.800 --> 02:07:50.819
Sorry.

02:07:50.939 --> 02:07:52.380
I'm Cricket.

02:07:52.439 --> 02:07:54.840
Blue, he said.

02:07:54.899 --> 02:07:56.460
I'm Blue.

02:07:56.520 --> 02:08:00.600
You sure are, she said, and giggled.

02:08:00.659 --> 02:08:02.520
Oh dear, I'm sorry.

02:08:02.579 --> 02:08:04.260
I bet you've heard that one before.

02:08:04.319 --> 02:08:08.279
He took a step closer to her. trying to

02:08:08.279 --> 02:08:10.319
rearrange his understanding of what kind

02:08:10.319 --> 02:08:11.640
of dragon she was.

02:08:11.699 --> 02:08:14.520
A hive wing who helped silk wings.

02:08:14.579 --> 02:08:16.500
That wasn't a thing.

02:08:16.560 --> 02:08:22.380
Um, shouldn't you be all mind controlled

02:08:22.380 --> 02:08:23.100
too?

02:08:23.159 --> 02:08:25.680
She finished for him and hesitated.

02:08:25.739 --> 02:08:28.680
Yes, I should be.

02:08:28.739 --> 02:08:32.399
Every other hive wing is, I have no idea

02:08:32.399 --> 02:08:33.239
why I'm not.

02:08:33.300 --> 02:08:36.840
She flicked her wings and settled them

02:08:36.840 --> 02:08:37.979
again with a little laugh.

02:08:38.100 --> 02:08:40.979
I can't believe I've kept that secret for

02:08:40.979 --> 02:08:41.760
6 years.

02:08:41.819 --> 02:08:44.279
And the 1st dragon I'm telling is a

02:08:44.279 --> 02:08:45.359
strange silkwing.

02:08:45.359 --> 02:08:47.880
Katy did is going to be so mad.

02:08:48.000 --> 02:08:50.939
Is that what happened to everyone?

02:08:51.000 --> 02:08:52.739
Mind control?

02:08:52.800 --> 02:08:55.020
You didn't know about that?

02:08:55.140 --> 02:08:56.100
She said.

02:08:56.159 --> 02:08:59.640
I mean, I suppose I didn't either until I

02:08:59.640 --> 02:09:00.840
saw it happen the 1st time.

02:09:00.899 --> 02:09:04.800
She doesn't do it very often, but Queen

02:09:04.800 --> 02:09:07.140
Wasp can control every hive wing in the

02:09:07.140 --> 02:09:11.939
tribe, one at a time, or just one hive, or

02:09:11.939 --> 02:09:13.619
everyone at once if she wants to.

02:09:13.680 --> 02:09:16.319
Whoa.

02:09:16.380 --> 02:09:19.260
Blue said, reeling a little.

02:09:19.319 --> 02:09:22.020
I know, she said.

02:09:22.079 --> 02:09:24.000
Except you?

02:09:24.060 --> 02:09:24.960
He said.

02:09:25.020 --> 02:09:26.640
Except me.

02:09:26.760 --> 02:09:28.680
Isn't that fascinating?

02:09:28.739 --> 02:09:32.399
Her face lit up, like all 3 moons rising

02:09:32.399 --> 02:09:32.699
at once.

02:09:32.760 --> 02:09:34.680
I can't figure it out.

02:09:34.739 --> 02:09:37.560
There's nothing in any of these books

02:09:37.560 --> 02:09:38.640
about how she does it.

02:09:38.699 --> 02:09:40.319
Is it genetic?

02:09:40.380 --> 02:09:42.300
Am I some kind of mutation?

02:09:42.359 --> 02:09:44.340
Or could it be something we eat?

02:09:44.399 --> 02:09:46.260
But I ate everything.

02:09:46.319 --> 02:09:49.319
And like, a lot of everything.

02:09:49.380 --> 02:09:51.420
I'm always hungry.

02:09:51.479 --> 02:09:52.920
It's so mysterious.

02:09:52.979 --> 02:09:55.619
There is seriously nothing about me

02:09:55.619 --> 02:09:57.420
that's different from all the other hive

02:09:57.420 --> 02:09:57.779
wings.

02:09:57.899 --> 02:10:00.300
Blue thought there was.

02:10:00.359 --> 02:10:02.939
He'd never met another hive wing like

02:10:02.939 --> 02:10:03.060
her.

02:10:03.119 --> 02:10:06.300
First of all, willing to talk to a silk

02:10:06.300 --> 02:10:07.619
wing as though they could be friends.

02:10:07.680 --> 02:10:11.279
Second of all, looking at him as if he

02:10:11.279 --> 02:10:12.420
was a real dragon.

02:10:12.479 --> 02:10:15.720
Not a wingless curiosity or nuisance to

02:10:15.720 --> 02:10:16.319
be stepped over.

02:10:16.380 --> 02:10:21.180
That must be such a weird feeling, he

02:10:21.180 --> 02:10:21.479
said.

02:10:21.539 --> 02:10:24.239
Having someone take over your body like

02:10:24.239 --> 02:10:27.180
that, making you say things and do things

02:10:27.180 --> 02:10:29.819
you wouldn't say or do yourself.

02:10:29.880 --> 02:10:32.460
Do you think they remember it afterward?

02:10:32.520 --> 02:10:36.119
Are they in there feeling trapped?

02:10:36.119 --> 02:10:37.739
While it's happening?

02:10:37.800 --> 02:10:41.640
They do remember it, she said.

02:10:41.699 --> 02:10:44.880
They remember pretty much everything.

02:10:44.939 --> 02:10:48.300
My sister, Katie did, says it's not a

02:10:48.300 --> 02:10:49.260
trapped feeling, though.

02:10:49.319 --> 02:10:52.979
It's more like, suddenly you really want

02:10:52.979 --> 02:10:54.720
to do exactly what everyone else is

02:10:54.720 --> 02:10:54.960
doing.

02:10:55.079 --> 02:10:56.939
There's no struggle.

02:10:57.000 --> 02:10:59.939
She says it's kind of peaceful. having

02:10:59.939 --> 02:11:01.859
someone else make all the decisions for

02:11:01.859 --> 02:11:02.460
you for a bit.

02:11:02.579 --> 02:11:04.560
Maybe.

02:11:04.619 --> 02:11:07.560
Blue thought of the tiny dragonettes

02:11:07.560 --> 02:11:09.119
attacking him and shivered.

02:11:09.180 --> 02:11:12.779
Except then later you'd feel like

02:11:12.779 --> 02:11:14.279
everything you did was still your

02:11:14.279 --> 02:11:14.760
choice.

02:11:14.819 --> 02:11:17.579
And you'd probably feel guilty about it

02:11:17.579 --> 02:11:19.979
even though it wasn't really you at all.

02:11:20.039 --> 02:11:22.439
She looked surprised.

02:11:22.500 --> 02:11:25.199
And then her gaze drifted up the shelves

02:11:25.199 --> 02:11:27.539
of books as she thought about what he'd

02:11:27.539 --> 02:11:27.659
said.

02:11:27.720 --> 02:11:31.920
That's true, she said. after a moment.

02:11:32.039 --> 02:11:35.159
I don't actually know if it ever bothers

02:11:35.159 --> 02:11:35.340
them.

02:11:35.399 --> 02:11:37.439
I wonder how I can find out.

02:11:37.500 --> 02:11:41.460
She flicked her tail thoughtfully, you

02:11:41.460 --> 02:11:43.380
know, without getting my nose cut off.

02:11:43.439 --> 02:11:46.619
I think, do you ever feel bad about what

02:11:46.619 --> 02:11:48.119
Queen Wasp makes you do?

02:11:48.119 --> 02:11:51.420
is definitely one of those questions I am

02:11:51.420 --> 02:11:52.380
not supposed to ask.

02:11:52.439 --> 02:11:55.920
Especially if you don't want anyone to

02:11:55.920 --> 02:11:57.840
know that the mind control doesn't work

02:11:57.840 --> 02:11:59.279
on you, he said.

02:11:59.340 --> 02:12:00.899
Right.

02:12:00.960 --> 02:12:04.020
Cricket fiddled with the earpiece of her

02:12:04.020 --> 02:12:04.380
glasses.

02:12:04.439 --> 02:12:07.079
Katie did is the only one who knows.

02:12:07.140 --> 02:12:10.380
I'm worried Queen Wasp might be angry if

02:12:10.380 --> 02:12:10.920
she found out.

02:12:10.979 --> 02:12:15.060
So, I hide whenever it happens and hope

02:12:15.060 --> 02:12:15.960
no one notices.

02:12:16.079 --> 02:12:18.479
I won't tell anyone.

02:12:18.600 --> 02:12:20.039
Blue promised.

02:12:20.100 --> 02:12:23.279
She gave him a sweet, slightly sad smile

02:12:23.279 --> 02:12:25.560
and it occurred to him that he might

02:12:25.560 --> 02:12:27.180
never have a chance to tell anyone

02:12:27.180 --> 02:12:27.720
anyway.

02:12:27.779 --> 02:12:31.020
He felt a sharp prickle of pain under his

02:12:31.020 --> 02:12:31.680
wristband.

02:12:31.739 --> 02:12:34.979
So, what did you do?

02:12:35.100 --> 02:12:36.000
She asked.

02:12:36.060 --> 02:12:38.579
Why is the whole hive looking for you?

02:12:38.640 --> 02:12:41.460
What kind of criminal enterprise have I

02:12:41.460 --> 02:12:42.539
gotten myself involved in?

02:12:42.600 --> 02:12:46.439
She kept smiling, but Blue noticed a

02:12:46.439 --> 02:12:48.060
shiver tremble across her wings.

02:12:48.119 --> 02:12:50.520
He guessed there was a part of her that

02:12:50.520 --> 02:12:53.220
had suddenly realized she was alone with

02:12:53.220 --> 02:12:56.460
a dragon who might be dangerous. him, of

02:12:56.460 --> 02:12:58.859
all dragons, scaring a hive wing.

02:12:58.979 --> 02:13:01.920
Nothing, he said quickly.

02:13:01.979 --> 02:13:04.920
He looked up at her and put one talon on

02:13:04.920 --> 02:13:06.479
the table palm open.

02:13:06.539 --> 02:13:09.659
I promise, I am totally harmless.

02:13:09.720 --> 02:13:13.140
The most harmless, thoroughly, utterly

02:13:13.140 --> 02:13:15.239
completely incapable of harm doing.

02:13:15.300 --> 02:13:17.939
Oh, she said.

02:13:18.060 --> 02:13:19.680
She thought for a 2nd.

02:13:19.739 --> 02:13:21.779
That is reassuring.

02:13:21.840 --> 02:13:23.880
Thoroughly, utterly, completely

02:13:23.880 --> 02:13:24.779
reassuring.

02:13:24.840 --> 02:13:27.960
Except for how it's exactly what a

02:13:27.960 --> 02:13:29.220
dangerous criminal would say.

02:13:29.279 --> 02:13:31.500
Is it really?

02:13:31.560 --> 02:13:33.960
He asked, wide-eyed.

02:13:34.020 --> 02:13:35.159
Cricket laughed.

02:13:35.220 --> 02:13:36.420
I don't know.

02:13:36.479 --> 02:13:39.000
I guess I'll have to ask all my dangerous

02:13:39.000 --> 02:13:39.600
criminal friends.

02:13:39.659 --> 02:13:43.199
He liked the way her laugh made sun

02:13:43.199 --> 02:13:45.840
colored scales ripple all down her long

02:13:45.840 --> 02:13:46.140
neck.

02:13:46.199 --> 02:13:49.199
His head was starting to feel strangely

02:13:49.199 --> 02:13:49.739
woozy.

02:13:49.800 --> 02:13:53.760
What would the least dangerous dragon in

02:13:53.760 --> 02:13:54.239
the world say?

02:13:54.239 --> 02:13:55.199
he asked.

02:13:55.260 --> 02:13:58.859
Why would the least dangerous dragon in

02:13:58.859 --> 02:14:01.260
the world be running away from hive wing

02:14:01.260 --> 02:14:01.619
guards?

02:14:01.619 --> 02:14:02.579
she countered.

02:14:02.640 --> 02:14:05.220
What could he possibly have done that's

02:14:05.220 --> 02:14:05.640
so terrible?

02:14:05.699 --> 02:14:08.699
It made Queen Wasp bust out her mind

02:14:08.699 --> 02:14:09.359
control powers?

02:14:09.420 --> 02:14:13.319
The question hit blue like an entire hive

02:14:13.319 --> 02:14:14.579
collapsing on his chest.

02:14:14.640 --> 02:14:17.100
What did I do?

02:14:17.220 --> 02:14:19.560
I've always been a good dragon.

02:14:19.619 --> 02:14:21.600
Why is this happening to me?

02:14:21.659 --> 02:14:24.899
Oh no, she said.

02:14:24.960 --> 02:14:27.600
Slipping off the table and crouching

02:14:27.600 --> 02:14:29.220
beside him as he folded to the floor.

02:14:29.340 --> 02:14:32.039
Why did that make you look so sad?

02:14:32.100 --> 02:14:33.899
What happened?

02:14:33.960 --> 02:14:37.380
She unfolded her wings to shelter the

02:14:37.380 --> 02:14:38.100
curve of his back.

02:14:38.159 --> 02:14:41.100
I don't know, he said.

02:14:41.159 --> 02:14:44.279
It was splendid having her wings over him

02:14:44.279 --> 02:14:47.699
like being hugged by the sun, although

02:14:47.699 --> 02:14:49.619
actually it would probably be terrible to

02:14:49.619 --> 02:14:50.939
be hugged by the sun.

02:14:51.000 --> 02:14:52.500
This was much cooler.

02:14:52.560 --> 02:14:54.779
What was he talking about?

02:14:54.840 --> 02:14:55.739
Oh, right.

02:14:55.800 --> 02:14:57.060
The worst day ever.

02:14:57.119 --> 02:15:01.380
One moment, it was a normal metamorphosis

02:15:01.380 --> 02:15:01.619
day.

02:15:01.680 --> 02:15:05.520
And then suddenly, Luna was on fire, and

02:15:05.520 --> 02:15:08.340
Swordtail was attacking guards, and Io

02:15:08.340 --> 02:15:11.579
was carrying me, and I don't even, I mean

02:15:11.579 --> 02:15:13.619
I would never disobey a hive wing.

02:15:13.680 --> 02:15:17.279
It all just happened so fast, and I was

02:15:17.279 --> 02:15:17.939
so scared.

02:15:18.000 --> 02:15:21.840
Where the book's blurrier from this angle

02:15:21.840 --> 02:15:23.460
or were his eyes losing focus?

02:15:23.520 --> 02:15:26.819
It's your metamorphosis day?

02:15:26.880 --> 02:15:28.319
Cricket said.

02:15:28.439 --> 02:15:31.560
She tipped her head at his wing buds, but

02:15:31.560 --> 02:15:33.180
politely didn't touch them.

02:15:33.239 --> 02:15:35.579
A polite hive wing.

02:15:35.640 --> 02:15:38.520
How did she get so weird and perfect?

02:15:38.579 --> 02:15:40.859
Are you sure?

02:15:40.920 --> 02:15:42.779
They don't look ready yet.

02:15:42.899 --> 02:15:45.720
She picked up one of his talons and

02:15:45.720 --> 02:15:47.220
examined his wrist scales.

02:15:47.340 --> 02:15:50.279
No, no, Blue said.

02:15:50.340 --> 02:15:53.279
It's Luna's metamorphosis day, my

02:15:53.279 --> 02:15:53.640
sister.

02:15:53.760 --> 02:15:57.000
The one on fire, Cricket said.

02:15:57.060 --> 02:15:58.439
Is she all right?

02:15:58.500 --> 02:16:00.180
Why was she on fire?

02:16:00.300 --> 02:16:01.140
Lightning?

02:16:01.260 --> 02:16:04.199
I think I'd have noticed a lightning

02:16:04.199 --> 02:16:05.159
striking the hive today.

02:16:05.220 --> 02:16:07.800
How would fire even get into?

02:16:08.039 --> 02:16:11.159
She stopped suddenly, staring at him with

02:16:11.159 --> 02:16:11.880
her mouth open.

02:16:11.939 --> 02:16:14.340
Did you get frozen?

02:16:14.399 --> 02:16:16.380
He said in a panic.

02:16:16.439 --> 02:16:18.779
Are you being mind controlled right now?

02:16:18.840 --> 02:16:22.859
Your sister's a flame silk?

02:16:22.979 --> 02:16:25.680
She whispered in her own voice.

02:16:25.800 --> 02:16:27.420
A real one?

02:16:27.479 --> 02:16:29.640
That's amazing.

02:16:29.699 --> 02:16:31.560
It is.

02:16:31.619 --> 02:16:34.319
You, you know about those?

02:16:34.379 --> 02:16:36.779
He tried to get to his feet.

02:16:36.840 --> 02:16:39.540
Discovered that his knees had chosen an

02:16:39.540 --> 02:16:42.600
entirely different life goal, staggered a

02:16:42.600 --> 02:16:44.459
little sideways, and fell into her.

02:16:44.579 --> 02:16:49.319
Uh-oh, Cricket said, wrapping her wings

02:16:49.319 --> 02:16:49.979
around him.

02:16:50.040 --> 02:16:51.959
Let me see your wristband.

02:16:52.020 --> 02:16:54.959
He could barely move his arm over to

02:16:54.959 --> 02:16:55.860
where she could catch it.

02:16:55.920 --> 02:16:58.979
She tugged on his wristband, trying to

02:16:58.979 --> 02:17:01.440
slide a claw underneath it, but it was

02:17:01.440 --> 02:17:02.159
heavy and snug.

02:17:02.219 --> 02:17:06.059
Why is my?

02:17:06.059 --> 02:17:07.019
He tried to say.

02:17:07.079 --> 02:17:09.360
But apparently words were too hard.

02:17:09.420 --> 02:17:11.100
Really?

02:17:11.159 --> 02:17:13.979
It was just unreasonable to expect entire

02:17:13.979 --> 02:17:16.319
word sentence groups arranged in order.

02:17:16.379 --> 02:17:20.519
Shh, she said, helping him lie down on

02:17:20.519 --> 02:17:20.879
his back.

02:17:20.940 --> 02:17:24.239
Don't be scared, but there might be a

02:17:24.239 --> 02:17:25.319
toxin in your wristband.

02:17:25.440 --> 02:17:28.860
I read a study about the idea once, but I

02:17:28.860 --> 02:17:30.420
didn't think they'd implemented it yet.

02:17:30.479 --> 02:17:32.340
Did you feel anything?

02:17:32.399 --> 02:17:35.159
Like a needle poking you, kind of?

02:17:35.219 --> 02:17:38.459
I bet they rigged it to inject you if

02:17:38.459 --> 02:17:39.779
they ever couldn't find you.

02:17:39.899 --> 02:17:42.000
Why?

02:17:42.059 --> 02:17:43.979
He mumbled.

02:17:44.040 --> 02:17:46.319
He wanted to ask if it was going to kill

02:17:46.319 --> 02:17:46.620
him.

02:17:46.680 --> 02:17:49.260
He thought he should probably be worried

02:17:49.260 --> 02:17:50.219
if he was about to die.

02:17:50.280 --> 02:17:53.459
But it would be much easier to close his

02:17:53.459 --> 02:17:54.360
eyes, wouldn't it?

02:17:54.420 --> 02:17:56.100
And stop thinking about it.

02:17:56.159 --> 02:17:58.500
It would be much easier to think about

02:17:58.500 --> 02:18:01.620
how sparkly cricket's glasses were, and

02:18:01.620 --> 02:18:04.379
how they made her face all interesting, as

02:18:04.379 --> 02:18:05.940
though there were lots of unexpected

02:18:05.940 --> 02:18:09.000
angles and layers to it, like a prism.

02:18:09.059 --> 02:18:11.159
Prism.

02:18:11.219 --> 02:18:12.839
Words were funny.

02:18:12.959 --> 02:18:15.839
They are hoping you'll flop over

02:18:15.839 --> 02:18:17.339
somewhere and be easy to catch.

02:18:17.399 --> 02:18:20.459
She said, wiggling a folded piece of

02:18:20.459 --> 02:18:22.319
paper between his wristband and his

02:18:22.319 --> 02:18:22.739
scales.

02:18:22.799 --> 02:18:25.559
Joke's on them, though, because you've

02:18:25.559 --> 02:18:26.339
got me to hide you.

02:18:26.459 --> 02:18:29.819
The paper caught on something hidden

02:18:29.819 --> 02:18:32.519
tearing a little gash in his skin, and he

02:18:32.519 --> 02:18:33.839
yelped with startled pain.

02:18:33.899 --> 02:18:35.639
I'm sorry.

02:18:35.700 --> 02:18:39.120
Cricket cupped his face in her talons and

02:18:39.120 --> 02:18:40.319
caught his eyes with hers.

02:18:40.379 --> 02:18:43.559
Like her gaze was amber, and he was safe

02:18:43.559 --> 02:18:44.399
inside of it.

02:18:44.459 --> 02:18:46.259
Don't conk out.

02:18:46.319 --> 02:18:48.659
We might have to go back into the tunnels

02:18:48.659 --> 02:18:49.920
if they start searching the school.

02:18:49.979 --> 02:18:52.260
Can't.

02:18:52.379 --> 02:18:54.359
Move.

02:18:54.420 --> 02:18:55.979
He slurred.

02:18:56.040 --> 02:18:59.399
I'm going to take off your wrist cuff, she

02:18:59.399 --> 02:18:59.700
said.

02:18:59.819 --> 02:19:01.020
Is that all right?

02:19:01.079 --> 02:19:03.120
Blue, can you hear me?

02:19:03.180 --> 02:19:05.879
Blink if that's all right with you.

02:19:05.940 --> 02:19:09.120
No way.

02:19:09.180 --> 02:19:12.299
He managed around his numb tongue.

02:19:12.360 --> 02:19:14.819
I'll be in.

02:19:14.819 --> 02:19:19.440
So much trouble.

02:19:19.559 --> 02:19:22.919
Oh, beautiful dragon.

02:19:22.979 --> 02:19:24.780
She said sympathetically.

02:19:24.840 --> 02:19:27.299
Don't you know how much trouble you're

02:19:27.299 --> 02:19:27.659
already in?

02:19:27.780 --> 02:19:29.879
He closed his eyes.

02:19:29.940 --> 02:19:32.340
Something wet was leaking out of them.

02:19:32.399 --> 02:19:35.219
Apparently, the toxin had affected his

02:19:35.219 --> 02:19:36.000
tear ducts, too.

02:19:36.059 --> 02:19:38.999
Crickets scrambled up and disappeared

02:19:38.999 --> 02:19:39.479
from his side.

02:19:39.540 --> 02:19:42.540
He opened his eyes again, afraid that

02:19:42.540 --> 02:19:43.620
she'd be gone completely.

02:19:43.680 --> 02:19:46.440
But she was only across the library

02:19:46.440 --> 02:19:48.659
carefully unscrewing one of the lamps

02:19:48.659 --> 02:19:51.540
from the wall, with a dust rag wrapped

02:19:51.540 --> 02:19:53.219
around her claws to protect them from the

02:19:53.219 --> 02:19:53.520
heat.

02:19:53.579 --> 02:19:56.760
Soon she had uncovered a small, glowing

02:19:56.760 --> 02:19:58.799
glass ball from inside the globe of the

02:19:58.799 --> 02:19:59.040
lamp.

02:19:59.100 --> 02:20:02.100
It shone bright enough to make Blue's

02:20:02.100 --> 02:20:02.459
eyes hurt.

02:20:02.520 --> 02:20:06.000
She folded the cloth over the ball. and

02:20:06.000 --> 02:20:08.520
carried it to the librarian's desk, where

02:20:08.520 --> 02:20:10.260
she cleared away the books and papers

02:20:10.260 --> 02:20:12.899
then set down a metal plate from a side

02:20:12.899 --> 02:20:13.500
drawer.

02:20:13.559 --> 02:20:15.659
Woom.

02:20:15.780 --> 02:20:17.040
Blue mumbled.

02:20:17.159 --> 02:20:20.520
Don't worry, I've done this before, she

02:20:20.520 --> 02:20:21.000
said.

02:20:21.059 --> 02:20:23.639
I mean, never anywhere quite so.

02:20:23.700 --> 02:20:27.059
Flammable, but I'm sure it'll be fine.

02:20:27.180 --> 02:20:29.879
She dug through the rest of the drawers

02:20:29.879 --> 02:20:31.440
until she found something that looked

02:20:31.440 --> 02:20:33.659
like a long, thin pair of tweezers.

02:20:33.719 --> 02:20:36.239
Blue had seen tools like that before.

02:20:36.360 --> 02:20:39.299
He'd even used them a few times, to

02:20:39.299 --> 02:20:41.700
untangle particularly messy snarls of

02:20:41.700 --> 02:20:41.940
silk.

02:20:42.059 --> 02:20:45.540
Cricket took a deep breath, unwrapped the

02:20:45.540 --> 02:20:47.879
ball, and caught it between the tweezers

02:20:47.879 --> 02:20:49.739
setting it down on the metal plate.

02:20:49.860 --> 02:20:53.459
She threw the rag into a far corner, still

02:20:53.459 --> 02:20:55.920
holding the ball steady, and then picked

02:20:55.920 --> 02:20:58.079
up a marble paperweight shaped like a

02:20:58.079 --> 02:20:59.579
coiled python.

02:20:59.639 --> 02:21:03.420
She moved so confidently and efficiently

02:21:03.420 --> 02:21:05.040
that it didn't occur to Blue to be afraid

02:21:05.040 --> 02:21:08.280
until the last moment, when she looked up

02:21:08.280 --> 02:21:11.219
at the ceiling and whispered, Please help

02:21:11.219 --> 02:21:13.079
me not set the library on fire, clear

02:21:13.079 --> 02:21:13.559
sight.

02:21:13.620 --> 02:21:16.319
He couldn't have stopped her anyway.

02:21:16.379 --> 02:21:18.959
As she brought the pale grace snake

02:21:18.959 --> 02:21:20.639
smashing down on the light ball.

02:21:20.700 --> 02:21:24.780
Glass splintered across the desk, and a

02:21:24.780 --> 02:21:27.000
powerful burnt metal smell filled the

02:21:27.000 --> 02:21:27.180
air.

02:21:27.239 --> 02:21:29.579
But cricket pounced forward with the

02:21:29.579 --> 02:21:31.440
tweezers and lifted something up.

02:21:31.500 --> 02:21:35.340
It looked like a filament of silk, as

02:21:35.340 --> 02:21:38.399
long as one of Blue's claws, but a light

02:21:38.399 --> 02:21:40.020
with fire from end to end.

02:21:40.079 --> 02:21:44.219
That was the source of light in all the

02:21:44.219 --> 02:21:45.360
lamps in the hive.

02:21:45.420 --> 02:21:47.040
Flame silk.

02:21:47.159 --> 02:21:49.620
How had he never known that before?

02:21:49.680 --> 02:21:52.739
He'd never even wondered how the lamps

02:21:52.739 --> 02:21:53.459
worked.

02:21:53.520 --> 02:21:55.979
He'd assumed it was a hive wing skill.

02:21:56.040 --> 02:21:58.860
If he'd had to guess, he would have

02:21:58.860 --> 02:22:01.020
imagined that perhaps some of them could

02:22:01.020 --> 02:22:03.780
create fire, like the dragons from the

02:22:03.780 --> 02:22:05.760
old stories he'd once lived across the

02:22:05.760 --> 02:22:06.000
sea.

02:22:06.059 --> 02:22:08.700
Scarcely breathing.

02:22:08.760 --> 02:22:10.979
Cricket eased across the room toward him

02:22:10.979 --> 02:22:13.620
holding the flame silk thread in the

02:22:13.620 --> 02:22:14.159
tweezers.

02:22:14.219 --> 02:22:18.059
Could she really set the whole library on

02:22:18.059 --> 02:22:18.479
fire?

02:22:18.600 --> 02:22:20.219
With that little thing?

02:22:20.280 --> 02:22:21.360
He wondered.

02:22:21.479 --> 02:22:22.620
If so.

02:22:22.799 --> 02:22:25.860
She's taking a big risk for me.

02:22:25.920 --> 02:22:30.479
She crouched beside him, and lifted his

02:22:30.479 --> 02:22:32.520
left arm gently in her free claws.

02:22:32.579 --> 02:22:34.500
Don't move.

02:22:34.620 --> 02:22:35.879
She said.

02:22:35.940 --> 02:22:39.059
I mean, I know you can't, but really

02:22:39.059 --> 02:22:39.600
don't.

02:22:39.659 --> 02:22:42.360
With infinite caution.

02:22:42.479 --> 02:22:44.819
She traced the flame silk across his

02:22:44.819 --> 02:22:45.540
wrist cuff.

02:22:45.600 --> 02:22:48.659
It seared a smoking black line in the

02:22:48.659 --> 02:22:51.840
bronze, right across the W in Silkworm

02:22:51.840 --> 02:22:52.200
Hall.

02:22:52.260 --> 02:22:56.579
Hawker is going to kill me, Blue thought

02:22:56.579 --> 02:22:57.239
deliriously.

02:22:57.299 --> 02:23:00.540
When I get to the checkpoint, he's going

02:23:00.540 --> 02:23:03.600
to make that very stern frowny face, and

02:23:03.600 --> 02:23:06.899
tut, tut, and check his list, and grumble

02:23:06.899 --> 02:23:09.600
about paperwork, and then stab me with

02:23:09.600 --> 02:23:10.559
his spear thingy.

02:23:10.620 --> 02:23:14.879
Cricket traced the line again, and then

02:23:14.879 --> 02:23:17.639
again with a flame silk thread, burning

02:23:17.639 --> 02:23:19.200
it a little deeper each time.

02:23:19.260 --> 02:23:22.440
The smell of blacksmiths and melting

02:23:22.440 --> 02:23:25.500
chains filled the room, swamping the

02:23:25.500 --> 02:23:26.459
scent of old paper.

02:23:26.520 --> 02:23:30.180
And then, a few careful passes later.

02:23:30.239 --> 02:23:33.180
The metal gave way and fell off his wrist

02:23:33.180 --> 02:23:36.059
brushing against his scales, and leaving

02:23:36.059 --> 02:23:38.040
a small scorch mark that hurt like a

02:23:38.040 --> 02:23:38.760
viper bite.

02:23:38.819 --> 02:23:41.159
Blue bit back a whimper.

02:23:41.219 --> 02:23:44.340
Oh, shoot, Cricket said.

02:23:44.399 --> 02:23:46.620
She jumped up and ran back to the

02:23:46.620 --> 02:23:49.020
librarian's desk. grabbed a small

02:23:49.020 --> 02:23:51.420
watering can, and poured water from it

02:23:51.420 --> 02:23:52.379
over his burn.

02:23:52.440 --> 02:23:55.200
Then she dropped the flame silk thread

02:23:55.200 --> 02:23:56.879
into the water that was left in the can.

02:23:56.940 --> 02:24:01.020
A sizzling, hissing sound, and a cloud of

02:24:01.020 --> 02:24:02.579
steam billowed out of the top of it.

02:24:02.639 --> 02:24:06.120
Blue's arm felt like it was floating.

02:24:06.180 --> 02:24:09.059
Like maybe it would drift right up to the

02:24:09.059 --> 02:24:11.879
roof and bump around between the books on

02:24:11.879 --> 02:24:12.659
the top shelves.

02:24:12.719 --> 02:24:16.620
He felt untethered from the earth, a

02:24:16.620 --> 02:24:18.360
feeling that was tangled up with how

02:24:18.360 --> 02:24:20.940
close he was to cricket, and how she

02:24:20.940 --> 02:24:22.200
maybe had superpowers.

02:24:22.319 --> 02:24:26.040
Or at least the absolute very best brain

02:24:26.040 --> 02:24:26.940
in the world.

02:24:27.000 --> 02:24:28.559
Cricket laughed.

02:24:28.620 --> 02:24:31.559
I don't know about that, she said.

02:24:31.620 --> 02:24:34.020
And he realized that he must have said

02:24:34.020 --> 02:24:34.799
something out loud.

02:24:34.860 --> 02:24:38.040
My teacher seemed to think my brain is

02:24:38.040 --> 02:24:38.940
terribly annoying.

02:24:39.000 --> 02:24:41.459
I like it.

02:24:41.520 --> 02:24:43.020
Blue said.

02:24:43.079 --> 02:24:46.200
Everything still felt blurry, but his

02:24:46.200 --> 02:24:48.420
mouth was working a little better, or at

02:24:48.420 --> 02:24:50.459
least, words were coming out of it in

02:24:50.459 --> 02:24:50.819
order.

02:24:50.879 --> 02:24:53.700
Even though those words didn't seem to be

02:24:53.700 --> 02:24:55.500
waiting for approval from the rest of

02:24:55.500 --> 02:24:55.739
him.

02:24:55.799 --> 02:24:59.159
He managed to sit up and smile at her.

02:24:59.280 --> 02:25:02.219
It's my new favorite brain.

02:25:02.340 --> 02:25:05.639
And then the world kind of tipped

02:25:05.639 --> 02:25:08.879
sideways and went dark, and Blue slipped

02:25:08.879 --> 02:25:10.020
quietly into the nothing.

02:25:10.079 --> 02:25:14.579
Chapter 8.

02:25:14.700 --> 02:25:17.700
Blue had the impression that he should

02:25:17.700 --> 02:25:18.120
wake up.

02:25:18.180 --> 02:25:21.420
That it might be a good idea, that the

02:25:21.420 --> 02:25:23.760
reason it was a good idea, might have

02:25:23.760 --> 02:25:25.979
something to do with how, wherever he was

02:25:25.979 --> 02:25:28.799
sleeping, wasn't swaying in the breeze

02:25:28.799 --> 02:25:29.879
the way it was supposed to.

02:25:30.000 --> 02:25:33.059
This web hammock he'd fallen asleep in

02:25:33.059 --> 02:25:35.280
was weirdly still and hard underneath

02:25:35.280 --> 02:25:36.059
him.

02:25:36.120 --> 02:25:37.739
And there was someone shaking his

02:25:37.739 --> 02:25:40.559
shoulder, someone whose wings brushed his

02:25:40.559 --> 02:25:41.280
face sometimes.

02:25:41.340 --> 02:25:42.840
Mother?

02:25:42.899 --> 02:25:45.719
Mother never smelled like books and

02:25:45.719 --> 02:25:46.260
apples.

02:25:46.319 --> 02:25:47.760
The way this dragon did.

02:25:47.879 --> 02:25:49.739
Are you awake?

02:25:49.799 --> 02:25:53.459
The dragon whispered, Blue, if you're not

02:25:53.459 --> 02:25:54.719
could you be?

02:25:55.319 --> 02:25:55.559
Please?

02:25:55.620 --> 02:25:56.879
Now, ish?

02:25:56.940 --> 02:26:01.079
Blue said.

02:26:01.139 --> 02:26:04.020
Which was odd. because he'd been trying

02:26:04.020 --> 02:26:09.540
to say, you bet, but apparently, was good

02:26:09.540 --> 02:26:10.799
enough for the dragon with all the

02:26:10.799 --> 02:26:12.899
questions, because she started trying to

02:26:12.899 --> 02:26:14.280
nudge him up to his feet.

02:26:14.459 --> 02:26:17.280
Oh, questions.

02:26:17.399 --> 02:26:18.899
It's cricket.

02:26:18.959 --> 02:26:21.600
What are you smiling about?

02:26:21.659 --> 02:26:23.159
She said curiously.

02:26:23.219 --> 02:26:24.959
I hope that's a good sign.

02:26:25.020 --> 02:26:27.420
Do you think you could smile and stand up

02:26:27.420 --> 02:26:28.079
at the same time?

02:26:28.139 --> 02:26:31.020
I would love to let you sleep more, but I

02:26:31.020 --> 02:26:32.040
think we really need to move.

02:26:32.100 --> 02:26:35.819
She froze for a moment, with him leaning

02:26:35.819 --> 02:26:36.840
heavily against her shoulder.

02:26:36.899 --> 02:26:39.840
Now the library was coming into focus

02:26:39.840 --> 02:26:40.500
around him.

02:26:40.559 --> 02:26:43.860
The glow of the lamps, the rows and rows

02:26:43.860 --> 02:26:46.559
of books, the sound of tramping talons

02:26:46.559 --> 02:26:47.579
from the hallway outside.

02:26:47.639 --> 02:26:50.639
Um, the what?

02:26:50.760 --> 02:26:53.639
He pointed at the door in alarm and she

02:26:53.639 --> 02:26:54.059
nodded.

02:26:54.120 --> 02:26:57.239
That's why I woke you, she whispered.

02:26:57.299 --> 02:26:59.100
Quick, into the tunnels.

02:26:59.159 --> 02:27:01.500
She bundled him under the table and

02:27:01.500 --> 02:27:02.399
through the trap door.

02:27:02.459 --> 02:27:05.520
His arms felt all wobbly, and his tail

02:27:05.520 --> 02:27:07.920
seemed to be entirely in the way, but he

02:27:07.920 --> 02:27:09.719
somehow managed to crawl into the dark

02:27:09.719 --> 02:27:10.500
space beyond.

02:27:10.620 --> 02:27:13.559
He dragged himself forward so Cricket

02:27:13.559 --> 02:27:14.819
could scrunch in behind him.

02:27:14.879 --> 02:27:18.180
The glow from the library lamps vanished

02:27:18.180 --> 02:27:20.459
as cricket pulled the trap door shut.

02:27:20.520 --> 02:27:23.579
Blue started to retreat farther into the

02:27:23.579 --> 02:27:26.340
shadows, but she caught his nearest talon

02:27:26.340 --> 02:27:28.500
and put one claw to her mouth in warning

02:27:28.500 --> 02:27:30.180
Blue froze.

02:27:30.239 --> 02:27:33.000
And in that instant, he heard the library

02:27:33.000 --> 02:27:34.319
door slam open.

02:27:34.379 --> 02:27:38.700
Three sets of talons thundered in, shaking

02:27:38.700 --> 02:27:40.739
the room, so that a couple of books

02:27:40.739 --> 02:27:43.799
toppled off tall shelves, and a small

02:27:43.799 --> 02:27:45.899
cloud of book dust wafted through the

02:27:45.899 --> 02:27:46.979
cracks in the trap door.

02:27:47.040 --> 02:27:49.559
He twisted his neck to peek over

02:27:49.559 --> 02:27:50.639
Cricket's shoulder.

02:27:50.760 --> 02:27:53.100
And the glimpses he could see as they

02:27:53.100 --> 02:27:53.579
moved around.

02:27:53.639 --> 02:27:56.579
The hive wing's eyes were blank white

02:27:56.579 --> 02:27:57.180
pearls.

02:27:57.299 --> 02:28:00.420
So the queen was still mind controlling

02:28:00.420 --> 02:28:00.600
them.

02:28:00.659 --> 02:28:02.940
He wondered how long he'd been

02:28:02.940 --> 02:28:03.540
unconscious.

02:28:03.600 --> 02:28:06.000
He wondered how long she could keep it

02:28:06.000 --> 02:28:06.180
up.

02:28:06.239 --> 02:28:08.760
He wondered if she planned to keep them

02:28:08.760 --> 02:28:12.000
all as her zombies until she found him, no

02:28:12.000 --> 02:28:13.319
matter how long that took.

02:28:13.559 --> 02:28:16.260
And then his heart stopped in his chest

02:28:16.260 --> 02:28:18.899
as he remembered the wrist cuff cricket

02:28:18.899 --> 02:28:19.799
had burned off him.

02:28:19.860 --> 02:28:23.040
He couldn't see it from his angle, but

02:28:23.040 --> 02:28:24.479
wasn't it still lying out there on the

02:28:24.479 --> 02:28:24.780
floor?

02:28:24.840 --> 02:28:27.420
Wouldn't they see it and know immediately

02:28:27.420 --> 02:28:28.260
that he'd been here?

02:28:28.319 --> 02:28:32.700
But several agonizing moments passed, and

02:28:32.700 --> 02:28:35.100
the searching dragons didn't cry out, or

02:28:35.100 --> 02:28:37.799
roar for backup, or hiss in triumph.

02:28:37.860 --> 02:28:41.280
They moved mechanically, soundlessly

02:28:41.280 --> 02:28:43.920
through the room, checking every obvious

02:28:43.920 --> 02:28:44.579
hiding spot.

02:28:44.639 --> 02:28:48.239
One crouched down to look under the table

02:28:48.239 --> 02:28:51.239
and Blue closed his eyes in fright, not

02:28:51.239 --> 02:28:52.079
daring to breathe.

02:28:52.200 --> 02:28:54.899
But the trap door must have looked like

02:28:54.899 --> 02:28:57.299
part of the wall, because the hive wing

02:28:57.299 --> 02:29:00.600
jet black, with flecks of red along his

02:29:00.600 --> 02:29:03.840
ears, wings, and claws, only grunted and

02:29:03.840 --> 02:29:04.139
moved on.

02:29:04.260 --> 02:29:08.040
Cricket twitched suddenly, as if startled

02:29:08.040 --> 02:29:11.100
and Blue realized he was leaning against

02:29:11.100 --> 02:29:14.219
her side, their tails entangled, their

02:29:14.219 --> 02:29:15.180
talons touching.

02:29:15.239 --> 02:29:18.840
He had been too terrified to notice, and

02:29:18.840 --> 02:29:20.520
he was afraid that pulling away would

02:29:20.520 --> 02:29:22.620
make a noise the searchers might hear.

02:29:22.680 --> 02:29:25.799
He checked her face, or what little of it

02:29:25.799 --> 02:29:27.600
he could see in the tiny bars of light.

02:29:27.659 --> 02:29:30.840
She had her gaze fixed on one of the hive

02:29:30.840 --> 02:29:31.319
wings.

02:29:31.379 --> 02:29:34.500
A yellow orange dragon freckled all over

02:29:34.500 --> 02:29:36.780
with black spots, but he couldn't quite

02:29:36.780 --> 02:29:38.040
interpret her expression.

02:29:38.100 --> 02:29:40.260
Dismay, regret.

02:29:40.319 --> 02:29:41.760
Anger?

02:29:41.879 --> 02:29:44.040
What is she feeling?

02:29:44.100 --> 02:29:45.299
He wondered.

02:29:45.360 --> 02:29:48.780
Hiding from her own tribe, in the dark

02:29:48.780 --> 02:29:51.600
with a stranger, risking her queen's

02:29:51.600 --> 02:29:53.040
wrath to help a silk wing.

02:29:53.040 --> 02:29:56.399
He wondered about the hive wings out

02:29:56.399 --> 02:29:57.180
there too.

02:29:57.239 --> 02:30:00.360
Their sweet family evening of slides and

02:30:00.360 --> 02:30:03.239
seesaws and zebra meat snacks had

02:30:03.239 --> 02:30:05.100
abruptly turned into a dragon hunt.

02:30:05.159 --> 02:30:07.440
Everything they'd been planning to do

02:30:07.440 --> 02:30:08.940
tonight had been ripped out from under

02:30:08.940 --> 02:30:09.180
them.

02:30:09.239 --> 02:30:11.940
They didn't even know where their own

02:30:11.940 --> 02:30:13.799
dragonettes were because right now

02:30:13.799 --> 02:30:16.379
finding glue was all they cared about.

02:30:16.440 --> 02:30:19.440
The giggling little dragonettes had gone

02:30:19.440 --> 02:30:22.319
from playing tag, to prowling the shadows

02:30:22.319 --> 02:30:25.020
of the hive with snarling teeth, every

02:30:25.020 --> 02:30:26.219
scale ready to attack.

02:30:26.280 --> 02:30:29.159
How could they all go home after this?

02:30:29.219 --> 02:30:32.340
Back to family dinners, and wing

02:30:32.340 --> 02:30:34.920
aerodynamics homework, knowing that

02:30:34.920 --> 02:30:36.780
someone could take over their minds and

02:30:36.780 --> 02:30:39.059
change their whole lives at any moment.

02:30:39.479 --> 02:30:42.479
The 3 hive wings touched their foreheads

02:30:42.479 --> 02:30:45.659
with one talon, all at the same time, with

02:30:45.659 --> 02:30:47.219
exact mirrored movements.

02:30:47.280 --> 02:30:49.860
Nothing in the library.

02:30:49.920 --> 02:30:51.659
They said in unison.

02:30:51.719 --> 02:30:54.840
A ripple of fury crossed each of their

02:30:54.840 --> 02:30:56.100
faces simultaneously.

02:30:56.159 --> 02:30:59.040
It must be here somewhere.

02:30:59.100 --> 02:31:00.239
Keep looking.

02:31:00.299 --> 02:31:02.879
They marched out the door.

02:31:03.000 --> 02:31:05.520
But Blue could hear their talon steps in

02:31:05.520 --> 02:31:07.500
the corridor for a long time after they

02:31:07.500 --> 02:31:08.159
were out of sight.

02:31:08.280 --> 02:31:11.399
Cricket opened her mouth to say something

02:31:11.399 --> 02:31:13.860
and this time he was the one to shush

02:31:13.860 --> 02:31:14.159
her.

02:31:14.219 --> 02:31:18.420
His antennae unfurled softly. feeling the

02:31:18.420 --> 02:31:19.319
vibrations in the air.

02:31:19.379 --> 02:31:23.760
Now that he was calmer and more awake, he

02:31:23.760 --> 02:31:25.799
could sense at least 20 other dragons

02:31:25.799 --> 02:31:26.520
searching the school.

02:31:26.579 --> 02:31:29.399
He could also feel crickets heart

02:31:29.399 --> 02:31:29.700
beating.

02:31:29.760 --> 02:31:33.360
Very close to his, and almost as fast.

02:31:33.420 --> 02:31:35.579
Don't be scared.

02:31:35.639 --> 02:31:38.159
He tried to think to her.

02:31:38.219 --> 02:31:40.440
There was no reason not to be.

02:31:40.500 --> 02:31:43.440
If they were caught, he was sure she'd be

02:31:43.440 --> 02:31:44.280
in awful trouble.

02:31:44.340 --> 02:31:46.860
But he'd do everything he could to keep

02:31:46.860 --> 02:31:47.399
her out of it.

02:31:47.520 --> 02:31:49.739
He'd let them catch him first.

02:31:49.799 --> 02:31:53.159
He reached out carefully through the dark

02:31:53.159 --> 02:31:55.739
and took one of her talons, pressing it

02:31:55.739 --> 02:31:56.399
to his own heart.

02:31:56.459 --> 02:31:59.639
I'm so glad you're here with me.

02:31:59.700 --> 02:32:02.219
She looked up at him.

02:32:02.280 --> 02:32:04.979
Small cracks of light dappling her face

02:32:04.979 --> 02:32:08.159
in gold and shadow, and he felt her pulse

02:32:08.159 --> 02:32:09.000
jump to match his.

02:32:09.120 --> 02:32:11.579
Oh.

02:32:11.639 --> 02:32:14.399
This is the thing that's forbidden.

02:32:14.459 --> 02:32:17.459
Blue realized, this feeling.

02:32:17.520 --> 02:32:20.040
Looking at a hive wing like this.

02:32:20.100 --> 02:32:22.200
Her looking back.

02:32:22.260 --> 02:32:25.319
If they could be in more trouble than

02:32:25.319 --> 02:32:27.479
they already were, This was how.

02:32:27.600 --> 02:32:30.479
But maybe that wasn't what she was

02:32:30.479 --> 02:32:30.840
feeling.

02:32:30.899 --> 02:32:34.620
Maybe he was still woozy from the toxin

02:32:34.620 --> 02:32:36.540
and confused by his life being upended.

02:32:36.600 --> 02:32:39.600
Maybe he was just imagining the flutter

02:32:39.600 --> 02:32:40.860
in their twining heartbeats.

02:32:40.979 --> 02:32:44.940
His antennae twitched quietly, following

02:32:44.940 --> 02:32:47.280
the vibrations of the dragons moving away

02:32:47.280 --> 02:32:48.540
from this section of the school.

02:32:48.600 --> 02:32:52.500
I think they've all gone upstairs, he

02:32:52.500 --> 02:32:52.979
whispered.

02:32:53.040 --> 02:32:54.840
Is there an upstairs?

02:32:54.899 --> 02:32:56.760
Yes.

02:32:56.819 --> 02:32:58.500
How can you tell where they are?

02:32:58.559 --> 02:33:00.059
She whispered back.

02:33:00.120 --> 02:33:01.799
Your antennae?

02:33:01.860 --> 02:33:03.120
He nodded.

02:33:03.180 --> 02:33:06.780
I found some old biology books that said

02:33:06.780 --> 02:33:09.780
hive wings used to have antennae too, she

02:33:09.780 --> 02:33:10.440
said softly.

02:33:10.500 --> 02:33:13.379
But when I asked my science teacher about

02:33:13.379 --> 02:33:16.440
it, he said not to be impertinent, and

02:33:16.440 --> 02:33:17.819
then the books disappeared from the

02:33:17.819 --> 02:33:18.360
library.

02:33:18.479 --> 02:33:20.040
She sighed.

02:33:20.100 --> 02:33:22.559
Everything interesting is off limits.

02:33:22.680 --> 02:33:25.260
Why can't we study our own evolution?

02:33:25.379 --> 02:33:27.959
Don't you want to know what the tribes

02:33:27.959 --> 02:33:31.020
were like 2000 years ago when Clearsight

02:33:31.020 --> 02:33:31.379
arrived?

02:33:31.440 --> 02:33:35.280
I never thought about it, he admitted.

02:33:35.340 --> 02:33:36.959
But she was right.

02:33:37.020 --> 02:33:39.780
If hive wings were all descendants of

02:33:39.780 --> 02:33:40.379
Clearsight.

02:33:40.440 --> 02:33:42.899
What had they been like before she came

02:33:42.899 --> 02:33:43.860
to Pantala?

02:33:43.920 --> 02:33:48.000
They stayed there, quietly, in the dark

02:33:48.000 --> 02:33:50.819
with their talons and tails entwined.

02:33:50.819 --> 02:33:53.579
For a long time, the sounds of the search

02:33:53.579 --> 02:33:57.000
tramped above them, around them, in and

02:33:57.000 --> 02:33:59.639
out, and along the halls, and every room

02:33:59.639 --> 02:34:00.780
of the enormous school.

02:34:00.840 --> 02:34:03.840
Blue felt the jarring thumps of tables

02:34:03.840 --> 02:34:06.719
being overturned, the rattling clatter of

02:34:06.719 --> 02:34:09.299
closets being emptied, all their contents

02:34:09.299 --> 02:34:11.040
clawed out and thrown on the floor.

02:34:11.100 --> 02:34:14.459
He felt tremendously sorry for whoever

02:34:14.459 --> 02:34:15.719
had to clean up all this tomorrow.

02:34:15.780 --> 02:34:19.260
He guessed Queen Wasp wouldn't helpfully

02:34:19.260 --> 02:34:20.760
brainwash them into doing that.

02:34:20.879 --> 02:34:24.840
At last all the vibrations faded, and

02:34:24.840 --> 02:34:27.180
Blue tested the air until he was sure the

02:34:27.180 --> 02:34:27.959
school was empty again.

02:34:28.020 --> 02:34:31.620
They're all gone, he whispered.

02:34:31.680 --> 02:34:35.399
That's a pretty cool superpower, she

02:34:35.399 --> 02:34:35.700
said.

02:34:35.760 --> 02:34:38.520
Smiling at his antennae as they curled

02:34:38.520 --> 02:34:38.879
back in.

02:34:38.940 --> 02:34:42.059
Not quite as cool as knowing everything

02:34:42.059 --> 02:34:43.979
about everything, he said.

02:34:44.040 --> 02:34:46.020
She blanked.

02:34:46.079 --> 02:34:47.700
Are you talking about me?

02:34:47.760 --> 02:34:49.620
I hardly know anything.

02:34:49.680 --> 02:34:51.780
There's so much, I don't know.

02:34:51.840 --> 02:34:53.639
I mean, yet.

02:34:53.700 --> 02:34:54.959
One day I will.

02:34:55.020 --> 02:34:55.739
I hope.

02:34:55.799 --> 02:34:57.059
I'm working on it.

02:34:57.120 --> 02:35:00.360
She wrinkled her snout, as though the

02:35:00.360 --> 02:35:02.520
existence of unanswered questions was one

02:35:02.520 --> 02:35:04.440
of the greatest trials of her life.

02:35:04.500 --> 02:35:08.219
Like, how Queen Wasps mind control

02:35:08.219 --> 02:35:08.520
works?

02:35:08.639 --> 02:35:10.319
I really want to know that.

02:35:10.379 --> 02:35:13.260
Do you wish?

02:35:13.379 --> 02:35:16.620
He hesitated, then plunged into his

02:35:16.620 --> 02:35:16.860
question.

02:35:16.920 --> 02:35:19.920
Do you wish you were like the other hive

02:35:19.920 --> 02:35:20.280
wings?

02:35:20.340 --> 02:35:24.059
If you could make yourself, um, mind

02:35:24.059 --> 02:35:24.899
controllable.

02:35:24.959 --> 02:35:26.040
Would you?

02:35:26.100 --> 02:35:29.040
No, she said.

02:35:29.100 --> 02:35:31.739
Her wings brushing his sides as they

02:35:31.739 --> 02:35:33.360
flared out and hit the walls of the

02:35:33.360 --> 02:35:33.719
tunnel.

02:35:33.840 --> 02:35:35.219
Would you?

02:35:35.280 --> 02:35:36.239
Who would?

02:35:36.299 --> 02:35:37.379
No.

02:35:37.500 --> 02:35:40.860
I'd fix it so it didn't work on anyone if

02:35:40.860 --> 02:35:41.280
I could.

02:35:41.340 --> 02:35:43.799
That's what you would do too, isn't it?

02:35:43.860 --> 02:35:45.840
At the very least.

02:35:45.899 --> 02:35:47.459
I'd fix Katy did.

02:35:47.520 --> 02:35:50.520
Oh, he said.

02:35:50.579 --> 02:35:52.200
Was that your sister?

02:35:52.319 --> 02:35:54.780
The yellow one with the black spots you

02:35:54.780 --> 02:35:55.139
were watching.

02:35:55.260 --> 02:35:57.120
She exhaled.

02:35:57.180 --> 02:35:58.620
Yes.

02:35:58.680 --> 02:36:01.379
She is my sister and my best friend.

02:36:01.440 --> 02:36:06.000
She normally looks much Kinder. than

02:36:06.000 --> 02:36:06.299
that.

02:36:06.360 --> 02:36:09.180
It must be awful.

02:36:09.239 --> 02:36:11.940
Blue said, studying her face.

02:36:12.000 --> 02:36:15.959
Seeing someone you love transformed, like

02:36:15.959 --> 02:36:17.760
her brain and soul were stolen.

02:36:17.819 --> 02:36:20.700
She looks like her, but she's not.

02:36:20.760 --> 02:36:23.639
And you don't know what she might do, or

02:36:23.639 --> 02:36:25.920
how she might treat you, but you know you

02:36:25.920 --> 02:36:26.579
can't reach her.

02:36:26.700 --> 02:36:29.639
Cricket tilted her head at him.

02:36:29.700 --> 02:36:31.739
That's right.

02:36:31.799 --> 02:36:32.940
She said.

02:36:33.000 --> 02:36:34.739
That's exactly what it's like.

02:36:34.860 --> 02:36:38.280
Katy did says it's fine and she doesn't

02:36:38.280 --> 02:36:40.500
mind, since it happens so rarely.

02:36:40.559 --> 02:36:44.280
But she can't see herself all creepy

02:36:44.280 --> 02:36:44.639
eyed.

02:36:44.700 --> 02:36:47.399
She doesn't know what it feels like for

02:36:47.399 --> 02:36:48.600
me to have to hide from her.

02:36:48.659 --> 02:36:52.680
She shivered slightly, and Blue realized

02:36:52.680 --> 02:36:54.120
he was still holding her talon.

02:36:54.180 --> 02:36:56.399
He let go of it reluctantly.

02:36:56.459 --> 02:37:00.479
I hope you do find a way to save her, he

02:37:00.479 --> 02:37:00.780
said.

02:37:00.840 --> 02:37:02.340
And all of them.

02:37:02.399 --> 02:37:06.120
I know the grunting one who checked under

02:37:06.120 --> 02:37:06.719
the table too.

02:37:06.780 --> 02:37:09.959
Cricket said quickly, as though she was

02:37:09.959 --> 02:37:11.639
trying to change the subject so she

02:37:11.639 --> 02:37:12.059
wouldn't cry.

02:37:12.180 --> 02:37:14.700
His name's bomb the deer.

02:37:14.760 --> 02:37:15.780
But he's awful.

02:37:15.899 --> 02:37:17.639
So there's not much difference between

02:37:17.639 --> 02:37:20.040
regular him and brain dead him.

02:37:20.100 --> 02:37:23.579
He thinks I'm in love with him, if you've

02:37:23.579 --> 02:37:25.260
ever wondered what the most enormous

02:37:25.260 --> 02:37:26.520
arrogance looks like.

02:37:26.579 --> 02:37:30.299
I guess I'd still save him, but maybe

02:37:30.299 --> 02:37:31.620
like, last.

02:37:31.680 --> 02:37:34.860
Why didn't they see my wrist cuff?

02:37:34.979 --> 02:37:38.280
Blue asked, or the broken glass, and the

02:37:38.280 --> 02:37:39.959
flame silk thread in the watering can?

02:37:40.020 --> 02:37:43.440
I cleaned it all up, of course, she

02:37:43.440 --> 02:37:43.739
said.

02:37:43.799 --> 02:37:46.020
You didn't notice, and between your

02:37:46.020 --> 02:37:46.500
snores?

02:37:46.620 --> 02:37:48.360
I wasn't.

02:37:48.420 --> 02:37:49.680
Did I?

02:37:49.739 --> 02:37:50.940
I didn't.

02:37:51.000 --> 02:37:51.719
Did I?

02:37:51.780 --> 02:37:53.520
Cricket laughed.

02:37:53.579 --> 02:37:55.979
No, you're a very polite sleeper.

02:37:56.040 --> 02:37:56.700
Don't worry.

02:37:56.760 --> 02:37:59.280
She glanced out of the library again.

02:37:59.340 --> 02:38:02.219
The only thing I couldn't do was replace

02:38:02.219 --> 02:38:03.420
the missing light globe.

02:38:03.540 --> 02:38:06.120
But those burn out or get stolen all the

02:38:06.120 --> 02:38:08.700
time, so hopefully no one will connect it

02:38:08.700 --> 02:38:08.879
to you.

02:38:08.940 --> 02:38:13.920
So every white globe in the hive has a

02:38:13.920 --> 02:38:15.719
bit of flame silk inside it.

02:38:15.780 --> 02:38:17.579
He said tentatively.

02:38:17.639 --> 02:38:20.219
Of course, she said.

02:38:20.280 --> 02:38:23.100
Every light globe in every hive.

02:38:23.159 --> 02:38:25.620
It would be tough to live the way we do

02:38:25.620 --> 02:38:26.819
without flame silk.

02:38:26.879 --> 02:38:29.280
We'd all be bumping around in the dark

02:38:29.280 --> 02:38:31.139
treading on everyone's claws.

02:38:31.200 --> 02:38:33.420
Plus, we need it for everything else

02:38:33.420 --> 02:38:34.500
that's made with fire.

02:38:34.559 --> 02:38:36.840
Metalwork, glass.

02:38:36.959 --> 02:38:39.840
She touched her spectacles self

02:38:39.000 --> 02:38:39.840
consciously.

02:38:39.899 --> 02:38:43.860
Do all the hive wings know about flame

02:38:43.860 --> 02:38:44.459
silks?

02:38:44.459 --> 02:38:45.239
he asked.

02:38:45.360 --> 02:38:47.459
Because I'd never heard of them until

02:38:47.459 --> 02:38:47.819
today.

02:38:47.879 --> 02:38:52.200
I think they know the queen has a source

02:38:52.200 --> 02:38:53.399
of flame silk.

02:38:53.520 --> 02:38:55.200
She said thoughtfully.

02:38:55.260 --> 02:38:57.780
But most of them probably don't think

02:38:57.780 --> 02:38:59.399
about where it comes from very much.

02:38:59.459 --> 02:39:02.280
It's just something you order when you

02:39:02.280 --> 02:39:02.639
need it.

02:39:02.700 --> 02:39:06.360
Blue opened and closed his mouth on his

02:39:06.360 --> 02:39:06.840
next question.

02:39:06.959 --> 02:39:10.500
He remembered the eerie golden lava

02:39:10.500 --> 02:39:13.260
erupting from Luna's wrists and weaving

02:39:13.260 --> 02:39:14.159
around her scales.

02:39:14.219 --> 02:39:19.319
Her silk was a, A commodity to the hive

02:39:19.319 --> 02:39:22.200
wings, something to be ordered, and

02:39:22.200 --> 02:39:23.940
bought, and sold and used.

02:39:24.000 --> 02:39:28.860
If your sister's a flame silk, Cricket

02:39:28.860 --> 02:39:30.540
said, reaching for his wrist.

02:39:30.600 --> 02:39:33.360
Does that mean you're going to be a flame

02:39:33.360 --> 02:39:33.899
silk too?

02:39:33.959 --> 02:39:37.500
She traced one claw over the spot where

02:39:37.500 --> 02:39:39.420
his silk would come out, and he

02:39:39.420 --> 02:39:39.840
shivered.

02:39:39.899 --> 02:39:42.840
I don't know, he said.

02:39:42.899 --> 02:39:46.440
I who said I would be, but we weren't

02:39:46.440 --> 02:39:48.540
taught anything about flame silks at

02:39:48.540 --> 02:39:49.139
Silkworm Hall.

02:39:49.200 --> 02:39:52.139
But that must be why they're chasing you

02:39:52.139 --> 02:39:53.280
right, she said.

02:39:53.340 --> 02:39:56.340
Queen Wasp would never let a flame soak

02:39:56.340 --> 02:39:58.139
wander around her hives unguarded.

02:39:58.200 --> 02:40:02.399
I've never been guarded before, he said.

02:40:02.459 --> 02:40:04.139
I've never done anything wrong.

02:40:04.200 --> 02:40:06.840
I'm really good at following the rules.

02:40:06.959 --> 02:40:09.239
She doesn't have to worry about me.

02:40:09.299 --> 02:40:11.399
He frowned.

02:40:11.459 --> 02:40:13.739
Touching the spot on his forehead that

02:40:13.739 --> 02:40:14.520
was starting to hurt.

02:40:14.579 --> 02:40:17.340
Maybe she just doesn't know that.

02:40:17.459 --> 02:40:20.399
Maybe I could go to her and explain that

02:40:20.399 --> 02:40:21.719
I'm a loyal silk wing.

02:40:21.780 --> 02:40:24.239
Maybe if I promise I'll be careful.

02:40:24.299 --> 02:40:26.459
She'll let me go back to my normal life.

02:40:26.520 --> 02:40:28.260
And Luna too.

02:40:28.319 --> 02:40:30.299
Luna isn't dangerous.

02:40:30.360 --> 02:40:32.520
Cricket hesitated.

02:40:32.579 --> 02:40:34.860
I think...

02:40:34.860 --> 02:40:38.700
I think hive wing policy is that all free

02:40:38.700 --> 02:40:41.940
flame silks are dangerous, no matter what

02:40:41.940 --> 02:40:42.360
they say.

02:40:42.479 --> 02:40:45.840
She unlatched the trap door and crawled

02:40:45.840 --> 02:40:46.680
back into the library.

02:40:46.739 --> 02:40:49.500
Blue followed her as she pulled a book

02:40:49.500 --> 02:40:52.079
off one of the high shelves, fluttering

02:40:52.079 --> 02:40:54.000
her wings a little to lift herself up to

02:40:54.000 --> 02:40:54.780
where she could reach it.

02:40:54.899 --> 02:40:57.899
She flipped through the pages, then

02:40:57.899 --> 02:40:58.860
flitted under his nose.

02:40:58.979 --> 02:41:02.639
Scarlet colors leaped off the page

02:41:02.639 --> 02:41:04.319
assaulting his eyeballs.

02:41:04.379 --> 02:41:08.520
The picture was of a hive on fire, burning

02:41:08.520 --> 02:41:11.100
from top to bottom, with screaming hive

02:41:11.100 --> 02:41:13.079
wing faces dimly visible through the

02:41:13.079 --> 02:41:13.319
smoke.

02:41:13.379 --> 02:41:17.579
At the top, huge dark letters proclaimed

02:41:17.579 --> 02:41:20.760
the consequences of unchained flame

02:41:20.760 --> 02:41:21.180
silks.

02:41:21.239 --> 02:41:24.479
Yikes, he said.

02:41:24.540 --> 02:41:27.299
I guess that's supposed to be you.

02:41:27.360 --> 02:41:30.780
She said, pointing to a silk wing

02:41:30.780 --> 02:41:32.520
standing in the middle of the burning

02:41:32.520 --> 02:41:34.979
hive, with fire pouring out of his

02:41:34.979 --> 02:41:36.059
wrists.

02:41:36.120 --> 02:41:38.459
The illustrated dragon had a gleeful

02:41:38.459 --> 02:41:41.399
unhinged grin on his face as he torched

02:41:41.399 --> 02:41:41.819
the city.

02:41:41.879 --> 02:41:43.979
Blue shuddered.

02:41:44.040 --> 02:41:47.219
I would never, he said.

02:41:47.340 --> 02:41:49.860
Why would anyone ever?

02:41:49.979 --> 02:41:51.719
That's just horrible.

02:41:51.780 --> 02:41:54.959
Cricket tugged the book back over to her

02:41:54.959 --> 02:41:58.260
and turned to the next page, studying the

02:41:58.260 --> 02:41:59.100
words.

02:41:59.159 --> 02:42:01.799
Her eyes darted so quickly across the

02:42:01.799 --> 02:42:04.260
text that Blue couldn't believe she was

02:42:04.260 --> 02:42:06.840
actually absorbing any of it until she

02:42:06.840 --> 02:42:09.120
said, okay, here.

02:42:09.180 --> 02:42:11.219
Flame silk genetics.

02:42:11.280 --> 02:42:14.159
A dragonette with one flame silk parent

02:42:14.159 --> 02:42:17.340
has a 50% chance of being a flame silk

02:42:17.340 --> 02:42:17.459
2.

02:42:17.639 --> 02:42:22.440
So we know Luna is, but you might, or

02:42:22.440 --> 02:42:23.159
might not be.

02:42:23.280 --> 02:42:26.340
She looked over the top of her glasses at

02:42:26.340 --> 02:42:26.579
him.

02:42:26.639 --> 02:42:28.260
Do you think you are?

02:42:28.319 --> 02:42:30.959
Do your wrists ever feel like they're

02:42:30.959 --> 02:42:31.260
burning?

02:42:31.319 --> 02:42:33.479
What symptoms did Luna have?

02:42:33.540 --> 02:42:36.840
She didn't have any, Blue said.

02:42:36.899 --> 02:42:40.319
I mean, not until today, when her silk

02:42:40.319 --> 02:42:43.079
started coming in all arr, now there's

02:42:43.079 --> 02:42:43.799
lava everywhere.

02:42:43.860 --> 02:42:46.559
She's been totally normal before now.

02:42:46.620 --> 02:42:50.639
So there's no way to know if you are or

02:42:50.639 --> 02:42:54.360
not until your metamorphosis day, Cricket

02:42:54.360 --> 02:42:54.780
said.

02:42:54.840 --> 02:42:56.100
Hmm.

02:42:56.159 --> 02:42:58.260
They must want to keep you locked up

02:42:58.260 --> 02:43:00.899
until then anyway, in case you try to run

02:43:00.899 --> 02:43:01.139
away.

02:43:01.200 --> 02:43:04.920
My friend IO's the one who made me run

02:43:04.920 --> 02:43:05.159
away.

02:43:05.219 --> 02:43:07.680
It wouldn't have occurred to me to run.

02:43:07.739 --> 02:43:11.639
Blue pointed out, at least, not until

02:43:11.639 --> 02:43:12.959
they started chasing me.

02:43:13.020 --> 02:43:16.620
What's the chrysalis?

02:43:16.680 --> 02:43:17.579
Cricket asked.

02:43:17.639 --> 02:43:20.100
The what?

02:43:20.159 --> 02:43:23.159
When we 1st met in the shed.

02:43:23.280 --> 02:43:25.979
You asked if I was with the chrysalis.

02:43:26.100 --> 02:43:29.280
Blue felt a twist of guilt in his chest.

02:43:29.340 --> 02:43:32.100
He was pretty sure that whatever the

02:43:32.100 --> 02:43:34.860
chrysalis was, hive wings weren't

02:43:34.860 --> 02:43:35.760
supposed to know about it.

02:43:35.819 --> 02:43:39.059
Even smart, sympathetic hive wings with

02:43:39.059 --> 02:43:39.899
interesting glasses.

02:43:39.959 --> 02:43:43.799
Io would be furious if she found out he'd

02:43:43.799 --> 02:43:46.139
blurted it out to the 1st dragon he met.

02:43:46.139 --> 02:43:48.959
Cricket was studying him curiously.

02:43:49.020 --> 02:43:50.819
Is it a secret?

02:43:50.879 --> 02:43:51.959
She said.

02:43:52.020 --> 02:43:53.819
A silkwing secret?

02:43:53.879 --> 02:43:56.100
Do you guys have lots of secrets from

02:43:56.100 --> 02:43:56.340
us?

02:43:56.399 --> 02:43:58.319
Can you tell me some of them?

02:43:58.379 --> 02:44:00.000
I promise not to tell anyone.

02:44:00.120 --> 02:44:02.579
There's so much I don't know about silk

02:44:02.579 --> 02:44:05.040
wings, but father won't let me ask the

02:44:05.040 --> 02:44:05.940
servants anything.

02:44:06.000 --> 02:44:08.579
I don't really know what it is.

02:44:08.639 --> 02:44:12.120
He admitted, trying to stem the tide of

02:44:12.120 --> 02:44:12.600
questions.

02:44:12.659 --> 02:44:15.360
My friend just told me they'd help me if

02:44:15.360 --> 02:44:15.959
I could find them.

02:44:16.020 --> 02:44:18.180
But I have no idea how to do that.

02:44:18.239 --> 02:44:21.420
He slid the flame silk book over and

02:44:21.420 --> 02:44:24.000
studied it himself, hoping he hadn't hurt

02:44:24.000 --> 02:44:25.139
cricket's feelings.

02:44:25.200 --> 02:44:30.059
So, if Flame Silk is so useful, then

02:44:30.059 --> 02:44:32.700
Queen Wasp probably isn't killing them

02:44:32.700 --> 02:44:33.180
right?

02:44:33.299 --> 02:44:35.879
Of course she isn't.

02:44:35.940 --> 02:44:38.219
Cricket said, startled.

02:44:38.280 --> 02:44:41.280
We are not barbarians, Blue.

02:44:41.399 --> 02:44:44.399
The queen's a little scary, but she's not

02:44:44.399 --> 02:44:44.879
a murderer.

02:44:44.940 --> 02:44:47.340
Blue would have said the same thing

02:44:47.340 --> 02:44:48.360
himself this morning.

02:44:48.420 --> 02:44:51.299
But something about watching those guards

02:44:51.299 --> 02:44:54.719
surround Luna, and then hiding from white

02:44:53.940 --> 02:44:57.299
eyed mind controlled dragons, was making

02:44:57.299 --> 02:44:58.979
him a little less certain about the

02:44:58.979 --> 02:45:00.120
queen's trustworthiness.

02:45:00.239 --> 02:45:03.780
Do you think I should turn myself in?

02:45:03.840 --> 02:45:06.059
He asked hesitantly.

02:45:06.120 --> 02:45:08.639
That sounded like the right thing to do

02:45:08.639 --> 02:45:12.059
except that it felt very, very wrong.

02:45:12.120 --> 02:45:15.659
Io's warning that he couldn't trust any

02:45:15.659 --> 02:45:17.340
hive wings rang in his ears.

02:45:17.399 --> 02:45:22.139
And here I am, of course, doing exactly

02:45:22.139 --> 02:45:22.680
that.

02:45:22.739 --> 02:45:25.979
Cricket thought for a moment, tapping her

02:45:25.979 --> 02:45:26.819
claws on the book.

02:45:26.879 --> 02:45:31.500
No, she said finally, slowly.

02:45:31.559 --> 02:45:33.899
They won't kill you.

02:45:33.959 --> 02:45:38.579
But if you are a flame silk, they'll, Well

02:45:38.579 --> 02:45:41.579
you'll end up with the other flame silks

02:45:41.579 --> 02:45:41.940
I guess.

02:45:42.000 --> 02:45:43.920
Where is that?

02:45:43.979 --> 02:45:46.799
He said, with a sudden rush of hope.

02:45:46.860 --> 02:45:49.739
That's where Luna will be.

02:45:49.799 --> 02:45:53.879
Oh, I'm sorry I made you look so excited

02:45:53.879 --> 02:45:55.799
Cricket said anxiously.

02:45:55.920 --> 02:45:58.319
Nobody knows where the flame silks are

02:45:58.319 --> 02:45:58.559
kept.

02:45:58.620 --> 02:46:00.479
Are you sure?

02:46:00.540 --> 02:46:03.540
Blue asked. someone must know.

02:46:03.600 --> 02:46:07.799
You're right, she said, leaping to her

02:46:07.799 --> 02:46:08.159
feet.

02:46:08.219 --> 02:46:09.659
Let's think.

02:46:09.719 --> 02:46:12.899
Flame silk orders go out all the time

02:46:12.899 --> 02:46:15.780
because each thread only burns for about

02:46:15.780 --> 02:46:18.120
one cycle of the smallest moon before it

02:46:18.120 --> 02:46:21.420
fades, which means someone has to get the

02:46:21.420 --> 02:46:24.059
flame silk from the dragons producing it

02:46:24.059 --> 02:46:24.840
to fill the orders.

02:46:24.899 --> 02:46:26.459
So whose job is it?

02:46:26.520 --> 02:46:29.280
And someone must keep them fed and taken

02:46:29.280 --> 02:46:29.760
care of.

02:46:29.879 --> 02:46:33.299
And guarded, Blue put in.

02:46:33.360 --> 02:46:34.440
She flinched.

02:46:34.559 --> 02:46:37.020
Yes, probably that too.

02:46:37.079 --> 02:46:39.959
She started pacing up and down between

02:46:39.959 --> 02:46:41.159
the library tables.

02:46:41.219 --> 02:46:44.100
And of course, Queen Wasp knows.

02:46:44.159 --> 02:46:46.680
So there must be a way to trace the flame

02:46:46.680 --> 02:46:48.420
silk back to wherever the dragons are.

02:46:48.540 --> 02:46:51.540
This is definitely a solvable mystery.

02:46:51.600 --> 02:46:55.440
Cricket hurried over to the librarian's

02:46:55.440 --> 02:46:57.180
desk and opened one of the bottom

02:46:57.180 --> 02:46:57.659
drawers.

02:46:57.719 --> 02:47:01.500
All right, forms, where are you?

02:47:01.559 --> 02:47:04.319
She's always complaining about how many

02:47:04.319 --> 02:47:05.399
there are to fill out.

02:47:05.459 --> 02:47:06.899
Order forms?

02:47:06.959 --> 02:47:09.600
Replacing library supplies.

02:47:09.659 --> 02:47:12.540
You would think a librarian would be all

02:47:12.540 --> 02:47:14.760
about alphabetizing her folders, wouldn't

02:47:14.760 --> 02:47:14.940
you?

02:47:15.000 --> 02:47:17.459
Do you think she noticed if I

02:47:17.459 --> 02:47:18.719
alphabetized them for her?

02:47:18.780 --> 02:47:22.020
Oh, light globes, here.

02:47:22.079 --> 02:47:25.139
She pulled out a sheaf of papers and

02:47:25.139 --> 02:47:26.219
narrowed her eyes at them.

02:47:26.280 --> 02:47:29.219
Blue glanced at one of the lamps.

02:47:29.340 --> 02:47:31.620
It was weird to think that there was a

02:47:31.620 --> 02:47:34.260
tiny thread of silk in there, glowing and

02:47:34.260 --> 02:47:34.620
burning.

02:47:34.680 --> 02:47:37.319
It was even weirder to think that the

02:47:37.319 --> 02:47:39.299
thread had come from a dragon very much

02:47:39.299 --> 02:47:39.840
like him.

02:47:39.899 --> 02:47:41.459
Or Luna.

02:47:41.520 --> 02:47:44.940
A dragon trapped somewhere, spilling

02:47:44.940 --> 02:47:47.100
flame from her arms for hive wings to

02:47:47.100 --> 02:47:49.319
gather and snip into little useful bits

02:47:49.319 --> 02:47:52.079
that could be packaged and sold across

02:47:52.079 --> 02:47:52.739
the continent.

02:47:52.799 --> 02:47:56.219
A dragon whose whole life would be about

02:47:56.219 --> 02:47:59.159
producing flame silk for hive wings, and

02:47:59.159 --> 02:48:00.059
nothing else.

02:48:00.120 --> 02:48:03.180
Maybe it came from my father.

02:48:03.239 --> 02:48:06.360
The thought dazed him for a moment.

02:48:06.420 --> 02:48:10.440
His father was a flame silk, kept under

02:48:10.440 --> 02:48:12.420
guard wherever other flame silks were

02:48:12.420 --> 02:48:12.659
kept.

02:48:12.719 --> 02:48:15.479
That's why Blue had never met him.

02:48:15.540 --> 02:48:17.879
He'd only been brought out for a moment

02:48:17.879 --> 02:48:19.620
to father more dragons.

02:48:19.680 --> 02:48:23.340
In the hopes of creating more flame silks

02:48:23.340 --> 02:48:24.299
Blue guessed.

02:48:24.360 --> 02:48:28.020
Which meant Queen Wasp knew exactly what

02:48:28.020 --> 02:48:29.639
Luna and Blue might become.

02:48:29.760 --> 02:48:33.600
She'd created them on purpose for that

02:48:33.600 --> 02:48:34.440
purpose.

02:48:34.680 --> 02:48:36.059
Hmm.

02:48:36.120 --> 02:48:37.799
Cricket said.

02:48:37.860 --> 02:48:41.280
It looks like the order forms get sent to

02:48:41.280 --> 02:48:43.079
a department in Wasp Hive.

02:48:43.139 --> 02:48:45.479
So maybe the flame silks are there.

02:48:45.540 --> 02:48:48.000
Or maybe that department forwards it on.

02:48:48.120 --> 02:48:52.200
If we can figure out where they are, Blue

02:48:52.200 --> 02:48:52.620
said.

02:48:52.680 --> 02:48:54.840
Maybe I could go see what it's like.

02:48:54.899 --> 02:48:57.059
Maybe it's not so terrible.

02:48:57.120 --> 02:49:00.059
Maybe that would help me decide whether I

02:49:00.059 --> 02:49:01.500
should turn myself in.

02:49:01.559 --> 02:49:04.139
Cricket tipped her head up at him.

02:49:04.200 --> 02:49:07.739
And if it is terrible, she asked.

02:49:07.799 --> 02:49:10.440
Would you want to rescue your sister?

02:49:10.500 --> 02:49:16.079
I. Yes, he admitted.

02:49:16.139 --> 02:49:18.479
Of course, that was what he was really

02:49:18.479 --> 02:49:21.000
thinking, and of course, cricket had

02:49:21.000 --> 02:49:21.600
figured that out.

02:49:21.659 --> 02:49:24.959
But I'm not exactly the right dragon for

02:49:24.959 --> 02:49:25.260
that job.

02:49:25.319 --> 02:49:27.120
Why not?

02:49:27.180 --> 02:49:32.219
Well, I mean, he waved vaguely at

02:49:32.219 --> 02:49:32.520
himself.

02:49:32.579 --> 02:49:34.319
I'm not very.

02:49:35.100 --> 02:49:37.379
I don't like making trouble.

02:49:37.440 --> 02:49:39.780
Troublemakers.

02:49:39.840 --> 02:49:43.139
I need sword tail, he blurted.

02:49:43.200 --> 02:49:44.879
He's the one who should rescue her.

02:49:44.940 --> 02:49:46.860
All right.

02:49:46.920 --> 02:49:49.620
Cricket said, whisking the forms back

02:49:49.620 --> 02:49:50.280
into the drawer.

02:49:50.340 --> 02:49:52.379
She smiled brightly a blue.

02:49:52.440 --> 02:49:54.299
Then let's go get him.

02:49:54.360 --> 02:49:58.680
Chapter 9.

02:49:58.739 --> 02:50:01.500
It's not that simple.

02:50:01.559 --> 02:50:02.940
Blue argued.

02:50:03.000 --> 02:50:05.040
Following cricket into the dim hallway

02:50:05.040 --> 02:50:06.299
beyond the library.

02:50:06.360 --> 02:50:09.360
Swartail attacked a bunch of hive wing

02:50:09.360 --> 02:50:09.719
guards.

02:50:09.780 --> 02:50:12.780
He's either on misbehavior's way, or

02:50:12.780 --> 02:50:14.040
somewhere worse by now.

02:50:14.100 --> 02:50:16.739
And I can't exactly stroll around the

02:50:16.739 --> 02:50:18.360
hive with everyone looking for me.

02:50:18.420 --> 02:50:21.540
I bet I can solve that problem.

02:50:21.600 --> 02:50:22.620
Cricket said.

02:50:22.680 --> 02:50:23.700
Let's think.

02:50:23.760 --> 02:50:25.200
Both problems maybe?

02:50:25.260 --> 02:50:26.639
Will you let me try?

02:50:26.700 --> 02:50:29.399
Um, sure.

02:50:29.459 --> 02:50:32.340
Blue said, distracted by the school

02:50:32.340 --> 02:50:33.000
around him.

02:50:33.059 --> 02:50:35.940
Rows of cubby holes lined the corridor.

02:50:36.000 --> 02:50:38.399
Many of them overflowing with crumpled

02:50:38.399 --> 02:50:41.760
papers, books, sticky bags of half eaten

02:50:41.760 --> 02:50:44.579
nectar snacks, seed packets, and little

02:50:44.579 --> 02:50:45.360
buckets of dirt.

02:50:45.479 --> 02:50:47.940
Every few steps, there was a glass

02:50:47.940 --> 02:50:50.399
terrarium embedded in the wall, with

02:50:50.399 --> 02:50:53.520
something growing in it, tidy clusters of

02:50:53.520 --> 02:50:56.399
blue forget me nots in one, long white

02:50:56.399 --> 02:50:59.520
carrots in another, prickly cactus balls

02:50:59.520 --> 02:51:01.319
bristling in an orderly row from a

02:51:01.319 --> 02:51:01.559
third.

02:51:01.680 --> 02:51:03.540
Whoa.

02:51:03.600 --> 02:51:04.860
Blue said.

02:51:04.920 --> 02:51:08.219
It's so Planty in here.

02:51:08.280 --> 02:51:11.399
We're an agriculture track school.

02:51:11.459 --> 02:51:13.260
Do Silk Wings have those?

02:51:13.319 --> 02:51:15.059
Cricket said.

02:51:15.120 --> 02:51:17.700
They passed one glass case that was full

02:51:17.700 --> 02:51:20.399
of water, crowded with dark flaps of

02:51:20.399 --> 02:51:21.299
purple seaweed.

02:51:21.360 --> 02:51:24.659
Blue squinted at it, and realized that it

02:51:24.659 --> 02:51:26.700
was lit by a small light globe on the

02:51:26.700 --> 02:51:27.899
roof of the terrarium.

02:51:27.959 --> 02:51:29.459
They all were.

02:51:29.520 --> 02:51:33.120
Tiny flame silk suns kept these plants

02:51:33.120 --> 02:51:33.600
alive.

02:51:33.719 --> 02:51:37.200
Maybe, Blue said.

02:51:37.260 --> 02:51:39.479
But I think they usually figure out which

02:51:39.479 --> 02:51:41.819
job to assign us after we finish school.

02:51:41.879 --> 02:51:45.180
Our lessons are things like the history

02:51:45.180 --> 02:51:47.940
of the leaf wing war. silk weaving

02:51:47.940 --> 02:51:50.700
reading, web structure, and following

02:51:50.700 --> 02:51:51.299
directions.

02:51:51.360 --> 02:51:53.760
Lots of following directions.

02:51:53.819 --> 02:51:57.120
I wish I could go to your school for a

02:51:57.120 --> 02:51:57.479
day.

02:51:57.540 --> 02:52:00.659
Cricket said, her wings twitching, as

02:52:00.659 --> 02:52:02.159
though she might fly out one of the

02:52:02.159 --> 02:52:03.180
skylights at any moment.

02:52:03.239 --> 02:52:06.600
I'd love to hear what other dragons are

02:52:06.600 --> 02:52:07.440
learning, wouldn't you?

02:52:07.559 --> 02:52:09.420
Are your teachers interesting?

02:52:09.479 --> 02:52:10.860
How big is your library?

02:52:10.920 --> 02:52:12.360
Do you have music classes?

02:52:12.420 --> 02:52:13.739
I wish we did.

02:52:13.799 --> 02:52:16.739
I don't understand music at all, and I

02:52:16.739 --> 02:52:17.520
really want to.

02:52:17.579 --> 02:52:20.520
But our curriculum is very focused so we

02:52:20.520 --> 02:52:22.379
can all become farmers and gardeners.

02:52:22.500 --> 02:52:25.139
That's what this is all about.

02:52:25.200 --> 02:52:28.200
She waved her claws at the corridor

02:52:28.200 --> 02:52:28.620
walls.

02:52:28.680 --> 02:52:31.620
Every student is assigned a terrarium for

02:52:31.620 --> 02:52:32.040
practice.

02:52:32.100 --> 02:52:34.920
Oh, Blue said.

02:52:34.979 --> 02:52:38.760
You don't seem like a farmer to me.

02:52:38.819 --> 02:52:41.520
I'd be an awesome farmer.

02:52:41.579 --> 02:52:45.059
If I wanted to be, she said, which I

02:52:45.059 --> 02:52:45.420
don't.

02:52:45.479 --> 02:52:48.959
I want to be a librarian, or a scientist

02:52:48.959 --> 02:52:50.219
or an inventor.

02:52:50.280 --> 02:52:52.799
But I'm a terrible farming student.

02:52:52.920 --> 02:52:55.860
Apparently there's only one way to do

02:52:55.860 --> 02:52:57.959
things, and that's how it's always been

02:52:57.959 --> 02:53:00.180
done, and there's no point in trying to

02:53:00.180 --> 02:53:02.219
innovate cricket.

02:53:02.280 --> 02:53:04.079
It's a waste of seeds.

02:53:04.139 --> 02:53:07.020
And oh dear, why can't you just grow

02:53:07.020 --> 02:53:08.760
potatoes like a useful dragon?

02:53:08.819 --> 02:53:12.600
She paused at one of the terrariums and

02:53:12.600 --> 02:53:14.040
tapped it lightly with her claw.

02:53:14.100 --> 02:53:15.659
This is mine.

02:53:15.780 --> 02:53:18.780
Blue was pretty sure he could have

02:53:18.780 --> 02:53:19.739
guessed that on his own.

02:53:19.799 --> 02:53:23.100
Unlike the other orderly terrariums.

02:53:23.159 --> 02:53:26.040
This box was a riot of leaves and color.

02:53:26.100 --> 02:53:28.799
As though a host of sunflowers had thrown

02:53:28.799 --> 02:53:31.200
a gala, and some marauding butterflies

02:53:31.200 --> 02:53:31.860
had crashed it.

02:53:31.920 --> 02:53:35.280
Velvety orange petals jostled for space

02:53:35.280 --> 02:53:37.979
with elegant trailing spider plants.

02:53:38.040 --> 02:53:40.559
Sapphire blue bulbs peeked out from

02:53:40.559 --> 02:53:42.959
behind heart shaped leaves with pink

02:53:42.959 --> 02:53:43.500
edges.

02:53:43.559 --> 02:53:48.299
It's like your brain, as a garden, Blue

02:53:48.299 --> 02:53:49.260
said wonderingly.

02:53:49.319 --> 02:53:50.879
Cricket laughed.

02:53:51.000 --> 02:53:54.840
And equally popular with my teachers, she

02:53:54.840 --> 02:53:55.139
said.

02:53:55.260 --> 02:53:56.579
Cricket.

02:53:56.639 --> 02:53:58.200
What a disaster.

02:53:58.260 --> 02:54:02.280
Why didn't you use one type of C like all

02:54:02.280 --> 02:54:03.059
the other students?

02:54:03.120 --> 02:54:07.440
Why must everything you touch be such a

02:54:07.440 --> 02:54:07.739
mess?

02:54:07.799 --> 02:54:11.459
Blue stepped closer and peered through

02:54:11.459 --> 02:54:12.780
the tangle of foliage.

02:54:12.840 --> 02:54:15.540
Deep in the heart of her terrarium.

02:54:15.600 --> 02:54:18.780
Well hidden by the other plants, there

02:54:18.780 --> 02:54:20.219
was a tiny tree.

02:54:20.280 --> 02:54:22.860
It was no taller than the length of 2

02:54:22.860 --> 02:54:26.219
claws, but it had a trunk, and miniature

02:54:26.219 --> 02:54:28.979
branches, and little perfect tufts of

02:54:28.979 --> 02:54:31.739
forest green needles all over it.

02:54:31.799 --> 02:54:32.639
It was beautiful.

02:54:32.700 --> 02:54:36.180
That, he breathed.

02:54:36.239 --> 02:54:39.420
That's a real, how did you?

02:54:39.540 --> 02:54:42.479
I found the seed on one of our gathering

02:54:42.479 --> 02:54:43.379
field trips.

02:54:43.440 --> 02:54:45.659
I had no idea what it was until it

02:54:45.659 --> 02:54:46.260
started to grow.

02:54:46.319 --> 02:54:48.719
She smiled at it wistfully.

02:54:48.780 --> 02:54:51.239
I had a feeling you'd see it.

02:54:51.360 --> 02:54:53.100
Most dragons don't.

02:54:53.159 --> 02:54:55.860
I think my terrarium is too messy to look

02:54:55.860 --> 02:54:56.579
at for very long.

02:54:56.639 --> 02:54:58.920
It offends their eyes or something.

02:54:58.979 --> 02:55:02.219
But my botany teacher finally spotted it

02:55:02.219 --> 02:55:02.639
last week.

02:55:02.700 --> 02:55:05.159
He wants me to uproot it and throw it

02:55:05.159 --> 02:55:05.459
away.

02:55:05.520 --> 02:55:07.079
She sighed.

02:55:07.139 --> 02:55:09.420
Poor little innocent tree.

02:55:09.540 --> 02:55:12.899
She turned and kept walking, and Blue

02:55:12.899 --> 02:55:13.500
followed her.

02:55:13.559 --> 02:55:15.540
Although he wished he could stay and

02:55:15.540 --> 02:55:16.739
stare at the tree a bit longer.

02:55:16.799 --> 02:55:18.600
He couldn't believe it was real.

02:55:18.659 --> 02:55:21.000
Surely Cricket loved it.

02:55:21.059 --> 02:55:23.280
It looked like a loved little tree.

02:55:23.340 --> 02:55:26.700
That's so sad, he said.

02:55:26.819 --> 02:55:29.280
What an awful thing to ask you to do.

02:55:29.340 --> 02:55:30.780
You brought it to life.

02:55:30.840 --> 02:55:35.100
I'm not going to let my tree die, she

02:55:35.100 --> 02:55:35.819
said firmly.

02:55:35.879 --> 02:55:37.559
But where can I hide it?

02:55:37.680 --> 02:55:40.680
Somewhere with light, where I can visit

02:55:40.680 --> 02:55:42.000
but no one will find it.

02:55:42.059 --> 02:55:44.340
I'll figure something out.

02:55:44.399 --> 02:55:47.159
She pushed open a door at the end of the

02:55:47.159 --> 02:55:47.399
hall.

02:55:47.520 --> 02:55:50.819
Revealing a room with long desks covered

02:55:50.819 --> 02:55:52.979
in glass beakers and small pots of soil.

02:55:53.040 --> 02:55:55.559
A metal cabinet at the back of the room

02:55:55.559 --> 02:55:58.620
was lit by a tiny globe inside, and the

02:55:58.620 --> 02:56:00.479
shelves were lined with neatly labeled

02:56:00.479 --> 02:56:02.700
bottles of liquid, organized by color.

02:56:02.760 --> 02:56:06.120
The top shelf ranged from a bright ruby

02:56:06.120 --> 02:56:07.799
red to a pale pink.

02:56:07.860 --> 02:56:10.559
The 2 middle shelves were shades of lemon

02:56:10.559 --> 02:56:13.020
and emerald and lime, and the bottom

02:56:13.020 --> 02:56:16.079
shelf held a few milky white bottles, and

02:56:16.079 --> 02:56:18.120
several with nearly colorless liquids in

02:56:18.120 --> 02:56:18.299
them.

02:56:18.360 --> 02:56:22.020
Blue crouched to look at one of them, and

02:56:22.020 --> 02:56:24.600
realized it was slightly aquamarine when

02:56:24.600 --> 02:56:25.920
the light hit it in a certain way.

02:56:25.979 --> 02:56:29.040
He didn't understand any of the labels

02:56:29.040 --> 02:56:30.180
printed on the bottles.

02:56:30.299 --> 02:56:33.000
There were letters and numbers, and some

02:56:33.000 --> 02:56:35.940
obscure squiggles symbols in between, but

02:56:35.940 --> 02:56:38.459
none of them formed recognizable words.

02:56:38.520 --> 02:56:41.280
This is our chemistry lab.

02:56:41.340 --> 02:56:42.420
Cricket said.

02:56:42.479 --> 02:56:44.459
We use some of these to help plants

02:56:44.459 --> 02:56:44.819
grow.

02:56:44.879 --> 02:56:47.700
Others will kill certain weeds if you

02:56:47.700 --> 02:56:48.600
apply them the right way.

02:56:48.659 --> 02:56:52.500
But a lot of these have other non

02:56:51.059 --> 02:56:52.979
botanical uses too.

02:56:53.100 --> 02:56:55.739
How many do you think I can take without

02:56:55.739 --> 02:56:57.659
Professor Earthworm noticing?

02:56:58.620 --> 02:57:02.399
Take, Blue said, startled, you can't

02:57:02.399 --> 02:57:03.180
steal from your school.

02:57:03.239 --> 02:57:06.360
She paused with a vial, the color of

02:57:06.360 --> 02:57:07.920
chamomile tea in her claws.

02:57:07.979 --> 02:57:11.459
But, Blue, these will help us.

02:57:11.520 --> 02:57:13.260
Don't you want to get your friend?

02:57:13.319 --> 02:57:15.299
Yes, but.

02:57:16.139 --> 02:57:18.659
But stealing is wrong, he stammered.

02:57:18.780 --> 02:57:21.719
He imagined the chemistry teacher coming

02:57:21.719 --> 02:57:23.760
in tomorrow morning and finding bottles

02:57:23.760 --> 02:57:24.540
missing.

02:57:24.600 --> 02:57:25.799
Wouldn't she be upset?

02:57:25.860 --> 02:57:28.260
Wouldn't she feel guilty and worried

02:57:28.260 --> 02:57:30.360
about who had taken them, and what might

02:57:30.360 --> 02:57:31.020
be done with them?

02:57:31.079 --> 02:57:33.180
She might blame her students.

02:57:33.239 --> 02:57:36.059
Someone might get in trouble unfairly.

02:57:36.120 --> 02:57:39.479
You really are good at following the

02:57:39.479 --> 02:57:40.319
rules, aren't you?

02:57:40.379 --> 02:57:42.479
Cricket said, intrigued.

02:57:42.540 --> 02:57:45.780
Like, you really believe in them.

02:57:45.899 --> 02:57:48.000
Don't you?

02:57:48.000 --> 02:57:48.840
he said.

02:57:48.899 --> 02:57:50.340
Doesn't everyone?

02:57:50.399 --> 02:57:52.680
She thought about that for a moment.

02:57:52.799 --> 02:57:56.040
He liked the way she stopped and thought

02:57:56.040 --> 02:57:57.540
carefully about the things he said.

02:57:57.600 --> 02:58:00.360
Most dragons already had their ideas

02:58:00.360 --> 02:58:01.559
settled in their heads.

02:58:01.620 --> 02:58:04.319
If they paused to think before responding

02:58:04.319 --> 02:58:06.780
it was only about how to explain to you

02:58:06.780 --> 02:58:07.319
that you were wrong.

02:58:07.379 --> 02:58:10.200
But cricket seemed to take in information

02:58:10.200 --> 02:58:12.959
and questions, and hold them up against

02:58:12.959 --> 02:58:15.659
the things she thought she knew, to see

02:58:15.659 --> 02:58:17.159
if there was anything new she'd missed.

02:58:17.219 --> 02:58:20.879
Weird, she said finally.

02:58:20.940 --> 02:58:23.700
I usually think of rules as things that

02:58:23.700 --> 02:58:25.379
get in the way of all the stuff I really

02:58:25.379 --> 02:58:26.040
want to know.

02:58:26.100 --> 02:58:31.079
I mean, how can don't ask questions, ever

02:58:31.079 --> 02:58:34.739
be a good rule, or only borrow one book

02:58:34.739 --> 02:58:36.120
at a time from the library.

02:58:36.239 --> 02:58:38.459
That's just ludicrous.

02:58:38.520 --> 02:58:41.399
No one ever explains rules like that in a

02:58:41.399 --> 02:58:41.940
sensible way.

02:58:42.000 --> 02:58:45.420
But don't hurt other dragons.

02:58:45.479 --> 02:58:48.420
That's a rule I think everyone believes

02:58:48.420 --> 02:58:49.319
in. right?

02:58:49.379 --> 02:58:54.420
So, I guess I believe in some rules, and

02:58:54.420 --> 02:58:56.700
I think rules in general can be useful.

02:58:56.760 --> 02:58:59.159
But I also think it's all right to stop

02:58:59.159 --> 02:59:01.620
and question some of the rules sometimes

02:59:01.620 --> 02:59:03.239
if they feel wrong to you.

02:59:03.299 --> 02:59:05.159
Doesn't that make sense?

02:59:05.219 --> 02:59:10.799
But don't steal is a rule everyone agrees

02:59:10.799 --> 02:59:12.420
on too, isn't it?

02:59:12.420 --> 02:59:13.020
he asked.

02:59:13.139 --> 02:59:16.860
I think that help dragons who need help

02:59:16.860 --> 02:59:20.040
might be more important than don't steal

02:59:20.040 --> 02:59:21.360
Cricket said.

02:59:21.420 --> 02:59:25.260
I mean, turn over fugitives to Queen Wasp

02:59:25.260 --> 02:59:27.780
when she is looking for them, is probably

02:59:27.780 --> 02:59:29.100
a rule too, you know?

02:59:29.159 --> 02:59:31.440
But I don't think you're dangerous.

02:59:31.500 --> 02:59:34.079
And I want to know more about flame silks

02:59:34.079 --> 02:59:36.719
and silk wings, and I think I can help

02:59:36.719 --> 02:59:36.899
you.

02:59:36.959 --> 02:59:40.319
I'd, I'd like to help you.

02:59:40.440 --> 02:59:44.520
Blue looked back at the citrus colored

02:59:44.520 --> 02:59:44.940
vials.

02:59:45.059 --> 02:59:47.219
He didn't want to drag her into more

02:59:47.219 --> 02:59:49.799
danger than he'd already put her in, but

02:59:49.799 --> 02:59:50.579
he did need help.

02:59:50.639 --> 02:59:53.760
And more important, Soartail and Luna

02:59:53.760 --> 02:59:54.420
needed help.

02:59:54.479 --> 02:59:58.200
This isn't their 1st rule line breaking

02:59:58.200 --> 02:59:58.920
he thought.

02:59:58.979 --> 03:00:02.700
The 1st rule I broke was running, even

03:00:02.700 --> 03:00:04.200
after the guards told me to stop.

03:00:04.260 --> 03:00:07.979
He still felt shaken all the way through

03:00:07.979 --> 03:00:10.620
his scales at the memory of disobeying

03:00:10.620 --> 03:00:11.639
hive wing orders.

03:00:11.700 --> 03:00:16.260
But if I'm going to rescue Luna, Or, at

03:00:16.260 --> 03:00:18.899
least, get Swordtail to rescue Luna.

03:00:18.959 --> 03:00:23.100
Then this won't be the last rule I break

03:00:23.100 --> 03:00:23.459
either.

03:00:23.520 --> 03:00:26.639
You're right, he said.

03:00:26.700 --> 03:00:31.440
Oh, my goodness, she said, looking

03:00:31.440 --> 03:00:32.760
genuinely startled.

03:00:32.819 --> 03:00:35.579
No one has ever said that to me.

03:00:35.700 --> 03:00:39.719
Then the dragons you know, haven't been

03:00:39.719 --> 03:00:41.579
listening to you very well, he said.

03:00:41.639 --> 03:00:43.559
I bet you're right about almost

03:00:43.559 --> 03:00:44.219
everything.

03:00:44.280 --> 03:00:46.079
Ooh.

03:00:46.139 --> 03:00:49.680
The perfect title for my memoir, she said

03:00:49.680 --> 03:00:50.159
grinning.

03:00:50.219 --> 03:00:52.379
Write about almost everything.

03:00:52.379 --> 03:00:53.639
Bye cricket.

03:00:53.700 --> 03:00:57.299
He laughed, letting her smile chase away

03:00:57.299 --> 03:00:57.899
his nerves.

03:00:57.959 --> 03:01:00.959
She carefully selected 6 vials from the

03:01:00.959 --> 03:01:03.780
back rows, rolled them in a thick black

03:01:03.780 --> 03:01:06.360
cloth, and tucked them into a bag she

03:01:06.360 --> 03:01:08.100
tied sideways across her chest.

03:01:08.159 --> 03:01:10.139
One more stop.

03:01:10.200 --> 03:01:11.219
She said.

03:01:11.280 --> 03:01:13.079
They hurried through the school again.

03:01:13.139 --> 03:01:16.139
Blue unfurled his antennae at each corner

03:01:16.139 --> 03:01:18.420
but he couldn't sense any other dragons

03:01:18.420 --> 03:01:19.379
anywhere in the building.

03:01:19.440 --> 03:01:21.780
The hunt for him had moved on.

03:01:21.840 --> 03:01:25.799
Or maybe paused for the night, he hoped

03:01:25.799 --> 03:01:27.000
without much optimism.

03:01:27.059 --> 03:01:30.299
The next room cricket took him into was

03:01:30.299 --> 03:01:32.340
huge and abutted the side of the hive

03:01:32.340 --> 03:01:34.680
because there was an enormous glass

03:01:34.680 --> 03:01:36.540
window all along one side of it.

03:01:36.600 --> 03:01:40.260
Outside, it was very dark, with only

03:01:40.260 --> 03:01:42.659
fragments of the savannah grass shifting

03:01:42.659 --> 03:01:44.159
silver in bits of moonlight.

03:01:44.219 --> 03:01:47.579
The 3 moons and most of the stars were

03:01:47.579 --> 03:01:49.260
hidden by thick clouds.

03:01:49.260 --> 03:01:51.959
After a few moments of blinking around

03:01:51.959 --> 03:01:54.899
Blue realized this was the art room he

03:01:54.899 --> 03:01:56.700
had glanced briefly through the cracks in

03:01:56.700 --> 03:01:57.360
the tunnels.

03:01:57.420 --> 03:01:59.940
Here was the easel with its perfectly

03:01:59.940 --> 03:02:01.920
perpendicular lines of blue and black.

03:02:01.979 --> 03:02:05.280
In fact, there was an entire row of

03:02:05.280 --> 03:02:07.260
easels with exactly the same painting on

03:02:07.260 --> 03:02:07.620
each one.

03:02:07.680 --> 03:02:10.799
Blue wasn't sure it was a painting.

03:02:10.860 --> 03:02:13.440
It seemed more like a plan for a

03:02:13.440 --> 03:02:14.280
gardening plot.

03:02:14.340 --> 03:02:16.500
In another corner of the room.

03:02:16.559 --> 03:02:19.440
A long table was lined with large sheets

03:02:19.440 --> 03:02:22.139
of paper, each one with a nearly exact

03:02:22.139 --> 03:02:24.180
replica of an orange painted in the

03:02:24.180 --> 03:02:24.360
center.

03:02:24.420 --> 03:02:27.059
The orange that had merited all this

03:02:27.059 --> 03:02:29.879
attention, was still posed nonchalantly

03:02:29.879 --> 03:02:31.559
on a stool in front of the table.

03:02:31.739 --> 03:02:33.420
Blue looked around.

03:02:33.479 --> 03:02:35.940
But none of the artwork looked like

03:02:35.940 --> 03:02:37.739
cricket's glorious terrarium.

03:02:37.799 --> 03:02:39.600
Where's yours?

03:02:39.600 --> 03:02:40.260
he asked.

03:02:40.319 --> 03:02:44.100
Oh, I'm not allowed to take art classes

03:02:44.100 --> 03:02:45.780
anymore, Cricket said.

03:02:45.840 --> 03:02:48.059
With a kind of carelessness, he was

03:02:48.059 --> 03:02:49.319
pretty sure she was faking.

03:02:49.440 --> 03:02:52.680
You can probably guess why.

03:02:52.739 --> 03:02:57.479
Good heavens, cricket, he said, putting

03:02:57.479 --> 03:02:59.399
on the voice she'd used several times

03:02:59.399 --> 03:02:59.879
already.

03:02:59.940 --> 03:03:04.020
No one has ever used that many colors on

03:03:04.020 --> 03:03:05.100
one piece of paper before.

03:03:05.159 --> 03:03:06.959
Look at this mess.

03:03:07.079 --> 03:03:10.200
Why can't you just draw a normal blue

03:03:10.200 --> 03:03:12.000
blueberry like every other dragon?

03:03:12.059 --> 03:03:15.659
She laughed so much, he had to catch her

03:03:15.659 --> 03:03:17.579
before she fell into one of the easels.

03:03:17.639 --> 03:03:19.680
Were you there?

03:03:19.739 --> 03:03:22.739
She gasped, wiping tears from her eyes.

03:03:22.799 --> 03:03:26.340
That's exactly what principal lovers

03:03:26.340 --> 03:03:26.819
sounded like.

03:03:26.879 --> 03:03:30.479
I bet your art was beautiful, he said.

03:03:30.600 --> 03:03:34.260
A beautiful pile of shredded scraps when

03:03:34.260 --> 03:03:36.840
she was done with it, she said with a

03:03:36.840 --> 03:03:37.440
half shrug.

03:03:37.500 --> 03:03:39.840
I had dreams for a while.

03:03:39.899 --> 03:03:42.479
That bee eaters and weaver birds found

03:03:42.479 --> 03:03:45.000
the pieces, and tucked them into their

03:03:45.000 --> 03:03:47.040
nests all across the grasslands.

03:03:47.159 --> 03:03:50.159
She wrestled another cabinet open.

03:03:50.219 --> 03:03:53.340
This time revealing rows of color coded

03:03:53.340 --> 03:03:55.739
paint pots and drawers of the cleanest

03:03:55.739 --> 03:03:58.440
paintbrushes Blue had ever seen, most of

03:03:58.440 --> 03:04:00.180
them as thin as his antennae.

03:04:00.239 --> 03:04:04.559
Um, he said, as she started selecting

03:04:04.559 --> 03:04:05.459
brushes and paint.

03:04:05.520 --> 03:04:08.100
Do I want to know what's happening?

03:04:08.159 --> 03:04:10.860
We are going to disguise you?

03:04:10.920 --> 03:04:12.600
She said with delight.

03:04:12.719 --> 03:04:15.540
What color have you always wanted to be?

03:04:15.600 --> 03:04:18.420
I mean, I think your scales are perfect.

03:04:18.479 --> 03:04:21.299
But like you said, you can't wonder the

03:04:21.299 --> 03:04:23.280
hive looking like yourself, can you?

03:04:23.340 --> 03:04:26.700
That's a purple anyone would spot from

03:04:26.700 --> 03:04:27.659
the next hive over.

03:04:27.719 --> 03:04:30.479
For a moment, I thought it would be so

03:04:30.479 --> 03:04:32.639
cool to disguise you as a hive wing.

03:04:32.700 --> 03:04:35.399
But then I was like, silly cricket.

03:04:35.459 --> 03:04:36.420
That won't work.

03:04:36.479 --> 03:04:38.819
There are no wingless hive wings.

03:04:38.879 --> 03:04:40.200
So what do you think?

03:04:40.260 --> 03:04:41.579
Orange?

03:04:41.639 --> 03:04:43.860
Our cook is mostly orange.

03:04:43.979 --> 03:04:47.459
You're going to paint me?

03:04:47.520 --> 03:04:48.659
Blue said.

03:04:48.719 --> 03:04:52.139
Or you could paint yourself, but I think

03:04:52.139 --> 03:04:54.120
I better do it, unless you're good at

03:04:54.120 --> 03:04:54.299
it.

03:04:54.360 --> 03:04:55.200
Are you?

03:04:55.260 --> 03:04:58.200
I have no idea, he said.

03:04:58.260 --> 03:05:00.360
I've never painted a dragon before.

03:05:00.420 --> 03:05:03.360
Me neither, she confessed.

03:05:03.420 --> 03:05:05.639
But I think it'll work if we use the

03:05:05.639 --> 03:05:06.000
right paint.

03:05:06.059 --> 03:05:07.139
Do you mind?

03:05:07.200 --> 03:05:07.979
Can I try?

03:05:08.040 --> 03:05:10.620
You think?

03:05:10.620 --> 03:05:12.540
He echoed nervously.

03:05:12.600 --> 03:05:15.180
Maybe a darker color.

03:05:15.239 --> 03:05:17.879
To be sure it'll cover yours, she said.

03:05:17.940 --> 03:05:21.120
Are there any sort of darkish silk

03:05:21.120 --> 03:05:21.420
wings?

03:05:21.479 --> 03:05:25.139
Swore tail has mostly dark blue scales

03:05:25.139 --> 03:05:26.159
Blue said.

03:05:26.219 --> 03:05:29.219
I've seen dark greens and reds and all

03:05:29.219 --> 03:05:30.059
shades of brown.

03:05:30.120 --> 03:05:33.299
Cricket pulled out a range of chocolate

03:05:33.299 --> 03:05:34.799
maroon and navy paints.

03:05:34.860 --> 03:05:39.120
All right, she said, herding him onto a

03:05:39.120 --> 03:05:40.500
drop cloth that covered part of the

03:05:40.500 --> 03:05:40.739
floor.

03:05:40.799 --> 03:05:43.739
Stay really still.

03:05:43.799 --> 03:05:46.559
Blue closed his eyes and froze.

03:05:46.620 --> 03:05:50.639
I'm putting myself in her talons, he

03:05:50.639 --> 03:05:50.879
thought.

03:05:50.940 --> 03:05:54.360
I really, really hope she knows what

03:05:54.360 --> 03:05:55.260
she's doing.

03:05:55.319 --> 03:05:58.260
Because if she doesn't, and someone

03:05:58.260 --> 03:06:00.600
recognizes me, and we get caught.

03:06:00.659 --> 03:06:04.200
We're both going to be in worse trouble

03:06:04.200 --> 03:06:05.520
than I can imagine.

03:06:05.579 --> 03:06:09.959
Chapter 10.

03:06:10.200 --> 03:06:13.200
I don't see how this could work.

03:06:13.260 --> 03:06:14.940
Blue protested.

03:06:15.000 --> 03:06:17.520
As cricket dipped a brush and to paint

03:06:17.520 --> 03:06:19.379
the color of the sea during a storm.

03:06:19.440 --> 03:06:22.739
Won't I just look like a silk wing with

03:06:22.739 --> 03:06:23.459
paint all over me?

03:06:23.520 --> 03:06:27.299
Not unless they look closely, and no one

03:06:27.299 --> 03:06:28.559
looks closely at Silk Wings.

03:06:28.620 --> 03:06:31.860
She started dabbing paint lightly across

03:06:31.860 --> 03:06:33.719
the purple scales on his back.

03:06:33.780 --> 03:06:36.719
It felt like salamanders prowling over

03:06:36.719 --> 03:06:40.319
him, tiny wet toes sliding along each

03:06:40.319 --> 03:06:41.520
individual scale.

03:06:41.579 --> 03:06:44.940
It felt like purrs and whispers, and

03:06:44.940 --> 03:06:47.219
ferns full of dewdrops trailing along his

03:06:47.219 --> 03:06:47.579
nerves.

03:06:47.700 --> 03:06:50.879
Cricket switched to a sponge to smooth

03:06:50.879 --> 03:06:53.280
out the paint, then to another brush for

03:06:53.280 --> 03:06:53.760
a different color.

03:06:53.819 --> 03:06:56.879
She hesitated, lightly touching his

03:06:56.879 --> 03:06:57.120
shoulder.

03:06:57.180 --> 03:07:00.959
I'm going to paint around your wing buds

03:07:00.959 --> 03:07:02.819
but I won't touch them, all right?

03:07:02.879 --> 03:07:04.680
He nodded.

03:07:04.739 --> 03:07:07.920
It was hypnotizing, the gentle brushing

03:07:07.920 --> 03:07:09.180
touch sweeping over him.

03:07:09.239 --> 03:07:13.139
He felt half bewitched, as though the

03:07:13.139 --> 03:07:15.299
toxin from his wristband might still be

03:07:15.299 --> 03:07:16.379
running through his veins.

03:07:16.440 --> 03:07:18.239
Cricket.

03:07:18.299 --> 03:07:20.280
Why are you helping me?

03:07:20.340 --> 03:07:21.360
He asked.

03:07:21.420 --> 03:07:25.319
Her talent stilled for a moment, then

03:07:25.319 --> 03:07:25.920
kept going.

03:07:25.979 --> 03:07:28.139
I don't know.

03:07:28.200 --> 03:07:31.020
Maybe because I know what it's like to

03:07:31.020 --> 03:07:33.000
hide while everyone is mind controlled.

03:07:33.120 --> 03:07:36.120
And because I've never met a flame silk

03:07:36.120 --> 03:07:37.799
and I'd love to know more about you.

03:07:37.860 --> 03:07:42.420
And because you're, She paused, struggling

03:07:42.420 --> 03:07:42.959
for a word.

03:07:43.020 --> 03:07:48.120
Pathetic, he offered, desperate, a tragic

03:07:48.120 --> 03:07:48.420
story.

03:07:48.479 --> 03:07:51.120
No, she said.

03:07:51.180 --> 03:07:52.920
Not that at all.

03:07:52.979 --> 03:07:56.159
You're... she trailed off again.

03:07:56.219 --> 03:08:00.959
Ah, ha, he said, devastatingly handsome.

03:08:01.079 --> 03:08:04.079
She laughed and poked his neck with the

03:08:04.079 --> 03:08:05.819
other end of the paintbrush.

03:08:05.879 --> 03:08:06.540
Stop it.

03:08:06.600 --> 03:08:08.639
You mustn't make me laugh while I'm

03:08:08.639 --> 03:08:09.780
wielding paint at you.

03:08:09.840 --> 03:08:12.959
He smelled cinnamon as she leaned in to

03:08:12.959 --> 03:08:13.920
paint around his ears.

03:08:13.979 --> 03:08:19.020
After a moment, she said, I mean, you're

03:08:19.020 --> 03:08:20.399
not, not.

03:08:20.520 --> 03:08:22.680
But what I was trying to say is

03:08:22.680 --> 03:08:23.219
interesting.

03:08:23.280 --> 03:08:25.020
You're interesting.

03:08:25.079 --> 03:08:27.479
And I usually spend all day with dragons

03:08:27.479 --> 03:08:30.540
like bombardier and earthworm, who are

03:08:30.540 --> 03:08:32.700
definitely not interesting.

03:08:32.760 --> 03:08:34.319
Huh.

03:08:34.440 --> 03:08:35.520
He said.

03:08:35.639 --> 03:08:38.100
She wants to study me.

03:08:38.159 --> 03:08:40.139
He caught himself thinking.

03:08:40.200 --> 03:08:42.959
I'm one of the forbidden library books

03:08:42.959 --> 03:08:43.799
come to life.

03:08:43.860 --> 03:08:44.639
That's all.

03:08:44.760 --> 03:08:47.159
A chance for her to learn more about my

03:08:47.159 --> 03:08:48.719
tribe in Flame Silk.

03:08:48.780 --> 03:08:50.399
It's not really about me.

03:08:50.520 --> 03:08:52.979
Which is better?

03:08:53.100 --> 03:08:55.739
Safer, for both of us.

03:08:55.799 --> 03:08:58.379
He sighed and closed his eyes.

03:08:58.440 --> 03:09:02.280
He imagined a 1000 moths weaving a web of

03:09:02.280 --> 03:09:05.040
silk around him, shrouding him in a 2nd

03:09:05.040 --> 03:09:05.399
skin.

03:09:05.459 --> 03:09:09.000
The paint felt like tiny beetle shells as

03:09:09.000 --> 03:09:11.579
it dried, glossy and thin and hard.

03:09:11.639 --> 03:09:16.260
After a while, Cricket said, hmm, what do

03:09:16.260 --> 03:09:16.500
you think?

03:09:16.559 --> 03:09:19.920
Blue half expected to see something like

03:09:19.920 --> 03:09:21.780
her terrarium when he opened his eyes.

03:09:21.840 --> 03:09:24.600
He was a little afraid he'd look like a

03:09:24.600 --> 03:09:25.799
rose garden on fire.

03:09:25.860 --> 03:09:28.500
But the dragon looking back at him from

03:09:28.500 --> 03:09:31.020
the cabinet mirror, was a nondescript

03:09:31.020 --> 03:09:33.659
silk wing in dark blues and the browns of

03:09:33.659 --> 03:09:36.180
dead leaves, with touches of deep red

03:09:36.180 --> 03:09:38.340
barely visible along his spine and

03:09:38.340 --> 03:09:38.639
snout.

03:09:38.760 --> 03:09:41.459
There were a few blobby spots around his

03:09:41.459 --> 03:09:44.100
claws, and his brighter blue peeked

03:09:44.100 --> 03:09:44.760
through here and there.

03:09:44.879 --> 03:09:47.219
But for the most part, the paint was

03:09:47.219 --> 03:09:47.459
even.

03:09:47.520 --> 03:09:50.639
He looked like a dragon no one would

03:09:50.639 --> 03:09:51.479
glance at twice.

03:09:51.540 --> 03:09:53.340
He blinked.

03:09:53.399 --> 03:09:54.360
Wow.

03:09:54.420 --> 03:09:55.979
Thank you, cricket.

03:09:56.040 --> 03:09:58.139
It's not perfect.

03:09:58.200 --> 03:10:01.500
But hopefully, it'll at least get you out

03:10:01.500 --> 03:10:04.139
of the hive, she said apologetically.

03:10:04.200 --> 03:10:06.479
Especially if everyone is still looking

03:10:06.479 --> 03:10:06.840
for you.

03:10:06.899 --> 03:10:11.280
Out of the hive, he thought with a

03:10:11.280 --> 03:10:11.700
shiver.

03:10:11.760 --> 03:10:14.459
He'd never gone any farther than the webs

03:10:14.459 --> 03:10:16.139
around cicada hive.

03:10:16.440 --> 03:10:20.219
Unlike Luna, he'd never even wanted to.

03:10:20.280 --> 03:10:24.180
I guess I'm ready to go find sword tail

03:10:24.180 --> 03:10:25.860
he said uncertainly.

03:10:25.920 --> 03:10:28.680
He'd never walked the streets of the hive

03:10:28.680 --> 03:10:29.639
alone at night before.

03:10:29.700 --> 03:10:32.280
He always went home to the webs before

03:10:32.280 --> 03:10:32.579
dark.

03:10:32.639 --> 03:10:36.059
Burnet and silver spot must be so worried

03:10:36.059 --> 03:10:36.540
about him.

03:10:36.600 --> 03:10:38.340
Which made him think.

03:10:38.399 --> 03:10:41.639
Cricket, don't you have to go home?

03:10:41.700 --> 03:10:46.079
She glanced out at the dark savannah, and

03:10:46.079 --> 03:10:48.000
the twinkling lights of other hives in

03:10:48.000 --> 03:10:48.420
the distance.

03:10:48.479 --> 03:10:51.719
I doubt my father will notice one way or

03:10:51.719 --> 03:10:52.020
another.

03:10:52.079 --> 03:10:56.879
Katie did well, but she knows I sometimes

03:10:56.879 --> 03:10:59.280
hide for a while after Queen Wasp takes

03:10:59.280 --> 03:10:59.760
over everyone.

03:10:59.819 --> 03:11:02.520
I get nervous that it'll happen again

03:11:02.520 --> 03:11:03.059
right away.

03:11:03.120 --> 03:11:07.440
And it's hard to be around dragons.

03:11:07.500 --> 03:11:10.139
Even Katie did, after seeing that.

03:11:10.200 --> 03:11:13.260
She started cleaning away the paints and

03:11:13.260 --> 03:11:13.680
brushes.

03:11:13.739 --> 03:11:16.260
Blue moved to help her, but she stopped

03:11:16.260 --> 03:11:16.620
him.

03:11:16.680 --> 03:11:19.500
Now, stay still until you're completely

03:11:19.500 --> 03:11:19.860
dry.

03:11:19.920 --> 03:11:23.340
Anyway, she's the only one who cares

03:11:23.340 --> 03:11:25.500
where I am, and she'll cover for me.

03:11:25.559 --> 03:11:27.719
For how long?

03:11:27.719 --> 03:11:29.159
He wondered.

03:11:29.280 --> 03:11:32.340
How far would Cricket's curiosity take

03:11:32.340 --> 03:11:34.559
her before she decided to leave him to

03:11:34.559 --> 03:11:38.219
his fate, all the way to Wasp Hive, to

03:11:38.219 --> 03:11:38.700
Luna?

03:11:38.760 --> 03:11:40.979
Did he dare hope for that much?

03:11:41.100 --> 03:11:44.760
Where do you think Sortell is?

03:11:44.879 --> 03:11:46.020
Cricket asked.

03:11:46.079 --> 03:11:48.780
Tucking the last pot of blue paint into

03:11:48.780 --> 03:11:49.020
place?

03:11:49.079 --> 03:11:52.200
Blue noticed that she'd put 2 of the pots

03:11:52.200 --> 03:11:52.860
in the wrong order?

03:11:52.920 --> 03:11:55.860
One was darker than the other, so it

03:11:55.860 --> 03:11:57.840
should come later in the line, and

03:11:57.840 --> 03:11:59.219
reached past her to switch them.

03:11:59.280 --> 03:12:03.360
My only guess is misbehaviors way.

03:12:03.420 --> 03:12:04.500
Blue said.

03:12:04.559 --> 03:12:07.559
He doesn't like being told what to do, so

03:12:07.559 --> 03:12:08.340
he's been there before.

03:12:08.399 --> 03:12:10.079
But I'm afraid.

03:12:10.200 --> 03:12:13.440
I mean, he's never actually attacked a

03:12:13.440 --> 03:12:14.819
hive wing like he did today.

03:12:14.879 --> 03:12:18.479
He felt a fizzing twist of anxiety in his

03:12:18.479 --> 03:12:18.899
stomach.

03:12:18.959 --> 03:12:21.479
What would the hive wings do with sword

03:12:21.479 --> 03:12:23.100
tail if they decided he was really

03:12:23.100 --> 03:12:23.579
dangerous?

03:12:23.639 --> 03:12:26.399
It's still the 1st stop.

03:12:26.520 --> 03:12:28.860
Even if he'll be moved to prison after

03:12:28.860 --> 03:12:30.659
that, cricket said.

03:12:30.659 --> 03:12:32.399
So that's probably where he is.

03:12:32.459 --> 03:12:35.879
I've never been to Misbehavior's way.

03:12:36.000 --> 03:12:39.360
She leaned forward and lightly tested the

03:12:39.360 --> 03:12:40.260
paint on his snout.

03:12:40.319 --> 03:12:43.260
Although father is always saying that's

03:12:43.260 --> 03:12:44.760
what my teachers should do with me.

03:12:44.879 --> 03:12:48.180
Like, we all know it's inevitable, just

03:12:48.180 --> 03:12:50.459
sticker there now, that kind of thing.

03:12:50.520 --> 03:12:54.420
You've never, haven't you at least walked

03:12:54.420 --> 03:12:54.899
along it?

03:12:54.959 --> 03:12:55.979
He asked.

03:12:56.100 --> 03:12:58.500
He was flummoxed when she shook her

03:12:58.500 --> 03:12:58.739
head.

03:12:58.799 --> 03:13:01.559
But, really?

03:13:01.620 --> 03:13:03.780
It's only a couple levels up from here.

03:13:03.840 --> 03:13:06.600
My school has 2 field trips there every

03:13:06.600 --> 03:13:06.780
year.

03:13:06.840 --> 03:13:09.780
Field trips?

03:13:09.899 --> 03:13:12.540
Cricket echoed, fluttering her wings

03:13:12.540 --> 03:13:13.020
back.

03:13:13.079 --> 03:13:14.579
What for?

03:13:14.639 --> 03:13:17.040
What can they possibly teach you there?

03:13:17.100 --> 03:13:19.559
Isn't it kind of scary for little

03:13:19.559 --> 03:13:20.399
dragonettes?

03:13:20.459 --> 03:13:23.520
She glanced around, making sure all

03:13:23.520 --> 03:13:25.739
traces of their activity were gone, and

03:13:25.739 --> 03:13:26.520
started for the door.

03:13:26.579 --> 03:13:30.180
Yes, he said fervently.

03:13:30.239 --> 03:13:32.459
I found it terrifying every time.

03:13:32.520 --> 03:13:34.319
I still do.

03:13:34.379 --> 03:13:37.799
That's um, kind of the point, I think.

03:13:37.860 --> 03:13:41.340
His scales felt crackly and strange as he

03:13:41.340 --> 03:13:43.920
walked behind her, but kind of cool too

03:13:43.920 --> 03:13:46.379
like wearing a mask fitted exactly to his

03:13:46.379 --> 03:13:46.680
face.

03:13:46.799 --> 03:13:49.379
Oh, she said.

03:13:49.440 --> 03:13:52.200
So it's to teach you to follow the

03:13:52.200 --> 03:13:52.559
rules.

03:13:52.620 --> 03:13:55.680
Poor little silkwing dragonettes.

03:13:55.739 --> 03:13:57.420
Do all your schools do that?

03:13:57.479 --> 03:13:59.280
I think so.

03:13:59.399 --> 03:14:02.940
Do they spend a lot of time scaring you?

03:14:03.000 --> 03:14:03.659
she asked.

03:14:03.719 --> 03:14:06.780
Like, on purpose?

03:14:06.840 --> 03:14:08.280
He shrugged.

03:14:08.340 --> 03:14:10.440
It was hard for him to concentrate on

03:14:10.440 --> 03:14:12.360
their conversation, because they had

03:14:12.360 --> 03:14:13.799
reached the front door of the school.

03:14:13.860 --> 03:14:16.260
Through the narrow windows on either

03:14:16.260 --> 03:14:16.559
side.

03:14:16.620 --> 03:14:19.139
He could see slivers of the prehistoric

03:14:19.139 --> 03:14:20.879
shapes of the playground structures

03:14:20.879 --> 03:14:23.760
outside, the ones that he'd last seen

03:14:23.760 --> 03:14:25.979
swarming with dragons trying to attack

03:14:25.979 --> 03:14:26.219
him.

03:14:26.280 --> 03:14:30.059
Now it looked deserted, like the bones of

03:14:30.059 --> 03:14:31.920
a whale graveyard at the bottom of the

03:14:31.920 --> 03:14:32.159
sea.

03:14:32.219 --> 03:14:36.059
Cricket stopped and peered out, pressing

03:14:36.059 --> 03:14:37.799
her face to the window so she could see

03:14:37.799 --> 03:14:39.540
as far in each direction as possible.

03:14:39.600 --> 03:14:43.020
I don't see anyone, she whispered.

03:14:43.079 --> 03:14:44.579
She hesitated.

03:14:44.639 --> 03:14:46.860
Her tail flicking back and forth

03:14:46.860 --> 03:14:48.899
uncertainly as she stared out at the

03:14:48.899 --> 03:14:49.319
playground.

03:14:49.379 --> 03:14:52.319
Blue's heart was beating like a trapped

03:14:52.319 --> 03:14:54.600
insect, throwing itself at the glass

03:14:54.600 --> 03:14:55.799
walls of its prison.

03:14:55.860 --> 03:14:58.260
But he had a sudden bolt of

03:14:58.260 --> 03:14:58.680
understanding.

03:14:58.739 --> 03:15:00.840
She felt the same way.

03:15:00.899 --> 03:15:04.020
Cricket had never gone outside while the

03:15:04.020 --> 03:15:05.100
mind control was happening.

03:15:05.159 --> 03:15:08.219
She was as scared as he was.

03:15:08.280 --> 03:15:10.860
I'll go first, he whispered.

03:15:10.979 --> 03:15:12.420
Really?

03:15:12.479 --> 03:15:16.020
She glanced at him, her eyes darting

03:15:16.020 --> 03:15:17.639
worriedly over his painted scales.

03:15:17.700 --> 03:15:21.659
But, don't worry, I have my awesome

03:15:21.659 --> 03:15:22.799
disguise, remember?

03:15:22.860 --> 03:15:23.819
He said.

03:15:23.879 --> 03:15:26.219
If the high wings are still under Queen

03:15:26.219 --> 03:15:27.540
Wasps control.

03:15:27.600 --> 03:15:29.340
They'll notice that you're not right

03:15:29.340 --> 03:15:29.639
away.

03:15:29.700 --> 03:15:32.940
But with luck, they won't notice a random

03:15:32.940 --> 03:15:35.940
silk wing wandering the park, I'll

03:15:35.940 --> 03:15:36.299
signal.

03:15:36.360 --> 03:15:38.340
Once I know if it's safe for you to come

03:15:38.340 --> 03:15:39.000
out or not.

03:15:39.059 --> 03:15:42.059
She hesitated again before nodding.

03:15:42.120 --> 03:15:45.000
He took a deep breath, pushed open the

03:15:45.000 --> 03:15:47.159
heavy door, and slipped down the stairs.

03:15:47.219 --> 03:15:51.540
Chapter 11.

03:15:51.840 --> 03:15:55.260
Blue walked cautiously through the park

03:15:55.260 --> 03:15:57.959
glancing around for dragons, but seeing

03:15:57.959 --> 03:15:58.379
no one.

03:15:58.440 --> 03:16:00.899
He made his way to the ledge and looked

03:16:00.899 --> 03:16:02.760
out of the cloud covered moons and

03:16:02.760 --> 03:16:03.719
rustling savannah.

03:16:03.780 --> 03:16:06.600
What had happened to IO?

03:16:06.659 --> 03:16:07.920
Did she get away?

03:16:07.979 --> 03:16:11.219
But there were no signs, no clues.

03:16:11.280 --> 03:16:14.159
Nothing in the quiet around him indicated

03:16:14.159 --> 03:16:16.200
that a massive dragon hunt had started

03:16:16.200 --> 03:16:17.520
here earlier that evening.

03:16:17.579 --> 03:16:20.459
He ducked his head and started back

03:16:20.459 --> 03:16:21.239
toward the school.

03:16:21.299 --> 03:16:24.540
Halfway there, he saw a dragon hurrying

03:16:24.540 --> 03:16:27.299
out of his side street, half in shadows.

03:16:27.360 --> 03:16:29.819
The stranger picked up a toy that had

03:16:29.819 --> 03:16:31.440
been left on one of the structures and

03:16:31.440 --> 03:16:33.479
paused, squinting at Blue.

03:16:33.540 --> 03:16:37.559
You'd better get back where you belong, he

03:16:37.559 --> 03:16:38.459
called in a sharp voice.

03:16:38.579 --> 03:16:40.920
The hunting parties will be leaving at

03:16:40.920 --> 03:16:41.579
dawn tomorrow.

03:16:41.639 --> 03:16:43.260
Yes, sir.

03:16:43.379 --> 03:16:44.520
Blue said.

03:16:44.579 --> 03:16:47.100
Trying to walk like he had a destination

03:16:47.100 --> 03:16:49.200
and study the dragon at the same time.

03:16:49.260 --> 03:16:52.500
The stranger grumbled something and left

03:16:52.500 --> 03:16:55.500
and in the glow of the street lights, blue

03:16:55.500 --> 03:16:57.239
caught a glimpse of black stripes across

03:16:57.239 --> 03:16:57.659
his back.

03:16:57.719 --> 03:17:01.739
A hive wing, one with his own eyes and

03:17:01.739 --> 03:17:02.459
his own mind.

03:17:02.520 --> 03:17:05.700
The queen had released her tribe for

03:17:05.700 --> 03:17:06.000
now.

03:17:06.059 --> 03:17:09.239
Blue waited until the hive wing was out

03:17:09.239 --> 03:17:11.399
of sight, then beckoned to cricket.

03:17:11.459 --> 03:17:13.799
She slipped out of the school, and

03:17:13.799 --> 03:17:15.899
together, they hurried down one of the

03:17:15.899 --> 03:17:18.120
deserted streets toward the outer spiral

03:17:18.120 --> 03:17:21.719
inside a few of the houses, blue saw

03:17:21.719 --> 03:17:23.340
lights glowing or moving around.

03:17:23.459 --> 03:17:26.579
He wondered how long ago the queen had

03:17:26.579 --> 03:17:27.000
let them go.

03:17:27.059 --> 03:17:30.299
He wondered how long it had taken all the

03:17:30.299 --> 03:17:32.639
families to reunite, and how they were

03:17:32.639 --> 03:17:33.120
all feeling.

03:17:33.180 --> 03:17:36.180
Were any of them resentful of the queen?

03:17:36.299 --> 03:17:39.120
Or did they blame him for disrupting

03:17:39.120 --> 03:17:40.079
their evening instead?

03:17:40.139 --> 03:17:42.959
Or perhaps they all felt as if they'd

03:17:42.959 --> 03:17:44.940
been useful and important helpers in the

03:17:44.940 --> 03:17:46.260
search for a dangerous criminal.

03:17:46.319 --> 03:17:49.979
Me, a dangerous criminal.

03:17:50.040 --> 03:17:52.979
When all I've ever wanted is to stay out

03:17:52.979 --> 03:17:53.520
of trouble.

03:17:53.579 --> 03:17:55.079
Wait.

03:17:55.139 --> 03:17:59.040
That hive wing, Blue said softly.

03:17:59.100 --> 03:18:01.620
He said something about hunting parties

03:18:01.620 --> 03:18:02.399
leaving at dawn.

03:18:02.459 --> 03:18:04.860
To look for you?

03:18:04.920 --> 03:18:06.000
Cricket asked.

03:18:06.059 --> 03:18:07.200
Uh-oh.

03:18:07.260 --> 03:18:09.719
That means we need to move fast if we

03:18:09.719 --> 03:18:10.920
want to get a head start on them.

03:18:10.979 --> 03:18:14.819
Their guards slumped at the entrance to

03:18:14.819 --> 03:18:15.420
the spiral.

03:18:15.479 --> 03:18:18.479
But their eyes glanced over Blue's muted

03:18:18.479 --> 03:18:21.000
colors, noted the haughty tilt to

03:18:21.000 --> 03:18:23.340
cricket's snout, and slanted away

03:18:23.340 --> 03:18:24.420
uninterested.

03:18:24.479 --> 03:18:27.600
Cricket went 1st and Blue followed.

03:18:27.659 --> 03:18:30.600
Keeping his head low, acting the part of

03:18:30.600 --> 03:18:32.639
a humble servant, following his

03:18:32.639 --> 03:18:34.739
mistress's midnight whim for a stroll.

03:18:34.799 --> 03:18:37.920
She paused a few levels up and glanced

03:18:37.920 --> 03:18:38.399
back at him.

03:18:38.459 --> 03:18:40.920
He nodded, through there.

03:18:41.040 --> 03:18:44.219
This was one of the only levels with a

03:18:44.219 --> 03:18:46.200
gate, although it wasn't locked.

03:18:46.260 --> 03:18:48.600
There was no risk of anyone escaping

03:18:48.600 --> 03:18:49.020
after all.

03:18:49.079 --> 03:18:52.260
Blue suspected the gate was there, so

03:18:52.260 --> 03:18:54.180
high wings wouldn't have to accidentally

03:18:54.180 --> 03:18:55.920
see the prisoners on their way between

03:18:55.920 --> 03:18:56.399
levels.

03:18:56.459 --> 03:19:00.239
Cricket pushed open the gate, and they

03:19:00.239 --> 03:19:02.579
emerged onto a path that was roughly

03:19:02.579 --> 03:19:04.500
cobbled with chunks of sharp stones.

03:19:04.620 --> 03:19:08.520
She winced as one stabbed her feet, then

03:19:08.520 --> 03:19:10.500
looked up at the columns that lined the

03:19:10.500 --> 03:19:10.860
walkway.

03:19:10.979 --> 03:19:14.819
Normally, Blue came here in a crowd of

03:19:14.819 --> 03:19:18.000
other dragons, young silk wings all wide

03:19:18.000 --> 03:19:19.440
eyed and hushed with terror.

03:19:19.500 --> 03:19:22.799
He always tried to stay near the back, so

03:19:22.799 --> 03:19:24.299
he wouldn't have to look at the prisoners

03:19:24.299 --> 03:19:25.500
too closely.

03:19:25.559 --> 03:19:27.540
But they were impossible to miss.

03:19:27.600 --> 03:19:31.319
Mounted on stone pedestals for all the

03:19:31.319 --> 03:19:34.319
world to stare at, looming over the heads

03:19:34.319 --> 03:19:35.579
of the visiting students.

03:19:35.639 --> 03:19:39.600
The stony path wound all around the level

03:19:39.600 --> 03:19:43.260
in and out, and over roughly shaped hills

03:19:43.260 --> 03:19:45.420
until it connected back with itself at

03:19:45.420 --> 03:19:46.139
the beginning again.

03:19:46.200 --> 03:19:49.620
In between the prisoner pedestals, were

03:19:49.620 --> 03:19:51.959
engraved tablets listing the rules of the

03:19:51.959 --> 03:19:54.540
hives, the consequences for breaking them

03:19:54.540 --> 03:19:58.319
odes to the greatness of Queen Wasp, and

03:19:58.319 --> 03:20:00.120
quotes from historical figures about

03:20:00.120 --> 03:20:02.760
obedience, safety, and community.

03:20:02.819 --> 03:20:05.879
Some of the quotes were from Clearsight

03:20:05.879 --> 03:20:06.239
herself.

03:20:06.299 --> 03:20:09.479
Blue had always liked that she sounded

03:20:09.479 --> 03:20:11.459
like she cared about the rules as much as

03:20:11.459 --> 03:20:11.760
he did.

03:20:11.819 --> 03:20:14.639
Above each prisoner hung a small

03:20:14.639 --> 03:20:17.819
spotlight, and on each pedestal, there

03:20:17.819 --> 03:20:19.440
was always a list posted of that

03:20:19.440 --> 03:20:22.200
prisoner's crimes described in dramatic

03:20:22.200 --> 03:20:22.620
detail.

03:20:22.620 --> 03:20:26.399
Tonight, the 1st few pedestals on

03:20:26.399 --> 03:20:27.959
misbehavior's way were empty.

03:20:28.020 --> 03:20:31.319
But as they walked the path, they saw

03:20:31.319 --> 03:20:32.639
figures on the ones up ahead.

03:20:32.700 --> 03:20:36.239
Cricket gave a start, jumping back to

03:20:36.239 --> 03:20:38.940
crash into blue, when she noticed the 1st

03:20:38.940 --> 03:20:40.079
one a few paces away.

03:20:40.139 --> 03:20:42.959
Sorry, she whispered.

03:20:43.020 --> 03:20:45.479
Is that, is it real?

03:20:45.540 --> 03:20:47.520
A real dragon, I mean?

03:20:47.579 --> 03:20:49.260
Or is it a statue?

03:20:49.379 --> 03:20:51.840
But I can hear it breathing.

03:20:51.899 --> 03:20:53.520
Can't I?

03:20:53.579 --> 03:20:55.799
That's a dragon.

03:20:55.860 --> 03:20:57.180
Blue confirmed.

03:20:57.239 --> 03:20:59.940
A silk wing, but not sword tail.

03:21:00.000 --> 03:21:03.479
The colors were all wrong, mostly white

03:21:03.479 --> 03:21:05.579
and brown, with flecks of green.

03:21:05.639 --> 03:21:08.819
She watched the immobile prisoner for a

03:21:08.819 --> 03:21:09.840
long, wary moment.

03:21:09.899 --> 03:21:12.840
It's not moving at all.

03:21:13.020 --> 03:21:14.700
She can't.

03:21:14.819 --> 03:21:18.420
Blue pointed out. of them can move.

03:21:18.479 --> 03:21:21.659
They drew closer to the occupied

03:21:21.659 --> 03:21:24.000
pedestals and looked up at the trapped

03:21:24.000 --> 03:21:24.659
criminals.

03:21:24.719 --> 03:21:28.020
Misbehavior's way had no need for cages

03:21:28.020 --> 03:21:28.739
or chains.

03:21:28.799 --> 03:21:32.819
Instead, Queen Wasp used an elite unit of

03:21:32.819 --> 03:21:35.399
high wing soldiers, all recruited to the

03:21:35.399 --> 03:21:37.500
job because they had a nerve poison in

03:21:37.500 --> 03:21:40.139
their claws or tail stinger. once the

03:21:40.139 --> 03:21:43.920
criminal, or misbehavior, was stabbed.

03:21:43.979 --> 03:21:45.959
That dragon wouldn't be able to move for

03:21:45.959 --> 03:21:46.680
an entire day.

03:21:46.739 --> 03:21:50.879
I read about this, Cricket said.

03:21:50.940 --> 03:21:53.040
Shifting her wings uncomfortably.

03:21:53.100 --> 03:21:56.760
But it's not what I pictured.

03:21:56.819 --> 03:21:59.280
Blue kept walking.

03:21:59.399 --> 03:22:01.860
He could see the colors of the prisoners

03:22:01.860 --> 03:22:02.760
with a glance.

03:22:02.819 --> 03:22:04.739
But it was hard to avoid getting caught

03:22:04.739 --> 03:22:05.700
by their expressions.

03:22:05.760 --> 03:22:08.879
So many of their faces were frozen in

03:22:08.879 --> 03:22:11.100
erectus of rage or fear.

03:22:11.159 --> 03:22:13.920
Most of them had been paralyzed while

03:22:13.920 --> 03:22:15.540
trying to run or fight.

03:22:15.600 --> 03:22:18.600
So they were contorted in odd positions

03:22:18.600 --> 03:22:21.120
stuck there until the toxin wore off.

03:22:21.180 --> 03:22:24.899
They passed a pale pink silk wing with

03:22:24.899 --> 03:22:27.719
long rose petal wings, his talons

03:22:27.719 --> 03:22:29.700
outstretched, as though he'd been

03:22:29.700 --> 03:22:30.600
pleading for mercy.

03:22:30.659 --> 03:22:33.420
His snout still wet with tears.

03:22:33.659 --> 03:22:36.899
They passed a snarling, scarlet hive wing

03:22:36.899 --> 03:22:39.180
in a defensive crouch, teeth bared.

03:22:39.239 --> 03:22:42.420
Another silk wing and shade of turquoise

03:22:42.420 --> 03:22:44.520
and tan looked as though she'd been

03:22:44.520 --> 03:22:46.079
trying to leap into flight when she was

03:22:46.079 --> 03:22:46.319
caught.

03:22:46.379 --> 03:22:49.319
Her neck strained hopelessly toward the

03:22:49.319 --> 03:22:49.620
ceiling.

03:22:49.739 --> 03:22:52.860
Her wings were in an awkward, half open

03:22:52.860 --> 03:22:53.219
position.

03:22:53.280 --> 03:22:55.920
That would probably feel awfully sore

03:22:55.920 --> 03:22:56.879
when they could move again.

03:22:56.940 --> 03:22:59.459
I thought they'd be asleep.

03:22:59.520 --> 03:23:01.860
Cricket said in a small voice.

03:23:01.920 --> 03:23:05.879
I thought the toxin knocked them out, like

03:23:05.879 --> 03:23:08.219
putting them in a temporary coma.

03:23:08.280 --> 03:23:11.399
She glanced up at the next frozen dragon

03:23:11.399 --> 03:23:12.540
and flinched away.

03:23:12.600 --> 03:23:16.379
But these dragons, Are they awake in

03:23:16.379 --> 03:23:16.559
there?

03:23:16.620 --> 03:23:19.139
So they can see everyone watching them?

03:23:19.200 --> 03:23:21.120
Do you think it hurts?

03:23:21.239 --> 03:23:24.420
It does, Blue said.

03:23:24.479 --> 03:23:27.959
Swordtail says, getting stabbed feels

03:23:27.959 --> 03:23:30.000
like fire burning every nerve in your

03:23:30.000 --> 03:23:30.239
body.

03:23:30.360 --> 03:23:33.840
Eventually the pain fades, but you're

03:23:33.840 --> 03:23:35.100
still paralyzed.

03:23:35.159 --> 03:23:38.100
So all you want to do is run or fly, or

03:23:38.100 --> 03:23:40.500
even blink, but you can't move a single

03:23:40.500 --> 03:23:42.959
muscle until the toxin wears off.

03:23:43.020 --> 03:23:46.319
Everything about misbehaviors away

03:23:46.319 --> 03:23:48.540
featured in his recurring nightmares.

03:23:48.600 --> 03:23:51.780
I didn't know, she said.

03:23:51.899 --> 03:23:54.840
I can't believe this was right here and I

03:23:54.840 --> 03:23:55.379
had no idea.

03:23:55.440 --> 03:23:57.899
I'm a terrible dragon.

03:23:57.959 --> 03:24:01.440
I don't think so, Blue said.

03:24:01.500 --> 03:24:04.319
He inhaled sharply as they rounded a bend

03:24:04.319 --> 03:24:04.799
in the path.

03:24:04.860 --> 03:24:07.440
There, that sword tail.

03:24:07.500 --> 03:24:09.479
He darted forward.

03:24:09.540 --> 03:24:11.760
Skidding to a stop at the base of Sword

03:24:11.760 --> 03:24:12.600
Tails column.

03:24:12.659 --> 03:24:16.139
Swordtail's paralyzed wings were spread

03:24:16.139 --> 03:24:16.620
wide.

03:24:16.739 --> 03:24:19.379
His tail frozen as it lashed back and

03:24:19.379 --> 03:24:19.680
forth.

03:24:19.739 --> 03:24:22.799
One of his front talons was outstretched

03:24:22.799 --> 03:24:25.559
the claws curved as though he was about

03:24:25.559 --> 03:24:26.879
to slash someone's face.

03:24:26.940 --> 03:24:30.600
It was a little scary, honestly, seeing

03:24:30.600 --> 03:24:32.700
his friend on the attack like that.

03:24:32.760 --> 03:24:35.520
Sortell's expression was determined and

03:24:35.520 --> 03:24:36.059
desperate.

03:24:36.180 --> 03:24:38.760
As though this was his very last chance

03:24:38.760 --> 03:24:40.379
to save the world.

03:24:40.440 --> 03:24:44.459
Hey, Blue said softly up at him.

03:24:44.520 --> 03:24:48.059
Sortail couldn't react, but Blue knew he

03:24:48.059 --> 03:24:48.479
could still hear.

03:24:48.540 --> 03:24:50.639
It's me, Blue.

03:24:50.700 --> 03:24:52.440
This is cricket.

03:24:52.500 --> 03:24:55.860
We're going to What are we going to do?

03:24:55.920 --> 03:24:57.420
He asked Cricket.

03:24:57.479 --> 03:24:59.879
Pick him up and carry him out of here?

03:24:59.940 --> 03:25:02.520
She wrinkled or snouted at him.

03:25:02.579 --> 03:25:05.219
A glimmer of her cheerful side sneaking

03:25:05.219 --> 03:25:07.079
through for the 1st time since they'd

03:25:07.079 --> 03:25:08.760
stepped onto misbehavior's way.

03:25:08.819 --> 03:25:11.579
I'm sure that would be very

03:25:11.579 --> 03:25:12.899
inconspicuous.

03:25:12.959 --> 03:25:16.200
She crouched on the cobblestones, took

03:25:16.200 --> 03:25:18.239
off her bag and unrolled the pouch of

03:25:18.239 --> 03:25:18.780
vials.

03:25:18.840 --> 03:25:21.600
They gleamed like raindrops on flower

03:25:21.600 --> 03:25:23.520
petals and the light shining from above.

03:25:23.579 --> 03:25:26.940
I don't know if this will work. she said

03:25:26.940 --> 03:25:29.639
pushing her glasses higher on her snout.

03:25:29.700 --> 03:25:32.819
I thought we needed to wake him up, but

03:25:32.819 --> 03:25:34.139
maybe this one would be better.

03:25:34.200 --> 03:25:36.959
Cricket selected a liquid, the color of

03:25:36.959 --> 03:25:39.899
grass. and gave blue a wry, nervous

03:25:39.899 --> 03:25:40.139
look.

03:25:40.200 --> 03:25:44.040
At least, we use this to save plants that

03:25:44.040 --> 03:25:44.760
have been poisoned.

03:25:44.879 --> 03:25:47.100
On plants?

03:25:47.100 --> 03:25:47.879
he said.

03:25:48.000 --> 03:25:49.920
Is it safe for dragons?

03:25:49.979 --> 03:25:51.959
I think so?

03:25:52.020 --> 03:25:53.340
She said.

03:25:53.399 --> 03:25:55.559
Have I ever tried it on a dragon?

03:25:55.620 --> 03:25:56.819
Not exactly.

03:25:56.879 --> 03:25:58.680
But it shouldn't make things worse

03:25:58.680 --> 03:25:59.219
anyway.

03:25:59.280 --> 03:26:02.819
This was not the most comforting answer.

03:26:02.879 --> 03:26:06.299
Blue looked up at SwordTail, wishing his

03:26:06.299 --> 03:26:08.700
friend could give him some sort of sign.

03:26:08.760 --> 03:26:11.760
Was Swortail willing to risk a mysterious

03:26:11.760 --> 03:26:14.340
unproven, possible antidote from a

03:26:14.340 --> 03:26:15.360
strange hive wing?

03:26:15.479 --> 03:26:17.579
Or would he rather be left alone?

03:26:17.639 --> 03:26:19.920
Who am I kidding?

03:26:19.979 --> 03:26:22.379
Sortell would risk anything to save

03:26:22.379 --> 03:26:22.979
Luna?

03:26:23.040 --> 03:26:25.319
I'm the one who would find it too scary.

03:26:25.379 --> 03:26:28.200
Do you want me to try it on him?

03:26:28.260 --> 03:26:29.340
Cricket said.

03:26:29.399 --> 03:26:31.260
I understand if you don't.

03:26:31.319 --> 03:26:34.139
I do, Blue said.

03:26:34.200 --> 03:26:35.819
I think we have to.

03:26:35.879 --> 03:26:39.299
He glanced back along the deserted path.

03:26:39.420 --> 03:26:42.299
He had a feeling that everyone in the

03:26:42.299 --> 03:26:44.700
hive was at home, recovering from the

03:26:44.700 --> 03:26:47.459
Queen's mind control earlier, and that

03:26:47.459 --> 03:26:49.559
was why they'd seen so few dragons out.

03:26:49.620 --> 03:26:53.040
But he was also afraid that WASP might

03:26:53.040 --> 03:26:54.840
seize control of them again at any

03:26:54.840 --> 03:26:55.079
moment.

03:26:55.139 --> 03:26:57.780
He couldn't imagine trying to fight his

03:26:57.780 --> 03:26:59.819
way out of the hive alongside cricket.

03:26:59.879 --> 03:27:02.700
But with sword tail, they might stand a

03:27:02.700 --> 03:27:02.940
chance.

03:27:03.059 --> 03:27:06.059
And Sordail would be able to rescue

03:27:06.059 --> 03:27:06.540
Luna.

03:27:06.600 --> 03:27:09.600
He was strong and brave, and not afraid

03:27:09.600 --> 03:27:10.739
of hive wing soldiers.

03:27:10.799 --> 03:27:14.100
All right, Cricket said.

03:27:14.159 --> 03:27:15.959
How am I going to do this?

03:27:16.020 --> 03:27:17.639
Let's think.

03:27:17.700 --> 03:27:21.000
She poked through the vials and drew out

03:27:21.000 --> 03:27:23.280
the tweezers she'd used on the flame silk

03:27:23.280 --> 03:27:23.879
in the library.

03:27:23.940 --> 03:27:26.520
Blue hadn't even noticed that she'd

03:27:26.520 --> 03:27:27.059
brought them along.

03:27:27.120 --> 03:27:31.200
Find me a big rock, she said to Blue.

03:27:31.260 --> 03:27:33.239
That wasn't too hard here.

03:27:33.299 --> 03:27:36.059
Blue found a loose cobblestone and kicked

03:27:36.059 --> 03:27:37.440
it until he could wobble it free.

03:27:37.500 --> 03:27:40.260
He brought it to cricket, and she beat

03:27:40.260 --> 03:27:44.399
her wings once, twice, 3 times, just

03:27:44.399 --> 03:27:46.260
enough to lift her up to the light over

03:27:46.260 --> 03:27:47.340
Swordtail's head.

03:27:47.399 --> 03:27:50.340
Here she hesitated, glancing down.

03:27:50.399 --> 03:27:53.459
Can you cover his eyes for me?

03:27:53.520 --> 03:27:55.200
She asked Blue.

03:27:55.260 --> 03:27:57.239
And keep yours closed too.

03:27:57.299 --> 03:28:01.020
Blue climbed up to balance awkwardly on

03:28:01.020 --> 03:28:03.059
the corner of the pedestal, where he

03:28:03.059 --> 03:28:05.520
could lean sideways and put his talons

03:28:05.520 --> 03:28:07.739
over sore tail's eyes.

03:28:07.799 --> 03:28:10.020
Obediently, he closed his own as well.

03:28:10.079 --> 03:28:13.440
There was a smashing sound from above him

03:28:13.440 --> 03:28:16.500
and tiny bits of glass pattered down all

03:28:16.500 --> 03:28:17.940
over him and sore tail.

03:28:18.000 --> 03:28:20.940
He shook his head, and squinted open his

03:28:20.940 --> 03:28:22.500
eyes into the new brightness.

03:28:22.559 --> 03:28:25.440
Sorry about that, Cricket said.

03:28:25.500 --> 03:28:26.639
Are you all right?

03:28:26.700 --> 03:28:28.020
He nodded.

03:28:28.079 --> 03:28:30.780
She was using the tweezers to work the

03:28:30.780 --> 03:28:31.739
flame silk thread out.

03:28:31.799 --> 03:28:34.799
He couldn't look straight at her or the

03:28:34.799 --> 03:28:36.479
thread without getting a headache.

03:28:36.540 --> 03:28:39.299
A moment later, she had it free.

03:28:39.360 --> 03:28:42.299
He hopped down to the ground, and she

03:28:42.299 --> 03:28:44.819
took his place on the pedestal, with a

03:28:44.819 --> 03:28:46.139
few careful strokes.

03:28:46.200 --> 03:28:48.780
She burned through Swordtail's wrist cuff

03:28:48.780 --> 03:28:51.239
in the same way she'd burned off blues.

03:28:51.360 --> 03:28:55.020
Blue met sore tail's eyes as the heavy

03:28:55.020 --> 03:28:56.520
band clunked to the ground.

03:28:56.639 --> 03:28:59.459
He didn't think he was imagining the

03:28:59.459 --> 03:29:00.899
spark of jubilation in them.

03:29:01.020 --> 03:29:05.100
All right, moment of truth, Cricket

03:29:05.100 --> 03:29:05.459
said.

03:29:05.520 --> 03:29:07.620
Would you mind passing me the vial?

03:29:07.739 --> 03:29:09.959
Very, very carefully.

03:29:10.020 --> 03:29:13.979
He uncorked it and held it high, keeping

03:29:13.979 --> 03:29:16.200
his claws as steady as he could, while

03:29:16.200 --> 03:29:17.340
she reached down for it.

03:29:17.399 --> 03:29:20.700
Now you might want to hold your breath

03:29:20.700 --> 03:29:21.479
she said.

03:29:21.540 --> 03:29:24.059
Clearside only knows what this could do

03:29:24.059 --> 03:29:24.540
to us.

03:29:24.600 --> 03:29:27.420
This is such a cool experiment.

03:29:27.479 --> 03:29:30.059
I feel like a real scientist, don't you?

03:29:30.120 --> 03:29:33.299
She took a deep breath herself and

03:29:33.299 --> 03:29:35.159
dropped the flame silk into the vial.

03:29:35.219 --> 03:29:38.340
The liquid started bubbling furiously.

03:29:38.399 --> 03:29:41.280
Cricket clamped the tweezers around the

03:29:41.280 --> 03:29:44.159
vial, and held it out under SwordTail's

03:29:44.159 --> 03:29:44.579
snout.

03:29:44.639 --> 03:29:47.940
Green smoke boiled up from the top of it

03:29:47.940 --> 03:29:50.760
enveloping Swordtail's face in a thick

03:29:50.760 --> 03:29:52.139
emerald cloud.

03:29:52.200 --> 03:29:54.600
Blue stared up at them.

03:29:54.659 --> 03:29:56.040
His heart pounding.

03:29:56.159 --> 03:30:00.420
Chapter 12.

03:30:00.780 --> 03:30:03.299
Please work.

03:30:03.360 --> 03:30:04.500
Blue prayed.

03:30:04.559 --> 03:30:07.319
Please, please be all right, sword tail.

03:30:07.379 --> 03:30:08.520
Clear sight.

03:30:08.579 --> 03:30:09.479
If you're listening.

03:30:09.540 --> 03:30:10.979
Please set him free.

03:30:11.100 --> 03:30:15.120
They waited several long, agonizing

03:30:15.120 --> 03:30:18.479
moments, all 3 dragons frozen in place.

03:30:18.540 --> 03:30:20.940
And then Swordtail twitched suddenly

03:30:20.940 --> 03:30:24.000
violently, knocking cricket off the

03:30:24.000 --> 03:30:26.879
pedestal with one flailing wing, Blue

03:30:26.879 --> 03:30:28.139
jumped to break or fall.

03:30:28.200 --> 03:30:30.840
The vial shattered on the stone path

03:30:30.840 --> 03:30:32.940
spilling what was left of the hissing

03:30:32.940 --> 03:30:33.840
green chemical.

03:30:33.899 --> 03:30:36.840
Crickets scrambled over to pick up the

03:30:36.840 --> 03:30:39.600
flame silk in her tweezers again, tucking

03:30:39.600 --> 03:30:41.700
the thread into a small stone jar with a

03:30:41.700 --> 03:30:44.399
tight lid that she'd also had hidden in

03:30:44.399 --> 03:30:45.059
her bag.

03:30:45.180 --> 03:30:49.379
Sortell let out a gasp, his jaw clenched

03:30:49.379 --> 03:30:53.100
his eyelids closed, and slowly, he

03:30:53.100 --> 03:30:55.739
lowered his reaching talon, shaking it

03:30:55.739 --> 03:30:57.120
hard as though it had been asleep.

03:30:57.180 --> 03:30:59.219
Sore tail?

03:30:59.219 --> 03:31:01.920
Blue said, Blue.

03:31:01.979 --> 03:31:03.659
Sortail croaked.

03:31:03.719 --> 03:31:06.479
He opened his eyes and gingerly inched

03:31:06.479 --> 03:31:08.219
his head around to look down at them.

03:31:08.280 --> 03:31:10.680
The poison seemed to be wearing off

03:31:10.680 --> 03:31:11.340
gradually.

03:31:11.399 --> 03:31:14.159
From his face, through his wings and back

03:31:14.159 --> 03:31:16.020
and at last to his tail.

03:31:16.079 --> 03:31:18.120
Do you feel all right?

03:31:18.180 --> 03:31:19.559
Cricket asked him.

03:31:19.620 --> 03:31:20.819
Anything weird?

03:31:20.879 --> 03:31:22.139
How's your nose?

03:31:22.200 --> 03:31:23.040
Did that hurt?

03:31:23.100 --> 03:31:25.079
I hope it didn't hurt, but it might

03:31:25.079 --> 03:31:25.319
have.

03:31:25.379 --> 03:31:26.040
I don't know.

03:31:26.100 --> 03:31:28.440
The plants can't exactly tell us if it

03:31:28.440 --> 03:31:28.680
does.

03:31:28.739 --> 03:31:29.940
Are you dizzy?

03:31:30.059 --> 03:31:31.260
How are your lungs?

03:31:31.319 --> 03:31:34.799
Sortail raised one talent to feel the

03:31:34.799 --> 03:31:36.600
trickle of dried blood on his neck.

03:31:36.659 --> 03:31:40.440
Oh, right, he said thickly.

03:31:40.500 --> 03:31:43.200
Cricket, Blue whispered.

03:31:43.260 --> 03:31:45.600
Are his eyes supposed to be turning

03:31:45.600 --> 03:31:45.959
green?

03:31:46.020 --> 03:31:49.139
The whites of Swordtail's eyes.

03:31:49.200 --> 03:31:52.739
Around his normally dark blue irises, or

03:31:52.739 --> 03:31:54.959
turning a shade of emerald green, only

03:31:54.959 --> 03:31:57.059
slightly paler than the liquid from the

03:31:57.059 --> 03:31:57.420
vial.

03:31:57.420 --> 03:31:59.159
Oh.

03:31:59.280 --> 03:32:01.260
Fascinating.

03:32:01.319 --> 03:32:02.639
Cricket said.

03:32:02.760 --> 03:32:04.920
Why would that happen?

03:32:05.040 --> 03:32:06.719
Is it affecting your vision?

03:32:06.780 --> 03:32:08.280
Can you see all right?

03:32:08.340 --> 03:32:10.200
She asked Swordtail.

03:32:10.260 --> 03:32:11.520
He blinked a few times.

03:32:11.579 --> 03:32:16.379
Bit greenish, he offered.

03:32:16.440 --> 03:32:18.719
No, wait.

03:32:18.780 --> 03:32:20.459
Uh-oh.

03:32:20.520 --> 03:32:22.020
Definitely bad.

03:32:22.079 --> 03:32:25.559
Blue is all the wrong colors.

03:32:25.620 --> 03:32:28.500
Oh no, Blue said.

03:32:28.559 --> 03:32:29.639
That's just paint.

03:32:29.700 --> 03:32:30.540
Don't worry.

03:32:30.600 --> 03:32:32.100
Huh.

03:32:32.159 --> 03:32:33.600
Sorrytails said.

03:32:33.659 --> 03:32:34.979
Sure.

03:32:35.040 --> 03:32:36.959
Sounds normal.

03:32:37.020 --> 03:32:39.420
Swordtail crouched.

03:32:39.479 --> 03:32:41.579
Then arched his back into a stretch like

03:32:41.579 --> 03:32:42.420
a jungle cat.

03:32:42.479 --> 03:32:45.120
He flared his wings and leaped down from

03:32:45.120 --> 03:32:47.459
the pedestal, landing in a wobbly

03:32:47.459 --> 03:32:48.059
sprawl.

03:32:48.120 --> 03:32:50.219
Woof, he said.

03:32:50.280 --> 03:32:53.219
Legs, disagreeing with me.

03:32:53.280 --> 03:32:56.280
He sat down heavily and frowned at his

03:32:56.280 --> 03:32:56.520
feet.

03:32:56.579 --> 03:32:58.079
Whoa.

03:32:58.139 --> 03:33:01.139
Very demanding licks.

03:33:01.200 --> 03:33:03.420
Cricket.

03:33:03.479 --> 03:33:05.639
You're a genius, Blue said.

03:33:05.700 --> 03:33:07.379
I can't believe that worked.

03:33:07.440 --> 03:33:10.020
Neither can I, she said.

03:33:10.079 --> 03:33:11.940
I should write a paper about this.

03:33:12.059 --> 03:33:13.799
No, a book.

03:33:13.860 --> 03:33:16.319
I mean, it's a real scientific

03:33:16.319 --> 03:33:17.159
breakthrough, right?

03:33:17.219 --> 03:33:18.780
We could.

03:33:18.899 --> 03:33:21.180
She stopped, realizing what she was

03:33:21.180 --> 03:33:21.479
saying.

03:33:21.540 --> 03:33:23.819
Oh, no.

03:33:23.879 --> 03:33:25.680
I guess I can do that.

03:33:25.739 --> 03:33:29.040
The Queen probably wouldn't appreciate

03:33:29.040 --> 03:33:29.520
it.

03:33:29.579 --> 03:33:30.840
Blue agreed.

03:33:30.959 --> 03:33:33.120
Soratell looked at them.

03:33:33.180 --> 03:33:35.040
A gleam in his newly green eyes.

03:33:35.100 --> 03:33:39.180
But I know some dragons, who would be

03:33:39.180 --> 03:33:40.500
very interested.

03:33:40.559 --> 03:33:42.059
He said.

03:33:42.180 --> 03:33:44.520
His voice was only a little bit slurred

03:33:44.520 --> 03:33:44.819
now.

03:33:44.879 --> 03:33:49.739
Very, very, very, ever so very

03:33:49.739 --> 03:33:50.459
interested.

03:33:50.520 --> 03:33:53.639
Does he mean the chrysalis?

03:33:53.700 --> 03:33:54.719
Blue wondered.

03:33:54.840 --> 03:33:58.020
He glanced back along the path at the

03:33:58.020 --> 03:33:59.159
other frozen figures.

03:33:59.219 --> 03:34:02.399
Would they set all these prisoners free?

03:34:02.459 --> 03:34:04.379
If they knew how cricket did it?

03:34:04.440 --> 03:34:09.059
And if they did, What would happen then?

03:34:09.120 --> 03:34:13.319
He imagined all the prisoners staggering

03:34:13.319 --> 03:34:15.899
off their pedestals, green eyed like

03:34:15.899 --> 03:34:18.959
sword tail, all of them angry and free at

03:34:18.959 --> 03:34:19.559
the same time.

03:34:19.559 --> 03:34:22.379
Would they attack hive wing soldiers?

03:34:22.440 --> 03:34:24.120
Or would they all run away?

03:34:24.180 --> 03:34:27.360
What does the chrysalis want exactly?

03:34:27.420 --> 03:34:30.780
Sortail shook his wings out again.

03:34:30.840 --> 03:34:32.639
Blue.

03:34:32.700 --> 03:34:33.780
Wow.

03:34:33.840 --> 03:34:35.639
I can't believe it's you.

03:34:35.700 --> 03:34:38.399
I mean, it's amazing that it's you.

03:34:38.459 --> 03:34:40.139
You, here.

03:34:40.200 --> 03:34:41.760
All kinds of amazing.

03:34:41.819 --> 03:34:44.700
He opened and closed his mouth a few

03:34:44.700 --> 03:34:46.680
times, as if trying to make all his

03:34:46.680 --> 03:34:47.639
muscles work again.

03:34:47.760 --> 03:34:52.319
That is, I mean, of all the dragons, I

03:34:52.319 --> 03:34:54.059
might have expected to come rescue me.

03:34:54.120 --> 03:34:55.020
He said.

03:34:55.139 --> 03:34:58.319
You and a strange little hive wing are

03:34:58.319 --> 03:35:00.659
probably the last on the list, but thank

03:35:00.659 --> 03:35:00.899
you.

03:35:00.959 --> 03:35:02.280
Did I say thank you?

03:35:02.399 --> 03:35:04.440
I've been thinking thank you very

03:35:04.440 --> 03:35:05.040
loudly.

03:35:05.100 --> 03:35:07.139
Probably should say it a few times.

03:35:07.260 --> 03:35:10.260
He touched Blue's shoulder with one of

03:35:10.260 --> 03:35:13.260
his talons, then let go, and gave an odd

03:35:13.260 --> 03:35:14.280
hop sideways.

03:35:14.340 --> 03:35:16.920
Sortail's whole body seemed to be

03:35:16.920 --> 03:35:18.239
vibrating just a little bit.

03:35:18.299 --> 03:35:20.760
Iu tried to get me away.

03:35:20.819 --> 03:35:23.399
Blue said, but we had to split up.

03:35:23.459 --> 03:35:25.139
Cricket saved me.

03:35:25.200 --> 03:35:27.719
Are you all right?

03:35:27.780 --> 03:35:30.120
Cricket asked Swordtail.

03:35:30.180 --> 03:35:32.459
What are you feeling right now?

03:35:32.520 --> 03:35:35.159
What happened to Luna?

03:35:35.219 --> 03:35:38.280
Swartail asked, all his manic energy

03:35:38.280 --> 03:35:39.899
suddenly focused on the question.

03:35:39.959 --> 03:35:41.879
Blue shook his head.

03:35:41.940 --> 03:35:43.799
I'm not sure.

03:35:43.860 --> 03:35:46.139
But we think they've taken her to where

03:35:46.139 --> 03:35:48.420
the queen keeps all her flame silks.

03:35:48.540 --> 03:35:51.360
We think it might be in or near Wasp

03:35:51.360 --> 03:35:51.780
Pive.

03:35:51.840 --> 03:35:54.600
So that's where we're going next.

03:35:54.659 --> 03:35:56.520
Cricket interjected.

03:35:56.579 --> 03:35:58.739
Blue blinked at her.

03:35:58.799 --> 03:36:01.620
That sure sounds like she's coming too.

03:36:01.680 --> 03:36:04.020
He didn't want to ask.

03:36:04.079 --> 03:36:07.139
He was afraid to jinx it, but he smiled

03:36:07.139 --> 03:36:09.360
at her when she looked his way, and she

03:36:09.360 --> 03:36:09.959
smiled back.

03:36:10.020 --> 03:36:13.860
I should get help, Sordell said.

03:36:13.920 --> 03:36:16.860
His tail had started lashing back and

03:36:16.860 --> 03:36:19.799
forth, like a whip, but he didn't seem to

03:36:19.799 --> 03:36:20.040
notice.

03:36:20.100 --> 03:36:23.100
His claws extended and closed.

03:36:23.159 --> 03:36:24.840
His ears flicked up and down.

03:36:24.899 --> 03:36:28.139
Even his antennae were fully unfurled and

03:36:28.139 --> 03:36:28.860
waving around.

03:36:28.920 --> 03:36:31.379
Help is a useful thing.

03:36:31.440 --> 03:36:33.659
There are dragons I can reach out to.

03:36:33.719 --> 03:36:35.760
The chrysalis?

03:36:35.819 --> 03:36:36.840
Cricket asked.

03:36:36.899 --> 03:36:38.459
How will you find them?

03:36:38.520 --> 03:36:39.600
What can they do?

03:36:39.719 --> 03:36:42.420
He narrowed his eyes at her.

03:36:42.479 --> 03:36:45.360
How do you know about the chrysalis?

03:36:45.479 --> 03:36:48.659
She doesn't, Blue said quickly.

03:36:48.719 --> 03:36:52.020
She knows as much as I do, which is

03:36:52.020 --> 03:36:52.620
pretty much nothing.

03:36:52.680 --> 03:36:55.680
Then it should stay that way.

03:36:55.739 --> 03:36:57.899
Swartail growled.

03:36:57.959 --> 03:37:00.719
His shoulders twitched, making his wings

03:37:00.719 --> 03:37:01.860
flutter up and back.

03:37:01.920 --> 03:37:03.479
Let's see.

03:37:03.540 --> 03:37:04.860
It would take a while.

03:37:04.920 --> 03:37:07.440
Leave a message, wait for a response.

03:37:07.559 --> 03:37:09.600
We'd have to find a safe place to hide.

03:37:09.659 --> 03:37:12.659
Blue doesn't have time to wait for other

03:37:12.659 --> 03:37:14.399
dragons, Cricket said.

03:37:14.520 --> 03:37:16.860
He needs to get as far away from this

03:37:16.860 --> 03:37:18.659
hive as possible before dawn.

03:37:18.719 --> 03:37:21.120
That's when the queen is going to take

03:37:21.120 --> 03:37:23.399
over everyone again and send them out

03:37:23.399 --> 03:37:24.239
looking for him.

03:37:24.239 --> 03:37:27.840
You can stay and contact the chrysalis if

03:37:27.840 --> 03:37:28.139
you want.

03:37:28.200 --> 03:37:29.159
Blue said.

03:37:29.219 --> 03:37:32.940
But we are leaving right now, Cricket

03:37:32.940 --> 03:37:33.360
finished.

03:37:33.420 --> 03:37:37.680
We are, Blue Thought, with a little glow

03:37:37.680 --> 03:37:38.340
of happiness.

03:37:38.399 --> 03:37:40.200
Cricket and me.

03:37:40.260 --> 03:37:43.860
To find Luna, Soretail asked.

03:37:43.920 --> 03:37:45.059
Blue nodded.

03:37:45.120 --> 03:37:46.799
Then I'm coming with you.

03:37:46.860 --> 03:37:47.819
He said.

03:37:47.879 --> 03:37:49.739
Yes, to save her.

03:37:49.799 --> 03:37:52.079
That is the most me thing to do.

03:37:52.200 --> 03:37:54.540
I am most definitely coming with you.

03:37:54.600 --> 03:37:57.959
He flexed his claws and bounced in place

03:37:57.959 --> 03:37:58.500
for a moment.

03:37:58.559 --> 03:38:01.799
And then Sortell suddenly ran at the

03:38:01.799 --> 03:38:04.020
stone pedestal and smashed his shoulder

03:38:04.020 --> 03:38:04.440
into it.

03:38:04.500 --> 03:38:07.739
Sore tail, Blue yelped.

03:38:07.799 --> 03:38:10.500
Soartail looked at him, grinning.

03:38:10.620 --> 03:38:13.200
Large cracks had appeared all along the

03:38:13.200 --> 03:38:13.559
stone.

03:38:13.620 --> 03:38:16.379
Look what I did, he said.

03:38:16.440 --> 03:38:18.180
I feel like I could knock over

03:38:18.180 --> 03:38:18.659
everything.

03:38:18.719 --> 03:38:21.000
All the columns, any building.

03:38:21.059 --> 03:38:22.260
The whole hive.

03:38:22.379 --> 03:38:25.319
Blue said with alarm.

03:38:25.379 --> 03:38:27.600
Cricket, is this normal?

03:38:27.659 --> 03:38:32.100
I have no idea, she said, wide eyed.

03:38:32.219 --> 03:38:35.040
What I gave him is sort of a stimulant

03:38:35.040 --> 03:38:37.680
and it does make the plants grow bigger

03:38:37.680 --> 03:38:38.159
and faster.

03:38:38.219 --> 03:38:40.920
I feel bigger.

03:38:40.979 --> 03:38:44.280
Swordtail declared, at a horrifying

03:38:44.280 --> 03:38:46.860
volume, I feel faster.

03:38:46.979 --> 03:38:49.620
He turned and sprinted away down the

03:38:49.620 --> 03:38:49.860
path.

03:38:49.920 --> 03:38:52.860
Uh-oh, Cricket said.

03:38:52.920 --> 03:38:55.799
Um, any chance he's always like this?

03:38:55.920 --> 03:38:58.680
No, Blue cried.

03:38:58.739 --> 03:39:00.540
This is definitely weird.

03:39:00.600 --> 03:39:02.639
Hmm, she said.

03:39:02.700 --> 03:39:04.620
How long do you think it'll last?

03:39:04.680 --> 03:39:06.420
How would I know?

03:39:06.540 --> 03:39:10.020
Crash when something up ahead of them.

03:39:10.079 --> 03:39:13.799
Thud, smash, ha, ha.

03:39:13.860 --> 03:39:15.899
Swordtail shouted.

03:39:15.959 --> 03:39:17.639
Blue bolted after his friend.

03:39:17.700 --> 03:39:19.739
Cricket close behind him.

03:39:19.799 --> 03:39:23.100
They found sword tail merrily lifting

03:39:23.100 --> 03:39:25.620
enormous rocks, and throwing them at the

03:39:25.620 --> 03:39:26.520
wall of the hive.

03:39:26.579 --> 03:39:30.180
Even paralyzed, the 2 nearest prisoners

03:39:30.180 --> 03:39:32.040
somehow managed to look alarmed.

03:39:32.159 --> 03:39:33.959
What are you doing?

03:39:34.020 --> 03:39:37.139
Blue yelped, catching Swordtail's arm.

03:39:37.200 --> 03:39:40.620
Making us a door, Swordtail answered.

03:39:40.680 --> 03:39:42.360
I'm in construction, you know?

03:39:42.420 --> 03:39:44.159
This is totally my job.

03:39:44.219 --> 03:39:47.760
He lifted another boulder, which looked

03:39:47.760 --> 03:39:49.680
much heavier than anything glue could

03:39:49.680 --> 03:39:51.659
have picked up and hurled it at the

03:39:51.659 --> 03:39:51.899
wall.

03:39:51.959 --> 03:39:54.780
The tree stuff was already splintered and

03:39:54.780 --> 03:39:57.120
cracked, with several small holes in it.

03:39:57.180 --> 03:40:00.239
Hey, grasshopper.

03:40:00.299 --> 03:40:03.120
Sortel shouted, making blue jump.

03:40:03.180 --> 03:40:05.280
Look how hard I'm working.

03:40:05.280 --> 03:40:06.600
Are you happy now?

03:40:06.659 --> 03:40:08.940
Swordtail.

03:40:09.000 --> 03:40:11.399
Please be quiet, Blue bagged.

03:40:11.459 --> 03:40:15.420
It's probably too late for that, Cricket

03:40:15.420 --> 03:40:18.299
said, glancing back along misbehavior's

03:40:18.299 --> 03:40:18.540
way.

03:40:18.600 --> 03:40:22.079
Take that, Sortell yelled.

03:40:22.139 --> 03:40:24.659
He heaved an entire stone tablet out of

03:40:24.659 --> 03:40:26.760
the ground and threw it as hard as he

03:40:26.760 --> 03:40:27.000
could.

03:40:27.059 --> 03:40:29.819
It smashed right through the side of the

03:40:29.819 --> 03:40:32.040
hive and plummeted out of sight.

03:40:32.100 --> 03:40:34.979
Blue stared at the gaping hole that was

03:40:34.979 --> 03:40:35.280
left.

03:40:35.340 --> 03:40:38.340
Fragments of tree stuff feathered out on

03:40:38.340 --> 03:40:41.159
all sides of it, and wood smelling dust

03:40:41.159 --> 03:40:42.120
hazed the air.

03:40:42.180 --> 03:40:46.620
This is vandalism, he thought, and

03:40:46.620 --> 03:40:48.299
destruction of hive property.

03:40:48.360 --> 03:40:50.579
There are definitely rules about this.

03:40:50.639 --> 03:40:54.420
Possibly on that tablet, Thorotel just

03:40:54.420 --> 03:40:55.739
hurled through the wall.

03:40:55.799 --> 03:40:58.079
On the other side of the hole.

03:40:58.139 --> 03:41:00.659
He could see clouds rimmed with moonlight

03:41:00.659 --> 03:41:03.420
and the far off lights of another hive.

03:41:03.479 --> 03:41:06.180
Where other dragons are having a

03:41:06.180 --> 03:41:08.520
perfectly normal evening that doesn't

03:41:08.520 --> 03:41:10.620
involve getting painted, hiding from

03:41:10.620 --> 03:41:12.959
soldiers, or watching their friends lose

03:41:12.959 --> 03:41:13.500
their minds.

03:41:13.559 --> 03:41:15.780
Let's go.

03:41:15.899 --> 03:41:18.959
Swartell cried, charging toward the

03:41:18.959 --> 03:41:19.260
opening.

03:41:19.319 --> 03:41:22.620
I can't, Blue said.

03:41:22.680 --> 03:41:23.219
We're too high.

03:41:23.280 --> 03:41:24.899
I don't have wings, remember?

03:41:24.959 --> 03:41:28.500
I'll carry you, Soratel said

03:41:28.500 --> 03:41:29.340
enthusiastically.

03:41:29.399 --> 03:41:30.840
I can do it.

03:41:30.899 --> 03:41:32.940
I'm as strong as 10 dragons.

03:41:33.059 --> 03:41:35.760
I can carry both of you at the same

03:41:35.760 --> 03:41:36.000
time.

03:41:36.120 --> 03:41:38.219
Absolutely not.

03:41:38.280 --> 03:41:40.500
Thank you, Cricket said.

03:41:40.559 --> 03:41:42.899
My own 2 wings work perfectly fine.

03:41:42.959 --> 03:41:45.420
She turned toward Blue.

03:41:45.719 --> 03:41:48.180
I think we have to go out this way, don't

03:41:48.180 --> 03:41:48.360
you?

03:41:48.420 --> 03:41:49.620
We can't go back.

03:41:49.680 --> 03:41:51.719
There must be guards coming to

03:41:51.719 --> 03:41:52.979
investigate the noise.

03:41:53.040 --> 03:41:55.680
Are you sure you want to come?

03:41:55.680 --> 03:41:56.940
Blue said.

03:41:57.000 --> 03:41:58.620
You could go home now.

03:41:58.680 --> 03:42:01.260
You could be safe and stay out of this

03:42:01.260 --> 03:42:01.680
whole mess.

03:42:01.799 --> 03:42:05.100
And never find out what happens.

03:42:05.219 --> 03:42:08.280
She adjusted her glasses and smiled at

03:42:08.280 --> 03:42:08.700
him.

03:42:08.760 --> 03:42:09.959
Are you kidding me?

03:42:10.020 --> 03:42:13.379
Sore tail flapped his wings at blue.

03:42:13.500 --> 03:42:16.920
Time to fly, short stuff, he shouted.

03:42:16.979 --> 03:42:19.440
By all the hives, sore tail.

03:42:19.500 --> 03:42:20.819
What is happening to you?

03:42:20.879 --> 03:42:22.139
Blue asked.

03:42:22.260 --> 03:42:26.399
Instead of answering, Sortell shot a long

03:42:26.399 --> 03:42:29.280
strand of silk at him and snared Blue's

03:42:29.280 --> 03:42:29.579
shoulders.

03:42:29.700 --> 03:42:33.180
He tugged blue closer, and wove several

03:42:33.180 --> 03:42:35.639
more strands into a quick harness to bind

03:42:35.639 --> 03:42:36.059
them together.

03:42:36.120 --> 03:42:40.020
Blue noticed that Swordtail's silk had

03:42:40.020 --> 03:42:42.420
also turned a strange new shade of pale

03:42:42.420 --> 03:42:43.260
green.

03:42:43.319 --> 03:42:45.899
I'm not sure this is a good idea.

03:42:45.959 --> 03:42:49.799
Blue said nervously, as Sortail clasped

03:42:49.799 --> 03:42:51.719
his front talons around Blue's chest.

03:42:51.780 --> 03:42:53.459
This close to the hole.

03:42:53.520 --> 03:42:56.819
He could see the rippling grass far, far

03:42:56.819 --> 03:42:57.600
below him.

03:42:57.659 --> 03:43:01.079
I'm not that light, and it's a long way

03:43:01.079 --> 03:43:01.500
down.

03:43:01.620 --> 03:43:05.940
To the moons, swordtail hollered, leaping

03:43:05.940 --> 03:43:06.600
out into the air.

03:43:06.659 --> 03:43:09.840
Blue felt a terrifying, plummeting

03:43:09.840 --> 03:43:12.299
feeling in his stomach, as they lurched

03:43:12.299 --> 03:43:15.540
awkwardly for a moment, down and down

03:43:15.540 --> 03:43:18.059
again toward the savannah, and then

03:43:18.059 --> 03:43:21.659
suddenly up, sideways, and up, and

03:43:21.659 --> 03:43:24.600
finally away, beating forward at a steady

03:43:24.600 --> 03:43:25.260
pace.

03:43:25.500 --> 03:43:28.079
The wind whipped and blew his face.

03:43:28.139 --> 03:43:31.139
It was cold out here in the dark, after

03:43:31.139 --> 03:43:33.000
the close warmth of the hive.

03:43:33.059 --> 03:43:35.520
He peeked backward and saw cricket

03:43:35.520 --> 03:43:37.079
soaring alongside them.

03:43:37.139 --> 03:43:38.340
Get it?

03:43:38.399 --> 03:43:41.940
Sortails said conversationally, Because

03:43:41.940 --> 03:43:45.239
Luna is like lunar, which means moons.

03:43:45.299 --> 03:43:49.139
So, to the moons is like, to Luna, but in

03:43:49.139 --> 03:43:49.559
code.

03:43:49.620 --> 03:43:51.059
So, awesome.

03:43:51.120 --> 03:43:52.559
I thought that was clever.

03:43:52.620 --> 03:43:56.219
He kept chattering as he flew, as though

03:43:56.219 --> 03:43:57.840
he couldn't stop the flow of words coming

03:43:57.840 --> 03:43:58.440
out of him.

03:43:58.500 --> 03:44:02.459
Blue looked back again, this time at the

03:44:02.459 --> 03:44:05.100
vast shape of cicada hive, and the

03:44:05.100 --> 03:44:07.079
silvery tangles of the webs far

03:44:07.079 --> 03:44:07.860
overhead.

03:44:07.920 --> 03:44:11.280
He thought of Burnet and Silverspot

03:44:11.280 --> 03:44:13.920
sleeping alone in their cell for the 1st

03:44:13.920 --> 03:44:15.600
time since Luna had hatched.

03:44:15.659 --> 03:44:17.100
Could they sleep?

03:44:17.159 --> 03:44:19.319
Or were they lying awake?

03:44:19.379 --> 03:44:22.079
Wishing they'd been wrong about Admiral?

03:44:22.139 --> 03:44:24.540
Worrying about Luna and Blue?

03:44:24.600 --> 03:44:27.239
Will I ever see them again?

03:44:27.299 --> 03:44:30.780
His home was disappearing behind him.

03:44:30.840 --> 03:44:32.700
He didn't know what was ahead.

03:44:32.760 --> 03:44:35.520
He only knew he couldn't turn back.

03:44:35.579 --> 03:44:38.159
And so he looked out toward the dark

03:44:38.159 --> 03:44:40.860
Savannah, and let his friends carry him

03:44:40.860 --> 03:44:42.299
forward into the night.

03:44:42.360 --> 03:44:46.559
Part two.

03:44:46.620 --> 03:44:49.020
Out of the hive.

03:44:49.079 --> 03:44:52.079
Chapter 13.

03:44:52.260 --> 03:44:55.620
They flew all the rest of that night

03:44:55.620 --> 03:44:58.559
swooping low to the savannah whenever the

03:44:58.559 --> 03:45:01.200
moons breached the clouds, just in case

03:45:01.200 --> 03:45:02.399
anyone was watching for them.

03:45:02.459 --> 03:45:06.059
Sortell charted a course straight across

03:45:06.059 --> 03:45:08.940
the circle toward Wasp Hive, which made

03:45:08.940 --> 03:45:11.280
sense, but quickly brought them to a part

03:45:11.280 --> 03:45:13.799
of the Savannah, where dragons rarely

03:45:13.799 --> 03:45:14.159
ventured.

03:45:14.219 --> 03:45:18.000
The grass was long and wild, and shapes

03:45:18.000 --> 03:45:21.719
prowled below them, growls, and shrieks

03:45:21.719 --> 03:45:24.479
and curling hoots rose from the darkness

03:45:24.479 --> 03:45:26.700
slicing through the constant hum of the

03:45:26.700 --> 03:45:27.239
insects.

03:45:27.299 --> 03:45:31.379
Once he got over his fear, Blue found the

03:45:31.379 --> 03:45:34.020
rhythm of sword tails' wings, lulling him

03:45:34.020 --> 03:45:35.159
into a kind of doze.

03:45:35.219 --> 03:45:39.360
His friend seemed tireless, soaring on

03:45:39.360 --> 03:45:40.620
and on without stopping.

03:45:40.739 --> 03:45:43.739
Blue hoped cricket was all right.

03:45:43.799 --> 03:45:46.860
He tried to call to her a few times, but

03:45:46.860 --> 03:45:48.239
the wind whipped his voice away.

03:45:48.299 --> 03:45:52.739
After a long time, Blue noticed that he

03:45:52.739 --> 03:45:54.600
could see the outlines of shrubs below

03:45:54.600 --> 03:45:56.520
him, gray and ghostly.

03:45:56.579 --> 03:45:59.940
He glanced up and saw an expanding band

03:45:59.940 --> 03:46:02.280
of pale yellow light along the edge of

03:46:02.280 --> 03:46:02.940
the sky.

03:46:03.000 --> 03:46:05.520
It's almost morning.

03:46:05.579 --> 03:46:07.680
He called out to Swordtail.

03:46:07.739 --> 03:46:09.840
We should hide for the day.

03:46:09.899 --> 03:46:12.719
That's what I think, Sortail answered.

03:46:12.780 --> 03:46:15.239
It's still half a day's journey to Wasp

03:46:15.239 --> 03:46:17.219
Hive, and they'll be out looking for us

03:46:17.219 --> 03:46:19.680
in force today, and it would be better to

03:46:19.680 --> 03:46:20.639
get there at night anyway.

03:46:20.700 --> 03:46:24.120
Night, an excellent time of day for

03:46:24.120 --> 03:46:24.780
heroics.

03:46:24.840 --> 03:46:28.739
Cricket, Blue called, trying to twist

03:46:28.739 --> 03:46:29.819
around to see her.

03:46:29.879 --> 03:46:33.659
Hide, she panted behind them.

03:46:33.719 --> 03:46:36.360
She looked exhausted, but her wings beat

03:46:36.360 --> 03:46:37.200
valiantly.

03:46:37.200 --> 03:46:39.059
Yes, good.

03:46:39.120 --> 03:46:40.139
Where?

03:46:40.260 --> 03:46:42.059
Where?

03:46:42.120 --> 03:46:45.540
Blue studied the Savannah as far as he

03:46:45.540 --> 03:46:46.500
could see in each direction.

03:46:46.559 --> 03:46:50.399
The yellow grass rippled, broken only by

03:46:50.399 --> 03:46:53.340
gnarled little shrubs, patches of barren

03:46:53.340 --> 03:46:56.040
dirt, or the winding path of dry river

03:46:56.040 --> 03:46:56.700
beds.

03:46:56.760 --> 03:46:59.100
The rainy season was coming soon.

03:46:59.159 --> 03:47:01.379
So the ground below them was dry.

03:47:01.500 --> 03:47:04.440
There was nothing large enough to hide in

03:47:04.440 --> 03:47:06.059
or under, or behind.

03:47:06.180 --> 03:47:09.360
Hunting parties of hive wings would spot

03:47:09.360 --> 03:47:10.860
them from the air with no trouble at

03:47:10.860 --> 03:47:11.100
all.

03:47:11.159 --> 03:47:14.100
Disguise ourselves as grass?

03:47:14.159 --> 03:47:17.520
Soitel suggested, disguise ourselves as

03:47:17.520 --> 03:47:18.059
shrubs.

03:47:18.120 --> 03:47:21.180
Disguise ourselves as elephants.

03:47:21.239 --> 03:47:22.200
That's it.

03:47:22.260 --> 03:47:23.579
Let's do it.

03:47:23.639 --> 03:47:26.579
That stuff still hasn't worn off.

03:47:26.639 --> 03:47:28.559
Blue called to Cricket.

03:47:28.620 --> 03:47:30.780
Or I can build us a web.

03:47:30.899 --> 03:47:35.399
Swartell said, a giant web, and we hide

03:47:35.399 --> 03:47:37.319
underneath it, and they'll think there

03:47:37.319 --> 03:47:39.840
must be some massively enormous spiders

03:47:39.840 --> 03:47:41.100
colonizing the Savannah.

03:47:41.159 --> 03:47:43.319
This will totally work.

03:47:43.379 --> 03:47:50.340
Let's fly a bit farther, Cricket said

03:47:50.340 --> 03:47:50.940
between breaths.

03:47:51.059 --> 03:47:52.620
Try to find somewhere.

03:47:52.680 --> 03:47:55.500
Blue barely blinked.

03:47:55.559 --> 03:47:57.479
He was staring so intently at the

03:47:57.479 --> 03:47:58.020
ground.

03:47:58.079 --> 03:48:01.200
Off to his left, he saw a herd of teeny

03:48:01.200 --> 03:48:03.959
tiny deer with enormous ears bounding

03:48:03.959 --> 03:48:06.239
through the grass, which was shorter and

03:48:06.239 --> 03:48:07.139
scrubbier here.

03:48:07.200 --> 03:48:10.559
A tall, long necked gray and white bird

03:48:10.559 --> 03:48:13.559
stalked slowly along one of the sun baked

03:48:13.559 --> 03:48:16.260
river beds, ignoring the smaller birds

03:48:16.260 --> 03:48:18.840
that perched on its back, or flew down to

03:48:18.840 --> 03:48:19.979
poke the barren soil.

03:48:20.100 --> 03:48:22.440
There was nowhere to hide.

03:48:22.500 --> 03:48:26.639
Blue's heart sank. as they flew on, and

03:48:26.639 --> 03:48:27.719
the sky grew brighter.

03:48:27.780 --> 03:48:29.579
This was a mistake.

03:48:29.639 --> 03:48:32.340
The savannah was the worst place they

03:48:32.340 --> 03:48:32.819
could have gone.

03:48:32.879 --> 03:48:36.719
And then, as the sun peaked over the

03:48:36.719 --> 03:48:39.959
horizon, he saw the vast looming shape of

03:48:39.959 --> 03:48:43.139
a hive in the distance, wasp hive.

03:48:43.200 --> 03:48:45.899
His heart kicked hard in his chest.

03:48:46.020 --> 03:48:50.579
The home of Queen Wasp, the grandest and

03:48:50.579 --> 03:48:53.520
wealthiest of all the hives, the location

03:48:53.520 --> 03:48:55.920
of the temple, where the book of clear

03:48:55.920 --> 03:48:58.500
sight was worshiped, and protected by

03:48:58.500 --> 03:49:01.319
generation after generation of librarians

03:49:01.319 --> 03:49:06.239
a hive full of power, and soldiers, and

03:49:06.239 --> 03:49:09.239
secrets, where the queen might be hiding

03:49:09.239 --> 03:49:09.719
his sister.

03:49:09.780 --> 03:49:14.159
And his father, and other flame silks.

03:49:14.219 --> 03:49:16.920
Are we really doing this?

03:49:16.979 --> 03:49:20.399
He thought, with sudden crashing anxiety

03:49:20.399 --> 03:49:22.500
what are we doing?

03:49:22.620 --> 03:49:26.219
Do we think we can sneak into Wasp Hive?

03:49:26.280 --> 03:49:28.920
of all places, and find something the

03:49:28.920 --> 03:49:30.479
queen wants to stay hidden?

03:49:30.540 --> 03:49:34.319
Sortel banged around, making Blue's

03:49:34.319 --> 03:49:36.120
stomach drop, and swooped back to

03:49:36.120 --> 03:49:36.540
cricket.

03:49:36.600 --> 03:49:39.840
We shouldn't get any closer, he said.

03:49:39.899 --> 03:49:42.479
She might send out hunters from her own

03:49:42.479 --> 03:49:44.879
hive to search for us too, if she's

03:49:44.879 --> 03:49:47.520
paranoid, which she is, which she should

03:49:47.520 --> 03:49:50.819
be because He cut himself off abruptly

03:49:50.819 --> 03:49:52.440
and nodded a few times.

03:49:52.500 --> 03:49:55.500
Because reasons.

03:49:55.680 --> 03:49:57.780
But where?

03:49:57.899 --> 03:49:59.940
Crickets spiraled in the air.

03:50:00.000 --> 03:50:01.860
There's nothing out here.

03:50:01.920 --> 03:50:04.020
I didn't know it would be like this.

03:50:04.079 --> 03:50:07.979
She looked tired and worried, and Blue

03:50:07.979 --> 03:50:10.079
felt a surge of guilt for dragging her

03:50:10.079 --> 03:50:10.739
into his mess.

03:50:10.799 --> 03:50:13.500
He tried to imagine what it must be like

03:50:13.500 --> 03:50:15.600
for her, far from home.

03:50:15.659 --> 03:50:19.559
Helping 2 runaway silk wings, knowing how

03:50:19.559 --> 03:50:21.180
much trouble she'd be in if she was

03:50:21.180 --> 03:50:21.659
caught with them.

03:50:21.780 --> 03:50:24.239
Is that something over there?

03:50:24.299 --> 03:50:26.399
Blue asked, pointing.

03:50:26.459 --> 03:50:29.459
There was a dark slash in the unending

03:50:29.459 --> 03:50:31.860
sea of cracked earth and yellow grass.

03:50:31.979 --> 03:50:33.659
Let's find out.

03:50:33.719 --> 03:50:35.459
Let's find out.

03:50:35.520 --> 03:50:36.899
Swartell said.

03:50:36.959 --> 03:50:39.719
He beat his wings and sword toward it.

03:50:39.780 --> 03:50:41.639
It's a hole.

03:50:41.700 --> 03:50:44.219
Blue thought. as they drew closer.

03:50:44.280 --> 03:50:46.680
A really big hole.

03:50:46.739 --> 03:50:49.379
It looked as though the earth had

03:50:49.379 --> 03:50:51.719
suddenly dropped away here. a long time

03:50:51.719 --> 03:50:55.559
ago, leaving a cavernous shaft lined with

03:50:55.559 --> 03:50:58.620
moss covered rocks, and long green plants

03:50:58.620 --> 03:51:00.299
trying to clamber out into the sunshine.

03:51:00.360 --> 03:51:03.000
It was impossible to see the bottom.

03:51:03.059 --> 03:51:06.000
Even when they landed on the rim, and

03:51:06.000 --> 03:51:07.379
tried to peer down into it.

03:51:07.440 --> 03:51:10.680
Outcroppings of rock blocked most of

03:51:10.680 --> 03:51:13.020
their view, and where they could see past

03:51:13.020 --> 03:51:13.979
those.

03:51:14.040 --> 03:51:15.959
All they saw was more darkness

03:51:15.959 --> 03:51:18.479
disappearing down and down.

03:51:18.600 --> 03:51:22.440
Sortail used his claws to cut away the

03:51:22.440 --> 03:51:23.940
silk connecting him and Blue.

03:51:24.059 --> 03:51:27.899
Blue took a few wobbly steps, shaking out

03:51:27.899 --> 03:51:29.819
his legs, and trying to get the feeling

03:51:29.819 --> 03:51:30.540
back into them.

03:51:30.659 --> 03:51:32.579
Are you all right?

03:51:32.639 --> 03:51:34.379
He asked Cricket.

03:51:34.440 --> 03:51:36.659
I was crouching on the edge of the

03:51:36.659 --> 03:51:39.360
sinkhole, holding her glasses on with one

03:51:39.360 --> 03:51:40.979
talon while she peered down.

03:51:41.040 --> 03:51:43.739
Absolutely, she said.

03:51:43.799 --> 03:51:45.479
What is this?

03:51:45.540 --> 03:51:47.520
How deep do you think it goes?

03:51:47.579 --> 03:51:48.780
What to the bottom?

03:51:48.840 --> 03:51:50.100
How did it get this way?

03:51:50.159 --> 03:51:52.500
Have you ever seen anything like this?

03:51:52.559 --> 03:51:55.979
I haven't been out on the savannah much

03:51:55.979 --> 03:51:56.399
either?

03:51:56.459 --> 03:51:57.239
He admitted.

03:51:57.299 --> 03:51:59.700
I didn't know it had sinkholes.

03:51:59.819 --> 03:52:01.920
Are we going down it?

03:52:02.040 --> 03:52:04.799
she asked, turning to SwordTail.

03:52:04.860 --> 03:52:05.940
Can we?

03:52:06.000 --> 03:52:09.360
Her eyes were shining, as though her

03:52:09.360 --> 03:52:11.100
tiredness had evaporated in the

03:52:11.100 --> 03:52:12.360
excitement of a new discovery.

03:52:12.420 --> 03:52:16.620
I don't know, he said, hopping from one

03:52:16.620 --> 03:52:18.299
foot to another with a restless energy.

03:52:18.360 --> 03:52:21.180
This seems like the most obvious place to

03:52:21.180 --> 03:52:24.059
hide, so I assume they'll check here, and

03:52:24.059 --> 03:52:25.559
then we'll be trapped to the bottom of a

03:52:25.559 --> 03:52:26.940
hole with no way to escape.

03:52:27.000 --> 03:52:29.459
I still think my elephant plan is the

03:52:29.459 --> 03:52:29.639
best.

03:52:29.700 --> 03:52:31.260
Elephants are great.

03:52:31.319 --> 03:52:34.620
I can look like an elephant, no problem.

03:52:34.680 --> 03:52:38.520
He struck an odd, dramatic pose, which

03:52:38.520 --> 03:52:39.899
blue guest was supposed to look

03:52:39.899 --> 03:52:41.040
elephantesque.

03:52:41.159 --> 03:52:43.020
What do you think?

03:52:43.139 --> 03:52:44.760
Cricket asked Blue.

03:52:44.819 --> 03:52:48.120
Sortel had a point, but where else could

03:52:48.120 --> 03:52:48.600
they hide?

03:52:48.659 --> 03:52:51.420
He turned to look over his shoulder at

03:52:51.420 --> 03:52:53.579
the distant shape of Wasp Hive.

03:52:53.639 --> 03:52:56.579
For a moment, he thought his vision had

03:52:56.579 --> 03:52:57.479
gone blurry.

03:52:57.540 --> 03:53:00.780
Then he thought, fleetingly, that a swarm

03:53:00.780 --> 03:53:02.639
of insects had surrounded the hive.

03:53:02.700 --> 03:53:06.659
But finally, with a chill of terror, he

03:53:06.659 --> 03:53:09.180
realized that the buzzing motion around

03:53:09.180 --> 03:53:11.819
the city came from the wings of dragons

03:53:11.819 --> 03:53:14.940
pouring out of every window and door, and

03:53:14.940 --> 03:53:16.860
shaking the webs with the wind they

03:53:16.860 --> 03:53:17.159
raised.

03:53:17.219 --> 03:53:18.959
Dawn was here.

03:53:19.020 --> 03:53:21.120
The hunt had begun.

03:53:21.180 --> 03:53:26.100
We go down, he said, quickly, right now.

03:53:26.159 --> 03:53:28.739
Cricket didn't hesitate.

03:53:28.799 --> 03:53:31.200
She dove over the edge and vanished.

03:53:31.260 --> 03:53:34.260
Sortell hooked his front talons under

03:53:34.260 --> 03:53:36.479
Blue's arms again, and leaped off as

03:53:36.479 --> 03:53:36.659
well.

03:53:36.719 --> 03:53:40.620
They dropped down and down, pushing off

03:53:40.620 --> 03:53:42.899
from the craggy lichen covered walls when

03:53:42.899 --> 03:53:45.180
they got too close, and maneuvering

03:53:45.180 --> 03:53:46.860
around bulbous outcroppings.

03:53:46.920 --> 03:53:49.799
The air got cooler and more damp as they

03:53:49.799 --> 03:53:50.280
descended.

03:53:50.340 --> 03:53:53.639
The shaft was narrow, leaving barely

03:53:53.639 --> 03:53:55.799
enough room in places for Soretail to

03:53:55.799 --> 03:53:56.700
keep his wings spread.

03:53:56.760 --> 03:54:00.299
What if there is no bottom to this hole?

03:54:00.360 --> 03:54:01.860
Blue worried?

03:54:01.920 --> 03:54:04.440
Or what do the hive wings get here before

03:54:04.440 --> 03:54:05.399
we find the bottom?

03:54:05.459 --> 03:54:08.399
Did they know about this sinkhole?

03:54:08.459 --> 03:54:10.920
How long before they came to search it?

03:54:10.979 --> 03:54:15.420
Finally, below his claws, Blue saw the

03:54:15.420 --> 03:54:17.399
rocks converge onto a kind of ground.

03:54:17.459 --> 03:54:20.819
Although it was really just more rock, but

03:54:20.819 --> 03:54:23.040
at least he could stand on it, and it

03:54:23.040 --> 03:54:24.540
seemed to be the bottom of the hole.

03:54:24.600 --> 03:54:28.139
Sortail let him down gently, and hopped

03:54:28.139 --> 03:54:29.879
onto a ledge to stretch his wings.

03:54:29.940 --> 03:54:33.120
Blue glanced up at the tiny strip of

03:54:33.120 --> 03:54:35.639
sunlight far overhead, then around for

03:54:35.639 --> 03:54:36.059
cricket.

03:54:36.120 --> 03:54:39.780
The rock under his feet slanted down and

03:54:39.780 --> 03:54:42.180
away from the shaft into a dark tunnel.

03:54:42.239 --> 03:54:45.059
It was the only way Cricket could have

03:54:45.059 --> 03:54:47.219
gone, so he followed uneasily.

03:54:47.280 --> 03:54:51.120
After a few steps, the tunnel widened

03:54:51.120 --> 03:54:54.180
into a cave, although by now, the light

03:54:54.180 --> 03:54:55.979
was so dim that he couldn't tell how big

03:54:55.979 --> 03:55:00.540
it was, he heard the faint drip, drop, of

03:55:00.540 --> 03:55:01.860
water, somewhere up ahead.

03:55:01.920 --> 03:55:04.920
Cricket, he whispered.

03:55:04.979 --> 03:55:06.360
Right here.

03:55:06.420 --> 03:55:09.780
She materialized out of the dark and

03:55:09.780 --> 03:55:11.280
brushed his shoulder with her wing.

03:55:11.399 --> 03:55:15.600
This cave is enormous, and watch your

03:55:15.600 --> 03:55:17.700
step, because there's a lake that starts

03:55:17.700 --> 03:55:20.100
a little ways down this slope, a lake

03:55:20.100 --> 03:55:22.020
blue, under the savannah.

03:55:22.079 --> 03:55:23.399
Would you have guessed?

03:55:23.579 --> 03:55:24.659
Isn't that wild?

03:55:24.719 --> 03:55:26.819
And there's something else strange?

03:55:26.879 --> 03:55:28.020
Come see.

03:55:28.079 --> 03:55:29.940
Or, I guess, feel.

03:55:30.000 --> 03:55:32.159
Seeing isn't really an option down here.

03:55:32.219 --> 03:55:35.459
She nudged him through the dark until he

03:55:35.459 --> 03:55:38.280
felt water lapping at his claws, and then

03:55:38.280 --> 03:55:41.100
a few steps later, something bumped

03:55:41.100 --> 03:55:41.760
against his leg.

03:55:41.760 --> 03:55:44.879
He jumped back, thinking it was alive.

03:55:44.940 --> 03:55:48.360
The cricket reached for it, and guided it

03:55:48.360 --> 03:55:50.819
into his talons, so he could feel that it

03:55:50.819 --> 03:55:53.280
was a large object, floating on the

03:55:53.280 --> 03:55:55.920
surface of the lake, and there was a rope

03:55:55.920 --> 03:55:58.620
tied to one end of it, which led to a

03:55:58.620 --> 03:56:00.540
stalagmite that jutted from the rocky

03:56:00.540 --> 03:56:00.840
floor.

03:56:00.899 --> 03:56:05.639
A rope, which meant someone had been here

03:56:05.639 --> 03:56:06.120
before them.

03:56:06.239 --> 03:56:08.520
What do you think it is?

03:56:08.579 --> 03:56:10.440
She whispered to him.

03:56:10.500 --> 03:56:12.479
I have no idea.

03:56:12.540 --> 03:56:14.100
He whispered back.

03:56:14.159 --> 03:56:17.579
Someone must have left it like this. she

03:56:17.579 --> 03:56:17.819
said.

03:56:17.879 --> 03:56:21.360
Maybe to carry things across the lake.

03:56:21.420 --> 03:56:24.180
But why not just fly across with whatever

03:56:24.180 --> 03:56:25.139
they had to carry?

03:56:25.200 --> 03:56:27.420
This is so mysterious.

03:56:27.479 --> 03:56:31.860
Blue heard the rustle of wings, as

03:56:31.860 --> 03:56:33.420
Soretailed ducked into the cave with

03:56:33.420 --> 03:56:33.600
them.

03:56:33.659 --> 03:56:37.139
I think I heard voices up above, he

03:56:37.139 --> 03:56:37.559
whispered.

03:56:37.680 --> 03:56:39.000
Can we go deeper?

03:56:39.059 --> 03:56:43.920
Let's see, Cricket whispered back, barely

03:56:43.920 --> 03:56:44.760
a breath on the air.

03:56:44.819 --> 03:56:48.059
They felt their way deeper into the cave

03:56:48.059 --> 03:56:50.579
staying close to the wall, and skirting

03:56:50.579 --> 03:56:51.659
the edge of the lake.

03:56:51.959 --> 03:56:55.379
Soon, that became impossible as they ran

03:56:55.379 --> 03:56:58.020
out of shoreline, and they had to wade

03:56:58.020 --> 03:57:00.420
into the cold, still silk of the water.

03:57:00.479 --> 03:57:04.319
It was terrifying, wading into the dark

03:57:04.319 --> 03:57:07.379
and ever deepening water, but not as

03:57:07.379 --> 03:57:09.000
terrifying as the thought of the hive

03:57:09.000 --> 03:57:09.840
wings behind them.

03:57:09.899 --> 03:57:13.559
Blue shivered as the water climbed up his

03:57:13.559 --> 03:57:16.979
legs, lapped at his underbelly, and soon

03:57:16.979 --> 03:57:18.780
covered his wing buds.

03:57:18.840 --> 03:57:21.360
He'd seen the ocean in the distance from

03:57:21.360 --> 03:57:23.879
the top of the webs, but he'd never been

03:57:23.879 --> 03:57:26.459
submerged in water, and he certainly had

03:57:26.459 --> 03:57:27.479
no idea how to swim.

03:57:27.540 --> 03:57:30.840
If the water got any deeper, he wasn't

03:57:30.840 --> 03:57:32.040
sure he'd be able to go on.

03:57:32.159 --> 03:57:36.479
There's a passage here, Cricket whispered

03:57:36.479 --> 03:57:39.120
or an alcove or something, I think.

03:57:39.180 --> 03:57:42.780
Ripples flickered around blue as cricket

03:57:42.780 --> 03:57:45.780
ducked away, then came back to tug on his

03:57:45.780 --> 03:57:45.899
arm.

03:57:46.020 --> 03:57:49.079
He held out his tail for sore tail to

03:57:49.079 --> 03:57:51.420
catch, then let Cricket guide him under a

03:57:51.420 --> 03:57:52.079
dip in the roof.

03:57:52.139 --> 03:57:55.319
Now he could feel walls on either side of

03:57:55.319 --> 03:57:58.319
him, and to his surprise, here and there

03:57:58.319 --> 03:58:00.540
he saw what looked like sticky trails of

03:58:00.540 --> 03:58:03.180
light webbing across the roof above, or

03:58:03.180 --> 03:58:04.500
sliding down the walls.

03:58:04.860 --> 03:58:07.440
Cricket paused, and brought her nose

03:58:07.440 --> 03:58:10.260
closer to one of these, studying it

03:58:10.260 --> 03:58:12.600
curiously for a moment before moving on.

03:58:12.659 --> 03:58:16.079
They waited forward for what felt like an

03:58:16.079 --> 03:58:16.620
eternity.

03:58:16.680 --> 03:58:20.219
And then the passage curved, and ahead of

03:58:20.219 --> 03:58:23.219
them, reflecting off the slick wet walls

03:58:23.219 --> 03:58:26.819
was the glow of firelight, blue froze

03:58:26.819 --> 03:58:28.799
touching cricket's wing.

03:58:28.920 --> 03:58:31.979
She stopped too, with a little gasp.

03:58:32.100 --> 03:58:33.780
Fire.

03:58:33.840 --> 03:58:35.340
Is this it?

03:58:35.399 --> 03:58:38.579
Did we find where Queen Wasp is hiding

03:58:38.579 --> 03:58:39.719
the flame silks?

03:58:39.780 --> 03:58:43.680
Or, What are we about to walk into?

03:58:43.799 --> 03:58:48.420
Chapter 14.

03:58:48.659 --> 03:58:53.340
Blue glanced back toward SwordTail, his

03:58:53.340 --> 03:58:55.020
face was dimly visible in the

03:58:55.020 --> 03:58:56.700
phosphorescent glow from the walls.

03:58:56.819 --> 03:59:00.239
Sortell edged past them to take the lead

03:59:00.239 --> 03:59:03.600
and they all inched forward, step by

03:59:03.600 --> 03:59:04.319
careful step.

03:59:04.379 --> 03:59:06.780
There was a cavern ahead.

03:59:06.840 --> 03:59:09.840
Stalactites bubbled down from a high

03:59:09.840 --> 03:59:10.440
ceiling.

03:59:10.500 --> 03:59:13.799
Streaks of orange and white marbled the

03:59:13.799 --> 03:59:16.440
stone walls, shot through with veins of

03:59:16.440 --> 03:59:18.120
glittering black and gold ore.

03:59:18.239 --> 03:59:21.120
The water lapped against the shore here

03:59:21.120 --> 03:59:23.700
before continuing into another, wider

03:59:23.700 --> 03:59:24.180
tunnel.

03:59:24.239 --> 03:59:27.479
Rock formations twisted up in shapes like

03:59:27.479 --> 03:59:30.120
dragon tails, making the cavern look like

03:59:30.120 --> 03:59:33.180
a weird forest of petrified trunks.

03:59:33.239 --> 03:59:35.459
The firelight wasn't coming from any

03:59:35.459 --> 03:59:37.020
flame silk dragons.

03:59:37.079 --> 03:59:39.840
It flickered from a small pile of burning

03:59:39.840 --> 03:59:43.379
sticks, not far from the water, and next

03:59:43.379 --> 03:59:45.719
to the fire, sitting with its back

03:59:45.719 --> 03:59:48.299
against one of the stalagmites, was a

03:59:48.299 --> 03:59:50.280
creature Blue had never seen in any

03:59:50.280 --> 03:59:51.659
animal studies in school.

03:59:51.780 --> 03:59:55.319
It looked a little bit like a monkey, but

03:59:55.319 --> 03:59:58.500
bigger, and not quite so hairy, apart

03:59:58.500 --> 04:00:00.780
from a patch of floppy brown fur on top

04:00:00.780 --> 04:00:01.200
of its head.

04:00:01.260 --> 04:00:04.559
It had nimble little paws, which were

04:00:04.559 --> 04:00:06.180
holding something that it was gazing at

04:00:06.180 --> 04:00:06.780
intently.

04:00:06.840 --> 04:00:09.239
Parts of it were wrapped in something

04:00:09.239 --> 04:00:12.239
like a cocoon made of jaguar fur, and

04:00:12.239 --> 04:00:13.200
deep red silk.

04:00:13.319 --> 04:00:17.159
At first, it didn't notice the 3 dragons

04:00:17.159 --> 04:00:18.360
emerging from the tunnel.

04:00:18.420 --> 04:00:20.819
It was too immersed in whatever it was

04:00:20.819 --> 04:00:21.239
looking at.

04:00:21.299 --> 04:00:24.299
Blue and Cricket exchanged wondering

04:00:24.299 --> 04:00:25.079
glances.

04:00:25.139 --> 04:00:28.680
She looked as bewildered as he felt, but

04:00:28.680 --> 04:00:29.700
also enchanted.

04:00:29.760 --> 04:00:32.760
Then Blue stepped on a rock that turned

04:00:32.760 --> 04:00:35.459
under his talons, and he lurched forward

04:00:35.459 --> 04:00:36.600
with a small splash.

04:00:36.659 --> 04:00:40.200
The creature's head popped up and its

04:00:40.200 --> 04:00:43.079
eyes, as brown and big in its face as

04:00:43.079 --> 04:00:46.620
crickets went wide, it jumped to its feet

04:00:46.620 --> 04:00:49.319
revealing that it stood on 2 paws instead

04:00:49.319 --> 04:00:51.719
of 4, dropped whatever it had been

04:00:51.719 --> 04:00:54.299
looking at, and drew a long knife from

04:00:54.299 --> 04:00:55.020
its cocoon.

04:00:55.079 --> 04:00:58.379
Blue and his friend stopped and stared at

04:00:58.379 --> 04:00:58.620
it.

04:00:58.680 --> 04:01:00.239
It stared at them.

04:01:00.299 --> 04:01:02.700
What is it thinking?

04:01:02.760 --> 04:01:04.020
Blue wondered.

04:01:04.139 --> 04:01:05.579
Can it think?

04:01:05.639 --> 04:01:07.739
What does it know about dragons?

04:01:07.799 --> 04:01:09.420
Is it just scared?

04:01:09.479 --> 04:01:11.280
Or is it having other emotions?

04:01:11.399 --> 04:01:13.979
What a sweet little face it has.

04:01:14.040 --> 04:01:15.840
Like a marmoset.

04:01:15.899 --> 04:01:18.479
But I've never seen a monkey with a knife

04:01:18.479 --> 04:01:18.840
before.

04:01:18.899 --> 04:01:22.799
Sometimes a monkey wandered up into the

04:01:22.799 --> 04:01:25.860
webs by accident, long black spidery

04:01:25.860 --> 04:01:28.680
limbs racing up the high vines, and out

04:01:28.680 --> 04:01:29.819
onto the silvery bridges.

04:01:29.879 --> 04:01:32.819
Blue remembered one that IO had played

04:01:32.819 --> 04:01:33.780
with for an entire day.

04:01:33.840 --> 04:01:36.840
She'd wanted to keep it, but her parents

04:01:36.840 --> 04:01:38.940
made her take it back to the Savannah and

04:01:38.940 --> 04:01:39.420
release it.

04:01:39.540 --> 04:01:42.059
They told her that if the hive wings

04:01:42.059 --> 04:01:44.579
found it, they might eat it, and that

04:01:44.579 --> 04:01:45.659
would be much more upsetting.

04:01:45.719 --> 04:01:47.819
It was hard to argue with that.

04:01:47.879 --> 04:01:51.059
This monkey's limbs seemed the wrong

04:01:51.059 --> 04:01:53.520
shape for climbing vines or swinging from

04:01:53.520 --> 04:01:56.639
trees, and its coiled energy was more

04:01:56.639 --> 04:01:59.399
like a panther's poised to spring at

04:01:59.399 --> 04:01:59.579
them.

04:01:59.639 --> 04:02:02.700
Do you really think it's going to try

04:02:02.700 --> 04:02:03.899
stabbing us with that thing?

04:02:04.020 --> 04:02:05.579
Cricket whispered.

04:02:05.700 --> 04:02:07.680
Her voice broke the spell.

04:02:07.739 --> 04:02:10.620
The creature spun around and fled between

04:02:10.620 --> 04:02:12.899
the stalagmites, disappearing through a

04:02:12.899 --> 04:02:14.280
crack in the wall behind it.

04:02:14.459 --> 04:02:16.799
Oh no, Cricket cried.

04:02:16.860 --> 04:02:18.659
Wait, come back.

04:02:18.780 --> 04:02:21.479
She floundered through the water up onto

04:02:21.479 --> 04:02:23.940
the shore, and scrambled after the little

04:02:23.940 --> 04:02:26.639
animal, but the crack was too small for a

04:02:26.639 --> 04:02:27.479
dragon to fit through.

04:02:27.540 --> 04:02:30.659
She crouched beside the opening, trying

04:02:30.659 --> 04:02:31.379
to peek inside.

04:02:31.500 --> 04:02:34.200
I promise we won't hurt you, little

04:02:34.200 --> 04:02:34.559
monkey.

04:02:34.680 --> 04:02:35.760
What are you?

04:02:35.819 --> 04:02:37.500
Please come back.

04:02:37.559 --> 04:02:40.979
That was really cute, Blue said.

04:02:41.040 --> 04:02:43.799
He waded onto the shore, carefully

04:02:43.799 --> 04:02:45.600
skirting the fire so he wouldn't

04:02:45.600 --> 04:02:46.559
accidentally put it out.

04:02:46.680 --> 04:02:49.020
After the darkness of the previous

04:02:49.020 --> 04:02:49.559
caves.

04:02:49.620 --> 04:02:52.620
It was nice to be able to see, and much

04:02:52.620 --> 04:02:54.659
warmer nearer the fire than in the lake.

04:02:54.719 --> 04:02:58.739
I thought it was freaky, Sortell said.

04:02:58.799 --> 04:03:00.180
Weird little thing.

04:03:00.299 --> 04:03:02.280
Did you see how it was looking at us?

04:03:02.340 --> 04:03:05.040
It was, I don't.

04:03:05.340 --> 04:03:08.219
He interrupted himself with an absolutely

04:03:08.219 --> 04:03:09.540
enormous yawn.

04:03:09.659 --> 04:03:13.920
I really want to know what it was, Cricket

04:03:13.920 --> 04:03:15.959
said, stamping one foot with

04:03:15.959 --> 04:03:16.440
frustration.

04:03:16.500 --> 04:03:19.739
I thought I'd studied all the flora and

04:03:19.739 --> 04:03:21.899
fauna around here, even the prehistoric

04:03:21.899 --> 04:03:22.079
stuff.

04:03:22.139 --> 04:03:24.659
I don't remember any pictures that looked

04:03:24.659 --> 04:03:25.139
like that.

04:03:25.200 --> 04:03:28.559
She tipped her head up, staring into

04:03:28.559 --> 04:03:30.420
space as though she was flipping through

04:03:30.420 --> 04:03:31.559
pages in her mind.

04:03:31.620 --> 04:03:36.120
Not a gorilla, not an orangutan, not a

04:03:36.120 --> 04:03:36.780
chimpanzee.

04:03:36.899 --> 04:03:38.940
What in the hive?

04:03:39.000 --> 04:03:41.700
Blue picked up the object the creature

04:03:41.700 --> 04:03:42.780
had been looking at.

04:03:42.840 --> 04:03:44.399
Oh, wow.

04:03:44.459 --> 04:03:47.040
Cricket, check this out.

04:03:47.100 --> 04:03:49.860
She wound her way back through the

04:03:49.860 --> 04:03:51.059
stalagmites toward him.

04:03:51.120 --> 04:03:53.520
He turned the thing over in his claws.

04:03:53.579 --> 04:03:55.739
The outside was flexible leather.

04:03:55.799 --> 04:03:58.620
The inside was many layers of smooth

04:03:58.620 --> 04:04:00.840
beaten paper, and there were little marks

04:04:00.840 --> 04:04:02.040
all over each page.

04:04:02.100 --> 04:04:03.659
What?

04:04:03.780 --> 04:04:06.299
Cricket said, astonished.

04:04:06.360 --> 04:04:08.760
She took it from him and flipped through

04:04:08.760 --> 04:04:09.659
it gently.

04:04:09.719 --> 04:04:11.579
Is this a book?

04:04:11.639 --> 04:04:13.200
It can be.

04:04:13.260 --> 04:04:16.379
Monkeys can't write books or read them.

04:04:16.440 --> 04:04:19.079
It's not a dragon book.

04:04:19.139 --> 04:04:20.940
It didn't come from a hive.

04:04:21.000 --> 04:04:22.260
Blue pointed out.

04:04:22.319 --> 04:04:24.059
Look how tiny it is.

04:04:24.120 --> 04:04:26.819
A dollhouse book?

04:04:26.879 --> 04:04:28.200
Cricket tried.

04:04:28.260 --> 04:04:30.540
Which the monkey found somewhere?

04:04:30.659 --> 04:04:32.520
She shook her head.

04:04:32.760 --> 04:04:34.079
No, you're right.

04:04:34.139 --> 04:04:36.059
This is the monkey's book.

04:04:36.180 --> 04:04:39.239
When we came in, I thought its expression

04:04:39.239 --> 04:04:40.260
looked familiar.

04:04:40.319 --> 04:04:42.479
And that's because it was reading.

04:04:42.540 --> 04:04:45.600
She hugged the book to her chest.

04:04:45.659 --> 04:04:48.540
Mystery animals in a cave under the

04:04:48.540 --> 04:04:49.200
savannah?

04:04:49.260 --> 04:04:50.520
Who can read?

04:04:50.579 --> 04:04:52.139
Blue.

04:04:52.200 --> 04:04:55.020
This is the biggest scientific discovery

04:04:55.020 --> 04:04:56.040
of our lifetime.

04:04:56.100 --> 04:04:58.440
I wouldn't have to be a gardener if I

04:04:58.440 --> 04:04:59.639
told the queen about this.

04:04:59.700 --> 04:05:02.579
I'm sure she'd let me change disciplines

04:05:02.579 --> 04:05:03.659
so I could study them.

04:05:03.719 --> 04:05:04.620
Don't you think?

04:05:04.680 --> 04:05:07.860
I'm a little worried she'd have them all

04:05:07.860 --> 04:05:10.139
rounded up and eaten, Blue admitted.

04:05:10.200 --> 04:05:11.940
Cricket looked horrified.

04:05:12.000 --> 04:05:13.260
No way.

04:05:13.319 --> 04:05:15.600
Is that really what you think of hive

04:05:15.600 --> 04:05:16.020
wings?

04:05:16.079 --> 04:05:18.479
That because we eat meat where heartless

04:05:18.479 --> 04:05:19.139
monsters?

04:05:19.200 --> 04:05:21.299
Do all silk wings think that?

04:05:21.360 --> 04:05:24.420
Um, Blue said.

04:05:24.479 --> 04:05:27.540
I mean, I wouldn't have said heartless

04:05:27.540 --> 04:05:30.299
but eating animals does seem kind of

04:05:30.299 --> 04:05:30.780
unnecessary.

04:05:30.840 --> 04:05:33.659
Cricket frowned and rubbed her head.

04:05:33.719 --> 04:05:36.479
As though she'd never spent any time

04:05:36.479 --> 04:05:38.520
thinking about whether eating animals was

04:05:38.520 --> 04:05:39.659
necessary.

04:05:39.719 --> 04:05:44.520
We don't eat everything, she said after a

04:05:44.520 --> 04:05:44.819
while.

04:05:44.879 --> 04:05:48.299
We don't eat lizards or snakes, since

04:05:48.299 --> 04:05:51.000
they're probably related to us, and I'm

04:05:51.000 --> 04:05:52.799
sure nobody would eat a species that can

04:05:52.799 --> 04:05:55.379
read and write, and might be as smart as

04:05:55.379 --> 04:05:55.680
we are.

04:05:55.739 --> 04:05:59.340
A loud rumbling sound broke into their

04:05:59.340 --> 04:06:01.319
conversation before Blue could answer.

04:06:01.379 --> 04:06:04.920
They both spun around in fright and

04:06:04.920 --> 04:06:07.260
discovered that it was the sound of sword

04:06:07.260 --> 04:06:08.520
tail snoring.

04:06:08.760 --> 04:06:11.520
The handsome silkwing was passed out by

04:06:11.520 --> 04:06:11.940
the fire.

04:06:12.059 --> 04:06:14.819
Wings flopped across the stone as though

04:06:14.819 --> 04:06:17.100
he'd staggered out of the water and

04:06:17.100 --> 04:06:19.319
collapsed in the 1st dry place he found.

04:06:19.440 --> 04:06:22.680
Well, that makes sense, Blue said.

04:06:22.739 --> 04:06:25.020
He did carry me halfway across the

04:06:25.020 --> 04:06:25.559
savannah.

04:06:25.620 --> 04:06:28.079
He probably needs to sleep for a week to

04:06:28.079 --> 04:06:28.379
recover.

04:06:28.440 --> 04:06:30.420
He caught himself.

04:06:30.479 --> 04:06:33.420
It was only a joke, but who knew what

04:06:33.420 --> 04:06:35.040
would happen to sword tail as the

04:06:35.040 --> 04:06:36.000
stimulant wore off.

04:06:36.059 --> 04:06:38.340
They couldn't afford to have sore tails

04:06:38.340 --> 04:06:39.299
sleep for a week.

04:06:39.420 --> 04:06:41.700
They needed to get to Luna as soon as

04:06:41.700 --> 04:06:44.280
possible. before she emerged from her

04:06:44.280 --> 04:06:45.360
cocoon all alone.

04:06:45.420 --> 04:06:48.180
Do you want to sleep too?

04:06:48.239 --> 04:06:49.559
Cricket asked.

04:06:49.680 --> 04:06:52.620
I can keep an eye out in case any hive

04:06:52.620 --> 04:06:54.719
wings come all the way down into the cave

04:06:54.719 --> 04:06:57.000
find a passage, and follow it through to

04:06:57.000 --> 04:06:57.239
here.

04:06:57.299 --> 04:07:00.360
Which I don't think they will.

04:07:00.420 --> 04:07:03.000
No, you should sleep.

04:07:03.059 --> 04:07:05.219
And I'll take 1st watch.

04:07:05.280 --> 04:07:06.540
Blue said.

04:07:06.600 --> 04:07:08.579
You were flying all night too.

04:07:08.639 --> 04:07:11.700
He could easily imagine how tired her

04:07:11.700 --> 04:07:12.420
wings must be.

04:07:12.540 --> 04:07:16.020
If he were in her scales, he knew he'd be

04:07:16.020 --> 04:07:18.180
feeling very anxious and emotional as

04:07:18.180 --> 04:07:20.639
well, given the stress of running away

04:07:20.639 --> 04:07:23.459
from her own tribe, and upending her safe

04:07:23.459 --> 04:07:26.399
hive wing life, surely even the

04:07:26.399 --> 04:07:28.200
excitement of discovering a new

04:07:28.200 --> 04:07:30.840
intelligent species couldn't outweigh the

04:07:30.840 --> 04:07:32.159
danger she'd put herself in.

04:07:32.219 --> 04:07:36.600
Which she did for me, to help me.

04:07:36.659 --> 04:07:41.100
All right, Cricket said with a yawn.

04:07:41.159 --> 04:07:43.979
If you're really sure, I wouldn't mind

04:07:43.979 --> 04:07:44.940
sleeping a little bit.

04:07:45.000 --> 04:07:46.680
Of course.

04:07:46.739 --> 04:07:49.920
He watched her stretch her wings and curl

04:07:49.920 --> 04:07:52.379
up on the rock, close enough for him to

04:07:52.379 --> 04:07:54.059
touch her talons if he needed to wake

04:07:54.059 --> 04:07:54.299
her.

04:07:54.360 --> 04:07:58.020
Her orange gold scales rose and fell

04:07:58.020 --> 04:08:00.540
slower and slower as she drifted off to

04:08:00.540 --> 04:08:00.780
sleep.

04:08:00.840 --> 04:08:04.079
The firelight flickered little shadows

04:08:04.079 --> 04:08:06.540
across her back, as though the ink blot

04:08:06.540 --> 04:08:08.700
splatter patterns were spreading, and

04:08:08.700 --> 04:08:10.020
shrinking, and dancing.

04:08:10.079 --> 04:08:13.620
Maybe she's not as scared as I would be

04:08:13.620 --> 04:08:14.819
he thought.

04:08:14.879 --> 04:08:16.379
Maybe for her.

04:08:16.440 --> 04:08:19.260
Finding out new things is enough to drive

04:08:19.260 --> 04:08:19.739
out her fear.

04:08:19.799 --> 04:08:23.340
Maybe this feels like an adventure to

04:08:23.340 --> 04:08:23.520
her.

04:08:23.579 --> 04:08:26.579
But that was hard for him to imagine.

04:08:26.639 --> 04:08:29.399
Especially when he pictured the army of

04:08:29.399 --> 04:08:31.860
mind controlled hive wings far above them

04:08:31.860 --> 04:08:36.000
combing the grasslands stalk by stock, who

04:08:36.000 --> 04:08:37.139
wouldn't be afraid of that.

04:08:37.260 --> 04:08:41.639
Maybe Swordtail, his best and bravest

04:08:41.639 --> 04:08:42.120
friend.

04:08:42.180 --> 04:08:44.219
He was a dragon who'd face that entire

04:08:44.219 --> 04:08:46.379
army to save Luna or Blue.

04:08:46.440 --> 04:08:49.559
His courage had always seemed foolish and

04:08:49.559 --> 04:08:51.780
dangerous, and impulsive to blue.

04:08:51.840 --> 04:08:54.899
But now he wished he had even a 10th of

04:08:54.899 --> 04:08:55.319
it himself.

04:08:55.379 --> 04:08:58.799
He lay down with his chin on his front

04:08:58.799 --> 04:09:01.559
talons, and thought about everyone who'd

04:09:01.559 --> 04:09:03.000
become entangled in this web.

04:09:03.120 --> 04:09:06.600
Io, who could be anywhere right now.

04:09:06.659 --> 04:09:10.799
Burnet and Silverspot, alone and worrying

04:09:10.799 --> 04:09:11.520
about their children.

04:09:11.639 --> 04:09:14.700
Katie did, wondering where her sister

04:09:14.700 --> 04:09:15.000
was.

04:09:15.059 --> 04:09:18.000
All the hive wings who were being forced

04:09:18.000 --> 04:09:20.459
to hunt for him, whether they understood

04:09:20.459 --> 04:09:21.120
why or not.

04:09:21.180 --> 04:09:24.239
And somewhere in the center of that web

04:09:24.239 --> 04:09:28.500
Queen Wasp, stealing the flame silks, and

04:09:28.500 --> 04:09:30.299
using her subjects like puppets.

04:09:30.360 --> 04:09:32.520
Was she angry right now?

04:09:32.579 --> 04:09:35.579
Or coldly certain that she'd find him

04:09:35.579 --> 04:09:36.059
soon?

04:09:36.120 --> 04:09:39.479
At least Luna was unaware of all this.

04:09:39.540 --> 04:09:42.780
Somewhere deep in her cocoon, she was

04:09:42.780 --> 04:09:43.200
asleep.

04:09:43.260 --> 04:09:45.059
Growing her wings in peace.

04:09:45.120 --> 04:09:48.479
She had no idea what kind of chaos her

04:09:48.479 --> 04:09:51.120
metamorphosis had set off, or what

04:09:51.120 --> 04:09:53.040
strange new prison she was going to wake

04:09:53.040 --> 04:09:53.520
up in.

04:09:53.579 --> 04:09:58.020
I'm coming, Luna, he thought fiercely.

04:09:58.079 --> 04:10:00.479
Sortell and I will find you.

04:10:00.540 --> 04:10:02.940
You're not going to wake up alone.

04:10:03.000 --> 04:10:04.139
I promise.

04:10:04.200 --> 04:10:08.700
Chapter 15.

04:10:09.120 --> 04:10:12.899
Blue stood at the bottom of the sinkhole

04:10:12.899 --> 04:10:13.620
looking up.

04:10:13.680 --> 04:10:16.680
He could just barely see the glow of

04:10:16.680 --> 04:10:18.420
moonlight reflecting off some of the

04:10:18.420 --> 04:10:19.559
rocks far overhead.

04:10:19.680 --> 04:10:23.040
His tail flicked a damp patch of moss on

04:10:23.040 --> 04:10:25.020
one of the rocks, and he shivered.

04:10:25.079 --> 04:10:27.780
Do you think it's safe to go up?

04:10:27.840 --> 04:10:29.159
Cricket asked.

04:10:29.219 --> 04:10:32.100
Hive wings prefer to hunt by day.

04:10:32.159 --> 04:10:34.020
Swordtail pointed out.

04:10:34.079 --> 04:10:37.020
Their night vision is poor, and they're

04:10:37.020 --> 04:10:39.180
lazy and arrogant, so I'm sure they're at

04:10:39.180 --> 04:10:41.340
home asleep, confident they'll catch us

04:10:41.340 --> 04:10:41.639
tomorrow.

04:10:41.700 --> 04:10:45.420
Cricket blinked at him, looking slightly

04:10:45.420 --> 04:10:45.600
hurt.

04:10:45.659 --> 04:10:49.559
I'm not at home asleep, she observed.

04:10:49.620 --> 04:10:51.360
Right.

04:10:51.420 --> 04:10:52.559
Blue said.

04:10:52.620 --> 04:10:54.659
That's not fair, Swordtail.

04:10:54.719 --> 04:10:56.700
They're not all lazy and arrogant.

04:10:56.760 --> 04:10:59.459
They're dragons, just like you and me and

04:10:59.459 --> 04:11:00.239
everyone we know.

04:11:00.299 --> 04:11:02.100
Some bad and some good.

04:11:02.159 --> 04:11:05.940
Dragons who stolen your sister and spent

04:11:05.940 --> 04:11:07.079
the last day hunting you.

04:11:07.200 --> 04:11:09.479
So they can throw you in their secret

04:11:09.479 --> 04:11:10.200
prison too.

04:11:10.260 --> 04:11:12.659
Soartail said sharply.

04:11:12.719 --> 04:11:15.959
That's Queen Wasp making them do that

04:11:15.959 --> 04:11:16.920
Blue said.

04:11:17.040 --> 04:11:18.780
They're not all like her.

04:11:18.840 --> 04:11:20.639
So what?

04:11:20.760 --> 04:11:23.819
They let her be like that, and never

04:11:23.819 --> 04:11:26.399
complain or speak up, because it means

04:11:26.399 --> 04:11:28.920
they get to be comfortable, Soritell

04:11:28.920 --> 04:11:29.159
said.

04:11:29.219 --> 04:11:30.659
Sorry, Blue.

04:11:30.719 --> 04:11:32.819
I'm not in the mood to feel sorry for the

04:11:32.819 --> 04:11:33.659
bad guys right now.

04:11:33.719 --> 04:11:36.780
He spread his wings and launched himself

04:11:36.780 --> 04:11:37.620
up to shaft.

04:11:37.680 --> 04:11:39.959
I'll go check if the coast is clear.

04:11:40.079 --> 04:11:43.319
Blue side is sore tail flew away.

04:11:43.379 --> 04:11:46.200
The strange, frenetic energy of the

04:11:46.200 --> 04:11:48.299
stimulant had worn off, and after

04:11:48.299 --> 04:11:51.299
sleeping almost the entire day, Sortell

04:11:51.299 --> 04:11:52.860
had woken up pretty much his normal self

04:11:52.860 --> 04:11:56.159
again, which was great, except for how

04:11:56.159 --> 04:11:58.739
his normal self could sometimes be a big

04:11:58.739 --> 04:12:01.440
honking rhinoceros, trampling over

04:12:01.440 --> 04:12:02.579
everyone else's feelings.

04:12:02.700 --> 04:12:04.799
I'm sorry.

04:12:04.860 --> 04:12:06.420
He said to Cricket.

04:12:06.479 --> 04:12:09.120
Don't be, she said.

04:12:09.239 --> 04:12:10.260
He's right.

04:12:10.319 --> 04:12:12.899
I never worried about how we treat silk

04:12:12.899 --> 04:12:15.120
wings or what happens to flame silks

04:12:15.120 --> 04:12:15.360
before.

04:12:15.479 --> 04:12:19.620
Neither did I, really, Blue admitted.

04:12:19.680 --> 04:12:21.540
But you're helping us now.

04:12:21.600 --> 04:12:23.219
You're not like the others.

04:12:23.280 --> 04:12:27.420
If Queen Wasp could control my mind, I

04:12:27.420 --> 04:12:29.280
probably would be, she said.

04:12:29.399 --> 04:12:32.760
It's just luck or some kind of mystery

04:12:32.760 --> 04:12:34.260
science that it doesn't work on me.

04:12:34.319 --> 04:12:37.680
Sortell swooped back down toward them.

04:12:37.739 --> 04:12:41.340
All quiet, as far as I can see and hear

04:12:41.340 --> 04:12:42.239
he said.

04:12:42.299 --> 04:12:43.559
If we fly now.

04:12:43.620 --> 04:12:46.440
We should make it to Wasp Hive before

04:12:46.440 --> 04:12:46.799
morning.

04:12:46.860 --> 04:12:49.139
And then what?

04:12:49.200 --> 04:12:50.280
Cricket asked.

04:12:50.340 --> 04:12:53.459
Then we figure something else out, he

04:12:53.459 --> 04:12:53.760
said.

04:12:53.819 --> 04:12:57.299
That sounds like a sword tail kind of

04:12:57.299 --> 04:12:59.159
plan, Blue Thought.

04:12:59.219 --> 04:13:00.780
But he didn't have anything better to

04:13:00.780 --> 04:13:02.579
offer, so he kept quiet.

04:13:02.639 --> 04:13:05.520
Sore Tail spun a harness around Blue

04:13:05.520 --> 04:13:07.860
again, and braced his forearms around

04:13:07.860 --> 04:13:08.700
Blue's chest.

04:13:08.760 --> 04:13:11.100
All right, he said.

04:13:11.159 --> 04:13:12.120
Off we.

04:13:12.239 --> 04:13:15.000
He vaulted into the air, and immediately

04:13:15.000 --> 04:13:17.520
lost his balance, smacking into the side

04:13:17.520 --> 04:13:19.319
of the canyon and thudding to the ground

04:13:19.319 --> 04:13:19.620
again.

04:13:19.680 --> 04:13:23.280
Blue's claws barked painfully against the

04:13:23.280 --> 04:13:24.780
stone, and he yelped.

04:13:24.840 --> 04:13:26.520
Oof.

04:13:26.579 --> 04:13:28.079
Soartail grunted.

04:13:28.139 --> 04:13:30.780
Sorry, let me just...

04:13:31.440 --> 04:13:33.239
He braced his legs and shoved himself

04:13:33.239 --> 04:13:35.760
aloft again, clutching Blue even more

04:13:35.760 --> 04:13:36.180
tightly.

04:13:36.239 --> 04:13:37.979
No luck.

04:13:38.040 --> 04:13:40.920
Blue could feel himself slipping, even

04:13:40.920 --> 04:13:43.620
with the harness, and sore tail's muscles

04:13:43.620 --> 04:13:45.659
were clearly straining to hold him.

04:13:45.719 --> 04:13:47.879
His wings beat as hard as he could.

04:13:47.940 --> 04:13:50.760
But a moment later, he had to drop back

04:13:50.760 --> 04:13:50.940
down.

04:13:51.000 --> 04:13:55.440
Uh oh, Cricket said, hovering above

04:13:55.440 --> 04:13:55.739
them.

04:13:55.799 --> 04:13:59.579
Blue glanced up at the far, far distant

04:13:59.579 --> 04:14:01.020
top of the hole again.

04:14:01.079 --> 04:14:03.780
Uh-oh, was a bit of an understatement.

04:14:03.840 --> 04:14:07.200
Sortell sized away the silk connecting

04:14:07.200 --> 04:14:09.600
them, and crouched, gasping for breath.

04:14:09.659 --> 04:14:12.899
If you can't carry him anymore, Cricket

04:14:12.899 --> 04:14:13.260
said.

04:14:13.319 --> 04:14:15.479
How are we going to get blue out of this

04:14:15.479 --> 04:14:16.079
cave?

04:14:16.139 --> 04:14:18.959
I don't understand why I can't.

04:14:19.020 --> 04:14:21.000
Sortell protested.

04:14:21.059 --> 04:14:23.579
I carried him all day yesterday.

04:14:23.639 --> 04:14:25.139
And it was no trouble at all.

04:14:25.200 --> 04:14:27.780
He flexed his arms and winced.

04:14:27.840 --> 04:14:30.659
I guess I do feel a little sore now.

04:14:30.719 --> 04:14:34.379
It was the stimulant, cricket said.

04:14:34.440 --> 04:14:37.139
It made you stronger and gave you energy

04:14:37.139 --> 04:14:38.819
but only until it wore off.

04:14:38.879 --> 04:14:40.500
That is so interesting.

04:14:40.559 --> 04:14:43.979
I wonder if anyone has any idea that it

04:14:43.979 --> 04:14:46.739
has that effect on dragons, or if other

04:14:46.739 --> 04:14:48.719
scientists have only ever used it on

04:14:48.719 --> 04:14:49.079
plans.

04:14:49.200 --> 04:14:51.840
Her eyes went a little dreamy.

04:14:51.899 --> 04:14:54.840
Maybe for the science fair next year?

04:14:54.899 --> 04:14:57.120
Do you have any more of it?

04:14:57.239 --> 04:15:00.239
So tell asked, eyeing the pouch tied

04:15:00.239 --> 04:15:01.020
around her chest.

04:15:01.079 --> 04:15:02.520
She shook her head.

04:15:02.579 --> 04:15:06.299
Now, and I wouldn't suggest taking it

04:15:06.299 --> 04:15:09.000
from a normal state, she said, not

04:15:09.000 --> 04:15:10.979
without some dilution experiments and

04:15:10.979 --> 04:15:12.059
animal studies first.

04:15:12.180 --> 04:15:14.819
I mean, you started off completely

04:15:14.819 --> 04:15:17.159
paralyzed, and look what it did to you.

04:15:17.219 --> 04:15:19.319
What it...

04:15:19.500 --> 04:15:20.819
What did I say?

04:15:20.940 --> 04:15:22.620
Swortell asked.

04:15:22.680 --> 04:15:24.840
Did I sound like a total idiot?

04:15:24.899 --> 04:15:26.459
You were fine.

04:15:26.520 --> 04:15:28.139
Blue assured him.

04:15:28.200 --> 04:15:29.520
It was adorable.

04:15:29.579 --> 04:15:31.440
Oh, good.

04:15:31.500 --> 04:15:33.360
Soartail grumbled.

04:15:33.420 --> 04:15:35.940
Adorable is just the look I was going for

04:15:35.940 --> 04:15:37.319
on our heroic mission.

04:15:37.379 --> 04:15:39.899
So what else can we do?

04:15:40.020 --> 04:15:42.719
Cricket said, studying the rocks around

04:15:42.719 --> 04:15:42.959
them.

04:15:43.020 --> 04:15:45.899
Blue, could you climb out?

04:15:45.959 --> 04:15:47.819
Of course.

04:15:47.879 --> 04:15:49.979
Swartail answered for him.

04:15:50.040 --> 04:15:53.159
Silkwings are all great climbers.

04:15:53.219 --> 04:15:57.959
Well, maybe, but all that way?

04:15:58.020 --> 04:16:00.959
Blue said, his courage failing.

04:16:01.020 --> 04:16:04.319
I mean, I don't mind the climbing part

04:16:04.319 --> 04:16:07.739
but the maybe falling part, and the very

04:16:07.739 --> 04:16:10.079
long way to fall, and the certain death

04:16:10.079 --> 04:16:12.959
if I fall parts, those I'm kind of less

04:16:12.959 --> 04:16:13.620
excited about.

04:16:13.680 --> 04:16:17.639
Plus, there's no way he'll make it to the

04:16:17.639 --> 04:16:18.540
top before morning.

04:16:18.600 --> 04:16:20.040
Sortell said.

04:16:20.100 --> 04:16:21.659
And then what do we do?

04:16:21.719 --> 04:16:24.780
Climb back down, risk the open Savannah

04:16:24.780 --> 04:16:25.079
again.

04:16:25.139 --> 04:16:27.959
There might be another option.

04:16:28.020 --> 04:16:30.239
Hang on, Cricket said.

04:16:30.299 --> 04:16:32.520
She spread her wings and flew away.

04:16:32.639 --> 04:16:35.639
Up and up till Blue could hardly see the

04:16:35.639 --> 04:16:38.459
shimmer of her sunlight colored scales.

04:16:38.520 --> 04:16:40.799
He had a horrible moment of imagining

04:16:40.799 --> 04:16:43.379
that she might not come back, but she'd

04:16:43.379 --> 04:16:45.840
reached the top, realize she could just

04:16:45.840 --> 04:16:48.420
go home and leave them and all their

04:16:48.420 --> 04:16:50.340
messy, troublesome danger behind.

04:16:50.399 --> 04:16:52.620
Blue.

04:16:52.680 --> 04:16:55.379
Sortell said, in a low voice.

04:16:55.440 --> 04:16:59.159
Blue glanced at him, and saw pity in his

04:16:59.159 --> 04:17:00.420
friend's dark blue eyes.

04:17:00.540 --> 04:17:04.260
Remember how you warned me once about

04:17:04.260 --> 04:17:05.639
falling in love with Luna?

04:17:05.700 --> 04:17:08.879
Soritell said, folding his wings back.

04:17:08.879 --> 04:17:11.399
You said we might not be partnered

04:17:11.399 --> 04:17:11.819
together.

04:17:11.879 --> 04:17:14.399
You said it would be better for both of

04:17:14.399 --> 04:17:17.100
us if we could wait to fall in love until

04:17:17.100 --> 04:17:18.719
we knew who our partners would be.

04:17:18.840 --> 04:17:22.319
Blue looked down at his claws.

04:17:22.379 --> 04:17:25.020
That felt like a very foolish thing to

04:17:25.020 --> 04:17:25.559
say now.

04:17:25.680 --> 04:17:28.620
As though a dragon could inject a nerve

04:17:28.620 --> 04:17:31.139
toxin into his feelings and leave them

04:17:31.139 --> 04:17:32.940
paralyzed until they might be usable.

04:17:33.000 --> 04:17:36.479
But he'd imagined how Luna and Swordtail

04:17:36.479 --> 04:17:39.059
would feel if Queen Wasp separated them.

04:17:39.180 --> 04:17:41.100
And it had been so awful.

04:17:41.159 --> 04:17:43.920
He'd been trying to protect them from

04:17:43.920 --> 04:17:44.100
that.

04:17:44.159 --> 04:17:47.399
This is much worse blue.

04:17:47.520 --> 04:17:49.139
Swartail said.

04:17:49.260 --> 04:17:50.879
She's a hive wing.

04:17:50.940 --> 04:17:53.639
You can never, never be with her.

04:17:53.700 --> 04:17:57.479
You should tell her to go home now, before

04:17:57.479 --> 04:17:59.100
it's too hard to say goodbye.

04:17:59.159 --> 04:18:01.440
I think it already is.

04:18:01.559 --> 04:18:03.420
Blue said softly.

04:18:03.540 --> 04:18:05.399
At least for me.

04:18:05.520 --> 04:18:10.020
Sortell put one wing over Blue's back and

04:18:10.020 --> 04:18:11.639
arrested his head against blues.

04:18:11.700 --> 04:18:13.979
I was afraid of that.

04:18:14.040 --> 04:18:15.180
He said.

04:18:15.239 --> 04:18:19.500
Cricket came swooping back down in a

04:18:19.500 --> 04:18:21.959
flapping of wings and landed on an

04:18:21.959 --> 04:18:23.459
outcropping a little ways above them.

04:18:23.520 --> 04:18:27.120
There's a crevice near the top, she

04:18:27.120 --> 04:18:27.420
said.

04:18:27.479 --> 04:18:30.659
It's not very big, but I think Blue could

04:18:30.659 --> 04:18:31.200
hide in it.

04:18:31.260 --> 04:18:34.200
If we can get him to it by morning, he

04:18:34.200 --> 04:18:36.239
could wait out the day there, and then

04:18:36.239 --> 04:18:38.159
we'd keep going to Wasp Hive tomorrow

04:18:38.159 --> 04:18:38.399
night.

04:18:38.520 --> 04:18:41.819
Blue felt the tension ripple through

04:18:41.819 --> 04:18:42.840
Swordtail's body.

04:18:42.899 --> 04:18:45.180
He knew what he was feeling.

04:18:45.239 --> 04:18:46.920
Another day's delay.

04:18:46.979 --> 04:18:49.920
A whole night wasted on one wingless

04:18:49.920 --> 04:18:51.479
dragon climbing out of a hole.

04:18:51.540 --> 04:18:54.600
When Luna was out there and needed their

04:18:54.600 --> 04:18:55.500
help, now.

04:18:55.620 --> 04:18:59.639
You can go on without me, if you'd

04:18:59.639 --> 04:19:00.000
rather.

04:19:00.120 --> 04:19:01.920
He said to Swordtail.

04:19:01.979 --> 04:19:04.379
He could see that sword tail was

04:19:04.379 --> 04:19:04.680
tempted.

04:19:04.739 --> 04:19:07.860
After all, what use was Blue going to be

04:19:07.860 --> 04:19:08.879
in a rescue anyway?

04:19:08.940 --> 04:19:10.860
He couldn't exactly fight.

04:19:10.920 --> 04:19:14.280
And if they had to escape in a hurry, he

04:19:14.280 --> 04:19:15.899
would massively slow them down.

04:19:15.959 --> 04:19:18.840
No, don't do that.

04:19:18.899 --> 04:19:20.100
Cricket said.

04:19:20.219 --> 04:19:22.500
I was hoping you'd use your silk to help

04:19:22.500 --> 04:19:23.520
Lou climb out.

04:19:23.639 --> 04:19:24.959
She pointed up.

04:19:25.020 --> 04:19:26.879
To catch him if he falls.

04:19:26.940 --> 04:19:30.239
Oh, Swordtail said.

04:19:30.299 --> 04:19:33.000
Light dawning in his eyes as he saw what

04:19:33.000 --> 04:19:33.420
she meant.

04:19:33.479 --> 04:19:35.819
Of course, that's a good idea.

04:19:35.940 --> 04:19:39.840
Cricket is full of good ideas, Blue

04:19:39.840 --> 04:19:40.200
said.

04:19:40.260 --> 04:19:43.379
She ducked her head and smiled at him, and

04:19:43.379 --> 04:19:44.579
he felt his heart explode.

04:19:44.700 --> 04:19:47.520
Definitely too late.

04:19:47.579 --> 04:19:50.159
I can say goodbye to her.

04:19:50.219 --> 04:19:52.739
Even if it means it'll hurt more later.

04:19:52.799 --> 04:19:55.319
I still want to be with her for as long

04:19:55.319 --> 04:19:55.860
as I can.

04:19:55.920 --> 04:20:01.020
All right, let's try this, Soitel said.

04:20:01.079 --> 04:20:03.420
Again shooting silk from his wrists.

04:20:03.540 --> 04:20:06.659
This time, the thicker, stronger strands

04:20:06.659 --> 04:20:09.299
that were usually used for building web

04:20:09.299 --> 04:20:09.959
bridges.

04:20:10.020 --> 04:20:13.079
He wound it around blue, leaving his

04:20:13.079 --> 04:20:15.540
limbs free to climb, then leaped out to

04:20:15.540 --> 04:20:17.819
the ledge above cricket, still holding

04:20:17.819 --> 04:20:18.780
the other end of the silk.

04:20:18.840 --> 04:20:20.399
Go ahead.

04:20:20.459 --> 04:20:21.540
He called.

04:20:21.600 --> 04:20:23.399
All right.

04:20:23.459 --> 04:20:25.020
This is happening.

04:20:25.079 --> 04:20:26.219
Blue thought.

04:20:26.280 --> 04:20:29.459
He sent up a silent prayer to Clearsight

04:20:29.459 --> 04:20:31.500
and started up the side of the Rocky

04:20:31.500 --> 04:20:31.979
Canyon.

04:20:32.040 --> 04:20:35.639
In fact, it was easier to climb than he'd

04:20:35.639 --> 04:20:36.299
expected.

04:20:36.360 --> 04:20:38.639
There were a lot of little crevices and

04:20:38.639 --> 04:20:41.639
nooks for him to dig his talons into, and

04:20:41.639 --> 04:20:43.979
the stone, overall, felt much sturdier

04:20:43.979 --> 04:20:45.959
than the webs he'd grown up clambering

04:20:45.959 --> 04:20:46.319
around on.

04:20:46.379 --> 04:20:49.500
At least the rocks didn't bounce and sway

04:20:49.500 --> 04:20:50.100
in the wind.

04:20:50.159 --> 04:20:53.280
And when he did stumble, losing his

04:20:53.280 --> 04:20:55.739
footing for a moment, he felt the

04:20:55.739 --> 04:20:57.899
strength of the webbing catch him, the

04:20:57.899 --> 04:21:00.120
strength of sore tail, just above him

04:21:00.120 --> 04:21:02.219
braced to save him before he fell.

04:21:02.280 --> 04:21:05.520
And cricket was beside him the whole way

04:21:05.520 --> 04:21:09.059
suggesting the easiest paths, pointing

04:21:09.059 --> 04:21:12.059
out places for him to rest, not for the

04:21:12.059 --> 04:21:12.479
1st time.

04:21:12.540 --> 04:21:15.780
Blue felt very, very grateful for his

04:21:15.780 --> 04:21:16.079
friends.

04:21:16.200 --> 04:21:20.100
Even though the climbing went well, it

04:21:20.100 --> 04:21:21.540
still seemed to take forever.

04:21:21.600 --> 04:21:24.719
It was a really deep hole after all.

04:21:24.780 --> 04:21:28.200
Blue's whole body was aching before he

04:21:28.200 --> 04:21:28.920
was halfway up.

04:21:28.979 --> 04:21:32.040
He found himself daydreaming wistfully

04:21:32.040 --> 04:21:35.280
about honey drops, and tiny sugar bees

04:21:35.280 --> 04:21:38.219
and silk hammocks, and when at last

04:21:38.219 --> 04:21:40.500
cricket said, it's here.

04:21:40.559 --> 04:21:41.940
It's just above you.

04:21:42.000 --> 04:21:44.879
He looked up and saw that the sky was

04:21:44.879 --> 04:21:47.340
already pale gray, and most of the stars

04:21:47.340 --> 04:21:48.239
had disappeared.

04:21:48.299 --> 04:21:50.159
Cricket was right.

04:21:50.219 --> 04:21:53.040
They were near the top, and he'd be able

04:21:53.040 --> 04:21:54.719
to climb out early the next night.

04:21:54.780 --> 04:21:57.299
If he wasn't caught by then.

04:21:57.360 --> 04:22:01.079
With one last heave, he hauled himself

04:22:01.079 --> 04:22:03.600
onto the ledge next to Cricket, letting

04:22:03.600 --> 04:22:05.399
Swordtail lift him with the webbing.

04:22:05.459 --> 04:22:09.180
He sprawled there, breathing hard, and

04:22:09.180 --> 04:22:10.739
wondering if his legs would ever work

04:22:10.739 --> 04:22:11.040
again.

04:22:11.100 --> 04:22:14.819
Sortell poked his head over the rim of

04:22:14.819 --> 04:22:16.860
the sinkhole, and squinted in the

04:22:16.860 --> 04:22:18.180
direction of Wasp Hive.

04:22:18.239 --> 04:22:22.559
I don't see anyone yet, he said, flying

04:22:22.559 --> 04:22:24.600
back to them, but you should still get

04:22:24.600 --> 04:22:25.680
hidden to be safe.

04:22:25.739 --> 04:22:28.020
Back here.

04:22:28.139 --> 04:22:30.719
Cricket flicked her tail at the rippling

04:22:30.719 --> 04:22:31.979
stone of the rock wall.

04:22:32.040 --> 04:22:35.159
Blue crawled over and saw how the bend of

04:22:35.159 --> 04:22:37.739
the rock and the dangling plants hid a

04:22:37.739 --> 04:22:40.260
narrow crack, just big enough for him to

04:22:40.260 --> 04:22:40.860
squeeze through.

04:22:40.920 --> 04:22:43.860
He was amazed that Cricket had even found

04:22:43.860 --> 04:22:44.700
it in the 1st place.

04:22:44.760 --> 04:22:48.420
She held the green leaves aside, so he

04:22:48.420 --> 04:22:50.819
could wedge himself in, and he discovered

04:22:50.819 --> 04:22:52.920
that the crack extended into the rock

04:22:52.920 --> 04:22:56.040
like a small cave, so he could go farther

04:22:56.040 --> 04:22:59.040
in, squishily turn around and lie down.

04:22:59.100 --> 04:23:02.159
Cricket poked her head in and watched him

04:23:02.159 --> 04:23:02.639
settle.

04:23:02.700 --> 04:23:05.040
Do you want company?

04:23:05.100 --> 04:23:07.379
Which would be kind of cramped.

04:23:07.440 --> 04:23:09.299
Or do you want the whole space?

04:23:09.360 --> 04:23:10.500
But alone.

04:23:10.559 --> 04:23:13.200
Company, Blue said.

04:23:13.319 --> 04:23:15.719
If, if you don't mind.

04:23:15.780 --> 04:23:19.920
I don't mind, if you don't mind my wings

04:23:19.920 --> 04:23:21.719
in your face, she said.

04:23:21.780 --> 04:23:24.659
She wriggled back out to tell sword tail

04:23:24.659 --> 04:23:27.239
and blew her the whoosh of his friend's

04:23:27.239 --> 04:23:29.280
wing beats retreating back down to the

04:23:29.280 --> 04:23:30.360
safety of the lake cave.

04:23:30.420 --> 04:23:33.600
Then Cricket was wedging herself in

04:23:33.600 --> 04:23:36.239
through the gap, making little squeaking

04:23:36.239 --> 04:23:38.040
noises as she tried to keep her wings

04:23:38.040 --> 04:23:39.420
clear of the rough stones.

04:23:39.479 --> 04:23:42.540
Blue pressed himself back as far as he

04:23:42.540 --> 04:23:45.840
could, and after a minute, she managed to

04:23:45.840 --> 04:23:48.299
get all the way in and lie down facing

04:23:48.299 --> 04:23:48.600
him.

04:23:48.659 --> 04:23:51.239
Thank you for your delightful

04:23:51.239 --> 04:23:51.959
invitation.

04:23:52.020 --> 04:23:55.319
She said, in a pretend lordly voice

04:23:55.319 --> 04:23:56.639
adjusting her glasses.

04:23:56.700 --> 04:24:00.059
I adore what you've done with the place.

04:24:00.120 --> 04:24:03.000
I'll be expecting tea and sliced avocados

04:24:03.000 --> 04:24:03.239
of course.

04:24:03.299 --> 04:24:06.479
Blue put his chin on his talons and

04:24:06.479 --> 04:24:06.899
chuckled.

04:24:06.959 --> 04:24:09.239
Don't make me think about food.

04:24:09.360 --> 04:24:14.100
I can't stop thinking about food, she

04:24:14.100 --> 04:24:14.459
said.

04:24:14.520 --> 04:24:15.899
I'm starving.

04:24:15.959 --> 04:24:18.840
Those fish I caught for breakfast, we're

04:24:18.840 --> 04:24:21.120
so small, and super weird.

04:24:21.180 --> 04:24:23.520
Did you see that they didn't have eyes?

04:24:23.639 --> 04:24:25.500
Oh, right, I showed you.

04:24:25.559 --> 04:24:27.299
Fish with no eyes.

04:24:27.360 --> 04:24:29.280
Do you think that's because there's no

04:24:29.280 --> 04:24:29.940
light down there?

04:24:30.000 --> 04:24:32.399
I guess I wouldn't rather eat something

04:24:32.399 --> 04:24:35.100
with eyes, but you should have tried them

04:24:35.100 --> 04:24:35.399
anyway.

04:24:35.459 --> 04:24:36.719
I could have caught more.

04:24:36.780 --> 04:24:40.500
That's all right, Blue said with a

04:24:40.500 --> 04:24:40.739
smile.

04:24:40.799 --> 04:24:43.139
I can wait for something in the vegetable

04:24:43.139 --> 04:24:43.440
family.

04:24:43.500 --> 04:24:46.020
Cricket studied him.

04:24:46.139 --> 04:24:48.840
What will you do with Luna?

04:24:48.840 --> 04:24:49.979
she asked.

04:24:50.040 --> 04:24:52.680
I mean, if you can set her free.

04:24:52.739 --> 04:24:54.180
Where will you go?

04:24:54.299 --> 04:24:56.940
Queen Wasp isn't going to stop looking

04:24:56.940 --> 04:24:57.659
for you.

04:24:57.719 --> 04:25:00.059
I have no idea.

04:25:00.180 --> 04:25:02.340
Blue said slowly.

04:25:02.399 --> 04:25:05.219
Honestly, he'd been imagining getting

04:25:05.219 --> 04:25:07.020
Luna and going home to their mothers.

04:25:07.079 --> 04:25:10.020
A part of him still felt as though this

04:25:10.020 --> 04:25:13.020
was a big misunderstanding, and if he

04:25:13.020 --> 04:25:15.120
could only convince Queen Wasp of how

04:25:15.120 --> 04:25:17.579
harmless they were, she let them go back

04:25:17.579 --> 04:25:18.420
to their normal lives.

04:25:18.479 --> 04:25:21.360
I wish we could do that.

04:25:21.420 --> 04:25:23.639
Why can't there be a way?

04:25:23.700 --> 04:25:28.020
Although, would it ever feel the same?

04:25:28.139 --> 04:25:31.680
Now that I know about the flame silks, and

04:25:31.680 --> 04:25:32.520
the mind control.

04:25:32.579 --> 04:25:35.219
Would we ever feel safe again?

04:25:35.280 --> 04:25:39.120
Maybe you could go live in the caves with

04:25:39.120 --> 04:25:42.420
the reading monkeys, Cricket said, with a

04:25:42.420 --> 04:25:45.000
dreamy smile in her voice, as though she

04:25:45.000 --> 04:25:46.920
was making a joke, but actually thought

04:25:46.920 --> 04:25:47.879
that sounded amazing.

04:25:47.940 --> 04:25:51.959
That one we saw did look very welcoming.

04:25:52.020 --> 04:25:55.319
Blue laughed in a stabby kind of way.

04:25:55.379 --> 04:25:59.579
But, I'd go farther away if I were you

04:25:59.579 --> 04:26:00.600
she said.

04:26:00.659 --> 04:26:03.600
As far from Queen Wasp as you can.

04:26:03.659 --> 04:26:07.860
Like one of the peninsulas, he asked.

04:26:07.979 --> 04:26:10.319
I thought they were too dangerous for

04:26:10.319 --> 04:26:10.860
dragons.

04:26:10.920 --> 04:26:13.079
That's what we're told.

04:26:13.200 --> 04:26:15.059
Crickets said, nodding.

04:26:15.120 --> 04:26:16.799
But maybe it's not true.

04:26:16.860 --> 04:26:19.799
Blue wasn't so sure.

04:26:19.860 --> 04:26:22.559
He'd seen drawings of some of the plants

04:26:22.559 --> 04:26:24.840
in the poison jungle, and they certainly

04:26:24.840 --> 04:26:27.000
looked as if they'd be happy to eat a few

04:26:27.000 --> 04:26:31.200
dragons, or impale some dragons, or melt

04:26:31.200 --> 04:26:33.059
some dragons and convert their bone

04:26:33.059 --> 04:26:34.260
sludge into nutrients.

04:26:34.379 --> 04:26:37.860
You could go farther than that, though

04:26:37.860 --> 04:26:39.780
Cricket said hesitantly.

04:26:39.840 --> 04:26:42.719
I could, he said.

04:26:42.780 --> 04:26:43.680
How?

04:26:43.739 --> 04:26:45.899
Maybe...

04:26:45.899 --> 04:26:49.319
Across the ocean, she said.

04:26:49.379 --> 04:26:52.379
He stared at her with wide eyes.

04:26:52.440 --> 04:26:55.260
Her body blocked most of the dim light

04:26:55.260 --> 04:26:55.979
from outside.

04:26:56.040 --> 04:26:58.319
So he couldn't really see the expression

04:26:58.319 --> 04:26:58.860
on her face.

04:26:58.920 --> 04:27:00.780
Was she joking?

04:27:00.840 --> 04:27:02.579
Are you joking?

04:27:02.639 --> 04:27:03.540
He asked.

04:27:03.600 --> 04:27:06.120
The distant kingdoms aren't real.

04:27:06.180 --> 04:27:09.059
The tilt of her head said she was

04:27:09.059 --> 04:27:09.540
puzzled.

04:27:09.600 --> 04:27:11.579
Of course they are.

04:27:11.639 --> 04:27:13.620
That's where Clearsight came from.

04:27:13.739 --> 04:27:16.319
Yes, but...

04:27:16.319 --> 04:27:18.540
But Clearsight was magic.

04:27:18.600 --> 04:27:22.139
Blue had always imagined the night black

04:27:22.139 --> 04:27:24.899
seer dragon. as a mythological figure

04:27:24.899 --> 04:27:27.840
like a star becoming a dragon and flying

04:27:27.840 --> 04:27:28.620
down to visit them.

04:27:28.680 --> 04:27:32.760
We say she came from the distant kingdoms

04:27:32.760 --> 04:27:35.100
but we might as well say she came from

04:27:35.100 --> 04:27:36.659
the moons or the sky.

04:27:36.719 --> 04:27:40.860
The moons and the sky are real places too

04:27:40.920 --> 04:27:42.780
cricket pointed out.

04:27:42.840 --> 04:27:46.799
Not places we can go, he protested.

04:27:46.860 --> 04:27:50.819
But we could go to the distant kingdoms

04:27:50.819 --> 04:27:51.719
Cricket said.

04:27:51.780 --> 04:27:53.100
I'm sure of it.

04:27:53.159 --> 04:27:55.860
It's just another big island, somewhere

04:27:55.860 --> 04:27:58.680
out to the east, full of other dragons.

04:27:58.739 --> 04:28:01.379
He stared at her silhouette.

04:28:01.440 --> 04:28:03.299
Thinking of how different their

04:28:03.299 --> 04:28:04.379
educations had been.

04:28:04.500 --> 04:28:08.940
At Silkworm Hall, he'd learned to revere

04:28:08.940 --> 04:28:11.639
Clearsight, and accept the wisdom she'd

04:28:11.639 --> 04:28:13.139
passed down in the book without

04:28:13.139 --> 04:28:13.680
question.

04:28:13.739 --> 04:28:16.500
He'd never been taught to think of her as

04:28:16.500 --> 04:28:19.260
a regular dragon like him, from a normal

04:28:19.260 --> 04:28:20.399
kingdom like his.

04:28:20.399 --> 04:28:24.659
Other dragons like Clearsight.

04:28:24.780 --> 04:28:25.620
He asked.

04:28:25.680 --> 04:28:28.860
Is it a whole continent full of dragons

04:28:28.860 --> 04:28:29.579
who can see the future?

04:28:29.639 --> 04:28:32.219
I don't know.

04:28:32.280 --> 04:28:33.600
Cricket said.

04:28:33.659 --> 04:28:36.719
Maybe. wouldn't it be so interesting to

04:28:36.719 --> 04:28:37.079
find out?

04:28:37.139 --> 04:28:41.280
Can you imagine being the 1st dragons to

04:28:41.280 --> 04:28:43.200
cross the ocean in 1000s of years?

04:28:43.319 --> 04:28:46.799
I mean, what kinds of tribes live over

04:28:46.799 --> 04:28:47.040
there?

04:28:47.100 --> 04:28:48.840
Do they look like us?

04:28:48.899 --> 04:28:50.760
Do they have other powers?

04:28:50.879 --> 04:28:53.340
Do they have reading monkeys?

04:28:53.399 --> 04:28:57.600
But if it is real, and it's that easy to

04:28:57.600 --> 04:28:59.819
get there, Blue argued.

04:28:59.879 --> 04:29:02.340
And Clearsight wouldn't be the only one

04:29:02.340 --> 04:29:03.840
to have done it in all that time.

04:29:03.959 --> 04:29:05.579
He shook his head.

04:29:05.639 --> 04:29:07.620
I think it's a myth.

04:29:07.680 --> 04:29:11.940
I think it's the perfect place to hide if

04:29:11.940 --> 04:29:14.459
Queen Wasp is looking for you, Cricket

04:29:14.459 --> 04:29:14.940
said.

04:29:15.000 --> 04:29:17.399
But you're right, that it wouldn't be

04:29:17.399 --> 04:29:18.120
easy to get there.

04:29:18.180 --> 04:29:20.940
We'd have to find out how Clearsight did

04:29:20.940 --> 04:29:21.120
it.

04:29:21.180 --> 04:29:24.780
Magic, Blue said promptly.

04:29:24.840 --> 04:29:27.299
Cricket leaned forward and bopped his

04:29:27.299 --> 04:29:28.079
nose with hers.

04:29:28.139 --> 04:29:31.559
Magic is just science we don't understand

04:29:31.559 --> 04:29:33.120
yet, she said.

04:29:33.180 --> 04:29:36.239
So maybe we can figure out her science.

04:29:36.299 --> 04:29:38.700
How exactly?

04:29:38.700 --> 04:29:39.780
he asked.

04:29:39.840 --> 04:29:44.639
With books, Cricket said, as though that

04:29:44.639 --> 04:29:47.459
was obvious, there must be clues in a

04:29:47.459 --> 04:29:48.120
book somewhere.

04:29:48.180 --> 04:29:51.840
He unfurled his antennae, sensing danger

04:29:51.840 --> 04:29:54.780
and put one of his talons over hers.

04:29:54.840 --> 04:29:55.920
Shh.

04:29:55.979 --> 04:29:58.620
There were sounds coming from outside.

04:29:58.680 --> 04:30:03.360
Chapter 16.

04:30:03.600 --> 04:30:07.680
Blue and Cricket waited intense silence.

04:30:07.739 --> 04:30:10.500
Wing beats, voices.

04:30:10.500 --> 04:30:12.780
Oh, whoosh.

04:30:12.840 --> 04:30:15.360
And then a cracking sound, like an

04:30:15.360 --> 04:30:17.579
antelope's neck being broken, and

04:30:17.579 --> 04:30:20.219
munching noises as it was devoured.

04:30:20.280 --> 04:30:21.360
Blue shivered.

04:30:21.479 --> 04:30:24.000
Who said you could eat?

04:30:24.000 --> 04:30:25.680
said one of the voices.

04:30:25.739 --> 04:30:27.959
Deep and sharp and female.

04:30:28.020 --> 04:30:31.200
I didn't eat all day yesterday.

04:30:31.260 --> 04:30:35.040
Another voice answered, whiny and male.

04:30:35.100 --> 04:30:38.879
You know, she never lets us while she's

04:30:38.879 --> 04:30:39.479
in control.

04:30:39.540 --> 04:30:42.120
So I figure, as long as we're out here

04:30:42.120 --> 04:30:44.040
and in charge of our own schools for once

04:30:44.040 --> 04:30:46.739
we can hunt breakfast and run away silk

04:30:46.739 --> 04:30:47.520
wings at the same time.

04:30:47.579 --> 04:30:50.219
The other hive wing growled.

04:30:50.280 --> 04:30:53.040
But there was a noise of ripping meat, as

04:30:53.040 --> 04:30:54.840
though she'd taken a chunk of the prey

04:30:54.840 --> 04:30:55.260
for herself.

04:30:55.319 --> 04:30:58.020
This is a waste of time.

04:30:58.079 --> 04:31:00.299
She muttered, chewing.

04:31:00.360 --> 04:31:03.659
Who cares about one stupid dragonette who

04:31:03.659 --> 04:31:05.639
might or might not have fire in his

04:31:05.639 --> 04:31:06.059
silk?

04:31:06.059 --> 04:31:08.940
He probably got eaten by a pack of lions

04:31:08.940 --> 04:31:11.159
or fell down a hole and died already.

04:31:11.219 --> 04:31:13.799
A hole like this one?

04:31:13.979 --> 04:31:17.040
The voices drew nearer, and blue felt

04:31:17.040 --> 04:31:18.360
crickets wings trembling.

04:31:18.420 --> 04:31:20.399
Should we check down there?

04:31:20.459 --> 04:31:23.700
Ugh, said the 1st dragon.

04:31:23.760 --> 04:31:25.920
My patrol went down there yesterday.

04:31:25.979 --> 04:31:28.500
It's dark and wet and haunted.

04:31:28.559 --> 04:31:29.940
I think we can skip it.

04:31:30.000 --> 04:31:31.799
Hello.

04:31:31.860 --> 04:31:35.159
The 2nd dragon shouted down the chasm

04:31:35.159 --> 04:31:37.020
making blue jump.

04:31:37.079 --> 04:31:41.579
Hello, annoying wingless dragon.

04:31:41.639 --> 04:31:44.459
Are you dead at the bottom of these rocks

04:31:44.459 --> 04:31:46.020
or almost dead?

04:31:46.139 --> 04:31:47.700
Could you croak?

04:31:47.760 --> 04:31:49.920
Yeah, I'm here, totally dead.

04:31:50.040 --> 04:31:52.860
Carry on, so we can all go home and say

04:31:52.860 --> 04:31:53.579
we found you.

04:31:53.700 --> 04:31:57.840
His companion actually laughed, which was

04:31:57.840 --> 04:31:59.280
the most surprising part of the

04:31:59.280 --> 04:32:01.440
conversation so far from Blue's point of

04:32:01.440 --> 04:32:01.620
view.

04:32:01.680 --> 04:32:05.579
Come on, finish your intestines so we can

04:32:05.579 --> 04:32:06.899
get going, she said.

04:32:06.959 --> 04:32:09.780
There are some scrub thickets over by

04:32:09.780 --> 04:32:11.579
Tetsi Hive that I think are worth

04:32:11.579 --> 04:32:12.000
checking out.

04:32:12.059 --> 04:32:15.899
It felt like a long time, and a lot of

04:32:15.899 --> 04:32:18.000
chewing noises later when they finally

04:32:18.000 --> 04:32:18.600
flew away.

04:32:18.659 --> 04:32:22.020
Blue let out of breath, and wondered how

04:32:22.020 --> 04:32:23.219
long he'd been holding it.

04:32:23.280 --> 04:32:26.159
His limbs were aching and heavy from the

04:32:26.159 --> 04:32:27.299
long night of climbing.

04:32:27.360 --> 04:32:29.520
And now that the danger had passed.

04:32:29.639 --> 04:32:31.680
He felt his eyelids drooping.

04:32:31.739 --> 04:32:33.840
It seemed safe enough to sleep.

04:32:33.959 --> 04:32:36.780
If anyone found him, he couldn't exactly

04:32:36.780 --> 04:32:38.459
escape in a hurry anyhow.

04:32:38.520 --> 04:32:41.219
He rested his chin on the ground and

04:32:41.219 --> 04:32:43.020
closed his eyes and slept.

04:32:43.079 --> 04:32:47.639
Blue slept for most of the day, drifting

04:32:47.639 --> 04:32:49.440
in and out when there were sounds of the

04:32:49.440 --> 04:32:50.219
hunt overhead.

04:32:50.280 --> 04:32:52.020
But each time he woke.

04:32:52.079 --> 04:32:53.280
Cricket was there.

04:32:53.399 --> 04:32:55.319
And he felt safe enough to sleep again.

04:32:55.379 --> 04:32:59.459
At last, she nudged him awake, and they

04:32:59.459 --> 04:33:01.559
squeezed out of the hidden crevice onto

04:33:01.559 --> 04:33:02.280
the ledge outside.

04:33:02.340 --> 04:33:06.840
The sky was just turning purple blue, and

04:33:06.840 --> 04:33:07.860
a few stars were out.

04:33:07.919 --> 04:33:11.039
Blue stretched out all his cramped

04:33:11.039 --> 04:33:13.319
muscles, while cricket flew down to get

04:33:13.319 --> 04:33:13.919
sore tail.

04:33:13.979 --> 04:33:17.099
After that, it took only a little more

04:33:17.099 --> 04:33:19.080
climbing before he reached the top of the

04:33:19.080 --> 04:33:22.080
sinkhole, and scrambled onto safe, flat

04:33:22.080 --> 04:33:22.439
ground.

04:33:22.500 --> 04:33:26.040
It was strange how dry it felt up here

04:33:26.040 --> 04:33:28.619
after the dampness of the deep cave.

04:33:28.680 --> 04:33:32.880
Dust billowed up between his claws as he

04:33:32.880 --> 04:33:34.439
cut off the silk harness and threw it

04:33:34.439 --> 04:33:34.919
down the hole.

04:33:34.979 --> 04:33:39.060
Now that he wasn't flying though, wasp

04:33:39.060 --> 04:33:40.560
hive looked horribly far away.

04:33:40.619 --> 04:33:43.319
Could they possibly make it there before

04:33:43.319 --> 04:33:43.919
dawn?

04:33:43.979 --> 04:33:45.419
Even if they did.

04:33:45.479 --> 04:33:48.000
Would there be anywhere else to hide as

04:33:48.000 --> 04:33:49.080
safe as the sinkhole?

04:33:49.139 --> 04:33:54.060
I'll scout ahead, Swartell called, soaring

04:33:54.060 --> 04:33:54.360
away.

04:33:54.419 --> 04:33:57.779
His deep blue wings were soon swallowed

04:33:57.779 --> 04:33:58.799
up by the night.

04:33:58.860 --> 04:34:00.959
And all blue could see of him where the

04:34:00.959 --> 04:34:03.000
little flickers of white along his back

04:34:03.000 --> 04:34:05.040
like a flurry of snow moths.

04:34:05.099 --> 04:34:08.399
Cricket landed to walk beside Blue

04:34:08.399 --> 04:34:11.039
between the tufts of grass and stabby

04:34:11.039 --> 04:34:11.999
little thorn bushes.

04:34:12.060 --> 04:34:15.419
He glanced down at his talons and

04:34:15.419 --> 04:34:17.279
realized that a lot of the paint had

04:34:17.279 --> 04:34:19.979
flaked off, probably from wading in the

04:34:19.979 --> 04:34:22.319
lake, and scraping against the rocks.

04:34:22.380 --> 04:34:25.439
His real colors were showing through all

04:34:25.439 --> 04:34:28.439
over his body, glints of aquamarine and

04:34:28.439 --> 04:34:30.959
violet, shimmering like buried jewels.

04:34:31.020 --> 04:34:33.720
They went as fast as they could.

04:34:33.779 --> 04:34:36.059
Although sometimes they had to detour

04:34:36.059 --> 04:34:39.119
around particularly dense shrubs, or ant

04:34:39.119 --> 04:34:40.439
hills as big as they were.

04:34:40.500 --> 04:34:43.799
At one point, a scorpion ran across

04:34:43.799 --> 04:34:46.860
Blue's foot, and he nearly shrieked, but

04:34:46.860 --> 04:34:47.759
managed not to.

04:34:47.819 --> 04:34:51.240
The air was full of buzzing and zipping

04:34:51.240 --> 04:34:53.759
and the tall grass rustled as snakes

04:34:53.759 --> 04:34:54.840
glided out of their way.

04:34:54.959 --> 04:34:57.659
Two of the moons were full.

04:34:57.779 --> 04:35:00.599
The other was barely a sliver behind a

04:35:00.599 --> 04:35:01.259
veil of clouds.

04:35:01.319 --> 04:35:04.020
Cricket tipped her head back to look up

04:35:04.020 --> 04:35:04.439
at them.

04:35:04.500 --> 04:35:07.439
Did you see the comet about half a year

04:35:07.439 --> 04:35:07.740
ago?

04:35:07.799 --> 04:35:08.819
she asked.

04:35:08.880 --> 04:35:12.180
The one that looked like an extra moon in

04:35:12.180 --> 04:35:12.479
the sky.

04:35:12.540 --> 04:35:14.159
It was so big.

04:35:14.220 --> 04:35:17.880
I wished so much that I had a telescope

04:35:17.880 --> 04:35:20.340
to study it with, but there's only one in

04:35:20.340 --> 04:35:23.639
Cicada Hive, and Lady Scarab won't lend

04:35:23.639 --> 04:35:24.060
it to anyone.

04:35:24.119 --> 04:35:27.059
You know lady scarab.

04:35:27.119 --> 04:35:28.199
Blue asked.

04:35:28.259 --> 04:35:30.779
You know Lady Scarab?

04:35:30.840 --> 04:35:32.400
She replied skeptically.

04:35:32.520 --> 04:35:37.200
No, we just, we ran into her, and the

04:35:37.200 --> 04:35:37.799
sugar dream.

04:35:37.860 --> 04:35:40.319
Early on Luna's metamorphosis day.

04:35:40.380 --> 04:35:41.639
She was.

04:35:42.840 --> 04:35:45.180
I feel like nice is the wrong word.

04:35:45.299 --> 04:35:48.840
But she was sort of fiercely not awful to

04:35:48.840 --> 04:35:49.080
us.

04:35:49.139 --> 04:35:52.560
That sounds like her, Cricket said

04:35:52.560 --> 04:35:53.159
ruefully.

04:35:53.220 --> 04:35:55.439
Fiercely not awful.

04:35:55.500 --> 04:35:58.860
Blue sensed there was more to cricket's

04:35:58.860 --> 04:36:00.900
connection with the old dragon, but she

04:36:00.900 --> 04:36:02.159
didn't seem to want to talk about it.

04:36:02.220 --> 04:36:05.459
He changed the subject to astronomy.

04:36:05.520 --> 04:36:08.220
And they happily discussed constellations

04:36:08.220 --> 04:36:10.619
and her theories about other planets

04:36:10.619 --> 04:36:12.599
until Blue realized they were reaching

04:36:12.599 --> 04:36:14.279
the outskirts of Wasp Hive.

04:36:14.340 --> 04:36:17.880
They crested a small hill, and studied

04:36:17.880 --> 04:36:19.500
the structures laid out below them.

04:36:19.560 --> 04:36:22.979
Wasp Hive was not quite like the other

04:36:22.979 --> 04:36:23.520
hives.

04:36:23.580 --> 04:36:26.880
It was bigger, for one thing, and the

04:36:26.880 --> 04:36:29.759
oldest hive on Pantala, so it was built

04:36:29.759 --> 04:36:31.740
in a heavier, more ornate style.

04:36:31.799 --> 04:36:35.700
They were carvings of cruel eyed wasps

04:36:35.700 --> 04:36:38.400
adorning the entrances, brandishing the

04:36:38.400 --> 04:36:40.439
wealth of the hive in their excess wood

04:36:40.439 --> 04:36:43.979
and onyx inlays, an enormous marble

04:36:43.979 --> 04:36:46.619
statue of Queen Wasp, loomed over the

04:36:46.619 --> 04:36:49.200
ground floor doors, so anyone entering

04:36:49.200 --> 04:36:51.060
that way would have to pass under her

04:36:51.060 --> 04:36:52.139
merciless gaze.

04:36:52.200 --> 04:36:55.139
But most dragons would enter at a higher

04:36:55.139 --> 04:36:55.439
level.

04:36:55.500 --> 04:36:58.439
Blue glanced up at the moonlit webs

04:36:58.439 --> 04:36:59.639
twining overhead.

04:36:59.700 --> 04:37:02.580
He could see the dark forms of silkwing

04:37:02.580 --> 04:37:05.340
family clusters up there. 100s of

04:37:05.340 --> 04:37:07.979
sleeping dragons, like stones seen

04:37:07.979 --> 04:37:08.459
through water.

04:37:08.520 --> 04:37:11.639
Did any of them know about flame silks?

04:37:11.700 --> 04:37:14.520
Did any of them help imprison and feed

04:37:14.520 --> 04:37:16.919
dragons, like Luna and his father?

04:37:16.979 --> 04:37:19.200
And did they hate it every day?

04:37:19.259 --> 04:37:22.619
Or was it just a normal job to them?

04:37:22.680 --> 04:37:25.799
He wondered if the chrysalis extended

04:37:25.799 --> 04:37:28.200
across hives, and whether any of them

04:37:28.200 --> 04:37:28.740
were in it.

04:37:28.799 --> 04:37:32.819
All around the hive were neatly laid out

04:37:32.819 --> 04:37:35.939
rows of enormous greenhouses, at least 30

04:37:35.939 --> 04:37:38.520
of them, in concentric circles

04:37:38.520 --> 04:37:41.159
surrounding the base of the hive, some

04:37:41.159 --> 04:37:44.159
were wild with growth, leaves rioting

04:37:44.159 --> 04:37:45.659
against the glass roofs.

04:37:45.720 --> 04:37:48.900
Others were quieter, with orderly rows of

04:37:48.900 --> 04:37:51.060
vegetables and soil boxes visible

04:37:51.060 --> 04:37:51.360
inside.

04:37:51.479 --> 04:37:56.819
That many greenhouses, so much glass.

04:37:56.880 --> 04:38:00.479
She needed fire to make that glass to

04:38:00.479 --> 04:38:02.400
build these, Blue thought.

04:38:02.459 --> 04:38:06.299
Fire she took from silk wings, from my

04:38:06.299 --> 04:38:06.479
dad.

04:38:06.540 --> 04:38:10.319
Flame silk was necessary to everything

04:38:10.319 --> 04:38:11.400
the queen did.

04:38:11.459 --> 04:38:14.639
She wasn't going to let them go easily.

04:38:14.700 --> 04:38:18.240
Soratell landed softly beside them.

04:38:18.299 --> 04:38:22.259
The main door is barred for the night, and

04:38:22.259 --> 04:38:24.060
possibly guarded inside as well.

04:38:24.119 --> 04:38:25.739
There's no way in there.

04:38:25.860 --> 04:38:28.500
He tipped his head back to study the

04:38:28.500 --> 04:38:28.919
hive.

04:38:28.979 --> 04:38:31.080
Let's think.

04:38:31.200 --> 04:38:33.479
Could we climb to one of the ledges?

04:38:33.540 --> 04:38:36.479
Cricket asked, using the vines and your

04:38:36.479 --> 04:38:37.200
silk for blue?

04:38:37.259 --> 04:38:40.739
Blue eyed the smooth walls of the hive

04:38:40.739 --> 04:38:41.519
uncertainly.

04:38:41.580 --> 04:38:44.099
It looked like a much more treacherous

04:38:44.099 --> 04:38:46.139
climb than the one out of the sinkhole

04:38:46.139 --> 04:38:48.419
and the nearest opening was a very long

04:38:48.419 --> 04:38:48.959
way up.

04:38:49.080 --> 04:38:54.540
Or, he said slowly, could we hide in one

04:38:54.540 --> 04:38:55.380
of the greenhouses?

04:38:55.439 --> 04:38:58.199
At least until we know a little more?

04:38:58.259 --> 04:39:01.799
That's a good point, Cricket said.

04:39:01.860 --> 04:39:04.740
If we go into the hive, we might get

04:39:04.740 --> 04:39:06.959
trapped in there, and it might not even

04:39:06.959 --> 04:39:08.459
be the right place to look, right?

04:39:08.520 --> 04:39:11.939
But if we find a place to hide, tomorrow

04:39:11.939 --> 04:39:14.099
I can go in and ask around about where

04:39:14.099 --> 04:39:15.360
the flame silks might be.

04:39:15.419 --> 04:39:19.379
Blue gave her an alarmed look, by

04:39:19.379 --> 04:39:19.739
yourself.

04:39:19.799 --> 04:39:22.500
Of course, she said.

04:39:22.560 --> 04:39:25.080
You 2 are probably all over the wanted

04:39:25.080 --> 04:39:27.599
posters by now, but who cares about me?

04:39:27.659 --> 04:39:30.779
I'm just a hive wing, doing normal hive

04:39:30.779 --> 04:39:31.380
wing things.

04:39:31.439 --> 04:39:35.519
Like suddenly appearing in a hive that's

04:39:35.519 --> 04:39:36.059
not your own?

04:39:36.119 --> 04:39:39.659
Blue said, asking obvious questions about

04:39:39.659 --> 04:39:41.459
the very thing that's got the queen

04:39:41.459 --> 04:39:43.139
running dragon hunts all over the

04:39:43.139 --> 04:39:43.679
Savannah.

04:39:43.740 --> 04:39:47.520
They won't be obvious questions.

04:39:47.580 --> 04:39:49.439
Cricket objected.

04:39:49.500 --> 04:39:52.380
They will be very subtle.

04:39:52.439 --> 04:39:55.740
I am an exceptionally subtle dragon, sir.

04:39:55.799 --> 04:39:59.159
Hmm, Blue said dubiously.

04:39:59.220 --> 04:40:02.580
Besides, it won't be suspicious because

04:40:02.580 --> 04:40:04.799
everyone will be talking about flame

04:40:04.799 --> 04:40:08.099
silks right now, she pointed out, and

04:40:08.099 --> 04:40:09.419
someone has to know where they are.

04:40:09.479 --> 04:40:12.180
Sortell was shaking his head.

04:40:12.240 --> 04:40:14.759
That's another day wasted.

04:40:14.819 --> 04:40:15.779
He said.

04:40:15.840 --> 04:40:18.900
Luna's only going to be in her cocoon 5

04:40:18.900 --> 04:40:19.319
days.

04:40:19.380 --> 04:40:21.959
We have to find her before she comes out

04:40:21.959 --> 04:40:24.479
and before Blue starts his own

04:40:24.479 --> 04:40:25.439
metamorphosis.

04:40:25.500 --> 04:40:28.439
Blue twitched, startled.

04:40:28.500 --> 04:40:30.959
His own metamorphosis.

04:40:31.020 --> 04:40:32.580
Thortell was right.

04:40:32.639 --> 04:40:35.340
That was... soon.

04:40:35.400 --> 04:40:38.759
Very, very soon.

04:40:38.819 --> 04:40:42.299
Where am I supposed to have my

04:40:42.299 --> 04:40:44.639
metamorphosis if I can't go back to the

04:40:44.639 --> 04:40:45.180
cocoon?

04:40:45.240 --> 04:40:48.119
And how can I help Luna if I'm stuck

04:40:48.119 --> 04:40:49.380
inside my own silk?

04:40:49.439 --> 04:40:52.919
I say we storm the hive right now.

04:40:53.040 --> 04:40:56.759
Soritell went on, I fly in, start

04:40:56.759 --> 04:40:58.979
knocking over guards, Force them to tell

04:40:58.979 --> 04:40:59.580
me where she is.

04:40:59.639 --> 04:41:03.659
I'd call that a splendid plan, Cricket

04:41:03.659 --> 04:41:04.080
said.

04:41:04.139 --> 04:41:08.639
If it resembled a plan in any way, You'll

04:41:08.639 --> 04:41:10.680
end up on the wasp hive version of

04:41:10.680 --> 04:41:13.259
misbehavior's way, before the sun is over

04:41:13.259 --> 04:41:13.919
the horizon.

04:41:13.979 --> 04:41:15.299
Blue agreed.

04:41:15.360 --> 04:41:19.319
And the wasp hive version might be more

04:41:19.319 --> 04:41:21.479
like headless corpses way.

04:41:21.540 --> 04:41:22.979
Cricket added.

04:41:23.040 --> 04:41:25.139
Soretail stamped his feet.

04:41:25.200 --> 04:41:27.479
I can't sit around all day again.

04:41:27.540 --> 04:41:31.560
We are not sitting around, Cricket said.

04:41:31.619 --> 04:41:34.919
We are spying and gathering information

04:41:34.919 --> 04:41:36.900
and thinking.

04:41:37.020 --> 04:41:39.479
You'd be surprised what a useful step

04:41:39.479 --> 04:41:40.860
that is when it comes to plans.

04:41:40.919 --> 04:41:44.099
She started down the hill toward the

04:41:44.099 --> 04:41:46.200
greenhouses, and the 2 silk wings

04:41:46.200 --> 04:41:46.680
followed her.

04:41:46.740 --> 04:41:49.020
Sortail grumbling under his breath.

04:41:49.080 --> 04:41:52.500
Blue felt guilty for being on Cricket's

04:41:52.500 --> 04:41:52.740
side.

04:41:52.799 --> 04:41:55.919
Of course, he wanted to rescue Luna just

04:41:55.919 --> 04:41:58.680
as much as Swortail did, but he didn't

04:41:58.680 --> 04:42:00.720
want to fight any guards, or demand

04:42:00.720 --> 04:42:03.900
answers, or rush in all teeth bared.

04:42:03.959 --> 04:42:06.299
He kind of wanted to do whatever would

04:42:06.299 --> 04:42:07.919
get him in the least trouble.

04:42:07.979 --> 04:42:09.900
That would also help Luna.

04:42:09.959 --> 04:42:13.139
The greenhouses were all the same size

04:42:13.139 --> 04:42:16.560
which was remarkably large, and divided

04:42:16.560 --> 04:42:19.080
from one another by neat gravel paths.

04:42:19.139 --> 04:42:22.139
Stakes with signs and arrows printed on

04:42:22.139 --> 04:42:24.479
them pointed the way to particular types

04:42:24.479 --> 04:42:27.180
of plants, and a list was affixed to the

04:42:27.180 --> 04:42:28.319
door of each greenhouse.

04:42:28.380 --> 04:42:32.639
Carrots, beans, eggplants, on one.

04:42:32.700 --> 04:42:37.560
Clementines, limes, on another, papyrus

04:42:37.560 --> 04:42:38.939
bamboo, on a third.

04:42:39.000 --> 04:42:41.759
They avoided the greenhouses that were

04:42:41.759 --> 04:42:44.159
too tidy, where every corner was visible

04:42:44.159 --> 04:42:46.619
and headed for the ones that looked the

04:42:46.619 --> 04:42:47.459
most overgrown.

04:42:47.520 --> 04:42:50.700
These are probably tended every day.

04:42:50.759 --> 04:42:53.939
Blue realized. as they walked between the

04:42:53.939 --> 04:42:55.139
towering glass walls.

04:42:55.200 --> 04:42:57.599
He was starting to feel anxious about his

04:42:57.599 --> 04:42:57.900
plan.

04:42:57.959 --> 04:43:00.840
Gardeners will come in to water the

04:43:00.840 --> 04:43:01.680
plants and find us.

04:43:01.740 --> 04:43:05.700
I will bonk them and conk them out

04:43:05.700 --> 04:43:07.619
Swordtail declared.

04:43:07.680 --> 04:43:09.479
Poor dragons.

04:43:09.540 --> 04:43:12.060
Just trying to do their jobs and take

04:43:12.060 --> 04:43:12.599
care of some plans.

04:43:12.659 --> 04:43:15.240
They don't deserve a day of being knocked

04:43:15.240 --> 04:43:17.639
unconscious, plus a massive headache.

04:43:17.700 --> 04:43:18.900
Blue thought.

04:43:19.020 --> 04:43:22.740
Well, said his brain unexpectedly.

04:43:22.799 --> 04:43:25.680
You don't deserve to be chased across the

04:43:25.680 --> 04:43:27.540
Savannah, and treated like a mass

04:43:27.540 --> 04:43:28.200
murderer.

04:43:28.259 --> 04:43:31.080
So perhaps there's a little unfairness to

04:43:31.080 --> 04:43:31.439
go around.

04:43:31.500 --> 04:43:35.099
He wrinkled his forehead, thinking about

04:43:35.099 --> 04:43:35.279
that.

04:43:35.340 --> 04:43:39.180
Did their injustice toward him mean that

04:43:39.180 --> 04:43:40.799
he'd be justified in hurting them?

04:43:40.860 --> 04:43:43.979
He wasn't the kind of dragon who ever

04:43:43.979 --> 04:43:46.799
hurt other dragons, but he could imagine

04:43:46.799 --> 04:43:47.939
what Luna would say.

04:43:48.000 --> 04:43:50.520
You're allowed to fight back.

04:43:50.580 --> 04:43:52.799
You should, when the world is like this.

04:43:52.860 --> 04:43:57.479
Look, Cricket whispered, pointing to one

04:43:57.479 --> 04:44:00.180
of the last greenhouses in the innermost

04:44:00.180 --> 04:44:02.099
circle near the back of the hive.

04:44:02.159 --> 04:44:04.860
The plant growth inside was dense and

04:44:04.860 --> 04:44:05.400
leafy.

04:44:05.459 --> 04:44:08.700
But what was even more interesting was

04:44:08.700 --> 04:44:10.619
the fact that the door was covered with a

04:44:10.619 --> 04:44:12.299
silk spun web barrier.

04:44:12.360 --> 04:44:15.540
They crossed to it and read the sign

04:44:15.540 --> 04:44:16.259
beside the door.

04:44:16.319 --> 04:44:20.639
Do not enter, by order of Queen Wasp

04:44:20.639 --> 04:44:22.259
Property of the Queen.

04:44:22.319 --> 04:44:25.560
Trespassing punishable by maiming

04:44:25.560 --> 04:44:29.099
dismemberment, impaling, and death, in

04:44:29.099 --> 04:44:29.580
that order.

04:44:29.639 --> 04:44:33.299
Blue lightly tapped the silk with one of

04:44:33.299 --> 04:44:35.459
his claws, and the threads vibrated.

04:44:35.520 --> 04:44:39.419
This is here, so she'll know if anyone

04:44:39.419 --> 04:44:40.380
tries to break in.

04:44:40.439 --> 04:44:43.020
Can you recreate it?

04:44:43.080 --> 04:44:46.500
Cricket asked Swordtail, from inside?

04:44:46.619 --> 04:44:49.680
Seems like a perfect place to hide if no

04:44:49.680 --> 04:44:50.459
one can come in here.

04:44:50.520 --> 04:44:55.979
Except, you know, Queen Wasp, Blue

04:44:55.979 --> 04:44:56.580
pointed out.

04:44:56.700 --> 04:45:00.779
Yeah, but she probably won't?

04:45:00.900 --> 04:45:02.279
Cricket guest.

04:45:02.340 --> 04:45:06.000
This sign is really clear though, Blue

04:45:06.000 --> 04:45:06.959
said anxiously.

04:45:07.020 --> 04:45:09.779
No trespassing at all.

04:45:09.840 --> 04:45:13.020
Maiming, and impaling, and death.

04:45:13.080 --> 04:45:16.259
I mean, this science seems to think it's

04:45:16.259 --> 04:45:17.400
a really serious rule.

04:45:17.459 --> 04:45:22.439
I think keep blue safe from brainwashed

04:45:22.439 --> 04:45:25.020
hive wings is a more serious rule.

04:45:25.080 --> 04:45:27.000
Cricket said firmly.

04:45:27.119 --> 04:45:31.740
Yeah, I can do this, said Swordtail, who'd

04:45:31.740 --> 04:45:32.580
been studying the web.

04:45:32.639 --> 04:45:35.819
It might not be an exact match, but it

04:45:35.819 --> 04:45:37.319
should look convincing enough from a

04:45:37.319 --> 04:45:37.979
distance.

04:45:38.040 --> 04:45:40.799
As Blue watched nervously.

04:45:40.860 --> 04:45:43.560
Swartail carefully dismantled the web

04:45:43.560 --> 04:45:45.479
enough for cricket to open the door.

04:45:45.720 --> 04:45:48.299
She stepped inside and let out a small

04:45:48.299 --> 04:45:48.840
gasp.

04:45:48.959 --> 04:45:52.080
It's really hot in here.

04:45:52.139 --> 04:45:54.180
She whispered back to them.

04:45:54.240 --> 04:45:56.459
How does she keep it this hot?

04:45:56.580 --> 04:45:59.099
I have a guess.

04:45:59.159 --> 04:46:01.200
Swordtail hissed.

04:46:01.259 --> 04:46:04.200
He scowled at the silk spiraling out of

04:46:04.200 --> 04:46:06.599
his wrists as he started reweaving the

04:46:06.599 --> 04:46:07.020
door cover.

04:46:07.080 --> 04:46:10.799
Blue squeezed in behind Cricket, and felt

04:46:10.799 --> 04:46:13.139
the humidity hit him, along with several

04:46:13.139 --> 04:46:14.459
flapping wet leaves.

04:46:14.580 --> 04:46:17.639
It was like walking into a storm cloud.

04:46:17.700 --> 04:46:20.939
He glanced down and wondered if the stone

04:46:20.939 --> 04:46:23.520
floor was lined with flame silk to keep

04:46:23.520 --> 04:46:24.299
it this temperature.

04:46:24.360 --> 04:46:28.080
Why do you think Queen Wasp keeps

04:46:28.080 --> 04:46:28.740
everyone out of here?

04:46:28.799 --> 04:46:31.080
Cricket whispered to him.

04:46:31.139 --> 04:46:33.900
Do any of these plants look unusual to

04:46:33.900 --> 04:46:34.080
you?

04:46:34.139 --> 04:46:37.799
I recognize some of them, but not all of

04:46:37.799 --> 04:46:38.099
them.

04:46:38.159 --> 04:46:39.599
Huh.

04:46:39.659 --> 04:46:42.000
She brushed his shoulder with her wing

04:46:42.000 --> 04:46:44.340
and they moved farther into the tangle of

04:46:44.340 --> 04:46:44.819
greenery.

04:46:44.880 --> 04:46:48.659
That was a good question, Blue realized.

04:46:48.720 --> 04:46:50.580
When he hadn't thought about.

04:46:50.639 --> 04:46:53.040
Because he was so tangled up in anxiety

04:46:53.040 --> 04:46:54.419
about breaking the rules.

04:46:54.779 --> 04:46:57.419
What was in here that Queen Wasp wanted

04:46:57.419 --> 04:46:58.619
to keep secret?

04:46:58.680 --> 04:47:01.139
Why was this place so forbidden?

04:47:01.200 --> 04:47:04.259
Now he could see that there were beds of

04:47:04.259 --> 04:47:06.779
dirt edged with boulders, and something

04:47:06.779 --> 04:47:07.919
like a path between them.

04:47:07.979 --> 04:47:11.400
But the plants had grown so wild that

04:47:11.400 --> 04:47:14.220
they vaulted over the paths, twined their

04:47:14.220 --> 04:47:16.259
branches together, and flung down

04:47:16.259 --> 04:47:18.240
curtains of hanging moss and trailing

04:47:18.240 --> 04:47:20.759
vines to disrupt any possible order.

04:47:20.819 --> 04:47:24.000
He and Cricket had to dock and weave

04:47:24.000 --> 04:47:26.220
through the greenery, and he kept getting

04:47:26.220 --> 04:47:29.220
his claws snagged on roots and unexpected

04:47:29.220 --> 04:47:29.639
runners.

04:47:29.700 --> 04:47:32.459
There were flowers everywhere too.

04:47:32.520 --> 04:47:35.819
Glorious purple exploding stars.

04:47:35.880 --> 04:47:40.380
Delicate pale orange orchids, clusters of

04:47:40.380 --> 04:47:43.319
petals, the color of bananas, and odd

04:47:43.319 --> 04:47:46.200
little globes and ruby red, and sapphire

04:47:46.200 --> 04:47:46.500
blue.

04:47:46.560 --> 04:47:48.840
What are these?

04:47:48.900 --> 04:47:51.720
Cricket whispered, mostly to herself?

04:47:51.840 --> 04:47:53.939
Fingering a vine of bright pink

04:47:53.939 --> 04:47:54.720
tendrils.

04:47:54.779 --> 04:47:56.580
And those.

04:47:56.639 --> 04:47:58.619
Why haven't we studied these?

04:47:58.680 --> 04:48:01.439
How did she get these 2 to grow next to

04:48:01.439 --> 04:48:01.799
each other?

04:48:01.860 --> 04:48:03.419
Whoa.

04:48:03.479 --> 04:48:05.520
Is that a new kind of fern?

04:48:05.580 --> 04:48:09.360
She wandered ahead, murmuring questions

04:48:09.360 --> 04:48:11.759
while Blue stopped to watch a really

04:48:11.759 --> 04:48:14.639
surprisingly cute snail, sauntering

04:48:14.639 --> 04:48:15.900
slowly up a tree trunk.

04:48:15.959 --> 04:48:19.380
Suddenly, Cricket's voice cut off with a

04:48:19.380 --> 04:48:21.060
shriek that was quickly muffled.

04:48:21.119 --> 04:48:23.520
Blue's head jerked up.

04:48:23.580 --> 04:48:26.759
Was Queen Wasp here, inside the

04:48:26.759 --> 04:48:27.360
greenhouse?

04:48:27.419 --> 04:48:29.099
Had she caught cricket?

04:48:29.159 --> 04:48:32.819
He ran after her, stumbling as he fought

04:48:32.819 --> 04:48:35.340
through vine tangles, and got smacked in

04:48:35.340 --> 04:48:38.459
the face by 80 more large wet leaves.

04:48:38.520 --> 04:48:40.619
He had to explain to the queen that none

04:48:40.619 --> 04:48:42.119
of this was Cricket's fault.

04:48:42.180 --> 04:48:43.619
He had to turn himself in.

04:48:43.680 --> 04:48:47.400
He pushed through a curtain of moss, and

04:48:47.400 --> 04:48:49.979
felt himself seized by strong claws.

04:48:50.040 --> 04:48:52.740
They threw him to the floor, flipped him

04:48:52.740 --> 04:48:55.439
onto his back. and tied all his talons

04:48:55.439 --> 04:48:57.659
together before he could even blink.

04:48:57.720 --> 04:49:00.180
He opened his mouth to yell for cricket.

04:49:00.240 --> 04:49:03.060
And another vine immediately looped

04:49:03.060 --> 04:49:05.759
around his snout, snapping his jaw shut.

04:49:05.819 --> 04:49:09.360
It felt as if barely a moment had passed

04:49:09.360 --> 04:49:11.880
but there he was, lying on the ground

04:49:11.880 --> 04:49:13.500
completely helpless.

04:49:13.560 --> 04:49:16.799
Blue craned his neck to look for cricket

04:49:16.799 --> 04:49:19.500
and spotted her, tied up the same way he

04:49:19.500 --> 04:49:21.360
was, and propped against a tree.

04:49:21.479 --> 04:49:25.500
Standing over her, was a wiry, dark green

04:49:25.500 --> 04:49:25.979
dragon.

04:49:26.040 --> 04:49:30.540
So, not Queen Wasp, he thought.

04:49:30.599 --> 04:49:33.240
Could that be the silk wing who covers

04:49:33.240 --> 04:49:33.840
the door for her?

04:49:33.900 --> 04:49:37.020
He tried to twist around to see his own

04:49:37.020 --> 04:49:39.959
attacker, and realized there were 3 of

04:49:39.959 --> 04:49:40.560
them all together.

04:49:40.619 --> 04:49:43.799
All of them had scales and shades of dark

04:49:43.799 --> 04:49:46.560
green, and they were all poised and

04:49:46.560 --> 04:49:49.080
waiting to catch Swordtail, who was

04:49:49.080 --> 04:49:50.759
blundering toward the noise Blue and

04:49:50.759 --> 04:49:51.540
Cricket had made.

04:49:51.599 --> 04:49:52.740
And then.

04:49:53.099 --> 04:49:55.259
Blue noticed something.

04:49:55.319 --> 04:49:57.060
Their captors.

04:49:57.119 --> 04:50:01.319
They had 2 wings each, not four.

04:50:01.380 --> 04:50:06.000
Long, graceful, swooping wings, shaped

04:50:06.000 --> 04:50:06.840
like leaves.

04:50:06.959 --> 04:50:11.279
Chapter 17.

04:50:11.459 --> 04:50:14.099
Leaf wings.

04:50:14.159 --> 04:50:16.439
They weren't extinct.

04:50:16.500 --> 04:50:17.880
They were here.

04:50:17.939 --> 04:50:21.419
In Queen Wasp's greenhouse, attacking

04:50:21.419 --> 04:50:24.119
dragons, real actual leaf wings.

04:50:24.180 --> 04:50:26.040
The posters were right.

04:50:26.099 --> 04:50:29.040
I should alert a hive wing authority

04:50:29.040 --> 04:50:31.860
immediately, Blue thought, feeling a

04:50:31.860 --> 04:50:32.580
little hysterical.

04:50:32.639 --> 04:50:35.279
But I can't, because they'll arrest me.

04:50:35.340 --> 04:50:39.659
But Leaf Wings, this close to Wasp Hive.

04:50:39.779 --> 04:50:42.659
He tried to grunt loudly to warn

04:50:42.659 --> 04:50:45.180
Swordtail, but it didn't do any good.

04:50:45.240 --> 04:50:47.459
The trio of leaf wings moved with a

04:50:47.459 --> 04:50:48.419
ruthless efficiency.

04:50:48.540 --> 04:50:51.779
And within a few heartbeats, Swordtail

04:50:51.779 --> 04:50:54.360
was tied up next to blue, blinking with

04:50:54.360 --> 04:50:55.500
similar bewilderment.

04:50:55.560 --> 04:50:57.659
Are there any more?

04:50:57.720 --> 04:50:59.159
One of them asked.

04:50:59.220 --> 04:51:03.000
I'll check, said another, and he quietly

04:51:03.000 --> 04:51:04.500
melted off into the trees.

04:51:04.560 --> 04:51:08.099
There was a long moment of silence.

04:51:08.159 --> 04:51:10.380
Blue glanced over at cricket again.

04:51:10.439 --> 04:51:13.319
She was watching the leaf wings with the

04:51:13.319 --> 04:51:16.139
same wide eyed expression she'd had when

04:51:16.139 --> 04:51:17.939
she saw the reading monkey in the cave.

04:51:18.000 --> 04:51:21.659
This is not an exciting scientific

04:51:21.659 --> 04:51:22.740
discovery cricket.

04:51:22.799 --> 04:51:24.360
He wanted to shout.

04:51:24.419 --> 04:51:28.020
These are very dangerous dragons.

04:51:28.080 --> 04:51:31.380
The leaf wings had tried to wipe out both

04:51:31.380 --> 04:51:32.639
their tribes in the last war.

04:51:32.759 --> 04:51:35.580
Wasn't she deathly afraid of them?

04:51:35.639 --> 04:51:38.700
He tried to look at the leaf wings with

04:51:38.700 --> 04:51:39.540
cricket's eyes.

04:51:39.599 --> 04:51:42.779
Maybe he would be less scared that way.

04:51:42.840 --> 04:51:45.959
Maybe he just needed to see them as

04:51:45.959 --> 04:51:48.720
fascinating and unusual, instead of

04:51:48.720 --> 04:51:50.819
deadly and really extremely deadly.

04:51:50.880 --> 04:51:54.360
The 2 that had stayed were both female

04:51:54.360 --> 04:51:56.880
and their faces were similar enough that

04:51:56.880 --> 04:51:58.319
he wondered if they were related.

04:51:58.380 --> 04:52:01.560
The one standing by cricket looked no

04:52:01.560 --> 04:52:04.139
older than he was, about 6 years old.

04:52:04.200 --> 04:52:07.860
Although he had no idea if leaf wings

04:52:07.860 --> 04:52:09.779
grew differently than silk wings.

04:52:09.840 --> 04:52:13.139
Small gold scales were speckled along the

04:52:13.139 --> 04:52:15.900
edges of her wings and talons, and across

04:52:15.900 --> 04:52:18.540
her snout, crinkled up in her scowl.

04:52:18.599 --> 04:52:21.540
The other one was a lot older and

04:52:21.540 --> 04:52:21.900
bigger.

04:52:22.020 --> 04:52:24.419
With an air of authority about her that

04:52:24.419 --> 04:52:27.180
made Blue instinctively want to hide, or

04:52:27.180 --> 04:52:28.979
say he was sorry, or both.

04:52:29.040 --> 04:52:31.619
Her scales were lighter green with

04:52:31.619 --> 04:52:32.580
patches of brown.

04:52:32.639 --> 04:52:35.880
And she had strange, pale burn scars

04:52:35.880 --> 04:52:38.400
splattered across her talons and up her

04:52:38.400 --> 04:52:39.000
forearms.

04:52:39.000 --> 04:52:42.060
Her scowl was also pretty terrifying.

04:52:42.119 --> 04:52:45.779
Both dragons had several small pouches

04:52:45.779 --> 04:52:49.439
hung about them, woven from long grass, or

04:52:49.439 --> 04:52:52.439
fashioned from leaves, Blue wondered what

04:52:52.439 --> 04:52:54.840
was inside, but had a sinking feeling

04:52:54.840 --> 04:52:56.459
that he would regret finding out.

04:52:56.520 --> 04:52:58.860
What are they thinking?

04:52:58.919 --> 04:53:00.119
He wondered.

04:53:00.180 --> 04:53:02.819
The matching scows were a pretty good

04:53:02.819 --> 04:53:05.159
clue that whatever it was, the general

04:53:05.159 --> 04:53:06.360
sentiment was hostile.

04:53:06.419 --> 04:53:08.880
How long have they been here?

04:53:08.939 --> 04:53:11.040
What are they here for?

04:53:11.099 --> 04:53:13.200
Are they glad they caught us?

04:53:13.259 --> 04:53:15.419
Or annoyed that we stumbled into their

04:53:15.419 --> 04:53:15.959
hiding place?

04:53:16.080 --> 04:53:17.759
Most important?

04:53:17.819 --> 04:53:20.159
What are they going to do with us?

04:53:20.220 --> 04:53:23.939
The leaves rustled, and the male leaf

04:53:23.939 --> 04:53:24.599
wing returned.

04:53:24.659 --> 04:53:27.840
He was a green, dark enough to disappear

04:53:27.840 --> 04:53:30.419
into shadows, and wore a small white

04:53:30.419 --> 04:53:32.340
seashell on a cord around his neck.

04:53:32.400 --> 04:53:34.380
He shook his head at the others.

04:53:34.439 --> 04:53:35.939
No one else.

04:53:36.060 --> 04:53:39.540
Good, said the older female.

04:53:39.599 --> 04:53:41.759
Did they break the web on the door?

04:53:41.819 --> 04:53:45.360
Yes, he said, but rebuilt it.

04:53:45.419 --> 04:53:48.360
Useful of them, she said.

04:53:48.419 --> 04:53:52.919
Huh, Blue thought, momentarily distracted

04:53:52.919 --> 04:53:53.580
from his panic.

04:53:53.700 --> 04:53:56.099
How did the leaf wings get in?

04:53:56.159 --> 04:53:59.700
They can't spin silk, so they couldn't

04:53:59.700 --> 04:54:01.080
have covered the door themselves.

04:54:01.139 --> 04:54:02.400
Could.

04:54:02.580 --> 04:54:05.220
Could Queen Wasp know they're here?

04:54:05.279 --> 04:54:07.259
He doubted that.

04:54:07.380 --> 04:54:11.819
Queen Wasp hated leaf wings for refusing

04:54:11.819 --> 04:54:12.779
to accept her rule.

04:54:12.840 --> 04:54:16.380
Why would she keep 3 of them stashed in a

04:54:16.380 --> 04:54:16.680
greenhouse?

04:54:16.740 --> 04:54:20.400
Across from him, Cricket flicked her tail

04:54:20.400 --> 04:54:22.740
trying to get the smaller leaf wings

04:54:22.740 --> 04:54:25.319
attention, but the scowling dragonette

04:54:25.319 --> 04:54:25.860
ignored her.

04:54:25.919 --> 04:54:29.340
The tall female, who seemed to be the

04:54:29.340 --> 04:54:31.979
leader of the group, scanned her 3

04:54:31.979 --> 04:54:33.959
captives with calculating green eyes.

04:54:34.020 --> 04:54:37.560
At last, she stepped forward and yanked

04:54:37.560 --> 04:54:39.419
the rope off Blue's snout.

04:54:39.479 --> 04:54:41.580
Ow he yelped.

04:54:41.639 --> 04:54:43.380
Who are you?

04:54:43.439 --> 04:54:45.720
she demanded, and what are you doing

04:54:45.720 --> 04:54:45.959
here?

04:54:46.080 --> 04:54:48.540
She jerked her head at cricket.

04:54:48.599 --> 04:54:51.000
Two silk wings with a hive wing?

04:54:51.060 --> 04:54:52.139
Do you work for her?

04:54:52.200 --> 04:54:55.020
No, Blue said.

04:54:55.080 --> 04:54:56.040
She's my friend.

04:54:56.099 --> 04:54:59.459
The youngest leaf wing let out a scornful

04:54:59.459 --> 04:55:02.040
laugh, but Blue's interrogator looked

04:55:02.040 --> 04:55:02.759
intrigued.

04:55:02.819 --> 04:55:07.259
Hive wings don't befriend Silk Wings, she

04:55:07.259 --> 04:55:07.560
said.

04:55:07.619 --> 04:55:08.819
They control you.

04:55:08.880 --> 04:55:10.439
They enslave you.

04:55:10.500 --> 04:55:11.700
They order you about.

04:55:11.759 --> 04:55:14.939
But then, that's what you signed up for

04:55:14.939 --> 04:55:15.599
isn't it?

04:55:15.659 --> 04:55:21.119
I, um, Blue said, I didn't sign up for

04:55:21.119 --> 04:55:22.500
anything, I think.

04:55:22.560 --> 04:55:25.979
True, said the male leaf wing.

04:55:26.040 --> 04:55:27.000
Too young.

04:55:27.060 --> 04:55:30.419
Don't be so literal, hemlock.

04:55:30.540 --> 04:55:31.799
The leader scoffed.

04:55:31.860 --> 04:55:34.020
You, tell me your names.

04:55:34.080 --> 04:55:38.700
I'm blue, he said, and that's cricket.

04:55:38.759 --> 04:55:40.860
And that's.

04:55:40.919 --> 04:55:43.259
He trailed off as he turned to Sortail

04:55:43.259 --> 04:55:45.060
and bound him furiously shaking his

04:55:45.060 --> 04:55:45.240
head.

04:55:45.299 --> 04:55:47.639
Ah, someone else.

04:55:47.700 --> 04:55:50.939
Trying to keep secrets won't do any good

04:55:50.939 --> 04:55:51.479
at this point.

04:55:51.540 --> 04:55:53.279
The leaf wing said.

04:55:53.340 --> 04:55:56.939
I only see 2 ways for this to end, with

04:55:56.939 --> 04:55:59.099
you all helping us, or dead.

04:55:59.159 --> 04:56:02.279
In the former case, it'll be much easier

04:56:02.279 --> 04:56:03.900
if we know your names.

04:56:03.959 --> 04:56:06.419
Or we could skip to the latter case right

04:56:06.419 --> 04:56:06.659
now.

04:56:06.720 --> 04:56:10.439
Sortell growled, and the little leaf wing

04:56:10.439 --> 04:56:11.700
bared her teeth at him.

04:56:11.759 --> 04:56:13.680
What?

04:56:13.680 --> 04:56:15.240
What are your names?

04:56:15.299 --> 04:56:17.700
Blue tried, thinking that was

04:56:17.700 --> 04:56:19.439
astonishingly brave of him.

04:56:19.500 --> 04:56:21.959
The leaf wing smiled slightly.

04:56:22.020 --> 04:56:25.619
I'm Belladonna, and that's Hemlock.

04:56:25.680 --> 04:56:27.360
Our daughter is sundew.

04:56:27.419 --> 04:56:29.639
Why would you tell them that?

04:56:29.759 --> 04:56:32.639
Sundew snapped in a burst of fury.

04:56:32.700 --> 04:56:34.619
They can't help us.

04:56:34.680 --> 04:56:36.659
They'll turn us in the moment they get a

04:56:36.659 --> 04:56:36.900
chance.

04:56:37.020 --> 04:56:39.900
We should kill them now and leave their

04:56:39.900 --> 04:56:41.939
corpses somewhere that'll really scare

04:56:41.939 --> 04:56:43.259
those worms in the hive.

04:56:43.319 --> 04:56:47.279
She lifted one of her wings and pulled a

04:56:47.279 --> 04:56:49.380
fiery red centipede out of a pouch.

04:56:49.380 --> 04:56:52.860
It flailed violently at the air, waving

04:56:52.860 --> 04:56:54.119
all its feet and hissing.

04:56:54.240 --> 04:56:59.400
Sundew, Belladonna said warningly, save

04:56:59.400 --> 04:57:00.000
that for later.

04:57:00.119 --> 04:57:03.240
Corpses lying around will notify the

04:57:03.240 --> 04:57:05.459
queen we're here, which would make our

04:57:05.459 --> 04:57:07.380
mission harder, remember?

04:57:07.500 --> 04:57:10.799
Sundew dropped the centipede back into

04:57:10.799 --> 04:57:11.520
its pouch.

04:57:11.580 --> 04:57:13.380
Her scowl deepened.

04:57:13.439 --> 04:57:18.419
Besides, Blue said, killing us would

04:57:18.419 --> 04:57:20.099
probably make the queen very happy.

04:57:20.159 --> 04:57:23.520
And I think maybe you don't want to do

04:57:23.520 --> 04:57:23.759
that?

04:57:23.819 --> 04:57:27.180
Belladonna narrowed her eyes at him.

04:57:27.240 --> 04:57:29.819
The queen wants you dead.

04:57:29.880 --> 04:57:31.080
Why?

04:57:31.139 --> 04:57:35.819
Well, he said, but he'd never been a good

04:57:35.819 --> 04:57:37.619
liar, and he couldn't come up with

04:57:37.619 --> 04:57:40.020
anything fast enough, and he didn't know

04:57:40.020 --> 04:57:41.520
what the right thing to say might be.

04:57:41.580 --> 04:57:44.159
So he went with the truth.

04:57:44.220 --> 04:57:48.119
She wants me locked up, in case I'm a

04:57:48.119 --> 04:57:48.720
flame silk.

04:57:48.779 --> 04:57:52.200
He held out his wrists, which looked as

04:57:52.200 --> 04:57:54.419
ordinary as ever, other than being

04:57:54.419 --> 04:57:55.740
covered in flaking paint.

04:57:55.799 --> 04:57:59.520
And she probably wants sore tailed dead

04:57:59.520 --> 04:58:01.680
because he attacked some guards to save

04:58:01.680 --> 04:58:02.159
my sister.

04:58:02.220 --> 04:58:04.740
And then he escaped cicada hive.

04:58:04.860 --> 04:58:06.779
Cricket.

04:58:06.840 --> 04:58:08.700
She doesn't know about cricket yet.

04:58:08.759 --> 04:58:10.139
I hope.

04:58:10.200 --> 04:58:13.319
But if she did, she'd be mad because

04:58:13.319 --> 04:58:15.000
cricket's been helping us hide from her.

04:58:15.060 --> 04:58:18.659
A helpful hive wing?

04:58:18.779 --> 04:58:20.939
Belladonna said thoughtfully.

04:58:21.000 --> 04:58:24.060
She regarded cricket in a way that made

04:58:24.060 --> 04:58:26.759
Blue think of quicksand. and crawler

04:58:26.759 --> 04:58:27.659
vines at midnight.

04:58:27.720 --> 04:58:31.500
That does sound like a useful dragon to

04:58:31.500 --> 04:58:31.740
know.

04:58:31.799 --> 04:58:35.759
Sounds like a bunch of 4 winged lies

04:58:35.759 --> 04:58:37.500
sundew spat.

04:58:37.560 --> 04:58:40.619
If Queen Wasp wanted you locked up, you'd

04:58:40.619 --> 04:58:41.759
be locked up.

04:58:41.819 --> 04:58:43.979
Not necessarily.

04:58:44.040 --> 04:58:47.099
She wants your whole tribe dead, and

04:58:47.099 --> 04:58:50.400
apparently you're, uh, not all that

04:58:50.400 --> 04:58:50.759
dead.

04:58:50.819 --> 04:58:52.740
Blue pointed out.

04:58:52.860 --> 04:58:55.619
By the way, how are you not dead?

04:58:55.680 --> 04:58:57.720
Are there a lot of you left?

04:58:57.779 --> 04:58:59.279
Where have you been living?

04:58:59.340 --> 04:59:02.040
None of your business.

04:59:02.040 --> 04:59:04.380
Sundew hissed.

04:59:04.439 --> 04:59:05.939
As if we tell you anything.

04:59:06.000 --> 04:59:08.159
Tree killers.

04:59:08.220 --> 04:59:09.720
Tree killers.

04:59:09.779 --> 04:59:12.060
Blue thought, startled.

04:59:12.119 --> 04:59:13.799
What an awful name.

04:59:13.860 --> 04:59:16.860
Was that how Leaf Wings saw the other 2

04:59:16.860 --> 04:59:17.340
tribes?

04:59:17.459 --> 04:59:20.520
Of course, it must be.

04:59:20.580 --> 04:59:21.900
After all.

04:59:21.959 --> 04:59:23.880
That's what we did.

04:59:23.939 --> 04:59:26.580
Even the silk wings, though?

04:59:26.700 --> 04:59:29.580
The silk wings only cut down trees under

04:59:29.580 --> 04:59:30.180
orders.

04:59:30.299 --> 04:59:32.939
Mostly they stayed out of the way as much

04:59:32.939 --> 04:59:33.479
as they could.

04:59:33.540 --> 04:59:37.740
But if I were a leaf wing, all I would

04:59:37.740 --> 04:59:40.740
see is hive wings destroying my home and

04:59:40.740 --> 04:59:43.080
silk wings helping, or standing by.

04:59:43.139 --> 04:59:47.759
If you are trying to hide from Queen Wasp

04:59:47.759 --> 04:59:51.060
Belladonna interjected, what are you

04:59:51.060 --> 04:59:52.020
doing in her greenhouse?

04:59:52.080 --> 04:59:54.840
Blue hesitated again.

04:59:54.900 --> 04:59:58.500
Sortel was shaking his head so hard, Blue

04:59:58.500 --> 05:00:00.119
thought it might topple right off his

05:00:00.119 --> 05:00:00.360
neck.

05:00:00.479 --> 05:00:03.479
But so what if these leaf wings knew

05:00:03.479 --> 05:00:04.200
about Luna?

05:00:04.259 --> 05:00:07.020
The longer he talked, the longer they all

05:00:07.020 --> 05:00:07.680
stayed alive.

05:00:07.740 --> 05:00:11.279
And maybe if he explained, and promised

05:00:11.279 --> 05:00:13.680
not to tell anyone they'd seen the leaf

05:00:13.680 --> 05:00:15.959
wings, Belladonna would decide to let

05:00:15.959 --> 05:00:16.319
them go.

05:00:16.380 --> 05:00:20.099
After all, it had to be pretty clear that

05:00:20.099 --> 05:00:22.080
he and his friends wouldn't be talking to

05:00:22.080 --> 05:00:25.080
Queen Wasp or any hive wing guards

05:00:25.080 --> 05:00:25.619
anytime soon.

05:00:25.680 --> 05:00:29.759
We're looking for my sister, he said.

05:00:29.819 --> 05:00:33.180
She's a flame silk, and Queen Wasp took

05:00:33.180 --> 05:00:33.419
her.

05:00:33.479 --> 05:00:36.599
We think she's keeping all the flame silk

05:00:36.599 --> 05:00:37.200
somewhere around here.

05:00:37.259 --> 05:00:41.639
Belladonna, hemlock, and sundew, all

05:00:41.639 --> 05:00:44.220
glanced at one another, suddenly alert.

05:00:44.279 --> 05:00:47.220
Bats, sundew started.

05:00:47.279 --> 05:00:50.279
Yes, Hemlock answered.

05:00:50.340 --> 05:00:53.880
Ah ha, said Belladonna.

05:00:53.939 --> 05:00:55.740
What?

05:00:55.860 --> 05:00:56.400
Blue asked.

05:00:56.459 --> 05:00:58.080
What aha.

05:00:58.139 --> 05:01:02.880
It seems, Belladonna said, taking a step

05:01:02.880 --> 05:01:05.880
closer to him, that we can be of use to

05:01:05.880 --> 05:01:07.259
one another after all.

05:01:07.319 --> 05:01:09.000
We.

05:01:09.000 --> 05:01:10.319
Can?

05:01:10.439 --> 05:01:14.040
You see, Belladonna went on.

05:01:14.099 --> 05:01:16.500
We know where the flame silks are.

05:01:16.619 --> 05:01:19.319
Blues jaw dropped.

05:01:19.380 --> 05:01:22.319
Cricket sat up, her ears twitching and

05:01:22.319 --> 05:01:23.099
her eyes bright.

05:01:23.159 --> 05:01:25.680
Even sore tail looked suddenly more

05:01:25.680 --> 05:01:26.700
excited than worried.

05:01:26.819 --> 05:01:28.380
Where are they?

05:01:28.500 --> 05:01:29.639
Blue asked.

05:01:29.700 --> 05:01:31.740
Did you see a new cocoon there?

05:01:31.799 --> 05:01:32.939
Was it all right?

05:01:33.000 --> 05:01:35.819
We can take you to their prison

05:01:35.819 --> 05:01:37.380
Belladonna said.

05:01:37.500 --> 05:01:40.560
We can even help you sneak in to rescue

05:01:40.560 --> 05:01:41.220
your sister.

05:01:41.340 --> 05:01:44.520
You just have to do one thing for us

05:01:44.520 --> 05:01:45.360
first.

05:01:45.419 --> 05:01:47.819
Blue's heart sank.

05:01:47.939 --> 05:01:50.700
Whatever the leaf wings wanted, it

05:01:50.700 --> 05:01:54.180
couldn't be good, or safe, or smart.

05:01:54.240 --> 05:01:57.959
I won't hurt anyone, he said.

05:01:58.020 --> 05:02:00.000
You don't have to.

05:02:00.060 --> 05:02:03.299
Belladonna said, with her quicksand

05:02:03.299 --> 05:02:03.779
smile.

05:02:03.900 --> 05:02:07.560
We are not here to attack the hive, or

05:02:07.560 --> 05:02:10.139
fight any dragons, no matter what your

05:02:10.139 --> 05:02:12.540
queen's propaganda says about us.

05:02:12.599 --> 05:02:14.880
We are here for one little thing.

05:02:14.939 --> 05:02:17.700
And since we've been having quite a lot

05:02:17.700 --> 05:02:19.919
of trouble figuring out how to accomplish

05:02:19.919 --> 05:02:22.860
our goal, I think you've come along just

05:02:22.860 --> 05:02:25.919
in the nick of time, a desperate silk

05:02:25.919 --> 05:02:29.099
wing, and a helpful hive wing are just

05:02:29.099 --> 05:02:29.759
what we need.

05:02:29.819 --> 05:02:32.400
For what?

05:02:32.459 --> 05:02:33.659
Blue asked.

05:02:33.720 --> 05:02:35.520
What do you want us to do?

05:02:35.580 --> 05:02:39.419
If you want our help finding your

05:02:39.419 --> 05:02:39.599
sister?

05:02:39.659 --> 05:02:41.759
Belladonna said smoothly.

05:02:41.819 --> 05:02:46.020
All you have to do is steal the book of

05:02:46.020 --> 05:02:47.220
clear sight for us.

05:02:47.279 --> 05:02:51.659
Chapter 18.

05:02:51.900 --> 05:02:56.099
Blue felt a reverent shiver run through

05:02:56.099 --> 05:02:58.979
him, even thinking the words book of

05:02:58.979 --> 05:02:59.639
clear sight.

05:02:59.759 --> 05:03:02.639
He'd spent a 100 nights lying in his

05:03:02.639 --> 05:03:05.520
hammock, gazing up at the silk shrouded

05:03:05.520 --> 05:03:07.979
stars, and imagining what it had been

05:03:07.979 --> 05:03:08.759
like to be her.

05:03:08.880 --> 05:03:12.900
The greatest seer who ever lived, the

05:03:12.900 --> 05:03:15.840
wisest of dragons, grandmother to an

05:03:15.840 --> 05:03:16.680
entire tribe.

05:03:16.799 --> 05:03:20.220
The legends said Clearsight had been able

05:03:20.220 --> 05:03:20.939
to see the future.

05:03:21.000 --> 05:03:24.900
But not just one future, all the possible

05:03:24.900 --> 05:03:25.619
futures.

05:03:25.680 --> 05:03:28.560
She had used that power to keep the

05:03:28.560 --> 05:03:30.419
tribes safe during her lifetime.

05:03:30.479 --> 05:03:33.840
They had survived hurricanes, forest

05:03:33.840 --> 05:03:37.380
fires, and a malevolent princess or four

05:03:37.380 --> 05:03:38.759
thanks to Clearsight.

05:03:38.819 --> 05:03:41.700
Her children and grandchildren and great

05:03:41.700 --> 05:03:44.040
grandchildren were protected from every

05:03:44.040 --> 05:03:47.700
danger, growing strong and powerful, and

05:03:47.700 --> 05:03:49.560
more numerous as the years went on.

05:03:49.619 --> 05:03:51.240
Then.

05:03:51.299 --> 05:03:54.000
When Clearsight saw her peaceful death

05:03:54.000 --> 05:03:57.180
approaching, she left one last gift for

05:03:57.180 --> 05:04:00.360
her descendants, a book that foretold the

05:04:00.360 --> 05:04:00.659
future.

05:04:00.720 --> 05:04:03.900
It warned them about everything in the

05:04:03.900 --> 05:04:04.319
years to come.

05:04:04.380 --> 05:04:07.380
The lightning strike that sheared away

05:04:07.380 --> 05:04:09.659
part of the sea cliff, the population

05:04:09.659 --> 05:04:11.819
explosion of sharks in the bay.

05:04:11.880 --> 05:04:14.939
The possible spread of a devastating bark

05:04:14.939 --> 05:04:15.959
disease in the forest.

05:04:16.020 --> 05:04:18.599
Clear sight wrote it all down.

05:04:18.659 --> 05:04:22.080
Centuries of warnings, so that she could

05:04:22.080 --> 05:04:24.540
continue to protect her beloved hive wing

05:04:24.540 --> 05:04:27.119
children, even long after her death.

05:04:27.180 --> 05:04:30.959
The book of Clearsight, was the hive

05:04:30.959 --> 05:04:32.159
wing's greatest treasure.

05:04:32.279 --> 05:04:34.680
It was the reason they were the most

05:04:34.680 --> 05:04:36.360
powerful tribe in Pentala.

05:04:36.419 --> 05:04:39.720
Queen Wasp had used it to defeat the leaf

05:04:39.720 --> 05:04:40.439
wings in the war.

05:04:40.560 --> 05:04:42.959
It made her invincible.

05:04:43.020 --> 05:04:46.380
And surely, Blue thought.

05:04:46.439 --> 05:04:48.779
Cold tentacles trailing through his

05:04:48.779 --> 05:04:49.200
mind.

05:04:49.259 --> 05:04:53.099
Surely, it included warnings about any

05:04:53.099 --> 05:04:55.500
dragons stupid enough to try to steal it

05:04:55.500 --> 05:04:55.860
from her.

05:04:55.919 --> 05:04:58.979
She might even know they were here right

05:04:58.979 --> 05:04:59.700
now.

05:04:59.759 --> 05:05:04.680
I know, Belladonna said, studying his

05:05:04.680 --> 05:05:05.220
face.

05:05:05.340 --> 05:05:08.220
I thought the same thing, but we've made

05:05:08.220 --> 05:05:08.819
it this far.

05:05:08.880 --> 05:05:10.799
And we've been hiding in her own

05:05:10.799 --> 05:05:13.740
greenhouse for 4 days without anyone

05:05:13.740 --> 05:05:14.939
showing up to capture us.

05:05:15.000 --> 05:05:18.659
If the book has warned her about us, she

05:05:18.659 --> 05:05:20.580
hasn't bothered to do anything about it

05:05:20.580 --> 05:05:26.159
yet, Hemlock added impassively, Belladonna

05:05:26.159 --> 05:05:28.799
shot him a look, we don't need them

05:05:28.799 --> 05:05:30.419
Sundew cried.

05:05:30.479 --> 05:05:32.759
I can steal the book of Clearsight by

05:05:32.759 --> 05:05:33.000
myself.

05:05:33.060 --> 05:05:37.200
You can't even get near the front door by

05:05:37.200 --> 05:05:37.619
yourself.

05:05:37.680 --> 05:05:40.020
Belladonna observed.

05:05:40.080 --> 05:05:43.200
Neither can we, Blue said.

05:05:43.259 --> 05:05:45.180
We're no use to your plan.

05:05:45.240 --> 05:05:47.580
We're wanted fugitives.

05:05:47.639 --> 05:05:51.119
She isn't, Hemlock said.

05:05:51.180 --> 05:05:53.220
Flicking one clawed cricket.

05:05:53.279 --> 05:05:54.779
That was true.

05:05:54.840 --> 05:05:56.400
Cricket could.

05:05:56.459 --> 05:05:58.860
But cricket was shaking her head.

05:05:58.919 --> 05:06:02.040
Blue's small flame of hope spluttered

05:06:02.040 --> 05:06:02.220
out.

05:06:02.279 --> 05:06:04.319
Of course she would say no.

05:06:04.380 --> 05:06:05.880
He couldn't blame her.

05:06:05.939 --> 05:06:07.979
She'd never even met Luna.

05:06:08.040 --> 05:06:10.680
She wouldn't risk her tribe's entire

05:06:10.680 --> 05:06:12.720
future to save a silk wing she didn't

05:06:12.720 --> 05:06:12.840
know.

05:06:12.959 --> 05:06:16.259
Helping a pathetic dragon hide from

05:06:16.259 --> 05:06:18.779
hunters was one thing, an exciting

05:06:18.779 --> 05:06:21.599
adventure, complete with anti paralysis

05:06:21.599 --> 05:06:23.159
smoke, and reading monkeys.

05:06:23.220 --> 05:06:26.220
Stealing the book of Clearsight, though?

05:06:26.279 --> 05:06:28.979
That was an unforgivable crime.

05:06:29.040 --> 05:06:32.700
She'd be betraying her whole tribe, not

05:06:32.700 --> 05:06:33.659
just her queen.

05:06:33.720 --> 05:06:37.740
No, Belladonna growled, suddenly

05:06:37.740 --> 05:06:38.159
furious.

05:06:38.220 --> 05:06:41.459
She darted across to cricket, and seized

05:06:41.459 --> 05:06:43.200
the hive wing's jaw in her talons.

05:06:43.259 --> 05:06:46.619
You don't say no to me, Hivewing.

05:06:46.680 --> 05:06:48.119
You have no right.

05:06:48.119 --> 05:06:50.880
After everything your tribe has done to

05:06:50.880 --> 05:06:53.099
our homes and our dragons.

05:06:53.159 --> 05:06:54.900
Don't hurt her.

05:06:55.020 --> 05:06:56.340
Blue cried.

05:06:56.400 --> 05:06:59.279
He tried to pull his talons free, but

05:06:59.279 --> 05:07:00.599
they were bound tightly.

05:07:00.659 --> 05:07:03.779
Look, can't you understand why she'd

05:07:03.779 --> 05:07:04.380
refuse?

05:07:04.439 --> 05:07:07.439
She wants to protect her tribe, same as

05:07:07.439 --> 05:07:07.619
you.

05:07:07.680 --> 05:07:10.259
You say you're not here to hurt anyone.

05:07:10.319 --> 05:07:12.900
But then what are you planning to do with

05:07:12.900 --> 05:07:14.040
a book once you have it?

05:07:14.099 --> 05:07:18.060
Belladonna hissed in Cricket's face and

05:07:18.060 --> 05:07:18.900
shoved her away.

05:07:18.959 --> 05:07:22.560
All we want to do is level the wind

05:07:22.560 --> 05:07:23.400
currents.

05:07:23.459 --> 05:07:24.360
She spat.

05:07:24.419 --> 05:07:27.060
Do you really think it's fair that the

05:07:27.060 --> 05:07:29.279
hive wings have had this secret knowledge

05:07:29.279 --> 05:07:32.880
for so long, that they've abused it to

05:07:32.880 --> 05:07:35.099
dominate and destroy other tribes?

05:07:35.159 --> 05:07:37.380
Do you think that's what your precious

05:07:37.380 --> 05:07:38.939
clear site intended?

05:07:39.000 --> 05:07:41.880
Cricket looked down at her feet.

05:07:41.939 --> 05:07:43.439
Blinking rapidly.

05:07:43.500 --> 05:07:47.040
Queen Wasp, has already read the whole

05:07:47.040 --> 05:07:49.200
thing, Belladonna went on.

05:07:49.259 --> 05:07:52.380
She probably even has a copy somewhere

05:07:52.380 --> 05:07:54.119
unless she's an idiot.

05:07:54.180 --> 05:07:56.279
We just want to read it too.

05:07:56.340 --> 05:07:58.979
Then we'll all know the same things.

05:07:59.040 --> 05:08:01.979
We'll have the same advance information.

05:08:02.040 --> 05:08:04.439
The leaf wings won't have anything more

05:08:04.439 --> 05:08:06.360
than what the hive wings have had for

05:08:06.360 --> 05:08:08.580
generations. equality.

05:08:08.639 --> 05:08:10.619
That's what we're looking for.

05:08:10.680 --> 05:08:13.080
Seems only fair.

05:08:13.139 --> 05:08:14.700
Hemlock agreed.

05:08:14.759 --> 05:08:19.200
But, um, Blue said nervously.

05:08:19.259 --> 05:08:21.779
But then won't you use that information

05:08:21.779 --> 05:08:23.220
to attack the hives?

05:08:23.279 --> 05:08:26.400
Belladonna's eyes glittered.

05:08:26.459 --> 05:08:29.279
That depends on what the book says.

05:08:29.340 --> 05:08:32.040
Stop being so nosy.

05:08:32.099 --> 05:08:34.259
Sundew said fiercely.

05:08:34.319 --> 05:08:37.080
Her talent twitched toward one of her

05:08:37.080 --> 05:08:39.180
pouches, but whatever was in there.

05:08:39.240 --> 05:08:41.220
She stopped herself from bringing it

05:08:41.220 --> 05:08:41.459
out.

05:08:41.520 --> 05:08:44.639
Either you help us or you die.

05:08:44.700 --> 05:08:45.840
It's very simple.

05:08:45.900 --> 05:08:49.139
Blue glanced at SwordTail.

05:08:49.200 --> 05:08:51.779
He could see instantly that SwordTail was

05:08:51.779 --> 05:08:52.560
fine with his plan.

05:08:52.619 --> 05:08:56.340
He'd be happy to help even leaf wings if

05:08:56.340 --> 05:08:58.979
it meant saving Luna, and he didn't care

05:08:58.979 --> 05:09:00.599
what happened to the hive wings

05:09:00.599 --> 05:09:01.020
afterward.

05:09:01.080 --> 05:09:03.419
But cricket.

05:09:03.479 --> 05:09:05.759
This was too much to ask.

05:09:05.819 --> 05:09:09.959
And yet, the truth was, it would be

05:09:09.959 --> 05:09:11.520
impossible to pull off without her.

05:09:11.580 --> 05:09:14.639
Blue closed his eyes and took a deep

05:09:14.639 --> 05:09:15.060
breath.

05:09:15.119 --> 05:09:18.779
I need to talk to my friends, he said.

05:09:18.840 --> 05:09:20.700
Give us some time to think about it.

05:09:20.759 --> 05:09:24.180
To think about it?

05:09:24.240 --> 05:09:26.400
Sundoo growled.

05:09:26.520 --> 05:09:28.799
She picked up a fallen branch and started

05:09:28.799 --> 05:09:31.080
snapping it into jagged splinters.

05:09:31.139 --> 05:09:32.759
Arrr.

05:09:32.819 --> 05:09:37.380
You have until midday, Belladonna said

05:09:37.380 --> 05:09:38.880
beckoning to her daughter.

05:09:38.939 --> 05:09:42.299
Then, we start formulating our plan.

05:09:42.360 --> 05:09:45.299
She turned and disappeared into the

05:09:45.299 --> 05:09:48.180
leaves, with sundew stomping furiously

05:09:48.180 --> 05:09:49.020
along behind her.

05:09:49.020 --> 05:09:52.979
Hemlock untied the vine around sore

05:09:52.979 --> 05:09:55.799
tail's snout, then stepped across and did

05:09:55.799 --> 05:09:57.180
the same for cricket.

05:09:57.240 --> 05:10:00.779
He paused, as the vine dropped away, and

05:10:00.779 --> 05:10:01.919
met Cricket's eyes.

05:10:01.979 --> 05:10:06.119
Choose wisely, he said to her.

05:10:06.180 --> 05:10:09.779
And then he, too, slipped away into the

05:10:09.779 --> 05:10:10.380
foliage.

05:10:10.439 --> 05:10:12.540
Blue looked up.

05:10:12.599 --> 05:10:15.959
This section was so overgrown, that he

05:10:15.959 --> 05:10:17.700
couldn't see the walls or the ceiling of

05:10:17.700 --> 05:10:18.240
the greenhouse.

05:10:18.299 --> 05:10:20.819
It was like they were in a cave made of

05:10:20.819 --> 05:10:21.180
leaves.

05:10:21.240 --> 05:10:24.180
But he could tell from their bright green

05:10:24.180 --> 05:10:26.700
color leeching into the plants that the

05:10:26.700 --> 05:10:27.959
sun was rising outside.

05:10:28.020 --> 05:10:30.779
He wondered if hunters were out already

05:10:30.840 --> 05:10:32.220
looking for him.

05:10:32.279 --> 05:10:35.520
Had anyone noticed cricket was missing

05:10:35.520 --> 05:10:35.700
yet?

05:10:35.759 --> 05:10:39.540
He rocked himself onto his side. and

05:10:39.540 --> 05:10:41.520
scooted awkwardly over the rocky ground

05:10:41.520 --> 05:10:43.259
until he was next to her.

05:10:43.319 --> 05:10:46.380
She gave him a half hearted smile, and

05:10:46.380 --> 05:10:47.700
nudged his neck with her nose.

05:10:47.759 --> 05:10:49.799
I'm sorry.

05:10:49.860 --> 05:10:53.759
He said to her, I'm really, really sorry

05:10:53.759 --> 05:10:55.080
I dragged you into this.

05:10:55.139 --> 05:10:58.080
Cricket looked very surprised.

05:10:58.139 --> 05:10:59.639
Did you?

05:10:59.700 --> 05:11:00.479
She said.

05:11:00.540 --> 05:11:03.419
I am pretty sure I dragged myself into it

05:11:03.419 --> 05:11:07.139
or leaped into it, with all 4 feet and

05:11:07.139 --> 05:11:07.979
all 4 wings.

05:11:08.040 --> 05:11:11.580
I might have been yelling, wee adventure

05:11:11.580 --> 05:11:14.220
in my head, if I didn't say that out

05:11:14.220 --> 05:11:14.520
loud.

05:11:14.580 --> 05:11:19.020
Well, maybe, he said, but you couldn't

05:11:19.020 --> 05:11:19.799
have expected this.

05:11:19.860 --> 05:11:23.400
Neither could you, she pointed out

05:11:23.400 --> 05:11:23.939
reasonably.

05:11:24.060 --> 05:11:26.700
Being captured by leaf wings?

05:11:26.759 --> 05:11:28.680
It's kind of amazing, isn't it?

05:11:28.740 --> 05:11:30.599
I can't believe they're still alive.

05:11:30.659 --> 05:11:33.360
Where have they been all this time?

05:11:33.419 --> 05:11:35.819
I must say they're a little more

05:11:35.819 --> 05:11:37.619
belligerent than I would have imagined.

05:11:37.680 --> 05:11:40.979
She moved her jaw from side to side

05:11:40.979 --> 05:11:41.759
wincing.

05:11:41.819 --> 05:11:43.139
Really?

05:11:43.200 --> 05:11:44.340
Blue said.

05:11:44.400 --> 05:11:46.919
We were taught that leaf wings would kill

05:11:46.919 --> 05:11:47.520
us on site.

05:11:47.580 --> 05:11:51.299
So to me, it seems quite friendly of them

05:11:51.299 --> 05:11:53.099
to postpone killing us until later.

05:11:53.220 --> 05:11:56.400
Cricket gave them a rueful smile.

05:11:56.459 --> 05:11:59.700
Is there any chance they won't kill us at

05:11:59.700 --> 05:12:00.060
all?

05:12:00.060 --> 05:12:00.959
she asked.

05:12:01.020 --> 05:12:05.639
Maybe if we help them, Blue said, or get

05:12:05.639 --> 05:12:06.540
away from them somehow.

05:12:06.659 --> 05:12:10.560
Blue glanced across at Sortail, who was

05:12:10.560 --> 05:12:12.779
flailing around on the ground, trying to

05:12:12.779 --> 05:12:15.299
bite away the vines binding his talons.

05:12:15.419 --> 05:12:18.180
Um, sore tail, he said.

05:12:18.240 --> 05:12:19.500
What do you think?

05:12:19.560 --> 05:12:22.200
I think they're listening to us.

05:12:22.259 --> 05:12:25.619
Sortell growled, so it's no use trying to

05:12:25.619 --> 05:12:27.000
make any escape plans.

05:12:27.060 --> 05:12:28.860
True.

05:12:28.979 --> 05:12:31.979
Belladonna's voice called from somewhere

05:12:31.979 --> 05:12:32.939
up in the branches.

05:12:33.000 --> 05:12:36.900
But I think we should help them, so I

05:12:36.900 --> 05:12:37.500
tell said.

05:12:37.560 --> 05:12:38.759
They have a point.

05:12:38.819 --> 05:12:41.279
The hive wings did destroy all their

05:12:41.279 --> 05:12:42.299
trees.

05:12:42.360 --> 05:12:44.880
Queen Wasp used the book's knowledge to

05:12:44.880 --> 05:12:46.139
nearly wipe them out.

05:12:46.200 --> 05:12:47.939
So why shouldn't they get to see the

05:12:47.939 --> 05:12:48.180
book?

05:12:48.240 --> 05:12:49.560
I don't care.

05:12:49.619 --> 05:12:51.659
As long as they take us to Luna.

05:12:51.720 --> 05:12:55.080
The only thing I'm not sure of is whether

05:12:55.080 --> 05:12:57.779
we can trust them to help us, after we do

05:12:57.779 --> 05:12:58.200
what they want.

05:12:58.259 --> 05:13:02.159
You can, Belladonna's voice called

05:13:02.159 --> 05:13:02.520
again.

05:13:02.580 --> 05:13:04.680
Of course you can.

05:13:04.740 --> 05:13:06.299
You ungrateful Beatles.

05:13:06.419 --> 05:13:08.700
Sundew yelled from somewhere else.

05:13:08.759 --> 05:13:11.700
We are not lying conniving hive wings.

05:13:11.759 --> 05:13:13.259
We're leaf wings.

05:13:13.319 --> 05:13:14.099
We are honorable.

05:13:14.220 --> 05:13:17.279
If you want to be in this conversation

05:13:17.279 --> 05:13:20.159
Blue shouted, just come back and be in it

05:13:20.159 --> 05:13:20.700
already.

05:13:20.759 --> 05:13:23.459
There was a moment of wrestling silence.

05:13:23.520 --> 05:13:27.540
No, no, said Belladonna's voice.

05:13:27.599 --> 05:13:29.939
Carry on. pretend we're not here.

05:13:30.000 --> 05:13:32.459
Sortail snorted.

05:13:32.520 --> 05:13:34.799
Well, I'm worried.

05:13:34.860 --> 05:13:37.020
Blue said to Swordtail.

05:13:37.080 --> 05:13:40.439
First of all, I'm sure it's impossible to

05:13:40.439 --> 05:13:41.159
steal the book.

05:13:41.220 --> 05:13:45.479
Secondly, even if we could, giving it to

05:13:45.479 --> 05:13:47.639
a tribe who tried to wipe us all out once

05:13:47.639 --> 05:13:49.979
upon a time, seems like maybe a bad

05:13:49.979 --> 05:13:50.279
idea.

05:13:50.400 --> 05:13:55.139
That's not what we, Sundew bellowed.

05:13:55.200 --> 05:13:56.639
Shh.

05:13:56.700 --> 05:13:58.680
Paladonna hushed her.

05:13:58.740 --> 05:14:02.099
We're leaving anyway, aren't we?

05:14:02.159 --> 05:14:03.599
Sortell said.

05:14:03.659 --> 05:14:05.099
We can't ever go home.

05:14:05.159 --> 05:14:09.240
You and me and Luna and IO if we can find

05:14:09.240 --> 05:14:09.540
her.

05:14:09.599 --> 05:14:13.259
And you too, if you want to come, he said

05:14:13.259 --> 05:14:13.860
to Cricket.

05:14:13.979 --> 05:14:16.080
We'll have to find a new place to live.

05:14:16.200 --> 05:14:20.099
Far away from Wasp, and the hives, and

05:14:20.099 --> 05:14:21.479
all her zombie hordes.

05:14:21.479 --> 05:14:24.240
So why should we care what happens to her

05:14:24.240 --> 05:14:26.400
or them after we're gone?

05:14:26.459 --> 05:14:29.220
We'll be safe, far away from here.

05:14:29.279 --> 05:14:32.939
But what about everyone else?

05:14:33.000 --> 05:14:34.380
Blue asked.

05:14:34.439 --> 05:14:36.900
Burn it and Silverspot?

05:14:36.959 --> 05:14:40.080
Your parents, all the dragons we went to

05:14:40.080 --> 05:14:40.500
school with.

05:14:40.560 --> 05:14:43.919
All our teachers, Cricket's sister.

05:14:43.979 --> 05:14:45.900
Don't you care about any of them?

05:14:45.959 --> 05:14:50.400
Soretail coiled his tail in close and

05:14:50.400 --> 05:14:51.240
spread his wings.

05:14:51.360 --> 05:14:54.659
I care about Luna, he said.

05:14:54.720 --> 05:14:55.680
That's it.

05:14:55.740 --> 05:14:59.220
Blue couldn't imagine that was true.

05:14:59.279 --> 05:15:01.619
Blue cared about all of them.

05:15:01.740 --> 05:15:05.159
Every dragon he'd ever spoken to, and all

05:15:05.159 --> 05:15:06.119
the ones he'd never seen.

05:15:06.180 --> 05:15:08.880
There were dragons out there eating

05:15:08.880 --> 05:15:11.700
blueberries, and dragons laughing at

05:15:11.700 --> 05:15:14.639
clumsy tiger cubs, and dragons learning

05:15:14.639 --> 05:15:17.400
to dance, and dragons crying as though

05:15:17.400 --> 05:15:19.020
their hearts would break over missing

05:15:19.020 --> 05:15:19.740
homework.

05:15:19.799 --> 05:15:22.080
He'd been all of them in some way.

05:15:22.139 --> 05:15:24.659
And he couldn't just toss them into the

05:15:24.659 --> 05:15:27.180
talons of these angry, vengeful dragons

05:15:27.180 --> 05:15:28.259
and fly off.

05:15:28.319 --> 05:15:31.259
He turned back to cricket.

05:15:31.319 --> 05:15:34.560
She'd managed to snap off a twig from the

05:15:34.560 --> 05:15:36.720
bush behind her, holding it between her

05:15:36.720 --> 05:15:38.459
teeth and passing it to her bound

05:15:38.459 --> 05:15:39.180
talons.

05:15:39.240 --> 05:15:42.119
She caught Blue's eye, and tapped the

05:15:42.119 --> 05:15:42.900
dirt with his stick.

05:15:42.959 --> 05:15:47.580
I'm not sure we have a choice, she said

05:15:47.580 --> 05:15:48.000
out loud.

05:15:48.060 --> 05:15:52.200
Awkwardly, she wrote, Pretend to agree.

05:15:52.259 --> 05:15:53.759
Escape later.

05:15:53.819 --> 05:15:56.580
Blue tilted his head at her.

05:15:56.639 --> 05:15:58.139
Could they do that?

05:15:58.200 --> 05:16:01.319
Say yes to the Leaf Wings plan?

05:16:01.380 --> 05:16:05.220
Agreed to go after the book, and then run

05:16:05.220 --> 05:16:06.840
off once they were inside the hive?

05:16:06.900 --> 05:16:10.439
They wouldn't have the leaf wings help to

05:16:10.439 --> 05:16:11.099
find Luna.

05:16:11.159 --> 05:16:13.500
But with luck, they could find her

05:16:13.500 --> 05:16:13.860
themselves.

05:16:13.919 --> 05:16:15.900
It felt underhanded.

05:16:15.959 --> 05:16:19.139
He didn't like lying to anyone, or

05:16:19.139 --> 05:16:20.159
breaking promises.

05:16:20.220 --> 05:16:23.639
Of course, he didn't love stealing

05:16:23.639 --> 05:16:25.139
priceless artifacts either.

05:16:25.200 --> 05:16:28.560
It's like Sundew said, right?

05:16:28.619 --> 05:16:30.000
Cricket went on.

05:16:30.060 --> 05:16:32.759
We do what they want, or they'll kill

05:16:32.759 --> 05:16:32.939
us.

05:16:33.060 --> 05:16:35.639
I won't let them kill you.

05:16:35.759 --> 05:16:37.080
Blue said.

05:16:37.139 --> 05:16:41.099
Something like a, ha. came from the

05:16:41.099 --> 05:16:43.619
direction of sundew's voice, followed by

05:16:43.619 --> 05:16:46.139
a shh, and the sound of a scuffle.

05:16:46.200 --> 05:16:49.500
Cricket tapped her message again, watching

05:16:49.500 --> 05:16:50.520
him significantly.

05:16:50.580 --> 05:16:54.299
Let's hear their plan, she said.

05:16:54.360 --> 05:16:56.939
If stealing the book means helping your

05:16:56.939 --> 05:17:00.599
sister and not dying, I can do that.

05:17:00.720 --> 05:17:04.020
They are right that Queen Wasp and the

05:17:04.020 --> 05:17:05.939
librarian already know everything that's

05:17:05.939 --> 05:17:06.599
in it anyway.

05:17:06.659 --> 05:17:11.099
Soratel had given up on untying his vines

05:17:11.099 --> 05:17:13.860
and lay in an undignified heap on the

05:17:13.860 --> 05:17:15.540
path, frowning at them.

05:17:15.599 --> 05:17:17.099
From his angle.

05:17:17.159 --> 05:17:19.740
Blue was pretty sure Sortell couldn't

05:17:19.740 --> 05:17:20.819
read what cricket had written.

05:17:20.880 --> 05:17:22.619
But it didn't matter.

05:17:22.680 --> 05:17:25.200
Once they were away from the leaf wings

05:17:25.200 --> 05:17:27.659
he'd explain, and Sortail would

05:17:27.659 --> 05:17:27.959
understand.

05:17:28.020 --> 05:17:31.139
Sounds like we're all in agreement

05:17:31.139 --> 05:17:32.700
Swordtail said.

05:17:32.819 --> 05:17:35.700
Blue sighed and leaned forward to brush

05:17:35.700 --> 05:17:36.959
away Cricket's message.

05:17:37.020 --> 05:17:39.840
All right, he called.

05:17:39.900 --> 05:17:42.900
We'll steal the book of Clearside for

05:17:42.900 --> 05:17:43.080
you.

05:17:43.139 --> 05:17:47.759
Chapter 19.

05:17:47.939 --> 05:17:51.479
Cricket's plan began to fall apart

05:17:51.479 --> 05:17:52.200
immediately.

05:17:52.259 --> 05:17:55.319
In the 1st place, the leaf wings were

05:17:55.319 --> 05:17:57.299
adamant that sundew had to go with them

05:17:57.299 --> 05:17:58.439
to sneak into the temple.

05:17:58.500 --> 05:18:00.360
What?

05:18:00.419 --> 05:18:01.560
Cricket said.

05:18:01.619 --> 05:18:02.459
How?

05:18:02.520 --> 05:18:04.619
There's no way to get her through the

05:18:04.619 --> 05:18:05.580
hive unnoticed.

05:18:05.639 --> 05:18:08.099
The 1st guard who spots her will kill

05:18:08.099 --> 05:18:08.700
her.

05:18:08.759 --> 05:18:11.759
In fact, any hive wing who sees her would

05:18:11.759 --> 05:18:12.659
probably do the same.

05:18:12.720 --> 05:18:14.759
It's true.

05:18:14.819 --> 05:18:16.500
Blue agreed.

05:18:16.560 --> 05:18:18.779
They are terrifying posters about you

05:18:18.779 --> 05:18:19.200
everywhere.

05:18:19.259 --> 05:18:23.340
We've been working on that, Belladonna

05:18:23.340 --> 05:18:23.700
said.

05:18:23.759 --> 05:18:26.220
Blue couldn't help thinking she seemed

05:18:26.220 --> 05:18:28.740
remarkably unconcerned about sending her

05:18:28.740 --> 05:18:29.580
daughter into danger.

05:18:29.639 --> 05:18:32.880
The tall leaf wing produced a pair of

05:18:32.880 --> 05:18:35.279
leaves that were similar in shape to the

05:18:35.279 --> 05:18:37.619
2nd smaller pair of wings on a silk

05:18:37.619 --> 05:18:37.979
wing.

05:18:37.979 --> 05:18:41.880
Sundew stood still, shooting daggers at

05:18:41.880 --> 05:18:44.459
cricket with her eyes, while Belladonna

05:18:44.459 --> 05:18:46.919
and Hemlock fastened the fake wings below

05:18:46.919 --> 05:18:48.599
and behind her real ones.

05:18:48.659 --> 05:18:51.779
Using a system of rigging them with vine

05:18:51.779 --> 05:18:54.119
ties under sundew's many pouches.

05:18:54.240 --> 05:18:56.099
No flying.

05:18:56.159 --> 05:18:59.880
Hemlock said sternly. touching sundew's

05:18:59.880 --> 05:19:00.299
snout.

05:19:00.419 --> 05:19:03.599
But as long as she keeps her wings folded

05:19:03.599 --> 05:19:06.180
it should be convincing enough inside the

05:19:06.180 --> 05:19:09.659
hive, Belladonna said, walking up to the

05:19:09.659 --> 05:19:12.840
guards outside, in sunlight, with plenty

05:19:12.840 --> 05:19:14.520
of opportunity for them to watch her

05:19:14.520 --> 05:19:16.740
coming, that was the part we were having

05:19:16.740 --> 05:19:17.340
trouble with.

05:19:17.340 --> 05:19:21.240
She smiled at cricket, a smile that went

05:19:21.240 --> 05:19:22.560
nowhere near her eyes.

05:19:22.619 --> 05:19:25.799
That's where you come in.

05:19:25.919 --> 05:19:31.020
She's still very green and leafy looking

05:19:31.080 --> 05:19:32.580
cricket protested.

05:19:32.639 --> 05:19:36.119
Even her real wings look like leaves, and

05:19:36.119 --> 05:19:38.099
she's so green.

05:19:38.159 --> 05:19:39.540
Blue.

05:19:39.599 --> 05:19:42.000
There aren't any silk wings that green

05:19:42.000 --> 05:19:42.720
are there?

05:19:42.779 --> 05:19:45.900
He spent a moment trying to remember all

05:19:45.900 --> 05:19:48.599
the green silk wings he knew before he

05:19:48.599 --> 05:19:50.700
realized that cricket wanted him to say

05:19:50.700 --> 05:19:53.400
oh no, never that green.

05:19:53.459 --> 05:19:55.860
We can fix that too.

05:19:55.919 --> 05:19:58.080
Sundu said spiritedly.

05:19:58.200 --> 05:20:01.860
She dumped out one of her pouches, sending

05:20:01.860 --> 05:20:04.080
a rainstorm of flower petals to the

05:20:04.080 --> 05:20:04.259
ground.

05:20:04.319 --> 05:20:06.419
Without choosing carefully.

05:20:06.479 --> 05:20:09.240
She grabbed a scarlet flower and rubbed

05:20:09.240 --> 05:20:11.400
it on her shoulder, leaving a patch of

05:20:11.400 --> 05:20:12.060
reddish green.

05:20:12.119 --> 05:20:17.159
Let me, hemlock said, gently taking the

05:20:17.159 --> 05:20:18.360
flower out of her talons.

05:20:18.419 --> 05:20:21.240
He sorted the pedals quickly into piles

05:20:21.240 --> 05:20:23.939
by color, then started applying rubbings

05:20:23.939 --> 05:20:26.340
of yellow, red, and blue in an even

05:20:26.340 --> 05:20:27.000
pattern.

05:20:27.060 --> 05:20:30.779
Cricket watched skeptically, but Blue was

05:20:30.779 --> 05:20:31.380
fairly impressed.

05:20:31.439 --> 05:20:34.020
It wasn't as thorough as the paint

05:20:34.020 --> 05:20:36.720
cricket had put on him, but it did make

05:20:36.720 --> 05:20:39.240
sundew look much less like a leaf wing by

05:20:39.240 --> 05:20:40.380
the time hemlock was done.

05:20:40.500 --> 05:20:43.740
Although maybe not quite a silk wing.

05:20:43.799 --> 05:20:46.979
She looked a little too furious to be a

05:20:46.979 --> 05:20:49.619
real silk wing, and the combination of

05:20:49.619 --> 05:20:51.360
colors wasn't exactly beautiful.

05:20:51.419 --> 05:20:53.880
The belladonna might be right.

05:20:53.939 --> 05:20:57.119
It was at least possible now that Sundew

05:20:57.119 --> 05:20:59.220
could pass through the corridors of Wasp

05:20:59.220 --> 05:21:00.720
Hive without getting caught.

05:21:00.779 --> 05:21:04.919
Wait, that's bad, he remembered.

05:21:04.979 --> 05:21:06.900
We want to leave her behind.

05:21:06.959 --> 05:21:09.479
We'll never be able to escape with her

05:21:09.479 --> 05:21:09.959
watching us.

05:21:10.020 --> 05:21:13.680
But there was no way to convince the leaf

05:21:13.680 --> 05:21:15.360
wings without raising their suspicions.

05:21:15.419 --> 05:21:17.880
And then it got worse.

05:21:17.939 --> 05:21:22.680
These 2 stay behind with us, Belladonna

05:21:22.680 --> 05:21:25.259
said, pointing to blue and sword tail.

05:21:25.319 --> 05:21:26.759
No way.

05:21:26.819 --> 05:21:28.680
Swordtail blurted.

05:21:28.740 --> 05:21:31.319
Cricket folded back her wings and lifted

05:21:31.319 --> 05:21:31.979
her chin.

05:21:32.040 --> 05:21:35.340
I'm not going without them, she said.

05:21:35.400 --> 05:21:36.599
I won't do it.

05:21:36.659 --> 05:21:37.919
I don't trust you.

05:21:37.979 --> 05:21:43.319
And I don't trust you, hive wing, said

05:21:43.319 --> 05:21:46.259
Belladonna, which is exactly why they're

05:21:46.259 --> 05:21:48.060
staying where I can keep an eye on them.

05:21:48.119 --> 05:21:50.700
You can have them back when I have the

05:21:50.700 --> 05:21:51.000
book.

05:21:51.060 --> 05:21:55.560
No, Cricket said, standing her ground.

05:21:55.619 --> 05:21:57.180
I can't do this alone.

05:21:57.240 --> 05:22:01.919
You'll have sun do, Belladonna pointed

05:22:01.919 --> 05:22:02.159
out.

05:22:02.220 --> 05:22:06.779
Yeah, Sundew said, you'll have me.

05:22:06.840 --> 05:22:09.299
That's like the opposite of being alone.

05:22:09.360 --> 05:22:12.419
I can do anything 20 dragons can do.

05:22:12.479 --> 05:22:17.220
I need my friends, Cricket said firmly.

05:22:17.279 --> 05:22:20.939
Belladonna and Hemlock exchanged a long

05:22:20.939 --> 05:22:21.840
thoughtful look.

05:22:21.900 --> 05:22:25.979
Finally, Hemlock said, just one.

05:22:26.040 --> 05:22:28.860
Both, said Cricket.

05:22:28.919 --> 05:22:32.099
One, said Belladonna.

05:22:32.159 --> 05:22:33.479
Choose which?

05:22:33.540 --> 05:22:35.759
Or we'll kill one of them and make your

05:22:35.759 --> 05:22:37.080
choice very easy.

05:22:37.139 --> 05:22:39.419
Cricket hesitated.

05:22:39.479 --> 05:22:41.819
Blue felt awful for her.

05:22:41.880 --> 05:22:44.700
How could they all escape if one of them

05:22:44.700 --> 05:22:47.220
was stuck in the greenhouse, but there

05:22:47.220 --> 05:22:48.360
wasn't anything she could do.

05:22:48.419 --> 05:22:49.680
He could see that.

05:22:49.740 --> 05:22:52.080
Lou.

05:22:52.200 --> 05:22:56.099
Cricket said, in a subdued voice, I'll

05:22:56.099 --> 05:22:56.700
take Blue.

05:22:56.759 --> 05:23:00.540
You should take sword tail, he said.

05:23:00.599 --> 05:23:03.180
He's a better fighter than me, if things

05:23:03.180 --> 05:23:03.659
go bad.

05:23:03.720 --> 05:23:07.740
I assume that's what she's for.

05:23:07.799 --> 05:23:10.500
Cricket said, nodding at Sundew.

05:23:10.560 --> 05:23:13.860
I really want you to come with me, Blue.

05:23:13.979 --> 05:23:14.939
Please?

05:23:15.000 --> 05:23:18.119
He realized that she was scared.

05:23:18.180 --> 05:23:21.060
Maybe even more scared than he was.

05:23:21.119 --> 05:23:24.840
She had gotten into this for him, and she

05:23:24.840 --> 05:23:27.720
felt safer with him than Swordtail, who

05:23:27.720 --> 05:23:30.180
she barely knew, and who had a tendency

05:23:30.180 --> 05:23:32.220
to say mean things about hive wings.

05:23:32.279 --> 05:23:35.520
Blue was afraid he'd be more than useless

05:23:35.520 --> 05:23:35.880
to her.

05:23:35.939 --> 05:23:39.060
But if she wanted him, he'd go to the

05:23:39.060 --> 05:23:41.880
ends of Penthala, or anywhere she asked.

05:23:41.939 --> 05:23:44.759
Of course, he said.

05:23:44.819 --> 05:23:47.580
Maybe they'd have a chance to slip away

05:23:47.580 --> 05:23:48.479
from Sundew.

05:23:48.540 --> 05:23:51.000
Maybe they'd come up with a way to save

05:23:51.000 --> 05:23:54.840
Swordtail and get out of this, even if he

05:23:54.840 --> 05:23:56.459
couldn't think of any solutions right

05:23:56.459 --> 05:23:56.700
now.

05:23:56.759 --> 05:24:00.900
Hemlock cut them loose, and let Cricket

05:24:00.900 --> 05:24:03.479
use some of the flower dye to cover the

05:24:03.479 --> 05:24:05.819
spots where Blue's real colors were

05:24:05.819 --> 05:24:06.119
showing through.

05:24:06.180 --> 05:24:10.020
The result was lopsided and weird looking

05:24:10.020 --> 05:24:12.720
like he had some kind of scale disease

05:24:12.720 --> 05:24:14.880
where bits of him were flaking off.

05:24:14.939 --> 05:24:18.119
But maybe that would make other dragons

05:24:18.119 --> 05:24:20.700
especially hive wings, keep their

05:24:20.700 --> 05:24:21.479
distance from him.

05:24:21.540 --> 05:24:24.240
The day felt endless.

05:24:24.299 --> 05:24:27.000
And yet it was alarmingly soon when

05:24:27.000 --> 05:24:31.080
Belladonna said, It's dusk, time to go.

05:24:31.139 --> 05:24:34.740
Blue took one of SoraTail's talons in his

05:24:34.740 --> 05:24:36.299
and squeezed.

05:24:36.360 --> 05:24:39.119
We'll come back for you, he said.

05:24:39.180 --> 05:24:43.020
I know, Swartell said, with the book.

05:24:43.080 --> 05:24:44.520
I know you can do it.

05:24:44.580 --> 05:24:48.240
How do I tell him we're only pretending?

05:24:48.360 --> 05:24:50.040
Blue thought desperately.

05:24:50.099 --> 05:24:52.500
How do I warn him he needs to escape?

05:24:52.560 --> 05:24:54.900
There was no way.

05:24:54.959 --> 05:24:58.139
Hemlock was standing next to him, watching

05:24:58.139 --> 05:24:59.159
them like a hawk.

05:24:59.220 --> 05:25:01.860
Right, Blue said.

05:25:01.919 --> 05:25:03.959
See you soon, swordtail.

05:25:04.080 --> 05:25:06.959
Sundew led them through the tangled

05:25:06.959 --> 05:25:08.819
greenery to the back of the greenhouse

05:25:08.819 --> 05:25:11.099
facing away from the hive.

05:25:11.159 --> 05:25:13.680
Carefully, she tapped on a pane of the

05:25:13.680 --> 05:25:14.220
glass wall.

05:25:14.279 --> 05:25:16.680
Then wedged her claws in the cracks

05:25:16.680 --> 05:25:18.900
around the edges, and levered it out.

05:25:18.959 --> 05:25:21.659
Oh, Cricket said.

05:25:21.720 --> 05:25:23.880
I wondered what you did to get in.

05:25:23.939 --> 05:25:27.000
Oh dear, isn't that going to be bad for

05:25:27.000 --> 05:25:27.419
the plans?

05:25:27.479 --> 05:25:30.959
I don't care 2 frogs about the plants.

05:25:31.080 --> 05:25:32.340
Sundew snapped.

05:25:32.459 --> 05:25:33.180
Go on.

05:25:33.240 --> 05:25:35.939
Cricket ducked through the opening.

05:25:36.000 --> 05:25:39.419
As Blue crouched to follow her, he saw

05:25:39.419 --> 05:25:41.580
Belladonna poke sundew between the

05:25:41.580 --> 05:25:44.159
shoulders so she'd stand more upright.

05:25:44.220 --> 05:25:48.479
Make us proud, she said to her daughter

05:25:48.479 --> 05:25:50.040
do not fail.

05:25:50.159 --> 05:25:53.520
Remember, this is what you were hatched

05:25:53.520 --> 05:25:53.759
to do.

05:25:53.819 --> 05:25:56.459
Remember how evil they are.

05:25:56.520 --> 05:25:59.279
Let your rage carry you.

05:25:59.340 --> 05:26:04.619
Yes, Belladonna, Sundew said firmly, I

05:26:04.619 --> 05:26:05.400
will not fail.

05:26:05.520 --> 05:26:09.599
And then Blue was outside, on one of the

05:26:09.599 --> 05:26:12.720
neat paths, standing next to cricket

05:26:12.720 --> 05:26:14.220
under a whale gray sky.

05:26:14.279 --> 05:26:18.119
Low clouds blotted out the moons, and

05:26:18.119 --> 05:26:19.139
most of the stars.

05:26:19.200 --> 05:26:21.599
The rainy season was definitely upon

05:26:21.599 --> 05:26:21.900
them.

05:26:21.959 --> 05:26:26.459
Sundew emerged a moment later, sliding

05:26:26.459 --> 05:26:28.139
the glass back into place behind her.

05:26:28.200 --> 05:26:30.900
They slipped silently between the

05:26:30.900 --> 05:26:34.020
greenhouses, Waving toward the front of

05:26:34.020 --> 05:26:35.040
Wasp Hive.

05:26:35.040 --> 05:26:38.819
As they got closer, Sundew held up one

05:26:38.819 --> 05:26:41.520
talon to stop them, then darted to the

05:26:41.520 --> 05:26:43.799
next corner and peered out at the hive

05:26:43.799 --> 05:26:44.159
entrance.

05:26:44.220 --> 05:26:46.380
Two guards.

05:26:46.439 --> 05:26:48.720
She whispered, then this should work.

05:26:48.779 --> 05:26:52.080
She dug into a pouch, and carefully

05:26:52.080 --> 05:26:55.139
pulled out a wooden box, which she opened

05:26:55.139 --> 05:26:58.080
to reveal a flower the size of a stingray

05:26:58.080 --> 05:26:59.580
and the color of moonlight.

05:26:59.639 --> 05:27:04.560
Take this, she said to Cricket, carefully

05:27:04.560 --> 05:27:09.060
do not crush any part of it until you get

05:27:09.060 --> 05:27:10.139
close to the guards.

05:27:10.200 --> 05:27:13.799
Then make them look at it, and smash it

05:27:13.799 --> 05:27:14.520
under their noses.

05:27:14.580 --> 05:27:17.220
What will it do?

05:27:17.279 --> 05:27:20.220
Cricket asked, eyeing the beautiful white

05:27:20.220 --> 05:27:20.700
bloom.

05:27:20.759 --> 05:27:22.560
Is it poisonous?

05:27:22.619 --> 05:27:23.880
Where did it come from?

05:27:23.939 --> 05:27:25.799
I don't want to poison anyone.

05:27:25.860 --> 05:27:28.259
It won't poison them.

05:27:28.380 --> 05:27:30.479
Sundew said impatiently.

05:27:30.540 --> 05:27:32.759
It'll just knock them out for a while.

05:27:32.819 --> 05:27:36.240
Don't you inhale it though, or you'll be

05:27:36.240 --> 05:27:37.080
useless to us.

05:27:37.139 --> 05:27:40.439
Cricket held the flower as far away from

05:27:40.439 --> 05:27:43.860
her as she could, took a deep breath, and

05:27:43.860 --> 05:27:45.299
stepped out of the cluster of

05:27:45.299 --> 05:27:45.959
greenhouses.

05:27:46.020 --> 05:27:50.279
She moved slowly, cautiously hobbling on

05:27:50.279 --> 05:27:52.860
3 legs, so she could hold the flower up

05:27:52.860 --> 05:27:55.259
in one talon with infinite gentleness.

05:27:55.380 --> 05:27:59.279
It hit blue suddenly, that this was a

05:27:59.279 --> 05:28:01.020
dangerous turning point for cricket.

05:28:01.080 --> 05:28:02.880
Up until now.

05:28:02.939 --> 05:28:05.700
She hadn't been seen with the fugitives.

05:28:05.759 --> 05:28:07.919
She could have returned home at any

05:28:07.919 --> 05:28:10.680
moment, slipping back into her ordinary

05:28:10.680 --> 05:28:13.319
life with a shrug, and an excuse about

05:28:13.319 --> 05:28:15.840
mind control and hunting, or something

05:28:15.840 --> 05:28:16.200
like that.

05:28:16.319 --> 05:28:19.799
But now she was facing real hive wing

05:28:19.799 --> 05:28:21.900
guards, who were likely to remember her.

05:28:22.020 --> 05:28:25.680
Whatever happened next, Cricket would be

05:28:25.680 --> 05:28:26.040
in trouble.

05:28:26.099 --> 05:28:29.279
Probably really bad trouble.

05:28:29.340 --> 05:28:32.220
I'm so sorry, cricket.

05:28:32.279 --> 05:28:34.500
Blue thought mournfully.

05:28:34.560 --> 05:28:36.060
I wish.

05:28:36.299 --> 05:28:38.700
His thoughts trailed off.

05:28:38.759 --> 05:28:42.000
He couldn't say, I wish we hadn't met.

05:28:42.060 --> 05:28:44.520
Because that was the furthest thing from

05:28:44.520 --> 05:28:44.939
the truth.

05:28:45.000 --> 05:28:47.400
He wished she was safe.

05:28:47.459 --> 05:28:48.540
That was all.

05:28:48.599 --> 05:28:52.080
Both guards leaped to their feet when

05:28:52.080 --> 05:28:53.099
they saw her approaching.

05:28:53.159 --> 05:28:54.900
Halt.

05:28:54.959 --> 05:28:56.759
One of the guards called.

05:28:56.819 --> 05:28:59.939
Cricket stopped where she was, halfway to

05:28:59.939 --> 05:29:01.740
the door, and the guards started

05:29:01.740 --> 05:29:02.759
whispering to each other.

05:29:02.819 --> 05:29:06.779
Blue glanced over at Sundew, who was

05:29:06.779 --> 05:29:08.819
watching with tension humming from every

05:29:08.819 --> 05:29:09.779
bone in her body.

05:29:09.840 --> 05:29:13.020
She looked ready to sprint out there and

05:29:13.020 --> 05:29:13.740
stab the guards.

05:29:13.799 --> 05:29:15.900
If they so much as sneezed funny.

05:29:15.959 --> 05:29:21.060
So, he said to her, your mother said you

05:29:21.060 --> 05:29:21.959
were hatched for this.

05:29:22.020 --> 05:29:24.240
What's that all about?

05:29:24.299 --> 05:29:27.240
Sundew looked over her shoulder at him

05:29:27.240 --> 05:29:28.259
incredulously.

05:29:28.319 --> 05:29:31.439
Are you seriously making small talk with

05:29:31.439 --> 05:29:32.220
me right now?

05:29:32.279 --> 05:29:34.799
No, he protested.

05:29:34.919 --> 05:29:36.720
That wasn't small talk.

05:29:36.779 --> 05:29:38.220
That was big talk.

05:29:38.279 --> 05:29:40.080
Actual talk?

05:29:40.139 --> 05:29:42.299
I actually want to know, I mean.

05:29:42.360 --> 05:29:46.500
It's nothing mystical, Sundew growled.

05:29:46.619 --> 05:29:49.380
She wanted a daughter to carry on our

05:29:49.380 --> 05:29:50.279
family's legacy.

05:29:50.400 --> 05:29:52.799
She trained me my whole life for one

05:29:52.799 --> 05:29:53.340
purpose.

05:29:53.400 --> 05:29:54.299
This.

05:29:54.360 --> 05:29:57.599
Stealing the book of Clear Side.

05:29:57.720 --> 05:30:00.720
She narrowed her eyes and paused for a

05:30:00.720 --> 05:30:00.900
moment.

05:30:00.959 --> 05:30:03.060
Sure.

05:30:03.119 --> 05:30:05.819
That didn't sound like the whole story

05:30:05.819 --> 05:30:08.099
but now the guards were calling cricket

05:30:08.099 --> 05:30:08.819
forward again.

05:30:08.880 --> 05:30:11.099
Who are you?

05:30:11.159 --> 05:30:12.299
one of them asked.

05:30:12.360 --> 05:30:14.759
Why weren't you back by curfew?

05:30:14.819 --> 05:30:17.400
And what have you got there?

05:30:17.459 --> 05:30:18.659
asked the other.

05:30:18.720 --> 05:30:21.419
I found something amazing.

05:30:21.479 --> 05:30:22.799
Cricket said.

05:30:22.860 --> 05:30:25.020
The queen will want to see it right

05:30:25.020 --> 05:30:25.319
away.

05:30:25.439 --> 05:30:28.319
It was hard to hear her from here.

05:30:28.380 --> 05:30:30.959
Her voice was much quieter than the

05:30:30.959 --> 05:30:31.439
guards.

05:30:31.500 --> 05:30:33.659
Blue strained to listen.

05:30:33.720 --> 05:30:36.900
Unless it's a map to that blasted flame

05:30:36.900 --> 05:30:37.560
silk.

05:30:37.619 --> 05:30:39.840
She's going to bite your head off, said

05:30:39.840 --> 05:30:40.500
the 1st guard.

05:30:40.619 --> 05:30:44.099
I tried the librarian 1st if I were you

05:30:44.099 --> 05:30:45.180
little dragon.

05:30:45.240 --> 05:30:46.619
She likes unusual things.

05:30:46.680 --> 05:30:50.400
And she's a bit less murdery than the

05:30:50.400 --> 05:30:53.279
Queen, agreed the 2nd guard, smiling.

05:30:53.340 --> 05:30:56.819
Blue felt a sharp twist of guilt.

05:30:56.880 --> 05:30:58.799
These guards were so friendly.

05:30:58.919 --> 05:31:01.259
And they were going to be in so much

05:31:01.259 --> 05:31:03.779
trouble if Blue and sundew got into the

05:31:03.779 --> 05:31:06.060
hive, and Queen Wasp found out.

05:31:06.119 --> 05:31:08.340
Would they lose their jobs?

05:31:08.400 --> 05:31:10.799
Or would their punishment be even worse?

05:31:10.860 --> 05:31:13.680
He worried at one of his claws.

05:31:13.740 --> 05:31:16.799
Why did it have to be such nice friendly

05:31:16.799 --> 05:31:17.700
guards in their way?

05:31:17.819 --> 05:31:21.060
A voice in his head that sounded like

05:31:21.060 --> 05:31:23.880
Luna whispered, maybe they're only

05:31:23.880 --> 05:31:25.799
friendly, because they're talking to a

05:31:25.799 --> 05:31:26.520
hive wing.

05:31:26.580 --> 05:31:28.979
Have you ever seen a guard be that nice

05:31:28.979 --> 05:31:29.939
to a silk wing?

05:31:30.000 --> 05:31:32.400
Did you even know they could smile?

05:31:32.520 --> 05:31:35.700
These same guards might have been out for

05:31:35.700 --> 05:31:37.439
the last 3 days hunting you.

05:31:37.500 --> 05:31:40.200
They might have been in a unit that came

05:31:40.200 --> 05:31:41.580
to shove me in a cage.

05:31:41.700 --> 05:31:44.400
They might spend their other shifts

05:31:44.400 --> 05:31:46.680
poking flame silks with spears to make

05:31:46.680 --> 05:31:47.580
them burn faster.

05:31:47.639 --> 05:31:51.240
Blue shivered, trying to shake off the

05:31:51.240 --> 05:31:51.419
voice.

05:31:51.479 --> 05:31:53.639
So what is it?

05:31:53.700 --> 05:31:57.240
The 1st guard asked, craning his neck as

05:31:57.240 --> 05:31:58.259
cricket approached.

05:31:58.319 --> 05:32:00.000
Isn't it beautiful?

05:32:00.119 --> 05:32:01.080
she said.

05:32:01.139 --> 05:32:03.599
And it smells like nothing I've ever

05:32:03.599 --> 05:32:04.319
smelled before.

05:32:04.380 --> 05:32:07.259
She held out the flower between the 2

05:32:07.259 --> 05:32:10.259
guards, so they both leaned in to sniff

05:32:10.259 --> 05:32:10.560
it.

05:32:10.619 --> 05:32:14.159
And then Cricket squeezed her claws shut

05:32:14.159 --> 05:32:16.560
crushing the pedals in her grip.

05:32:16.680 --> 05:32:19.860
Blue couldn't see exactly when it hit

05:32:19.860 --> 05:32:22.680
them, but a moment later, the guards

05:32:22.680 --> 05:32:23.880
crumpled to the ground.

05:32:23.939 --> 05:32:26.880
One of them hit his head on the hive wall

05:32:26.880 --> 05:32:30.000
as he fell, and cricket flinched, reaching

05:32:30.000 --> 05:32:30.840
toward him too late.

05:32:30.900 --> 05:32:34.560
She crouched over him, folding in his

05:32:34.560 --> 05:32:36.900
blade wings and checking his pulse.

05:32:36.959 --> 05:32:40.080
The prolescent flower lay where she'd

05:32:40.080 --> 05:32:42.540
dropped it on the dirt, its edges brown

05:32:42.540 --> 05:32:43.680
and wrinkled now.

05:32:43.680 --> 05:32:47.220
Sundew sprinted toward the entrance, and

05:32:47.220 --> 05:32:48.900
Blue scrambled to follow her.

05:32:48.959 --> 05:32:50.639
Leave them.

05:32:50.700 --> 05:32:52.740
Sundew snapped at cricket.

05:32:52.799 --> 05:32:55.439
I don't know how much they got, or how

05:32:55.439 --> 05:32:56.279
long it'll last.

05:32:56.340 --> 05:32:58.919
If I were you, I would have shoved it

05:32:58.919 --> 05:32:59.880
right up their snouts.

05:33:00.000 --> 05:33:03.000
Well, I wasn't going to do that.

05:33:03.060 --> 05:33:04.979
Cricket said crossly.

05:33:05.040 --> 05:33:07.740
And it worked fine, didn't it?

05:33:07.799 --> 05:33:09.299
What kind of flower is that?

05:33:09.360 --> 05:33:11.400
Is it related to nightshade?

05:33:11.520 --> 05:33:14.340
Blue bent over the 2nd guard?

05:33:14.400 --> 05:33:16.740
surreptitiously making sure she was

05:33:16.740 --> 05:33:17.040
alive.

05:33:17.099 --> 05:33:20.580
She was, and that she'd fallen in a

05:33:20.580 --> 05:33:21.360
comfortable position.

05:33:21.419 --> 05:33:25.139
Sundew strode on without waiting, and

05:33:25.139 --> 05:33:27.360
both cricket and blue had to jump up and

05:33:27.360 --> 05:33:30.419
run after her, under the malevolent gaze

05:33:30.419 --> 05:33:32.520
of the giant queen wasp statue.

05:33:32.639 --> 05:33:36.000
The ground level doors to the hive were

05:33:36.000 --> 05:33:39.000
massive and ostentatiously made of wood

05:33:39.000 --> 05:33:42.479
with wasps carved all over them, and a

05:33:42.479 --> 05:33:44.159
profile of the queen on each side.

05:33:44.220 --> 05:33:47.400
Sundoo paused in front of one for a

05:33:47.400 --> 05:33:50.520
moment, then reached up and raked her

05:33:50.520 --> 05:33:53.340
claws across the queen's elegant snout

05:33:53.340 --> 05:33:55.500
leaving splintery furrows in the wood.

05:33:55.560 --> 05:33:59.759
That was unnecessary, Cricket protested.

05:33:59.819 --> 05:34:02.220
You ruined a really nice carving.

05:34:02.340 --> 05:34:06.240
Wait until I get to her actual face.

05:34:06.360 --> 05:34:08.700
Sundew snarled.

05:34:08.759 --> 05:34:11.099
She yanked the door open a crack and

05:34:11.099 --> 05:34:11.759
peeked through.

05:34:11.819 --> 05:34:14.220
Then shoved it a little farther and

05:34:14.220 --> 05:34:15.779
squeezed herself through the gap.

05:34:15.779 --> 05:34:19.560
Blue and Cricket went next, spilling out

05:34:19.560 --> 05:34:21.959
onto the streets of Wasp Hive's lowest

05:34:21.959 --> 05:34:22.259
level.

05:34:22.319 --> 05:34:26.099
What they saw was a deserted street of

05:34:26.099 --> 05:34:29.340
warehouses, rows and rows of blocky

05:34:29.340 --> 05:34:32.220
buildings, each a perfect beige cube

05:34:32.220 --> 05:34:34.919
reaching from floor to ceiling, with one

05:34:34.919 --> 05:34:35.700
large door.

05:34:35.759 --> 05:34:40.020
Storage, blue guest, although of what

05:34:40.020 --> 05:34:41.340
exactly he wasn't sure.

05:34:41.459 --> 05:34:45.180
Each door was marked with a symbol, all

05:34:45.180 --> 05:34:47.099
of which were unfamiliar to him.

05:34:47.159 --> 05:34:49.680
He only had a moment to think about it

05:34:49.680 --> 05:34:52.380
because sundew had already started up the

05:34:52.380 --> 05:34:54.779
path that led to the next level.

05:34:54.840 --> 05:34:56.520
Blue ran after her and caught her

05:34:56.520 --> 05:34:56.880
shoulder.

05:34:56.939 --> 05:34:58.619
What?

05:34:58.619 --> 05:34:59.459
she snapped.

05:34:59.520 --> 05:35:03.840
Let cricket go first. he said, and walk

05:35:03.840 --> 05:35:05.220
like a normal silk wing.

05:35:05.279 --> 05:35:08.340
We don't charge around with, I have

05:35:08.340 --> 05:35:10.319
somewhere to be and someone to set on

05:35:10.319 --> 05:35:11.099
fire faces.

05:35:11.159 --> 05:35:14.220
Even if your disguise was way better than

05:35:14.220 --> 05:35:14.580
it is.

05:35:14.639 --> 05:35:18.180
Walking and scowling like that, will get

05:35:18.180 --> 05:35:19.200
you caught in a heartbeat.

05:35:19.319 --> 05:35:23.040
Fine. she said, fuming.

05:35:23.159 --> 05:35:25.500
Show me how you walk.

05:35:25.560 --> 05:35:27.720
Blue turned to cricket.

05:35:27.779 --> 05:35:29.580
Have you been here before?

05:35:29.639 --> 05:35:30.959
He asked her.

05:35:31.020 --> 05:35:33.180
Do you know where the temple is?

05:35:33.240 --> 05:35:35.700
Yes, she said.

05:35:35.759 --> 05:35:39.540
My class visited the temple last year, and

05:35:39.540 --> 05:35:41.040
my dad took me a couple of times.

05:35:41.159 --> 05:35:43.020
It's up in the center of the hive.

05:35:43.080 --> 05:35:46.799
He nodded and stepped back so she could

05:35:46.799 --> 05:35:47.279
lead the way.

05:35:47.400 --> 05:35:49.860
Then he ducked his head and trailed after

05:35:49.860 --> 05:35:52.380
her, looking as harmless and

05:35:52.380 --> 05:35:53.700
inconspicuous as he could.

05:35:53.759 --> 05:35:58.020
Sundew fell into step beside him, growling

05:35:58.020 --> 05:36:00.060
and muttering under her breath.

05:36:00.119 --> 05:36:02.159
Tuck your chin a little more.

05:36:02.220 --> 05:36:05.939
Blue suggested softly, keep your eyes on

05:36:05.939 --> 05:36:06.240
the ground.

05:36:06.299 --> 05:36:09.119
Don't look directly at any hive wings.

05:36:09.180 --> 05:36:10.740
Try not to make any noise.

05:36:10.799 --> 05:36:12.900
She hissed at him.

05:36:12.959 --> 05:36:15.900
You're just like I always pictured Silk

05:36:15.900 --> 05:36:17.279
Wings, she spat.

05:36:17.340 --> 05:36:19.259
Subservient worms.

05:36:19.319 --> 05:36:22.319
He stopped midstab and frowned at her.

05:36:22.380 --> 05:36:25.380
We are not, he said.

05:36:25.439 --> 05:36:29.099
We're pacifists, yes, and we follow the

05:36:29.099 --> 05:36:31.619
rules, but it's kept us alive, hasn't

05:36:31.619 --> 05:36:31.740
it?

05:36:31.799 --> 05:36:34.560
There's a lot more silk wings left in the

05:36:34.560 --> 05:36:36.000
world than leaf wings, I bet.

05:36:36.060 --> 05:36:39.299
He added hurriedly, since he wasn't

05:36:39.299 --> 05:36:39.779
actually sure.

05:36:39.900 --> 05:36:43.080
Up until this morning, he'd have guessed

05:36:43.080 --> 05:36:46.139
the number of leaf wings left was zero.

05:36:46.200 --> 05:36:48.779
But he must have been right, because she

05:36:48.779 --> 05:36:50.279
spun and glared at him.

05:36:50.340 --> 05:36:53.099
If you'd been willing to fight with us

05:36:53.099 --> 05:36:54.779
we'd all still be alive.

05:36:54.900 --> 05:36:58.500
Or we'd all be dead, he pointed out.

05:36:58.560 --> 05:37:01.619
The significantly more likely scenario.

05:37:01.680 --> 05:37:04.740
I don't know why Willow wants to save

05:37:04.740 --> 05:37:05.520
your tribe.

05:37:05.580 --> 05:37:07.080
Sundew snapped.

05:37:07.139 --> 05:37:09.720
You're as much of a problem as the hive

05:37:09.720 --> 05:37:13.200
wings, with your nodding and smiling, and

05:37:13.200 --> 05:37:15.060
agreeing to let them trample all over

05:37:15.060 --> 05:37:15.299
you.

05:37:15.419 --> 05:37:18.180
I'd throw you all into the sea if it were

05:37:18.180 --> 05:37:18.599
up to me.

05:37:18.659 --> 05:37:21.659
Cricket came back around the bend in the

05:37:21.659 --> 05:37:22.020
tunnel.

05:37:22.139 --> 05:37:25.200
Can we try to be a little more quiet?

05:37:25.319 --> 05:37:26.220
She said.

05:37:26.279 --> 05:37:28.560
We'll be at their residential levels

05:37:28.560 --> 05:37:28.799
soon.

05:37:28.860 --> 05:37:33.779
Which meant more dragons around, and more

05:37:33.779 --> 05:37:36.360
hive wings who might overhear sundew and

05:37:36.360 --> 05:37:36.959
blue arguing.

05:37:37.020 --> 05:37:40.259
He bit back everything he wanted to say

05:37:40.259 --> 05:37:42.419
to the leaf wing and hurried after

05:37:42.419 --> 05:37:45.119
cricket, walking like he normally did

05:37:45.119 --> 05:37:48.060
around hive wings, which was a perfectly

05:37:48.060 --> 05:37:51.419
fine way to walk, he thought, in that it

05:37:51.419 --> 05:37:53.279
kept you out of trouble, and it was

05:37:53.279 --> 05:37:55.860
polite, and with sundue right?

05:37:55.919 --> 05:37:58.560
Was he confusing obedience and good

05:37:58.560 --> 05:38:01.020
behavior, with letting the hive wings

05:38:01.020 --> 05:38:02.099
trample all over him?

05:38:02.159 --> 05:38:05.459
What else was I supposed to do exactly?

05:38:05.520 --> 05:38:07.080
He wondered.

05:38:07.139 --> 05:38:11.159
Stare right at hive wings, speak up, pick

05:38:11.159 --> 05:38:14.580
fights, end up on misbehaviors way all

05:38:14.580 --> 05:38:16.319
the time, like sore tail.

05:38:16.380 --> 05:38:18.479
I don't like being yelled at.

05:38:18.540 --> 05:38:21.060
Acting the way I do has been a good way

05:38:21.060 --> 05:38:21.779
to avoid that.

05:38:21.840 --> 05:38:25.319
Wasp Hive was constructed much like

05:38:25.319 --> 05:38:28.500
cicada hive, but bigger, with wider

05:38:28.500 --> 05:38:31.319
hallways and tunnels, and higher ceilings

05:38:31.319 --> 05:38:31.860
on each level.

05:38:31.979 --> 05:38:35.159
The walls of the tunnels were painted

05:38:35.159 --> 05:38:38.279
with black and yellow stripes, or 6 sided

05:38:38.279 --> 05:38:41.400
honeycomb patterns, alternating by level

05:38:41.400 --> 05:38:45.540
weavings and posters of queen wasp, glared

05:38:45.540 --> 05:38:46.740
at them around every bend.

05:38:46.799 --> 05:38:49.680
The tunnels became busier as they

05:38:49.680 --> 05:38:52.919
ascended, and blue drew closer to cricket

05:38:52.919 --> 05:38:54.779
with a nervous jittering in his chest.

05:38:54.840 --> 05:38:58.259
They passed a family of hive wings

05:38:58.259 --> 05:39:01.380
arguing over where to go for dinner, a

05:39:01.380 --> 05:39:03.119
silk wing carrying a basket of clean

05:39:03.119 --> 05:39:06.540
blankets, a pair of hive wings, singing

05:39:06.540 --> 05:39:08.520
and teasing each other about getting the

05:39:08.520 --> 05:39:09.000
words wrong.

05:39:09.060 --> 05:39:12.180
Everyone seemed so normal.

05:39:12.240 --> 05:39:16.259
Their lives were carrying on, despite

05:39:16.259 --> 05:39:18.240
days spent under the queen's mind

05:39:18.240 --> 05:39:18.720
control.

05:39:18.779 --> 05:39:22.259
A few of them nodded politely at cricket

05:39:22.259 --> 05:39:24.720
but nobody even glanced at blue or

05:39:24.720 --> 05:39:25.319
sundew.

05:39:25.380 --> 05:39:29.279
And then cricket slowed down, flicking

05:39:29.279 --> 05:39:31.200
her wings back as she stepped out of the

05:39:31.200 --> 05:39:34.200
tunnels and onto a polished floor made of

05:39:34.200 --> 05:39:36.360
real wood, not tree stuff.

05:39:36.419 --> 05:39:40.319
Blue bit back at gasp as he followed her

05:39:40.319 --> 05:39:41.700
onto the smooth surface.

05:39:41.759 --> 05:39:46.080
It gleamed in waves of gold and amber and

05:39:46.080 --> 05:39:49.259
brown, all the way across the vast space

05:39:49.259 --> 05:39:52.020
in front of them, to the foot of the

05:39:52.020 --> 05:39:53.279
temple of Clearsight.

05:39:53.340 --> 05:39:57.659
Chapter 20.

05:39:58.020 --> 05:40:01.020
Blue had read that the temple of

05:40:01.020 --> 05:40:02.340
Clearside was the most beautiful

05:40:02.340 --> 05:40:03.599
structure in the world.

05:40:03.720 --> 05:40:06.299
He knew that it had been built by

05:40:06.299 --> 05:40:08.459
Clearsight's grandchildren, then

05:40:08.459 --> 05:40:10.560
partially destroyed 100s of years later

05:40:10.560 --> 05:40:13.259
during the war with the leaf wings, and

05:40:13.259 --> 05:40:15.900
then moved to be reconstructed here in

05:40:15.900 --> 05:40:18.299
the heart of Wasp Hive, where it could be

05:40:18.299 --> 05:40:18.779
kept safe.

05:40:18.840 --> 05:40:22.259
Books had told him that it was made of 60

05:40:22.259 --> 05:40:25.439
different kinds of wood, all polished and

05:40:25.439 --> 05:40:27.779
painstakingly fitted together, so it

05:40:27.779 --> 05:40:29.220
looked like a perfect miracle.

05:40:29.279 --> 05:40:32.459
But books couldn't describe the feeling

05:40:32.459 --> 05:40:34.200
of peace that hit him when he saw it.

05:40:34.259 --> 05:40:38.040
The temple wasn't an enormous towering

05:40:38.040 --> 05:40:40.439
structure, as he'd always imagined.

05:40:40.500 --> 05:40:43.740
It was no bigger than the cocoon, but

05:40:43.740 --> 05:40:46.020
built with elegant balance and graceful

05:40:46.020 --> 05:40:46.680
proportions.

05:40:46.740 --> 05:40:49.500
The columns that lined the front of it

05:40:49.500 --> 05:40:51.720
were of a wood so dark, it was almost

05:40:51.720 --> 05:40:54.900
black, embedded with tiny flecks of

05:40:54.900 --> 05:40:56.880
quartz that looked like distant stars.

05:40:56.939 --> 05:41:00.180
The roof swept into dragon tell points at

05:41:00.180 --> 05:41:02.459
each corner, and a central dome was

05:41:02.459 --> 05:41:05.400
covered in curved golden wood tiles that

05:41:05.400 --> 05:41:06.299
looked like scales.

05:41:06.360 --> 05:41:09.060
It sat quietly in the center of the vast

05:41:09.060 --> 05:41:11.340
wooden courtyard, surrounded by

05:41:11.340 --> 05:41:13.860
reflecting pools, and little nooks lined

05:41:13.860 --> 05:41:14.880
with bookshelves.

05:41:15.000 --> 05:41:18.000
Even at this hour, blue saw few dragons

05:41:18.000 --> 05:41:21.000
curled here and there on a bench, beside

05:41:21.000 --> 05:41:24.060
a pool, on a bamboo mat between shelves

05:41:24.060 --> 05:41:25.319
all of them reading.

05:41:25.380 --> 05:41:29.040
Tiny flame silk lanterns glowed beside

05:41:29.040 --> 05:41:31.500
them, a few floated on the water of the

05:41:31.500 --> 05:41:34.380
pools, and others hung from the rafters

05:41:34.380 --> 05:41:34.860
of the temple.

05:41:34.919 --> 05:41:38.939
Another light glowed on the dome, and

05:41:38.939 --> 05:41:41.279
when Blue looked up, he realized there

05:41:41.279 --> 05:41:43.979
was a skylight overhead that pierced all

05:41:43.979 --> 05:41:46.380
the levels all the way up to the top of

05:41:46.380 --> 05:41:46.799
the hive.

05:41:46.919 --> 05:41:48.599
In the distance.

05:41:48.659 --> 05:41:51.659
He could see the stars, and the corner of

05:41:51.659 --> 05:41:53.459
one of the moons shining down on the

05:41:53.459 --> 05:41:53.759
temple.

05:41:53.819 --> 05:41:56.819
It must be covered with glass to keep the

05:41:56.819 --> 05:41:59.580
reins out, but it was kept so clean it

05:41:59.580 --> 05:42:01.319
looked like a direct hole to the sky.

05:42:01.380 --> 05:42:04.619
The effect was somewhere between magic

05:42:04.619 --> 05:42:06.299
library and peace garden.

05:42:06.360 --> 05:42:09.240
And Blue found himself consumed with

05:42:09.240 --> 05:42:11.279
sadness, that he'd never been here

05:42:11.279 --> 05:42:11.520
before.

05:42:11.580 --> 05:42:14.580
And most likely would never be able to

05:42:14.580 --> 05:42:15.180
come here again.

05:42:15.240 --> 05:42:18.720
He wished he could live like these hive

05:42:18.720 --> 05:42:21.360
wings, with this place at his claw tips

05:42:21.360 --> 05:42:21.720
every day.

05:42:21.779 --> 05:42:24.659
He wished he could work for the librarian

05:42:24.659 --> 05:42:27.060
taking care of the temple and all these

05:42:27.060 --> 05:42:29.880
books, sweeping the floors and feeding

05:42:29.880 --> 05:42:32.759
the coy, and keeping it beautiful, and

05:42:32.759 --> 05:42:34.680
never getting yelled at by angry leaf

05:42:34.680 --> 05:42:37.619
wings, or chased by angry queen zombies.

05:42:37.680 --> 05:42:41.099
Instead, he was here to destroy this

05:42:41.099 --> 05:42:43.799
peaceful place by stealing the one thing

05:42:43.799 --> 05:42:44.759
it was built around.

05:42:44.819 --> 05:42:48.060
They walked toward the temple as quietly

05:42:48.060 --> 05:42:51.119
as they could, a long carpet of dark blue

05:42:51.119 --> 05:42:53.759
silk stretched toward the temple door and

05:42:53.759 --> 05:42:55.200
muffled their talon steps.

05:42:55.259 --> 05:42:59.159
Golden dragonflies and green lizards, were

05:42:59.159 --> 05:43:00.840
woven in a subtle pattern through the

05:43:00.840 --> 05:43:01.200
carpet.

05:43:01.259 --> 05:43:04.200
It was more beautiful than even Blue's

05:43:04.200 --> 05:43:06.659
favorite cocoon weavings, and it felt

05:43:06.659 --> 05:43:07.799
impossibly ancient.

05:43:07.860 --> 05:43:11.939
He glanced sideways at sundew, to see if

05:43:11.939 --> 05:43:14.040
the aura of the temple had calmed her

05:43:14.040 --> 05:43:14.520
down at all.

05:43:14.580 --> 05:43:16.979
She caught him looking and hurried to

05:43:16.979 --> 05:43:18.119
scowl back onto her face.

05:43:18.180 --> 05:43:20.580
Don't you think it's amazing?

05:43:20.700 --> 05:43:22.080
He whispered.

05:43:22.139 --> 05:43:25.740
No, she whispered back ferociously.

05:43:25.799 --> 05:43:28.139
She waved her tail at the carvings around

05:43:28.139 --> 05:43:28.380
them.

05:43:28.439 --> 05:43:31.439
How many trees had to die to make this

05:43:31.439 --> 05:43:31.799
place?

05:43:31.860 --> 05:43:34.080
He didn't answer.

05:43:34.139 --> 05:43:37.020
He felt in his bones that the temple was

05:43:37.020 --> 05:43:38.520
worth everything it took to make it.

05:43:38.639 --> 05:43:41.580
But he could also imagine how hard it was

05:43:41.580 --> 05:43:44.939
for some do, mourning the vast forests of

05:43:44.939 --> 05:43:46.680
trees that used to cover Pentala.

05:43:46.740 --> 05:43:49.560
Queen Wasp and the hive wings had

05:43:49.560 --> 05:43:50.459
destroyed all of that.

05:43:50.520 --> 05:43:54.180
Not just the leaf wings homes, but the

05:43:54.180 --> 05:43:56.220
spirits of the trees they'd clearly loved

05:43:56.220 --> 05:43:56.520
too.

05:43:56.580 --> 05:44:00.299
Two hive wing guards stood on either side

05:44:00.299 --> 05:44:02.759
of the arched temple door, holding long

05:44:02.759 --> 05:44:03.900
spears.

05:44:03.959 --> 05:44:06.180
Blue felt panic stirring in his chest.

05:44:06.240 --> 05:44:09.060
He tapped Cricket's wing and she paused

05:44:09.060 --> 05:44:10.139
turning back to him.

05:44:10.200 --> 05:44:14.580
Sundu and I don't have wristbands, he

05:44:14.580 --> 05:44:15.360
said softly.

05:44:15.419 --> 05:44:16.919
These guards.

05:44:16.979 --> 05:44:18.419
I think they'll notice.

05:44:18.479 --> 05:44:22.380
Cricket nodded, as though he'd drawn her

05:44:22.380 --> 05:44:23.819
attention to an interesting fish.

05:44:23.880 --> 05:44:26.759
She strolled off the carpet path and over

05:44:26.759 --> 05:44:29.040
to one of the pools, sitting down beside

05:44:29.040 --> 05:44:31.740
it, and beckoning for blue and sundew to

05:44:31.740 --> 05:44:32.040
do the same.

05:44:32.099 --> 05:44:35.459
Those aren't the only guards, she

05:44:35.459 --> 05:44:37.200
murmured, when they were beside her.

05:44:37.259 --> 05:44:39.479
She crouched closer to the water.

05:44:39.540 --> 05:44:42.540
There's another pair guarding the inner

05:44:42.540 --> 05:44:44.400
door, and in the room with the book

05:44:44.400 --> 05:44:44.819
itself.

05:44:44.880 --> 05:44:48.119
There's always either 2 more guards or

05:44:48.119 --> 05:44:48.900
the librarian.

05:44:48.959 --> 05:44:52.139
The book is in a wooden case, which is

05:44:52.139 --> 05:44:54.419
locked, and only the librarian has the

05:44:54.419 --> 05:44:54.599
key.

05:44:54.659 --> 05:44:58.080
Where is the librarian if she's not with

05:44:58.080 --> 05:44:58.380
a book?

05:44:58.439 --> 05:45:00.000
Sundew whispered.

05:45:00.060 --> 05:45:03.299
She lives in a back room of the temple, so

05:45:03.299 --> 05:45:05.340
she can be near the book at all times.

05:45:05.400 --> 05:45:07.439
Once a librarian is chosen.

05:45:07.500 --> 05:45:09.479
She never leaves the temple again.

05:45:09.540 --> 05:45:11.880
Blue had known that.

05:45:11.939 --> 05:45:13.560
Yikes.

05:45:13.619 --> 05:45:16.139
What would it be like to be a dragon who

05:45:16.139 --> 05:45:18.840
was never allowed to fly or see the sky?

05:45:18.900 --> 05:45:22.439
Even though the temple was perfect, he

05:45:22.439 --> 05:45:24.419
couldn't imagine anyone who'd be happy to

05:45:24.419 --> 05:45:25.439
be trapped in it forever.

05:45:25.500 --> 05:45:29.340
So possibly 6 guards, plus the

05:45:29.340 --> 05:45:29.880
librarian.

05:45:29.939 --> 05:45:31.500
Sundew muttered.

05:45:31.560 --> 05:45:33.779
You know, it would have been quite

05:45:33.779 --> 05:45:35.520
helpful if you'd mentioned any of this

05:45:35.520 --> 05:45:37.439
earlier today during the planning

05:45:37.439 --> 05:45:38.099
stages.

05:45:38.159 --> 05:45:42.360
I forgot until I saw the temple, Cricket

05:45:42.360 --> 05:45:43.259
said innocently.

05:45:43.319 --> 05:45:45.840
Sorry, I haven't been here in a while.

05:45:45.900 --> 05:45:50.099
Sundew growled softly and started poking

05:45:50.099 --> 05:45:51.419
through her pouches.

05:45:51.479 --> 05:45:53.459
Cricket caught Blue's eye and gave him a

05:45:53.459 --> 05:45:55.080
small, nervous smile.

05:45:55.139 --> 05:45:58.200
Blue was sure Cricket had remembered the

05:45:58.200 --> 05:46:01.020
details of the guards all along, but she

05:46:01.020 --> 05:46:02.819
was still trying to find a way to get out

05:46:02.819 --> 05:46:03.540
of stealing the book.

05:46:03.599 --> 05:46:05.939
He wished he could do something to help

05:46:05.939 --> 05:46:06.180
her.

05:46:06.240 --> 05:46:08.520
He wished he could think of a way to

05:46:08.520 --> 05:46:11.520
rescue Luna, protect the tribes from an

05:46:11.520 --> 05:46:14.159
invasion of leaf wings, save the book of

05:46:14.159 --> 05:46:16.259
Clearsight, and escape with his friends.

05:46:16.319 --> 05:46:20.159
Ideally with a minimum of danger, violence

05:46:20.159 --> 05:46:22.139
or dragons yelling at him.

05:46:22.200 --> 05:46:24.180
His heart stopped suddenly.

05:46:24.299 --> 05:46:28.259
Maybe there was one possible way out of

05:46:28.259 --> 05:46:28.500
this.

05:46:28.560 --> 05:46:31.979
The problem was, it was risky and

05:46:31.979 --> 05:46:32.400
insane.

05:46:32.459 --> 05:46:35.939
But then, so was stealing the book of

05:46:35.939 --> 05:46:36.540
Clear Sight.

05:46:36.599 --> 05:46:40.080
We could tell the guards, he thought.

05:46:40.139 --> 05:46:42.900
We could turn in sundew and expose her

05:46:42.900 --> 05:46:43.380
disguise.

05:46:43.439 --> 05:46:45.720
We give her to Queen Wasp.

05:46:45.840 --> 05:46:48.540
We tell them where Belladonna and hemlock

05:46:48.540 --> 05:46:51.000
are hiding, so the soldiers can swoop in

05:46:51.000 --> 05:46:53.279
and save sore tail and catch them.

05:46:53.340 --> 05:46:54.900
We'd be heroes.

05:46:54.959 --> 05:46:56.580
Wouldn't we?

05:46:56.639 --> 05:47:00.540
Surely capturing 3 leaf wings and

05:47:00.540 --> 05:47:02.159
exposing a plot to steal the Book of

05:47:02.159 --> 05:47:04.439
Clearsight would be the greatest gift

05:47:04.439 --> 05:47:06.240
they could ever give Queen Wasp.

05:47:06.299 --> 05:47:08.520
She would have to forgive them for

05:47:08.520 --> 05:47:09.000
everything else.

05:47:09.119 --> 05:47:10.860
Wouldn't she?

05:47:10.919 --> 05:47:13.259
He tried to follow that thought.

05:47:13.319 --> 05:47:16.139
Would she forgive Sordail for attacking

05:47:16.139 --> 05:47:16.680
her soldiers?

05:47:16.740 --> 05:47:18.540
What about IO?

05:47:18.599 --> 05:47:20.639
Could she be forgiven too?

05:47:20.700 --> 05:47:24.119
Would Queen Wasp let Blue and Luna go

05:47:24.119 --> 05:47:25.919
back to their safe, ordinary lives with

05:47:25.919 --> 05:47:26.400
their mothers?

05:47:26.459 --> 05:47:30.000
Maybe if they promised to give all their

05:47:30.000 --> 05:47:31.259
flame silk to her?

05:47:31.319 --> 05:47:33.900
Would she let Sortell and Luna be

05:47:33.900 --> 05:47:34.619
partnered together?

05:47:34.680 --> 05:47:36.599
What about his father?

05:47:36.659 --> 05:47:39.000
When she set him free too?

05:47:39.060 --> 05:47:41.279
If he was even still alive?

05:47:41.400 --> 05:47:44.700
What about all the other flame silks?

05:47:44.759 --> 05:47:47.939
If there were others, Would she think 3

05:47:47.939 --> 05:47:50.040
leaf wings were a fair trade for however

05:47:50.040 --> 05:47:52.680
many silk wings she had trapped in her

05:47:52.680 --> 05:47:53.819
flame silk factory?

05:47:53.880 --> 05:47:57.599
If not, could he accept his own freedom

05:47:57.599 --> 05:47:59.939
and Luna's, knowing he'd left others

05:47:59.939 --> 05:48:00.299
behind?

05:48:00.360 --> 05:48:03.779
Or what if Queen Wasp took the

05:48:03.779 --> 05:48:04.380
information?

05:48:04.439 --> 05:48:07.439
Destroyed the leaf wings, and then gave

05:48:07.439 --> 05:48:08.520
them nothing in return.

05:48:08.580 --> 05:48:12.060
He might betray sundew and break his

05:48:12.060 --> 05:48:14.939
promises, only to end up in a 1000 times

05:48:14.939 --> 05:48:16.319
as much trouble as before.

05:48:16.380 --> 05:48:19.619
He'd be walking straight into the queen's

05:48:19.619 --> 05:48:21.180
clutches with no leverage.

05:48:21.240 --> 05:48:23.880
And how would we explain cricket?

05:48:23.939 --> 05:48:25.560
He realized.

05:48:25.619 --> 05:48:28.919
What if telling the queen about the leaf

05:48:28.919 --> 05:48:29.279
wings?

05:48:29.340 --> 05:48:32.700
And how we found them, and where we've

05:48:32.700 --> 05:48:33.779
been for the last 3 days.

05:48:33.840 --> 05:48:37.680
Means she figures out that cricket can't

05:48:37.680 --> 05:48:38.520
be mind controlled.

05:48:38.639 --> 05:48:42.599
He needed to keep her out of this if he

05:48:42.599 --> 05:48:42.959
did it.

05:48:43.020 --> 05:48:44.759
He had no idea how.

05:48:44.819 --> 05:48:47.700
He needed to ask cricket for advice.

05:48:47.759 --> 05:48:50.400
He needed to think, but he didn't have

05:48:50.400 --> 05:48:50.580
time.

05:48:50.639 --> 05:48:53.759
Sundew slipped something out of one of

05:48:53.759 --> 05:48:55.680
her pouches and palmed it.

05:48:55.799 --> 05:48:56.639
She nodded to Cricket.

05:48:56.700 --> 05:48:58.860
Walked straight inside.

05:48:58.919 --> 05:49:00.299
Don't look guilty.

05:49:00.360 --> 05:49:02.880
What are you going to do?

05:49:03.000 --> 05:49:04.439
Cricket whispered.

05:49:04.500 --> 05:49:06.479
Something effective?

05:49:06.540 --> 05:49:08.099
Sundu hissed.

05:49:08.159 --> 05:49:08.700
Let's go.

05:49:08.759 --> 05:49:12.060
Cricket led the way back to the silk path

05:49:12.060 --> 05:49:13.979
and headed toward the front door of the

05:49:13.979 --> 05:49:14.939
temple.

05:49:15.000 --> 05:49:16.740
One of the guards was watching them

05:49:16.740 --> 05:49:19.259
intently, while the other had his gaze

05:49:19.259 --> 05:49:20.159
focused on his spear.

05:49:20.279 --> 05:49:23.040
Blue found it harder and harder to

05:49:23.040 --> 05:49:23.340
breathe.

05:49:23.400 --> 05:49:24.900
Should he do it now?

05:49:24.959 --> 05:49:27.479
He could run forward and throw himself on

05:49:27.479 --> 05:49:28.259
the guard's mercy.

05:49:28.380 --> 05:49:31.380
If he was going to betray sundew, he had

05:49:31.380 --> 05:49:33.659
to do it before they were caught in order

05:49:33.659 --> 05:49:35.580
to earn Queen Wasp's gratitude.

05:49:35.639 --> 05:49:37.979
But cricket.

05:49:38.040 --> 05:49:40.080
Is this what she would want?

05:49:40.139 --> 05:49:43.619
He heard whisking sounds from behind him

05:49:43.619 --> 05:49:46.080
like 2 tiny puffs of air.

05:49:46.139 --> 05:49:48.240
He glanced back at sundew.

05:49:48.299 --> 05:49:50.159
She jerked her chin at him.

05:49:50.220 --> 05:49:50.939
Keep walking.

05:49:51.000 --> 05:49:53.700
Cricket had reached the steps of the

05:49:53.700 --> 05:49:54.000
temple.

05:49:54.060 --> 05:49:55.380
This was it.

05:49:55.439 --> 05:49:58.080
The guards would step forward and demand

05:49:58.080 --> 05:49:59.220
to see their wristbands.

05:49:59.279 --> 05:50:02.159
They'd arrest him and sundew on the spot

05:50:02.159 --> 05:50:04.680
and it would only be a moment before they

05:50:04.680 --> 05:50:07.380
realized sundew's 2nd pair of wings was

05:50:07.380 --> 05:50:07.680
fake.

05:50:07.740 --> 05:50:09.720
Turn her in.

05:50:09.779 --> 05:50:11.279
Turn her in now.

05:50:11.340 --> 05:50:15.000
Blue took a deep breath and focused on

05:50:15.000 --> 05:50:16.439
the guard who'd been watching them.

05:50:16.500 --> 05:50:19.139
Which is when he realized.

05:50:19.259 --> 05:50:21.479
The guard wasn't moving.

05:50:21.540 --> 05:50:24.720
His eyes were still fixed on the carpet

05:50:24.720 --> 05:50:27.000
where they'd been, several steps back.

05:50:27.060 --> 05:50:30.360
His black wings, spotted with large

05:50:30.360 --> 05:50:33.180
yellow and red splotches, were halfway

05:50:33.180 --> 05:50:35.700
raised and his mouth was slightly open, as

05:50:35.700 --> 05:50:36.720
though he'd been about to speak.

05:50:36.779 --> 05:50:40.259
But he was as still as the statue of

05:50:40.259 --> 05:50:41.340
Queen Wasp outside.

05:50:41.400 --> 05:50:45.720
As still as the prisoners on misbehaviors

05:50:45.720 --> 05:50:46.139
weigh.

05:50:46.200 --> 05:50:48.959
Blue whipped his head around to the other

05:50:48.959 --> 05:50:49.319
guard.

05:50:49.439 --> 05:50:53.099
She was paralyzed the same way, frozen

05:50:53.099 --> 05:50:55.139
with her spear and her talons, and a

05:50:55.139 --> 05:50:56.099
slight frown on her face.

05:50:56.220 --> 05:50:59.040
How did son do do that?

05:50:59.099 --> 05:51:02.159
Only hive wings had that kind of nerve

05:51:02.159 --> 05:51:04.139
toxin, and only a few of them.

05:51:04.200 --> 05:51:07.139
And as far as blue knew, they could only

05:51:07.139 --> 05:51:09.540
wield it from up close by stabbing little

05:51:09.540 --> 05:51:10.919
stingers into their victims.

05:51:11.040 --> 05:51:13.979
But Sundew had done it from a distance

05:51:13.979 --> 05:51:17.040
somehow, and so quietly, that none of the

05:51:17.040 --> 05:51:18.840
dragons in the temple grounds had even

05:51:18.840 --> 05:51:19.680
looked up from their books.

05:51:19.799 --> 05:51:22.500
Unless someone looked carefully at the

05:51:22.500 --> 05:51:24.779
guards, it was possible no one would

05:51:24.779 --> 05:51:26.700
notice they were paralyzed at all for

05:51:26.700 --> 05:51:27.360
most of the night.

05:51:27.419 --> 05:51:31.560
Keep moving, Sundu whispered.

05:51:31.619 --> 05:51:33.180
You're both staring.

05:51:33.240 --> 05:51:35.819
Cricket shook herself and stepped through

05:51:35.819 --> 05:51:36.419
the archway.

05:51:36.479 --> 05:51:38.759
Blue wished he could pull her aside and

05:51:38.759 --> 05:51:39.000
talk.

05:51:39.060 --> 05:51:40.919
She must be terrified.

05:51:40.979 --> 05:51:43.200
At least, he was terrified.

05:51:43.259 --> 05:51:46.259
The room they stepped into was as

05:51:46.259 --> 05:51:47.880
tranquil as the grounds outside.

05:51:47.939 --> 05:51:51.060
To their left, a painting of clear sight

05:51:51.060 --> 05:51:53.700
took up almost the entire wall, with

05:51:53.700 --> 05:51:55.619
small lanterns flickering on either side

05:51:55.619 --> 05:51:56.220
of it.

05:51:56.279 --> 05:51:58.439
She looked kind and wise.

05:51:58.500 --> 05:52:00.540
Light blue had always imagined.

05:52:00.599 --> 05:52:03.900
Offerings were piled below the painting.

05:52:03.959 --> 05:52:07.319
Bundles of wilting marigolds, tiny silver

05:52:07.319 --> 05:52:10.020
sugar cakes, little weavings of poems.

05:52:10.080 --> 05:52:13.500
To their right, the wall was divided into

05:52:13.500 --> 05:52:16.200
100s of small cubby holes in a honeycomb

05:52:16.200 --> 05:52:16.619
pattern.

05:52:16.680 --> 05:52:19.740
Most of the holes held scraps of paper

05:52:19.740 --> 05:52:23.159
wishes written by dragon claws, dreams

05:52:23.159 --> 05:52:24.959
for what they hoped the future would hold

05:52:24.959 --> 05:52:27.060
folded and tucked inside.

05:52:27.119 --> 05:52:29.819
A desk stood in the corner with more

05:52:29.819 --> 05:52:31.619
paper for anyone who wanted to write one

05:52:31.619 --> 05:52:32.040
of their own.

05:52:32.099 --> 05:52:35.459
Blue imagined all the dragons who had

05:52:35.459 --> 05:52:35.880
come through here.

05:52:35.939 --> 05:52:39.240
All their shaking talons asking clear

05:52:39.240 --> 05:52:42.419
sight for hope, for luck, for love.

05:52:42.540 --> 05:52:45.840
Hive wings and silk wings alike visited

05:52:45.840 --> 05:52:48.000
the temple and believed in clear sight.

05:52:48.060 --> 05:52:50.340
She helped them believe in a better

05:52:50.340 --> 05:52:50.580
future.

05:52:50.700 --> 05:52:54.299
Will they lose that faith without the

05:52:54.299 --> 05:52:54.479
book?

05:52:54.599 --> 05:52:56.459
If we steal it?

05:52:56.520 --> 05:52:58.560
Does this all fall apart?

05:52:58.619 --> 05:53:01.080
Will anyone come here anymore?

05:53:01.139 --> 05:53:04.860
He knew what he wished he could ride on

05:53:04.860 --> 05:53:06.000
one of those scraps of paper.

05:53:06.060 --> 05:53:08.819
Please keep my friends safe.

05:53:08.880 --> 05:53:11.759
Please, tell me what to do.

05:53:11.880 --> 05:53:15.540
Cricket didn't pause in the antechamber.

05:53:15.659 --> 05:53:17.700
She kept walking toward the inner

05:53:17.700 --> 05:53:18.180
sanctum.

05:53:18.240 --> 05:53:21.479
Blue, who had slowed down to look around

05:53:21.479 --> 05:53:23.939
was able to watch sundo as she went past

05:53:23.939 --> 05:53:24.540
him.

05:53:24.599 --> 05:53:26.819
He saw her lift something to her mouth

05:53:26.819 --> 05:53:30.479
and swiftly blow into it, once, slight

05:53:30.479 --> 05:53:31.259
tilt to the right.

05:53:31.319 --> 05:53:32.580
Twice.

05:53:32.639 --> 05:53:35.340
She had uncanny aim.

05:53:35.400 --> 05:53:38.400
He saw the moment each guard froze.

05:53:38.459 --> 05:53:42.419
Spears slightly lifted, mouths ajar, as

05:53:42.419 --> 05:53:44.040
though they'd sensed a threat and were

05:53:44.040 --> 05:53:45.180
about to order them to halt.

05:53:45.240 --> 05:53:47.580
Whatever she was shooting.

05:53:47.639 --> 05:53:49.500
The guards were no use to him now.

05:53:49.560 --> 05:53:52.439
He couldn't hand over sundew to a pair of

05:53:52.439 --> 05:53:52.919
statues.

05:53:52.979 --> 05:53:55.860
How are we going to get out of this?

05:53:55.979 --> 05:53:59.279
There had to be more than just guards

05:53:59.279 --> 05:54:00.299
between them and the book.

05:54:00.360 --> 05:54:02.939
Maybe the case would be impossible to get

05:54:02.939 --> 05:54:03.180
into?

05:54:03.240 --> 05:54:05.159
He really hoped it was.

05:54:05.279 --> 05:54:08.639
Cricket stepped between the 2 guards

05:54:08.639 --> 05:54:10.799
casting them each a nervous glance.

05:54:10.860 --> 05:54:13.200
Neither of them so much as twitched.

05:54:13.319 --> 05:54:16.259
With a deep breath, she opened the double

05:54:16.259 --> 05:54:18.360
doors and stepped into the final room.

05:54:18.419 --> 05:54:22.500
This one was small and shadowy, and

05:54:22.500 --> 05:54:25.200
perfectly square, like standing inside a

05:54:25.200 --> 05:54:25.979
wooden box.

05:54:26.040 --> 05:54:28.979
Blue squinted at the glimmering ceiling

05:54:28.979 --> 05:54:31.560
and realized that it was inlaid with

05:54:31.560 --> 05:54:32.700
Moonstone stars.

05:54:32.759 --> 05:54:35.340
The only light in the room was a lantern

05:54:35.340 --> 05:54:37.500
that hung over the case that held the

05:54:37.500 --> 05:54:37.680
book.

05:54:37.740 --> 05:54:39.659
Blue caught his breath.

05:54:39.720 --> 05:54:43.319
He knew it wasn't the book itself, but

05:54:43.319 --> 05:54:45.299
the case was carved to look like a book

05:54:45.299 --> 05:54:45.599
too.

05:54:45.659 --> 05:54:49.139
A book with dragons sweeping across the

05:54:49.139 --> 05:54:51.479
