06:06:29.040 --> 06:06:31.799
the librarian's tail, and clung to it

06:06:31.799 --> 06:06:33.479
with their small wriggling legs.

06:06:33.540 --> 06:06:36.180
Their antennae searched her scales as

06:06:36.180 --> 06:06:36.840
though puzzled.

06:06:36.900 --> 06:06:38.819
What are you doing?

06:06:38.880 --> 06:06:40.319
The queen demanded.

06:06:40.380 --> 06:06:43.500
When you're inside a dragon?

06:06:43.560 --> 06:06:44.520
Sundew said.

06:06:44.580 --> 06:06:47.040
You can fill everything they can, can't

06:06:47.040 --> 06:06:47.220
you?

06:06:47.340 --> 06:06:49.319
Or else you wouldn't have screamed when I

06:06:49.319 --> 06:06:49.799
broke your arm.

06:06:49.919 --> 06:06:53.700
Yes, Cricket answered for her.

06:06:53.759 --> 06:06:56.639
I know she leaves dragons when they're

06:06:56.639 --> 06:06:57.180
hurt or dying.

06:06:57.240 --> 06:07:02.880
Oh, I see your game, the queen scoffed.

06:07:02.939 --> 06:07:05.220
I can take a lot more pain than a broken

06:07:05.220 --> 06:07:05.819
arm though.

06:07:05.939 --> 06:07:08.400
I'm not afraid of anything you can do to

06:07:08.400 --> 06:07:08.880
this body.

06:07:09.000 --> 06:07:13.319
That may be, said Sundew, but I'm

06:07:13.319 --> 06:07:14.939
guessing that's because you've never been

06:07:14.939 --> 06:07:16.619
bitten by a bullet ant before.

06:07:16.680 --> 06:07:20.159
Blue had never even heard of a bullet ant

06:07:20.159 --> 06:07:22.860
and from her silence, he guessed the

06:07:22.860 --> 06:07:23.759
queen hadn't either.

06:07:23.819 --> 06:07:27.419
They all watched the tiny ants circle for

06:07:27.419 --> 06:07:30.540
a moment, and then start climbing up and

06:07:30.540 --> 06:07:33.240
up the librarian's tail, and along her

06:07:33.240 --> 06:07:33.479
spine.

06:07:33.599 --> 06:07:37.080
The librarian didn't move and didn't move

06:07:37.080 --> 06:07:38.340
and didn't move.

06:07:38.400 --> 06:07:41.400
And then, as one of them ran toward her

06:07:41.400 --> 06:07:44.099
neck, she flicked her wing instinctively

06:07:44.099 --> 06:07:45.000
to knock it off her.

06:07:45.060 --> 06:07:49.080
Instead, it latched onto the wing tip and

06:07:49.080 --> 06:07:51.360
bit down with little pincer jaws.

06:07:51.419 --> 06:07:54.779
The scream that came out of the librarian

06:07:54.779 --> 06:07:56.459
was like nothing blew had ever heard

06:07:56.459 --> 06:07:56.700
before.

06:07:56.759 --> 06:07:59.819
She collapsed as though her bones had

06:07:59.819 --> 06:08:02.279
melted, and Sundew dropped her to the

06:08:02.279 --> 06:08:04.860
floor, where the dragon lay shaking all

06:08:04.860 --> 06:08:07.139
over, and screaming that terrible

06:08:07.139 --> 06:08:07.860
scream.

06:08:07.919 --> 06:08:10.740
Sundew stepped over the patches of blood

06:08:10.740 --> 06:08:13.259
on the floor. took the jar from cricket

06:08:13.259 --> 06:08:15.840
and neatly scooped up the 2 ants without

06:08:15.840 --> 06:08:16.619
letting them touch her.

06:08:16.680 --> 06:08:19.860
She screwed the lid back on very tightly

06:08:19.860 --> 06:08:21.840
and packed it away again in her pouch.

06:08:21.900 --> 06:08:25.259
Then she crouched by the librarian's head

06:08:25.259 --> 06:08:27.599
and peeled open one of her eyelids.

06:08:27.659 --> 06:08:29.220
Had enough?

06:08:29.279 --> 06:08:31.919
She asked the white eyeball beneath.

06:08:31.979 --> 06:08:34.680
This pain is going to last half a day

06:08:34.680 --> 06:08:35.580
just so you know.

06:08:35.639 --> 06:08:37.560
It's not stopping anytime soon.

06:08:37.619 --> 06:08:43.680
I'll kill you for this, the queen

06:08:43.680 --> 06:08:44.159
hissed.

06:08:44.220 --> 06:08:46.919
And then abruptly, the eye rolled back

06:08:46.919 --> 06:08:48.599
and became a normal eye.

06:08:48.659 --> 06:08:52.740
Dark orange irises and dilated pupils

06:08:52.740 --> 06:08:54.000
stared up at sundew.

06:08:54.060 --> 06:08:56.220
The librarian stopped screaming.

06:08:56.279 --> 06:08:58.439
You...

06:08:58.439 --> 06:09:02.040
You did it, she said in a strained

06:09:02.040 --> 06:09:02.400
voice.

06:09:02.520 --> 06:09:03.959
Ow.

06:09:04.020 --> 06:09:05.040
Ow.

06:09:05.099 --> 06:09:06.659
Oh.

06:09:06.720 --> 06:09:11.099
I know it's worth it, but ow, it's hard

06:09:11.099 --> 06:09:12.180
to really know that right now.

06:09:12.240 --> 06:09:15.720
I tried once before to hurt myself badly

06:09:15.720 --> 06:09:18.119
enough that she'd set me free, but it

06:09:18.119 --> 06:09:18.479
didn't work.

06:09:18.540 --> 06:09:22.020
This is so much worse though.

06:09:22.080 --> 06:09:26.040
She sat up. holding her wing out at an

06:09:26.040 --> 06:09:28.380
awkward angle and moaning softly.

06:09:28.439 --> 06:09:30.419
Is she really gone?

06:09:30.479 --> 06:09:32.220
Sundew asked.

06:09:32.279 --> 06:09:34.080
The librarian nodded.

06:09:34.139 --> 06:09:35.340
Yes.

06:09:35.400 --> 06:09:37.560
For the 1st time in years.

06:09:37.619 --> 06:09:42.119
She inhaled and exhaled slowly, then

06:09:42.119 --> 06:09:44.040
glanced at her wing and winced again.

06:09:44.099 --> 06:09:47.279
If she's really gone, then here.

06:09:47.340 --> 06:09:48.599
Sundew said.

06:09:48.659 --> 06:09:51.540
Digging out a pair of dark green leaves

06:09:51.540 --> 06:09:52.139
from another pouch.

06:09:52.259 --> 06:09:55.680
To this and spit it on the spot where the

06:09:55.680 --> 06:09:56.340
ant bit you.

06:09:56.400 --> 06:09:59.520
It'll deaden the nerve, and should dull

06:09:59.520 --> 06:10:00.779
the pain for a while at least.

06:10:00.840 --> 06:10:04.560
Thank you, the librarian said.

06:10:04.619 --> 06:10:06.779
She put the leaves in her mouth and

06:10:06.779 --> 06:10:07.319
started chewing.

06:10:07.380 --> 06:10:10.619
It'll also make your tongue feel very

06:10:10.619 --> 06:10:13.319
weird, Sundu added, just to warn you.

06:10:13.380 --> 06:10:18.840
The librarian agreed, making a face.

06:10:18.900 --> 06:10:22.139
Has the queen been controlling you all

06:10:22.139 --> 06:10:22.380
this time?

06:10:22.500 --> 06:10:23.819
Cricket asked.

06:10:23.880 --> 06:10:27.180
The librarian nodded. talking awkwardly

06:10:27.180 --> 06:10:28.259
around the leaves in her mouth.

06:10:28.319 --> 06:10:33.000
Ever since the initiation ceremony.

06:10:33.060 --> 06:10:36.240
I woke up from the ritual with her inside

06:10:36.240 --> 06:10:36.959
my head.

06:10:37.080 --> 06:10:40.560
When she sleeps, she makes me sleep.

06:10:40.619 --> 06:10:43.619
She's always in there.

06:10:43.680 --> 06:10:45.419
She shuddered.

06:10:45.479 --> 06:10:49.020
I was so proud to be chosen.

06:10:49.080 --> 06:10:51.419
I never knew what it would mean.

06:10:51.479 --> 06:10:54.779
I had no idea she did this.

06:10:54.840 --> 06:10:59.759
That's horrible, Blue said softly.

06:10:59.819 --> 06:11:02.639
The book felt fragile and warm in his

06:11:02.639 --> 06:11:03.180
talons.

06:11:03.240 --> 06:11:05.580
He wanted to protect it with all his

06:11:05.580 --> 06:11:08.220
heart, and he was sure anyone who wanted

06:11:08.220 --> 06:11:10.080
to be the librarian must feel the same

06:11:10.080 --> 06:11:10.319
way.

06:11:10.380 --> 06:11:13.139
They didn't need to be brainwashed into

06:11:13.139 --> 06:11:13.319
it.

06:11:13.380 --> 06:11:16.319
Queen Wasp didn't even give them a chance

06:11:16.319 --> 06:11:17.639
to show their loyalty.

06:11:17.700 --> 06:11:19.919
She forced it upon them instead.

06:11:19.979 --> 06:11:23.580
She'll be back in your head as soon as

06:11:23.580 --> 06:11:24.299
she thinks it's safe.

06:11:24.360 --> 06:11:25.860
Cricket pointed out.

06:11:25.919 --> 06:11:30.119
I know, the librarian said, nodding.

06:11:30.180 --> 06:11:33.840
But even a moment to be myself, is more

06:11:33.840 --> 06:11:35.400
than I ever thought I'd have again.

06:11:35.459 --> 06:11:38.939
She spread the leaf paste over the edge

06:11:38.939 --> 06:11:41.040
of her wing, and the pain lines around

06:11:41.040 --> 06:11:42.060
her eyes relaxed.

06:11:42.119 --> 06:11:45.419
Oh, thank clear sight.

06:11:45.479 --> 06:11:48.419
Sundew glanced across a blue.

06:11:48.479 --> 06:11:52.319
So, she said, we have the book, which is

06:11:52.319 --> 06:11:54.419
great, but we're surrounded by hive

06:11:54.419 --> 06:11:56.159
zombies who would really like to kill us

06:11:56.159 --> 06:11:58.319
which is less great.

06:11:58.380 --> 06:12:01.380
Can you throw bullet ants at them?

06:12:01.439 --> 06:12:03.959
he asked, or blow dart them?

06:12:04.020 --> 06:12:07.200
I don't have many more blow darts, she

06:12:07.200 --> 06:12:09.720
said, or enough bullet ans for everyone

06:12:09.720 --> 06:12:12.540
in the whole hive, although that would be

06:12:12.540 --> 06:12:13.740
my kind of revenge.

06:12:13.860 --> 06:12:16.919
She started collecting the pouches she'd

06:12:16.919 --> 06:12:18.959
lost during the fight, checking their

06:12:18.959 --> 06:12:20.939
contents, and resettling them around

06:12:20.939 --> 06:12:21.299
her.

06:12:21.360 --> 06:12:23.759
She kicked the pair of fake wings into

06:12:23.759 --> 06:12:24.180
the corner.

06:12:24.240 --> 06:12:27.900
I'll help you, the librarian said

06:12:27.900 --> 06:12:28.500
quietly.

06:12:28.560 --> 06:12:30.180
You will?

06:12:30.299 --> 06:12:34.080
Blue said, surprised, but we're stealing

06:12:34.080 --> 06:12:34.380
the book.

06:12:34.439 --> 06:12:36.959
Your whole purpose in life is to keep it

06:12:36.959 --> 06:12:37.200
safe.

06:12:37.259 --> 06:12:40.139
The librarian looked at the book in his

06:12:40.139 --> 06:12:43.020
talons, and her eyes were sadder than any

06:12:43.020 --> 06:12:44.520
dragons he'd ever seen before.

06:12:44.580 --> 06:12:48.479
I think it's time someone else knew the

06:12:48.479 --> 06:12:50.340
book's secrets, she said.

06:12:50.400 --> 06:12:54.119
And if the queen kills me for it, I'll

06:12:54.119 --> 06:12:55.740
still be better off than I was this

06:12:55.740 --> 06:12:55.979
morning.

06:12:56.099 --> 06:12:58.020
How can you help us?

06:12:58.139 --> 06:13:01.200
Sundew asked practically, is there

06:13:01.200 --> 06:13:01.919
another way out of here?

06:13:02.040 --> 06:13:05.340
Not exactly, she answered.

06:13:05.400 --> 06:13:07.860
But I can get you up to the dome at

06:13:07.860 --> 06:13:08.099
least.

06:13:08.159 --> 06:13:12.000
The librarian got to her feet. wincing

06:13:12.000 --> 06:13:13.799
from the other wounds Sundew had given

06:13:13.799 --> 06:13:16.380
her, and limped to the back corner where

06:13:16.380 --> 06:13:17.340
she'd 1st appeared.

06:13:17.400 --> 06:13:20.040
She couldn't put any weight on her broken

06:13:20.040 --> 06:13:22.979
arm, and Blue wondered if sundew felt

06:13:22.979 --> 06:13:24.900
anywhere near as terrible as he did about

06:13:24.900 --> 06:13:25.139
that.

06:13:25.200 --> 06:13:28.860
A secret panel in the wooden wall slid

06:13:28.860 --> 06:13:29.700
aside at her touch.

06:13:29.759 --> 06:13:31.799
And they all followed her through into

06:13:31.799 --> 06:13:33.180
the librarian's quarters.

06:13:33.240 --> 06:13:36.540
Compared to the other rooms of the temple

06:13:36.540 --> 06:13:38.580
this one felt cold and empty.

06:13:38.639 --> 06:13:42.000
A bamboo mat in the corner, and a small

06:13:42.000 --> 06:13:44.159
bookshelf, were the only 2 items in the

06:13:44.159 --> 06:13:44.279
room.

06:13:44.400 --> 06:13:48.479
It looks like a prison cell, Blue

06:13:48.479 --> 06:13:48.959
thought.

06:13:49.020 --> 06:13:51.959
The position of librarian was supposed to

06:13:51.959 --> 06:13:54.599
be the tribe's greatest honor, but

06:13:54.599 --> 06:13:57.479
instead it was a trick, a snare set to

06:13:57.479 --> 06:13:59.279
trap one of the brightest minds of the

06:13:59.279 --> 06:14:01.439
hive wings, and keep her useless

06:14:01.439 --> 06:14:01.740
forever.

06:14:01.799 --> 06:14:05.700
Another panel set aside to reveal a

06:14:05.700 --> 06:14:07.080
spiral staircase going up.

06:14:07.139 --> 06:14:10.979
They climbed after the librarian, rounding

06:14:10.979 --> 06:14:12.959
the last curve to find themselves in an

06:14:12.959 --> 06:14:15.720
attic that smelled of wood chips and

06:14:15.720 --> 06:14:16.619
boiled silk.

06:14:16.680 --> 06:14:19.560
The underside of the dome curved over

06:14:19.560 --> 06:14:22.080
their heads, and Blue saw a door on one

06:14:22.080 --> 06:14:24.060
side that led to a small balcony.

06:14:24.119 --> 06:14:26.279
What was this for?

06:14:26.340 --> 06:14:29.459
Cricket asked, blinking around at the

06:14:29.459 --> 06:14:31.740
dust and abandoned boxes.

06:14:31.799 --> 06:14:33.540
She picked up an odd looking tool that

06:14:33.540 --> 06:14:35.340
looked a bit like a curved dragon

06:14:35.340 --> 06:14:35.880
tongue.

06:14:35.939 --> 06:14:39.479
I think librarians used to make books up

06:14:39.479 --> 06:14:39.659
here.

06:14:39.720 --> 06:14:42.119
The librarian said wistfully.

06:14:42.180 --> 06:14:45.299
Oh, Cricket said.

06:14:45.360 --> 06:14:48.419
She ran one claw along the top of a dusty

06:14:48.419 --> 06:14:48.720
table.

06:14:48.779 --> 06:14:51.360
That's what I thought they did too.

06:14:51.419 --> 06:14:53.759
Not anymore.

06:14:53.819 --> 06:14:56.159
Not in a long time.

06:14:56.220 --> 06:14:59.520
The librarian led the way to the balcony

06:14:59.520 --> 06:15:01.319
door and peeked out through the glass.

06:15:01.380 --> 06:15:03.119
Oh, dear.

06:15:03.180 --> 06:15:06.299
Sundew edged in beside her and looked out

06:15:06.299 --> 06:15:06.599
as well.

06:15:06.659 --> 06:15:08.880
Hmm, she snorted.

06:15:08.939 --> 06:15:10.200
I can take them.

06:15:10.259 --> 06:15:13.919
Every hive wing and wasp hive.

06:15:13.979 --> 06:15:14.880
Cricket said.

06:15:14.939 --> 06:15:17.819
You are terrifying, but I still find that

06:15:17.819 --> 06:15:18.779
a little hard to believe.

06:15:18.840 --> 06:15:22.799
Unless you have something else alarming

06:15:22.799 --> 06:15:23.759
in one of those pouches.

06:15:23.880 --> 06:15:25.680
Blue said, hopefully.

06:15:25.740 --> 06:15:28.319
Sundew tapped the floor thoughtfully with

06:15:28.319 --> 06:15:29.099
one claw.

06:15:29.159 --> 06:15:33.180
Maybe, she said, but I need fire to make

06:15:33.180 --> 06:15:33.419
it work.

06:15:33.479 --> 06:15:37.080
I have fire, Cricket said.

06:15:37.139 --> 06:15:39.119
She scrambled to pull out the little

06:15:39.119 --> 06:15:41.400
stone jar with a flame silk thread inside

06:15:41.400 --> 06:15:43.439
and tipped it to show sundew.

06:15:43.500 --> 06:15:44.939
Would this work?

06:15:45.000 --> 06:15:47.520
The leaf wing's eyes gleamed.

06:15:47.580 --> 06:15:48.900
I think so.

06:15:48.959 --> 06:15:51.240
Be careful.

06:15:51.299 --> 06:15:54.840
The librarian pleaded, as Sundew took the

06:15:54.840 --> 06:15:56.040
jar in her claws.

06:15:56.040 --> 06:15:58.080
Don't set the temple on fire.

06:15:58.200 --> 06:16:01.979
You can have the book, but please leave

06:16:01.979 --> 06:16:02.580
the temple.

06:16:02.639 --> 06:16:06.119
Sandu hesitated, as though she would have

06:16:06.119 --> 06:16:08.340
loved to set the whole hive on fire.

06:16:08.400 --> 06:16:10.500
But after a moment, she nodded.

06:16:10.560 --> 06:16:12.180
Stand back.

06:16:12.240 --> 06:16:16.020
She took a branch covered with long, waxy

06:16:16.020 --> 06:16:17.819
looking red brown leaves out of another

06:16:17.819 --> 06:16:18.240
pouch.

06:16:18.360 --> 06:16:22.500
With careful, slow movements, she dipped

06:16:22.500 --> 06:16:24.959
the point of each one into the jar until

06:16:24.959 --> 06:16:26.939
it touched the flame silk and caught

06:16:26.939 --> 06:16:27.180
fire.

06:16:27.240 --> 06:16:30.360
A bright flame flared for a moment on

06:16:30.360 --> 06:16:33.180
each leaf, then vanished into curls of

06:16:33.180 --> 06:16:33.840
reddish smoke.

06:16:33.900 --> 06:16:37.500
Sundew handed the jar back to cricket, and

06:16:37.500 --> 06:16:39.959
opened the door to the balcony, holding

06:16:39.959 --> 06:16:41.819
the burning branch out away from her.

06:16:41.939 --> 06:16:45.900
Now Blue could see the temple grounds, and

06:16:45.900 --> 06:16:48.240
the hive wings who covered every inch of

06:16:48.240 --> 06:16:50.580
space between the temple and the door.

06:16:50.639 --> 06:16:54.419
Orange, yellow, red, and black scales

06:16:54.419 --> 06:16:57.840
rippled like a vast sea of poisonous

06:16:57.840 --> 06:16:58.319
snakes.

06:16:58.380 --> 06:17:01.139
As sundew stepped onto the balcony of the

06:17:01.139 --> 06:17:03.959
dome, every head snapped toward her in

06:17:03.959 --> 06:17:06.840
unison, blank eyes latching onto her.

06:17:06.959 --> 06:17:10.259
One branch of burning leaves seemed very

06:17:10.259 --> 06:17:13.020
small in the face of all those talons and

06:17:13.020 --> 06:17:13.919
teeth and claws.

06:17:13.979 --> 06:17:17.159
Blue shivered, and he felt cricket put

06:17:17.159 --> 06:17:19.319
one wing over his back and lean against

06:17:19.319 --> 06:17:19.619
him.

06:17:19.680 --> 06:17:23.459
I should be comforting her, he thought.

06:17:23.520 --> 06:17:25.799
I'm the one who's ruined her life.

06:17:25.860 --> 06:17:28.860
But if she was still willing to be close

06:17:28.860 --> 06:17:31.080
to him, perhaps she forgave him.

06:17:31.080 --> 06:17:33.779
Perhaps she still liked him anyway.

06:17:33.840 --> 06:17:36.959
Sundew hissed at the crowd of hive

06:17:36.959 --> 06:17:37.439
wings.

06:17:37.500 --> 06:17:40.319
Smoke was rolling off the leaves now

06:17:40.319 --> 06:17:43.200
growing thicker and thicker and redder

06:17:43.200 --> 06:17:43.919
and darker.

06:17:43.979 --> 06:17:47.159
She glanced at it one more time, checking

06:17:47.159 --> 06:17:50.159
that it was all smoke and no flames, and

06:17:50.159 --> 06:17:51.540
then she threw it with all her might

06:17:51.540 --> 06:17:53.700
directly into the middle of the watching

06:17:53.700 --> 06:17:54.479
dragons.

06:17:54.540 --> 06:17:58.259
It hit a yellow black dragon, who shook

06:17:58.259 --> 06:17:59.819
it off and hopped away with a yelp.

06:17:59.880 --> 06:18:02.520
The dragon's closest to him began

06:18:02.520 --> 06:18:03.119
coughing.

06:18:03.180 --> 06:18:06.119
They sank to the ground, one by one

06:18:06.119 --> 06:18:08.759
hacking and wheezing as the smoke

06:18:08.759 --> 06:18:11.340
billowed up and out, swallowing the

06:18:11.340 --> 06:18:12.119
dragons around it.

06:18:12.180 --> 06:18:15.840
But it wasn't enough, for each hive wing

06:18:15.840 --> 06:18:17.159
incapacitated by the smoke.

06:18:17.279 --> 06:18:20.220
There were 5 more still grimly standing

06:18:20.220 --> 06:18:22.319
between them and the only way out.

06:18:22.380 --> 06:18:25.439
Capture the flame silk.

06:18:25.500 --> 06:18:26.880
They intoned.

06:18:27.000 --> 06:18:28.919
Kill the other two.

06:18:28.979 --> 06:18:32.340
The buzz of their wings filled the

06:18:32.340 --> 06:18:32.819
chamber.

06:18:32.880 --> 06:18:35.819
As dragon after dragon rose into the air

06:18:35.819 --> 06:18:37.680
and surged toward the dome.

06:18:37.799 --> 06:18:41.340
Blue's heartbeat surged with panic.

06:18:41.400 --> 06:18:43.979
Wait, that's not the only way out.

06:18:44.040 --> 06:18:45.720
He looked up.

06:18:45.779 --> 06:18:49.200
There was the skylight, and the stars far

06:18:49.200 --> 06:18:49.619
above them.

06:18:49.680 --> 06:18:52.439
The hole was barely large enough for a

06:18:52.439 --> 06:18:53.340
dragon to fit through.

06:18:53.400 --> 06:18:56.279
But he and cricket and sundew were all

06:18:56.279 --> 06:18:56.939
fairly small.

06:18:57.000 --> 06:18:59.279
If they could break the glass at the top

06:18:59.279 --> 06:19:01.380
they could at least get outside the

06:19:01.380 --> 06:19:01.740
hive.

06:19:01.799 --> 06:19:06.299
Up, he shouted, grabbing Cricket's arm

06:19:06.299 --> 06:19:06.720
and pointing.

06:19:06.840 --> 06:19:08.880
We can go out the skylight.

06:19:08.939 --> 06:19:12.119
She followed his gaze, then looked back

06:19:12.119 --> 06:19:12.360
at him.

06:19:12.479 --> 06:19:14.340
What about you?

06:19:14.400 --> 06:19:15.419
She asked.

06:19:15.540 --> 06:19:17.220
How do we get you up there?

06:19:17.279 --> 06:19:19.439
Oh.

06:19:19.799 --> 06:19:22.439
He twisted to look back at his wing buds

06:19:22.439 --> 06:19:24.540
as though perhaps they'd have magically

06:19:24.540 --> 06:19:26.400
turned into wings in the last several

06:19:26.400 --> 06:19:27.419
heartbeats.

06:19:27.479 --> 06:19:29.459
Will carry him.

06:19:29.520 --> 06:19:33.119
Sunju threw open her wings and leaped up

06:19:33.119 --> 06:19:33.900
off the balcony.

06:19:33.959 --> 06:19:37.200
Let's go, and hold on to that book.

06:19:37.259 --> 06:19:40.500
She started smashing hive wings aside

06:19:40.500 --> 06:19:41.880
with her tail and talons.

06:19:41.939 --> 06:19:44.159
He clutched the book to his chest.

06:19:44.220 --> 06:19:47.400
Cricket whirled around in a panic and

06:19:47.400 --> 06:19:49.799
grabbed a long, twisted silk rope from

06:19:49.799 --> 06:19:50.580
one of the tables.

06:19:50.639 --> 06:19:52.979
She and the librarian threw it around

06:19:52.979 --> 06:19:55.619
Blue's shoulders and chest and tied it

06:19:55.619 --> 06:19:55.860
fast.

06:19:55.919 --> 06:19:58.500
They each took an end and ran to the

06:19:58.500 --> 06:19:58.919
balcony.

06:19:58.979 --> 06:20:03.479
I wish I had wings, Blue thought, closing

06:20:03.479 --> 06:20:03.779
his eyes.

06:20:03.840 --> 06:20:06.840
I wish I were more than a dead weight for

06:20:06.840 --> 06:20:07.919
my friends to drag around.

06:20:08.040 --> 06:20:12.060
The rope jerked tight under his arms, and

06:20:12.060 --> 06:20:13.979
he was dragged smack into the balcony

06:20:13.979 --> 06:20:17.040
railing, nearly tumbling over it before

06:20:17.040 --> 06:20:19.319
the rope steadied, and he felt himself

06:20:19.319 --> 06:20:21.479
lifted up, up into the air.

06:20:21.540 --> 06:20:25.380
He tilted sideways almost immediately, as

06:20:25.380 --> 06:20:28.020
the librarian's bigger wings soared ahead

06:20:28.020 --> 06:20:30.240
and Cricket faltered under his weight.

06:20:30.360 --> 06:20:33.540
Then Zundu swept up beside her and took

06:20:33.540 --> 06:20:35.819
the rope as well, tugging him upright.

06:20:35.880 --> 06:20:39.299
All he could do was dangle helplessly

06:20:39.299 --> 06:20:41.759
holding on to the book for dear life

06:20:41.759 --> 06:20:45.000
right below his talons, the smoke still

06:20:45.000 --> 06:20:47.580
billowed, and the seething mass of hive

06:20:47.580 --> 06:20:49.200
wings snapped and churned.

06:20:49.319 --> 06:20:52.619
Three of them surged toward his feet, and

06:20:52.619 --> 06:20:54.000
he kicked at them frantically.

06:20:54.060 --> 06:20:56.819
Ah, help, he shouted.

06:20:56.880 --> 06:21:00.479
A cascade of little red centipedes poured

06:21:00.479 --> 06:21:01.500
down from above him.

06:21:01.560 --> 06:21:04.619
Each dragon they struck let out a shriek

06:21:04.619 --> 06:21:07.259
of alarm or pain, and dropped away

06:21:07.259 --> 06:21:08.520
clawing at his face.

06:21:08.580 --> 06:21:11.700
The dome was shrinking below him.

06:21:11.759 --> 06:21:14.700
Blue looked up and saw sundew, then

06:21:14.700 --> 06:21:16.560
Cricket duck into the skylight hole.

06:21:16.619 --> 06:21:19.080
The librarian was hovering beside it

06:21:19.080 --> 06:21:21.900
taking up the slack in his rope, waiting

06:21:21.900 --> 06:21:22.979
to let them go 1st.

06:21:23.040 --> 06:21:26.819
And then suddenly, she looked down at him

06:21:26.819 --> 06:21:28.500
and her eyes were white again.

06:21:28.560 --> 06:21:31.680
Nice try, she said.

06:21:31.799 --> 06:21:34.680
Cricket, Blue screamed.

06:21:34.740 --> 06:21:37.380
The librarian's claws slashed through the

06:21:37.380 --> 06:21:38.939
rope connecting him to his friends.

06:21:39.000 --> 06:21:42.900
He tumbled sideways, jerking to a stop at

06:21:42.900 --> 06:21:45.240
the end of the severed rope, but feeling

06:21:45.240 --> 06:21:47.520
the knot start to slip loose around his

06:21:47.520 --> 06:21:47.819
chest.

06:21:47.939 --> 06:21:51.240
Crickets shot back down the shaft and

06:21:51.240 --> 06:21:53.220
flew at the librarian's face.

06:21:53.340 --> 06:21:56.220
The librarian ducked away, gave her an

06:21:56.220 --> 06:21:59.880
evil grin, and let Blue's rope fall from

06:21:59.880 --> 06:22:00.659
her hands.

06:22:00.659 --> 06:22:03.479
His stomach flipped as he started to

06:22:03.479 --> 06:22:04.020
plummet.

06:22:04.080 --> 06:22:07.200
Then jerked to a stop again, as cricket

06:22:07.200 --> 06:22:08.700
caught the end of the rope.

06:22:08.759 --> 06:22:11.279
But she wasn't strong enough to lift him

06:22:11.279 --> 06:22:11.520
alone.

06:22:11.580 --> 06:22:14.459
Even with her wings beating as hard as

06:22:14.459 --> 06:22:16.919
she could, they were both sinking down

06:22:16.919 --> 06:22:18.299
toward the hive wings.

06:22:18.360 --> 06:22:20.939
Cricket, he yelled.

06:22:21.000 --> 06:22:22.560
You have to go without me.

06:22:22.619 --> 06:22:25.380
They won't kill me, but they're under

06:22:25.380 --> 06:22:26.279
orders to kill you.

06:22:26.340 --> 06:22:28.380
Take the book and go.

06:22:28.439 --> 06:22:30.240
I'm not.

06:22:30.599 --> 06:22:33.180
She started to shout back, but he was

06:22:33.180 --> 06:22:34.919
already tossing the book up toward her.

06:22:35.040 --> 06:22:37.740
She had to drop the rope to catch it.

06:22:37.799 --> 06:22:40.080
She did it instinctively.

06:22:40.139 --> 06:22:42.060
As he'd known she would.

06:22:42.119 --> 06:22:45.119
She was as well trained to love the book

06:22:45.119 --> 06:22:45.840
as he was.

06:22:45.900 --> 06:22:49.139
All their lives, they'd known it was the

06:22:49.139 --> 06:22:51.119
most precious object in their world.

06:22:51.180 --> 06:22:53.700
She'd reach for it without thinking.

06:22:53.759 --> 06:22:56.580
Even if her conscious mind would have

06:22:56.580 --> 06:22:58.319
chosen to save blue instead.

06:22:58.319 --> 06:23:03.419
As he fell, as a 1000 claws reached up to

06:23:03.419 --> 06:23:06.060
seize him, he saw a cricket clutch the

06:23:06.060 --> 06:23:08.099
book to her chest and shout his name.

06:23:08.159 --> 06:23:12.000
He saw sundew pummel the librarian hard

06:23:12.000 --> 06:23:13.979
enough to knock the hive wing out of the

06:23:13.979 --> 06:23:14.099
air.

06:23:14.159 --> 06:23:17.819
He saw Sundew grab Cricket's arm and pull

06:23:17.819 --> 06:23:18.180
her away.

06:23:18.240 --> 06:23:21.419
And he saw Cricket's last look back.

06:23:21.479 --> 06:23:24.299
And he saw their tails disappearing away

06:23:24.299 --> 06:23:25.619
up the skylight.

06:23:25.680 --> 06:23:30.240
And then, all he could see was orange and

06:23:30.240 --> 06:23:33.779
yellow and black and red, as the talons

06:23:33.779 --> 06:23:34.740
closed around him.

06:23:34.799 --> 06:23:38.159
And the queen had him in her grasp at

06:23:38.159 --> 06:23:38.459
last.

06:23:38.520 --> 06:23:43.200
Part three.

06:23:43.319 --> 06:23:45.959
Metamorphosis.

06:23:46.020 --> 06:23:49.020
Chapter 22.

06:23:49.259 --> 06:23:52.740
Blue was dragged roughly through the hive

06:23:52.740 --> 06:23:53.159
tunnels.

06:23:53.220 --> 06:23:56.639
The Queen had dispatched 5 dragons to

06:23:56.639 --> 06:23:59.459
take him away, which was 4 too many for a

06:23:59.459 --> 06:24:00.779
dragon as harmless as blue.

06:24:00.840 --> 06:24:03.959
It kept stepping on one another's toes

06:24:03.959 --> 06:24:07.259
and growling, and bumping wings, and all

06:24:07.259 --> 06:24:09.240
trying to hold onto his elbows at once

06:24:09.240 --> 06:24:11.759
which he definitely did not have enough

06:24:11.759 --> 06:24:13.020
elbows for them to do.

06:24:13.080 --> 06:24:16.020
Their eyes were their own again.

06:24:16.080 --> 06:24:18.779
So the queen had apparently decided she

06:24:18.779 --> 06:24:20.520
didn't need to be concerned about blue

06:24:20.520 --> 06:24:23.580
anymore, which meant all the rest of her

06:24:23.580 --> 06:24:26.340
brainwashed subjects were off hunting for

06:24:26.340 --> 06:24:27.299
cricket and sundew.

06:24:27.419 --> 06:24:29.040
Did they get away?

06:24:29.099 --> 06:24:30.779
Are they all right?

06:24:30.840 --> 06:24:34.680
He worried and worried about this, as he

06:24:34.680 --> 06:24:36.240
was shoved between blustering hive

06:24:36.240 --> 06:24:36.659
wings.

06:24:36.720 --> 06:24:38.700
They were descending through the levels

06:24:38.700 --> 06:24:40.860
but to where, Blue had no idea.

06:24:40.919 --> 06:24:43.860
He kept expecting the queen herself to

06:24:43.860 --> 06:24:44.159
appear.

06:24:44.220 --> 06:24:47.159
He jumped each time they turned on to a

06:24:47.159 --> 06:24:48.900
level with black and yellow stripes.

06:24:48.959 --> 06:24:51.599
They reached the bottom level with no

06:24:51.599 --> 06:24:52.319
sign of her, though.

06:24:52.439 --> 06:24:54.779
The guards pushed him out into the

06:24:54.779 --> 06:24:56.639
streets of warehouses he'd seen on the

06:24:56.639 --> 06:24:57.659
way in.

06:24:57.720 --> 06:25:00.119
One flicked her wings at him, and he

06:25:00.119 --> 06:25:02.220
realized the tips were sharp little

06:25:02.220 --> 06:25:05.759
stingers, probably venomous, another kept

06:25:05.759 --> 06:25:08.819
baring his fangs, so those could probably

06:25:08.819 --> 06:25:10.919
kill him with just a scratch too.

06:25:10.979 --> 06:25:13.500
Where are they taking me?

06:25:13.560 --> 06:25:16.740
Blue wondered, staring at the blank walls

06:25:16.740 --> 06:25:17.819
as they marched past.

06:25:17.880 --> 06:25:20.459
How am I going to be punished?

06:25:20.459 --> 06:25:23.580
He remembered the tortured faces on

06:25:23.580 --> 06:25:25.919
misbehavior's way, and shivered.

06:25:25.979 --> 06:25:29.880
This feeling, of being in trouble, of

06:25:29.880 --> 06:25:32.400
having done something wrong, of knowing

06:25:32.400 --> 06:25:34.200
so many dragons were angry at you.

06:25:34.259 --> 06:25:37.500
This was everything he'd tried to avoid

06:25:37.500 --> 06:25:38.220
his whole life.

06:25:38.279 --> 06:25:40.439
He hated it.

06:25:40.500 --> 06:25:43.799
He wanted to go back to his desk, and get

06:25:43.799 --> 06:25:46.020
all the answers right on the quiz, and

06:25:46.020 --> 06:25:49.139
have the teacher smile and say, nice work

06:25:49.139 --> 06:25:49.439
Blue.

06:25:49.560 --> 06:25:52.979
He wanted to dig out his good citizenship

06:25:52.979 --> 06:25:55.860
award and show it to these hive wings to

06:25:55.860 --> 06:25:58.380
prove he wasn't as bad a dragon as they

06:25:58.380 --> 06:25:59.099
thought he was.

06:25:59.159 --> 06:26:00.959
But...

06:26:00.959 --> 06:26:02.639
I'm not.

06:26:02.700 --> 06:26:06.419
I mean, I've done all the things they

06:26:06.419 --> 06:26:07.020
think I have.

06:26:07.080 --> 06:26:09.299
But that doesn't make me bad.

06:26:09.360 --> 06:26:13.020
He clung to that thought like it was a

06:26:13.020 --> 06:26:15.119
harness, and someone was lifting him

06:26:15.119 --> 06:26:15.599
through the sky.

06:26:15.659 --> 06:26:20.700
Yes, I broke hive wing rules, but I had

06:26:20.700 --> 06:26:21.479
good reasons too.

06:26:21.540 --> 06:26:23.759
I'm not trying to hurt anyone.

06:26:23.819 --> 06:26:26.759
I just wanted to find my sister and set

06:26:26.759 --> 06:26:27.180
her free.

06:26:27.240 --> 06:26:31.680
Queen Wasp didn't have to be so secretive

06:26:31.680 --> 06:26:34.080
and menacing and terrifying in the 1st

06:26:34.080 --> 06:26:34.259
place.

06:26:34.319 --> 06:26:38.159
The hive wing stopped suddenly in front

06:26:38.159 --> 06:26:40.439
of a blocky building that looked exactly

06:26:40.439 --> 06:26:41.639
the same as all the others.

06:26:41.700 --> 06:26:44.520
The only difference was a carving on the

06:26:44.520 --> 06:26:45.119
gray door.

06:26:45.180 --> 06:26:47.580
This time of a small lantern.

06:26:47.639 --> 06:26:50.159
Little sparks coming off it to indicate

06:26:50.159 --> 06:26:50.880
it was glowing.

06:26:50.939 --> 06:26:54.479
Blue suddenly had a guess about where he

06:26:54.479 --> 06:26:54.840
was going.

06:26:54.900 --> 06:26:58.560
One of the hive wings pounded on the door

06:26:58.560 --> 06:27:00.060
in a series of knocks.

06:27:00.119 --> 06:27:03.299
Three quick, 4 slow, too quick.

06:27:03.360 --> 06:27:06.479
After a moment, it was flung open

06:27:06.479 --> 06:27:09.900
revealing a wizened, mostly orange dragon

06:27:09.900 --> 06:27:12.240
with black patches here and there.

06:27:12.299 --> 06:27:16.020
He gestured for them to come inside and

06:27:16.020 --> 06:27:17.279
slammed the door behind them.

06:27:17.340 --> 06:27:20.520
Shapes loomed around them in the dim

06:27:20.520 --> 06:27:21.060
interior.

06:27:21.119 --> 06:27:24.479
Giant crates as far as blue could tell

06:27:24.479 --> 06:27:25.860
stacked up to the ceiling.

06:27:25.919 --> 06:27:30.180
They maneuvered between these, left, right

06:27:30.180 --> 06:27:31.020
right?

06:27:31.139 --> 06:27:33.779
left again, until Blue lost track.

06:27:33.840 --> 06:27:36.180
But he thought they were about in the

06:27:36.180 --> 06:27:38.459
center of the warehouse when they reached

06:27:38.459 --> 06:27:41.759
a wide open, well lit space, surrounded

06:27:41.759 --> 06:27:43.680
by a circle of watchful hive wing

06:27:43.680 --> 06:27:43.979
guards.

06:27:44.040 --> 06:27:47.520
At first, Blue thought they were staring

06:27:47.520 --> 06:27:50.819
into empty space, or perhaps at one

06:27:50.819 --> 06:27:51.779
another across the way.

06:27:51.840 --> 06:27:55.020
It wasn't until he got closer that he

06:27:55.020 --> 06:27:57.000
realized they were looking down.

06:27:57.060 --> 06:28:00.119
Down through an enormous sheet of glass

06:28:00.119 --> 06:28:02.220
at a stone cavern below the floor.

06:28:02.279 --> 06:28:04.979
That was also where all the light was

06:28:04.979 --> 06:28:05.819
coming from.

06:28:05.880 --> 06:28:08.639
The dragon from the door shoved him past

06:28:08.639 --> 06:28:10.500
the guards before Blue could take a close

06:28:10.500 --> 06:28:10.799
look.

06:28:10.860 --> 06:28:14.040
But he caught a glimpse of cauldrons that

06:28:14.040 --> 06:28:16.740
seemed to be full of molten gold, and

06:28:16.740 --> 06:28:18.060
dragons moving between them.

06:28:18.119 --> 06:28:22.259
Shortly beyond the circle of guards, the

06:28:22.259 --> 06:28:25.020
old dragon shoved aside a crate, and

06:28:25.020 --> 06:28:26.819
heaved open a trap door underneath

06:28:26.819 --> 06:28:29.819
revealing a set of stairs descending into

06:28:29.819 --> 06:28:30.180
the earth.

06:28:30.299 --> 06:28:34.319
He started down, and Blue's guards nudged

06:28:34.319 --> 06:28:34.979
him into following.

06:28:35.040 --> 06:28:38.819
Lamps punctuated the turns of the

06:28:38.819 --> 06:28:41.279
stairwell, but they seemed unnecessary.

06:28:41.340 --> 06:28:43.979
The glow from the light at the bottom of

06:28:43.979 --> 06:28:46.200
the stairs could have illuminated a

06:28:46.200 --> 06:28:48.119
stairwell 3 times as long.

06:28:48.180 --> 06:28:51.360
Blue had to shield his eyes and blink

06:28:51.360 --> 06:28:53.520
hard for a moment when they reached the

06:28:53.520 --> 06:28:53.759
bottom.

06:28:53.880 --> 06:28:57.119
His head ached, as though he'd walked

06:28:57.119 --> 06:28:58.020
right up to the sun.

06:28:58.080 --> 06:29:00.180
What's this?

06:29:00.299 --> 06:29:03.599
A gruff voice demanded, while Blue's eyes

06:29:03.599 --> 06:29:04.439
were still adjusting.

06:29:04.500 --> 06:29:07.259
The flame silk everyone's been looking

06:29:07.259 --> 06:29:08.759
for, came the answer.

06:29:08.819 --> 06:29:10.799
Can be.

06:29:10.860 --> 06:29:12.659
Someone poked his shoulder.

06:29:12.720 --> 06:29:14.099
Wrong color.

06:29:14.220 --> 06:29:16.799
Ah, did his scales just fall off?

06:29:16.860 --> 06:29:19.799
It's paint or something?

06:29:19.860 --> 06:29:21.599
said another dragon.

06:29:21.659 --> 06:29:24.240
She started scraping at his scales with

06:29:24.240 --> 06:29:24.959
her claws.

06:29:25.020 --> 06:29:27.000
Yeesh!

06:29:27.060 --> 06:29:28.740
Look, it comes off.

06:29:28.799 --> 06:29:30.540
That just scrubber.

06:29:30.599 --> 06:29:35.400
Wait, this little scrap is the dragon

06:29:35.400 --> 06:29:37.619
we've been hunting across the Savannah?

06:29:37.619 --> 06:29:39.360
Someone else chimed in.

06:29:39.419 --> 06:29:41.639
He's not a flame silk?

06:29:41.880 --> 06:29:44.040
He hasn't even got wings or silk yet.

06:29:44.099 --> 06:29:48.000
We knew that idiot, said the 1st voice.

06:29:48.060 --> 06:29:51.360
He's just probably a flame silk.

06:29:51.419 --> 06:29:53.639
We have to keep an eye on him in case he

06:29:53.639 --> 06:29:53.880
is.

06:29:53.939 --> 06:29:56.759
Oh, boring.

06:29:56.819 --> 06:29:58.799
When does metamorphosis?

06:29:58.860 --> 06:30:00.479
Dunno.

06:30:00.540 --> 06:30:02.040
Soon I reckon.

06:30:02.099 --> 06:30:05.040
Blue's heart gave a nervous jump.

06:30:05.099 --> 06:30:06.659
It was soon.

06:30:06.720 --> 06:30:08.819
Really, really soon.

06:30:08.880 --> 06:30:11.220
He kept forgetting to worry about it.

06:30:11.279 --> 06:30:14.340
His was supposed to start right after

06:30:14.340 --> 06:30:15.360
Luna's ended.

06:30:15.419 --> 06:30:18.419
Would he have to spin his cocoon here?

06:30:18.479 --> 06:30:22.919
Far away from his mother, his hive, and

06:30:22.919 --> 06:30:25.139
the cocoon where he'd always expected to

06:30:25.139 --> 06:30:25.740
transform.

06:30:25.860 --> 06:30:28.680
He felt his wrist gingerly.

06:30:28.740 --> 06:30:30.599
They seemed normal.

06:30:30.659 --> 06:30:33.959
No pain, no burning feelings.

06:30:34.020 --> 06:30:36.659
What if he went through his metamorphosis

06:30:36.659 --> 06:30:39.419
and wasn't a flame silk?

06:30:39.479 --> 06:30:41.639
What would the queen do with him then?

06:30:41.700 --> 06:30:45.119
Sending him back home to burn it and

06:30:45.119 --> 06:30:47.459
Silverspot didn't seem like the most

06:30:47.459 --> 06:30:48.840
likely option somehow.

06:30:48.900 --> 06:30:52.259
Someone arrived with scrubbing brushes

06:30:52.259 --> 06:30:54.360
and briskly scoured the paint off his

06:30:54.360 --> 06:30:54.900
scales.

06:30:54.959 --> 06:30:56.939
He stood still and didn't struggle.

06:30:57.060 --> 06:30:59.400
There wasn't much point in being a

06:30:59.400 --> 06:31:00.720
different color now after all.

06:31:00.779 --> 06:31:04.680
Besides, his eyes were finally adjusting

06:31:04.680 --> 06:31:07.560
to the light, and he was transfixed by

06:31:07.560 --> 06:31:08.700
his new surroundings.

06:31:08.759 --> 06:31:11.220
They were standing on a ledge at the

06:31:11.220 --> 06:31:13.500
bottom of the stairs, looking out over

06:31:13.500 --> 06:31:15.360
the cave he'd glimpsed from above.

06:31:15.419 --> 06:31:19.020
If he looked up, he could see the green

06:31:19.020 --> 06:31:21.180
yellow, orange glow of the eyes watching

06:31:21.180 --> 06:31:22.259
through the glass ceiling.

06:31:22.380 --> 06:31:25.740
More hive wing guards were stationed down

06:31:25.740 --> 06:31:28.799
here, peering into the cauldrons, and

06:31:28.799 --> 06:31:30.900
occasionally poking the working silk

06:31:30.900 --> 06:31:32.819
wings with their tails or spears.

06:31:33.180 --> 06:31:35.639
Several of those silk wings were ordinary

06:31:35.639 --> 06:31:39.060
dragons, doing ordinary work, transporting

06:31:39.060 --> 06:31:42.419
cargo, carrying food and water, cleaning

06:31:42.419 --> 06:31:46.740
putting out fires, but the rest, the rest

06:31:46.740 --> 06:31:48.000
were flame silks.

06:31:48.060 --> 06:31:51.000
Blue counted 9 at 1st glance.

06:31:51.060 --> 06:31:53.580
They were scattered across the cavern

06:31:53.580 --> 06:31:56.520
each on his or her own rocky perch.

06:31:56.580 --> 06:31:58.380
Four of them were asleep.

06:31:58.439 --> 06:31:59.939
Two were eating.

06:32:00.119 --> 06:32:02.520
The other 3 had their wrists extended.

06:32:02.580 --> 06:32:06.060
Fiery silk threads spilling out into the

06:32:06.060 --> 06:32:08.340
massive stone cauldrons set below them.

06:32:08.459 --> 06:32:11.939
He stared at them, trying to guess which

06:32:11.939 --> 06:32:12.779
one was his father.

06:32:12.900 --> 06:32:16.439
The large, bored one who looked like he

06:32:16.439 --> 06:32:18.599
might fall asleep and topple into his own

06:32:18.599 --> 06:32:19.439
silk fire.

06:32:19.560 --> 06:32:23.279
The lime striped one, who was nibbling a

06:32:23.279 --> 06:32:24.840
persimmon as though it had greatly

06:32:24.840 --> 06:32:25.500
offended him.

06:32:25.560 --> 06:32:27.959
But he decided to eat it anyway.

06:32:28.020 --> 06:32:31.619
The one with pale pink wings whose talons

06:32:31.619 --> 06:32:33.240
twitched constantly in his sleep.

06:32:33.299 --> 06:32:37.799
And then, at last, he saw what he most

06:32:37.799 --> 06:32:38.700
wanted to see.

06:32:38.759 --> 06:32:43.139
An incandescent gold cocoon, tucked in

06:32:43.139 --> 06:32:45.060
its own hollow on the far side of the

06:32:45.060 --> 06:32:46.139
cave.

06:32:46.200 --> 06:32:47.700
Luna.

06:32:47.759 --> 06:32:51.659
He took a step toward her, hesitated, and

06:32:51.659 --> 06:32:52.619
looked back at the guards.

06:32:52.680 --> 06:32:55.500
The scrubbing brushes had been carted

06:32:55.500 --> 06:32:55.740
away.

06:32:55.799 --> 06:32:58.680
His original escorts had gone back up the

06:32:58.680 --> 06:33:01.259
stairs, leaving the one guard from the

06:33:01.259 --> 06:33:03.599
door, and the 3 who'd come to investigate

06:33:03.599 --> 06:33:04.139
his arrival.

06:33:04.200 --> 06:33:07.619
These 4 were all leaning on their spears

06:33:07.619 --> 06:33:10.259
or chewing on strips of dried gazelle

06:33:10.259 --> 06:33:11.400
chatting to one another.

06:33:11.459 --> 06:33:14.279
One of them noticed his glance.

06:33:14.340 --> 06:33:17.040
She grinned at him with all her teeth.

06:33:17.099 --> 06:33:19.560
Go ahead, she said.

06:33:19.619 --> 06:33:21.119
Get used to the place.

06:33:21.180 --> 06:33:22.979
I gather you're going to be here for a

06:33:22.979 --> 06:33:23.220
while.

06:33:23.279 --> 06:33:25.560
The others chuckled.

06:33:25.619 --> 06:33:27.720
Although Blue didn't think it was really

06:33:27.720 --> 06:33:29.939
the most clever menacing comment she

06:33:29.939 --> 06:33:30.659
could have come up with.

06:33:30.720 --> 06:33:34.680
He took another few steps away, but they

06:33:34.680 --> 06:33:36.360
all went back to their conversation and

06:33:36.360 --> 06:33:36.900
ignored him.

06:33:36.959 --> 06:33:40.380
I guess I really can walk around.

06:33:40.439 --> 06:33:44.580
He'd expected a cage, or a paralyzing

06:33:44.580 --> 06:33:47.459
nerve toxin, or some kind of beating

06:33:47.459 --> 06:33:47.880
perhaps.

06:33:47.939 --> 06:33:51.060
But maybe this was the queen's way of

06:33:51.060 --> 06:33:53.340
letting him know how unimportant he was.

06:33:53.400 --> 06:33:55.919
Or how trapped.

06:33:55.979 --> 06:33:59.159
He could wander as far as he liked

06:33:59.159 --> 06:34:01.979
because there was nowhere to go, and no

06:34:01.979 --> 06:34:02.580
way out.

06:34:02.580 --> 06:34:05.819
Blue clambered down from the ledge

06:34:05.819 --> 06:34:08.700
hopping from rocky foothold to craggy

06:34:08.700 --> 06:34:10.919
stalacmite, until he reached the same

06:34:10.919 --> 06:34:13.020
level of the cavern as Luna's cocoon.

06:34:13.080 --> 06:34:16.200
Behind him, he heard the hive wing guards

06:34:16.200 --> 06:34:18.360
laughing, and he wondered if they were

06:34:18.360 --> 06:34:19.680
mocking his winglessness.

06:34:19.740 --> 06:34:23.459
Well, I won't be wingless much longer.

06:34:23.520 --> 06:34:28.560
His biggest fear, his metamorphosis, was

06:34:28.560 --> 06:34:29.819
only days away.

06:34:29.880 --> 06:34:32.220
It didn't seem fair that he'd have to

06:34:32.220 --> 06:34:32.939
deal with that too.

06:34:33.000 --> 06:34:34.799
In the middle of everything else

06:34:34.799 --> 06:34:35.459
terrifying.

06:34:35.520 --> 06:34:39.360
His route to the cocoon led him past the

06:34:39.360 --> 06:34:42.180
bored looking flame silk, who glanced up

06:34:42.180 --> 06:34:43.860
with a spark of interest in his eyes.

06:34:43.919 --> 06:34:48.779
Hey, said the flame silk, in a lazy but

06:34:48.779 --> 06:34:51.180
commanding voice, who are you?

06:34:51.240 --> 06:34:53.340
Blue hesitated.

06:34:53.400 --> 06:34:55.979
He didn't want to alienate anyone who

06:34:55.979 --> 06:34:58.799
might be a friend down here, and for all

06:34:58.799 --> 06:35:01.139
he knew, this could be Admiral.

06:35:01.200 --> 06:35:04.080
I'm Blue, he said.

06:35:04.139 --> 06:35:06.540
My sister's in that cocoon over there.

06:35:06.599 --> 06:35:10.740
Oh, said the other dragon.

06:35:10.799 --> 06:35:13.439
He shook one of his wrists vigorously

06:35:13.439 --> 06:35:16.500
watched the silk spool for a moment, then

06:35:16.500 --> 06:35:17.819
turned his gaze back to blue.

06:35:17.939 --> 06:35:19.740
Right.

06:35:19.799 --> 06:35:21.000
The new blood.

06:35:21.060 --> 06:35:23.759
Did you know we were coming?

06:35:23.819 --> 06:35:24.840
Blue asked.

06:35:24.900 --> 06:35:27.720
Some of us hoped, he answered.

06:35:27.779 --> 06:35:30.000
Ad's been counting the days.

06:35:30.119 --> 06:35:33.840
He nodded over at Luna's cocoon, and Blue

06:35:33.840 --> 06:35:36.000
finally noticed that there was a dragon

06:35:36.000 --> 06:35:36.900
sitting next to it.

06:35:36.959 --> 06:35:41.040
Add Admiral.

06:35:41.099 --> 06:35:44.580
Bloom moved forward, studying his

06:35:44.580 --> 06:35:44.819
father.

06:35:44.880 --> 06:35:48.240
Admiral was a shimmering blue green

06:35:48.240 --> 06:35:51.180
somewhere between Blue's bright morpho

06:35:51.180 --> 06:35:53.819
butterfly blue, and Luna's elegant

06:35:53.819 --> 06:35:54.840
caterpillar color.

06:35:54.900 --> 06:35:57.659
He had darker purple streaks along his

06:35:57.659 --> 06:36:00.180
wings, and matching spots of white on

06:36:00.180 --> 06:36:00.599
each one.

06:36:00.659 --> 06:36:04.259
His eyes were brown, with a faint gold

06:36:04.259 --> 06:36:07.200
tinged to them, and he traced one claw

06:36:07.200 --> 06:36:10.139
around and around in an infinity loop on

06:36:10.139 --> 06:36:12.720
the ground as he watched Luna's cocoon.

06:36:12.779 --> 06:36:16.200
For a long moment he didn't look up.

06:36:16.259 --> 06:36:18.959
Even when Blue stopped right across the

06:36:18.959 --> 06:36:22.439
cocoon from him, but at last, Admiral

06:36:22.439 --> 06:36:26.040
raised his head and saw his son, his eyes

06:36:26.040 --> 06:36:26.700
lit up.

06:36:26.759 --> 06:36:30.180
You're the other one, he said.

06:36:30.240 --> 06:36:31.259
You're early.

06:36:31.319 --> 06:36:35.220
Oh, yes, Blue said.

06:36:35.279 --> 06:36:37.740
He gestured vaguely the guards on the

06:36:37.740 --> 06:36:38.639
entrance ledge.

06:36:38.700 --> 06:36:43.439
I was, uh, well, captured, I guess.

06:36:43.500 --> 06:36:46.139
I'm so glad you're here.

06:36:46.200 --> 06:36:49.740
Admiral said warmly, I'm your father.

06:36:49.799 --> 06:36:51.180
I'm Admiral.

06:36:51.299 --> 06:36:54.000
I know, Blue said.

06:36:54.119 --> 06:36:55.740
My name's Blue.

06:36:55.799 --> 06:36:58.560
Wait, you're glad we're here.

06:36:58.619 --> 06:37:02.220
Glad that Luna and I are trapped down

06:37:02.220 --> 06:37:02.459
here.

06:37:02.520 --> 06:37:03.659
Just like you.

06:37:03.779 --> 06:37:06.959
We have such an important job.

06:37:07.080 --> 06:37:10.020
Admiral said, rubbing his wrists.

06:37:10.080 --> 06:37:11.520
So important.

06:37:11.580 --> 06:37:13.319
When do you think she'll wake up?

06:37:13.380 --> 06:37:16.200
Blue calculated backward.

06:37:16.319 --> 06:37:19.380
Not tomorrow night, the night after that

06:37:19.380 --> 06:37:20.340
he said.

06:37:20.400 --> 06:37:22.740
That would be 5 days from when she went

06:37:22.740 --> 06:37:22.919
in.

06:37:22.979 --> 06:37:25.200
Admiral nodded.

06:37:25.259 --> 06:37:28.439
I can't believe one of mine is a flame

06:37:28.439 --> 06:37:30.060
silk, he said.

06:37:30.119 --> 06:37:31.799
And maybe both.

06:37:31.860 --> 06:37:35.459
Club Tell was taken out to have eggs a

06:37:35.459 --> 06:37:38.099
year before me, but neither of his had

06:37:38.099 --> 06:37:39.419
any flame whatsoever.

06:37:39.479 --> 06:37:42.360
His chest swelled with pride.

06:37:42.419 --> 06:37:46.619
But Blue looked around at the cavern

06:37:46.619 --> 06:37:46.979
again.

06:37:47.040 --> 06:37:48.360
Isn't it?

06:37:48.479 --> 06:37:51.840
Sorry, but isn't it kind of terrible?

06:37:51.900 --> 06:37:53.700
Being a flame silk.

06:37:53.759 --> 06:37:55.080
Terrible.

06:37:55.139 --> 06:37:58.500
Gosh, no, said Admiral.

06:37:58.560 --> 06:38:01.200
I mean, I'd make some changes.

06:38:01.259 --> 06:38:02.520
I'm working on that.

06:38:02.580 --> 06:38:05.099
Working on what?

06:38:05.159 --> 06:38:06.479
Blue asked.

06:38:06.540 --> 06:38:08.880
Was his father also part of his secret

06:38:08.880 --> 06:38:09.479
resistance?

06:38:09.599 --> 06:38:13.259
Admiral waved at a rocky nest nearby

06:38:13.259 --> 06:38:16.200
where piles of papers were neatly stacked

06:38:16.200 --> 06:38:17.759
along the stone shelves around it.

06:38:17.880 --> 06:38:21.119
Each stack tied with a pale gold thread.

06:38:21.180 --> 06:38:23.099
Changing the system.

06:38:23.159 --> 06:38:25.439
He said, solving problems.

06:38:25.500 --> 06:38:29.040
With papers.

06:38:29.099 --> 06:38:30.900
Blue squinted at them.

06:38:30.959 --> 06:38:32.700
Their letters.

06:38:32.759 --> 06:38:36.659
Admiral said patiently, my copies of them

06:38:36.659 --> 06:38:36.959
obviously.

06:38:37.020 --> 06:38:40.080
I write one to the queen every 7 days

06:38:40.080 --> 06:38:43.020
outlining the current problems I see, and

06:38:43.020 --> 06:38:44.639
offering proposals for fixing them.

06:38:44.700 --> 06:38:48.419
Oh, Blue said, impressed.

06:38:48.479 --> 06:38:49.860
That was a lot of letters.

06:38:49.979 --> 06:38:53.639
So she writes back, or she comes to visit

06:38:53.639 --> 06:38:53.939
you?

06:38:54.000 --> 06:38:58.919
Well, neither, said Admiral, but she's

06:38:58.919 --> 06:38:59.340
very busy.

06:38:59.400 --> 06:39:01.200
Lots of hives to run.

06:39:01.319 --> 06:39:04.680
Two tribes to manage, leaf wings to guard

06:39:04.680 --> 06:39:07.439
against, the dip in flame silk production

06:39:07.439 --> 06:39:10.200
is just one of her many problems, which

06:39:10.200 --> 06:39:11.580
I'm going to help solve.

06:39:11.639 --> 06:39:15.599
There's a flame silk shortage, Blue

06:39:15.599 --> 06:39:16.020
said.

06:39:16.080 --> 06:39:20.340
No, said Admiral unconvincingly.

06:39:20.400 --> 06:39:23.040
And it's not a problem, because we're

06:39:23.040 --> 06:39:24.779
solving it, with her help.

06:39:24.900 --> 06:39:28.740
He added, nodding at Luna's cocoon, and

06:39:28.740 --> 06:39:29.520
hopefully yours.

06:39:29.580 --> 06:39:32.520
Blue stared at him in alarm.

06:39:32.580 --> 06:39:34.740
Was this your idea?

06:39:34.740 --> 06:39:38.759
he asked. fathering potential flame silks

06:39:38.759 --> 06:39:40.740
so more dragons could be trapped in this

06:39:40.740 --> 06:39:41.040
cave.

06:39:41.099 --> 06:39:45.419
Well, no, his father admitted.

06:39:45.479 --> 06:39:47.220
The queen came up with that.

06:39:47.279 --> 06:39:48.540
Very clever.

06:39:48.599 --> 06:39:51.599
And works out well for me because, A

06:39:51.599 --> 06:39:54.659
better company, and B, more signatures

06:39:54.659 --> 06:39:55.619
for my petitions.

06:39:55.680 --> 06:39:57.540
Petitions.

06:39:57.599 --> 06:39:58.919
Blue echoed.

06:39:58.979 --> 06:40:03.000
My suggestion was longer rest cycles

06:40:03.000 --> 06:40:05.340
between production and more citrus in our

06:40:05.340 --> 06:40:06.959
diet, which we got.

06:40:07.080 --> 06:40:10.319
The citrus, I mean, tangerines for

06:40:10.319 --> 06:40:11.700
everyone with every meal.

06:40:11.759 --> 06:40:14.520
Every meal.

06:40:14.580 --> 06:40:17.279
Really makes you wish for a lemon or a

06:40:17.279 --> 06:40:18.240
banana now and then.

06:40:18.299 --> 06:40:19.740
Good for us, though.

06:40:19.799 --> 06:40:22.139
She vetoed the longer rest cycles.

06:40:22.200 --> 06:40:23.099
That's all right.

06:40:23.159 --> 06:40:26.580
So, what else have you changed?

06:40:26.639 --> 06:40:27.779
Blue asked.

06:40:27.840 --> 06:40:30.000
Oh, lots of things.

06:40:30.060 --> 06:40:32.700
Admiral said with a modest shrug.

06:40:32.759 --> 06:40:35.400
I started almost as soon as I got here.

06:40:35.520 --> 06:40:39.180
Once I realized there was a system and a

06:40:39.180 --> 06:40:41.400
way to accomplish real change within that

06:40:41.400 --> 06:40:41.939
system.

06:40:41.939 --> 06:40:43.860
Yeah.

06:40:43.919 --> 06:40:45.840
Blue was intrigued.

06:40:45.900 --> 06:40:48.180
Doing things inside the rules.

06:40:48.240 --> 06:40:50.459
That sounded like something he could

06:40:50.459 --> 06:40:52.860
handle a bit better than Swordtail and

06:40:52.860 --> 06:40:54.060
Luna's revolution.

06:40:54.119 --> 06:40:56.400
Maybe his father could teach him how to

06:40:56.400 --> 06:40:56.700
do it.

06:40:56.759 --> 06:41:00.180
Maybe there was a way to be a good dragon

06:41:00.180 --> 06:41:02.340
stay out of trouble, and still make

06:41:02.340 --> 06:41:02.880
things better.

06:41:02.939 --> 06:41:07.439
Although, tangerines were not quite the

06:41:07.439 --> 06:41:09.540
epic change Blue wanted to see in the

06:41:09.540 --> 06:41:09.720
world.

06:41:09.840 --> 06:41:13.080
Can I read some of your letters?

06:41:13.139 --> 06:41:14.340
Blue asked.

06:41:14.400 --> 06:41:16.020
Of course.

06:41:16.080 --> 06:41:19.740
Admiral leaped excitedly to his feet, and

06:41:19.740 --> 06:41:21.180
bounded over to his alcove.

06:41:21.299 --> 06:41:23.880
He came back with an armful of papers and

06:41:23.880 --> 06:41:25.259
laid them out in front of Blue.

06:41:25.319 --> 06:41:26.639
Wait.

06:41:26.700 --> 06:41:29.040
Is this flame silk?

06:41:29.159 --> 06:41:30.299
Blue asked.

06:41:30.360 --> 06:41:32.819
Touching the thread that tied one stack

06:41:32.819 --> 06:41:33.180
together?

06:41:33.240 --> 06:41:36.060
He squinted at it, puzzled.

06:41:36.119 --> 06:41:37.860
Why isn't it setting the letters on

06:41:37.860 --> 06:41:38.159
fire?

06:41:38.220 --> 06:41:40.200
Admiral laughed.

06:41:40.259 --> 06:41:42.959
This is great, he said.

06:41:43.020 --> 06:41:44.700
I feel like such a dad.

06:41:44.759 --> 06:41:46.680
I get to teach you so much.

06:41:46.740 --> 06:41:49.619
There are different kinds of flame silk

06:41:49.619 --> 06:41:49.919
buddy.

06:41:49.979 --> 06:41:52.560
It wouldn't be much good to us if it only

06:41:52.560 --> 06:41:53.939
burned everything in sight.

06:41:54.060 --> 06:41:57.180
We need the kind for building webs too.

06:41:57.299 --> 06:41:59.040
Something we can sleep on.

06:41:59.099 --> 06:42:01.259
Stickier silk for climbing with.

06:42:01.319 --> 06:42:03.659
We can choose which kind we produce.

06:42:03.720 --> 06:42:07.860
He tipped his wrists up, flexed his claws

06:42:07.860 --> 06:42:10.319
and glanced at the nearest guard, who

06:42:10.319 --> 06:42:11.700
wasn't paying any attention to them.

06:42:11.759 --> 06:42:15.000
Um, I'll show you later.

06:42:15.060 --> 06:42:17.340
Not a good idea to waste any silk, you

06:42:17.340 --> 06:42:17.520
know?

06:42:17.580 --> 06:42:21.360
Blue flipped through the letters, thinking

06:42:21.360 --> 06:42:22.500
about this new information.

06:42:22.619 --> 06:42:25.259
It was quite a relief to hear that he

06:42:25.259 --> 06:42:27.000
wouldn't accidentally set the world on

06:42:27.000 --> 06:42:28.979
fire every time he used his silk.

06:42:29.099 --> 06:42:32.040
Maybe going through metamorphosis with

06:42:32.040 --> 06:42:34.979
his flame silk parent nearby actually was

06:42:34.979 --> 06:42:35.400
a good idea.

06:42:35.459 --> 06:42:39.599
Maybe the queen was trying to help me and

06:42:39.599 --> 06:42:40.860
Luna by bringing us here.

06:42:40.919 --> 06:42:43.080
And yet.

06:42:43.319 --> 06:42:45.599
He glanced around at the cavern.

06:42:45.659 --> 06:42:48.360
The flame silk dragons looked fine.

06:42:48.419 --> 06:42:50.459
They didn't seem miserable.

06:42:50.580 --> 06:42:53.639
But if they were so important and the

06:42:53.639 --> 06:42:56.220
queen was willing to listen to them, why

06:42:56.220 --> 06:42:57.659
were they kept imprisoned in this

06:42:57.659 --> 06:42:58.080
cavern?

06:42:58.139 --> 06:43:00.599
Why were they such a big secret?

06:43:00.659 --> 06:43:03.240
At least from most other silk wings?

06:43:03.299 --> 06:43:06.180
Why weren't they allowed to choose this

06:43:06.180 --> 06:43:06.659
life?

06:43:06.659 --> 06:43:08.279
Or something else?

06:43:08.340 --> 06:43:11.520
Father, Blue said.

06:43:11.580 --> 06:43:14.520
Do any flame silks ever leave this

06:43:14.520 --> 06:43:14.819
place?

06:43:14.880 --> 06:43:18.659
Sure, Admiral said unexpectedly.

06:43:18.720 --> 06:43:21.659
I mean, I left, didn't I?

06:43:21.720 --> 06:43:23.220
Long enough to have you.

06:43:23.340 --> 06:43:26.939
Right, but how long was that for?

06:43:27.000 --> 06:43:28.259
Blue asked.

06:43:28.319 --> 06:43:31.380
Did you get to decide when and where you

06:43:31.380 --> 06:43:32.880
went or who you were with?

06:43:32.939 --> 06:43:38.159
Well, no, Admiral said, but it was a

06:43:38.159 --> 06:43:38.939
lovely visit.

06:43:39.000 --> 06:43:40.740
Cicada hive is so pretty.

06:43:40.860 --> 06:43:42.900
That mosaic garden.

06:43:42.959 --> 06:43:43.380
Wow.

06:43:43.439 --> 06:43:45.840
Have you gone anywhere else?

06:43:45.900 --> 06:43:47.220
Blue asked.

06:43:47.279 --> 06:43:48.840
How often do you leave?

06:43:48.900 --> 06:43:52.439
Um...

06:43:52.439 --> 06:43:55.439
Admiral scrunched up his snout, as though

06:43:55.439 --> 06:43:58.259
he was counting in his head, Blue leaned

06:43:58.259 --> 06:43:58.919
forward, hopefully.

06:43:58.979 --> 06:44:00.540
Right.

06:44:00.599 --> 06:44:04.740
That was it, actually, that one time.

06:44:04.799 --> 06:44:09.840
In your whole life, Blue asked, dismayed

06:44:09.840 --> 06:44:12.060
you've spent your whole life in this one

06:44:12.060 --> 06:44:12.599
cave.

06:44:12.659 --> 06:44:15.900
Oh no, said Admiral.

06:44:15.959 --> 06:44:17.939
I grew up in Hornet Hive.

06:44:18.000 --> 06:44:20.279
Didn't move here until my metamorphosis

06:44:20.279 --> 06:44:23.279
went into my cocoon there, woke up here

06:44:23.279 --> 06:44:26.639
quiet a surprise, really delightful once

06:44:26.639 --> 06:44:29.099
I realized how important we are, and what

06:44:29.099 --> 06:44:29.939
an honor this is.

06:44:30.060 --> 06:44:33.000
Blue regarded him skeptically.

06:44:33.060 --> 06:44:35.819
Haven't you ever asked the queen if you

06:44:35.819 --> 06:44:36.180
could leave?

06:44:36.240 --> 06:44:39.240
Sure, Admiral said.

06:44:39.299 --> 06:44:42.299
That stag on the end is vacation time

06:44:42.299 --> 06:44:45.900
requests, and field trip proposals, and

06:44:45.900 --> 06:44:48.479
some of my theories on how more flying

06:44:48.479 --> 06:44:50.099
might improve our silk production.

06:44:50.220 --> 06:44:52.680
Afraid I don't have any good evidence for

06:44:52.680 --> 06:44:53.099
that though.

06:44:53.159 --> 06:44:55.860
More of a wishful thinking kind of

06:44:55.860 --> 06:44:56.459
hypothesis.

06:44:56.520 --> 06:44:57.779
I realize that.

06:44:57.840 --> 06:45:00.180
Completely reasonable that she always

06:45:00.180 --> 06:45:00.720
says no.

06:45:00.779 --> 06:45:03.599
Blue picked up another letter.

06:45:03.659 --> 06:45:06.360
His father's handwriting was neat and

06:45:06.360 --> 06:45:07.259
very legible.

06:45:07.319 --> 06:45:08.759
His spelling was perfect.

06:45:08.819 --> 06:45:11.639
His sentences concise and convincing.

06:45:11.700 --> 06:45:15.119
This one was a politely worded outline of

06:45:15.119 --> 06:45:17.459
a proposal for a skylight, or anything

06:45:17.459 --> 06:45:20.099
like a window, suggesting that a little

06:45:20.099 --> 06:45:22.020
sun on their scales might also be

06:45:22.020 --> 06:45:23.639
beneficial for their silk output.

06:45:23.700 --> 06:45:26.759
There were several letters below it along

06:45:26.759 --> 06:45:27.360
the same lines.

06:45:27.419 --> 06:45:30.360
With modifications to the proposal to

06:45:30.360 --> 06:45:32.880
make it as cost effective, or easy to

06:45:32.880 --> 06:45:34.200
accomplish as possible.

06:45:34.259 --> 06:45:37.319
One even included a drawing of a sequence

06:45:37.319 --> 06:45:39.479
of mirrors that could bring the sunshine

06:45:39.479 --> 06:45:41.939
to them via a long path of reflections.

06:45:42.000 --> 06:45:46.020
Blue could clearly see, from looking at

06:45:46.020 --> 06:45:48.060
the cavern, that every one of these

06:45:48.060 --> 06:45:49.500
letters had been ignored.

06:45:49.560 --> 06:45:51.659
Who's the midget?

06:45:51.720 --> 06:45:54.599
One of the other flame silks, the one

06:45:54.599 --> 06:45:57.180
with green stripes shouted at Admiral.

06:45:57.240 --> 06:45:58.560
Is that your offspring?

06:45:58.619 --> 06:46:00.240
He's scrawny like you.

06:46:00.299 --> 06:46:02.400
Is he a vacuous earthworm too?

06:46:02.520 --> 06:46:04.740
Mind your own business.

06:46:04.860 --> 06:46:06.540
Admiral roared.

06:46:06.599 --> 06:46:09.119
He doesn't need to hear your toad sucking

06:46:09.119 --> 06:46:09.299
voice.

06:46:09.419 --> 06:46:13.319
Better than your millipedian claw waving

06:46:13.319 --> 06:46:15.360
folder all, the dragon yelled.

06:46:15.419 --> 06:46:17.880
Are you poisoning his ears with your

06:46:17.880 --> 06:46:18.959
stupid ideas already?

06:46:19.080 --> 06:46:21.840
Did you tell him the queen chews up all

06:46:21.840 --> 06:46:23.939
your letters and spits them out?

06:46:24.000 --> 06:46:26.159
Because they're the dumbest things she's

06:46:26.159 --> 06:46:26.520
ever read?

06:46:26.639 --> 06:46:28.680
That's not true.

06:46:28.740 --> 06:46:30.180
And it would help.

06:46:30.240 --> 06:46:33.419
If certain dragons weren't such trolls

06:46:33.419 --> 06:46:34.200
about everything.

06:46:34.319 --> 06:46:39.119
Admiral yelled back, as if anyone would

06:46:39.119 --> 06:46:42.540
ever believe that less, citrus might be

06:46:42.540 --> 06:46:42.900
helpful.

06:46:42.959 --> 06:46:45.840
I swear, he said to Blue.

06:46:45.900 --> 06:46:48.360
I think he sneaks over and reads my

06:46:48.360 --> 06:46:50.580
letters, just so he can write ones

06:46:50.580 --> 06:46:52.619
arguing for the exact opposite of

06:46:52.619 --> 06:46:53.520
anything I propose.

06:46:53.580 --> 06:46:55.979
Who is that?

06:46:56.099 --> 06:46:58.619
Blue asked, wide eyed.

06:46:58.680 --> 06:47:00.000
Why is he so mean?

06:47:00.060 --> 06:47:04.380
That's fritelery, Admiral growled.

06:47:04.439 --> 06:47:06.840
He just wants everyone to hate the world

06:47:06.840 --> 06:47:07.860
as much as he does.

06:47:07.919 --> 06:47:09.479
Don't talk to him.

06:47:09.540 --> 06:47:12.419
He made an effort to smile at Blue.

06:47:12.540 --> 06:47:13.560
See?

06:47:13.619 --> 06:47:15.720
This is why I'm glad you're here.

06:47:15.779 --> 06:47:18.299
It'll be nice to have someone new to talk

06:47:18.299 --> 06:47:18.540
to.

06:47:18.599 --> 06:47:21.659
Someone with a little perspective.

06:47:21.720 --> 06:47:24.060
Someone who knows how to look on the

06:47:24.060 --> 06:47:24.659
bright side.

06:47:24.779 --> 06:47:27.419
You do know how to look on the bright

06:47:27.419 --> 06:47:28.860
side, don't you?

06:47:28.919 --> 06:47:32.819
I guess I do, Blue said.

06:47:32.880 --> 06:47:35.279
Wasn't that what he'd spend his whole

06:47:35.279 --> 06:47:36.000
life doing?

06:47:36.060 --> 06:47:39.000
Finding a silver lining to any cloud

06:47:39.000 --> 06:47:41.700
convincing himself that there was nothing

06:47:41.700 --> 06:47:43.799
wrong with how silk wings were treated.

06:47:43.860 --> 06:47:47.639
Ignoring Luna's complaints, assuming that

06:47:47.639 --> 06:47:49.860
their safety was worth sacrificing a few

06:47:49.860 --> 06:47:50.400
freedoms.

06:47:50.520 --> 06:47:53.759
He looked down at the letters in his

06:47:53.759 --> 06:47:54.540
talons again.

06:47:54.599 --> 06:47:57.900
After all these years of trying to work

06:47:57.900 --> 06:48:00.659
with the Queen Wasp's rules, in Queen

06:48:00.659 --> 06:48:04.139
Wasp's Hive, under Queen Wasp's Control

06:48:04.139 --> 06:48:07.020
and his father accomplished no more than

06:48:07.020 --> 06:48:08.520
a handful of tangerines.

06:48:08.639 --> 06:48:11.759
Had he accepted the loss of all his

06:48:11.759 --> 06:48:13.860
freedom because he thought he could find

06:48:13.860 --> 06:48:14.819
a way to make it work?

06:48:14.819 --> 06:48:17.819
Didn't he want more out of his life?

06:48:17.880 --> 06:48:20.159
Didn't he want to fight back?

06:48:20.220 --> 06:48:22.080
Do I?

06:48:22.139 --> 06:48:25.139
It was like cricket said.

06:48:25.200 --> 06:48:29.220
Some rules were unjust, and some things

06:48:29.220 --> 06:48:31.020
were more important than following the

06:48:31.020 --> 06:48:31.319
rules.

06:48:31.380 --> 06:48:35.459
He put down the letters, and arrested his

06:48:35.459 --> 06:48:37.919
front talons on Luna's warm golden

06:48:37.919 --> 06:48:38.580
cocoon.

06:48:38.639 --> 06:48:41.759
It was very hot, but it didn't burn him.

06:48:41.819 --> 06:48:45.840
This is not going to be our life, Luna.

06:48:45.959 --> 06:48:47.939
He promised silently.

06:48:48.000 --> 06:48:51.959
I won't spend the next 100 years writing

06:48:51.959 --> 06:48:52.979
fruitless letters.

06:48:53.040 --> 06:48:57.360
Father's way, obeying the system, hasn't

06:48:57.360 --> 06:48:57.720
worked.

06:48:57.779 --> 06:48:59.700
So we'll find another.

06:48:59.819 --> 06:49:03.119
Or will burn it all down.

06:49:03.180 --> 06:49:08.040
Chapter 23.

06:49:08.279 --> 06:49:12.119
Admiral found a place for blue close to

06:49:12.119 --> 06:49:14.819
his own nest, a hollow in the rock large

06:49:14.819 --> 06:49:17.520
enough for a dragon to settle into, with

06:49:17.520 --> 06:49:19.200
several crannies in the wall where he

06:49:19.200 --> 06:49:21.659
could keep things, if he ever had

06:49:21.659 --> 06:49:22.319
anything.

06:49:22.380 --> 06:49:25.020
Apparently there was a request process

06:49:25.020 --> 06:49:26.819
involving a number of forms.

06:49:26.880 --> 06:49:30.240
At 1st the hollow seemed a little too big

06:49:30.240 --> 06:49:30.779
to blue.

06:49:30.900 --> 06:49:33.419
And then he fell to shiver across his

06:49:33.419 --> 06:49:36.720
wings, as he realized his father was

06:49:36.720 --> 06:49:39.180
thinking of Blue's future, and how much

06:49:39.180 --> 06:49:40.139
bigger he might grow.

06:49:40.200 --> 06:49:43.740
Admiral had chosen a nest where Blue

06:49:43.740 --> 06:49:45.599
could spend the entire rest of his life.

06:49:45.659 --> 06:49:48.479
But I'm not going to.

06:49:48.540 --> 06:49:50.520
That's not going to happen.

06:49:50.580 --> 06:49:53.819
He tried to believe it as he lay down to

06:49:53.819 --> 06:49:56.400
sleep, but his dreams were restless and

06:49:56.400 --> 06:49:56.819
unhappy.

06:49:56.939 --> 06:50:00.119
He dreamed of getting his talons stuck in

06:50:00.119 --> 06:50:02.159
a crevice and trying to pull them out.

06:50:02.220 --> 06:50:05.159
He dreamed of letters piling up around

06:50:05.159 --> 06:50:05.880
his claws.

06:50:06.000 --> 06:50:09.299
He dreamed of clear sight, sitting on the

06:50:09.299 --> 06:50:11.819
steps of her temple. looking down at him

06:50:11.819 --> 06:50:13.319
with enormous disappointment.

06:50:13.439 --> 06:50:17.220
When he woke up, his wrists were

06:50:17.220 --> 06:50:17.700
itching.

06:50:17.759 --> 06:50:21.119
Am I going to be a flame silk?

06:50:21.240 --> 06:50:23.580
The cavern was quiet.

06:50:23.639 --> 06:50:26.819
Most of the regular silk wings were gone

06:50:26.819 --> 06:50:29.580
and 7 of the flame silks were asleep.

06:50:29.580 --> 06:50:33.180
Blue climbed down to Luna's cocoon and

06:50:33.180 --> 06:50:33.900
leaned against it.

06:50:33.959 --> 06:50:37.020
He wished he could talk to his sister, or

06:50:37.020 --> 06:50:37.619
cricket.

06:50:37.680 --> 06:50:39.840
Is cricket all right?

06:50:39.900 --> 06:50:41.400
Did she escape?

06:50:41.459 --> 06:50:45.959
Or. His mind shied away from the

06:50:45.959 --> 06:50:46.439
alternative.

06:50:46.500 --> 06:50:49.139
He couldn't imagine the world without

06:50:49.139 --> 06:50:49.860
cricket in it.

06:50:49.919 --> 06:50:52.439
He couldn't imagine his own life without

06:50:52.439 --> 06:50:53.279
cricket in it.

06:50:53.340 --> 06:50:57.000
A hive wing guard came stomping over. and

06:50:57.000 --> 06:50:58.259
Blue sat up hopefully.

06:50:58.319 --> 06:51:00.959
Maybe this dragon could tell him

06:51:00.959 --> 06:51:02.159
something about what had happened.

06:51:02.220 --> 06:51:05.700
But the guard went right past him and

06:51:05.700 --> 06:51:07.680
jabbed Admiral in the side with one of

06:51:07.680 --> 06:51:08.580
her sharp claws.

06:51:08.639 --> 06:51:12.060
Admiral woke up with a snort, blinking

06:51:12.060 --> 06:51:12.419
rapidly.

06:51:12.479 --> 06:51:14.639
Time to spin.

06:51:14.700 --> 06:51:16.319
The guard snarled.

06:51:16.380 --> 06:51:17.099
You're late.

06:51:17.159 --> 06:51:19.439
So sorry.

06:51:19.560 --> 06:51:21.900
Admiral said, rubbing his eyes.

06:51:21.959 --> 06:51:23.639
You're quite right.

06:51:23.700 --> 06:51:26.279
I've been a little discombobulated by the

06:51:26.279 --> 06:51:27.959
arrival of my children, of course.

06:51:28.020 --> 06:51:31.259
Otherwise, I'm always on time, aren't I?

06:51:31.319 --> 06:51:32.939
Very punctual dragon.

06:51:33.000 --> 06:51:33.479
That's me.

06:51:33.540 --> 06:51:35.700
Very little reminding required.

06:51:35.759 --> 06:51:36.779
Don't you agree?

06:51:36.840 --> 06:51:40.860
Quit your yapping and excusing, the guard

06:51:40.860 --> 06:51:41.459
grumbled.

06:51:41.520 --> 06:51:43.200
Silk, now.

06:51:43.319 --> 06:51:45.900
She dragged a cauldron out from under

06:51:45.900 --> 06:51:48.419
Admiral's Nest, and thunked it into place

06:51:48.419 --> 06:51:49.619
right below Admiral.

06:51:49.680 --> 06:51:51.240
Of course.

06:51:51.360 --> 06:51:54.419
Admiral held out his arms and closed his

06:51:54.419 --> 06:51:54.599
eyes.

06:51:54.659 --> 06:51:58.860
A long, dragging moment passed, and then

06:51:58.860 --> 06:52:00.659
a thread of flame emerged from one

06:52:00.659 --> 06:52:01.080
wrist.

06:52:01.139 --> 06:52:04.319
It spiraled down into the cauldron

06:52:04.319 --> 06:52:07.380
pouring slowly, like cold honey.

06:52:07.439 --> 06:52:10.680
It was another long moment before a 2nd

06:52:10.680 --> 06:52:13.200
thread appeared from the other wrist, and

06:52:13.200 --> 06:52:15.180
this one seemed dimmer than the 1st.

06:52:15.240 --> 06:52:18.779
The guard scowled at the slow moving silk

06:52:18.779 --> 06:52:21.180
and Blue wondered what she was feeling.

06:52:21.240 --> 06:52:23.340
Was she worried about what would happen

06:52:23.340 --> 06:52:25.560
to the hives if there was a flame silk

06:52:25.560 --> 06:52:26.040
shortage?

06:52:26.099 --> 06:52:28.619
Or did the guards get punished if the

06:52:28.619 --> 06:52:30.540
flame silks didn't meet a certain quota?

06:52:30.599 --> 06:52:33.419
Or was there any chance she was actually

06:52:33.419 --> 06:52:35.520
concerned about the dragons under her

06:52:35.520 --> 06:52:36.000
charge?

06:52:36.060 --> 06:52:39.180
What a weird life this would be?

06:52:39.240 --> 06:52:40.500
He thought.

06:52:40.560 --> 06:52:44.279
Every morning, you wake up and go through

06:52:44.279 --> 06:52:46.860
a secret warehouse staircase into an

06:52:46.860 --> 06:52:48.119
underground cavern.

06:52:48.180 --> 06:52:51.060
You spend the day poking other dragons to

06:52:51.060 --> 06:52:53.400
make them work. and standing guard so

06:52:53.400 --> 06:52:54.000
they can't leave.

06:52:54.060 --> 06:52:56.279
Isn't it boring?

06:52:56.340 --> 06:52:58.139
It must be boring.

06:52:58.200 --> 06:53:00.900
Especially for the ones sitting in a

06:53:00.900 --> 06:53:03.419
circle in the dark warehouse, staring

06:53:03.419 --> 06:53:04.380
through the glass all day.

06:53:04.439 --> 06:53:08.099
The hive wing turned to leave, and

06:53:08.099 --> 06:53:09.540
admiral's eyes popped open.

06:53:09.599 --> 06:53:12.959
Sandfly, he said quickly.

06:53:13.020 --> 06:53:14.939
Have you met my son?

06:53:15.000 --> 06:53:15.540
This is Blue.

06:53:15.659 --> 06:53:18.900
He says my daughter's name is Luna, and

06:53:18.900 --> 06:53:21.000
she'll be coming out tomorrow night with

06:53:21.000 --> 06:53:21.659
her wings.

06:53:21.720 --> 06:53:24.479
And soak to add to the quota.

06:53:24.540 --> 06:53:25.619
Isn't that wonderful?

06:53:25.680 --> 06:53:28.860
Sandfly looked down at blue and the gold

06:53:28.860 --> 06:53:29.520
cocoon.

06:53:29.580 --> 06:53:31.619
She didn't say anything for a few

06:53:31.619 --> 06:53:32.220
heartbeats.

06:53:32.340 --> 06:53:36.180
Her scales were pale yellow, and speckled

06:53:36.180 --> 06:53:39.119
everywhere with tiny black spots, like a

06:53:39.119 --> 06:53:40.439
swarm of flies in the desert.

06:53:40.500 --> 06:53:43.080
It was easy to see how her parents had

06:53:43.080 --> 06:53:43.799
chosen her name.

06:53:43.860 --> 06:53:48.060
They're very young, she said at length.

06:53:48.180 --> 06:53:50.639
Blue couldn't tell if she was feeling

06:53:50.639 --> 06:53:52.860
sorry for them, with a life of

06:53:52.860 --> 06:53:55.560
imprisonment lying ahead, or if she was

06:53:55.560 --> 06:53:57.479
pleased at the idea of how much silk

06:53:57.479 --> 06:53:59.520
they'd be able to produce over the length

06:53:59.520 --> 06:54:00.240
of that life.

06:54:01.080 --> 06:54:03.360
Excuse me, he said.

06:54:03.419 --> 06:54:06.180
I'm sorry to bother you, but I was

06:54:06.180 --> 06:54:08.459
wondering, do you know what happened to

06:54:08.459 --> 06:54:10.080
the dragons who stole the book of

06:54:10.080 --> 06:54:10.979
Clearsight yesterday?

06:54:11.040 --> 06:54:15.419
Sandfly leaped backward, as though he'd

06:54:15.419 --> 06:54:17.159
jabbed her with an electric eel.

06:54:17.220 --> 06:54:18.599
What?

06:54:18.659 --> 06:54:19.919
She roared.

06:54:20.040 --> 06:54:22.680
Half of the sleeping heads in the cavern

06:54:22.680 --> 06:54:24.240
popped up and turned their way.

06:54:24.299 --> 06:54:26.340
That didn't happen.

06:54:26.400 --> 06:54:28.139
No one would dare.

06:54:28.200 --> 06:54:29.639
Oh.

06:54:29.759 --> 06:54:31.380
Blue trailed off.

06:54:31.439 --> 06:54:33.720
It hadn't occurred to him that the queen

06:54:33.720 --> 06:54:35.939
would lie to everyone about this. and

06:54:35.939 --> 06:54:37.439
make the librarian lie too.

06:54:37.500 --> 06:54:40.200
But now that he thought about it, he

06:54:40.200 --> 06:54:40.919
wasn't surprised.

06:54:41.040 --> 06:54:43.979
Losing the book of Clear Sight would be

06:54:43.979 --> 06:54:45.360
pretty terrible for morale.

06:54:45.360 --> 06:54:48.419
She could easily just close up the case

06:54:48.419 --> 06:54:50.939
and pretend it was still in there.

06:54:51.000 --> 06:54:54.599
That is, if cricket and sundew did escape

06:54:54.599 --> 06:54:55.080
with a book.

06:54:55.139 --> 06:54:58.680
What a horrible thing to say.

06:54:58.740 --> 06:55:00.360
Samfly barked.

06:55:00.419 --> 06:55:03.840
Behind her, Admiral gave Blue a pained

06:55:03.840 --> 06:55:07.979
fix this, expression, I'm sorry, Blue

06:55:07.979 --> 06:55:08.400
said.

06:55:08.459 --> 06:55:09.599
I'm so sorry.

06:55:09.659 --> 06:55:13.500
I meant the dragons who tried to steal

06:55:13.500 --> 06:55:14.580
the book of Clearside.

06:55:14.639 --> 06:55:17.400
Of course, the librarian stopped them.

06:55:17.459 --> 06:55:19.020
Of course it's safe.

06:55:19.080 --> 06:55:20.520
Um.

06:55:20.819 --> 06:55:22.919
Those dragons, though.

06:55:22.979 --> 06:55:24.540
Do you know if they got away?

06:55:24.599 --> 06:55:28.439
Sandfly was shaking out her wings as

06:55:28.439 --> 06:55:29.700
though they were crawling with

06:55:29.700 --> 06:55:30.540
caterpillars.

06:55:30.599 --> 06:55:33.959
Ugh, she said, I'm going to have

06:55:33.959 --> 06:55:35.040
nightmares for days.

06:55:35.099 --> 06:55:37.500
What kind of traitor would steal the book

06:55:37.500 --> 06:55:38.340
of Clearsight?

06:55:38.400 --> 06:55:40.860
That's so obviously wrong?

06:55:40.919 --> 06:55:43.439
So obviously wrong.

06:55:43.500 --> 06:55:47.040
Blue stared down at his talons.

06:55:47.099 --> 06:55:50.340
The talons that had unlocked the case and

06:55:50.340 --> 06:55:52.380
lifted out the precious book.

06:55:52.439 --> 06:55:53.880
It was me.

06:55:53.939 --> 06:55:55.860
I'm the traitor.

06:55:55.979 --> 06:55:59.279
But the librarian had wanted them to have

06:55:59.279 --> 06:56:00.779
it. when she was herself.

06:56:00.840 --> 06:56:04.200
She'd said it was time for other dragons

06:56:04.200 --> 06:56:05.639
to know the book's secrets.

06:56:05.700 --> 06:56:09.540
He decided not to mention that, in case

06:56:09.540 --> 06:56:11.639
Sandfly had another heart attack.

06:56:11.700 --> 06:56:14.639
He was also carefully avoiding the fact

06:56:14.639 --> 06:56:17.159
that one of the criminal dragons was a

06:56:17.159 --> 06:56:19.680
leaf wing, in case that wasn't public

06:56:19.680 --> 06:56:24.119
knowledge, and might set off a riot, Right

06:56:24.119 --> 06:56:26.819
he said, trying one more time.

06:56:27.000 --> 06:56:28.919
So the queen really wanted to catch

06:56:28.919 --> 06:56:29.220
them.

06:56:29.279 --> 06:56:31.200
But did she?

06:56:31.259 --> 06:56:35.159
I have no idea, Sandfly said.

06:56:35.220 --> 06:56:36.840
She settled her wings again.

06:56:36.900 --> 06:56:39.479
I was down here until midnight last

06:56:39.479 --> 06:56:39.720
night.

06:56:39.779 --> 06:56:42.599
No one at home mentioned any public

06:56:42.599 --> 06:56:45.479
executions yesterday, but maybe they'll

06:56:45.479 --> 06:56:46.619
be held today or tomorrow.

06:56:46.680 --> 06:56:51.240
Blue managed not to gasp or burst into

06:56:51.240 --> 06:56:51.599
tears.

06:56:51.659 --> 06:56:55.380
She assumes they were caught because

06:56:55.380 --> 06:56:57.720
she's a hive wing, but she doesn't

06:56:57.720 --> 06:56:58.259
actually know.

06:56:58.319 --> 06:56:59.880
They might be safe.

06:56:59.939 --> 06:57:03.180
Or they might be in another prison

06:57:03.180 --> 06:57:05.759
somewhere, waiting to be executed.

06:57:05.880 --> 06:57:09.240
If only he could escape and go look for

06:57:09.240 --> 06:57:09.419
them.

06:57:09.479 --> 06:57:12.840
But he didn't have cricket's clever ideas

06:57:12.840 --> 06:57:15.720
or sore tails impulsive courage, or

06:57:15.720 --> 06:57:17.880
sundew's helpful pouches of weapons.

06:57:17.939 --> 06:57:20.939
He was just a little wingless dragon

06:57:20.939 --> 06:57:22.680
stuck in a cavern of flame.

06:57:22.740 --> 06:57:25.919
Still, he could at least try.

06:57:25.979 --> 06:57:29.639
Blue spent the rest of the day exploring

06:57:29.639 --> 06:57:32.220
every corner of the Flame Silk Cave.

06:57:32.279 --> 06:57:35.580
He walked the entire perimeter, clambering

06:57:35.580 --> 06:57:37.139
up and down the rocks wherever he needed

06:57:37.139 --> 06:57:37.439
to.

06:57:37.560 --> 06:57:40.619
The guards by the staircase gave him

06:57:40.619 --> 06:57:43.139
weird looks as he went by, but they

06:57:43.139 --> 06:57:43.799
didn't stop him.

06:57:43.919 --> 06:57:45.540
Nobody stopped him.

06:57:45.599 --> 06:57:48.360
Although he got the distinct feeling that

06:57:48.360 --> 06:57:50.220
all the flame silks were watching him

06:57:50.220 --> 06:57:52.259
whenever they thought he wasn't looking.

06:57:52.319 --> 06:57:56.639
There were 3 female flame silks and 7

06:57:56.639 --> 06:57:59.279
males, most of them quite a lot older

06:57:59.279 --> 06:57:59.759
than Blue.

06:57:59.819 --> 06:58:02.639
He guessed that Admiral might be the

06:58:02.639 --> 06:58:03.900
youngest one the queen had.

06:58:03.959 --> 06:58:06.840
A couple of them seemed to stay in their

06:58:06.840 --> 06:58:09.299
nests all the time, cycling between

06:58:09.299 --> 06:58:11.819
sleeping, eating and producing silk

06:58:11.819 --> 06:58:13.919
without ever moving from their spots.

06:58:13.919 --> 06:58:17.159
He saw a few others get up and fly around

06:58:17.159 --> 06:58:18.840
although they couldn't go far.

06:58:18.900 --> 06:58:21.299
There was enough room to spread their

06:58:21.299 --> 06:58:24.060
wings, but they couldn't soar, and there

06:58:24.060 --> 06:58:25.500
wasn't any wind to ride.

06:58:25.500 --> 06:58:27.779
If this is my future.

06:58:27.840 --> 06:58:30.599
Well, I never get to fly in the clouds.

06:58:30.659 --> 06:58:33.659
How will I ever learn to fly properly

06:58:33.659 --> 06:58:35.759
without any wind currents down here?

06:58:35.819 --> 06:58:39.840
The guards and the flame silks seemed to

06:58:39.840 --> 06:58:41.819
have a very precise schedule in their

06:58:41.819 --> 06:58:42.060
heads.

06:58:42.180 --> 06:58:45.419
They rotated production cycles and rest

06:58:45.419 --> 06:58:48.720
intervals in careful synchronization, so

06:58:48.720 --> 06:58:51.299
there were always at least 3 flame silks

06:58:51.299 --> 06:58:53.279
working, even in the middle of the

06:58:53.279 --> 06:58:53.459
night.

06:58:53.580 --> 06:58:57.360
Blue had covered almost the entire cave.

06:58:57.419 --> 06:58:59.759
By the time his father's turn at the

06:58:59.759 --> 06:59:00.599
cauldron was done.

06:59:00.659 --> 06:59:03.360
There were a few ledges and corners that

06:59:03.360 --> 06:59:05.159
he hadn't figured out how to climb up to

06:59:05.159 --> 06:59:07.860
yet, but he had walked between all the

06:59:07.860 --> 06:59:10.500
stalagmites, and surreptitiously poked

06:59:10.500 --> 06:59:12.360
his nose and every large gap in the

06:59:12.360 --> 06:59:12.599
rocks.

06:59:12.720 --> 06:59:15.900
So far, he hadn't found any secret

06:59:15.900 --> 06:59:16.560
passages, though.

06:59:16.619 --> 06:59:18.779
From across the cave.

06:59:18.840 --> 06:59:21.479
He saw sandfly drop a bucket of food

06:59:21.479 --> 06:59:24.000
beside Admiral, and roll the cauldron

06:59:24.000 --> 06:59:24.240
away.

06:59:24.299 --> 06:59:27.360
He started back, his head full of

06:59:27.360 --> 06:59:27.659
questions.

06:59:27.720 --> 06:59:29.880
Hello, dear.

06:59:29.939 --> 06:59:33.540
One of the flame silks said, popping her

06:59:33.540 --> 06:59:35.700
head over the edge of her nest, just as

06:59:35.700 --> 06:59:36.659
he was about to pass her.

06:59:36.720 --> 06:59:39.299
He jumped, and she giggled.

06:59:39.360 --> 06:59:40.860
I'm Danaid.

06:59:40.919 --> 06:59:43.560
My, aren't you a shiny one?

06:59:43.619 --> 06:59:46.680
We haven't had any visitors in so long.

06:59:46.740 --> 06:59:50.220
And now we'll have 2 new flame silks.

06:59:50.279 --> 06:59:51.419
How delightful.

06:59:51.540 --> 06:59:53.700
She sighed happily.

06:59:53.759 --> 06:59:56.580
Her scales were so orange, she almost

06:59:56.580 --> 06:59:59.099
looked like a hive wing, but there was no

06:59:59.099 --> 06:59:59.819
black among them.

06:59:59.880 --> 07:00:03.720
Instead, flecks of white dotted her spine

07:00:03.720 --> 07:00:06.180
and long streaks of white striped her

07:00:06.180 --> 07:00:06.479
wings.

07:00:06.540 --> 07:00:09.119
She looked old enough to be Blue's great

07:00:09.119 --> 07:00:09.840
grandmother.

07:00:09.900 --> 07:00:13.200
I might not be a flame silk.

07:00:13.259 --> 07:00:15.720
Blue said, checking his wrists again.

07:00:15.779 --> 07:00:18.959
Not to worry, she said.

07:00:19.020 --> 07:00:22.020
I'm sure you'll still be delightful

07:00:22.020 --> 07:00:22.560
company.

07:00:22.619 --> 07:00:25.380
Better than all these grousing old

07:00:25.380 --> 07:00:26.580
dragons, anyhow.

07:00:26.700 --> 07:00:29.520
Some of them can't keep secret.

07:00:29.580 --> 07:00:33.000
She shot an irritated look at the pale

07:00:33.000 --> 07:00:34.139
pink flame silk.

07:00:34.259 --> 07:00:37.860
And some of them think very highly of

07:00:37.860 --> 07:00:38.220
themselves.

07:00:38.279 --> 07:00:41.159
I can hear you.

07:00:41.279 --> 07:00:43.860
Fiddlery shouted from his nest.

07:00:43.919 --> 07:00:46.860
We all can, called another.

07:00:46.919 --> 07:00:50.459
I know, Danaid shouted back.

07:00:50.580 --> 07:00:53.759
We are in a cave, but I'm having a

07:00:53.759 --> 07:00:55.439
private conversation.

07:00:55.560 --> 07:00:58.080
So stick your snouts somewhere else.

07:00:58.139 --> 07:01:02.520
I told you, I thought you wanted me to

07:01:02.520 --> 07:01:04.080
tell Fritillery that you like to

07:01:04.080 --> 07:01:04.619
stripes.

07:01:04.740 --> 07:01:07.799
The pink silkwing said in a wounded voice

07:01:07.799 --> 07:01:10.560
Aren't you ever going to forgive me?

07:01:10.619 --> 07:01:13.740
Well, I don't like them anymore.

07:01:13.799 --> 07:01:15.479
Dene had snapped.

07:01:15.540 --> 07:01:18.240
I think they make him look skinny and

07:01:18.240 --> 07:01:19.919
arrogant and potato brained.

07:01:19.979 --> 07:01:24.060
You wish you were as smart as a potato.

07:01:24.119 --> 07:01:26.040
Fritillery bellowed.

07:01:26.099 --> 07:01:29.939
Go suck a lime, Danae had shouted.

07:01:30.000 --> 07:01:32.279
I hope your face gets eaten by dung

07:01:32.279 --> 07:01:32.759
beetles.

07:01:32.819 --> 07:01:37.380
Now, now, settle down, said one of the

07:01:37.380 --> 07:01:39.180
hive wing guards in a bored voice.

07:01:39.299 --> 07:01:42.240
Anyway, where were we?

07:01:42.360 --> 07:01:45.060
Danae had said to Blue, her voice

07:01:45.060 --> 07:01:46.560
suddenly all sweetness again.

07:01:46.619 --> 07:01:50.520
And it wasn't my fault, the festoon

07:01:50.520 --> 07:01:53.340
overheard me telling Heliconian, that you

07:01:53.340 --> 07:01:54.419
thought he was stealing all the

07:01:54.419 --> 07:01:55.080
radishes.

07:01:55.139 --> 07:01:57.720
The pink dragon went on querulously.

07:01:57.779 --> 07:02:00.060
You should be mad at him for

07:02:00.060 --> 07:02:01.259
eavesdropping.

07:02:01.319 --> 07:02:02.220
Not me.

07:02:02.279 --> 07:02:06.900
I was, then they had snapped, but he died

07:02:06.900 --> 07:02:08.759
5 years ago, you half wit.

07:02:08.819 --> 07:02:11.279
Oh, right.

07:02:11.340 --> 07:02:14.639
The pink dragon flopped sideways in his

07:02:14.639 --> 07:02:15.000
nest.

07:02:15.060 --> 07:02:17.520
Ignore them, sweetheart.

07:02:17.580 --> 07:02:19.439
Then they had said to Blue.

07:02:19.500 --> 07:02:21.659
Is it always like this?

07:02:21.720 --> 07:02:23.159
Blue aft.

07:02:23.220 --> 07:02:25.500
He waved his hands at the flame silks.

07:02:25.560 --> 07:02:27.000
Like what?

07:02:27.119 --> 07:02:29.279
The Naiad asked cheerfully.

07:02:29.400 --> 07:02:32.400
The arguing?

07:02:32.459 --> 07:02:33.360
He tried.

07:02:33.479 --> 07:02:36.180
He'd seen at least 3 other shouting

07:02:36.180 --> 07:02:38.580
matches erupt that morning while he'd

07:02:38.580 --> 07:02:39.599
been searching the cave.

07:02:39.659 --> 07:02:41.880
Who's arguing?

07:02:41.880 --> 07:02:43.319
than they had said.

07:02:43.380 --> 07:02:45.240
Was it old fritillery?

07:02:45.299 --> 07:02:46.080
He's the worst.

07:02:46.200 --> 07:02:47.580
Don't talk to him.

07:02:47.639 --> 07:02:49.680
Zeneca is terrible too.

07:02:49.740 --> 07:02:52.619
Always gossiping and bad mouthing

07:02:52.619 --> 07:02:52.919
everyone.

07:02:52.979 --> 07:02:56.639
You already know you can't trust pirate

07:02:56.639 --> 07:02:57.000
over there.

07:02:57.060 --> 07:03:00.180
The pink flame silk let out a grumbling

07:03:00.180 --> 07:03:02.279
sigh, and turned his head away from

07:03:02.279 --> 07:03:02.580
them.

07:03:02.639 --> 07:03:06.299
Clubtail is perfectly nice, but by all

07:03:06.299 --> 07:03:09.240
the hives, he never stops talking.

07:03:09.299 --> 07:03:11.880
Heliconian ruins everything.

07:03:11.939 --> 07:03:15.119
She flipped her tail over the side of the

07:03:15.119 --> 07:03:16.560
nest and smiled at Blue.

07:03:16.619 --> 07:03:18.000
Really?

07:03:18.060 --> 07:03:20.340
I am the only one worth knowing.

07:03:20.400 --> 07:03:24.840
Danaid, stop poisoning my son's mind

07:03:24.840 --> 07:03:27.779
Admiral said, appearing a blue side

07:03:27.779 --> 07:03:28.500
suddenly.

07:03:28.560 --> 07:03:31.619
He's on my side, not yours.

07:03:31.680 --> 07:03:37.020
There are sides, Blue said, confused.

07:03:37.080 --> 07:03:40.979
No, Admiral said, but Danaid is

07:03:40.979 --> 07:03:42.000
definitely on the wrong one.

07:03:42.060 --> 07:03:44.939
Let me introduce you to the dragons you

07:03:44.939 --> 07:03:46.259
should be friends with.

07:03:46.319 --> 07:03:48.779
Then they had hissed at him.

07:03:48.840 --> 07:03:51.479
You can't keep the new friends all to

07:03:51.479 --> 07:03:52.020
yourself.

07:03:52.080 --> 07:03:53.099
She cried.

07:03:53.159 --> 07:03:56.220
New friends are for sharing.

07:03:56.279 --> 07:03:57.900
Let him decide for himself who he wants

07:03:57.900 --> 07:03:58.500
to talk to.

07:03:58.560 --> 07:04:02.880
Eat bugs, Danaid, Admiral said sharply.

07:04:02.939 --> 07:04:05.939
He led Blue away, his snout in the air.

07:04:06.000 --> 07:04:10.139
Isn't she dreadful, he said, loud enough

07:04:10.139 --> 07:04:12.060
for the orange silk wing to overhear?

07:04:12.119 --> 07:04:14.400
She seemed all right to me.

07:04:14.459 --> 07:04:15.659
Blue said.

07:04:15.720 --> 07:04:17.939
No, Admiral said.

07:04:18.000 --> 07:04:19.560
She's dreadful.

07:04:19.619 --> 07:04:21.240
What is going on?

07:04:21.360 --> 07:04:23.580
Blue asked, bewildered.

07:04:23.639 --> 07:04:24.840
With what?

07:04:24.900 --> 07:04:28.439
Admiral paused to toss Blue a tangerine

07:04:28.439 --> 07:04:29.040
smiling.

07:04:29.159 --> 07:04:32.819
It's just, you guys seem to spend a lot

07:04:32.819 --> 07:04:34.259
of time fighting with each other.

07:04:34.319 --> 07:04:36.000
Blue pointed out.

07:04:36.060 --> 07:04:37.500
Do we?

07:04:37.619 --> 07:04:39.659
Admiral looked surprised.

07:04:39.779 --> 07:04:42.720
No more than most dragons, I'm sure.

07:04:42.779 --> 07:04:46.919
Way more than the dragons I know, Blue

07:04:46.919 --> 07:04:47.220
said.

07:04:47.340 --> 07:04:49.500
Admiral flipped one of his wings

07:04:49.500 --> 07:04:50.340
dismissively.

07:04:50.400 --> 07:04:52.919
Well, I suppose we've all been stuck

07:04:52.919 --> 07:04:54.000
together for so long.

07:04:54.060 --> 07:04:56.400
There's bound to be a little tension here

07:04:56.400 --> 07:04:56.759
and there.

07:04:56.819 --> 07:04:59.159
Come meet Zeneca, though.

07:04:59.279 --> 07:05:01.919
She's very sweet, and always has clever

07:05:01.919 --> 07:05:03.000
things to say about the others.

07:05:03.060 --> 07:05:07.259
Seneca shared her kale and kumquats with

07:05:07.259 --> 07:05:09.360
them, and spent their entire conversation

07:05:09.360 --> 07:05:11.880
glancing around the cave to make sure

07:05:11.880 --> 07:05:14.040
everyone else saw that she was officially

07:05:14.040 --> 07:05:16.020
getting to meet the new Silk Wing first.

07:05:16.080 --> 07:05:19.380
She also made a point of warning Blue

07:05:19.380 --> 07:05:22.020
away from Danaid and a few other flame

07:05:22.020 --> 07:05:22.439
silks.

07:05:22.560 --> 07:05:25.680
This went on with each Dragon Blue met

07:05:25.680 --> 07:05:27.900
and by the time he wound up back in his

07:05:27.900 --> 07:05:29.520
nest, He was exhausted.

07:05:29.580 --> 07:05:32.700
He couldn't keep track of who hated who

07:05:32.700 --> 07:05:35.340
except they all seemed to hate fritillery

07:05:35.340 --> 07:05:36.240
which was mutual.

07:05:36.299 --> 07:05:39.299
The cavern was seething with petty

07:05:39.299 --> 07:05:42.840
rivalries, long held grudges, and easily

07:05:42.840 --> 07:05:43.979
provoked tempers.

07:05:44.040 --> 07:05:48.000
He flopped down next to Luna's cocoon, and

07:05:48.000 --> 07:05:49.020
rested his head against it.

07:05:49.080 --> 07:05:52.799
He couldn't wait for his sensible, funny

07:05:52.799 --> 07:05:54.299
normal sister to come out.

07:05:54.360 --> 07:05:57.779
No wonder they're starved for new

07:05:57.779 --> 07:05:58.200
company.

07:05:58.259 --> 07:06:01.139
Being trapped in here for so long has

07:06:01.139 --> 07:06:02.939
turned them all super weird.

07:06:03.000 --> 07:06:05.759
Almost my turn again.

07:06:05.819 --> 07:06:08.819
Admiral said, shaking his wrists out.

07:06:08.880 --> 07:06:11.400
He tapped the insides of his arms with

07:06:11.400 --> 07:06:14.040
his claws, as though hoping it would wake

07:06:14.040 --> 07:06:15.299
up his silk glands.

07:06:15.360 --> 07:06:18.180
Father, Blue said.

07:06:18.240 --> 07:06:20.159
Why do you all fight with each other?

07:06:20.220 --> 07:06:22.439
Aren't there more important enemies?

07:06:22.500 --> 07:06:24.360
Like who?

07:06:24.419 --> 07:06:25.799
Admiral asked.

07:06:25.919 --> 07:06:27.360
The queen.

07:06:27.419 --> 07:06:28.799
The hive wings.

07:06:28.860 --> 07:06:32.279
The guards who imprison you here, Lou

07:06:32.279 --> 07:06:34.020
said, lowering his voice.

07:06:34.139 --> 07:06:37.560
Oh, tosh, said Admiral.

07:06:37.619 --> 07:06:39.000
The queen is our employer.

07:06:39.060 --> 07:06:42.360
The guards keep us fed and safe and on

07:06:42.360 --> 07:06:42.900
schedule.

07:06:42.959 --> 07:06:45.419
Blue shook his head.

07:06:45.540 --> 07:06:48.119
How could his father not understand that

07:06:48.119 --> 07:06:49.139
this was a prison?

07:06:49.259 --> 07:06:51.540
Maybe after you've been here for a

07:06:51.540 --> 07:06:51.779
while.

07:06:51.840 --> 07:06:54.299
You have to convince yourself you chose

07:06:54.299 --> 07:06:56.939
this, so it all feels less awful.

07:06:57.000 --> 07:07:00.959
He'd met 2 dragons among the flame silks

07:07:00.959 --> 07:07:03.479
who he suspected weren't as resigned or

07:07:03.479 --> 07:07:05.220
falsely content as admiral.

07:07:05.279 --> 07:07:08.759
Heliconian was restless and fidgety and

07:07:08.759 --> 07:07:10.139
glanced at the exits a lot.

07:07:10.200 --> 07:07:13.319
She also asked the only questions about

07:07:13.319 --> 07:07:15.540
the outside world, and what was happening

07:07:15.540 --> 07:07:16.560
beyond the cavern.

07:07:16.619 --> 07:07:20.040
And pirate seemed desperately unhappy

07:07:20.040 --> 07:07:22.020
although he wouldn't say anything bad

07:07:22.020 --> 07:07:23.220
about the hive wings.

07:07:23.220 --> 07:07:26.759
Also, Fritillery, with his everlasting

07:07:26.759 --> 07:07:27.540
bad temper.

07:07:27.599 --> 07:07:29.340
Surely he wanted to escape.

07:07:29.459 --> 07:07:33.180
I just think it's silly to be so mad at

07:07:33.180 --> 07:07:35.040
each other, Blue said.

07:07:35.099 --> 07:07:37.380
When there are far worse things going on

07:07:37.380 --> 07:07:40.200
and dragons who are treating you far more

07:07:40.200 --> 07:07:41.459
terribly than Danaid.

07:07:41.520 --> 07:07:44.040
If you all could stop fighting and stand

07:07:44.040 --> 07:07:46.200
together, maybe you could actually change

07:07:46.200 --> 07:07:46.680
things.

07:07:46.799 --> 07:07:49.139
No, no.

07:07:49.200 --> 07:07:51.299
Admiral said firmly.

07:07:51.360 --> 07:07:53.880
I would never work with Danaid or

07:07:53.880 --> 07:07:55.500
ClubTail or White Spec.

07:07:55.560 --> 07:07:58.860
They are selfish ignoramuses and wrong

07:07:58.860 --> 07:07:59.340
about everything.

07:07:59.400 --> 07:08:02.099
I can get things done through the queen.

07:08:02.220 --> 07:08:04.020
Blue side.

07:08:04.080 --> 07:08:06.959
He could see these dragons had baked

07:08:06.959 --> 07:08:08.520
their opinions of one another in a

07:08:08.520 --> 07:08:10.799
furnace, and were determined to stick to

07:08:10.799 --> 07:08:11.400
their factions.

07:08:11.459 --> 07:08:15.659
He slept poorly again that night, troubled

07:08:15.659 --> 07:08:16.979
by dreams of searching for cricket

07:08:16.979 --> 07:08:19.080
through the dark halls of her school.

07:08:19.139 --> 07:08:22.740
No matter how many corners he turned, or

07:08:22.740 --> 07:08:25.380
how many doors he opened, he never found

07:08:25.380 --> 07:08:26.220
the library.

07:08:26.279 --> 07:08:30.119
But he ran into Danaid, and Fritillery

07:08:30.119 --> 07:08:33.540
and Pirate, over and over again, all of

07:08:33.540 --> 07:08:35.220
them yelling over his head at someone

07:08:35.220 --> 07:08:36.540
else across the room.

07:08:36.599 --> 07:08:39.180
Then, just before he woke up.

07:08:39.240 --> 07:08:42.240
He found a room with Luna's cocoon in it

07:08:42.240 --> 07:08:45.240
but the threads were cut open, and no one

07:08:45.240 --> 07:08:45.599
was inside.

07:08:45.720 --> 07:08:49.319
He scrambled out of his nest before he

07:08:49.319 --> 07:08:52.319
was fully awake, stumbling over his claws

07:08:52.319 --> 07:08:53.880
as he hurried to her cocoon.

07:08:53.939 --> 07:08:57.959
It was still there, still safe, still

07:08:57.959 --> 07:08:58.259
warm.

07:08:58.380 --> 07:09:01.919
The silk walls seemed thinner than before

07:09:01.919 --> 07:09:04.500
so he thought he could see the shadow of

07:09:04.500 --> 07:09:05.459
Luna on the other side.

07:09:05.520 --> 07:09:09.000
He leaned against it again and whispered

07:09:09.000 --> 07:09:10.500
Luna.

07:09:10.560 --> 07:09:11.939
I miss you.

07:09:12.000 --> 07:09:16.259
The silk moved against his scales, a

07:09:16.259 --> 07:09:19.080
slight push and give, as though the

07:09:19.080 --> 07:09:21.720
dragon inside was rolling over or nudging

07:09:21.720 --> 07:09:22.380
him back.

07:09:22.619 --> 07:09:25.080
She's coming out tonight.

07:09:25.139 --> 07:09:28.919
Blue said, grinning, when Admiral came

07:09:28.919 --> 07:09:29.880
over to check on him.

07:09:29.880 --> 07:09:33.419
Even in this peculiar place, he couldn't

07:09:33.419 --> 07:09:34.979
help feeling excited for Luna.

07:09:35.040 --> 07:09:38.400
She'd finally have wings like she always

07:09:38.400 --> 07:09:38.819
wanted.

07:09:38.880 --> 07:09:41.819
But would she ever get to really use

07:09:41.819 --> 07:09:42.000
them?

07:09:42.060 --> 07:09:45.299
His smile dimmed as the cocoon rock

07:09:45.299 --> 07:09:45.779
again.

07:09:45.840 --> 07:09:48.419
Even though this was the last place he

07:09:48.419 --> 07:09:49.020
wanted to be.

07:09:49.080 --> 07:09:52.139
He was glad he'd be here for Luna when

07:09:52.139 --> 07:09:52.619
she came out.

07:09:52.680 --> 07:09:55.200
He was glad he'd be the one to explain

07:09:55.200 --> 07:09:57.659
everything. instead of a bunch of

07:09:57.659 --> 07:09:58.860
squabbling strangers.

07:09:58.979 --> 07:10:01.799
Dad, Blue said.

07:10:01.860 --> 07:10:03.959
What do you think will happen to me?

07:10:03.959 --> 07:10:06.959
If I end up not being a flame silk.

07:10:07.080 --> 07:10:10.500
You'll get one of the regular Silkwing

07:10:10.500 --> 07:10:11.099
jobs down here.

07:10:11.159 --> 07:10:13.259
His father said breezily.

07:10:13.319 --> 07:10:16.380
Moving cauldrons or chopping food or

07:10:16.380 --> 07:10:17.939
cleaning, that sort of thing.

07:10:18.000 --> 07:10:20.459
But what if I want to go home?

07:10:20.520 --> 07:10:23.580
Blue asked, wishing he could stop his

07:10:23.580 --> 07:10:24.479
voice from trembling.

07:10:24.540 --> 07:10:27.240
Would I really have to stay here?

07:10:27.360 --> 07:10:30.720
Admiral drummed his claws on the rocks

07:10:30.720 --> 07:10:31.200
below him.

07:10:31.259 --> 07:10:33.959
Well, he said.

07:10:34.080 --> 07:10:36.599
The queen doesn't exactly like to have

07:10:36.599 --> 07:10:38.700
silk wings wandering around who know

07:10:38.700 --> 07:10:39.779
where this cavern is.

07:10:39.900 --> 07:10:43.560
Blue's shoulders slumped, and Admiral

07:10:43.560 --> 07:10:44.340
hurried on quickly.

07:10:44.400 --> 07:10:47.400
But tell you what, I'll ride her a letter

07:10:47.400 --> 07:10:48.779
or lots of letters.

07:10:48.840 --> 07:10:51.900
If you're not a flame silk, I'll think of

07:10:51.900 --> 07:10:53.939
some very good reasons why you should get

07:10:53.939 --> 07:10:54.419
to go home.

07:10:54.479 --> 07:10:56.099
I'll convince her.

07:10:56.159 --> 07:10:57.180
Don't worry.

07:10:57.240 --> 07:11:00.599
It might take a while, but then maybe

07:11:00.599 --> 07:11:01.860
you'll decide you want to stay.

07:11:01.919 --> 07:11:03.479
It's quite nice here.

07:11:03.540 --> 07:11:06.060
And this is where I am.

07:11:06.119 --> 07:11:09.540
He finished, with a wistful note in his

07:11:09.540 --> 07:11:10.139
voice.

07:11:10.200 --> 07:11:12.779
I know, Blue said.

07:11:12.840 --> 07:11:16.259
I'll think about it, he added, to make

07:11:16.259 --> 07:11:17.220
his dad feel better.

07:11:17.279 --> 07:11:20.220
That day passed much like the one

07:11:20.220 --> 07:11:20.520
before.

07:11:20.580 --> 07:11:23.759
Blue prowled all the corners again

07:11:23.759 --> 07:11:26.639
looking for loose stones, or a breath of

07:11:26.639 --> 07:11:27.419
air from outside.

07:11:27.479 --> 07:11:30.479
He tried to avoid getting dragged into

07:11:30.479 --> 07:11:33.060
the fight between the flame silks, but it

07:11:33.060 --> 07:11:33.900
was almost impossible.

07:11:33.959 --> 07:11:37.020
Every time he walked across the cave

07:11:37.020 --> 07:11:39.540
someone would call him over, and then

07:11:39.540 --> 07:11:41.159
someone else would start shouting about

07:11:41.159 --> 07:11:43.619
how he shouldn't associate with worm

07:11:43.619 --> 07:11:45.000
eating low lives like that.

07:11:45.060 --> 07:11:47.819
And soon they'd all be arguing over an

07:11:47.819 --> 07:11:49.979
offensive remark one of them had made 10

07:11:49.979 --> 07:11:50.459
years ago.

07:11:50.580 --> 07:11:53.580
And finally, Admiral would have to come

07:11:53.580 --> 07:11:55.080
hustle blue away to safety.

07:11:55.139 --> 07:11:57.659
But he did find a spot.

07:11:57.720 --> 07:12:01.380
Just one. that gave him a spark of hope.

07:12:01.439 --> 07:12:04.619
It was in the wall under the ledge where

07:12:04.619 --> 07:12:06.419
the hive wings guarded the staircase.

07:12:06.540 --> 07:12:09.840
Here the rock slanted back a ways into a

07:12:09.840 --> 07:12:12.360
craggy corner, and when Blue ran his

07:12:12.360 --> 07:12:15.419
talons over the stone, he found a hole.

07:12:15.479 --> 07:12:17.220
It wasn't a very big hole.

07:12:17.279 --> 07:12:19.979
It was just large enough for him to fit

07:12:19.979 --> 07:12:22.319
one of his arms through it, but when he

07:12:22.319 --> 07:12:24.840
did, he felt open space on the other

07:12:24.840 --> 07:12:25.200
side.

07:12:25.319 --> 07:12:29.880
Open space and a touch of chilliness, as

07:12:29.880 --> 07:12:31.740
though there was another big cave back

07:12:31.740 --> 07:12:34.619
there, or maybe even a passage.

07:12:34.680 --> 07:12:36.959
The rocks he could feel on the back of

07:12:36.959 --> 07:12:38.580
the wall seemed damp.

07:12:38.639 --> 07:12:41.700
He tried peering through, but he couldn't

07:12:41.700 --> 07:12:42.720
see anything but darkness.

07:12:42.779 --> 07:12:46.680
He returned to his nest, trying to think

07:12:46.680 --> 07:12:47.400
like cricket.

07:12:47.520 --> 07:12:49.740
How would she get through the wall?

07:12:49.860 --> 07:12:51.060
if she were stuck in here?

07:12:51.119 --> 07:12:54.900
It was early evening when Luna's cocoon

07:12:54.900 --> 07:12:55.740
started squirming.

07:12:55.860 --> 07:12:59.520
He crouched beside it, touching the silk

07:12:59.520 --> 07:13:01.560
gently with his talons whenever it seemed

07:13:01.560 --> 07:13:03.419
as if it might rock too far away.

07:13:03.479 --> 07:13:07.080
Their father was there too, watching with

07:13:07.080 --> 07:13:07.799
shining eyes.

07:13:07.860 --> 07:13:11.459
A crack appeared at one end of the golden

07:13:11.459 --> 07:13:12.000
cocoon.

07:13:12.119 --> 07:13:15.000
Blue held his breath as it widened

07:13:15.000 --> 07:13:16.319
slicing off the tip.

07:13:16.380 --> 07:13:19.560
Claws appeared in the gap, pushing away

07:13:19.560 --> 07:13:21.959
the top of the cocoon, and then you could

07:13:21.959 --> 07:13:24.180
see Luna's head, shoving her way out as

07:13:24.180 --> 07:13:24.599
well.

07:13:24.659 --> 07:13:27.000
Luna, he called.

07:13:27.060 --> 07:13:28.380
I'm here.

07:13:28.439 --> 07:13:29.159
You're doing great.

07:13:29.279 --> 07:13:30.720
You're almost done.

07:13:30.840 --> 07:13:34.439
She couldn't answer yet, but he saw her

07:13:34.439 --> 07:13:36.419
antennae unfurl and wave at him.

07:13:36.479 --> 07:13:40.020
Luna wriggled and heaved, and slowly

07:13:40.020 --> 07:13:42.659
dragged her whole body out, until finally

07:13:42.659 --> 07:13:45.360
she left the empty husk of the cocoon

07:13:45.360 --> 07:13:45.779
behind her.

07:13:45.840 --> 07:13:50.639
Whoosh, she said, collapsing on her

07:13:50.639 --> 07:13:51.840
stomach on the warm rocks.

07:13:51.959 --> 07:13:55.259
Her wings unfolded gracefully from her

07:13:55.259 --> 07:13:58.200
back and spread out to dry, like

07:13:58.200 --> 07:14:00.479
cascading petals of green sunlight.

07:14:00.540 --> 07:14:01.860
They were beautiful.

07:14:01.919 --> 07:14:05.159
You did it, blue cheered.

07:14:05.220 --> 07:14:07.979
He lay down beside her and nudged her

07:14:07.979 --> 07:14:08.819
snout with his.

07:14:08.880 --> 07:14:11.159
Your wings are amazing.

07:14:11.220 --> 07:14:13.500
So amazing, Luna.

07:14:13.560 --> 07:14:16.619
His throat closed over everything else he

07:14:16.619 --> 07:14:17.220
wanted to say.

07:14:17.279 --> 07:14:19.919
She smiled sleepily at him.

07:14:19.979 --> 07:14:23.759
Then why are you crying, little brother?

07:14:23.880 --> 07:14:24.659
she asked.

07:14:24.720 --> 07:14:27.479
Overwhelmed by my gloriousness?

07:14:27.599 --> 07:14:31.860
Pretty much, he said with a sniffly

07:14:31.860 --> 07:14:32.099
laugh.

07:14:32.220 --> 07:14:34.139
I missed you so much.

07:14:34.200 --> 07:14:39.119
Aw, she said, covering one of his talons

07:14:39.119 --> 07:14:39.720
with hers.

07:14:39.779 --> 07:14:42.180
It was only 5 days, silly.

07:14:42.299 --> 07:14:47.520
Yeah, but they were really stressful days

07:14:47.520 --> 07:14:48.720
he said.

07:14:48.720 --> 07:14:52.259
She blinked at him for a long moment, and

07:14:52.259 --> 07:14:54.419
then her gaze slowly shifted to the cave

07:14:54.419 --> 07:14:57.060
walls behind him, and the glow of the

07:14:57.060 --> 07:14:59.340
light from all the flame silk cauldrons

07:14:59.340 --> 07:15:01.799
and the stranger watching them eagerly

07:15:01.799 --> 07:15:03.180
from extremely close by.

07:15:03.299 --> 07:15:06.540
She rolled her wrists in and stared at

07:15:06.540 --> 07:15:08.700
them, then sat up abruptly.

07:15:08.759 --> 07:15:13.919
Hi, said Admiral, oh wow, I can't believe

07:15:13.919 --> 07:15:14.639
this is happening.

07:15:14.700 --> 07:15:16.500
I'm so happy to meet you.

07:15:16.560 --> 07:15:18.959
Luna stared at him.

07:15:19.020 --> 07:15:22.799
Then at blue with an, explain this, face.

07:15:22.860 --> 07:15:26.159
This is Admiral, Blue said.

07:15:26.220 --> 07:15:27.479
Our dad.

07:15:27.540 --> 07:15:30.119
He felt a twinge of pain in his own

07:15:30.119 --> 07:15:31.860
wrists, and glanced down.

07:15:31.919 --> 07:15:33.659
Uh-oh.

07:15:33.720 --> 07:15:37.080
Where those pinpricks of gold, lava under

07:15:37.080 --> 07:15:37.680
his scales?

07:15:37.740 --> 07:15:41.099
This is the greatest day of my life

07:15:41.099 --> 07:15:44.459
Admiral declared, with a most enormous

07:15:44.459 --> 07:15:45.419
grin on his face.

07:15:45.479 --> 07:15:48.240
Enough smiling.

07:15:48.299 --> 07:15:52.080
Time to spin, Sandfly said, stomping up

07:15:52.080 --> 07:15:53.279
and poking him in the shoulder.

07:15:53.340 --> 07:15:57.720
I give them 3 days until they figure out

07:15:57.720 --> 07:15:59.700
that you're the most annoying dragon in

07:15:59.700 --> 07:15:59.939
here.

07:16:00.000 --> 07:16:02.459
Fritillery shouted from across the

07:16:02.459 --> 07:16:02.880
cavern.

07:16:02.939 --> 07:16:06.360
Luna glanced around frantically, her

07:16:06.360 --> 07:16:07.200
wings fluttering.

07:16:07.259 --> 07:16:10.139
She leaned forward and seized Blue's

07:16:10.139 --> 07:16:11.040
talons between hers.

07:16:11.159 --> 07:16:12.779
Blue.

07:16:12.840 --> 07:16:13.680
She said.

07:16:13.740 --> 07:16:15.240
Where are we?

07:16:15.299 --> 07:16:20.040
Chapter 24.

07:16:20.279 --> 07:16:26.520
So, sore tail, might be nearby, Blue said

07:16:26.520 --> 07:16:28.860
or might have been captured.

07:16:28.919 --> 07:16:33.119
This is somehow too much information, and

07:16:33.119 --> 07:16:35.400
absolutely not enough information at the

07:16:35.400 --> 07:16:35.880
same time.

07:16:35.939 --> 07:16:38.819
Luna said, rubbing her forehead.

07:16:38.880 --> 07:16:41.220
Tangerine?

07:16:41.279 --> 07:16:42.419
Admiral offered.

07:16:42.479 --> 07:16:46.380
Thanks, she said, taking it and peeling

07:16:46.380 --> 07:16:46.860
it quickly.

07:16:46.979 --> 07:16:50.279
She'd been eating nonstop while Blue told

07:16:50.279 --> 07:16:51.419
her the whole story.

07:16:51.479 --> 07:16:54.900
Admiral, it turned out, had a stash of

07:16:54.900 --> 07:16:57.360
food tucked away in his nest, and he was

07:16:57.360 --> 07:16:59.819
surprisingly adept at tossing fruit while

07:16:59.819 --> 07:17:01.560
spinning flame silk at the same time.

07:17:01.619 --> 07:17:05.040
But the queen hasn't come down to yell at

07:17:05.040 --> 07:17:05.520
you or anything?

07:17:05.580 --> 07:17:07.020
Luna asked.

07:17:07.080 --> 07:17:09.360
No, Blue said.

07:17:09.419 --> 07:17:12.360
I really thought she would, or that I'd

07:17:12.360 --> 07:17:13.919
get dragged into her throne room and

07:17:13.919 --> 07:17:14.459
punished.

07:17:14.520 --> 07:17:15.959
But this seems to be it.

07:17:16.020 --> 07:17:19.740
She just had me thrown in here.

07:17:19.799 --> 07:17:23.819
Like a lost thing that she found and put

07:17:23.819 --> 07:17:24.599
back in its place.

07:17:24.659 --> 07:17:26.880
Luna said grumpily.

07:17:26.939 --> 07:17:29.819
I mean, I'm glad you weren't punished

07:17:29.819 --> 07:17:30.119
Blue.

07:17:30.180 --> 07:17:32.939
But the queen uses punishment mostly to

07:17:32.939 --> 07:17:34.500
send a message to the rest of her

07:17:34.500 --> 07:17:34.979
subjects.

07:17:35.099 --> 07:17:37.979
So I'm guessing she didn't want to draw

07:17:37.979 --> 07:17:40.020
attention to the fact that she has flame

07:17:40.020 --> 07:17:43.380
silks, or that a little wingless silk

07:17:43.380 --> 07:17:45.180
wing was able to hide from her for so

07:17:45.180 --> 07:17:45.659
long.

07:17:45.720 --> 07:17:49.619
That was only because I met cricket, Blue

07:17:49.619 --> 07:17:49.979
said.

07:17:50.040 --> 07:17:52.380
She's the one who figured out how to hide

07:17:52.380 --> 07:17:52.740
me.

07:17:52.799 --> 07:17:55.380
Luna rolled her eyes at him

07:17:55.380 --> 07:17:56.099
affectionately.

07:17:56.159 --> 07:18:00.180
Trust you to find the one good hive wing

07:18:00.180 --> 07:18:01.200
in the entire tribe.

07:18:01.259 --> 07:18:03.900
Now, I'll never be able to convince you

07:18:03.900 --> 07:18:05.040
that they're all evil.

07:18:05.099 --> 07:18:08.099
Because they're not, he protested.

07:18:08.159 --> 07:18:10.979
There must be others as nice as cricket.

07:18:11.040 --> 07:18:15.240
Maybe not as smart, or pretty, or funny

07:18:15.240 --> 07:18:18.479
or kind, but probably a few that are

07:18:18.479 --> 07:18:18.779
nice.

07:18:18.840 --> 07:18:20.880
Luna shook her head.

07:18:20.939 --> 07:18:22.319
I doubt it.

07:18:22.380 --> 07:18:24.959
But even if they are, they never get a

07:18:24.959 --> 07:18:27.240
chance to be, because of the queen's

07:18:27.240 --> 07:18:28.080
brainwashing.

07:18:28.200 --> 07:18:30.900
She shuddered from antennae to tail.

07:18:30.959 --> 07:18:34.080
That mind control thing sounds so

07:18:34.080 --> 07:18:35.159
creepy.

07:18:35.220 --> 07:18:37.979
It is, Blue said.

07:18:38.040 --> 07:18:40.380
I hope IO's all right.

07:18:40.439 --> 07:18:41.700
Me too.

07:18:41.759 --> 07:18:43.979
I hope she found the chrysalis.

07:18:44.040 --> 07:18:47.279
Luna, did you know about the chrysalis?

07:18:47.400 --> 07:18:48.900
A little bit.

07:18:49.020 --> 07:18:52.560
Luna stood up, shaking out her wings and

07:18:52.560 --> 07:18:54.299
testing different positions she could

07:18:54.299 --> 07:18:54.900
hold them in.

07:18:54.959 --> 07:18:58.799
I knew Sortell and IO had just met them.

07:18:58.860 --> 07:19:01.139
I was hoping to join once I had my

07:19:01.139 --> 07:19:01.500
wings.

07:19:01.619 --> 07:19:04.500
I didn't quite figure on waking up in

07:19:04.500 --> 07:19:04.740
here.

07:19:04.799 --> 07:19:08.400
Blue winced, and she gave him a sharp

07:19:08.400 --> 07:19:08.700
look.

07:19:08.759 --> 07:19:11.040
Is your silk coming in?

07:19:11.159 --> 07:19:12.540
Does it feel hot?

07:19:12.599 --> 07:19:15.540
She took his talons and turned them over

07:19:15.540 --> 07:19:16.740
to study his wrists.

07:19:16.799 --> 07:19:19.259
It was hard to see if they were glowing

07:19:19.259 --> 07:19:21.240
with all the light from the other flame

07:19:21.240 --> 07:19:22.139
silk in the cave.

07:19:22.259 --> 07:19:25.860
I'm supposed to spin my cocoon tomorrow

07:19:25.860 --> 07:19:27.299
night, Blue said.

07:19:27.360 --> 07:19:29.639
I wish I didn't have to do it in here.

07:19:29.759 --> 07:19:32.279
He'd been nervous enough about his

07:19:32.279 --> 07:19:34.500
metamorphosis when he knew it would

07:19:34.500 --> 07:19:37.020
happen in a tranquil, peaceful safety of

07:19:37.020 --> 07:19:37.500
the cocoon.

07:19:37.560 --> 07:19:40.259
But it was much more unnerving to imagine

07:19:40.259 --> 07:19:43.080
spinning his silk here, in this too

07:19:43.080 --> 07:19:45.900
bright place, with its shouting dragons

07:19:45.900 --> 07:19:48.540
and stomping guards all staring at him.

07:19:48.599 --> 07:19:51.720
There must be a way out, Luna said.

07:19:51.779 --> 07:19:53.819
She looked up at the guards by the

07:19:53.819 --> 07:19:54.299
stairwell.

07:19:54.360 --> 07:19:56.700
How many guards do you think there are?

07:19:56.819 --> 07:19:59.459
Luna, Blue said.

07:19:59.580 --> 07:20:01.439
There's no way we can fight them.

07:20:01.500 --> 07:20:02.880
Just you and me?

07:20:02.939 --> 07:20:04.139
That's crazy.

07:20:04.200 --> 07:20:06.720
But now I can do this.

07:20:06.779 --> 07:20:08.040
She said.

07:20:08.099 --> 07:20:11.939
She held out one arm, and a flaming silk

07:20:11.939 --> 07:20:13.200
thread burst from her wrist.

07:20:13.259 --> 07:20:16.380
It hit one of Admiral's piles of letters

07:20:16.380 --> 07:20:18.180
and instantly set it ablaze.

07:20:18.240 --> 07:20:19.560
Ah!

07:20:19.619 --> 07:20:20.759
Admiral cried.

07:20:20.880 --> 07:20:23.220
He leaped over and knocked the burning

07:20:23.220 --> 07:20:25.619
pile away from the others, then stamped

07:20:25.619 --> 07:20:26.939
it out with his talons.

07:20:27.000 --> 07:20:28.919
When it was a pile of ashes on the

07:20:28.919 --> 07:20:29.279
rocks.

07:20:29.340 --> 07:20:32.340
He picked up the fiery strand of silk and

07:20:32.340 --> 07:20:33.599
brandished it at Luna.

07:20:33.659 --> 07:20:35.759
This is not a toy.

07:20:35.880 --> 07:20:37.139
Look what you did.

07:20:37.200 --> 07:20:39.720
Now, how will I remember what I've

07:20:39.720 --> 07:20:40.439
already written?

07:20:40.500 --> 07:20:42.779
The queen doesn't like repetition.

07:20:42.840 --> 07:20:44.040
This is terrible.

07:20:44.099 --> 07:20:46.439
You need to learn to be careful with your

07:20:46.439 --> 07:20:47.520
flame silk, young lady.

07:20:47.580 --> 07:20:49.020
Sorry.

07:20:49.080 --> 07:20:51.119
Luna said innocently.

07:20:51.180 --> 07:20:53.159
Blue blanked at Admiral.

07:20:53.279 --> 07:20:57.659
Dad, you're, you're holding the flame

07:20:57.659 --> 07:20:59.220
silk, and your talent.

07:20:59.279 --> 07:21:01.139
Why isn't it burning you?

07:21:01.259 --> 07:21:05.099
Admiral climbed back into his nest, and

07:21:05.099 --> 07:21:07.200
dropped Luna's flame silk into his own

07:21:07.200 --> 07:21:07.860
cauldron.

07:21:07.919 --> 07:21:10.740
It glowed a much brighter orange gold

07:21:10.740 --> 07:21:12.240
than what was already in there.

07:21:12.299 --> 07:21:16.259
Flame silk dragons can be burned by flame

07:21:16.259 --> 07:21:17.459
silk, he said.

07:21:17.520 --> 07:21:18.959
That would be absurd.

07:21:19.020 --> 07:21:21.900
Wow, Blue said.

07:21:21.959 --> 07:21:23.400
Wait.

07:21:23.459 --> 07:21:25.740
So if some already burned me.

07:21:25.860 --> 07:21:29.759
No, it will still burn you until you've

07:21:29.759 --> 07:21:31.619
gone through metamorphosis, whether

07:21:31.619 --> 07:21:33.479
you're going to be a flame silk or not.

07:21:33.540 --> 07:21:38.279
Admiral said, Luna, come here and let me

07:21:38.279 --> 07:21:39.720
show you the different kind you can

07:21:39.720 --> 07:21:39.959
make.

07:21:40.020 --> 07:21:42.900
Flame silk is a big responsibility.

07:21:42.959 --> 07:21:46.860
Luna rolled her eyes at blue, but she

07:21:46.860 --> 07:21:48.299
went over to their father and gave him

07:21:48.299 --> 07:21:49.139
her full attention.

07:21:49.200 --> 07:21:52.259
Blue side, rubbing his wrists.

07:21:52.380 --> 07:21:56.340
His wing buds were tingling too, in a way

07:21:56.340 --> 07:21:58.139
that was both exciting and

07:21:58.139 --> 07:21:59.099
uncomfortable.

07:21:59.159 --> 07:22:01.380
He wished he could go run through the

07:22:01.380 --> 07:22:01.860
savannah.

07:22:01.919 --> 07:22:05.520
Under the stars, just breathing air that

07:22:05.520 --> 07:22:08.340
wasn't thick and hot and overly stuffed

07:22:08.340 --> 07:22:09.000
with oranges.

07:22:09.060 --> 07:22:12.060
He scrambled down to the central floor of

07:22:12.060 --> 07:22:14.459
the cavern and made his way to the spot

07:22:14.459 --> 07:22:16.979
under the staircase ledge, where he'd

07:22:16.979 --> 07:22:18.540
found the hole earlier that day.

07:22:18.599 --> 07:22:21.180
He guessed it was close to the middle of

07:22:21.180 --> 07:22:21.779
the night.

07:22:21.840 --> 07:22:24.959
Only 2 guards were on the stairs, and the

07:22:24.959 --> 07:22:27.720
regular silkwing workers were gone, to a

07:22:27.720 --> 07:22:29.340
cramped apartment home in one of the

07:22:29.340 --> 07:22:31.500
warehouses, according to Admiral.

07:22:31.560 --> 07:22:34.200
Most of the flame silks were asleep

07:22:34.200 --> 07:22:37.860
Danaid, Admiral, and Fritillery were the

07:22:37.860 --> 07:22:40.380
only ones awake, pouring silk into their

07:22:40.380 --> 07:22:41.340
cauldrons.

07:22:41.400 --> 07:22:44.939
Blue could feel Danaid's eyes on him as

07:22:44.939 --> 07:22:45.959
he poked through the rocks.

07:22:46.020 --> 07:22:48.479
He was out of sight of the staircase

07:22:48.479 --> 07:22:49.200
guards here.

07:22:49.259 --> 07:22:51.419
But the ones up above the glass could

07:22:51.419 --> 07:22:51.959
still see him.

07:22:52.020 --> 07:22:55.439
He glanced up to confirm this, and the

07:22:55.439 --> 07:22:57.720
glow of at least 6 pairs of eyes stared

07:22:57.720 --> 07:22:57.959
back.

07:22:58.020 --> 07:23:01.139
So even if he could chisel through the

07:23:01.139 --> 07:23:04.080
wall, he'd never get a chance to, there

07:23:04.080 --> 07:23:06.060
was no way to do anything surreptitious

07:23:06.060 --> 07:23:06.360
in here.

07:23:06.419 --> 07:23:09.720
He found the hole again and slipped his

07:23:09.720 --> 07:23:12.060
claws through, reaching for that feeling

07:23:12.060 --> 07:23:12.659
of freedom.

07:23:12.720 --> 07:23:15.659
The dark open space on the other side

07:23:15.659 --> 07:23:18.599
that might lead anywhere, to the outside

07:23:18.599 --> 07:23:21.779
world, to the sky and all its stars.

07:23:21.840 --> 07:23:25.919
On the other side of the wall, unseen

07:23:25.919 --> 07:23:28.200
something slipped gently between his

07:23:28.200 --> 07:23:29.759
claws and squeezed.

07:23:29.880 --> 07:23:35.220
Blue came this close to screaming his

07:23:35.220 --> 07:23:35.580
head off.

07:23:35.639 --> 07:23:38.580
But at the same moment, he heard someone

07:23:38.580 --> 07:23:40.439
whisper, shh.

07:23:40.500 --> 07:23:43.020
He bit down hard on his tongue and

07:23:43.020 --> 07:23:43.259
froze.

07:23:43.380 --> 07:23:46.319
Blue, the voice whispered.

07:23:46.319 --> 07:23:48.840
He tilted his head closer to the wall.

07:23:48.900 --> 07:23:50.759
Cricket?

07:23:50.819 --> 07:23:51.900
Shh.

07:23:51.959 --> 07:23:53.700
Yes, it's me.

07:23:53.819 --> 07:23:57.779
And me, someone else whispered fiercely.

07:23:57.840 --> 07:24:00.119
Is Luna all right?

07:24:00.180 --> 07:24:01.979
Whispered a 3rd voice.

07:24:02.099 --> 07:24:03.299
Sore tail.

07:24:03.360 --> 07:24:05.759
She's amazing.

07:24:05.880 --> 07:24:07.259
Blue said softly.

07:24:07.319 --> 07:24:11.159
I can't believe you're all, Blue, don't

07:24:11.159 --> 07:24:12.959
talk, Cricket interrupted.

07:24:13.020 --> 07:24:15.119
They're watching you very closely.

07:24:15.240 --> 07:24:18.599
It's suspicious enough that you're over

07:24:18.599 --> 07:24:19.919
here with your arm in a hole.

07:24:19.979 --> 07:24:22.860
If you keep talking to the wall, someone's

07:24:22.860 --> 07:24:23.700
going to investigate.

07:24:23.819 --> 07:24:26.939
She squeezed his claws again and let go.

07:24:27.000 --> 07:24:30.119
Reluctantly he pulled his talon back

07:24:30.119 --> 07:24:33.659
although it felt emptier than ever now, as

07:24:33.659 --> 07:24:36.119
though it had found its missing half, and

07:24:36.119 --> 07:24:37.200
now it had to be alone again.

07:24:37.319 --> 07:24:40.380
He wanted to reach for her once more.

07:24:40.439 --> 07:24:43.380
To be sure she was real, and really there

07:24:43.380 --> 07:24:44.759
and really alive.

07:24:44.819 --> 07:24:47.580
But he could see how that might look a

07:24:47.580 --> 07:24:48.119
bit strange.

07:24:48.240 --> 07:24:50.819
Danaid was pretending to look at her

07:24:50.819 --> 07:24:51.240
wrists.

07:24:51.360 --> 07:24:53.880
But she was leaning so far toward him

07:24:53.880 --> 07:24:56.099
that she was in danger of toppling out of

07:24:56.099 --> 07:24:56.459
her nest.

07:24:56.520 --> 07:25:00.060
The eyes up above, stared and stared.

07:25:00.119 --> 07:25:02.700
He wasn't sure they ever blinked.

07:25:02.759 --> 07:25:05.939
Was that a hive wing power some guards

07:25:05.939 --> 07:25:06.360
had?

07:25:06.419 --> 07:25:08.040
No need for eyelids.

07:25:08.159 --> 07:25:11.159
He sat down and started building a small

07:25:11.159 --> 07:25:13.200
pyramid of pebbles, trying to look

07:25:13.200 --> 07:25:13.740
harmless.

07:25:13.799 --> 07:25:16.139
That was something he was usually pretty

07:25:16.139 --> 07:25:16.619
good at.

07:25:16.680 --> 07:25:19.439
The leaf wings were trying to build a

07:25:19.439 --> 07:25:22.799
tunnel, Cricket said softly, to get into

07:25:22.799 --> 07:25:23.819
the hive from below.

07:25:23.880 --> 07:25:26.939
That's how they found this place, by

07:25:26.939 --> 07:25:28.619
accident, as they were digging

07:25:28.619 --> 07:25:28.979
underneath.

07:25:29.040 --> 07:25:30.840
Did you find your father?

07:25:30.900 --> 07:25:33.599
Sorry, I know you can't answer.

07:25:33.659 --> 07:25:36.240
But Luna came out of her cocoon?

07:25:36.299 --> 07:25:38.639
Are there a lot of blame silks down

07:25:38.639 --> 07:25:38.819
here?

07:25:38.880 --> 07:25:41.340
Oh, you can't answer that either?

07:25:41.400 --> 07:25:44.400
I can't believe how big this cave is.

07:25:44.459 --> 07:25:48.000
Not big enough, if you're trapped in it

07:25:48.000 --> 07:25:48.779
for your entire life.

07:25:48.840 --> 07:25:50.279
Blue thought.

07:25:50.340 --> 07:25:53.400
He thought he should be more horrified by

07:25:53.400 --> 07:25:55.740
the idea of leaf wings tunneling into the

07:25:55.740 --> 07:25:56.099
hives.

07:25:56.220 --> 07:25:59.459
Six days ago, the image of leaf wings

07:25:59.459 --> 07:26:01.139
suddenly bursting out of the ground

07:26:01.139 --> 07:26:03.900
inside his city, would have been the most

07:26:03.900 --> 07:26:05.759
terrifying thing he could possibly

07:26:05.759 --> 07:26:06.119
imagine.

07:26:06.180 --> 07:26:09.779
But he'd met a few other, more terrifying

07:26:09.779 --> 07:26:10.740
things since then.

07:26:10.799 --> 07:26:14.099
Listen, Sundew hissed.

07:26:14.159 --> 07:26:16.139
Cricket wants to get you out of there.

07:26:16.200 --> 07:26:20.159
I do too, Sortell chimed in.

07:26:20.220 --> 07:26:22.380
Right, but I don't care what he thinks.

07:26:22.500 --> 07:26:24.240
Sundew clarified.

07:26:24.299 --> 07:26:27.419
Cricket nearly died with me though, so I

07:26:27.419 --> 07:26:28.860
kind of feel like I owe you guys one.

07:26:28.919 --> 07:26:31.259
My parents have more important things to

07:26:31.259 --> 07:26:31.619
do.

07:26:31.740 --> 07:26:33.959
But I might be able to come up with a

07:26:33.959 --> 07:26:34.200
plan.

07:26:34.259 --> 07:26:36.299
Can you be ready tomorrow night?

07:26:36.360 --> 07:26:38.880
Blue's heart sank.

07:26:38.939 --> 07:26:41.220
He shook his head and shifted himself

07:26:41.220 --> 07:26:43.860
around the rock pyramid, pretending to

07:26:43.860 --> 07:26:45.959
reach for another stone, but really

07:26:45.959 --> 07:26:48.060
angling so whoever was peering through

07:26:48.060 --> 07:26:49.740
the hole could see his wing buds.

07:26:49.799 --> 07:26:52.619
He heard cricket let out a soft gasp.

07:26:52.740 --> 07:26:56.639
He's about to go into metamorphosis, she

07:26:56.639 --> 07:26:58.919
whispered to sundo, but you have to get

07:26:58.919 --> 07:27:00.360
him out now, tonight.

07:27:00.479 --> 07:27:04.500
Oh, rotten bark beetles, Sundew

07:27:04.500 --> 07:27:05.040
grumbled.

07:27:05.099 --> 07:27:06.180
Fine.

07:27:06.240 --> 07:27:07.560
I'll do it the messy way.

07:27:07.619 --> 07:27:08.520
Blue.

07:27:08.580 --> 07:27:11.099
Can you see a crack in the wall, near the

07:27:11.099 --> 07:27:13.439
bottom, that arches around in a half

07:27:13.439 --> 07:27:14.099
circle?

07:27:14.159 --> 07:27:16.979
Blue glanced casually at the wall?

07:27:17.099 --> 07:27:19.500
He spotted what she meant immediately.

07:27:19.560 --> 07:27:21.900
It looked like a sun setting.

07:27:21.959 --> 07:27:24.540
Can you and Luna fit through there?

07:27:24.599 --> 07:27:26.520
If I can knock out the chunk of rock

07:27:26.520 --> 07:27:27.419
underneath the crack?

07:27:27.540 --> 07:27:29.700
He thought so.

07:27:29.819 --> 07:27:32.099
Although we hadn't spent enough time with

07:27:32.099 --> 07:27:34.319
Luna's wings yet to be sure how big they

07:27:34.319 --> 07:27:34.560
were.

07:27:34.619 --> 07:27:37.319
He was a little more worried about how to

07:27:37.319 --> 07:27:39.900
fit Admiral through, but his father was

07:27:39.900 --> 07:27:40.860
quite skinny.

07:27:40.919 --> 07:27:42.540
He'd just have to squish.

07:27:42.599 --> 07:27:46.380
Blue gave a very slight nod, scattering

07:27:46.380 --> 07:27:47.759
his pebbles as though he'd gotten

07:27:47.759 --> 07:27:49.080
frustrated with his construction.

07:27:49.200 --> 07:27:50.880
Great.

07:27:50.939 --> 07:27:51.900
Go get her.

07:27:51.959 --> 07:27:53.700
And everyone be ready to run.

07:27:53.759 --> 07:27:55.740
Good luck, Blue.

07:27:55.799 --> 07:27:57.119
Cricket whispered.

07:27:57.180 --> 07:27:59.159
Tell Luna I'm here.

07:27:59.220 --> 07:28:02.220
Swordell interjected, very heroically.

07:28:02.279 --> 07:28:05.220
You sat around in a greenhouse and then

07:28:05.220 --> 07:28:06.479
followed me into a tunnel.

07:28:06.599 --> 07:28:08.159
Sundu observed.

07:28:08.220 --> 07:28:10.979
I'm not sure you qualify for a statue in

07:28:10.979 --> 07:28:11.939
your honor just yet.

07:28:12.060 --> 07:28:13.740
Shh.

07:28:13.799 --> 07:28:15.540
Cricket scolded both of them.

07:28:15.599 --> 07:28:18.419
Blue picked up a pebble and pretended to

07:28:18.419 --> 07:28:21.060
peer at it closely, then set it down and

07:28:21.060 --> 07:28:22.259
headed back over to Luna.

07:28:22.380 --> 07:28:24.720
Everything all right?

07:28:24.779 --> 07:28:27.119
Dane had asked as he went by.

07:28:27.180 --> 07:28:29.459
She leaned her elbows on the edge of her

07:28:29.459 --> 07:28:31.919
nest, watching him with wide eyed

07:28:31.919 --> 07:28:32.340
interest.

07:28:32.400 --> 07:28:35.220
Oh, yes, Blue said.

07:28:35.279 --> 07:28:37.020
Just some pretty rocks.

07:28:37.080 --> 07:28:38.459
I think my sister would like.

07:28:38.520 --> 07:28:41.340
You will introduce her to me.

07:28:41.400 --> 07:28:42.599
Won't you?

07:28:42.659 --> 07:28:43.919
Danaid said.

07:28:43.979 --> 07:28:46.560
And her voice was an odd mixture of pushy

07:28:46.560 --> 07:28:47.639
and wistful.

07:28:47.700 --> 07:28:50.220
No matter what your dad says.

07:28:50.340 --> 07:28:54.540
Of course, Blue said. feeling guilty.

07:28:54.659 --> 07:28:57.299
He couldn't stay here just to keep these

07:28:57.299 --> 07:28:58.919
lonely flame silks company.

07:28:58.979 --> 07:29:01.799
But he was sorry that escaping with Luna

07:29:01.799 --> 07:29:03.720
meant abandoning them to their endless

07:29:03.720 --> 07:29:04.259
quarrels.

07:29:04.380 --> 07:29:06.779
Is there any way to bring them along?

07:29:06.900 --> 07:29:08.580
Could they come with us?

07:29:08.639 --> 07:29:11.639
He didn't know how to alert the other

07:29:11.639 --> 07:29:13.439
flame silks without attracting the

07:29:13.439 --> 07:29:15.840
attention of the guards, and given what

07:29:15.840 --> 07:29:18.419
he knew about them so far, he was afraid

07:29:18.419 --> 07:29:20.759
even the idea of an escape plan would

07:29:20.759 --> 07:29:22.740
somehow trigger a screaming match that

07:29:22.740 --> 07:29:23.759
would give everything away.

07:29:23.819 --> 07:29:27.479
He hurried back to Luna, worrying over

07:29:27.479 --> 07:29:28.500
the problem in his head.

07:29:28.560 --> 07:29:30.720
Rescuing her was everything.

07:29:30.779 --> 07:29:33.659
It was the whole reason he'd broken so

07:29:33.659 --> 07:29:35.759
many rules and gotten in so much

07:29:35.759 --> 07:29:36.180
trouble.

07:29:36.240 --> 07:29:39.479
It was the most important thing, getting

07:29:39.479 --> 07:29:40.200
her out of here.

07:29:40.259 --> 07:29:43.259
But he wished there was a way to rescue

07:29:43.259 --> 07:29:43.860
all of them.

07:29:43.919 --> 07:29:46.619
Luna sat up as he approached.

07:29:46.680 --> 07:29:49.380
And her eyes gleamed when she saw the

07:29:49.380 --> 07:29:50.400
expression on his face.

07:29:50.459 --> 07:29:53.520
She'd always been able to read him, ever

07:29:53.520 --> 07:29:55.259
since they 1st hatched.

07:29:55.319 --> 07:29:58.680
You've found a way out, she whispered

07:29:58.680 --> 07:29:59.400
excitedly.

07:29:59.459 --> 07:30:01.319
Our friends are here.

07:30:01.380 --> 07:30:02.939
He whispered back.

07:30:03.000 --> 07:30:04.319
Then let's go.

07:30:04.439 --> 07:30:07.200
She jumped to her feet and looked up at

07:30:07.200 --> 07:30:07.680
Admiral.

07:30:07.740 --> 07:30:09.060
Hmm?

07:30:09.119 --> 07:30:11.400
He said, blinking down at them.

07:30:11.459 --> 07:30:14.520
I was just composing another letter in my

07:30:14.520 --> 07:30:16.799
head, to thank the queen for bringing you

07:30:16.799 --> 07:30:17.340
here, of course.

07:30:17.400 --> 07:30:20.159
My letters can't all be complaints, you

07:30:20.159 --> 07:30:20.340
know.

07:30:20.459 --> 07:30:21.779
Oh, no.

07:30:21.900 --> 07:30:22.860
That wouldn't do.

07:30:22.919 --> 07:30:25.979
I must also show my gratitude when she is

07:30:25.979 --> 07:30:26.880
so generous with us.

07:30:26.939 --> 07:30:29.819
My thank you letter in regards to the

07:30:29.819 --> 07:30:31.919
tangerines was a work of art.

07:30:31.979 --> 07:30:35.099
He shot a regretful look at the pile of

07:30:35.099 --> 07:30:37.619
ashes, as though wondering how many more

07:30:37.619 --> 07:30:40.020
masterpieces had been lost to Luna's

07:30:40.020 --> 07:30:43.919
flame silk, Father, Blue said softly.

07:30:43.979 --> 07:30:46.979
We have a way out of here, but we have to

07:30:46.979 --> 07:30:47.580
go right now.

07:30:47.639 --> 07:30:49.740
Go?

07:30:49.799 --> 07:30:51.060
Admiral echoed.

07:30:51.119 --> 07:30:52.259
What do you mean?

07:30:52.319 --> 07:30:55.740
We are going to escape, Luna said.

07:30:55.799 --> 07:30:57.060
All 3 of us.

07:30:57.119 --> 07:30:59.639
Come on, quick, while the guards are

07:30:59.639 --> 07:31:00.540
looking sleepy.

07:31:00.599 --> 07:31:03.299
But I'm in the middle of my spinning

07:31:03.299 --> 07:31:03.900
rotation.

07:31:03.959 --> 07:31:06.959
Admiral said, and I haven't made nearly

07:31:06.959 --> 07:31:07.860
enough for the quota.

07:31:07.919 --> 07:31:10.139
You're going to have to make it up with

07:31:10.139 --> 07:31:11.880
all your bright, lovely silk.

07:31:12.119 --> 07:31:13.799
They'll probably give you a turn in the

07:31:13.799 --> 07:31:15.900
morning, once you've rested a bit.

07:31:15.959 --> 07:31:18.659
No, Luna said firmly.

07:31:18.720 --> 07:31:21.240
I'm not giving anyone my bright, lovely

07:31:21.240 --> 07:31:21.840
silk.

07:31:21.959 --> 07:31:24.479
It's mine, and I'm escaping with Blue

07:31:24.479 --> 07:31:25.020
right now.

07:31:25.080 --> 07:31:28.799
Admiral Twitched, as though the word

07:31:28.799 --> 07:31:31.380
escape was finally crawling into his

07:31:31.380 --> 07:31:31.560
ears.

07:31:31.680 --> 07:31:34.799
No, no, he said.

07:31:34.860 --> 07:31:36.720
The hives need our silk.

07:31:36.840 --> 07:31:38.939
We're providing a great service.

07:31:39.000 --> 07:31:40.020
We're very important.

07:31:40.080 --> 07:31:41.880
You're very important.

07:31:41.939 --> 07:31:43.319
You can't.

07:31:43.680 --> 07:31:45.479
You can't leave.

07:31:45.599 --> 07:31:47.700
What are you even talking about?

07:31:47.759 --> 07:31:49.860
We're not allowed to leave.

07:31:49.919 --> 07:31:51.659
That rule is pretty clear.

07:31:51.720 --> 07:31:55.919
Come with us, please, Blue bagged.

07:31:55.979 --> 07:31:58.439
This is no way to live, Father.

07:31:58.500 --> 07:32:00.900
We could be together and free.

07:32:00.959 --> 07:32:02.220
Out there.

07:32:02.279 --> 07:32:04.020
Out where?

07:32:04.080 --> 07:32:05.819
Admiral scoffed.

07:32:05.880 --> 07:32:07.799
There's nowhere the queen doesn't

07:32:07.799 --> 07:32:08.099
control.

07:32:08.159 --> 07:32:10.020
No, no.

07:32:10.080 --> 07:32:12.479
We mustn't anger her with ungrateful

07:32:12.479 --> 07:32:13.979
stunts like escape attempts.

07:32:14.040 --> 07:32:14.939
Oh, dear.

07:32:15.000 --> 07:32:17.759
Oh dear, you'll get us all in trouble.

07:32:17.819 --> 07:32:19.200
It'll make everything worse.

07:32:19.259 --> 07:32:22.259
How could it be worse than this?

07:32:22.319 --> 07:32:23.520
Luna asked.

07:32:23.580 --> 07:32:26.520
In the beginning, there were chains

07:32:26.520 --> 07:32:29.279
Admiral said, on our ankles.

07:32:29.340 --> 07:32:31.500
I was the one who got rid of those.

07:32:31.560 --> 07:32:35.099
It only took me about 4 years and 200 or

07:32:35.099 --> 07:32:37.740
so letters, but I finally convinced her

07:32:37.740 --> 07:32:40.139
we could be trusted without them, and now

07:32:40.139 --> 07:32:41.459
you want to break that trust?

07:32:41.520 --> 07:32:45.720
This is not a mutual relationship, Luna

07:32:45.720 --> 07:32:46.020
said.

07:32:46.080 --> 07:32:48.060
The queen is using you.

07:32:48.119 --> 07:32:50.759
She's giving you next to nothing, and

07:32:50.759 --> 07:32:52.319
you're letting her walk all over you

07:32:52.319 --> 07:32:53.459
instead of fighting back.

07:32:53.520 --> 07:32:55.799
We're not going to be a part of that.

07:32:55.860 --> 07:32:57.659
She turned to Blue.

07:32:57.720 --> 07:32:59.880
I don't think this is going to work.

07:33:00.000 --> 07:33:01.380
We have to go without him.

07:33:01.439 --> 07:33:05.639
Oh no, Admiral cried.

07:33:05.700 --> 07:33:06.720
You can't.

07:33:06.779 --> 07:33:09.180
You'll undo all the progress I've made

07:33:09.180 --> 07:33:09.779
with a queen.

07:33:09.840 --> 07:33:12.900
We have rules for a reason, you know, and

07:33:12.900 --> 07:33:14.159
she'll be so disappointed.

07:33:14.279 --> 07:33:16.680
So escape with us.

07:33:16.740 --> 07:33:18.779
Blue couldn't give up.

07:33:18.840 --> 07:33:21.419
He couldn't just leave his father here.

07:33:21.479 --> 07:33:25.200
Father, you don't have to follow rules

07:33:25.200 --> 07:33:27.720
that are unjust, and you don't have to do

07:33:27.720 --> 07:33:28.919
everything the queen says.

07:33:28.979 --> 07:33:31.799
Don't you feel like there are rules in

07:33:31.799 --> 07:33:33.599
your heart that are more important?

07:33:33.659 --> 07:33:36.900
About helping other dragons and standing

07:33:36.900 --> 07:33:39.119
up for anyone who's being treated badly

07:33:39.119 --> 07:33:42.659
and loving whoever you want, and choosing

07:33:42.659 --> 07:33:44.939
to live your life in your own kind

07:33:44.939 --> 07:33:45.720
peaceful way.

07:33:45.779 --> 07:33:49.560
He glanced over and saw Luna staring at

07:33:49.560 --> 07:33:50.220
him in surprise.

07:33:50.279 --> 07:33:53.159
She reached out with one wing and pulled

07:33:53.159 --> 07:33:53.759
him into a hug.

07:33:53.880 --> 07:33:56.459
Wow, she said.

07:33:56.520 --> 07:33:59.459
It really was a long 5 days, wasn't it?

07:33:59.580 --> 07:34:03.060
Well, I just understood it.

07:34:03.119 --> 07:34:06.659
Finally, he said, that there are dragons

07:34:06.659 --> 07:34:09.180
who aren't safe, and dragons, I could

07:34:09.180 --> 07:34:09.479
help.

07:34:09.540 --> 07:34:12.720
And being a good little silk wing who

07:34:12.720 --> 07:34:15.540
follows the rules was making my life easy

07:34:15.540 --> 07:34:18.360
but also helping to keep a bad system in

07:34:18.360 --> 07:34:18.659
place.

07:34:18.720 --> 07:34:21.840
I didn't know before how bad it was for

07:34:21.840 --> 07:34:22.860
so many dragons.

07:34:22.919 --> 07:34:26.040
Like you, Father, like all the flame

07:34:26.040 --> 07:34:26.759
silks in here.

07:34:26.880 --> 07:34:29.040
This isn't right.

07:34:29.099 --> 07:34:31.860
And you shouldn't want it for your

07:34:31.860 --> 07:34:33.360
children, Luna said.

07:34:33.419 --> 07:34:36.360
If you want to stay, that's fine, but

07:34:36.360 --> 07:34:36.840
we're going.

07:34:36.900 --> 07:34:39.720
She turned blue toward the center of the

07:34:39.720 --> 07:34:39.959
cave.

07:34:40.020 --> 07:34:43.259
No, Admiral said.

07:34:43.319 --> 07:34:44.700
No, no, it's wrong.

07:34:44.819 --> 07:34:46.259
I can't let you do this.

07:34:46.319 --> 07:34:47.459
Guards.

07:34:47.520 --> 07:34:49.860
Blue inhaled sharply.

07:34:49.919 --> 07:34:52.560
The hive wings by the staircase whipped

07:34:52.560 --> 07:34:53.520
their heads toward them.

07:34:53.580 --> 07:34:56.580
His father was sabotaging their escape

07:34:56.580 --> 07:34:58.740
turning them in to keep them trapped

07:34:58.740 --> 07:34:58.979
here.

07:34:59.040 --> 07:35:01.919
They had to run, but their escape route

07:35:01.919 --> 07:35:04.319
looked a whole continent away, and it

07:35:04.319 --> 07:35:05.159
wasn't even open yet.

07:35:05.279 --> 07:35:06.959
Guards!

07:35:07.080 --> 07:35:08.220
Admiral bellowed.

07:35:08.279 --> 07:35:08.939
Listen.

07:35:09.060 --> 07:35:11.459
Stop annoying the guards.

07:35:11.580 --> 07:35:14.459
The Naiad shouted at Admiral. interrupting

07:35:14.459 --> 07:35:14.639
him.

07:35:14.759 --> 07:35:16.979
They don't want to hear your thoughts on

07:35:16.979 --> 07:35:19.259
potassium at this hour, or ever.

07:35:19.319 --> 07:35:22.799
It's not that, Admiral yelled back

07:35:22.799 --> 07:35:25.560
although my thoughts on potassium are

07:35:25.560 --> 07:35:27.299
very well researched and relevant.

07:35:27.360 --> 07:35:31.439
But hey, guards, guards, my dragonettes

07:35:31.439 --> 07:35:33.959
your brains are a pile of bananas.

07:35:34.080 --> 07:35:36.240
Fritillery hollered from his perch.

07:35:36.299 --> 07:35:38.340
Never one to miss out on a fight.

07:35:38.400 --> 07:35:40.799
Your dragonettes are boring.

07:35:40.919 --> 07:35:43.020
They are not.

07:35:43.139 --> 07:35:46.380
Then Ad and Admiral roared in unison.

07:35:46.439 --> 07:35:49.799
I think they're charming, then I had

07:35:49.799 --> 07:35:50.159
yelled.

07:35:50.220 --> 07:35:53.040
You don't even know them, Admiral

07:35:53.040 --> 07:35:53.459
shouted.

07:35:53.520 --> 07:35:56.220
They're my dragonettes, and they're

07:35:56.220 --> 07:35:57.900
fascinating, but they're...

07:35:57.900 --> 07:36:00.479
Well, then, they're the opposite of you.

07:36:00.540 --> 07:36:02.220
Then they had bellowed.

07:36:02.279 --> 07:36:04.319
What is happening?

07:36:04.380 --> 07:36:07.439
Luna said to Blue, covering her ears?

07:36:07.500 --> 07:36:09.840
There was something about the sparkle in

07:36:09.840 --> 07:36:10.919
Danaid's eyes.

07:36:10.979 --> 07:36:13.560
Blue wasn't sure if it was her usual

07:36:13.560 --> 07:36:16.380
spirited fury, or if maybe.

07:36:16.500 --> 07:36:20.040
I think Danaid might be trying to help us

07:36:20.040 --> 07:36:21.659
he said quietly.

07:36:21.720 --> 07:36:23.819
He glanced up at the guards.

07:36:23.939 --> 07:36:26.580
They were sitting down again, rolling

07:36:26.580 --> 07:36:28.200
their eyes at one another as though

07:36:28.200 --> 07:36:30.479
they'd heard fights like this a 1000000

07:36:30.479 --> 07:36:30.840
times.

07:36:30.959 --> 07:36:32.639
Follow me.

07:36:32.700 --> 07:36:34.619
Walk, don't run.

07:36:34.680 --> 07:36:35.880
Act casual.

07:36:35.939 --> 07:36:39.360
He climbed down through the stalagmites

07:36:39.360 --> 07:36:41.340
trying to quiet his thudding heart.

07:36:41.400 --> 07:36:43.439
Guards!

07:36:43.500 --> 07:36:45.119
Admiral yelled again.

07:36:45.180 --> 07:36:48.119
But as Blue had hoped, Admiral didn't

07:36:48.119 --> 07:36:49.139
jump up and chase them.

07:36:49.200 --> 07:36:51.540
He would have to stop his silk spinning

07:36:51.540 --> 07:36:54.060
to do so, and that was yet another rule

07:36:54.060 --> 07:36:54.959
he'd never break.

07:36:55.020 --> 07:36:57.720
Shut up.

07:36:57.779 --> 07:37:00.840
Pirate whined, sitting up and rubbing his

07:37:00.840 --> 07:37:01.439
eyes.

07:37:01.500 --> 07:37:05.340
Why are you making so much noise?

07:37:05.400 --> 07:37:06.240
It's the middle of the night.

07:37:06.299 --> 07:37:10.740
Yeah, some of us were sleeping.

07:37:10.799 --> 07:37:12.840
Whitesbeck shouted.

07:37:12.900 --> 07:37:15.240
You're not helping matters with your

07:37:15.240 --> 07:37:15.959
bellowing.

07:37:16.020 --> 07:37:18.659
Heliconian chimed in from the nest

07:37:18.659 --> 07:37:19.680
closest to him.

07:37:19.740 --> 07:37:22.380
Now all 10 of them were awake and

07:37:22.380 --> 07:37:22.919
shouting.

07:37:22.979 --> 07:37:24.840
It was perfect cover.

07:37:24.900 --> 07:37:27.659
The high wing guards looked like the last

07:37:27.659 --> 07:37:30.000
thing they wanted to do was come down and

07:37:30.000 --> 07:37:32.759
get involved in this, and no matter how

07:37:32.759 --> 07:37:35.279
much Admiral roared, they couldn't hear

07:37:35.279 --> 07:37:37.139
his accusations over the noise of

07:37:37.139 --> 07:37:37.619
everyone else.

07:37:37.680 --> 07:37:40.799
Blue paused at Danaid's nest.

07:37:40.860 --> 07:37:44.700
Thank you, he said, holding one talon up

07:37:44.700 --> 07:37:44.939
to her.

07:37:45.000 --> 07:37:47.700
She took it and squeezed it with a wink.

07:37:47.759 --> 07:37:49.080
Whatever I'm doing?

07:37:49.139 --> 07:37:50.400
It's great fun.

07:37:50.520 --> 07:37:53.580
This is Luna, he said.

07:37:53.639 --> 07:37:57.659
Luna, this is Danaid, who is definitely a

07:37:57.659 --> 07:37:58.860
dragon worth knowing.

07:37:58.979 --> 07:38:01.979
Danaid beamed over the edge of her nest

07:38:01.979 --> 07:38:02.819
at Luna.

07:38:02.880 --> 07:38:05.040
Nice to meet you, she said.

07:38:05.099 --> 07:38:06.779
Now, scoot.

07:38:06.840 --> 07:38:08.880
I can see something exciting is about to

07:38:08.880 --> 07:38:09.119
happen.

07:38:09.180 --> 07:38:13.080
She nodded over at the wall, and Blue

07:38:13.080 --> 07:38:15.479
realized that the crack looked wider than

07:38:15.479 --> 07:38:17.880
before, and some things seemed to be

07:38:17.880 --> 07:38:18.540
coming through it.

07:38:18.599 --> 07:38:21.779
You could come with us, he said.

07:38:21.840 --> 07:38:25.139
I'm not sure my old heart could stand

07:38:25.139 --> 07:38:27.299
running from my life, she said.

07:38:27.360 --> 07:38:30.479
But if you find a more sedate way to get

07:38:30.479 --> 07:38:31.020
us out of here.

07:38:31.080 --> 07:38:32.700
Come back for me.

07:38:32.759 --> 07:38:34.439
He nodded.

07:38:34.500 --> 07:38:35.880
I will try.

07:38:36.000 --> 07:38:37.500
I promise.

07:38:37.560 --> 07:38:40.020
She went back to shouting at the other

07:38:40.020 --> 07:38:42.419
flame silks as he and Luna moved away.

07:38:42.479 --> 07:38:45.840
It was funny to think of Danaid wanting

07:38:45.840 --> 07:38:48.360
anything sedate when she seemed so

07:38:48.360 --> 07:38:49.979
delighted in the middle of chaos.

07:38:50.099 --> 07:38:54.299
The stone gave a low crack as they

07:38:54.299 --> 07:38:56.880
crouched beside it, and Blue realized

07:38:56.880 --> 07:38:58.619
that it was being pushed out of the

07:38:58.619 --> 07:38:58.919
wall.

07:38:58.979 --> 07:39:00.959
By...

07:39:00.959 --> 07:39:03.000
Were those roots?

07:39:03.060 --> 07:39:05.880
He gingerly touched one of the thick

07:39:05.880 --> 07:39:07.919
brown fingers that were shoving their way

07:39:07.919 --> 07:39:08.700
through the crack.

07:39:08.759 --> 07:39:12.419
It felt like branches, woody and knobbly

07:39:12.419 --> 07:39:13.080
under his claws.

07:39:13.139 --> 07:39:16.020
Sundew was growing something.

07:39:16.080 --> 07:39:19.200
Somehow, faster than anything should be

07:39:19.200 --> 07:39:21.599
able to grow, and it was shoving the

07:39:21.599 --> 07:39:23.939
rocks apart, breaking through the crack

07:39:23.939 --> 07:39:25.919
creating an opening.

07:39:25.979 --> 07:39:29.459
He dug his talons in around the boulder

07:39:29.459 --> 07:39:30.180
and yanked.

07:39:30.240 --> 07:39:33.180
Luna did the same, and with a lot of

07:39:33.180 --> 07:39:35.759
grunting and muscle pulling, they felt it

07:39:35.759 --> 07:39:38.340
slowly give way until it tumbled out at

07:39:38.340 --> 07:39:38.939
their feet.

07:39:39.000 --> 07:39:42.479
The hole in the wall yawned at them and

07:39:42.479 --> 07:39:45.419
on the other side, beyond the roots, he

07:39:45.419 --> 07:39:47.819
saw 3 faces crowding in to peer through.

07:39:47.939 --> 07:39:51.000
Swartail reached toward Luna.

07:39:51.060 --> 07:39:53.819
You're safe, he whispered.

07:39:53.880 --> 07:39:57.360
And I have wings, she answered giddily.

07:39:57.419 --> 07:39:59.220
She shoved blue in front of her.

07:39:59.279 --> 07:40:00.900
Go on, quick.

07:40:01.020 --> 07:40:03.540
Suddenly, there was a furious pounding

07:40:03.540 --> 07:40:04.080
overhead.

07:40:04.200 --> 07:40:08.340
Smash, smash, smash, against the glass.

07:40:08.400 --> 07:40:09.959
They'd been spotted.

07:40:10.020 --> 07:40:12.060
That meant the guards were coming.

07:40:12.119 --> 07:40:13.860
All the guards.

07:40:13.919 --> 07:40:17.700
Blue dove into the hole, and wiggled

07:40:17.700 --> 07:40:19.979
through into the dark, navigating a small

07:40:19.979 --> 07:40:21.599
thicket of leafy branches.

07:40:21.659 --> 07:40:24.419
He felt the warmth of cricket's talons

07:40:24.419 --> 07:40:26.880
lifting him up, and saw a light glinting

07:40:26.880 --> 07:40:27.419
off her glasses.

07:40:27.540 --> 07:40:31.380
I'm so glad you're alive, he said

07:40:31.380 --> 07:40:32.040
breathlessly.

07:40:32.099 --> 07:40:35.939
I had a feeling you'd rescue me, except I

07:40:35.939 --> 07:40:37.619
thought maybe I had to come rescue you

07:40:37.619 --> 07:40:39.000
but I didn't know how.

07:40:39.060 --> 07:40:41.099
You did rescue me.

07:40:41.220 --> 07:40:44.220
Just by being you, she said.

07:40:44.279 --> 07:40:47.220
Oh gosh, that wasn't corny at all.

07:40:47.340 --> 07:40:50.580
Luna popped through and Soritail swept

07:40:50.580 --> 07:40:51.900
his wings around her.

07:40:51.959 --> 07:40:54.060
My love, he cried.

07:40:54.119 --> 07:40:57.659
By the forest, all of you stop being

07:40:57.659 --> 07:40:58.919
sickening and run.

07:40:58.979 --> 07:41:00.479
Sundu cried.

07:41:00.540 --> 07:41:03.479
She took off in a whirl of green scales

07:41:03.479 --> 07:41:05.340
disappearing rapidly into the dark.

07:41:05.459 --> 07:41:09.180
Luna produced a small wisp of flame that

07:41:09.180 --> 07:41:11.220
lit up the tunnel just enough for them to

07:41:11.220 --> 07:41:12.659
see, and they ran.

07:41:12.720 --> 07:41:16.139
But before she did, for that moment in

07:41:16.139 --> 07:41:19.020
the dark, Blue had glanced down at his

07:41:19.020 --> 07:41:22.680
wrists, and saw tiny globes of fire under

07:41:22.680 --> 07:41:23.220
his scales.

07:41:23.340 --> 07:41:28.020
Chapter 25.

07:41:28.259 --> 07:41:32.580
They ran and climbed and ducked and slid

07:41:32.580 --> 07:41:35.340
down loose pebbly dirt slopes, following

07:41:35.340 --> 07:41:37.979
the flicker of Luna's silk, and the flash

07:41:37.979 --> 07:41:39.659
of sundew's tail up ahead.

07:41:39.720 --> 07:41:42.840
Their escape root smelled like earthworms

07:41:42.840 --> 07:41:43.680
and cut grass.

07:41:43.740 --> 07:41:46.680
Twice they had to squeeze through gaps so

07:41:46.680 --> 07:41:49.080
narrow, Blue was worried Swordtail

07:41:49.080 --> 07:41:49.619
wouldn't fit.

07:41:49.680 --> 07:41:52.259
Most of the time the ceiling was low

07:41:52.259 --> 07:41:54.299
enough to scrape their heads, and

07:41:54.299 --> 07:41:57.419
sometimes the dirt turned to damp mud

07:41:57.419 --> 07:41:58.619
clogging up their talons.

07:41:58.680 --> 07:42:00.419
But after a while.

07:42:00.479 --> 07:42:03.479
They slowed down to listen, and they

07:42:03.479 --> 07:42:04.919
couldn't hear anyone behind them.

07:42:04.979 --> 07:42:07.680
Maybe they couldn't get through the hole

07:42:07.680 --> 07:42:08.340
from the cavern.

07:42:08.400 --> 07:42:09.540
Blue said.

07:42:09.599 --> 07:42:12.840
Maybe sundew's fast growing roots had

07:42:12.840 --> 07:42:13.380
blocked the way.

07:42:13.439 --> 07:42:17.040
Or they got stuck at the bottleneck gaps

07:42:17.040 --> 07:42:19.740
Soritell said, rubbing his shoulder.

07:42:19.799 --> 07:42:22.200
They'll be out searching for the other

07:42:22.200 --> 07:42:24.479
end of the tunnel, Sundew said.

07:42:24.599 --> 07:42:26.880
Good thing it's quite a long way from the

07:42:26.880 --> 07:42:27.299
hive.

07:42:27.360 --> 07:42:30.060
She turned to keep going and they

07:42:30.060 --> 07:42:32.939
followed, moving at a steadier pace now.

07:42:33.000 --> 07:42:36.419
Soon the dirt tunnels shifted up and

07:42:36.419 --> 07:42:39.000
released them into a stone cave, similar

07:42:39.000 --> 07:42:42.000
in size to the flame silk cavern, but

07:42:42.000 --> 07:42:43.799
cold and dark and empty.

07:42:43.860 --> 07:42:47.220
From there on, they climbed through

07:42:47.220 --> 07:42:48.840
natural passages in the rocks.

07:42:48.900 --> 07:42:51.840
At one point, they hopped up the side of

07:42:51.840 --> 07:42:54.360
a trickling waterfall that sprayed their

07:42:54.360 --> 07:42:55.319
scales with mist.

07:42:55.380 --> 07:42:58.139
Blue thought he heard a river rushing

07:42:58.139 --> 07:42:59.040
somewhere close by.

07:42:59.099 --> 07:43:02.880
He also heard odd, whispering, chittering

07:43:02.880 --> 07:43:05.819
sounds inside the echoes, as though the

07:43:05.819 --> 07:43:07.799
caves were haunted by musical squirrels.

07:43:07.860 --> 07:43:12.360
Or reading monkeys, he realized.

07:43:12.479 --> 07:43:15.119
These caves could be connected to the

07:43:15.119 --> 07:43:17.099
ones where he and Cricket had seen the

07:43:17.099 --> 07:43:18.180
little monkey creature.

07:43:18.240 --> 07:43:20.580
Maybe there were lots of them living down

07:43:20.580 --> 07:43:20.880
here.

07:43:21.000 --> 07:43:24.000
Like cricket's science project, dream

07:43:24.000 --> 07:43:24.599
come true.

07:43:24.720 --> 07:43:29.400
And then, a long while later, he heard a

07:43:29.400 --> 07:43:30.720
sound like distant roaring.

07:43:30.840 --> 07:43:32.639
What's that?

07:43:32.759 --> 07:43:34.619
He whispered to Cricket.

07:43:34.680 --> 07:43:36.599
I'm not sure.

07:43:36.659 --> 07:43:37.680
She answered.

07:43:37.740 --> 07:43:39.419
The smell is different too.

07:43:39.479 --> 07:43:40.619
Did you notice?

07:43:40.680 --> 07:43:43.200
Doesn't it smell like salt and?

07:43:43.200 --> 07:43:44.939
Fish, maybe?

07:43:45.000 --> 07:43:47.580
Oh, oh, I know what it is.

07:43:47.639 --> 07:43:49.080
Sundew.

07:43:49.139 --> 07:43:50.400
Are we going to the ocean?

07:43:50.459 --> 07:43:53.639
Just then they rounded a corner of the

07:43:53.639 --> 07:43:57.119
tunnel, and there it was, the ocean.

07:43:57.180 --> 07:44:00.479
They were standing in an enormous cave

07:44:00.479 --> 07:44:02.220
that looked out onto the beach.

07:44:02.279 --> 07:44:04.380
It was early morning.

07:44:04.439 --> 07:44:07.919
Rivulets of water ran and branched and

07:44:07.919 --> 07:44:10.020
reconvened all through the sandy floor of

07:44:10.020 --> 07:44:10.500
the cave.

07:44:10.560 --> 07:44:13.979
Seabirds dove and wheeled in and out

07:44:13.979 --> 07:44:16.319
visiting their nests near the rocky

07:44:16.319 --> 07:44:16.799
ceiling.

07:44:16.860 --> 07:44:20.639
Cricket ran forward, her talons splashing

07:44:20.639 --> 07:44:22.680
in the wet sand to the mouth of the

07:44:22.680 --> 07:44:23.220
cave.

07:44:23.279 --> 07:44:26.400
She opened her wings to the wind, so they

07:44:26.400 --> 07:44:28.619
billowed out like pages flung into the

07:44:28.619 --> 07:44:28.860
sky.

07:44:28.919 --> 07:44:31.860
The waves roared cheerfully at her.

07:44:31.919 --> 07:44:34.139
Oh, wow.

07:44:34.200 --> 07:44:37.020
Luna said, waiting up beside her.

07:44:37.080 --> 07:44:39.959
She spread her wings too, and they sat

07:44:39.959 --> 07:44:43.139
side by side for a moment, gold, orange

07:44:43.139 --> 07:44:44.580
black, and pale green.

07:44:44.639 --> 07:44:48.360
Hive wing and silk wing gazing out at the

07:44:48.360 --> 07:44:48.599
sea.

07:44:48.659 --> 07:44:52.319
Blue sidled up beside them and looked out

07:44:52.319 --> 07:44:52.860
at the beach.

07:44:52.919 --> 07:44:55.860
It stretched away beyond sight in each

07:44:55.860 --> 07:44:58.619
direction, with tall cliffs overlooking

07:44:58.619 --> 07:45:00.240
the beach as far as he could see.

07:45:00.299 --> 07:45:03.779
Up at the top of the cliffs, long grass

07:45:03.779 --> 07:45:05.459
tossed and waved in the wind.

07:45:05.520 --> 07:45:08.759
The ocean was so big.

07:45:08.819 --> 07:45:11.520
He'd never quite imagined how big it

07:45:11.520 --> 07:45:14.580
could be or how noisy or how active.

07:45:14.639 --> 07:45:17.880
It never stopped moving, charging up the

07:45:17.880 --> 07:45:21.000
beach, sprinting away, rolling and

07:45:21.000 --> 07:45:23.880
turning blue, green, gray, with sprays of

07:45:23.880 --> 07:45:24.479
white.

07:45:24.540 --> 07:45:26.459
Have you ever been here before?

07:45:26.520 --> 07:45:28.139
Cricket asked him.

07:45:28.200 --> 07:45:31.259
I haven't, but I've always wanted to

07:45:31.259 --> 07:45:31.919
visit the sea.

07:45:31.979 --> 07:45:33.959
Doesn't it feel like a promise?

07:45:34.020 --> 07:45:36.360
Like the night before an exciting

07:45:36.360 --> 07:45:36.720
journey?

07:45:36.779 --> 07:45:40.200
The distant kingdoms are out there, Blue.

07:45:40.259 --> 07:45:41.279
I know it.

07:45:41.340 --> 07:45:44.819
She squinted at the tossing waves, as

07:45:44.819 --> 07:45:46.380
though she might be able to glimpse the

07:45:46.380 --> 07:45:48.240
far off continent on the other side of

07:45:48.240 --> 07:45:48.599
the world.

07:45:48.659 --> 07:45:51.419
Clear site's home.

07:45:51.479 --> 07:45:54.000
We could learn so much if we could just

07:45:54.000 --> 07:45:55.380
figure out how to get there.

07:45:55.500 --> 07:45:58.020
Luna gave a rueful laugh.

07:45:58.080 --> 07:46:01.080
I'm afraid we have enough to deal with on

07:46:01.080 --> 07:46:02.939
this continent, she said.

07:46:03.000 --> 07:46:06.000
I'm all for exploring new worlds, but I

07:46:06.000 --> 07:46:07.319
think we have to save this one first.

07:46:07.380 --> 07:46:12.479
Or we could just leave, Cricket said, in

07:46:12.479 --> 07:46:13.139
a quieter voice.

07:46:13.200 --> 07:46:15.779
If it's too dangerous here.

07:46:15.840 --> 07:46:18.419
Maybe we'd be safer over there.

07:46:18.479 --> 07:46:21.720
Yes, we might be.

07:46:21.779 --> 07:46:22.979
Luna said.

07:46:23.040 --> 07:46:25.500
But the dragons we left behind would

07:46:25.500 --> 07:46:26.220
still be in danger.

07:46:26.279 --> 07:46:30.060
She turned as sore tail and sun dew came

07:46:30.060 --> 07:46:30.540
up to join them.

07:46:30.659 --> 07:46:33.659
Blue realized it was raining.

07:46:33.720 --> 07:46:36.599
A quiet drizzle plip plopped across the

07:46:36.599 --> 07:46:37.139
sand.

07:46:37.200 --> 07:46:39.840
Turning the air misty in the pale dawn

07:46:39.840 --> 07:46:40.200
light.

07:46:40.259 --> 07:46:43.680
He held out his burning wrists so the

07:46:43.680 --> 07:46:45.180
raindrops could cool them down.

07:46:45.240 --> 07:46:48.119
Thank you for getting us out of there.

07:46:48.180 --> 07:46:49.740
He said to Sundu.

07:46:49.799 --> 07:46:51.119
Where are your parents?

07:46:51.240 --> 07:46:54.000
Sulking, she said.

07:46:54.060 --> 07:46:56.040
They didn't want me to reveal the

07:46:56.040 --> 07:46:58.200
existence of the tunnel to the hive wings

07:46:58.200 --> 07:47:00.840
even though we'd already decided we can't

07:47:00.840 --> 07:47:01.080
use it.

07:47:01.139 --> 07:47:04.020
Also, they're mad that I haven't given

07:47:04.020 --> 07:47:04.799
them this yet.

07:47:04.860 --> 07:47:08.520
She tapped one of her larger pouches, and

07:47:08.520 --> 07:47:09.599
it made a thunking sound.

07:47:09.659 --> 07:47:12.840
But they are not the boss of me, and I

07:47:12.840 --> 07:47:14.159
told them they could have it once you

07:47:14.159 --> 07:47:14.459
were free.

07:47:14.580 --> 07:47:16.500
I'll meet up with them tonight.

07:47:16.560 --> 07:47:18.720
And then what will you do?

07:47:18.779 --> 07:47:20.340
Sortell asked.

07:47:20.400 --> 07:47:23.220
Go back to the other leaf wings, she

07:47:23.220 --> 07:47:23.580
said.

07:47:23.639 --> 07:47:25.560
Figure out our next plan.

07:47:25.619 --> 07:47:28.740
Since this one didn't go exactly the way

07:47:28.740 --> 07:47:29.400
we expected.

07:47:29.459 --> 07:47:31.619
Is that?

07:47:31.740 --> 07:47:34.259
Luna started, pointing to the pouch.

07:47:34.319 --> 07:47:36.240
Do you really have?

07:47:36.240 --> 07:47:39.119
Sundoo reached in and drew out the book

07:47:39.119 --> 07:47:39.900
of Clear Sight.

07:47:39.959 --> 07:47:43.139
It looked even smaller and less mystical

07:47:43.139 --> 07:47:43.740
in the daylight.

07:47:43.799 --> 07:47:47.099
It just looked like a very old book that

07:47:47.099 --> 07:47:49.619
someone had sewn together, a little

07:47:49.619 --> 07:47:50.340
crookedly.

07:47:50.520 --> 07:47:54.360
But it holds the secrets of our future.

07:47:54.479 --> 07:47:57.479
Blue thought, with a shiver of awe.

07:47:57.540 --> 07:47:59.520
And we could read it.

07:47:59.639 --> 07:48:02.819
We could read it right now, and know

07:48:02.819 --> 07:48:03.840
everything that's going to happen.

07:48:03.900 --> 07:48:06.060
Can I show them?

07:48:06.119 --> 07:48:08.400
Cricket asked sundew.

07:48:08.459 --> 07:48:11.220
The leaf wing nodded, passing the book to

07:48:11.220 --> 07:48:11.459
her.

07:48:11.520 --> 07:48:15.060
Cricket found a flat, dry boulder, and

07:48:15.060 --> 07:48:16.799
swept off all the sand on it with her

07:48:16.799 --> 07:48:17.340
tail.

07:48:17.400 --> 07:48:20.459
Blue sat down beside her, and Cricket

07:48:20.459 --> 07:48:23.099
scooted closer to him, so Luna could sit

07:48:23.099 --> 07:48:23.700
on her other side.

07:48:23.759 --> 07:48:27.540
It's not what we thought it was, Cricket

07:48:27.540 --> 07:48:27.900
said.

07:48:27.959 --> 07:48:31.680
It's, well, it's something else

07:48:31.680 --> 07:48:32.220
completely.

07:48:32.279 --> 07:48:35.759
She opened the book to the 1st page.

07:48:35.819 --> 07:48:39.900
Dear grandchildren, and great

07:48:39.900 --> 07:48:42.240
grandchildren, and great great

07:48:42.240 --> 07:48:45.000
grandchildren, and all the many great

07:48:45.000 --> 07:48:46.139
grandchildren to come.

07:48:46.200 --> 07:48:49.979
How funny it feels to know you so well.

07:48:50.099 --> 07:48:52.560
When there are so many of you, I'm never

07:48:52.560 --> 07:48:52.979
going to meet.

07:48:53.099 --> 07:48:57.060
I see you all the time, especially when

07:48:57.060 --> 07:48:58.919
I'm just on the edge of falling asleep

07:48:58.919 --> 07:49:01.080
the future is so clear.

07:49:01.139 --> 07:49:02.220
Suddenly.

07:49:02.340 --> 07:49:04.500
Now that I won't be able to change

07:49:04.500 --> 07:49:04.979
anything.

07:49:05.040 --> 07:49:09.599
My time is almost up, and yours is just

07:49:09.599 --> 07:49:10.020
beginning.

07:49:10.080 --> 07:49:13.919
I won't be able to control anything after

07:49:13.919 --> 07:49:14.279
this.

07:49:14.340 --> 07:49:17.340
I won't be able to use my visions to

07:49:17.340 --> 07:49:17.880
protect you.

07:49:17.939 --> 07:49:19.680
To keep you all safe.

07:49:19.740 --> 07:49:23.580
But then, one thing I've learned over my

07:49:23.580 --> 07:49:27.900
long, strange, lovely life is that I

07:49:27.900 --> 07:49:29.759
never could actually control the future

07:49:29.759 --> 07:49:31.500
as much as I thought I could.

07:49:31.560 --> 07:49:34.979
I should have learned that lesson with my

07:49:34.979 --> 07:49:37.560
1st love, back home in Pyria.

07:49:37.680 --> 07:49:39.779
But I kept trying anyway.

07:49:39.840 --> 07:49:42.659
And I did manage to keep you all alive.

07:49:42.779 --> 07:49:46.799
I battled the future for that much, and I

07:49:46.799 --> 07:49:47.040
won.

07:49:47.099 --> 07:49:50.700
But the future will always win in the end

07:49:50.700 --> 07:49:53.340
because it continues on forever.

07:49:53.400 --> 07:49:55.139
To where I cannot go.

07:49:55.200 --> 07:49:57.959
So this is my last battle.

07:49:58.020 --> 07:50:01.259
The last thing I can do to try and keep

07:50:01.259 --> 07:50:03.119
my claws on the balance of the future.

07:50:03.180 --> 07:50:06.119
To keep you safe as long as I can.

07:50:06.180 --> 07:50:10.080
In this book, are my visions of what is

07:50:10.080 --> 07:50:10.680
yet to come.

07:50:10.799 --> 07:50:14.459
Some of it seems small, but I have

07:50:14.459 --> 07:50:15.299
included everything.

07:50:15.360 --> 07:50:18.180
Even if I can't tell yet why it's

07:50:18.180 --> 07:50:18.540
important.

07:50:18.599 --> 07:50:22.080
I leave you this, and hope that it will

07:50:22.080 --> 07:50:24.240
make life better for both our tribes.

07:50:24.299 --> 07:50:27.119
I hope you will use it to protect the

07:50:27.119 --> 07:50:29.819
dragons around you, especially the ones

07:50:29.819 --> 07:50:32.639
who are the most threatened, regardless

07:50:32.639 --> 07:50:35.040
of who they are, and how you think you

07:50:35.040 --> 07:50:35.759
feel about them.

07:50:35.819 --> 07:50:40.439
There are some hard times ahead. as there

07:50:40.439 --> 07:50:42.479
always are, everywhere.

07:50:42.540 --> 07:50:43.979
And for everyone.

07:50:44.040 --> 07:50:47.459
I'm sorry, I won't be here to help you

07:50:47.459 --> 07:50:49.020
rebuild after the earthquake.

07:50:49.139 --> 07:50:52.080
I hope I've written down enough advice to

07:50:52.080 --> 07:50:53.099
get you through the famine.

07:50:53.159 --> 07:50:55.860
But most of what I see is joy.

07:50:55.979 --> 07:50:58.919
Your futures are full of joy.

07:50:58.979 --> 07:51:03.659
What a miracle it is to be a dragon, alive

07:51:03.659 --> 07:51:06.299
right now, and part of this wonderful

07:51:06.299 --> 07:51:06.540
world.

07:51:06.599 --> 07:51:09.180
Do you ever stop to think about that?

07:51:09.240 --> 07:51:12.299
About what an odd and lucky thing it is

07:51:12.299 --> 07:51:15.959
to be this soul inside this body, to live

07:51:15.959 --> 07:51:18.240
in a world with so many marvels in it.

07:51:18.299 --> 07:51:21.659
I am so grateful to have known and loved

07:51:21.659 --> 07:51:22.020
you all.

07:51:22.080 --> 07:51:25.680
All the hurricanes and earthquakes, and

07:51:25.680 --> 07:51:28.860
fires, and storms, cannot break you.

07:51:28.860 --> 07:51:30.959
If you remember a few things.

07:51:31.020 --> 07:51:33.779
We are here to love with our whole

07:51:33.779 --> 07:51:34.319
hearts.

07:51:34.380 --> 07:51:37.799
Lean into your kindness and empathy in

07:51:37.799 --> 07:51:40.860
the face of evil, but do not let evil

07:51:40.860 --> 07:51:41.040
win.

07:51:41.099 --> 07:51:43.979
You are the only dragon who can decide

07:51:43.979 --> 07:51:44.939
who you want to be.

07:51:45.000 --> 07:51:47.939
Don't let yourself get stuck on someone

07:51:47.939 --> 07:51:48.900
else's path.

07:51:48.959 --> 07:51:52.439
Search for what's true, and think for

07:51:52.439 --> 07:51:52.740
yourself.

07:51:52.799 --> 07:51:55.439
Over a 100 years ago.

07:51:55.500 --> 07:51:58.560
I thought my life was finished, and there

07:51:58.560 --> 07:52:00.119
was nothing left to live for.

07:52:00.180 --> 07:52:02.520
I was so, so wrong.

07:52:02.580 --> 07:52:04.200
Keep going.

07:52:04.259 --> 07:52:06.720
The list of things to live for is

07:52:06.720 --> 07:52:09.479
limitless, and it is possible to be happy

07:52:09.479 --> 07:52:09.840
again.

07:52:09.900 --> 07:52:13.979
And this one is going to sound ridiculous

07:52:13.979 --> 07:52:14.819
coming from me.

07:52:14.880 --> 07:52:19.020
Don't worry about the future so much, or

07:52:19.020 --> 07:52:20.459
else you might miss out on the

07:52:20.459 --> 07:52:21.659
extraordinary present.

07:52:21.720 --> 07:52:25.200
Be happy, dragons of the future.

07:52:25.259 --> 07:52:28.680
You can change the world with your joy

07:52:28.680 --> 07:52:30.779
and your hope.

07:52:30.840 --> 07:52:33.659
All my love, clear sight.

07:52:33.720 --> 07:52:37.560
Blue glanced up and saw Luna wiping away

07:52:37.560 --> 07:52:38.220
tears.

07:52:38.279 --> 07:52:43.020
This is exactly how I imagined Clearsight

07:52:43.020 --> 07:52:43.799
he said.

07:52:43.860 --> 07:52:48.479
Of course you did, Luna said, with a

07:52:48.479 --> 07:52:49.139
catch in her voice.

07:52:49.259 --> 07:52:53.159
You have faith in other dragons, whereas

07:52:53.159 --> 07:52:55.619
I thought she was a conniving manipulator

07:52:55.619 --> 07:52:57.959
who deliberately set up her descendants

07:52:57.959 --> 07:52:59.700
to be the most powerful tribe in

07:52:59.700 --> 07:53:00.360
Pentala.

07:53:00.419 --> 07:53:01.979
She shook her head.

07:53:02.040 --> 07:53:03.840
Yep.

07:53:03.900 --> 07:53:06.419
Me too. said sundew.

07:53:06.479 --> 07:53:08.220
Oh, no.

07:53:08.340 --> 07:53:10.500
Blue said, shocked.

07:53:10.560 --> 07:53:11.639
She wasn't.

07:53:11.700 --> 07:53:13.020
She wouldn't.

07:53:13.080 --> 07:53:17.220
I see that, Luna said, waving her talent

07:53:17.220 --> 07:53:17.639
at the book.

07:53:17.700 --> 07:53:20.700
But at some point, that's what her

07:53:20.700 --> 07:53:22.020
descendants decided to do.

07:53:22.080 --> 07:53:24.840
Why didn't she see that coming and stop

07:53:24.840 --> 07:53:25.080
them?

07:53:25.200 --> 07:53:27.060
Because...

07:53:27.060 --> 07:53:28.860
Cricket said softly.

07:53:28.919 --> 07:53:32.759
It turns out, she wasn't all knowing and

07:53:32.759 --> 07:53:33.959
all seeing after all.

07:53:34.020 --> 07:53:38.220
She started turning pages, pointing to

07:53:38.220 --> 07:53:39.659
the date up at the top.

07:53:39.720 --> 07:53:43.319
After about 200 years, the flow of

07:53:43.319 --> 07:53:45.000
visions slowed dramatically.

07:53:45.060 --> 07:53:48.659
A hurricane here, a tsunami 90 years

07:53:48.659 --> 07:53:48.900
later.

07:53:48.959 --> 07:53:52.259
A few more tiny notes, full of question

07:53:52.259 --> 07:53:52.799
marks.

07:53:52.860 --> 07:53:56.759
And then, on a date marked about 900

07:53:56.759 --> 07:54:00.000
years after the 1st she'd written, Take

07:54:00.000 --> 07:54:00.720
care of the trees.

07:54:00.779 --> 07:54:03.959
I think they might be in danger, but I

07:54:03.959 --> 07:54:04.500
can't see why.

07:54:04.560 --> 07:54:07.139
Help the leaf wings protect them.

07:54:07.200 --> 07:54:08.939
I love you.

07:54:09.000 --> 07:54:10.680
Good luck.

07:54:10.740 --> 07:54:13.380
Cricket turned the page.

07:54:13.439 --> 07:54:16.919
The next spread was blank, and so was the

07:54:16.919 --> 07:54:18.900
next, and the next.

07:54:18.959 --> 07:54:22.500
The last few pages of the book were

07:54:22.500 --> 07:54:22.860
empty.

07:54:22.919 --> 07:54:27.240
The last vision from Clearsight was dated

07:54:27.240 --> 07:54:28.680
over a 1000 years ago.

07:54:28.799 --> 07:54:33.659
Chapter 26.

07:54:33.779 --> 07:54:37.080
Blue looked up at Cricket and Luna.

07:54:37.139 --> 07:54:38.639
Blinking and confusion.

07:54:38.700 --> 07:54:41.340
Where's the rest of it?

07:54:41.340 --> 07:54:42.060
he asked.

07:54:42.119 --> 07:54:44.040
What about the tree wars?

07:54:44.040 --> 07:54:46.139
And us trying to steal the book.

07:54:46.139 --> 07:54:49.020
And everything Queen Wasp knows.

07:54:49.080 --> 07:54:51.240
She doesn't know anything.

07:54:51.360 --> 07:54:53.639
Luna said furiously.

07:54:53.700 --> 07:54:56.520
She was faking it the whole time.

07:54:56.759 --> 07:54:57.840
The power of the book.

07:54:57.900 --> 07:55:00.540
Everything that makes the hive wing so

07:55:00.540 --> 07:55:03.119
superior, it's all lies.

07:55:03.240 --> 07:55:07.319
In case you're curious, Sundew

07:55:07.319 --> 07:55:07.979
interjected.

07:55:08.040 --> 07:55:11.279
This is my not at all surprised face.

07:55:11.340 --> 07:55:13.319
Cricket was nodding.

07:55:13.380 --> 07:55:16.139
Clear sight never saw this far ahead.

07:55:16.200 --> 07:55:18.720
She had no idea her book would be used

07:55:18.720 --> 07:55:19.259
this way.

07:55:19.319 --> 07:55:23.400
But Blue still couldn't wrap his head

07:55:23.400 --> 07:55:23.819
around it.

07:55:23.880 --> 07:55:27.959
But Queen Wasp said Clearsight wanted the

07:55:27.959 --> 07:55:29.580
tribes to unite under her rule.

07:55:29.639 --> 07:55:32.580
That was the whole reason Queen Monarch

07:55:32.580 --> 07:55:33.479
gave up her throne.

07:55:33.599 --> 07:55:36.659
Because if it was in the book of

07:55:36.659 --> 07:55:39.000
Clearsight, it had to be important.

07:55:39.060 --> 07:55:41.580
It was a lie blue.

07:55:41.639 --> 07:55:45.000
Luna jumped up, and Thordtail came over

07:55:45.000 --> 07:55:46.259
to stand beside her.

07:55:46.319 --> 07:55:49.979
Wasp lied and used the book to seize

07:55:49.979 --> 07:55:50.520
power.

07:55:50.580 --> 07:55:54.119
And to drive out the leaf wings, sundew

07:55:54.119 --> 07:55:54.419
said.

07:55:54.479 --> 07:55:57.360
Queen Sequoia wouldn't agree to step down

07:55:57.360 --> 07:55:59.819
without seeing the book first, which, of

07:55:59.819 --> 07:56:01.560
course, WASP wouldn't allow.

07:56:01.560 --> 07:56:05.340
Our queen said, if she'd seen it in clear

07:56:05.340 --> 07:56:07.619
sight's own handwriting, she might have

07:56:07.619 --> 07:56:10.439
considered it, which I think is insane in

07:56:10.439 --> 07:56:11.099
the 1st place.

07:56:11.159 --> 07:56:13.259
We don't need anyone else to be our

07:56:13.259 --> 07:56:13.680
queen.

07:56:13.740 --> 07:56:15.840
How could she?

07:56:15.900 --> 07:56:19.619
Blue said, closing the book and resting

07:56:19.619 --> 07:56:20.580
his claws on it.

07:56:20.639 --> 07:56:22.439
I don't understand.

07:56:22.500 --> 07:56:25.860
How could Queen Wasp read this?

07:56:25.919 --> 07:56:28.080
And then decide to become the total

07:56:28.080 --> 07:56:30.299
opposite of what Clearsight says to be?

07:56:30.360 --> 07:56:33.540
Cricket put her talent over his on the

07:56:33.540 --> 07:56:33.720
book?

07:56:33.779 --> 07:56:37.619
Some dragons, care infinitely more about

07:56:37.619 --> 07:56:40.439
themselves than anyone else, she said.

07:56:40.500 --> 07:56:43.500
Which I think is hard for a dragon like

07:56:43.500 --> 07:56:44.340
you to imagine.

07:56:44.400 --> 07:56:47.159
Well, he said.

07:56:47.220 --> 07:56:50.040
I am very angry about this.

07:56:50.099 --> 07:56:53.220
Angry enough to do something about it?

07:56:53.400 --> 07:56:54.720
Sundu asked.

07:56:54.779 --> 07:56:57.599
She lifted her chin challengingly.

07:56:57.659 --> 07:56:59.639
Like what?

07:56:59.700 --> 07:57:00.959
Sortell asked.

07:57:01.080 --> 07:57:03.720
We're going to take down the hive wings

07:57:03.720 --> 07:57:04.799
Sundew said.

07:57:04.860 --> 07:57:07.259
We could use some dragons on the inside.

07:57:07.319 --> 07:57:09.479
Swortail snorted.

07:57:09.540 --> 07:57:12.180
You may not have noticed, but we're not

07:57:12.180 --> 07:57:13.860
exactly on the inside anymore.

07:57:13.919 --> 07:57:17.939
We know dragons who are, though, Luna

07:57:17.939 --> 07:57:18.299
said.

07:57:18.360 --> 07:57:20.220
Giving him a significant look.

07:57:20.279 --> 07:57:24.900
Wait, what does take down the hive wings

07:57:24.900 --> 07:57:25.319
mean?

07:57:25.380 --> 07:57:26.580
Blue asked.

07:57:26.639 --> 07:57:28.080
Are you going to hurt them?

07:57:28.139 --> 07:57:30.599
Sundew scowled at him.

07:57:30.659 --> 07:57:33.119
That is sort of the point of a

07:57:33.119 --> 07:57:33.779
revolution.

07:57:33.840 --> 07:57:34.919
She snapped.

07:57:35.040 --> 07:57:37.680
She snatched the book away from him and

07:57:37.680 --> 07:57:38.759
stuffed it back in her pouch.

07:57:38.819 --> 07:57:40.799
I thought you said you were mad.

07:57:40.860 --> 07:57:45.360
Yes, but no, Blue said.

07:57:45.419 --> 07:57:48.959
The hive wings have also been lied to, and

07:57:48.959 --> 07:57:50.639
brainwashed and tricked.

07:57:50.700 --> 07:57:52.500
The queen is the problem.

07:57:52.560 --> 07:57:55.200
You have to fight her, not the whole

07:57:55.200 --> 07:57:55.560
tribe.

07:57:55.619 --> 07:57:57.599
I mean, we do.

07:57:57.659 --> 07:57:59.520
We have to stop her.

07:57:59.639 --> 07:58:03.659
His wrists flared with pain, as though

07:58:03.659 --> 07:58:05.220
they were trying to remind him that he

07:58:05.220 --> 07:58:06.959
had slightly more urgent things to do

07:58:06.959 --> 07:58:10.259
first, such as, for instance, growing

07:58:10.259 --> 07:58:10.680
wings.

07:58:10.740 --> 07:58:14.759
Let's rest for a while, Cricket said

07:58:14.759 --> 07:58:16.560
watching him with concern.

07:58:16.619 --> 07:58:19.439
Everyone thinks better after sleeping.

07:58:19.500 --> 07:58:22.680
She hopped down to a dry patch of soft

07:58:22.680 --> 07:58:25.500
sand, in a sheltered corner of the cave

07:58:25.500 --> 07:58:28.799
and dug a small hollow, Blue?

07:58:28.919 --> 07:58:32.159
He gratefully slid down and sank into the

07:58:32.159 --> 07:58:33.060
hollow next to her.

07:58:33.119 --> 07:58:35.939
His wing buds were really starting to

07:58:35.939 --> 07:58:38.939
ache, and his head felt strangely fuzzy

07:58:38.939 --> 07:58:39.479
too.

07:58:39.540 --> 07:58:41.639
He sort of wished he could spin his

07:58:41.639 --> 07:58:44.099
cocoon now, and shut out the whole mess

07:58:44.099 --> 07:58:46.380
and all the decisions they might have to

07:58:46.380 --> 07:58:47.099
make.

07:58:47.159 --> 07:58:49.680
But the thought also terrified him.

07:58:49.740 --> 07:58:52.799
He didn't want to be cut off from Cricket

07:58:52.799 --> 07:58:54.479
and Luna for 5 days.

07:58:54.540 --> 07:58:56.580
With no way to know what was going on.

07:58:56.639 --> 07:58:59.759
And what if something went wrong with his

07:58:59.759 --> 07:59:00.779
metamorphosis?

07:59:00.840 --> 07:59:04.619
What could go more wrong than turning out

07:59:04.619 --> 07:59:06.299
to be a flame silk?

07:59:06.299 --> 07:59:06.720
he thought.

07:59:06.779 --> 07:59:11.400
Well, I don't need to sleep, Luna said.

07:59:11.459 --> 07:59:13.680
I'm going to test out my new wings.

07:59:13.740 --> 07:59:14.580
Want to come?

07:59:14.639 --> 07:59:17.279
she said, bumping sore tails side.

07:59:17.340 --> 07:59:19.799
Obviously, yes, he said.

07:59:19.860 --> 07:59:22.979
Be careful, Sundew warned.

07:59:23.040 --> 07:59:25.139
The hive wings will be out in force

07:59:25.139 --> 07:59:25.919
looking for us.

07:59:25.979 --> 07:59:28.439
It would be safer to stay inside until

07:59:28.439 --> 07:59:28.860
dark.

07:59:28.979 --> 07:59:31.380
Just a little flight?

07:59:31.500 --> 07:59:33.119
Luna wheedled.

07:59:33.180 --> 07:59:36.240
I finally have wings, and we're so far

07:59:36.240 --> 07:59:37.259
from the hives.

07:59:37.319 --> 07:59:38.580
I promise we'll be careful.

07:59:38.639 --> 07:59:40.860
Sundew shrugged.

07:59:40.919 --> 07:59:43.799
You're not my tribe, she said, but if you

07:59:43.799 --> 07:59:45.900
get caught, I'm not rescuing you again.

07:59:45.959 --> 07:59:50.340
Noted, Luna said, bounding to the cave

07:59:50.340 --> 07:59:50.880
entrance.

07:59:50.939 --> 07:59:52.680
Be back soon, Blue.

07:59:52.740 --> 07:59:55.259
She soared up into the sky.

07:59:55.319 --> 07:59:58.020
Scattering raindrops in all directions

07:59:58.020 --> 08:00:00.180
with sword tail in her wake.

08:00:00.240 --> 08:00:01.500
Blue side.

08:00:01.560 --> 08:00:04.799
I wish I were that excited about getting

08:00:04.799 --> 08:00:06.299
wings, he said.

08:00:06.419 --> 08:00:08.279
I mean, I am.

08:00:08.340 --> 08:00:11.459
I'm just... nervous too.

08:00:11.520 --> 08:00:14.520
That sounds normal to me.

08:00:14.580 --> 08:00:15.720
Cricket said.

08:00:15.779 --> 08:00:17.939
But you'll be all right once it starts.

08:00:18.000 --> 08:00:19.500
How are you feeling?

08:00:19.560 --> 08:00:21.599
Do you have the same symptoms as Luna?

08:00:21.720 --> 08:00:24.540
He lifted his wrists and she held them

08:00:24.540 --> 08:00:25.919
gently while she studied them.

08:00:25.979 --> 08:00:30.419
Your silk glands look very bright, she

08:00:30.419 --> 08:00:30.779
said.

08:00:30.840 --> 08:00:34.080
So did Luna's, he said.

08:00:34.139 --> 08:00:38.159
Kind of golden and fiery, just like this

08:00:38.159 --> 08:00:40.680
Wow, she said.

08:00:40.740 --> 08:00:43.619
I might be best friends with a real flame

08:00:43.619 --> 08:00:44.159
silk.

08:00:44.279 --> 08:00:46.860
He couldn't squash down his smile.

08:00:46.919 --> 08:00:48.479
Best friend.

08:00:48.540 --> 08:00:51.900
Well, my circle of options is a little

08:00:51.900 --> 08:00:54.479
smaller than it used to be. she said

08:00:54.479 --> 08:00:57.479
flicking her tail at the cave, and it's

08:00:57.479 --> 08:00:59.159
Sundew, who was sorting through her

08:00:59.159 --> 08:01:00.299
pouches and grumbling.

08:01:00.360 --> 08:01:03.659
But the truth is, I'd want you to be my

08:01:03.659 --> 08:01:06.540
best friend, even if I knew every dragon

08:01:06.540 --> 08:01:07.439
in Pantala.

08:01:07.560 --> 08:01:11.700
Same, he said, resting his head on his

08:01:11.700 --> 08:01:13.020
talons.

08:01:13.080 --> 08:01:13.979
That's how I see you.

08:01:14.040 --> 08:01:18.060
Best friend, best brain, best heart.

08:01:18.119 --> 08:01:21.240
Aw, she said.

08:01:21.299 --> 08:01:23.759
She lay down and snuggled up next to

08:01:23.759 --> 08:01:23.939
him.

08:01:24.000 --> 08:01:26.580
Are you totally asleep yet?

08:01:26.639 --> 08:01:29.880
Before you fall asleep, can you tell me

08:01:29.880 --> 08:01:32.459
about the Flame Silk Cavern, how does it

08:01:32.459 --> 08:01:32.639
work?

08:01:32.700 --> 08:01:34.259
How many dragons live there?

08:01:34.319 --> 08:01:35.400
What are they like?

08:01:35.459 --> 08:01:38.279
Blue drowsily tried to answer her

08:01:38.279 --> 08:01:40.680
questions, but sleep pulled him down

08:01:40.680 --> 08:01:43.979
inexorably, chasing away the pain in his

08:01:43.979 --> 08:01:44.700
back and wrists.

08:01:44.819 --> 08:01:47.819
It was peaceful with cricket by his side

08:01:47.819 --> 08:01:49.740
and the rain pattering on the rocks

08:01:49.740 --> 08:01:50.159
around them.

08:01:50.220 --> 08:01:53.220
He felt calm again for the 1st time in

08:01:53.220 --> 08:01:53.580
days.

08:01:53.639 --> 08:01:57.419
He didn't know how long he slept, but he

08:01:57.419 --> 08:01:59.580
woke suddenly, to the sound of screams

08:01:59.580 --> 08:02:02.939
from outside, across the cave.

08:02:03.000 --> 08:02:04.619
Sundew dropped a handful of twigs and

08:02:04.619 --> 08:02:05.459
leaped to her feet.

08:02:05.520 --> 08:02:08.220
The 3 of them ran to the cave entrance

08:02:08.220 --> 08:02:09.000
and looked out.

08:02:09.060 --> 08:02:12.720
Up in the sky, a pair of hive wings had

08:02:12.720 --> 08:02:15.959
sore tail and Luna cornered, they circled

08:02:15.959 --> 08:02:18.900
like hawks, jabbing and fainting, with

08:02:18.900 --> 08:02:21.119
claws and spears and stingers on their

08:02:21.119 --> 08:02:22.139
tails.

08:02:22.200 --> 08:02:23.459
Luna!

08:02:23.520 --> 08:02:24.419
Blue cried.

08:02:24.479 --> 08:02:26.880
Starting forward, and immediately

08:02:26.880 --> 08:02:29.880
stumbling over his talons, Sundu caught

08:02:29.880 --> 08:02:31.860
him, pulling him back into the cave.

08:02:31.919 --> 08:02:34.080
No way, she said.

08:02:34.200 --> 08:02:35.759
You can't fight in your condition.

08:02:35.819 --> 08:02:38.880
You can barely fight when you're not half

08:02:38.880 --> 08:02:40.020
Lubion Silk.

08:02:40.139 --> 08:02:42.540
She shoved him into Cricket's arms.

08:02:42.599 --> 08:02:43.919
Make him stay here.

08:02:44.040 --> 08:02:47.040
The leaf wing took off into the sky.

08:02:47.099 --> 08:02:50.279
It was raining harder than before, with a

08:02:50.279 --> 08:02:52.020
strong wind whipping up the seas.

08:02:52.139 --> 08:02:55.979
Blue watched in a daze as sundew smashed

08:02:55.979 --> 08:02:57.959
into the hive wings, taking them by

08:02:57.959 --> 08:02:58.439
surprise.

08:02:58.500 --> 08:03:01.500
One wheeled around to grapple with her

08:03:01.500 --> 08:03:03.900
and Swordtail broke away to tackle the

08:03:03.900 --> 08:03:04.380
other.

08:03:04.439 --> 08:03:07.319
They struggled for several rain soaked

08:03:07.319 --> 08:03:10.200
moments. talons slipping on wet scales.

08:03:10.259 --> 08:03:13.080
Blue had always thought of Soretail as

08:03:13.080 --> 08:03:14.099
the best fighter he knew.

08:03:14.220 --> 08:03:17.700
The next to sundew and the soldiers, he

08:03:17.700 --> 08:03:19.740
seemed badly outmatched.

08:03:19.799 --> 08:03:22.200
The hive wing twisted to slash a claw

08:03:22.200 --> 08:03:24.959
along his side, and Swordail roared with

08:03:24.959 --> 08:03:25.259
pain.

08:03:25.319 --> 08:03:29.099
Alone in the sky, Luna flung out her

08:03:29.099 --> 08:03:32.040
front talons, Blue could see that she was

08:03:32.040 --> 08:03:34.619
trying to protect Swordtail, that she was

08:03:34.619 --> 08:03:36.299
trying to set his attacker on fire.

08:03:36.419 --> 08:03:39.540
But her silk whipped out faster and

08:03:39.540 --> 08:03:40.979
wilder than she'd expected.

08:03:41.040 --> 08:03:44.159
The wind seized the golden strands and

08:03:44.159 --> 08:03:46.799
flung them together, weaving knots over

08:03:46.799 --> 08:03:47.400
Luna's head.

08:03:47.459 --> 08:03:51.000
In a sudden heartbeat, a sail of flame

08:03:51.000 --> 08:03:53.939
silk billowed out above Luna, and then

08:03:53.939 --> 08:03:57.659
the storm roared in, snared the sail, and

08:03:57.659 --> 08:03:58.560
blew her out to sea.

08:03:58.680 --> 08:04:00.540
Luna.

08:04:00.659 --> 08:04:02.520
Blue cried desperately.

08:04:02.580 --> 08:04:05.279
His sister seemed to be struggling with

08:04:05.279 --> 08:04:07.200
the silk, but she couldn't break free.

08:04:07.259 --> 08:04:11.040
Lightning flashed, and a moment later, the

08:04:11.040 --> 08:04:12.360
clouds had swallowed her up.

08:04:12.419 --> 08:04:16.139
Sortail smashed his attacker in the face

08:04:16.139 --> 08:04:18.840
and flew after Luna, shouting her name.

08:04:18.900 --> 08:04:22.020
His wings beat frantically as he tried to

08:04:22.020 --> 08:04:22.380
catch up.

08:04:22.439 --> 08:04:24.540
Then he was gone too.

08:04:24.599 --> 08:04:28.020
Sundew was left grimly battling the 2

08:04:28.020 --> 08:04:28.979
hive wings alone.

08:04:29.040 --> 08:04:30.840
We have to.

08:04:31.740 --> 08:04:34.740
We have to go after them, Blue said.

08:04:34.799 --> 08:04:38.040
His whole body was starting to shake, and

08:04:38.040 --> 08:04:39.779
his wrists felt like they were literally

08:04:39.779 --> 08:04:40.560
on fire.

08:04:40.619 --> 08:04:43.740
Luna, sore tail.

08:04:43.860 --> 08:04:47.040
You can't go anywhere, Blue, Cricket

08:04:47.040 --> 08:04:47.340
said.

08:04:47.400 --> 08:04:49.860
She put her wings around him and guided

08:04:49.860 --> 08:04:52.680
him back into the cave, way to the back

08:04:52.680 --> 08:04:55.740
toward the tunnels and secret passages.

08:04:55.799 --> 08:04:57.000
It's starting.

08:04:57.119 --> 08:04:59.580
We need to hide you somewhere safe.

08:04:59.639 --> 08:05:00.060
Let's think.

08:05:00.119 --> 08:05:03.119
But they'll come back.

08:05:03.180 --> 08:05:04.139
She promised.

08:05:04.200 --> 08:05:07.020
The storm will blow itself out, and

08:05:07.020 --> 08:05:09.000
they'll fly back here and want to find

08:05:09.000 --> 08:05:10.259
you safe and sound.

08:05:10.319 --> 08:05:11.279
Okay?

08:05:11.340 --> 08:05:13.799
You'll make things much worse if you go

08:05:13.799 --> 08:05:15.419
out there and get captured by hive

08:05:15.419 --> 08:05:15.779
wings.

08:05:15.840 --> 08:05:19.020
She guided him down one of the passages

08:05:19.020 --> 08:05:21.599
staring him around jutting spires of

08:05:21.599 --> 08:05:22.200
stone.

08:05:22.200 --> 08:05:25.139
Sundew, he mumbled.

08:05:25.259 --> 08:05:29.580
Can take care of herself, she said, in

08:05:29.580 --> 08:05:31.380
case you hadn't noticed, she's pretty

08:05:31.380 --> 08:05:31.919
fierce.

08:05:32.040 --> 08:05:32.939
Come on.

08:05:33.000 --> 08:05:34.860
I think I saw a cave this way.

08:05:34.919 --> 08:05:37.259
It's about as well hidden as we can get.

08:05:37.319 --> 08:05:39.720
He couldn't argue.

08:05:39.779 --> 08:05:41.159
He couldn't think.

08:05:41.220 --> 08:05:43.619
Apparently his head was no longer

08:05:43.619 --> 08:05:44.759
connected to his body.

08:05:44.819 --> 08:05:48.599
The walls were shifting and rolling, and

08:05:48.599 --> 08:05:49.860
kind of sparkling too.

08:05:49.919 --> 08:05:53.759
He felt dizzy, and sick, and very hot.

08:05:53.819 --> 08:05:56.819
It felt like an endless march before

08:05:56.819 --> 08:05:59.220
cricket maneuvered him between 2 pillars

08:05:59.220 --> 08:06:01.740
into a small curving cave with smooth

08:06:01.740 --> 08:06:02.279
walls.

08:06:02.340 --> 08:06:05.880
These ones really were sparkling, he

08:06:05.880 --> 08:06:06.180
thought.

08:06:06.240 --> 08:06:08.939
But actually, his eyes weren't to be

08:06:08.939 --> 08:06:10.200
trusted, so who knew?

08:06:10.259 --> 08:06:15.599
I wish I were in the cocoon, he said, his

08:06:15.599 --> 08:06:16.560
teeth chattering.

08:06:16.619 --> 08:06:18.659
I wish I were home.

08:06:18.720 --> 08:06:22.439
I know, Cricket said sadly.

08:06:22.560 --> 08:06:24.240
I know, Blue.

08:06:24.299 --> 08:06:26.040
I'm so sorry you can't be.

08:06:26.159 --> 08:06:30.060
He sank to his knees, and the silk

08:06:30.060 --> 08:06:31.919
started to pour from his wrists.

08:06:31.979 --> 08:06:36.419
It was bright and burning, flame silk all

08:06:36.419 --> 08:06:38.939
the way through, and it wove swiftly

08:06:38.939 --> 08:06:40.439
around his tail and talons.

08:06:40.500 --> 08:06:43.740
Everywhere it touched him, his muscles

08:06:43.740 --> 08:06:46.860
relaxed, and a feeling of peace slowly

08:06:46.860 --> 08:06:49.619
swept over him, like a wave filling him

08:06:49.619 --> 08:06:49.799
up.

08:06:49.919 --> 08:06:53.880
I'll be right here, Blue, Cricket said.

08:06:53.939 --> 08:06:56.939
He lay down, looking up into her

08:06:56.939 --> 08:06:59.580
wonderful face, lit by the glow of his

08:06:59.580 --> 08:07:00.360
flame silk.

08:07:00.479 --> 08:07:02.819
I'll be here the whole time.

08:07:02.880 --> 08:07:04.979
I'll be here when you wake up.

08:07:05.040 --> 08:07:06.479
You'll be safe.

08:07:06.540 --> 08:07:07.799
I promise.

08:07:07.860 --> 08:07:10.619
Blue was a dragon who didn't like

08:07:10.619 --> 08:07:11.040
change.

08:07:11.099 --> 08:07:15.360
But in the last 5 days, he'd discovered

08:07:15.360 --> 08:07:17.340
that his whole world was very different

08:07:17.340 --> 08:07:18.479
than he'd imagined.

08:07:18.540 --> 08:07:21.840
His queen was a controller of minds.

08:07:21.900 --> 08:07:25.020
The book of Clearsight was a lie.

08:07:25.080 --> 08:07:28.200
And his father was a prisoner in a flame

08:07:28.200 --> 08:07:29.159
silk factory.

08:07:29.220 --> 08:07:33.180
And Blue was in love with a hive wing.

08:07:33.240 --> 08:07:35.700
He'd made it through all of those

08:07:35.700 --> 08:07:37.020
discoveries.

08:07:37.080 --> 08:07:38.220
He was stronger now.

08:07:38.279 --> 08:07:40.560
He saw things more clearly.

08:07:40.619 --> 08:07:42.959
Like Clearsight had written.

08:07:43.020 --> 08:07:45.840
He had to keep going, and decide for

08:07:45.840 --> 08:07:48.000
himself what kind of dragon he wanted to

08:07:48.000 --> 08:07:48.540
be.

08:07:48.599 --> 08:07:50.939
After everything he'd been through.

08:07:51.060 --> 08:07:53.459
He knew he could handle a little thing

08:07:53.459 --> 08:07:54.479
like growing wings.

08:07:54.540 --> 08:07:57.419
The gold fire wrapped around him.

08:07:57.479 --> 08:08:01.080
Blue closed his eyes. let the change

08:08:01.080 --> 08:08:01.680
begin.

08:08:01.740 --> 08:08:06.240
Epilogue.

08:08:06.299 --> 08:08:09.060
Luna opened her eyes.

08:08:09.119 --> 08:08:12.540
A seagull skittered away from her, calling

08:08:12.540 --> 08:08:14.759
indignantly about dragons who pretended

08:08:14.759 --> 08:08:16.139
to be food and then weren't.

08:08:16.200 --> 08:08:19.020
She was lying in wet sand.

08:08:19.319 --> 08:08:22.319
Wet sand was clumped between her talons

08:08:22.319 --> 08:08:24.900
and in her ears, and in the cracks

08:08:24.900 --> 08:08:25.799
between her scales.

08:08:25.860 --> 08:08:28.319
Her face was half buried in it.

08:08:28.380 --> 08:08:31.439
She was pretty much plastered with wet

08:08:31.439 --> 08:08:33.119
sand from horns to tail.

08:08:33.240 --> 08:08:36.240
A wave rushed up from behind her

08:08:36.240 --> 08:08:39.180
swooshing under her back talons and tail

08:08:39.180 --> 08:08:42.060
soaking her underbelly, and whisking away

08:08:42.060 --> 08:08:42.360
again.

08:08:42.479 --> 08:08:45.479
Luna pushed herself up to a sitting

08:08:45.479 --> 08:08:47.159
position with a groan of pain.

08:08:47.220 --> 08:08:50.279
She fanned out her wings to check them.

08:08:50.340 --> 08:08:52.560
One was badly bruised.

08:08:52.619 --> 08:08:55.439
She had a vague memory of being hit by a

08:08:55.439 --> 08:08:56.099
hailstone.

08:08:56.159 --> 08:08:59.400
And one of her back ankles twinged

08:08:59.400 --> 08:09:01.500
horribly when she tried to stand on it.

08:09:01.560 --> 08:09:04.979
She dragged herself up the beach, away

08:09:04.979 --> 08:09:06.240
from the bustling waves.

08:09:06.299 --> 08:09:09.479
Ow, everything ached.

08:09:09.599 --> 08:09:12.419
She squinted up at the aggressively

08:09:12.419 --> 08:09:13.200
cheerful sun.

08:09:13.259 --> 08:09:16.439
How far had she been blown from blue and

08:09:16.439 --> 08:09:17.159
sword tail?

08:09:17.220 --> 08:09:19.799
This beach didn't look like the one where

08:09:19.799 --> 08:09:20.880
she'd started out.

08:09:20.939 --> 08:09:23.279
Instead of tall cliffs.

08:09:23.340 --> 08:09:26.279
The sand here rolled up into low hills

08:09:26.279 --> 08:09:28.380
with patches of shrubs.

08:09:28.439 --> 08:09:30.959
Luna could see quite far up and down the

08:09:30.959 --> 08:09:33.599
coast and inland, but she couldn't see

08:09:33.599 --> 08:09:36.060
any sign of caves, or hives.

08:09:36.119 --> 08:09:39.119
She rubbed her head, trying to remember

08:09:39.119 --> 08:09:40.439
the map of Pantala.

08:09:40.500 --> 08:09:43.979
She'd been in the air for days, tangled

08:09:43.979 --> 08:09:46.020
in her silk balloon as the storm swept

08:09:46.020 --> 08:09:46.560
her along.

08:09:46.619 --> 08:09:49.740
She remembered nothing but white capped

08:09:49.740 --> 08:09:50.580
waves below her.

08:09:50.639 --> 08:09:52.380
Could she?

08:09:52.439 --> 08:09:54.000
She couldn't be.

08:09:54.119 --> 08:09:55.619
Surely.

08:09:55.680 --> 08:09:59.459
Talons landed on the sand slightly uphill

08:09:59.459 --> 08:09:59.700
from her.

08:09:59.819 --> 08:10:03.479
Luna started back, lifting one wrist to

08:10:03.479 --> 08:10:05.639
shoot fire if her wing was a hive wing.

08:10:05.700 --> 08:10:07.619
But it wasn't.

08:10:07.680 --> 08:10:11.400
This dragon was pale yellow, with light

08:10:11.400 --> 08:10:14.459
brown triangle markings on her wings, only

08:10:14.459 --> 08:10:17.759
2 wings, just one pair, like a leaf wing

08:10:17.759 --> 08:10:20.520
but with her coloring, she definitely

08:10:20.520 --> 08:10:22.139
wasn't a leaf wing.

08:10:22.259 --> 08:10:24.599
And her wings weren't leaf shaped

08:10:24.599 --> 08:10:24.840
either.

08:10:24.900 --> 08:10:28.259
They looked closer to bat wings, but

08:10:28.259 --> 08:10:30.060
covered in scales instead of fur.

08:10:30.119 --> 08:10:32.700
The dragon took a step toward her.

08:10:32.759 --> 08:10:35.759
And Luna realized there was something odd

08:10:35.759 --> 08:10:36.659
at the end of her tail.

08:10:36.779 --> 08:10:40.319
A barb, like she'd only ever seen before

08:10:40.319 --> 08:10:41.580
on scorpions.

08:10:41.639 --> 08:10:43.380
What are you?

08:10:43.500 --> 08:10:45.479
Luna said fiercely.

08:10:45.540 --> 08:10:49.560
Oh, you speak dragon said the stranger.

08:10:49.680 --> 08:10:50.880
That's lucky.

08:10:51.000 --> 08:10:53.580
What else would I speak?

08:10:53.700 --> 08:10:54.779
Luna asked.

08:10:54.840 --> 08:10:55.740
Who are you?

08:10:55.799 --> 08:10:56.819
Where am I?

08:10:56.880 --> 08:11:00.119
I guess I thought your continent might

08:11:00.119 --> 08:11:01.080
have a different language.

08:11:01.200 --> 08:11:03.599
The yellow dragon said with a shrug.

08:11:03.659 --> 08:11:05.400
I'm Jerboa.

08:11:05.459 --> 08:11:08.819
My Continent?

08:11:08.880 --> 08:11:10.139
Luna echoed.

08:11:10.200 --> 08:11:11.939
She lowered her arm.

08:11:12.060 --> 08:11:13.500
Do you mean?

08:11:14.279 --> 08:11:16.259
Did I really cross the ocean?

08:11:16.319 --> 08:11:18.299
It looks that way?

08:11:18.360 --> 08:11:22.200
Treboa said wryly, but not entirely

08:11:22.200 --> 08:11:23.580
unscathed, I think.

08:11:23.639 --> 08:11:24.659
Are you injured?

08:11:24.720 --> 08:11:27.419
Just a little.

08:11:27.479 --> 08:11:30.299
Luna tried to take a step and winced.

08:11:30.360 --> 08:11:33.659
Yar, that's ow.

08:11:33.720 --> 08:11:35.279
My name's Luna.

08:11:35.340 --> 08:11:38.459
My hut is just around that bend.

08:11:38.520 --> 08:11:41.880
Truboa said, coming over and levering her

08:11:41.880 --> 08:11:43.139
wing under Luna's.

08:11:43.200 --> 08:11:44.159
Hang on.

08:11:44.220 --> 08:11:45.419
We'll be there in no time.

08:11:45.540 --> 08:11:48.479
They started across the sand.

08:11:48.540 --> 08:11:51.180
Luna found it much more difficult to walk

08:11:51.180 --> 08:11:52.319
in than Jaboa did.

08:11:52.439 --> 08:11:55.319
Her wing kept sagging unexpectedly under

08:11:55.319 --> 08:11:58.319
her claws, or sucking around her talons.

08:11:58.380 --> 08:12:01.680
I have to get back, Luna said.

08:12:01.740 --> 08:12:03.299
My friends are over there.

08:12:03.360 --> 08:12:06.180
They need me, especially my little

08:12:06.180 --> 08:12:06.419
brother.

08:12:06.479 --> 08:12:09.659
She tried to guess how long she'd been up

08:12:09.659 --> 08:12:10.139
in the storm.

08:12:10.200 --> 08:12:13.319
She was starving, but that wasn't much of

08:12:13.319 --> 08:12:13.680
a clue.

08:12:13.799 --> 08:12:16.799
Blue must have started his metamorphosis

08:12:16.799 --> 08:12:17.340
by now.

08:12:17.400 --> 08:12:19.380
Was he still in his cocoon?

08:12:19.439 --> 08:12:20.819
Was he all right?

08:12:20.880 --> 08:12:24.240
Well, you're not going far on these wings

08:12:24.240 --> 08:12:24.599
today?

08:12:24.659 --> 08:12:26.099
Traboa said.

08:12:26.159 --> 08:12:27.479
But help is coming.

08:12:27.540 --> 08:12:29.759
I have a feeling it'll be here soon.

08:12:29.880 --> 08:12:33.599
Trabella's hut was tucked into a cove

08:12:33.599 --> 08:12:36.599
cozy and well built, with a recently

08:12:36.599 --> 08:12:38.819
thatched roof made of palm fronds.

08:12:38.939 --> 08:12:41.639
Luna touched the wood of the door on the

08:12:41.639 --> 08:12:42.180
way inside.

08:12:42.240 --> 08:12:46.020
It was a real wood, and she was startled

08:12:46.020 --> 08:12:48.299
to see it used for a house as small as

08:12:48.299 --> 08:12:48.479
this.

08:12:48.540 --> 08:12:51.599
Maybe Jerboa was wealthier and more

08:12:51.599 --> 08:12:52.740
powerful than she appeared.

08:12:52.799 --> 08:12:56.580
Or maybe it's different over here, she

08:12:56.580 --> 08:12:57.119
realized.

08:12:57.180 --> 08:12:59.580
Maybe there are still plenty of trees on

08:12:59.580 --> 08:13:00.000
this continent.

08:13:00.060 --> 08:13:03.840
Jerboa helped her over to a bed made of

08:13:03.840 --> 08:13:06.360
more palm leaves, and Luna collapsed onto

08:13:06.360 --> 08:13:09.299
it, surprised by how exhausted she was.

08:13:09.360 --> 08:13:12.299
She was sure she'd slept on the beach for

08:13:12.299 --> 08:13:15.299
a while after a crash landing, but the

08:13:15.299 --> 08:13:16.979
walk to the hut had tired her out again.

08:13:17.099 --> 08:13:21.840
Sleep for a bit, Treboa said, I'll make

08:13:21.840 --> 08:13:22.740
fish stew.

08:13:22.860 --> 08:13:24.959
Luna wrinkled her snout.

08:13:25.080 --> 08:13:28.259
Um, she said, that's all right.

08:13:28.319 --> 08:13:29.880
Do you have any fruit?

08:13:29.939 --> 08:13:31.080
Or honey?

08:13:31.139 --> 08:13:32.700
She added, hopefully.

08:13:32.759 --> 08:13:35.340
Jerboa flicked her wings back with a

08:13:35.340 --> 08:13:36.119
thoughtful expression.

08:13:36.180 --> 08:13:39.360
Not a fish eater, she said.

08:13:39.419 --> 08:13:42.659
What about crabs, or rabbits, or

08:13:42.659 --> 08:13:43.439
seagulls?

08:13:43.560 --> 08:13:45.479
Luna shook her head.

08:13:45.479 --> 08:13:48.959
No animals, thank you, she said politely

08:13:49.020 --> 08:13:52.139
and her stomach growled as if disagreeing

08:13:52.139 --> 08:13:52.439
with her.

08:13:52.500 --> 08:13:54.540
I'll see what I have.

08:13:54.659 --> 08:13:57.720
Drabola glided off to another corner of

08:13:57.720 --> 08:14:00.299
the hut, and Luna felt herself slipping

08:14:00.299 --> 08:14:01.200
into a doze.

08:14:01.259 --> 08:14:02.759
Sometime later.

08:14:02.819 --> 08:14:04.619
Treboa shook her awake.

08:14:04.680 --> 08:14:06.900
Talon, gentle on her shoulder.

08:14:06.959 --> 08:14:10.500
Luna, our guests are here.

08:14:10.560 --> 08:14:12.959
Luna blinked awake.

08:14:13.020 --> 08:14:16.380
The light had shifted outside, and there

08:14:16.380 --> 08:14:17.580
were quiet voices coming through the

08:14:17.580 --> 08:14:17.880
window.

08:14:17.939 --> 08:14:21.419
I'll go get them, Traboa said.

08:14:21.479 --> 08:14:22.619
Don't be alarmed.

08:14:22.680 --> 08:14:24.720
This is who you need to talk to.

08:14:24.779 --> 08:14:27.180
She went out the door.

08:14:27.240 --> 08:14:30.540
Luna tried to think, although her brain

08:14:30.540 --> 08:14:33.060
felt overwhelmed and still muddled with

08:14:33.060 --> 08:14:33.299
sleep.

08:14:33.360 --> 08:14:34.979
Who was here?

08:14:35.040 --> 08:14:36.479
How could they help her?

08:14:36.540 --> 08:14:38.279
To who?

08:14:38.340 --> 08:14:41.459
Said a new voice, which was attached to a

08:14:41.459 --> 08:14:43.259
dragon ducking through the doorway.

08:14:43.319 --> 08:14:46.380
He was smaller than Jerboa, closer to

08:14:46.380 --> 08:14:48.659
Luna's size, but with the same kind of

08:14:48.659 --> 08:14:50.819
wings and tail as Jerboa.

08:14:50.939 --> 08:14:53.759
His scales were sand colored like hers as

08:14:53.759 --> 08:14:55.860
well, and he wore a hoop earring in one

08:14:55.860 --> 08:14:56.099
ear.

08:14:56.159 --> 08:14:59.099
But following him through the doorway was

08:14:59.099 --> 08:15:00.360
another dragon entirely.

08:15:00.419 --> 08:15:04.139
She was black from nose to talons, except

08:15:04.139 --> 08:15:06.419
for a few silver scales scattered under

08:15:06.419 --> 08:15:09.419
her wings, and 2 teardrop silver scales

08:15:09.419 --> 08:15:10.560
in the corners of her eyes.

08:15:10.680 --> 08:15:13.860
A startled jolt ran through Luna.

08:15:13.919 --> 08:15:16.020
Waking her up like a bolt of lightning.

08:15:16.080 --> 08:15:20.880
This dragon looked like clear sight, or

08:15:20.880 --> 08:15:23.159
at least, the way Clearside always looked

08:15:23.159 --> 08:15:23.880
in pictures.

08:15:23.880 --> 08:15:27.299
Luna sat up as the 2 of them came closer

08:15:27.299 --> 08:15:29.340
with Jerboa behind them.

08:15:29.400 --> 08:15:33.599
Oh, wow, said the one with the earring

08:15:33.599 --> 08:15:34.560
noticing Luna.

08:15:34.680 --> 08:15:35.939
What?

08:15:36.000 --> 08:15:38.459
Said the clear sight looking dragon.

08:15:38.520 --> 08:15:39.599
How?

08:15:39.659 --> 08:15:43.080
I believe this is our 1st visitor from

08:15:43.080 --> 08:15:45.419
the lost continent, Jaboa said.

08:15:45.479 --> 08:15:47.220
She blew in with a storm.

08:15:47.340 --> 08:15:50.639
The little black dragon sat down and

08:15:50.639 --> 08:15:52.680
tipped her head, as though she was

08:15:52.680 --> 08:15:53.880
listening to something far away.

08:15:53.939 --> 08:15:58.259
I'm Moon, she said, and this is Kibley.

08:15:58.380 --> 08:16:00.419
Are you really from across the sea?

08:16:00.479 --> 08:16:02.400
I guess so.

08:16:02.520 --> 08:16:03.900
Luna said.

08:16:03.959 --> 08:16:06.299
It was kind of an accident coming here.

08:16:06.360 --> 08:16:08.040
I'm Luna.

08:16:08.099 --> 08:16:10.919
Hi Luna, said Kibley.

08:16:10.979 --> 08:16:12.779
This must be pretty weird for you too.

08:16:12.840 --> 08:16:15.180
You have so many wings.

08:16:15.240 --> 08:16:16.619
I mean, that's cool.

08:16:16.680 --> 08:16:19.259
Is it hard to fly with all those wings?

08:16:19.319 --> 08:16:20.700
That's a silly question.

08:16:20.759 --> 08:16:23.220
I can't believe we're meeting a dragon

08:16:23.220 --> 08:16:24.119
from another continent.

08:16:24.180 --> 08:16:25.619
This is amazing.

08:16:25.680 --> 08:16:29.819
Are you, like, clear sight?

08:16:29.880 --> 08:16:31.619
Luna asked Moon.

08:16:31.680 --> 08:16:33.360
Can you see the future?

08:16:33.419 --> 08:16:35.880
Moon's eyebrows shot up.

08:16:35.939 --> 08:16:39.180
You know about clear sight?

08:16:39.299 --> 08:16:43.560
I know some things about her, Luna said.

08:16:43.680 --> 08:16:46.860
Thinking darkly of the book, and the lies

08:16:46.860 --> 08:16:48.299
Queen Wasp had told about it.

08:16:48.419 --> 08:16:52.319
I know she came from here, and she had

08:16:52.319 --> 08:16:53.639
scales like yours.

08:16:53.880 --> 08:16:55.740
I always wondered if there were other

08:16:55.740 --> 08:16:57.659
dragons over here who could see the

08:16:57.659 --> 08:16:58.080
future too.

08:16:58.139 --> 08:17:01.319
I can, sort of.

08:17:01.380 --> 08:17:02.520
Moon said.

08:17:02.580 --> 08:17:04.380
Not as well as she could.

08:17:04.439 --> 08:17:06.419
But I had a vision about you.

08:17:06.479 --> 08:17:08.340
That's why we're here.

08:17:08.400 --> 08:17:10.799
Was it about getting me home?

08:17:10.860 --> 08:17:14.279
Luna asked, sitting forward and flaring

08:17:14.279 --> 08:17:14.759
her wings.

08:17:14.819 --> 08:17:16.979
Do you know how I can get back there?

08:17:17.040 --> 08:17:20.099
Moon shot Khibli an uneasy look?

08:17:20.220 --> 08:17:23.099
Not exactly, she said.

08:17:23.159 --> 08:17:25.139
Although we can work on it.

08:17:25.200 --> 08:17:27.060
I have some ideas.

08:17:27.180 --> 08:17:28.860
Kibley said brightly.

08:17:28.919 --> 08:17:31.979
Good, Luna said.

08:17:32.040 --> 08:17:34.740
She settled back into the palm fronds.

08:17:34.799 --> 08:17:37.319
She was suddenly sure that storm had

08:17:37.319 --> 08:17:38.340
brought her here for a reason.

08:17:38.459 --> 08:17:42.479
Let's figure out how to get me home, and

08:17:42.479 --> 08:17:43.680
you can all come with me.

08:17:43.740 --> 08:17:46.200
Especially you, Vision Dragon.

08:17:46.259 --> 08:17:48.180
Me?

08:17:48.299 --> 08:17:49.200
Moon said.

08:17:49.259 --> 08:17:51.360
Oh, I don't know.

08:17:51.479 --> 08:17:54.240
I haven't seen anything about, you have

08:17:54.240 --> 08:17:55.680
to, Luna said.

08:17:55.740 --> 08:17:58.740
This dragon could be the secret weapon

08:17:58.740 --> 08:18:00.779
the silk wings and leaf wings needed.

08:18:00.900 --> 08:18:03.479
My tribe needs your help.

08:18:03.540 --> 08:18:06.959
Triumph sizzled through her veins.

08:18:07.020 --> 08:18:10.259
We are coming for you, Queen Wasp.

08:18:10.319 --> 08:18:13.020
And now we have a dragon who can really

08:18:13.020 --> 08:18:14.159
see the future.

08:18:14.159 --> 08:18:17.939
The reign of the hive wings is over.

08:18:18.000 --> 08:18:25.200
A guide to the dragons of Pentala.

08:18:25.259 --> 08:18:27.659
Hive wings.

08:18:27.720 --> 08:18:29.099
Description.

08:18:29.159 --> 08:18:33.720
Red, yellow, and or orange, but always

08:18:33.720 --> 08:18:36.360
mixed with some black scales, 4 wings.

08:18:36.479 --> 08:18:40.259
Abilities vary from dragon to dragon.

08:18:40.319 --> 08:18:43.500
Examples include deadly stingers that can

08:18:43.500 --> 08:18:45.720
extend from their wrists to stab their

08:18:45.720 --> 08:18:46.200
enemies.

08:18:46.259 --> 08:18:49.860
Venom in their teeth or claws, a

08:18:49.860 --> 08:18:52.259
paralyzing toxin that can immobilize

08:18:52.259 --> 08:18:52.979
their prey.

08:18:53.040 --> 08:18:57.119
Or boiling acid, sprayed from a stinger

08:18:57.119 --> 08:18:57.779
on their tails.

08:18:57.840 --> 08:19:01.139
Queen, Queen Wasp.

08:19:01.259 --> 08:19:05.159
Silk wings, description.

08:19:05.220 --> 08:19:08.459
Silkwing dragonettes are born wingless

08:19:08.459 --> 08:19:11.279
but go through a metamorphosis at age 6.

08:19:11.340 --> 08:19:14.700
When they develop 4 huge wings and silk

08:19:14.700 --> 08:19:17.279
spinning abilities, as beautiful and

08:19:17.279 --> 08:19:20.459
gentle as butterflies, with scales in any

08:19:20.459 --> 08:19:23.340
color under the sun, except black.

08:19:23.639 --> 08:19:27.659
Abilities, can spin silk from glands on

08:19:27.659 --> 08:19:30.000
their wrists to create webs or other

08:19:30.000 --> 08:19:33.000
woven articles, can detect vibrations

08:19:33.000 --> 08:19:35.159
with their antennae to assess threats.

08:19:35.220 --> 08:19:40.439
Queen, Queen Wasp, the last Silkwing

08:19:40.439 --> 08:19:43.439
Queen, before the tree wars, was Queen

08:19:43.439 --> 08:19:44.099
Monarch.

08:19:44.159 --> 08:19:46.740
Leaf Wings.

08:19:46.860 --> 08:19:50.099
Description, wiped out during the tree

08:19:50.099 --> 08:19:52.740
wars with the hive wings, but while they

08:19:52.740 --> 08:19:54.900
lived, this tribe had green and brown

08:19:54.900 --> 08:19:58.139
scales, and wings shaped like leaves

08:19:58.139 --> 08:20:01.319
abilities, could absorb energy from

08:20:01.319 --> 08:20:03.180
sunlight, and were accomplished

08:20:03.180 --> 08:20:03.720
gardeners.

08:20:03.779 --> 08:20:07.259
Some were rumored to have unusual control

08:20:07.259 --> 08:20:08.220
over plants.

08:20:08.340 --> 08:20:10.259
Queen.

08:20:10.319 --> 08:20:13.319
Last known queen of the leaf wings was

08:20:13.319 --> 08:20:16.919
Queen Sequoia, about 100 years ago, at

08:20:16.919 --> 08:20:18.299
the time of the tree wars.

